VALUES
  (15180, 19, 78, 58, 'For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.', '5~03707~ 9~01116~, 14~07065~ 18~06456~.'),
  (4248, 4, 16, 49, 'Now they that died in the plague were fourteen thousand and seven hundred, beside them that died about the matter of Korah.', '3~04191~ 6~04046~ 8~06240~ 9~0702~* 10~0505~ 12~07651~ 13~03967~, 17~04191~ 20~01697~ 22~07141~.'),
  (17679, 23, 1, 16, 'Wash you, make you clean; put away the evil of your doings from before mine eyes; cease to do evil;', '&para; 0~07364~ 4~02135~; 6~05493~ 8~07455~ 11~04611~ 13~05048~ 15~05869~; 16~02308~ 19~07489~;'),
  (21688, 26, 46, 24, 'Then said he unto me, These are the places of them that boil, where the ministers of the house shall boil the sacrifice of the people.', '1~0559~ [6] 8~01004~ 12~01310~, 15~08334~ 18~01004~ 20~01310~ 22~02077~ 25~05971~.'),
  (19428, 24, 19, 12, 'Thus will I do unto this place, saith the LORD, and to the inhabitants thereof, and even make this city as Tophet:', '3~06213~ 6~04725~, 7~05002~ 9~03068~, 13~03427~ [16] 17~05414~ 19~05892~ 21~08612~:'),
  (4552, 4, 26, 57, 'And these are they that were numbered of the Levites after their families: of Gershon, the family of the Gershonites: of Kohath, the family of the Kohathites: of Merari, the family of the Merarites.', '&para; [2] 6~06485~ 9~03881~ 12~04940~: 14~01648~, 16~04940~ 19~01649~: 21~06955~, 23~04940~ 26~06956~: 28~04847~, 30~04940~ 33~04848~.'),
  (129, 1, 5, 23, 'And all the days of Enoch were three hundred sixty and five years:', '3~03117~ 5~02585~ 7~07969~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~* 10~08346~ 12~02568~ 13~08141~:'),
  (10910, 13, 18, 12, 'Moreover Abishai the son of Zeruiah slew of the Edomites in the valley of salt eighteen thousand.', '1~052~ 3~01121~ 5~06870~ 6~05221~ 9~0123~ 12~01516~ 14~04417~ 15~06240~ 16~08083~* 17~0505~.'),
  (26201, 43, 4, 30, 'Then they went out of the city, and came unto him.', '0~3767~ 2~1831~ 4~1537~ 6~4172~, 7~2532~ 8~2064~ 9~4314~ 10~846~.'),
  (19280, 24, 13, 5, 'So I went, and hid it by Euphrates, as the LORD commanded me.', '2~03212~, 4~02934~ 7~06578~, 10~03068~ 11~06680~'),
  (4031, 4, 11, 2, 'And the people cried unto Moses; and when Moses prayed unto the LORD, the fire was quenched.', '2~05971~ 3~06817~ 5~04872~; 8~04872~ 9~06419~ 12~03068~, 14~0784~ 16~08257~.'),
  (20146, 24, 49, 10, 'But I have made Esau bare, I have uncovered his secret places, and he shall not be able to hide himself: his seed is spoiled, and his brethren, and his neighbours, and he is not.', '4~06215~ 5~02834~, 8~01540~ 11~04565~, 17~03201~ 19~02247~ 22~02233~ 24~07703~, 27~0251~, 30~07934~, [33]'),
  (350, 1, 14, 10, 'And the vale of Siddim was full of slimepits; and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, and fell there; and they that remained fled to the mountain.', '2~06010~ 4~07708~ [5 7] 7~0875~ 8~02564~ 9~0875~;* 12~04428~ 14~05467~ 16~06017~ 17~05127~, 19~05307~ 24~07604~ 25~05127~ 28~02022~.'),
  (23958, 40, 23, 30, 'And say, If we had been in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets.', '0~2532~ 1~3004~, 2~1487~ 5~2258~ 6~1722~ 8~2250~ 10~2257~ 11~3962~, 13~302~ 14~3756~ 16~2258~ 17~2844~ 19~846~ 20~1722~ 22~129~ 25~4396~.'),
  (30799, 66, 5, 4, 'And I wept much, because no man was found worthy to open and to read the book, neither to look thereon.', '0~2532~ 1~1473~ 2~2799~ 3~4183~, 4~3754~ 6~3762~ 8~2147~ 9~514~ 11~455~ 12~2532~ 14~314~ 16~975~, 17~3777~ 19~991~ 20~846~.'),
  (14348, 19, 31, 8, 'And hast not shut me up into the hand of the enemy: thou hast set my feet in a large room.', '5~05462~ 8~03027~ 11~0341~: 14~05975~ 16~07272~ 20~04800~.'),
  (12217, 15, 8, 7, 'And of the sons of Elam; Jeshaiah the son of Athaliah, and with him seventy males.', '3~01121~ 5~05867~; 6~03470~ 8~01121~ 10~06271~, 14~07657~ 15~02145~.'),
  (17625, 22, 6, 2, 'My beloved is gone down into his garden, to the beds of spices, to feed in the gardens, and to gather lilies.', '1~01730~ 4~03381~ 7~01588~, 10~06170~ 12~01314~, 14~07462~ 17~01588~, 20~03950~ 21~07799~.'),
  (27643, 44, 20, 1, 'And after the uproar was ceased, Paul called unto him the disciples, and embraced them, and departed for to go into Macedonia.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3326~ 3~2351~ 5~3973~, 6~3972~ 7~4341~ [9] 11~3101~, 12~2532~ 13~782~ [14] 16~1831~ 19~4198~ 20~1519~ 21~3109~.'),
  (29844, 55, 2, 1, 'Thou therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.', '&para; 0~4771~ 1~3767~, 2~3450~ 3~5043~, 5~1743~ 6~1722~ 8~5485~ 11~1722~ 12~5547~ 13~2424~.'),
  (14265, 19, 25, 5, 'Lead me in thy truth, and teach me: for thou art the God of my salvation; on thee do I wait all the day.', '0~01869~ 4~0571~, 6~03925~ [10] 12~0430~ 15~03468~; 20~06960~ 23~03117~.'),
  (23529, 40, 12, 30, 'He that is not with me is against me; and he that gathereth not with me scattereth abroad.', '2~5607~ 3~3361~ 4~3326~ 5~1700~ 6~2076~ 7~2596~ 8~1700~; 9~2532~ 12~4863~ 13~3361~ 14~3326~ 15~1700~ 17~4650~.'),
  (8498, 10, 18, 12, 'And the man said unto Joab, Though I should receive a thousand shekels of silver in mine hand, yet would I not put forth mine hand against the king''s son: for in our hearing the king charged thee and Abishai and Ittai, saying, Beware that none touch the young man Absalom.', '2~0376~ 3~0559~ 5~03097~, 6~03863~ 9~08254~ 11~0505~ [12] 14~03701~ 17~03709~, [18] 23~07971~ 25~03027~ 28~04428~ 29~01121~: 33~0241~ 35~04428~ 36~06680~ 39~052~ 41~0863~, 42~0559~, 43~08104~ [46] 49~05288~ 50~053~.'),
  (25637, 42, 16, 4, 'I am resolved what to do, that, when I am put out of the stewardship, they may receive me into their houses.', '2~1097~ 3~5101~ 5~4160~, 6~2443~, 7~3752~ 11~3179~ 14~3622~, 17~1209~ 18~3165~ 19~1519~ 20~846~ 21~3624~.'),
  (21056, 26, 23, 40, 'And furthermore, that ye have sent for men to come from far, unto whom a messenger was sent; and, lo, they came: for whom thou didst wash thyself, paintedst thy eyes, and deckedst thyself with ornaments,', '1~0637~, 5~07971~ 7~0582~ 9~0935~ 11~04801~, 15~04397~ [16] 17~07971~; 21~0935~: 26~07364~ 28~03583~ 30~05869~, 32~05710~ 35~05716~,'),
  (29732, 54, 1, 20, 'Of whom is Hymenaeus and Alexander; whom I have delivered unto Satan, that they may learn not to blaspheme.', '1~3739~ 2~2076~ 3~5211~ 4~2532~ 5~223~; 6~3739~ 9~3860~ 11~4567~, 12~2443~ 15~3811~ 16~3361~ 18~987~.'),
  (11429, 14, 11, 6, 'He built even Bethlehem, and Etam, and Tekoa,', '1~01129~ 3~01035~, 5~05862~, 7~08620~,'),
  (28712, 46, 14, 18, 'I thank my God, I speak with tongues more than ye all:', '1~2168~ 2~3450~ 3~2316~, 5~2980~ 7~1100~ 9~3123~ 10~5216~ 11~3956~:'),
  (12666, 16, 12, 33, 'And Azariah, Ezra, and Meshullam,', '1~05838~, 2~05830~, 4~04918~,'),
  (14662, 19, 49, 5, 'Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?', '3~03372~ 6~03117~ 8~07451~, [9] 11~05771~ 14~06120~ 16~05437~'),
  (18800, 23, 58, 5, 'Is it such a fast that I have chosen? a day for a man to afflict his soul? is it to bow down his head as a bulrush, and to spread sackcloth and ashes under him? wilt thou call this a fast, and an acceptable day to the LORD?', '4~06685~ 8~0977~? 10~03117~ 13~0120~ 15~06031~ 17~05315~? [18 19] 22~03721~ 24~07218~ 27~0100~, 30~03331~ 31~08242~ 33~0665~ [34 35] 38~07121~ 39~02088~ 41~06685~, 44~07522~ 45~03117~ 48~03068~?'),
  (23196, 40, 2, 17, 'Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet, saying,', '0~5119~ 2~4137~ 4~3588~ 6~4483~ 7~5259~ 8~2408~ 10~4396~, 11~3004~,'),
  (19953, 24, 40, 3, 'Now the LORD hath brought it, and done according as he hath said: because ye have sinned against the LORD, and have not obeyed his voice, therefore this thing is come upon you.', '2~03068~ 4~0935~ [5] 7~06213~ 12~01696~: 16~02398~ 19~03068~, 23~08085~ 25~06963~, 28~01697~'),
  (3867, 4, 7, 12, 'And he that offered his offering the first day was Nahshon the son of Amminadab, of the tribe of Judah:', '3~07126~ 5~07133~ 7~07223~ 8~03117~ 10~05177~ 12~01121~ 14~05992~, 17~04294~ 19~03063~:'),
  (28202, 45, 9, 31, 'But Israel, which followed after the law of righteousness, hath not attained to the law of righteousness.', '0~1161~ 1~2474~, 3~1377~ 6~3551~ 8~1343~, 9~5348~ 10~3756~ 11~5348~ 12~1519~ 14~3551~ 16~1343~.'),
  (13989, 19, 5, 7, 'But as for me, I will come into thy house in the multitude of thy mercy: and in thy fear will I worship toward thy holy temple.', '&para; 6~0935~ [7] 9~01004~ 12~07230~ 15~02617~: [16] 19~03374~ 22~07812~ 25~06944~ 26~01964~.'),
  (21906, 27, 5, 23, 'But hast lifted up thyself against the Lord of heaven; and they have brought the vessels of his house before thee, and thou, and thy lords, thy wives, and thy concubines, have drunk wine in them; and thou hast praised the gods of silver, and gold, of brass, iron, wood, and stone, which see not, nor hear, nor know: and the God in whose hand thy breath is, and whose are all thy ways, hast thou not glorified:', '3~07313~ 5~05922~ 7~04756~ 9~08065~; 13~0858~ 15~03984~ 18~01005~ 19~06925~ 22~0607~, 25~07261~, 27~07695~, 30~03904~, 32~08355~ 33~02562~ 39~07624~ 41~0426~ 43~03702~, 45~01722~, 47~05174~, 48~06523~, 49~0636~, 51~069~, 53~02370~ 54~03809~, 55~03809~ 56~08086~, 57~03809~ 58~03046~: 61~0426~ 64~03028~ 66~05396~ [67] [70] 71~03606~ 73~0735~, 76~03809~ 77~01922~:'),
  (476, 1, 19, 15, 'And when the morning arose, then the angels hastened Lot, saying, Arise, take thy wife, and thy two daughters, which are here; lest thou be consumed in the iniquity of the city.', '&para; 1~03644~ 3~07837~ 4~05927~, 7~04397~ 8~0213~ 9~03876~, 10~0559~, 11~06965~, 12~03947~ 14~0802~, 17~08147~ 18~01323~, 21~04672~; 25~05595~ 28~05771~ 31~05892~.'),
  (30753, 66, 2, 20, 'Notwithstanding I have a few things against thee, because thou sufferest that woman Jezebel, which calleth herself a prophetess, to teach and to seduce my servants to commit fornication, and to eat things sacrificed unto idols.', '0~235~ 2~2192~ 5~3641~ 6~2596~ 7~4675~, 8~3754~ 10~1439~ 12~1135~ 13~2403~, 14~3588~ 15~3004~ 16~1438~ 18~4398~, 20~1321~ 21~2532~ 23~4105~ 24~1699~ 25~1401~ 28~4203~, 29~2532~ 31~5315~ 35~1494~.'),
  (25356, 42, 9, 43, 'And they were all amazed at the mighty power of God. But while they wondered every one at all things which Jesus did, he said unto his disciples,', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~1605~ 3~3956~ 4~1605~ 5~1909~ 8~3168~ 10~2316~. 11~1161~ 14~2296~ 16~3956~ 17~1909~ 19~3956~ 20~3739~ 21~2424~ 22~4160~, 24~2036~ 25~4314~ 26~846~ 27~3101~,'),
  (16167, 19, 132, 7, 'We will go into his tabernacles: we will worship at his footstool.', '2~0935~ 5~04908~: 8~07812~ 11~07272~ 12~01916~.*'),
  (24140, 40, 27, 1, 'When the morning was come, all the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against Jesus to put him to death:', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4405~ 4~1096~, 5~3956~ 8~749~ 9~2532~ 10~4245~ 13~2992~ 14~2983~ 15~4824~ 16~2596~ 17~2424~ 18~5620~ 19~2289~ 20~846~ 22~2289~:'),
  (11212, 14, 1, 10, 'Give me now wisdom and knowledge, that I may go out and come in before this people: for who can judge this thy people, that is so great?', '0~05414~ 3~02451~ 5~04093~, 10~03318~ 13~0935~ 14~06440~ 16~05971~: 20~08199~ 23~05971~, [24 26] 27~01419~?'),
  (26982, 44, 2, 17, 'And it shall come to pass in the last days, saith God, I will pour out of my Spirit upon all flesh: and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, and your young men shall see visions, and your old men shall dream dreams:', '0~2532~ 5~2071~ 6~1722~ 8~2078~ 9~2250~, 10~3004~ 11~2316~, 15~1632~ 16~575~ 17~3450~ 18~4151~ 19~1909~ 20~3956~ 21~4561~: 22~2532~ 23~5216~ 24~5207~ 25~2532~ 26~5216~ 27~2364~ 29~4395~, 30~2532~ 31~5216~ 33~3495~ 35~3700~ 36~3706~, 37~2532~ 38~5216~ 40~4245~ 42~1798~ 43~1797~:'),
  (363, 1, 14, 23, 'That I will not take from a thread even to a shoelatchet, and that I will not take any thing that is thine, lest thou shouldest say, I have made Abram rich:', '3~0518~ [4] 7~02339~ 11~08288~ 12~05275~,* 17~0518~ 18~03947~ [22] 27~0559~, 30~06238~ 31~087~ 32~06238~:'),
  (28982, 47, 9, 10, 'Now he that ministereth seed to the sower both minister bread for your food, and multiply your seed sown, and increase the fruits of your righteousness;)', '0~1161~ 3~2023~ 4~4690~ 7~4687~ 8~2532~ 9~5524~ 10~740~ 11~1519~ [12] 13~1035~, 14~2532~ 15~4129~ 16~5216~ 18~4703~, 19~2532~ 20~837~ 22~1081~ 24~5216~ 25~1343~;)'),
  (20618, 26, 8, 5, 'Then said he unto me, Son of man, lift up thine eyes now the way toward the north. So I lifted up mine eyes the way toward the north, and behold northward at the gate of the altar this image of jealousy in the entry.', '1~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~, 9~05375~ 11~05869~ 14~01870~ 17~06828~. 21~05375~ 23~05869~ 25~01870~ 28~06828~, 31~06828~ 34~08179~ 37~04196~ 39~05566~ 41~07068~ 44~0872~.'),
  (21217, 26, 30, 4, 'And the sword shall come upon Egypt, and great pain shall be in Ethiopia, when the slain shall fall in Egypt, and they shall take away her multitude, and her foundations shall be broken down.', '2~02719~ 4~0935~ 6~04714~, 9~02479~ 13~03568~, 16~02491~ 18~05307~ 20~04714~, 25~03947~ 27~01995~, 30~03247~ 34~02040~.'),
  (8744, 11, 1, 19, 'And he hath slain oxen and fat cattle and sheep in abundance, and hath called all the sons of the king, and Abiathar the priest, and Joab the captain of the host: but Solomon thy servant hath he not called.', '3~02076~ 4~07794~ 7~04806~ 9~06629~ 11~07230~, 14~07121~ 17~01121~ 20~04428~, 22~054~ 24~03548~, 26~03097~ 28~08269~ 31~06635~: 33~08010~ 35~05650~ 39~07121~.'),
  (3700, 4, 3, 3, 'These are the names of the sons of Aaron, the priests which were anointed, whom he consecrated to minister in the priest''s office.', '[1] 3~08034~ 6~01121~ 8~0175~, 10~03548~ 13~04886~, 16~04390~ 17~03027~* 23~03547~.'),
  (11381, 14, 9, 9, 'And she gave the king an hundred and twenty talents of gold, and of spices great abundance, and precious stones: neither was there any such spice as the queen of Sheba gave king Solomon.', '2~05414~ 4~04428~ 6~03967~ 8~06242~ 9~03603~ 11~02091~, 14~01314~ 15~03966~ 16~07230~, 18~03368~ 19~068~: 25~01314~ 28~04436~ 30~07614~ 31~05414~ 32~04428~ 33~08010~.'),
  (6712, 7, 7, 11, 'And thou shalt hear what they say; and afterward shall thine hands be strengthened to go down unto the host. Then went he down with Phurah his servant unto the outside of the armed men that were in the host.', '3~08085~ 6~01696~; 8~0310~ 11~03027~ 13~02388~ 16~03381~ 19~04264~. 23~03381~ 25~06513~ 27~05288~ 30~07097~ 34~02571~ [36] 39~04264~.'),
  (20799, 26, 16, 28, 'Thou hast played the whore also with the Assyrians, because thou wast unsatiable; yea, thou hast played the harlot with them, and yet couldest not be satisfied.', '4~02181~ 8~0804~ 9~01121~,* 10~01115~ 13~07646~; 19~02181~ 27~07654~.'),
  (22844, 36, 3, 15, 'The LORD hath taken away thy judgments, he hath cast out thine enemy: the king of Israel, even the LORD, is in the midst of thee: thou shalt not see evil any more.', '1~03068~ 4~05493~ 6~04941~, 10~06437~ 12~0341~: 14~04428~ 16~03478~, [17] 19~03068~, [20] 23~07130~ 29~07200~ 30~07451~'),
  (20537, 26, 3, 26, 'And I will make thy tongue cleave to the roof of thy mouth, that thou shalt be dumb, and shalt not be to them a reprover: for they are a rebellious house.', '5~03956~ 6~01692~ 12~02441~, 17~0481~, 25~03198~ 26~0376~:* [29] 31~04805~ 32~01004~.'),
  (10240, 12, 25, 10, 'And all the army of the Chaldees, that were with the captain of the guard, brake down the walls of Jerusalem round about.', '3~02428~ 6~03778~, [8 9] 11~07227~ 14~02876~, 16~05422~ 18~02346~ 20~03389~ 22~05439~.'),
  (12798, 17, 5, 10, 'Nevertheless Haman refrained himself: and when he came home, he sent and called for his friends, and Zeresh his wife.', '1~02001~ 2~0662~ 7~0935~ 8~01004~, 10~07971~ 12~0935~ 15~0157~, 17~02238~ 19~0802~.'),
  (963, 1, 32, 31, 'And as he passed over Penuel the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon his thigh.', '4~05674~ 5~06439~ 7~08121~ 8~02224~ 13~06760~ 16~03409~.'),
  (156, 1, 6, 18, 'But with thee will I establish my covenant; and thou shalt come into the ark, thou, and thy sons, and thy wife, and thy sons'' wives with thee.', '5~06965~ 7~01285~; 11~0935~ 12~0413~ 14~08392~, 15~0859~, 18~01121~, 21~0802~, 24~01121~ 25~0802~'),
  (7849, 9, 24, 3, 'And he came to the sheepcotes by the way, where was a cave; and Saul went in to cover his feet: and David and his men remained in the sides of the cave.', '2~0935~ 5~06629~ 6~01448~ 8~01870~, [10] 12~04631~; 14~07586~ 16~0935~ 18~05526~ 20~07272~: 22~01732~ 25~0582~ 26~03427~ 29~03411~ 32~04631~.'),
  (24574, 41, 9, 25, 'When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him, Thou dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 5~3793~ 8~1998~, 10~2008~ 12~169~ 13~4151~, 14~3004~ 16~846~, [17] 18~216~ 19~2532~ 20~2974~ 21~4151~, 22~1473~ 23~2004~ 24~4671~, 25~1831~ 27~1537~ 28~846~, 29~2532~ 30~1525~ 32~3371~ 33~1519~ 34~846~.'),
  (8273, 10, 11, 7, 'And when Uriah was come unto him, David demanded of him how Joab did, and how the people did, and how the war prospered.', '2~0223~ 4~0935~ 7~01732~ 8~07592~ [9 10] 12~03097~ 13~07965~, 17~05971~ 18~07965~, 22~04421~ 23~07965~.'),
  (29633, 52, 4, 14, 'For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again, even so them also which sleep in Jesus will God bring with him.', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 3~4100~ 4~3754~ 5~2424~ 6~599~ 7~2532~ 9~450~, 11~3779~ 13~2532~ 15~2837~ 16~1223~ 17~2424~ 18~71~ 19~2316~ 20~71~ 21~4862~ 22~846~.'),
  (28930, 47, 6, 16, 'And what agreement hath the temple of God with idols? for ye are the temple of the living God; as God hath said, I will dwell in them, and walk in them; and I will be their God, and they shall be my people.', '0~1161~ 1~5101~ 2~4783~ 5~3485~ 7~2316~ 8~3326~ 9~1497~? 10~1063~ 11~5210~ 12~2075~ 14~3485~ 17~2198~ 18~2316~; 19~2531~ 20~2316~ 22~2036~ 23~3754~,* 26~1774~ 27~1722~ 28~846~, 29~2532~ 31~1704~ [32] 33~2532~ 36~2071~ 37~846~ 38~2316~, 39~2532~ 40~846~ 42~2071~ 43~3427~ 44~2992~.'),
  (17225, 20, 28, 20, 'A faithful man shall abound with blessings: but he that maketh haste to be rich shall not be innocent.', '&para; 1~0530~ 2~0376~ 4~07227~ 6~01293~: 11~0213~ 14~06238~ 18~05352~.'),
  (18388, 23, 37, 27, 'Therefore their inhabitants were of small power, they were dismayed and confounded: they were as the grass of the field, and as the green herb, as the grass on the housetops, and as corn blasted before it be grown up.', '2~03427~ [3] 5~07116~ 6~03027~, 9~02865~ 11~0954~: [14] 16~06212~ 19~07704~, [21] 23~03419~ 24~01877~, [25] 27~02682~ 30~01406~, [32 33] 34~07709~ 35~06440~ 39~07054~.'),
  (866, 1, 30, 32, 'I will pass through all thy flock to day, removing from thence all the speckled and spotted cattle, and all the brown cattle among the sheep, and the spotted and speckled among the goats: and of such shall be my hire.', '2~05674~ 6~06629~ 8~03117~, 9~05493~ 14~05348~ 16~02921~ 17~07716~, 21~02345~ 22~07716~ 25~03775~, 28~02921~ 30~05348~ 33~05795~: [35 36] 40~07939~.'),
  (5986, 6, 7, 4, 'So there went up thither of the people about three thousand men: and they fled before the men of Ai.', '3~05927~ 7~05971~ 9~07969~ 10~0505~ 11~0376~: 14~05127~ 15~06440~ 17~0582~ 19~05857~.'),
  (26994, 44, 2, 29, 'Men and brethren, let me freely speak unto you of the patriarch David, that he is both dead and buried, and his sepulchre is with us unto this day.', '0~435~ [1] 2~80~, 3~2036~ 4~1832~ 5~3954~ 6~3326~* 7~2036~ 8~4314~ 9~5209~ 10~4012~ 12~3966~ 13~1138~, 14~3754~ 16~5053~ 17~2532~ 18~5053~ 19~2532~ 20~2290~, 21~2532~ 22~846~ 23~3418~ 24~2076~ 25~1722~ 26~2254~ 27~891~ 28~5026~ 29~2250~.'),
  (30081, 58, 7, 1, 'For this Melchisedec, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him;', '&para; 0~1063~ 1~3778~ 2~3198~, 3~935~ 5~4532~, 6~2409~ 10~5310~ 11~2316~, 12~3588~ 13~4876~ 14~11~ 15~5290~ 16~575~ 18~2871~ 21~935~, 22~2532~ 23~2127~ 24~846~;'),
  (18936, 23, 66, 5, 'Hear the word of the LORD, ye that tremble at his word; Your brethren that hated you, that cast you out for my name''s sake, said, Let the LORD be glorified: but he shall appear to your joy, and they shall be ashamed.', '&para; 0~08085~ 2~01697~ 5~03068~, 8~02730~ 11~01697~; 13~0251~ 15~08130~ 20~05077~ 23~08034~ 25~0559~, 28~03068~ 30~03513~: 34~07200~ 37~08057~, 42~0954~.'),
  (6878, 7, 12, 2, 'And Jephthah said unto them, I and my people were at great strife with the children of Ammon; and when I called you, ye delivered me not out of their hands.', '1~03316~ 2~0559~ 8~05971~ 9~01961~ 11~03966~ 12~07379~ 13~0376~ 15~01121~ 17~05983~; 21~02199~ 24~03467~ 30~03027~.'),
  (2950, 3, 8, 28, 'And Moses took them from off their hands, and burnt them on the altar upon the burnt offering: they were consecrations for a sweet savour: it is an offering made by fire unto the LORD.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 7~03709~, 9~06999~ [10] 13~04196~ 17~05930~: [19] 20~04394~ 23~05207~ 24~07381~: [26] 31~0801~ 34~03068~.'),
  (19219, 24, 10, 9, 'Silver spread into plates is brought from Tarshish, and gold from Uphaz, the work of the workman, and of the hands of the founder: blue and purple is their clothing: they are all the work of cunning men.', '0~03701~ 3~07554~ 5~0935~ 7~08659~, 9~02091~ 11~0210~, 13~04639~ 16~02796~, 20~03027~ 23~06884~: 24~08504~ 26~0713~ [27] 29~03830~: [31] 34~04639~ 36~02450~ [37]'),
  (15393, 19, 90, 6, 'In the morning it flourisheth, and groweth up; in the evening it is cut down, and withereth.', '2~01242~ 4~06692~, 7~02498~; 10~06153~ 14~04135~, 16~03001~.'),
  (16763, 20, 13, 7, 'There is that maketh himself rich, yet hath nothing: there is that maketh himself poor, yet hath great riches.', '&para; 1~03426~ 5~06238~, [7] [9 10] 14~07326~, 15~03605~ [16] 17~07227~ 18~01952~.'),
  (25602, 42, 15, 1, 'Then drew near unto him all the publicans and sinners for to hear him.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~1448~* 5~846~ 6~3956~ 8~5057~ 9~2532~ 10~268~ 13~191~ 14~846~.'),
  (8843, 11, 3, 19, 'And this woman''s child died in the night; because she overlaid it.', '2~0802~ 3~01121~ 4~04191~ 7~03915~; 10~07901~'),
  (2224, 2, 25, 24, 'And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, and make thereto a crown of gold round about.', '3~06823~ 6~02889~ 7~02091~, 9~06213~ 12~02213~ 14~02091~ 16~05439~.'),
  (18061, 23, 21, 17, 'And the residue of the number of archers, the mighty men of the children of Kedar, shall be diminished: for the LORD God of Israel hath spoken it.', '2~07605~ 5~04557~ 7~07198~, 10~01368~ 13~01121~ 15~06938~, 18~04591~: 21~03068~ 22~0430~ 24~03478~ 26~01696~ [27]'),
  (22963, 38, 6, 7, 'And the bay went forth, and sought to go that they might walk to and fro through the earth: and he said, Get you hence, walk to and fro through the earth. So they walked to and fro through the earth.', '2~0554~ 4~03318~, 6~01245~ 8~03212~ 15~01980~ 18~0776~: 21~0559~, 24~03212~, 28~01980~ 31~0776~. 37~01980~ 40~0776~.'),
  (4494, 4, 25, 18, 'For they vex you with their wiles, wherewith they have beguiled you in the matter of Peor, and in the matter of Cozbi, the daughter of a prince of Midian, their sister, which was slain in the day of the plague for Peor''s sake.', '2~06887~ 6~05231~, 10~05230~ 14~01697~ 16~06465~, 20~01697~ 22~03579~, 24~01323~ 27~05387~ 29~04080~, 31~0269~, 34~05221~ 37~03117~ 40~04046~ 42~06465~ 43~01697~.'),
  (14709, 19, 51, 9, 'Hide thy face from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities.', '0~05641~ 2~06440~ 5~02399~, 8~04229~ 11~05771~.'),
  (7752, 9, 20, 15, 'But also thou shalt not cut off thy kindness from my house for ever: no, not when the LORD hath cut off the enemies of David every one from the face of the earth.', '[1] 6~03772~ 8~02617~ 11~01004~ 12~05704~ 13~05769~: 18~03068~ 21~03772~ 23~0341~ 25~01732~ 27~0376~ 30~06440~ 33~0127~.'),
  (14178, 19, 19, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handiwork.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 9~08064~ 10~05608~ 12~03519~ 14~0410~; 17~07549~ 19~05046~ 20~03027~ 21~04639~.*'),
  (28313, 45, 14, 17, 'For the kingdom of God is not meat and drink; but righteousness, and peace, and joy in the Holy Ghost.', '0~1063~ 2~932~ 4~2316~ 5~2076~ 6~3756~ 7~1035~ 8~2532~ 9~4213~; 10~235~ 11~1343~, 12~2532~ 13~1515~, 14~2532~ 15~5479~ 16~1722~ 18~40~ 19~4151~.'),
  (25634, 42, 16, 1, 'And he said also unto his disciples, There was a certain rich man, which had a steward; and the same was accused unto him that he had wasted his goods.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~3004~ 3~2532~ 4~4314~ 5~846~ 6~3101~, 8~2258~ 10~5100~ 11~4145~ 12~444~, 13~3739~ 14~2192~ 16~3623~; 17~2532~ 19~3778~ 21~1225~ 23~846~ 24~5613~ 27~1287~ 28~846~ 29~5224~.'),
  (30828, 66, 7, 2, 'And I saw another angel ascending from the east, having the seal of the living God: and he cried with a loud voice to the four angels, to whom it was given to hurt the earth and the sea,', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 3~243~ 4~32~ 5~305~ 6~575~ 8~2246~ 9~395~,* 10~2192~ 12~4973~ 15~2198~ 16~2316~: 17~2532~ 19~2896~ 22~3173~ 23~5456~ 26~5064~ 27~32~, 29~3739~ 30~846~ 32~1325~ 34~91~ 36~1093~ 37~2532~ 39~2281~,'),
  (10342, 13, 2, 28, 'And the sons of Onam were, Shammai, and Jada. And the sons of Shammai; Nadab, and Abishur.', '2~01121~ 4~0208~ 6~08060~, 8~03047~. 11~01121~ 13~08060~; 14~05070~, 16~051~.'),
  (12723, 17, 1, 12, 'But the queen Vashti refused to come at the king''s commandment by his chamberlains: therefore was the king very wroth, and his anger burned in him.', '2~04436~ 3~02060~ 4~03985~ 6~0935~ 9~04428~ 10~01697~ 11~03027~ [12] 13~05631~: 17~04428~ 18~03966~ 19~07107~, 22~02534~ 23~01197~'),
  (22463, 30, 6, 4, 'That lie upon beds of ivory, and stretch themselves upon their couches, and eat the lambs out of the flock, and the calves out of the midst of the stall;', '1~07901~ 3~04296~ 5~08127~, 7~05628~ 11~06210~, 13~0398~ 15~03733~ 19~06629~, 22~05695~ 26~08432~ 29~04770~;'),
  (7329, 9, 5, 3, 'And when they of Ashdod arose early on the morrow, behold, Dagon was fallen upon his face to the earth before the ark of the LORD. And they took Dagon, and set him in his place again.', '4~0796~ 6~07925~ 9~04283~, 11~01712~ [12] 13~05307~ 16~06440~ 19~0776~ 20~06440~ 22~0727~ 25~03068~. 28~03947~ 29~01712~, 31~07725~ 35~04725~ 36~07725~.'),
  (8791, 11, 2, 13, 'And Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon. And she said, Comest thou peaceably? And he said, Peaceably.', '1~0138~ 3~01121~ 5~02294~ 6~0935~ 8~01339~ 10~0517~ 12~08010~. 15~0559~, 16~0935~ 18~07965~? 21~0559~, 22~07965~.'),
  (22100, 27, 12, 10, 'Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand; but the wise shall understand.', '0~07227~ 3~01305~, 6~03835~, 8~06884~; 11~07563~ 14~07561~: 19~07563~ 21~0995~; 24~07919~ 26~0995~.'),
  (23935, 40, 23, 7, 'And greetings in the markets, and to be called of men, Rabbi, Rabbi.', '0~2532~ 1~783~ 2~1722~ 4~58~, 5~2532~ 8~2564~ 9~5259~ 10~444~, 11~4461~, 12~4461~.'),
  (4469, 4, 24, 18, 'And Edom shall be a possession, Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies; and Israel shall do valiantly.', '1~0123~ 5~03424~, 6~08165~ 11~03424~ 14~0341~; 16~03478~ 18~06213~ 19~02428~.'),
  (9975, 12, 16, 4, 'And he sacrificed and burnt incense in the high places, and on the hills, and under every green tree.', '2~02076~ 5~06999~ 9~01116~, 13~01389~, 17~07488~ 18~06086~.'),
  (24786, 41, 14, 21, 'The Son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! good were it for that man if he had never been born.', '1~5207~ 3~444~ 4~3303~ 5~5217~, 6~2531~ 9~1125~ 10~4012~ 11~846~: 12~1161~ 13~3759~ 15~1565~ 16~444~ 17~1223~ 18~3739~ 20~5207~ 22~444~ 24~3860~! 25~2570~ 27~2258~ 29~1565~ 30~444~ 31~1487~ 32~846~ 33~1080~ 34~3756~ 36~1080~.'),
  (26047, 42, 24, 42, 'And they gave him a piece of a broiled fish, and of an honeycomb.', '0~1161~ 2~1929~ 3~846~ 5~3313~ 8~3702~ 9~2486~, 10~2532~ 11~575~ 13~2781~ 14~3193~.*'),
  (25780, 42, 19, 35, 'And they brought him to Jesus: and they cast their garments upon the colt, and they set Jesus thereon.', '0~2532~ 2~71~ 3~846~ 4~4314~ 5~2424~: 6~2532~ 8~1977~ 9~1438~ 10~2440~ 11~1977~ 12~1909~* 14~4454~, 15~1977~ 17~1913~ 18~2424~ 19~1913~.');
