VALUES
  (23043, 38, 11, 6, 'For I will no more pity the inhabitants of the land, saith the LORD: but, lo, I will deliver the men every one into his neighbour''s hand, and into the hand of his king: and they shall smite the land, and out of their hand I will not deliver them.', '5~02550~ 7~03427~ 10~0776~, 11~05002~ 13~03068~: 18~04672~ 20~0120~ 22~0376~ 25~07453~ 26~03027~, 30~03027~ 33~04428~: 37~03807~ 39~0776~, 44~03027~ 48~05337~ [49]'),
  (13419, 18, 22, 21, 'Acquaint now thyself with him, and be at peace: thereby good shall come unto thee.', '&para; 0~05532~ 8~07999~: 10~02896~ 12~0935~'),
  (24241, 41, 1, 16, 'Now as he walked by the sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea: for they were fishers.', '0~1161~ 3~4043~ 4~3844~ 6~2281~ 8~1056~, 10~1492~ 11~4613~ 12~2532~ 13~406~ 14~846~ 15~80~ 16~906~ 18~293~ 19~1722~ 21~2281~: 22~1063~ 24~2258~ 25~231~.'),
  (29974, 57, 1, 20, 'Yea, brother, let me have joy of thee in the Lord: refresh my bowels in the Lord.', '0~3483~, 1~80~, 2~3685~ 3~1473~ 5~3685~ 7~4675~ 8~1722~ 10~2962~: 11~373~ 12~3450~ 13~4698~ 14~1722~ 16~2962~.'),
  (10853, 13, 16, 25, 'For great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised: he also is to be feared above all gods.', '1~01419~ [2] 4~03068~, 6~03966~ 9~01984~: [12] 15~03372~ 18~0430~.'),
  (5758, 5, 31, 24, 'And it came to pass, when Moses had made an end of writing the words of this law in a book, until they were finished,', '6~04872~ 10~03615~ 12~03789~ 14~01697~ 17~08451~ 20~05612~, 24~08552~,'),
  (7261, 9, 2, 14, 'And he struck it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot; all that the fleshhook brought up the priest took for himself. So they did in Shiloh, unto all the Israelites that came thither.', '2~05221~ [3] 6~03595~, 8~01731~, 10~07037~, 12~06517~; 16~04207~ 18~05927~ 20~03548~ 21~03947~ 26~06213~ 28~07887~ 32~03478~ 34~0935~'),
  (29424, 50, 2, 17, 'Yea, and if I be offered upon the sacrifice and service of your faith, I joy, and rejoice with you all.', '0~235~, 2~1499~ 5~4689~ 6~1909~ 8~2378~ 9~2532~ 10~3009~ 12~5216~ 13~4102~, 15~5463~, 16~2532~ 18~4796~ 19~5213~ 20~3956~.'),
  (25860, 42, 21, 20, 'And when ye shall see Jerusalem compassed with armies, then know that the desolation thereof is nigh.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3752~ 4~1492~ 5~2419~ 6~2944~ 7~5259~ 8~4760~, 9~5119~ 10~1097~ 11~3754~ 13~2050~ 14~846~ 16~1448~.'),
  (21321, 26, 33, 32, 'And, lo, thou art unto them as a very lovely song of one that hath a pleasant voice, and can play well on an instrument: for they hear thy words, but they do them not.', '[3] 9~05690~ 10~07892~ 16~03303~ 17~06963~, 21~02895~ 24~05059~: 27~08085~ 29~01697~, 32~06213~'),
  (29977, 57, 1, 23, 'There salute thee Epaphras, my fellowprisoner in Christ Jesus;', '1~782~ 2~4571~ 3~1889~, 4~3450~ 5~4869~ 6~1722~ 7~5547~ 8~2424~;'),
  (14402, 19, 34, 5, 'They looked unto him, and were lightened: and their faces were not ashamed.', '1~05027~ 6~05102~: 9~06440~ 12~02659~.'),
  (6612, 7, 4, 6, 'And she sent and called Barak the son of Abinoam out of Kedeshnaphtali, and said unto him, Hath not the LORD God of Israel commanded, saying, Go and draw toward mount Tabor, and take with thee ten thousand men of the children of Naphtali and of the children of Zebulun?', '2~07971~ 4~07121~ 5~01301~ 7~01121~ 9~042~ 12~06943~, 14~0559~ 20~03068~ 21~0430~ 23~03478~ 24~06680~, [25] 26~03212~ 28~04900~ 30~02022~ 31~08396~, 33~03947~ 36~06235~ 37~0505~ 38~0376~ 41~01121~ 43~05321~ 47~01121~ 49~02074~?'),
  (28284, 45, 13, 2, 'Whosoever therefore resisteth the power, resisteth the ordinance of God: and they that resist shall receive to themselves damnation.', '1~5620~ 2~498~ 4~1849~, 5~436~ 7~1296~ 9~2316~: 10~1161~ 13~436~ 15~2983~ 17~1438~ 18~2917~.'),
  (21354, 26, 35, 1, 'Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (25804, 42, 20, 11, 'And again he sent another servant: and they beat him also, and entreated him shamefully, and sent him away empty.', '0~2532~ 1~4369~ 3~3992~ 4~2087~ 5~1401~: 6~1161~ 8~1194~ 10~2548~, 11~2532~ [13] 14~818~, [17] 18~1821~ 19~2756~.'),
  (29728, 54, 1, 16, 'Howbeit for this cause I obtained mercy, that in me first Jesus Christ might shew forth all longsuffering, for a pattern to them which should hereafter believe on him to life everlasting.', '0~235~ 2~5124~ 3~1223~ 6~1653~, 7~2443~ 8~1722~ 9~1698~ 10~4413~ 11~2424~ 12~5547~ 15~1731~ 16~3956~ 17~3115~, 18~4314~ 20~5296~ 25~3195~ 26~4100~ 27~1909~ 28~846~ 29~1519~ 30~2222~ 31~166~.'),
  (9350, 11, 18, 1, 'And it came to pass after many days, that the word of the LORD came to Elijah in the third year, saying, Go, shew thyself unto Ahab; and I will send rain upon the earth.', '&para; [5] 6~07227~ 7~03117~, 10~01697~ 13~03068~ 16~0452~ 19~07992~ 20~08141~, 21~0559~, 22~03212~, 23~07200~ 26~0256~; 30~05414~ 31~04306~ 32~06440~ 34~0127~.'),
  (20522, 26, 3, 11, 'And go, get thee to them of the captivity, unto the children of thy people, and speak unto them, and tell them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear.', '1~03212~, 2~0935~ 8~01473~, 11~01121~ 14~05971~, 16~01696~ 20~0559~ 23~0559~ 25~0136~ 26~03069~; 30~08085~, 35~02308~.'),
  (25259, 42, 8, 2, 'And certain women, which had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities, Mary called Magdalene, out of whom went seven devils,', '0~2532~ 1~5100~ 2~1135~, 3~3739~ 5~2258~ 6~2323~ 7~575~ 8~4190~ 9~4151~ 10~2532~ 11~769~, 12~3137~ 13~2564~ 14~3094~, 16~575~ 17~3739~ 18~1831~ 19~2033~ 20~1140~,'),
  (29208, 48, 6, 4, 'But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing in himself alone, and not in another.', '0~1161~ 1~1381~ 3~1538~ 4~1381~ 6~1438~ 7~2041~, 8~2532~ 9~5119~ 12~2192~ 13~2745~ 14~1519~ 15~1438~ 16~3441~, 17~2532~ 18~3756~ 19~1519~ 20~2087~.'),
  (25171, 42, 6, 13, 'And when it was day, he called unto him his disciples: and of them he chose twelve, whom also he named apostles;', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 3~1096~ 4~2250~, 6~4377~ [7 8] 9~846~ 10~3101~: 11~2532~ 12~575~ 13~846~ 15~1586~ 16~1427~, 17~3739~ 18~2532~ 20~3687~ 21~652~;'),
  (25349, 42, 9, 36, 'And when the voice was past, Jesus was found alone. And they kept it close, and told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen.', '0~2532~ 3~5456~ 5~1096~ 6~1722~,* 7~2424~ 9~2147~ 10~3441~. 11~2532~ 12~846~ [14] 15~4601~, 16~2532~ 17~518~ 19~3762~ 20~1722~ 21~1565~ 22~2250~ 23~3762~ 27~3739~ 30~3708~.'),
  (11286, 14, 5, 10, 'There was nothing in the ark save the two tables which Moses put therein at Horeb, when the LORD made a covenant with the children of Israel, when they came out of Egypt.', '[0 1] 5~0727~ 8~08147~ 9~03871~ 11~04872~ 12~05414~ [13] 15~02722~, 18~03068~ 19~03772~ [20 21] 24~01121~ 26~03478~, 30~03318~ 32~04714~.'),
  (4820, 4, 33, 54, 'And ye shall divide the land by lot for an inheritance among your families: and to the more ye shall give the more inheritance, and to the fewer ye shall give the less inheritance: every man''s inheritance shall be in the place where his lot falleth; according to the tribes of your fathers ye shall inherit.', '3~05157~ 5~0776~ 7~01486~ 10~05157~ 13~04940~: [14] 17~07227~ 22~07235~ 23~05159~, 27~04592~ 32~04591~ 33~05159~: [36] 44~01486~ 45~03318~; 49~04294~ 52~01~ 55~05157~.'),
  (18737, 23, 54, 5, 'For thy Maker is thine husband; the LORD of hosts is his name; and thy Redeemer the Holy One of Israel; The God of the whole earth shall he be called.', '2~06213~ [3] 5~01166~; 7~03068~ 9~06635~ [10] 12~08034~; 15~01350~ 18~06918~ 20~03478~; 22~0430~ 26~0776~ 30~07121~.'),
  (15347, 19, 89, 12, 'The north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name.', '1~06828~ 4~03225~ 7~01254~ 9~08396~ 11~02768~ 13~07442~ 16~08034~.'),
  (12367, 16, 3, 31, 'After him repaired Malchiah the goldsmith''s son unto the place of the Nethinims, and of the merchants, over against the gate Miphkad, and to the going up of the corner.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 3~04441~ 5~06885~ 6~01121~ 9~01004~ 12~05411~, 16~07402~, 20~08179~ 21~04663~, 26~05944~ 29~06438~.'),
  (20040, 24, 44, 21, 'The incense that ye burned in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, ye, and your fathers, your kings, and your princes, and the people of the land, did not the LORD remember them, and came it not into his mind?', '1~07002~ 4~06999~ 7~05892~ 9~03063~, 13~02351~ 15~03389~, 19~01~, 21~04428~, 24~08269~, 27~05971~ 30~0776~, 34~03068~ 35~02142~ 38~05927~ [40] 43~03820~?'),
  (27423, 44, 13, 45, 'But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with envy, and spake against those things which were spoken by Paul, contradicting and blaspheming.', '0~1161~ 3~2453~ 4~1492~ 6~3793~, 9~4130~ 11~2205~, 12~2532~ 14~483~ 19~3004~ 20~5259~ 21~3972~, 22~483~ 23~2532~ 24~987~.'),
  (5880, 6, 2, 5, 'And it came to pass about the time of shutting of the gate, when it was dark, that the men went out: whither the men went I wot not: pursue after them quickly; for ye shall overtake them.', '[5 7] 9~05462~ 12~08179~, 16~02822~, 19~0582~ 21~03318~: 24~0582~ 25~01980~ 27~03045~ 29~07291~ 30~0310~ 32~04118~; 36~05381~'),
  (17443, 21, 7, 5, 'It is better to hear the rebuke of the wise, than for a man to hear the song of fools.', '[0 1] 2~02896~ 4~08085~ 6~01606~ 9~02450~, 13~0376~ 15~08085~ 17~07892~ 19~03684~.'),
  (7086, 7, 20, 25, 'And Benjamin went forth against them out of Gibeah the second day, and destroyed down to the ground of the children of Israel again eighteen thousand men; all these drew the sword.', '1~01144~ 3~03318~ 4~07125~ 8~01390~ 10~08145~ 11~03117~, 14~07843~ 17~0776~ 20~01121~ 22~03478~ 24~06240~ 25~08083~* 26~0505~ 27~0376~; 30~08025~ 32~02719~.'),
  (13461, 18, 24, 16, 'In the dark they dig through houses, which they had marked for themselves in the daytime: they know not the light.', '2~02822~ 5~02864~ 6~01004~, [7] 10~02856~ 15~03119~: 17~03045~ 20~0216~.'),
  (1534, 1, 50, 23, 'And Joseph saw Ephraim''s children of the third generation: the children also of Machir the son of Manasseh were brought up upon Joseph''s knees.', '1~03130~ 2~07200~ 3~0669~ 4~01121~ 7~08029~ [8] 10~01121~ 13~04353~ 15~01121~ 17~04519~ 20~03205~ 22~03130~ 23~01290~.'),
  (19656, 24, 29, 12, 'Then shall ye call upon me, and ye shall go and pray unto me, and I will hearken unto you.', '3~07121~ 9~01980~ 11~06419~ 17~08085~'),
  (11375, 14, 9, 3, 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, and the house that he had built,', '3~04436~ 5~07614~ 7~07200~ 9~02451~ 11~08010~, 14~01004~ 18~01129~,'),
  (15979, 19, 119, 72, 'The law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.', '&para; 1~08451~ 4~06310~ [5] 6~02896~ 10~0505~ 12~02091~ 14~03701~.'),
  (27702, 44, 21, 22, 'What is it therefore? the multitude must needs come together: for they will hear that thou art come.', '0~5101~ 2~2076~ 3~3767~? 5~4128~ 6~1163~ 7~3843~ 9~4905~: 10~1063~ 13~191~ 14~3754~ 17~2064~.'),
  (6623, 7, 4, 17, 'Howbeit Sisera fled away on his feet to the tent of Jael the wife of Heber the Kenite: for there was peace between Jabin the king of Hazor and the house of Heber the Kenite.', '&para; 1~05516~ 3~05127~ 6~07272~ 9~0168~ 11~03278~ 13~0802~ 15~02268~ 17~07017~: [19 20] 21~07965~ 23~02985~ 25~04428~ 27~02674~ 30~01004~ 32~02268~ 34~07017~.'),
  (19996, 24, 42, 12, 'And I will shew mercies unto you, that he may have mercy upon you, and cause you to return to your own land.', '3~05414~ 4~07356~ 11~07355~ 18~07725~ 22~0127~.'),
  (17696, 23, 2, 2, 'And it shall come to pass in the last days, that the mountain of the Lord''s house shall be established in the top of the mountains, and shall be exalted above the hills; and all nations shall flow unto it.', '8~0319~ 9~03117~, [10] 12~02022~ 15~03068~ 16~01004~ 19~03559~ 22~07218~ 25~02022~, 29~05375~ 32~01389~; 35~01471~ 37~05102~'),
  (3290, 3, 19, 4, 'Turn ye not unto idols, nor make to yourselves molten gods: I am the LORD your God.', '0~06437~ 4~0457~, 6~06213~ 9~04541~ 10~0430~: [12] 14~03068~ 16~0430~.'),
  (11860, 14, 30, 24, 'For Hezekiah king of Judah did give to the congregation a thousand bullocks and seven thousand sheep; and the princes gave to the congregation a thousand bullocks and ten thousand sheep: and a great number of priests sanctified themselves.', '1~02396~ 2~04428~ 4~03063~ 6~07311~ 9~06951~ 11~0505~ 12~06499~ 14~07651~ 15~0505~ 16~06629~; 19~08269~ 20~07311~ 23~06951~ 25~0505~ 26~06499~ 28~06235~ 29~0505~ 30~06629~: 34~07230~ 36~03548~ 37~06942~'),
  (479, 1, 19, 18, 'And Lot said unto them, Oh, not so, my Lord:', '1~03876~ 2~0559~ 9~0113~:'),
  (13758, 18, 36, 13, 'But the hypocrites in heart heap up wrath: they cry not when he bindeth them.', '2~02611~ 4~03820~ 6~07760~ 7~0639~: 9~07768~ 13~0631~'),
  (72, 1, 3, 16, 'Unto the woman he said, I will greatly multiply thy sorrow and thy conception; in sorrow thou shalt bring forth children; and thy desire shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule over thee.', '&para; 2~0802~ 4~0559~, 7~07235~ 8~07235~ 10~06093~ 13~02032~; 15~06089~ 19~03205~ 20~01121~; 23~08669~ [24 25] 28~0376~, 32~04910~'),
  (10647, 13, 9, 24, 'In four quarters were the porters, toward the east, west, north, and south.', '1~0702~ 2~07307~ 5~07778~, 8~04217~, 9~03220~, 10~06828~, 12~05045~.'),
  (9958, 12, 15, 25, 'But Pekah the son of Remaliah, a captain of his, conspired against him, and smote him in Samaria, in the palace of the king''s house, with Argob and Arieh, and with him fifty men of the Gileadites: and he killed him, and reigned in his room.', '1~06492~ 3~01121~ 5~07425~, 7~07991~ 10~07194~ 14~05221~ 17~08111~, 20~0759~ 23~04428~ 24~01004~, 26~0709~ 28~0745~, 32~02572~ 33~0376~ 36~01569~ 37~01121~:* 40~04191~ 43~04427~'),
  (19448, 24, 20, 17, 'Because he slew me not from the womb; or that my mother might have been my grave, and her womb to be always great with me.', '2~04191~ 7~07358~; 11~0517~ 16~06913~, 19~07358~ [20 21] 22~05769~ 23~02030~ [24 25]'),
  (17309, 20, 31, 16, 'She considereth a field, and buyeth it: with the fruit of her hands she planteth a vineyard.', '1~02161~ 3~07704~, 5~03947~ 9~06529~ 12~03709~ 14~05193~ 16~03754~.'),
  (24738, 41, 13, 10, 'And the gospel must first be published among all nations.', '0~2532~ 2~2098~ 3~1163~ 4~4412~ 6~2784~ 7~1519~ 8~3956~ 9~1484~.'),
  (20390, 25, 3, 27, 'It is good for a man that he bear the yoke in his youth.', '[0 1] 2~02896~ 5~01397~ 8~05375~ 10~05923~ 13~05271~.'),
  (30301, 59, 1, 19, 'Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to wrath:', '&para; 0~5620~, 1~3450~ 2~27~ 3~80~, 4~2077~ 5~3956~ 6~444~ 7~2077~ 8~5036~ 9~1519~ 10~191~, 11~1021~ 12~1519~ 13~2980~, 14~1021~ 15~1519~ 16~3709~:'),
  (12587, 16, 10, 29, 'They clave to their brethren, their nobles, and entered into a curse, and into an oath, to walk in God''s law, which was given by Moses the servant of God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the LORD our Lord, and his judgments and his statutes;', '1~02388~ 4~0251~, 6~0117~, 8~0935~ 11~0423~, 15~07621~, 17~03212~ 19~0430~ 20~08451~, 23~05414~ 24~03027~ 25~04872~ 27~05650~ 29~0430~, 32~08104~ 34~06213~ 37~04687~ 40~03068~ 42~0113~, 45~04941~ 48~02706~;'),
  (1648, 2, 5, 11, 'Go ye, get you straw where ye can find it: yet not ought of your work shall be diminished.', '0~03212~ 2~03947~ 4~08401~ 5~0834~ 8~04672~ 10~03588~ 12~01697~ 15~05656~ 18~01639~.'),
  (2647, 2, 38, 9, 'And he made the court: on the south side southward the hangings of the court were of fine twined linen, an hundred cubits:', '&para; 2~06213~ 4~02691~: 7~05045~ 8~06285~ 9~08486~ 11~07050~ 14~02691~ [15 16] 18~07806~ 19~08336~, 21~03967~ 22~0520~:'),
  (13822, 18, 38, 20, 'That thou shouldest take it to the bound thereof, and that thou shouldest know the paths to the house thereof?', '3~03947~ 7~01366~ 13~0995~ 15~05410~ [16] 18~01004~'),
  (6510, 6, 24, 27, 'And Joshua said unto all the people, Behold, this stone shall be a witness unto us; for it hath heard all the words of the LORD which he spake unto us: it shall be therefore a witness unto you, lest ye deny your God.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ 6~05971~, 9~068~ 13~05713~ 19~08085~ 22~0561~ 25~03068~ 28~01696~ 36~05713~ 41~03584~ 43~0430~.'),
  (1457, 1, 48, 1, 'And it came to pass after these things, that one told Joseph, Behold, thy father is sick: and he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim.', '&para; 5~0310~ 7~01697~, [9] 10~0559~ 11~03130~, 14~01~ [15] 16~02470~: 19~03947~ 23~08147~ 24~01121~, 25~04519~ 27~0669~.'),
  (28359, 45, 16, 7, 'Salute Andronicus and Junia, my kinsmen, and my fellowprisoners, who are of note among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.', '0~782~ 1~408~ 2~2532~ 3~2458~, 4~3450~ 5~4773~, 6~2532~ 7~3450~ 8~4869~, 9~3748~ 10~1526~ 12~1978~ 13~1722~ 15~652~, 16~3739~ 17~2532~ 18~1096~ 19~1722~ 20~5547~ 21~4253~ 22~1700~.'),
  (27852, 44, 26, 13, 'At midday, O king, I saw in the way a light from heaven, above the brightness of the sun, shining round about me and them which journeyed with me.', '1~3319~ 2~2250~,* 4~935~, 6~1492~ 7~2596~ 9~3598~ 11~5457~ 13~3771~, 14~5228~ 16~2987~ 19~2246~, 22~4034~ 23~3165~ 24~2532~ 27~4198~ 28~4862~ 29~1698~.'),
  (12505, 16, 8, 3, 'And he read therein before the street that was before the water gate from the morning until midday, before the men and the women, and those that could understand; and the ears of all the people were attentive unto the book of the law.', '2~07121~ 4~06440~ 6~07339~ [8] 9~06440~ 11~04325~ 12~08179~ 15~0216~ 17~03117~ 18~04276~,* 21~0582~ 24~0802~, 29~0995~; 32~0241~ 36~05971~ [37 38] 41~05612~ 44~08451~.'),
  (29390, 50, 1, 13, 'So that my bonds in Christ are manifest in all the palace, and in all other places;', '1~5620~ 2~3450~ 3~1199~ 4~1722~ 5~5547~ 6~1096~ 7~5318~ 8~1722~ 9~3650~ 11~4232~, 12~2532~ 14~3956~ 15~3062~ [16]'),
  (29576, 51, 4, 18, 'The salutation by the hand of me Paul. Remember my bonds. Grace be with you. Amen.', '1~783~ 4~5495~ 6~1699~ 7~3972~. 8~3421~ 9~3450~ 10~1199~. 11~5485~ [12] 13~3326~ 14~5216~. 15~281~ 16~1125~.* [17 18~575~ 19~4516~ 20~4314~ 21~2858~ 22~1223~ 23~5190~ 24~2532~ 25] 25~3682~'),
  (8154, 10, 5, 15, 'Ibhar also, and Elishua, and Nepheg, and Japhia,', '0~02984~ 3~0474~, 5~05298~, 7~03309~,'),
  (26197, 43, 4, 26, 'Jesus saith unto her, I that speak unto thee am he.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1473~ 6~2980~ 8~4671~ 9~1510~ [10]'),
  (3272, 3, 18, 16, 'Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy brother''s wife: it is thy brother''s nakedness.', '3~01540~ 5~06172~ 8~0251~ 9~0802~: [11] 13~0251~ 14~06172~.'),
  (7455, 9, 11, 3, 'And the elders of Jabesh said unto him, Give us seven days'' respite, that we may send messengers unto all the coasts of Israel: and then, if there be no man to save us, we will come out to thee.', '2~02205~ 4~03003~ 5~0559~ 10~07651~ 11~03117~ 12~07503~, 16~07971~ 17~04397~ 21~01366~ 23~03478~: [27 28] 32~03467~ 37~03318~'),
  (23840, 40, 21, 4, 'All this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying,', '0~3650~ 1~1161~* 2~5124~ 4~1096~, 5~2443~ 9~4137~ 10~3588~ 12~4483~ 13~1223~ 15~4396~, 16~3004~,'),
  (14231, 19, 22, 18, 'They part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.', '1~02505~ 3~0899~ 7~05307~ 8~01486~ 11~03830~.'),
  (25544, 42, 13, 13, 'And he laid his hands on her: and immediately she was made straight, and glorified God.', '0~2532~ 2~2007~ [3] 4~5495~ 5~2007~ 6~846~: 7~2532~ 8~3916~ 12~461~, 13~2532~ 14~1392~ 15~2316~.'),
  (19492, 24, 22, 29, 'O earth, earth, earth, hear the word of the LORD.', '1~0776~, 2~0776~, 3~0776~, 4~08085~ 6~01697~ 9~03068~.'),
  (21200, 26, 29, 8, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will bring a sword upon thee, and cut off man and beast out of thee.', '&para; 2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 9~0935~ 11~02719~ 16~03772~ 17~0120~ 19~0929~'),
  (12748, 17, 2, 15, 'Now when the turn of Esther, the daughter of Abihail the uncle of Mordecai, who had taken her for his daughter, was come to go in unto the king, she required nothing but what Hegai the king''s chamberlain, the keeper of the women, appointed. And Esther obtained favour in the sight of all them that looked upon her.', '3~08447~ 5~0635~, 7~01323~ 9~032~ 11~01730~ 13~04782~, 16~03947~ 20~01323~, 22~05060~ 25~0935~ 28~04428~, 30~01245~ 31~01697~ 34~01896~ 36~04428~ 37~05631~, 39~08104~ 42~0802~, 43~0559~. 45~0635~ 46~05375~ 47~02580~ 50~05869~ 55~07200~'),
  (7210, 8, 4, 13, 'So Boaz took Ruth, and she was his wife: and when he went in unto her, the LORD gave her conception, and she bare a son.', '&para; 1~01162~ 2~03947~ 3~07327~, 8~0802~: 13~0935~ 17~03068~ 18~05414~ 20~02032~, 23~03205~ 25~01121~.'),
  (3375, 3, 22, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (12869, 17, 9, 26, 'Wherefore they called these days Purim after the name of Pur. Therefore for all the words of this letter, and of that which they had seen concerning this matter, and which had come unto them,', '2~07121~ 4~03117~ 5~06332~ 8~08034~ 10~06332~. 15~01697~ 18~0107~, [20 21] 25~07200~ 28~03602~, 32~05060~'),
  (29726, 54, 1, 14, 'And the grace of our Lord was exceeding abundant with faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.', '0~1161~ 2~5485~ 4~2257~ 5~2962~ 8~5250~ 9~3326~ 10~4102~ 11~2532~ 12~26~ 13~3588~ 15~1722~ 16~5547~ 17~2424~.'),
  (20230, 24, 51, 9, 'We would have healed Babylon, but she is not healed: forsake her, and let us go every one into his own country: for her judgment reacheth unto heaven, and is lifted up even to the skies.', '3~07495~ 4~0894~, 9~07495~: 10~05800~ 15~03212~ 17~0376~ 21~0776~: 24~04941~ 25~05060~ 27~08064~, 31~05375~ [32] 35~07834~.'),
  (10311, 13, 1, 51, 'Hadad died also. And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah, duke Aliah, duke Jetheth,', '0~01908~ 1~04191~ 5~0441~ 7~0123~ 9~0441~ 10~08555~, 11~0441~ 12~05933~, 13~0441~ 14~03509~,'),
  (1526, 1, 50, 15, 'And when Joseph''s brethren saw that their father was dead, they said, Joseph will peradventure hate us, and will certainly requite us all the evil which we did unto him.', '&para; 2~03130~ 3~0251~ 4~07200~ 7~01~ 9~04191~, 11~0559~, 12~03130~ 14~03863~ 16~07852~, 19~07725~ 20~07725~ 24~07451~ 27~01580~'),
  (7926, 9, 26, 14, 'And David cried to the people, and to Abner the son of Ner, saying, Answerest thou not, Abner? Then Abner answered and said, Who art thou that criest to the king?', '1~01732~ 2~07121~ 5~05971~, 8~074~ 10~01121~ 12~05369~, 13~0559~, 14~06030~ 17~074~? 19~074~ 20~06030~ 22~0559~, [24] [26] 27~07121~ 30~04428~?'),
  (9522, 11, 22, 34, 'And a certain man drew a bow at a venture, and smote the king of Israel between the joints of the harness: wherefore he said unto the driver of his chariot, Turn thine hand, and carry me out of the host; for I am wounded.', '[2] 3~0376~ 4~04900~ 6~07198~ 9~08537~, 11~05221~ 13~04428~ 15~03478~ 18~01694~ 21~08302~: 24~0559~ 30~07395~, 31~02015~ 33~03027~, 37~03318~ 40~04264~; 44~02470~.'),
  (15398, 19, 90, 11, 'Who knoweth the power of thine anger? even according to thy fear, so is thy wrath.', '1~03045~ 3~05797~ 6~0639~? 11~03374~, [12 13] 15~05678~.'),
  (1198, 1, 40, 21, 'And he restored the chief butler unto his butlership again; and he gave the cup into Pharaoh''s hand:', '2~07725~ 4~08269~ 5~08248~ 8~04945~ 9~07725~; 12~05414~ 14~03563~ 16~06547~ 17~03709~:'),
  (6219, 6, 15, 10, 'And the border compassed from Baalah westward unto mount Seir, and passed along unto the side of mount Jearim, which is Chesalon, on the north side, and went down to Bethshemesh, and passed on to Timnah:', '2~01366~ 3~05437~ 5~01173~ 6~03220~ 8~02022~ 9~08165~, 11~05674~ 15~03802~ 17~02022~ 18~03297~, [20] 21~03693~, 25~06828~, 28~03381~ 30~01053~, 33~05674~ 35~08553~:'),
  (11203, 14, 1, 1, 'And Solomon the son of David was strengthened in his kingdom, and the LORD his God was with him, and magnified him exceedingly.', '&para; 1~08010~ 3~01121~ 5~01732~ 7~02388~ 10~04438~, 13~03068~ 15~0430~ [16] 20~01431~ 22~04605~.'),
  (7294, 9, 3, 11, 'And the LORD said to Samuel, Behold, I will do a thing in Israel, at which both the ears of every one that heareth it shall tingle.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~08050~, 9~06213~ 11~01697~ 13~03478~, 16~08147~ 18~0241~ 23~08085~ 26~06750~.'),
  (5398, 5, 18, 8, 'They shall have like portions to eat, beside that which cometh of the sale of his patrimony.', '4~02506~ 6~0398~, 13~04465~ 16~01~.'),
  (23530, 40, 12, 31, 'Wherefore I say unto you, All manner of sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men: but the blasphemy against the Holy Ghost shall not be forgiven unto men.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 7~3956~ 8~266~ 9~2532~ 10~988~ 13~863~ 15~444~: 16~1161~ 18~988~ [19] [21] 22~4151~ 23~863~ 24~3756~ 26~863~ 28~444~.'),
  (17597, 22, 4, 6, 'Until the day break, and the shadows flee away, I will get me to the mountain of myrrh, and to the hill of frankincense.', '2~03117~ 3~06315~, 6~06752~ 8~05127~, 11~03212~ 15~02022~ 17~04753~, 21~01389~ 23~03828~.'),
  (1058, 1, 36, 13, 'And these are the sons of Reuel; Nahath, and Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah: these were the sons of Bashemath Esau''s wife.', '[2] 4~01121~ 6~07467~; 7~05184~, 9~02226~, 10~08048~, 12~04199~: 16~01121~ 18~01315~ 19~06215~ 20~0802~.'),
  (26919, 43, 21, 5, 'Then Jesus saith unto them, Children, have ye any meat? They answered him, No.', '0~3767~ 1~2424~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~3813~, 7~2192~ 8~3387~ 9~4371~? 11~611~ 12~846~, 13~3756~.'),
  (25321, 42, 9, 8, 'And of some, that Elias had appeared; and of others, that one of the old prophets was risen again.', '0~1161~ 1~5259~ 2~5100~, 3~3754~ 4~2243~ 6~5316~; 7~1161~ 9~243~, 10~3754~ 11~1520~ 14~744~ 15~4396~ 18~450~.'),
  (2194, 2, 24, 12, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Come up to me into the mount, and be there: and I will give thee tables of stone, and a law, and commandments which I have written; that thou mayest teach them.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~05927~ 12~02022~, 19~05414~ 21~03871~ 23~068~, 26~08451~, 28~04687~ 32~03789~; 36~03384~'),
  (8259, 10, 10, 12, 'Be of good courage, and let us play the men for our people, and for the cities of our God: and the LORD do that which seemeth him good.', '3~02388~, 9~02388~ 12~05971~, 16~05892~ 19~0430~: 22~03068~ 23~06213~ 26~05869~ 28~02896~.'),
  (17754, 23, 5, 6, 'And I will lay it waste: it shall not be pruned, nor digged; but there shall come up briers and thorns: I will also command the clouds that they rain no rain upon it.', '3~07896~ 5~01326~: 10~02168~, 12~05737~; 17~05927~ 18~08068~ 20~07898~: 24~06680~ 26~05645~ 29~04305~ 31~04306~'),
  (30667, 63, 1, 6, 'And this is love, that we walk after his commandments. This is the commandment, That, as ye have heard from the beginning, ye should walk in it.', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~2076~ 3~26~, 4~2443~ 6~4043~ 7~2596~ 8~846~ 9~1785~. 10~3778~ 11~2076~ 13~1785~, 14~2443~, 15~2531~ 18~191~ 19~575~ 21~746~, 24~4043~ 25~1722~ 26~846~.'),
  (18588, 23, 45, 18, 'For thus saith the LORD that created the heavens; God himself that formed the earth and made it; he hath established it, he created it not in vain, he formed it to be inhabited: I am the LORD; and there is none else.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~01254~ 8~08064~; 9~0430~ 12~03335~ 14~0776~ 16~06213~ 20~03559~ 23~01254~ 27~08414~, 29~03335~ 33~03427~: [35] 37~03068~; [39 40]');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (25469, 42, 11, 51, 'From the blood of Abel unto the blood of Zacharias, which perished between the altar and the temple: verily I say unto you, It shall be required of this generation.', '0~575~ 2~129~ 4~6~ 5~2193~ 7~129~ 9~2197~, 10~3588~ 11~622~ 12~3342~ 14~2379~ 15~2532~ 17~3624~: 18~3483~ 20~3004~ 22~5213~, 26~1567~ 27~575~ 28~5026~ 29~1074~.'),
  (28947, 47, 7, 15, 'And his inward affection is more abundant toward you, whilst he remembereth the obedience of you all, how with fear and trembling ye received him.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 3~4698~ 4~2076~ 6~4056~ 7~1519~ 8~5209~, 11~363~ 13~5218~ 15~5216~ 16~3956~, 17~5613~ 18~3326~ 19~5401~ 20~2532~ 21~5156~ 23~1209~ 24~846~.'),
  (19040, 24, 4, 4, 'Circumcise yourselves to the LORD, and take away the foreskins of your heart, ye men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem: lest my fury come forth like fire, and burn that none can quench it, because of the evil of your doings.', '0~04135~ 4~03068~, 7~05493~ 9~06190~ 12~03824~, 14~0376~ 16~03063~ 18~03427~ 20~03389~: 23~02534~ 25~03318~ 27~0784~, 29~01197~ 33~03518~ [34] 35~06440~ 38~07455~ 41~04611~.'),
  (1062, 1, 36, 17, 'And these are the sons of Reuel Esau''s son; duke Nahath, duke Zerah, duke Shammah, duke Mizzah: these are the dukes that came of Reuel in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Bashemath Esau''s wife.', '[2] 4~01121~ 6~07467~ 7~06215~ 8~01121~; 9~0441~ 10~05184~, 11~0441~ 12~02226~, 13~0441~ 14~08048~, 15~0441~ 16~04199~: [18] 20~0441~ [21 22] 24~07467~ 27~0776~ 29~0123~; [31] 33~01121~ 35~01315~ 36~06215~ 37~0802~.'),
  (24731, 41, 13, 3, 'And as he sat upon the mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,', '0~2532~ 2~846~ 3~2521~ 4~1519~ 6~3735~ 8~1636~ 10~2713~ 12~2411~, 13~4074~ 14~2532~ 15~2385~ 16~2532~ 17~2491~ 18~2532~ 19~406~ 20~1905~ 21~846~ 22~2398~ 23~2596~,*'),
  (29125, 48, 3, 7, 'Know ye therefore that they which are of faith, the same are the children of Abraham.', '1~1097~ 2~686~ 3~3754~ 7~1537~ 8~4102~, 10~3778~ 11~1526~ 13~5207~ 15~11~.'),
  (10867, 13, 16, 39, 'And Zadok the priest, and his brethren the priests, before the tabernacle of the LORD in the high place that was at Gibeon,', '1~06659~ 3~03548~, 6~0251~ 8~03548~, 9~06440~ 11~04908~ 14~03068~ 18~01116~ [20] 22~01391~,'),
  (18561, 23, 44, 19, 'And none considereth in his heart, neither is there knowledge nor understanding to say, I have burned part of it in the fire; yea, also I have baked bread upon the coals thereof; I have roasted flesh, and eaten it: and shall I make the residue thereof an abomination? shall I fall down to the stock of a tree?', '2~07725~ 5~03820~, [7 8] 9~01847~ 11~08394~ 13~0559~, 16~08313~ 17~02677~ 20~01119~ 22~0784~; 27~0644~ 28~03899~ 31~01513~ 35~06740~ 36~01320~, 38~0398~ [39] 43~06213~ 45~03499~ 48~08441~? 52~05456~ 55~0944~ 58~06086~?'),
  (2706, 2, 39, 37, 'The pure candlestick, with the lamps thereof, even with the lamps to be set in order, and all the vessels thereof, and the oil for light,', '1~02889~ 2~04501~, [3] 5~05216~ [7 8] 10~05216~ 15~04634~, 19~03627~ 23~08081~ 25~03974~,'),
  (26512, 43, 10, 16, 'And other sheep I have, which are not of this fold: them also I must bring, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.', '0~2532~ 1~243~ 2~4263~ 4~2192~, 5~3739~ 6~2076~ 7~3756~ 8~1537~ 9~5026~ 10~833~: 12~2548~ 13~3165~ 14~1163~ 15~71~, 16~2532~ 19~191~ 20~3450~ 21~5456~; 22~2532~ 25~1096~ 26~3391~ 27~4167~, [28] 29~1520~ 30~4166~.'),
  (30016, 58, 3, 5, 'And Moses verily was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken after;', '0~2532~ 1~3475~ 2~3303~ [3] 4~4103~ 5~1722~ 6~3650~ 7~846~ 8~3624~, 9~5613~ 11~2324~, 12~1519~ 14~3142~ 23~2980~;'),
  (14869, 19, 64, 10, 'The righteous shall be glad in the LORD, and shall trust in him; and all the upright in heart shall glory.', '1~06662~ 4~08055~ 7~03068~, 10~02620~ 16~03477~ 18~03820~ 20~01984~.'),
