  (11379, 14, 9, 7, 'Happy are thy men, and happy are these thy servants, which stand continually before thee, and hear thy wisdom.', '0~0835~ [1] 3~0582~, 5~0835~ [6] 9~05650~, 11~05975~ 12~08548~ 13~06440~ 16~08085~ 18~02451~.'),
  (25758, 42, 19, 13, 'And he called his ten servants, and delivered them ten pounds, and said unto them, Occupy till I come.', '0~1161~ 2~2564~ 3~1438~ 4~1176~ 5~1401~, 7~1325~ 8~846~ 9~1176~ 10~3414~, 11~2532~ 12~2036~ 13~4314~ 14~846~, 15~4231~ 16~2193~ 18~2064~.'),
  (13615, 18, 31, 18, '(For from my youth he was brought up with me, as with a father, and I have guided her from my mother''s womb;)', '3~05271~ 7~01431~ [11] 13~01~, 17~05148~ 21~0517~ 22~0990~;)'),
  (24199, 40, 27, 60, 'And laid it in his own new tomb, which he had hewn out in the rock: and he rolled a great stone to the door of the sepulchre, and departed.', '0~2532~ 1~5087~ 2~846~ 3~1722~ 5~846~ 6~2537~ 7~3419~, 8~3739~ 12~2998~ 13~1722~ 15~4073~: 16~2532~ 18~4351~ 20~3173~ 21~3037~ 24~2374~ 27~3419~, 29~565~.'),
  (25075, 42, 3, 38, 'Which was the son of Enos, which was the son of Seth, which was the son of Adam, which was the son of God.', '[2 3] 5~1800~, [8 9] 11~4589~, [14 15] 17~76~, [20 21] 23~2316~.'),
  (815, 1, 29, 16, 'And Laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.', '1~03837~ 3~08147~ 4~01323~: 6~08034~ 9~01419~ [10] 11~03812~, 14~08034~ 17~06996~ [18] 19~07354~.'),
  (482, 1, 19, 21, 'And he said unto him, See, I have accepted thee concerning this thing also, that I will not overthrow this city, for the which thou hast spoken.', '2~0559~ 5~02009~, 8~05375~ 9~06440~ 12~01697~ 18~02015~ 20~05892~, 23~0834~ 26~01696~.'),
  (26874, 43, 19, 34, 'But one of the soldiers with a spear pierced his side, and forthwith came there out blood and water.', '0~235~ 1~1520~ 4~4757~ 7~3057~ 8~3572~ 9~846~ 10~4125~, 11~2532~ 12~2117~ 15~1831~ 16~129~ 17~2532~ 18~5204~.'),
  (5011, 5, 4, 1, 'Now therefore hearken, O Israel, unto the statutes and unto the judgments, which I teach you, for to do them, that ye may live, and go in and possess the land which the LORD God of your fathers giveth you.', '&para; 2~08085~, 4~03478~, 7~02706~ 11~04941~, 14~03925~ 18~06213~ [19] 23~02421~, 26~0935~ 28~03423~ 30~0776~ 33~03068~ 34~0430~ 37~01~ 38~05414~'),
  (19419, 24, 19, 3, 'And say, Hear ye the word of the LORD, O kings of Judah, and inhabitants of Jerusalem; Thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will bring evil upon this place, the which whosoever heareth, his ears shall tingle.', '1~0559~, 2~08085~ 5~01697~ 8~03068~, 10~04428~ 12~03063~, 14~03427~ 16~03389~; 18~0559~ 20~03068~ 22~06635~, 24~0430~ 26~03478~; 30~0935~ 31~07451~ 34~04725~, 38~08085~, 40~0241~ 42~06750~.'),
  (9070, 11, 9, 11, '(Now Hiram the king of Tyre had furnished Solomon with cedar trees and fir trees, and with gold, according to all his desire,) that then king Solomon gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee.', '[0] 1~02438~ 3~04428~ 5~06865~ 7~05375~ 8~08010~ 10~0730~ 11~06086~ 13~01265~ 14~06086~, 17~02091~, 22~02656~,) 24~0227~ 25~04428~ 26~08010~ 27~05414~ 28~02438~ 29~06242~ 30~05892~ 33~0776~ 35~01551~.'),
  (22145, 28, 4, 3, 'Therefore shall the land mourn, and every one that dwelleth therein shall languish, with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven; yea, the fishes of the sea also shall be taken away.', '3~0776~ 4~056~, 9~03427~ 12~0535~, 15~02416~ 18~07704~, 22~05775~ 24~08064~; 27~01709~ 30~03220~ 35~0622~.'),
  (3808, 4, 5, 11, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (29134, 48, 3, 16, 'Now to Abraham and his seed were the promises made. He saith not, And to seeds, as of many; but as of one, And to thy seed, which is Christ.', '0~1161~ 2~11~ 3~2532~ 4~846~ 5~4690~ 6~4483~ 8~1860~ 9~4483~. 11~3004~ 12~3756~, 13~2532~ 15~4690~, 16~5613~ 17~1909~ 18~4183~; 19~235~ 20~5613~ 21~1909~ 22~1520~, 23~2532~ 25~4675~ 26~4690~, 27~3739~ 28~2076~ 29~5547~.'),
  (19760, 24, 32, 20, 'Which hast set signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, even unto this day, and in Israel, and among other men; and hast made thee a name, as at this day;', '2~07760~ 3~0226~ 5~04159~ 8~0776~ 10~04714~, [11] 14~03117~, 17~03478~, [20] 21~0120~; 24~06213~ 27~08034~, 31~03117~;'),
  (11658, 14, 22, 5, 'He walked also after their counsel, and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramothgilead: and the Syrians smote Joram.', '1~01980~ 5~06098~, 7~03212~ 9~03088~ 11~01121~ 13~0256~ 14~04428~ 16~03478~ 18~04421~ 20~02371~ 21~04428~ 23~0758~ 25~01568~ 26~07433~:* 29~07421~ 30~05221~ 31~03141~.'),
  (7851, 9, 24, 5, 'And it came to pass afterward, that David''s heart smote him, because he had cut off Saul''s skirt.', '5~0310~, 7~01732~ 8~03820~ 9~05221~ 15~03772~ 16~07586~ 17~03671~.'),
  (24551, 41, 9, 2, 'And after six days Jesus taketh with him Peter, and James, and John, and leadeth them up into an high mountain apart by themselves: and he was transfigured before them.', '0~2532~ 1~3326~ 2~1803~ 3~2250~ 4~2424~ 5~3880~ [6 7] 8~4074~, 9~2532~ 10~2385~, 11~2532~ 12~2491~, 13~2532~ 14~399~ 15~846~ 16~399~ 17~1519~ 19~5308~ 20~3735~ 21~2398~ 22~2596~ 23~3441~: 24~2532~ 27~3339~ 28~1715~ 29~846~.'),
  (10045, 12, 18, 13, 'Now in the fourteenth year of king Hezekiah did Sennacherib king of Assyria come up against all the fenced cities of Judah, and took them.', '3~06240~ 4~0702~* 5~08141~ 7~04428~ 8~02396~ 10~05576~ 11~04428~ 13~0804~ 15~05927~ 19~01219~ 20~05892~ 22~03063~, 24~08610~'),
  (11984, 14, 35, 9, 'Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethaneel, his brethren, and Hashabiah and Jeiel and Jozabad, chief of the Levites, gave unto the Levites for passover offerings five thousand small cattle, and five hundred oxen.', '0~03562~ 3~08098~ 5~05417~, 7~0251~, 9~02811~ 11~03273~ 13~03107~, 14~08269~ 17~03881~, 18~07311~ 21~03881~ 24~06453~ 25~02568~ 26~0505~ [27 28] 30~02568~ 31~03967~ 32~01241~.'),
  (19763, 24, 32, 23, 'And they came in, and possessed it; but they obeyed not thy voice, neither walked in thy law; they have done nothing of all that thou commandedst them to do: therefore thou hast caused all this evil to come upon them:', '3~0935~, 5~03423~ 9~08085~ 12~06963~, 14~01980~ 17~08451~; 20~06213~ 26~06680~ 29~06213~: 36~07451~ 38~07122~'),
  (7890, 9, 25, 22, 'So and more also do God unto the enemies of David, if I leave of all that pertain to him by the morning light any that pisseth against the wall.', '0~03541~ 2~03254~ 4~06213~ 5~0430~ 8~0341~ 10~01732~, 13~07604~ [17] 20~05704~ 22~01242~ 23~0216~ 26~08366~ 29~07023~.'),
  (19458, 24, 21, 9, 'He that abideth in this city shall die by the sword, and by the famine, and by the pestilence: but he that goeth out, and falleth to the Chaldeans that besiege you, he shall live, and his life shall be unto him for a prey.', '2~03427~ 5~05892~ 7~04191~ 10~02719~, 14~07458~, 18~01698~: 23~03318~, 25~05307~ 28~03778~ 30~06696~ 34~02421~ 37~05315~ 44~07998~.'),
  (3714, 4, 3, 17, 'And these were the sons of Levi by their names; Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari.', '4~01121~ 6~03878~ 9~08034~; 10~01648~, 12~06955~, 14~04847~.'),
  (28189, 45, 9, 18, 'Therefore hath he mercy on whom he will have mercy, and whom he will he hardeneth.', '0~3767~ 1~686~ 3~1653~ 5~3739~ 7~2309~ [8 9] 10~1161~ 11~3739~ 13~2309~ 15~4645~.'),
  (10424, 13, 4, 31, 'And at Bethmarcaboth, and Hazarsusim, and at Bethbirei, and at Shaaraim. These were their cities unto the reign of David.', '2~01024~, 4~02702~, 7~01011~, 10~08189~. [12] 14~05892~ 17~04427~ 19~01732~.'),
  (3546, 3, 26, 17, 'And I will set my face against you, and ye shall be slain before your enemies: they that hate you shall reign over you; and ye shall flee when none pursueth you.', '3~05414~ 5~06440~ 12~05062~ 13~06440~ 15~0341~: 18~08130~ 21~07287~ 27~05127~ 30~07291~'),
  (5534, 5, 24, 3, 'And if the latter husband hate her, and write her a bill of divorcement, and giveth it in her hand, and sendeth her out of his house; or if the latter husband die, which took her to be his wife;', '[1] 3~0314~ 4~0376~ 5~08130~ 8~03789~ 11~05612~ 13~03748~, 15~05414~ [16] 19~03027~, 21~07971~ 26~01004~; 30~0314~ 31~0376~ 32~04191~, 34~03947~ [36 37] 39~0802~;'),
  (26554, 43, 11, 16, 'Then said Thomas, which is called Didymus, unto his fellowdisciples, Let us also go, that we may die with him.', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ 2~2381~, 3~3588~ 5~3004~ 6~1324~, 9~4827~, 11~71~ 12~2532~ 13~71~, 14~2443~ 15~2249~ 17~599~ 18~3326~ 19~846~.'),
  (19192, 24, 9, 8, 'Their tongue is as an arrow shot out; it speaketh deceit: one speaketh peaceably to his neighbour with his mouth, but in heart he layeth his wait.', '1~03956~ [2 3] 5~02671~ 7~07819~; 9~01696~ 10~04820~: [11] 12~01696~ 13~07965~ 16~07453~ 19~06310~, 22~07130~ 24~07760~ 26~0696~.'),
  (17978, 23, 15, 9, 'For the waters of Dimon shall be full of blood: for I will bring more upon Dimon, lions upon him that escapeth of Moab, and upon the remnant of the land.', '2~04325~ 4~01775~ 7~04390~ 9~01818~: 13~07896~ 14~03254~ 16~01775~, 17~0738~ 21~06413~ 23~04124~, 27~07611~ 30~0127~.'),
  (26229, 43, 5, 4, 'For an angel went down at a certain season into the pool, and troubled the water: whosoever then first after the troubling of the water stepped in was made whole of whatsoever disease he had.', '0~1063~ 2~32~ 4~2597~ 5~2596~ 8~2540~ 9~1722~ 11~2861~, 12~2532~ 13~5015~ 15~5204~: 17~3767~ 18~4413~ 19~3326~ 21~5016~ 24~5204~ 26~1684~ 28~1096~ 29~5199~ 30~3739~ 31~1221~ 32~3553~ 34~2722~.'),
  (13071, 18, 9, 11, 'Lo, he goeth by me, and I see him not: he passeth on also, but I perceive him not.', '2~05674~ 7~07200~ [8] 12~02498~ 16~0995~'),
  (2988, 3, 10, 6, 'And Moses said unto Aaron, and unto Eleazar and unto Ithamar, his sons, Uncover not your heads, neither rend your clothes; lest ye die, and lest wrath come upon all the people: but let your brethren, the whole house of Israel, bewail the burning which the LORD hath kindled.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~0175~, 7~0499~ 10~0385~, 12~01121~, 13~06544~ 16~07218~, 18~06533~ 20~0899~; 23~04191~, 26~07107~ 31~05712~: 35~0251~, 38~01004~ 40~03478~, 41~01058~ 43~08316~ 46~03068~ 48~08313~.'),
  (20693, 26, 12, 4, 'Then shalt thou bring forth thy stuff by day in their sight, as stuff for removing: and thou shalt go forth at even in their sight, as they that go forth into captivity.', '4~03318~ 6~03627~ 8~03119~ 11~05869~, 13~03627~ 15~01473~: 20~03318~ 22~06153~ 25~05869~, 30~04161~ 32~01473~.'),
  (21082, 26, 24, 17, 'Forbear to cry, make no mourning for the dead, bind the tire of thine head upon thee, and put on thy shoes upon thy feet, and cover not thy lips, and eat not the bread of men.', '0~01826~ 2~0602~, 3~06213~ 5~060~ 8~04191~, 9~02280~ 14~06287~ 19~07760~ 21~05275~ 24~07272~, 26~05844~ [28] 29~08222~, 31~0398~ 34~03899~ 36~0582~.'),
  (20088, 24, 47, 6, 'O thou sword of the LORD, how long will it be ere thou be quiet? put up thyself into thy scabbard, rest, and be still.', '0~01945~ 2~02719~ 5~03068~, [8 10] 11~03808~ 14~08252~? 16~0622~ 20~08593~, 21~07280~, 24~01826~.'),
  (25666, 42, 17, 1, 'Then said he unto the disciples, It is impossible but that offences will come: but woe unto him, through whom they come!', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 5~3101~, 7~2076~ 8~418~ 9~3361~ 11~4625~ 13~2064~: 14~1161~ 15~3759~ [16 17] 18~1223~ 19~3739~ 21~2064~!'),
  (28682, 46, 13, 1, 'Though I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, and have not charity, I am become as sounding brass, or a tinkling cymbal.', '&para; 0~1437~ 2~2980~ 5~1100~ 7~444~ 8~2532~ 10~32~, 11~1161~ 12~2192~ 13~3361~ 14~26~, 17~1096~ [18] 19~2278~ 20~5475~, 21~2228~ 23~214~ 24~2950~.'),
  (12631, 16, 11, 34, 'Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat,', '0~02307~, 1~06650~, 2~05041~,'),
  (17144, 20, 25, 22, 'For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the LORD shall reward thee.', '3~02846~ 6~01513~ 9~07218~, 12~03068~ 14~07999~'),
  (21175, 26, 28, 9, 'Wilt thou yet say before him that slayeth thee, I am God? but thou shalt be a man, and no God, in the hand of him that slayeth thee.', '2~0559~ 3~0559~ 4~06440~ 7~02026~ [10] 11~0430~? [14 15] 17~0120~, 20~0410~, 23~03027~ 27~02490~'),
  (733, 1, 27, 2, 'And he said, Behold now, I am old, I know not the day of my death:', '2~0559~, 7~02204~, 9~03045~ 12~03117~ 15~04194~:'),
  (15562, 19, 103, 4, 'Who redeemeth thy life from destruction; who crowneth thee with lovingkindness and tender mercies;', '1~01350~ 3~02416~ 5~07845~; 7~05849~ 10~02617~ 13~07356~;'),
  (4684, 4, 31, 14, 'And Moses was wroth with the officers of the host, with the captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, which came from the battle.', '1~04872~ 3~07107~ 6~06485~ 9~02428~, [10] 12~08269~ 14~0505~, 16~08269~ 18~03967~, 20~0935~ 21~06635~ 23~04421~.'),
  (28109, 45, 7, 2, 'For the woman which hath an husband is bound by the law to her husband so long as he liveth; but if the husband be dead, she is loosed from the law of her husband.', '0~1063~ 2~1135~ 6~5220~ 8~1210~ 11~3551~ [13] 14~435~ 19~2198~; 20~1161~ 21~1437~ 23~435~ 25~599~, 28~2673~ 29~575~ 31~3551~ [33] 34~435~.'),
  (12993, 18, 6, 6, 'Can that which is unsavoury be eaten without salt? or is there any taste in the white of an egg?', '4~08602~ 6~0398~ 8~04417~? 11~03426~ [12] 13~02940~ 16~07388~ 19~02495~?'),
  (6535, 7, 1, 19, 'And the LORD was with Judah; and he drave out the inhabitants of the mountain; but could not drive out the inhabitants of the valley, because they had chariots of iron.', '2~03068~ 5~03063~; 9~03423~ [10 12] 14~02022~; 17~03808~ 19~03423~ 21~03427~ 24~06010~, 28~07393~ 30~01270~.'),
  (8379, 10, 14, 16, 'For the king will hear, to deliver his handmaid out of the hand of the man that would destroy me and my son together out of the inheritance of God.', '2~04428~ 4~08085~, 6~05337~ 8~0519~ 12~03709~ 15~0376~ [16 17] 18~08045~ 22~01121~ 23~03162~ 27~05159~ 29~0430~.'),
  (15271, 19, 84, 3, 'Yea, the sparrow hath found an house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young, even thine altars, O LORD of hosts, my King, and my God.', '2~06833~ 4~04672~ 6~01004~, 9~01866~ 11~07064~ 17~07896~ 19~0667~, [20] 22~04196~, 24~03068~ 26~06635~, 28~04428~, 31~0430~.'),
  (19008, 24, 2, 34, 'Also in thy skirts is found the blood of the souls of the poor innocents: I have not found it by secret search, but upon all these.', '3~03671~ 5~04672~ 7~01818~ 10~05315~ 13~034~ 14~05355~: 18~04672~ 22~04290~,'),
  (29619, 52, 3, 13, 'To the end he may stablish your hearts unblameable in holiness before God, even our Father, at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ with all his saints.', '2~1519~ 5~4741~ 6~5216~ 7~2588~ 8~273~ 9~1722~ 10~42~ 11~1715~ 12~2316~, 13~2532~ 14~2257~ 15~3962~, 16~1722~ 18~3952~ 20~2257~ 21~2962~ 22~2424~ 23~5547~ 24~3326~ 25~3956~ 26~846~ 27~40~.'),
  (11733, 14, 25, 20, 'But Amaziah would not hear; for it came of God, that he might deliver them into the hand of their enemies, because they sought after the gods of Edom.', '1~0558~ 4~08085~; [7] 9~0430~, 13~05414~ 17~03027~ [18 20] 23~01875~ 26~0430~ 28~0123~.'),
  (29064, 47, 13, 5, 'Examine yourselves, whether ye be in the faith; prove your own selves. Know ye not your own selves, how that Jesus Christ is in you, except ye be reprobates?', '0~3985~ 1~1438~, 2~1487~ 4~2075~ 5~1722~ 7~4102~; 8~1381~ 11~1438~ 12~2228~.* 14~1921~ 15~3756~ 18~1438~, 20~3754~ 21~2424~ 22~5547~ 23~2076~ 24~1722~ 25~5213~, 26~1509~ 28~2075~ 29~96~ 30~5100?~*'),
  (6839, 7, 11, 3, 'Then Jephthah fled from his brethren, and dwelt in the land of Tob: and there were gathered vain men to Jephthah, and went out with him.', '1~03316~ 2~01272~ 3~06440~ 5~0251~, 7~03427~ 10~0776~ 12~02897~: 16~03950~ 17~07386~ 18~0582~ 20~03316~, 23~03318~'),
  (845, 1, 30, 11, 'And Leah said, A troop cometh: and she called his name Gad.', '1~03812~ 2~0559~, 4~01409~ 5~0935~: 8~07121~ 10~08034~ 11~01410~.'),
  (14356, 19, 31, 16, 'Make thy face to shine upon thy servant: save me for thy mercies'' sake.', '2~06440~ 4~0215~ 7~05650~: 8~03467~ 12~02617~'),
  (23940, 40, 23, 12, 'And whosoever shall exalt himself shall be abased; and he that shall humble himself shall be exalted.', '0~1161~ 1~3748~ 3~5312~ 4~1438~ 7~5013~; 8~2532~ 9~3748~ 12~5013~ 13~1438~ 16~5312~.'),
  (9358, 11, 18, 9, 'And he said, What have I sinned, that thou wouldest deliver thy servant into the hand of Ahab, to slay me?', '2~0559~, 6~02398~, 10~05414~ 12~05650~ 15~03027~ 17~0256~, 19~04191~'),
  (25097, 42, 4, 22, 'And all bare him witness, and wondered at the gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth. And they said, Is not this Joseph''s son?', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~3140~ 3~846~ 4~3140~, 5~2532~ 6~2296~ 7~1909~ 9~5485~ 10~3056~ 11~3588~ 12~1607~ 14~1537~ 15~846~ 16~4750~. 17~2532~ 19~3004~, 20~2076~ 21~3756~ 22~3778~ 23~2501~ 24~5207~?'),
  (29937, 56, 2, 13, 'Looking for that blessed hope, and the glorious appearing of the great God and our Saviour Jesus Christ;', '1~4327~ 3~3107~ 4~1680~, 5~2532~ 7~1391~ 8~2015~ 11~3173~ 12~2316~ 13~2532~ 14~2257~ 15~4990~ 16~2424~ 17~5547~;'),
  (15224, 19, 80, 17, 'Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man whom thou madest strong for thyself.', '2~03027~ 6~0376~ 10~03225~, 13~01121~ 15~0120~ [16] 19~0553~'),
  (26869, 43, 19, 29, 'Now there was set a vessel full of vinegar: and they filled a sponge with vinegar, and put it upon hyssop, and put it to his mouth.', '0~3767~ 3~2749~ 5~4632~ 6~3324~ 8~3690~: 9~1161~ 11~4130~ 13~4699~ 15~3690~, 16~2532~ [18] 19~4060~ 20~5301~, 22~4374~ [23] 25~846~ 26~4750~.'),
  (12910, 18, 2, 10, 'But he said unto her, Thou speakest as one of the foolish women speaketh. What? shall we receive good at the hand of God, and shall we not receive evil? In all this did not Job sin with his lips.', '2~0559~ 6~01696~ 8~0259~ 12~05036~ 13~01696~. 14~01571~? 17~06901~ 18~02896~ 23~0430~, 28~06901~ 29~07451~? 35~0347~ 36~02398~ 39~08193~.'),
  (29326, 49, 5, 6, 'Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things cometh the wrath of God upon the children of disobedience.', '0~538~ 2~3367~ 3~538~ 4~5209~ 6~2756~ 7~3056~: 8~1063~ 9~1223~ 12~5023~ 13~2064~ 15~3709~ 17~2316~ 18~1909~ 20~5207~ 22~543~.'),
  (3526, 3, 25, 52, 'And if there remain but few years unto the year of jubilee, then he shall count with him, and according unto his years shall he give him again the price of his redemption.', '3~07604~ 5~04592~ 6~08141~ 9~08141~ 11~03104~, 15~02803~ [18] 19~06310~ 22~08141~ 27~07725~ 32~01353~.'),
  (23887, 40, 22, 5, 'But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his farm, another to his merchandise:', '0~1161~ 4~272~ [5] 9~565~, 10~3303~ 11~1519~ 12~2398~ 13~68~, 14~1161~ 15~1519~ 16~846~ 17~1711~:'),
  (23624, 40, 14, 17, 'And they say unto him, We have here but five loaves, and two fishes.', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 6~2192~ 7~5602~ 8~1508~ 9~3756~* 10~4002~ 11~740~, 12~2532~ 13~1417~ 14~2486~.'),
  (27785, 44, 23, 35, 'I will hear thee, said he, when thine accusers are also come. And he commanded him to be kept in Herod''s judgment hall.', '2~1251~ 3~4675~, 5~5346~, 6~3752~ 7~4675~ 8~2725~ 9~3854~ 10~2532~ 11~3854~. 12~5037~ 14~2753~ 15~846~ 18~5442~ 19~1722~ 20~2264~ 22~4232~.'),
  (6711, 7, 7, 10, 'But if thou fear to go down, go thou with Phurah thy servant down to the host:', '3~03373~ 6~03381~, 7~03381~ 10~06513~ 12~05288~ 13~03381~ 16~04264~:'),
  (8117, 10, 3, 29, 'Let it rest on the head of Joab, and on all his father''s house; and let there not fail from the house of Joab one that hath an issue, or that is a leper, or that leaneth on a staff, or that falleth on the sword, or that lacketh bread.', '2~02342~ 5~07218~ 7~03097~, 12~01~ 13~01004~; 18~03772~ 21~01004~ 23~03097~ 28~02100~, 33~06879~, 36~02388~ 39~06418~, 42~05307~ 45~02719~, 48~02638~ 49~03899~.'),
  (14166, 19, 18, 39, 'For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.', '3~0247~ 6~02428~ 9~04421~: 12~03766~ 18~06965~'),
  (16846, 20, 15, 30, 'The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart: and a good report maketh the bones fat.', '&para; 1~03974~ 4~05869~ 5~08055~ 7~03820~: [8] 10~02896~ 11~08052~ 12~01878~ 14~06106~ 15~01878~.'),
  (5692, 5, 29, 7, 'And when ye came unto this place, Sihon the king of Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, came out against us unto battle, and we smote them:', '3~0935~ 6~04725~, 7~05511~ 9~04428~ 11~02809~, 13~05747~ 15~04428~ 17~01316~, 19~03318~ 20~07125~ 23~04421~, 26~05221~'),
  (22082, 27, 11, 37, 'Neither shall he regard the God of his fathers, nor the desire of women, nor regard any god: for he shall magnify himself above all.', '3~0995~ 5~0430~ 8~01~, 11~02532~ 13~0802~, 15~0995~ 17~0433~: 21~01431~'),
  (11835, 14, 29, 35, 'And also the burnt offerings were in abundance, with the fat of the peace offerings, and the drink offerings for every burnt offering. So the service of the house of the LORD was set in order.', '4~05930~ [5] 7~07230~, 10~02459~ 14~08002~, 18~05262~ [20] 22~05930~. 25~05656~ 28~01004~ 31~03068~ 35~03559~.'),
  (639, 1, 24, 44, 'And she say to me, Both drink thou, and I will also draw for thy camels: let the same be the woman whom the LORD hath appointed out for my master''s son.', '2~0559~ 6~08354~ 12~07579~ 15~01581~: [16] [19] 21~0802~ 24~03068~ 27~03198~ 30~0113~ 31~01121~.'),
  (18353, 23, 36, 14, 'Thus saith the king, Let not Hezekiah deceive you: for he shall not be able to deliver you.', '1~0559~ 3~04428~, 6~02396~ 7~05377~ 14~03201~ 16~05337~'),
  (17036, 20, 22, 12, 'The eyes of the LORD preserve knowledge, and he overthroweth the words of the transgressor.', '&para; 1~05869~ 4~03068~ 5~05341~ 6~01847~, 9~05557~ 11~01697~ 14~0898~.'),
  (13840, 18, 38, 38, 'When the dust groweth into hardness, and the clods cleave fast together?', '2~06083~ 3~03332~ 5~04165~, 8~07263~ 11~01692~?'),
  (5187, 5, 9, 24, 'Ye have been rebellious against the LORD from the day that I knew you.', '3~04784~ 6~03068~ 9~03117~ 12~03045~'),
  (27296, 44, 10, 21, 'Then Peter went down to the men which were sent unto him from Cornelius; and said, Behold, I am he whom ye seek: what is the cause wherefore ye are come?', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 3~2597~ 4~4314~ 6~435~ 7~3588~ 9~649~ 10~4314~ 11~846~ 12~575~ 13~2883~; 15~2036~, 16~2400~, 17~1473~ 18~1510~ 20~3739~ 22~2212~: 23~5101~ [24] 26~156~ 27~3739~ 28~1223~ 30~3918~?'),
  (21916, 27, 6, 2, 'And over these three presidents; of whom Daniel was first: that the princes might give accounts unto them, and the king should have no damage.', '1~05924~ 2~04481~ 3~08532~ 4~05632~; 6~04481~ 7~01841~ [8] 9~02298~: 10~0459~ 12~0324~ 13~01934~ 14~03052~ 15~02941~ 20~04430~ 22~01934~ 23~03809~ 24~05142~.'),
  (8033, 10, 1, 4, 'And David said unto him, How went the matter? I pray thee, tell me. And he answered, That the people are fled from the battle, and many of the people also are fallen and dead; and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead also.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 5~04100~ 8~01697~? 12~05046~ 16~0559~, 19~05971~ 21~05127~ 24~04421~, 26~07235~ 29~05971~ 32~05307~ 34~04191~; 36~07586~ 38~03083~ 40~01121~ 42~04191~'),
  (24065, 40, 26, 1, 'And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished all these sayings, he said unto his disciples,', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~1096~, 5~3753~ 6~2424~ 8~5055~ 9~3956~ 10~5128~ 11~3056~, 13~2036~ 15~846~ 16~3101~,'),
  (25394, 42, 10, 19, 'Behold, I give unto you power to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy: and nothing shall by any means hurt you.', '0~2400~, 2~1325~ 4~5213~ 5~1849~ 7~3961~ 8~1883~ 9~3789~ 10~2532~ 11~4651~, 12~2532~ 13~1909~ 14~3956~ 16~1411~ 19~2190~: 20~2532~ 21~3762~ 22~91~ 25~3364~ 26~91~ 27~5209~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (3370, 3, 21, 20, 'Or crookbacked, or a dwarf, or that hath a blemish in his eye, or be scurvy, or scabbed, or hath his stones broken;', '1~01384~, 4~01851~, 9~08400~ 12~05869~, 15~01618~, 17~03217~, 21~0810~ 22~04790~;'),
  (17398, 21, 4, 8, 'There is one alone, and there is not a second; yea, he hath neither child nor brother: yet is there no end of all his labour; neither is his eye satisfied with riches; neither saith he, For whom do I labour, and bereave my soul of good? This is also vanity, yea, it is a sore travail.', '1~03426~ 2~0259~ [3] [5 6] 9~08145~; 14~01121~ 16~0251~: [18 19] 21~07093~ 25~05999~; 29~05869~ 30~07646~ 32~06239~; [34 35] 40~06001~, 42~02637~ 44~05315~ 46~02896~? [48] 50~01892~, [53] 55~07451~ 56~06045~.'),
  (29475, 50, 4, 17, 'Not because I desire a gift: but I desire fruit that may abound to your account.', '0~3756~ 1~3754~ 3~1934~ 5~1390~: 6~235~ 8~1934~ 9~2590~ 12~4121~ 13~1519~ 14~5216~ 15~3056~.'),
  (15208, 19, 80, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Shoshannimeduth, A Psalm of Asaph. Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~07802~, 7~04210~ 9] 9~0623~ 11~0238~, 13~07462~ 15~03478~, 18~05090~ 19~03130~ 22~06629~; 25~03427~ [26] 28~03742~, 30~03313~.'),
  (14512, 19, 38, 13, 'But I, as a deaf man, heard not; and I was as a dumb man that openeth not his mouth.', '4~02795~ [5] 6~08085~ [9 10] 14~0483~ [15] 16~06605~ 19~06310~.'),
  (12417, 16, 6, 7, 'And thou hast also appointed prophets to preach of thee at Jerusalem, saying, There is a king in Judah: and now shall it be reported to the king according to these words. Come now therefore, and let us take counsel together.', '4~05975~ 5~05030~ 7~07121~ 11~03389~, 12~0559~, [13 14] 16~04428~ 18~03063~: 24~08085~ 27~04428~ 31~01697~. 32~03212~ 39~03289~ 40~03162~.'),
  (25573, 42, 14, 7, 'And he put forth a parable to those which were bidden, when he marked how they chose out the chief rooms; saying unto them,', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~3004~ 5~3850~ 6~4314~ 10~2564~, 13~1907~ 14~4459~ 17~1586~ 20~4411~; 21~3004~ 22~4314~ 23~846~,'),
  (17650, 22, 8, 1, 'O that thou wert as my brother, that sucked the breasts of my mother! when I should find thee without, I would kiss thee; yea, I should not be despised.', '&para; 1~05414~ [3] 6~0251~, 8~03243~ 10~07699~ 13~0517~! [14] 17~04672~ 19~02351~, 22~05401~ 29~0936~.'),
  (21231, 26, 30, 18, 'At Tehaphnehes also the day shall be darkened, when I shall break there the yokes of Egypt: and the pomp of her strength shall cease in her: as for her, a cloud shall cover her, and her daughters shall go into captivity.', '1~08471~ 4~03117~ 7~02821~ 11~07665~ 14~04133~ 16~04714~: 19~01347~ 22~05797~ 24~07673~ 26~01931~: 31~06051~ 33~03680~ 37~01323~ 39~03212~ 41~07628~.'),
  (10571, 13, 7, 28, 'And their possessions and habitations were, Bethel and the towns thereof, and eastward Naaran, and westward Gezer, with the towns thereof; Shechem also and the towns thereof, unto Gaza and the towns thereof:', '2~0272~ 4~04186~ [5] 6~01008~ 9~01323~ 12~04217~ 13~05295~, 15~04628~ 16~01507~, 19~01323~ 21~07927~ 25~01323~ 28~05804~ 31~01323~'),
  (2693, 2, 39, 24, 'And they made upon the hems of the robe pomegranates of blue, and purple, and scarlet, and twined linen.', '2~06213~ 5~07757~ 8~04598~ 9~07416~ [10] 11~08504~, 13~0713~, 15~08438~ 16~08144~,* [17] 18~07806~ [19]'),
  (26637, 43, 12, 42, 'Nevertheless among the chief rulers also many believed on him; but because of the Pharisees they did not confess him, lest they should be put out of the synagogue:', '&para; 0~3305~ 1~3676~* 2~1537~ 5~758~ 6~2532~ 7~4183~ 8~4100~ 9~1519~ 10~846~; 11~235~ 12~1223~ 15~5330~ 17~3670~ 18~3756~ 19~3670~ [20] 21~3363~ 24~1096~ 29~656~:'),
  (7924, 9, 26, 12, 'So David took the spear and the cruse of water from Saul''s bolster; and they gat them away, and no man saw it, nor knew it, neither awaked: for they were all asleep; because a deep sleep from the LORD was fallen upon them.', '1~01732~ 2~03947~ 4~02595~ 7~06835~ 9~04325~ 11~07586~ 12~07226~; 17~03212~, 21~07200~ [22] 24~03045~ [25] 27~06974~: [30] 32~03463~; 36~08639~ 39~03068~ 41~05307~'),
  (28396, 46, 1, 17, 'For Christ sent me not to baptize, but to preach the gospel: not with wisdom of words, lest the cross of Christ should be made of none effect.', '&para; 0~1063~ 1~5547~ 2~649~ 3~3165~ 4~3756~ 6~907~, 7~235~ 11~2097~: 12~3756~ 13~1722~ 14~4678~ 16~3056~, 17~3363~ 19~4716~ 21~5547~ 27~2758~.'),
  (15475, 19, 96, 1, 'O sing unto the LORD a new song: sing unto the LORD, all the earth.', '&para; 1~07891~ 4~03068~ 6~02319~ 7~07892~: 8~07891~ 11~03068~, 14~0776~.'),
  (3224, 3, 16, 18, 'And he shall go out unto the altar that is before the LORD, and make an atonement for it; and shall take of the blood of the bullock, and of the blood of the goat, and put it upon the horns of the altar round about.', '4~03318~ 7~04196~ [9] 10~06440~ 12~03068~, 16~03722~ 21~03947~ 24~01818~ 27~06499~, 31~01818~ 34~08163~, 36~05414~ [37] 40~07161~ 43~04196~ 45~05439~.'),
  (3653, 4, 1, 44, 'These are those that were numbered, which Moses and Aaron numbered, and the princes of Israel, being twelve men: each one was for the house of his fathers.', '&para; [1] 5~06485~, 7~04872~ 9~0175~ 10~06485~, 13~05387~ 15~03478~, [16] 17~08147~ 18~06240~* 19~0376~: 20~0376~ 21~0259~ 25~01004~ 28~01~.'),
  (30201, 58, 11, 13, 'These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off, and were persuaded of them, and embraced them, and confessed that they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth.', '0~3778~ 1~3956~ 2~599~ 3~2596~ 4~4102~, 5~3361~ 7~2983~ 9~1860~, 10~235~ 12~1492~ 13~846~ 15~4207~, 16~2532~ 19~3982~ [20] 21~2532~ 22~782~ [23] 24~2532~ 25~3670~ 26~3754~ 28~1526~ 29~3581~ 30~2532~ 31~3927~ 32~1909~ 34~1093~.'),
  (7435, 9, 10, 10, 'And when they came thither to the hill, behold, a company of prophets met him; and the spirit of God came upon him, and he prophesied among them.', '3~0935~ 7~01389~, 10~02256~ 12~05030~ 13~07125~ 17~07307~ 19~0430~ 20~06743~ 25~05012~ 26~08432~'),
  (10254, 12, 25, 24, 'And Gedaliah sware to them, and to their men, and said unto them, Fear not to be the servants of the Chaldees: dwell in the land, and serve the king of Babylon; and it shall be well with you.', '1~01436~ 2~07650~ 8~0582~, 10~0559~ 13~03372~ 18~05650~ 21~03778~: 22~03427~ 25~0776~, 27~05647~ 29~04428~ 31~0894~; 36~03190~'),
  (24669, 41, 11, 18, 'And the scribes and chief priests heard it, and sought how they might destroy him: for they feared him, because all the people was astonished at his doctrine.', '0~2532~ 2~1122~ 3~2532~ 5~749~ 6~191~ [7] 8~2532~ 9~2212~ 10~4459~ 13~622~ 14~846~: 15~1063~ 17~5399~ 18~846~, 19~3754~ 20~3956~ 22~3793~ 24~1605~ 25~1909~ 26~846~ 27~1322~.'),
  (29510, 51, 1, 29, 'Whereunto I also labour, striving according to his working, which worketh in me mightily.', '0~3739~ 1~1519~* 2~2872~ 3~2532~ 4~2872~, 5~75~ 7~2596~ 8~846~ 9~1753~, 10~3588~ 11~1754~ 12~1722~ 13~1698~ 14~1411~ 15~1722~.*'),
  (3757, 4, 4, 9, 'And they shall take a cloth of blue, and cover the candlestick of the light, and his lamps, and his tongs, and his snuffdishes, and all the oil vessels thereof, wherewith they minister unto it:', '3~03947~ 5~0899~ 7~08504~, 9~03680~ 11~04501~ 14~03974~, 17~05216~, 20~04457~, 23~04289~, 27~08081~ 28~03627~ 32~08334~'),
  (13196, 18, 14, 6, 'Turn from him, that he may rest, till he shall accomplish, as an hireling, his day.', '0~08159~ 6~02308~, 10~07521~, 13~07916~, 15~03117~.'),
  (14463, 19, 37, 4, 'Delight thyself also in the LORD; and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart.', '0~06026~ 5~03068~; 9~05414~ 12~04862~ 15~03820~.'),
  (6646, 7, 5, 16, 'Why abodest thou among the sheepfolds, to hear the bleatings of the flocks? For the divisions of Reuben there were great searchings of heart.', '1~03427~ 3~0996~ 5~04942~, 7~08085~ 9~08292~ 12~05739~? 15~06390~ 17~07205~ [18 19] 20~01419~ 21~02714~ 23~03820~.'),
  (22997, 38, 8, 12, 'For the seed shall be prosperous; the vine shall give her fruit, and the ground shall give her increase, and the heavens shall give their dew; and I will cause the remnant of this people to possess all these things.', '2~02233~ [3 4] 5~07965~; 7~01612~ 9~05414~ 11~06529~, 14~0776~ 16~05414~ 18~02981~, 21~08064~ 23~05414~ 25~02919~; 31~07611~ 34~05971~ 36~05157~ [39]'),
  (20324, 25, 1, 5, 'Her adversaries are the chief, her enemies prosper; for the LORD hath afflicted her for the multitude of her transgressions: her children are gone into captivity before the enemy.', '1~06862~ 4~07218~, 6~0341~ 7~07951~; 10~03068~ 12~03013~ 16~07230~ 19~06588~: 21~05768~ 23~01980~ 25~07628~ 26~06440~ 28~06862~.'),
  (29733, 54, 2, 1, 'I exhort therefore, that, first of all, supplications, prayers, intercessions, and giving of thanks, be made for all men;', '&para; 1~3870~ 2~3767~, 4~4412~ 6~3956~, 7~1162~, 8~4335~, 9~1783~, [10] 13~2169~, 15~4160~ 16~5228~ 17~3956~ 18~444~;'),
  (806, 1, 29, 7, 'And he said, Lo, it is yet high day, neither is it time that the cattle should be gathered together: water ye the sheep, and go and feed them.', '2~0559~, 3~02005~, [4 5] 7~01419~ 8~03117~, [10 11] 12~06256~ 15~04735~ 19~0622~: 20~08248~ 23~06629~, 25~03212~ [26] 27~07462~ [28]'),
  (11559, 14, 18, 8, 'And the king of Israel called for one of his officers, and said, Fetch quickly Micaiah the son of Imla.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~07121~ 7~0259~ [8 9] 10~05631~, 12~0559~, 14~04116~ 15~04319~ 17~01121~ 19~03229~.'),
  (24699, 41, 12, 15, 'Shall we give, or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them, Why tempt ye me? bring me a penny, that I may see it.', '2~1325~, 3~2228~ 6~3361~ 7~1325~? 8~1161~ 10~1492~ 11~846~ 12~5272~, 13~2036~ 15~846~, 16~5101~ 18~3985~ 19~3165~? 20~5342~ 21~3427~ 23~1220~, 24~2443~ 27~1492~ [28]'),
  (9761, 12, 8, 26, 'Two and twenty years old was Ahaziah when he began to reign; and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Athaliah, the daughter of Omri king of Israel.', '0~08147~ 2~06242~ 3~08141~ 4~01121~ [5] 6~0274~ 11~04427~; 14~04427~ 15~0259~ 16~08141~ 18~03389~. 21~0517~ 22~08034~ [23] 24~06271~, 26~01323~ 28~06018~ 29~04428~ 31~03478~.'),
  (18312, 23, 33, 24, 'And the inhabitant shall not say, I am sick: the people that dwell therein shall be forgiven their iniquity.', '2~07934~ 5~0559~, 8~02470~: 10~05971~ 12~03427~ [14 15] 16~05375~ [17] 18~05771~.'),
  (20184, 24, 50, 9, 'For, lo, I will raise and cause to come up against Babylon an assembly of great nations from the north country: and they shall set themselves in array against her; from thence she shall be taken: their arrows shall be as of a mighty expert man; none shall return in vain.', '&para; 4~05782~ 9~05927~ 11~0894~ 13~06951~ 15~01419~ 16~01471~ 19~06828~ 20~0776~: 27~06186~ 35~03920~: 37~02671~ [38 39] 43~01368~ 45~07919~ 48~07725~ 50~07387~.'),
  (15060, 19, 74, 3, 'Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations; even all that the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.', '1~07311~ 3~06471~ 6~05331~ 7~04876~; [8] [10] 12~0341~ 15~07489~ 18~06944~.'),
  (27650, 44, 20, 8, 'And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~2425~ 4~2985~ 5~1722~ 8~5253~, 9~3757~ 11~2258~ 13~4863~.'),
  (4776, 4, 33, 10, 'And they removed from Elim, and encamped by the Red sea.', '2~05265~ 4~0362~, 6~02583~ 9~05488~ 10~03220~.'),
  (21091, 26, 24, 26, 'That he that escapeth in that day shall come unto thee, to cause thee to hear it with thine ears?', '[0] 3~06412~ 6~03117~ 8~0935~ [13] 15~02045~ [16] [18] 19~0241~?'),
  (8619, 10, 22, 9, 'There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.', '2~05927~ 4~06227~ 8~0639~, 10~0784~ 14~06310~ 15~0398~: 16~01513~ 18~01197~'),
  (9269, 11, 15, 12, 'And he took away the sodomites out of the land, and removed all the idols that his fathers had made.', '3~05674~ 5~06945~ 9~0776~, 11~05493~ 14~01544~ 17~01~ 19~06213~.'),
  (28772, 46, 15, 38, 'But God giveth it a body as it hath pleased him, and to every seed his own body.', '0~1161~ 1~2316~ 2~1325~ 3~846~ 5~4983~ 6~2531~ 10~2309~, 11~2532~ 13~1538~ 14~4690~ 16~2398~ 17~4983~.'),
  (6150, 6, 12, 14, 'The king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one;', '1~04428~ 3~02767~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~06166~, 9~0259~;'),
  (25385, 42, 10, 10, 'But into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you not, go your ways out into the streets of the same, and say,', '0~1161~ 1~1519~ 2~302~ 3~3739~* 4~4172~ 6~1525~, 7~2532~ 9~1209~ 10~5209~ 11~3361~, 15~1831~ 16~1519~ 18~4113~ 21~846~, 23~2036~,'),
  (11709, 14, 24, 23, 'And it came to pass at the end of the year, that the host of Syria came up against him: and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, and destroyed all the princes of the people from among the people, and sent all the spoil of them unto the king of Damascus.', '7~08622~ 10~08141~, [11] 13~02428~ 15~0758~ 17~05927~ 22~0935~ 24~03063~ 26~03389~, 28~07843~ 31~08269~ 34~05971~ 38~05971~, 40~07971~ 43~07998~ 48~04428~ 50~01834~.'),
  (16360, 19, 146, 10, 'The LORD shall reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the LORD.', '1~03068~ 3~04427~ 5~05769~, [6] 8~0430~, 10~06726~, 12~01755~ 13~01755~. 14~01984~ 17~03050~.'),
  (6426, 6, 21, 38, 'And out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with her suburbs, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Mahanaim with her suburbs,', '4~04294~ 6~01410~, 7~07433~ 9~01568~ 12~04054~, [13 14] 16~05892~ 18~04733~ 21~07523~; 23~04266~ 26~04054~,'),
  (25932, 42, 22, 54, 'Then took they him, and led him, and brought him into the high priest''s house. And Peter followed afar off.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4815~ 3~846~, 5~71~ [6] 7~2532~ 8~1521~ 9~846~ 10~1519~ 13~749~ 14~3624~. 15~1161~ 16~4074~ 17~190~ 19~3113~.'),
  (9154, 11, 11, 38, 'And it shall be, if thou wilt hearken unto all that I command thee, and wilt walk in my ways, and do that is right in my sight, to keep my statutes and my commandments, as David my servant did; that I will be with thee, and build thee a sure house, as I built for David, and will give Israel unto thee.', '7~08085~ 12~06680~ 16~01980~ 19~01870~, 21~06213~ [22 23] 24~03477~ 27~05869~, 29~08104~ 31~02708~ 34~04687~, 36~01732~ 38~05650~ 39~06213~; 47~01129~ 50~0539~ 51~01004~, 54~01129~ 56~01732~, 59~05414~ 60~03478~'),
  (18655, 23, 49, 10, 'They shall not hunger nor thirst; neither shall the heat nor sun smite them: for he that hath mercy on them shall lead them, even by the springs of water shall he guide them.', '3~07456~ 5~06770~; 9~08273~ 11~08121~ 12~05221~ 18~07355~ 22~05090~ 27~04002~ 29~04325~ 32~05095~'),
  (27467, 44, 15, 9, 'And put no difference between us and them, purifying their hearts by faith.', '0~2532~ 1~1252~ 2~3762~ 3~1252~ 4~5037~ 5~3342~* 6~2257~ 7~2532~ 8~846~, 9~2511~ 10~846~ 11~2588~ 13~4102~.'),
  (1645, 2, 5, 8, 'And the tale of the bricks, which they did make heretofore, ye shall lay upon them; ye shall not diminish ought thereof: for they be idle; therefore they cry, saying, Let us go and sacrifice to our God.', '2~04971~ 5~03843~, 9~06213~ 10~08543~ 11~08032~,* 14~07760~ 20~01639~ [21] [25] 26~07503~; 29~06817~, 30~0559~, 33~03212~ [34] 35~02076~ 38~0430~.'),
  (25215, 42, 7, 8, 'For I also am a man set under authority, having under me soldiers, and I say unto one, Go, and he goeth; and to another, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth it.', '0~1063~ 1~1473~ 2~2532~ 3~1510~ 5~444~ 6~5021~ 7~5259~ 8~1849~, 9~2192~ 10~5259~ 11~1683~ 12~4757~, 13~2532~ 15~3004~ 17~5129~, 18~4198~, 19~2532~ 21~4198~; 22~2532~ 24~243~, 25~2064~, 26~2532~ 28~2064~; 29~2532~ 31~3450~ 32~1401~, 33~4160~ 34~5124~, 35~2532~ 37~4160~ [38]'),
  (13005, 18, 6, 18, 'The paths of their way are turned aside; they go to nothing, and perish.', '1~0734~ 4~01870~ 7~03943~; 9~05927~ 11~08414~, 13~06~.'),
  (6630, 7, 4, 24, 'And the hand of the children of Israel prospered, and prevailed against Jabin the king of Canaan, until they had destroyed Jabin king of Canaan.', '2~03027~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~ 8~03212~ 9~01980~,* 11~07186~ 13~02985~ 15~04428~ 17~03667~, 21~03772~ 22~02985~ 23~04428~ 25~03667~.'),
  (28897, 47, 5, 4, 'For we that are in this tabernacle do groan, being burdened: not for that we would be unclothed, but clothed upon, that mortality might be swallowed up of life.', '0~1063~ 1~2532~ 3~5607~ 4~1722~ [5] 6~4636~ 8~4727~, 10~916~: 11~3756~ 13~1894~ 15~2309~ 17~1562~, 18~235~ 20~1902~, 21~2443~ 22~2349~ 26~2666~ 27~5259~ 28~2222~.'),
  (20802, 26, 16, 31, 'In that thou buildest thine eminent place in the head of every way, and makest thine high place in every street; and hast not been as an harlot, in that thou scornest hire;', '3~01129~ 6~01354~ 9~07218~ 12~01870~, 14~06213~ 17~07413~ 20~07339~; 27~02181~, 31~07046~ 32~0868~;'),
  (1869, 2, 12, 48, 'And when a stranger shall sojourn with thee, and will keep the passover to the LORD, let all his males be circumcised, and then let him come near and keep it; and he shall be as one that is born in the land: for no uncircumcised person shall eat thereof.', '3~01616~ 5~01481~ 10~06213~ 12~06453~ 15~03068~, 19~02145~ 21~04135~, 27~07126~ 29~06213~ 39~0249~ 42~0776~: 46~06189~ 48~0398~'),
  (18661, 23, 49, 16, 'Behold, I have graven thee upon the palms of my hands; thy walls are continually before me.', '3~02710~ [9] 10~03709~; 12~02346~ [13] 14~08548~'),
  (22957, 38, 6, 1, 'And I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and, behold, there came four chariots out from between two mountains; and the mountains were mountains of brass.', '&para; 2~07725~, 5~05375~ 7~05869~, 9~07200~, 13~03318~ 14~0702~ 15~04818~ 16~03318~ 19~08147~ 20~02022~; 23~02022~ [24] 25~02022~ 27~05178~.'),
  (27867, 44, 26, 28, 'Then Agrippa said unto Paul, Almost thou persuadest me to be a Christian.', '0~1161~ 1~67~ 2~5346~ 3~4314~ 4~3972~, 5~3641~ 6~1722~ 7~3982~ 8~3165~ 10~1096~ 12~5546~.'),
  (21361, 26, 35, 8, 'And I will fill his mountains with his slain men: in thy hills, and in thy valleys, and in all thy rivers, shall they fall that are slain with the sword.', '3~04390~ 5~02022~ 8~02491~ [9] 12~01389~, 16~01516~, 21~0650~, 24~05307~ 27~02491~ 30~02719~.'),
  (21462, 26, 39, 5, 'Thou shalt fall upon the open field: for I have spoken it, saith the Lord GOD.', '2~05307~ 5~06440~ 6~07704~: 10~01696~ [11] 12~05002~ 14~0136~ 15~03069~.'),
  (17664, 23, 1, 1, 'The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.', '&para; 1~02377~ 3~03470~ 5~01121~ 7~0531~, 10~02372~ 12~03063~ 14~03389~ 17~03117~ 19~05818~, 20~03147~, 21~0271~, [22] 23~03169~, 24~04428~ 26~03063~.'),
  (22985, 38, 7, 14, 'But I scattered them with a whirlwind among all the nations whom they knew not. Thus the land was desolate after them, that no man passed through nor returned: for they laid the pleasant land desolate.', '6~05590~ 10~01471~ 13~03045~ 17~0776~ 19~08074~ 20~0310~ 26~05674~ 28~07725~: 31~07760~ 33~02532~ 34~0776~ 35~08047~.'),
  (22740, 34, 3, 19, 'There is no healing of thy bruise; thy wound is grievous: all that hear the bruit of thee shall clap the hands over thee: for upon whom hath not thy wickedness passed continually?', '[0 1] 3~03545~ 6~07667~; 8~04347~ 10~02470~: 13~08085~ 15~08088~ 19~08628~ 21~03709~ 30~07451~ 31~05674~ 32~08548~?'),
  (19569, 24, 25, 26, 'And all the kings of the north, far and near, one with another, and all the kingdoms of the world, which are upon the face of the earth: and the king of Sheshach shall drink after them.', '3~04428~ 6~06828~, 7~07350~ 9~07138~, 10~0376~ 12~0251~, 16~04467~ 19~0776~, [21] 24~06440~ 27~0127~: 30~04428~ 32~08347~ 34~08354~ 35~0310~'),
  (3125, 3, 14, 9, 'But it shall be on the seventh day, that he shall shave all his hair off his head and his beard and his eyebrows, even all his hair he shall shave off: and he shall wash his clothes, also he shall wash his flesh in water, and he shall be clean.', '6~07637~ 7~03117~, 11~01548~ 14~08181~ 17~07218~ 20~02206~ 23~05869~ 24~01354~,* 28~08181~ 31~01548~ 36~03526~ 38~0899~, 42~07364~ 44~01320~ 46~04325~, 51~02891~.'),
  (29484, 51, 1, 3, 'We give thanks to God and the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying always for you,', '&para; 2~2168~ 4~2316~ 5~2532~ 7~3962~ 9~2257~ 10~2962~ 11~2424~ 12~5547~, 13~4336~ 14~3842~ 15~4012~ 16~5216~,'),
  (938, 1, 32, 6, 'And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, We came to thy brother Esau, and also he cometh to meet thee, and four hundred men with him.', '2~04397~ 3~07725~ 5~03290~, 6~0559~, 8~0935~ 11~0251~ 12~06215~, 16~01980~ 19~07125~, 22~03967~ 23~0376~'),
  (11178, 13, 29, 6, 'Then the chief of the fathers and princes of the tribes of Israel, and the captains of thousands and of hundreds, with the rulers of the king''s work, offered willingly,', '2~08269~ 5~01~ 7~08269~ 10~07626~ 12~03478~, 15~08269~ 17~0505~ 20~03967~, 23~08269~ 26~04428~ 27~04399~, 29~05068~,'),
  (9679, 12, 5, 24, 'And when he came to the tower, he took them from their hand, and bestowed them in the house: and he let the men go, and they departed.', '3~0935~ 6~06076~, 8~03947~ [9] 12~03027~, 14~06485~ [15] 18~01004~: 23~0582~ 24~07971~, 27~03212~.'),
  (24353, 41, 4, 20, 'And these are they which are sown on good ground; such as hear the word, and receive it, and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some an hundred.', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~1526~ 6~4687~ 7~1909~ 8~2570~ 9~1093~; 11~3748~ 12~191~ 14~3056~, 15~2532~ 16~3858~ [17] 18~2532~ 21~2592~, 22~1520~ 23~5144~, 24~1520~ 25~2532~* 26~1835~, 27~2532~ 28~1520~ 30~1540~.'),
  (7683, 9, 17, 58, 'And Saul said to him, Whose son art thou, thou young man? And David answered, I am the son of thy servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~ 6~01121~ [7] [9] 11~05288~? 13~01732~ 14~0559~, [16] 18~01121~ 21~05650~ 22~03448~ 24~01022~.'),
  (10252, 12, 25, 22, 'And as for the people that remained in the land of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had left, even over them he made Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, ruler.', '&para; [1 2] 4~05971~ 6~07604~ 9~0776~ 11~03063~, 13~05019~ 14~04428~ 16~0894~ 18~07604~, 24~01436~ 26~01121~ 28~0296~, 30~01121~ 32~08227~, 33~06485~.'),
  (13397, 18, 21, 33, 'The clods of the valley shall be sweet unto him, and every man shall draw after him, as there are innumerable before him.', '1~07263~ 4~05158~ 7~04985~ 12~0120~ 14~04900~ 15~0310~ [18 19] 20~04557~ 21~06440~'),
  (6098, 6, 10, 28, 'And that day Joshua took Makkedah, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and the king thereof he utterly destroyed, them, and all the souls that were therein; he let none remain: and he did to the king of Makkedah as he did unto the king of Jericho.', '&para; 2~03117~ 3~03091~ 4~03920~ 5~04719~, 7~05221~ 11~06310~ 14~02719~, 17~04428~ 21~02763~, 26~05315~ [28] 31~07604~ 33~08300~: 36~06213~ 39~04428~ 41~04719~ 44~06213~ 47~04428~ 49~03405~.'),
  (8092, 10, 3, 4, 'And the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; and the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;', '2~07243~, 3~0138~ 5~01121~ 7~02294~; 10~02549~, 11~08203~ 13~01121~ 15~037~;'),
  (6744, 7, 8, 18, 'Then said he unto Zebah and Zalmunna, What manner of men were they whom ye slew at Tabor? And they answered, As thou art, so were they; each one resembled the children of a king.', '&para; 1~0559~ 4~02078~ 6~06759~, 7~0375~ 10~0582~ [11 12] 15~02026~ 17~08396~? 20~0559~, 22~03644~ [23] [25] 28~0259~ 29~08389~ 31~01121~ 34~04428~.'),
  (29639, 52, 5, 2, 'For yourselves know perfectly that the day of the Lord so cometh as a thief in the night.', '0~1063~ 1~846~ 2~1492~ 3~199~ 4~3754~ 6~2250~ 9~2962~ 10~3779~ 11~2064~ 12~5613~ 14~2812~ 15~1722~ 17~3571~.'),
  (4980, 5, 2, 36, 'From Aroer, which is by the brink of the river of Arnon, and from the city that is by the river, even unto Gilead, there was not one city too strong for us: the LORD our God delivered all unto us:', '1~06177~, [3] 6~08193~ 9~05158~ 11~0769~, [13] 15~05892~ [17] 20~05158~, 23~01568~, 28~07151~ 30~07682~ 34~03068~ 36~0430~ 37~05414~ 40~06440~:'),
  (28767, 46, 15, 33, 'Be not deceived: evil communications corrupt good manners.', '0~4105~ 1~3361~ 2~4105~: 3~2556~ 4~3657~ 5~5351~ 6~5543~ 7~2239~.'),
  (1135, 1, 38, 11, 'Then said Judah to Tamar his daughter in law, Remain a widow at thy father''s house, till Shelah my son be grown: for he said, Lest peradventure he die also, as his brethren did. And Tamar went and dwelt in her father''s house.', '1~0559~ 2~03063~ 4~08559~ 8~03618~, 9~03427~ 11~0490~ 14~01~ 15~01004~, 17~07956~ 19~01121~ 21~01431~: 24~0559~, 28~04191~ 32~0251~ [33] 35~08559~ 36~03212~ 38~03427~ 41~01~ 42~01004~.'),
  (13232, 18, 15, 20, 'The wicked man travaileth with pain all his days, and the number of years is hidden to the oppressor.', '1~07563~ 3~02342~ [7] 8~03117~, 11~04557~ 13~08141~ 15~06845~ 18~06184~.'),
  (6716, 7, 7, 15, 'And it was so, when Gideon heard the telling of the dream, and the interpretation thereof, that he worshipped, and returned into the host of Israel, and said, Arise; for the LORD hath delivered into your hand the host of Midian.', '[3] 5~01439~ 6~08085~ 8~04557~ 11~02472~, 14~07667~ 18~07812~, 20~07725~ 23~04264~ 25~03478~, 27~0559~, 28~06965~; 31~03068~ 33~05414~ 36~03027~ 38~04264~ 40~04080~.'),
  (6782, 7, 9, 21, 'And Jotham ran away, and fled, and went to Beer, and dwelt there, for fear of Abimelech his brother.', '1~03147~ 3~01272~, 5~05127~, 7~03212~ 9~0876~, 11~03427~ 14~06440~ 16~040~ 18~0251~.'),
  (8946, 11, 7, 4, 'And there were windows in three rows, and light was against light in three ranks.', '[1 2] 3~08261~ [4] 5~07969~ 6~02905~, 8~04237~ [9] 11~04237~ [12] 13~07969~ 14~06471~.'),
  (1940, 2, 15, 15, 'Then the dukes of Edom shall be amazed; the mighty men of Moab, trembling shall take hold upon them; all the inhabitants of Canaan shall melt away.', '0~0227~ 2~0441~ 4~0123~ 7~0926~; 10~0352~ 12~04124~, 13~07461~ 16~0270~ 21~03427~ 23~03667~ 26~04127~.'),
  (19082, 24, 5, 15, 'Lo, I will bring a nation upon you from far, O house of Israel, saith the LORD: it is a mighty nation, it is an ancient nation, a nation whose language thou knowest not, neither understandest what they say.', '3~0935~ 5~01471~ 9~04801~, 11~01004~ 13~03478~, 14~05002~ 16~03068~: [18] 20~0386~ 21~01471~, [23] 25~05769~ 26~01471~, 28~01471~ 30~03956~ 32~03045~ 35~08085~ 38~01696~.'),
  (24095, 40, 26, 31, 'Then saith Jesus unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock shall be scattered abroad.', '&para; 0~5119~ 1~3004~ 2~2424~ 4~846~, 5~3956~ 6~5210~ 9~4624~ 10~1722~ 12~1698~ 13~1722~* 14~5026~ 15~3571~: 16~1063~ 19~1125~, 22~3960~ 24~4166~, 25~2532~ 27~4263~ 30~4167~ 34~1287~.'),
  (7059, 7, 19, 28, 'And he said unto her, Up, and let us be going. But none answered. Then the man took her up upon an ass, and the man rose up, and gat him unto his place.', '2~0559~ 5~06965~, 10~03212~. 13~06030~. 16~0376~ 17~03947~ [19] 22~02543~, 25~0376~ 27~06965~, 29~03212~ 33~04725~.'),
  (14528, 19, 39, 7, 'And now, Lord, what wait I for? my hope is in thee.', '&para; 2~0136~, 4~06960~ 8~08431~ [9]'),
  (19140, 24, 7, 12, 'But go ye now unto my place which was in Shiloh, where I set my name at the first, and see what I did to it for the wickedness of my people Israel.', '1~03212~ 6~04725~ [8] 10~07887~, 13~07931~ 15~08034~ 18~07223~, 20~07200~ 23~06213~ 26~06440~ 28~07451~ 31~05971~ 32~03478~.'),
  (14673, 19, 49, 16, 'Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;', '3~03372~ 5~0376~ 8~06238~, 11~03519~ 14~01004~ 16~07235~;'),
  (28486, 46, 6, 3, 'Know ye not that we shall judge angels? how much more things that pertain to this life?', '1~1492~ 2~3756~ 3~3754~ 6~2919~ 7~32~? 10~1065~ 11~3386~ 16~982~?'),
  (7839, 9, 23, 22, 'Go, I pray you, prepare yet, and know and see his place where his haunt is, and who hath seen him there: for it is told me that he dealeth very subtly.', '0~03212~, 4~03559~ 7~03045~ 9~07200~ 11~04725~ 14~07272~ [16] 19~07200~ 25~0559~ [27] 30~06191~ 31~06191~.'),
  (20569, 26, 5, 14, 'Moreover I will make thee waste, and a reproach among the nations that are round about thee, in the sight of all that pass by.', '3~05414~ 5~02723~, 8~02781~ 11~01471~ [13] 15~05439~ 19~05869~ 24~05674~.'),
  (9637, 12, 4, 26, 'Run now, I pray thee, to meet her, and say unto her, Is it well with thee? is it well with thy husband? is it well with the child? And she answered, It is well.', '0~07323~ 6~07125~ 9~0559~ [12 13] 14~07965~ [17 18] 19~07965~ 22~0376~? [23 24] 25~07965~ 28~03206~? 31~0559~, [32 33] 34~07965~.'),
  (17985, 23, 16, 7, 'Therefore shall Moab howl for Moab, every one shall howl: for the foundations of Kirhareseth shall ye mourn; surely they are stricken.', '2~04124~ 3~03213~ 5~04124~, 9~03213~: 12~0808~ 14~07025~ 17~01897~; [19 20] 21~05218~.'),
  (22197, 28, 7, 10, 'And the pride of Israel testifieth to his face: and they do not return to the LORD their God, nor seek him for all this.', '2~01347~ 4~03478~ 5~06030~ 8~06440~: 13~07725~ 16~03068~ 18~0430~, 20~01245~');
