VALUES
  (25776, 42, 19, 31, 'And if any man ask you, Why do ye loose him? thus shall ye say unto him, Because the Lord hath need of him.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~5100~ 4~2065~ 5~5209~, 6~1302~ 9~3089~ [10] 11~3779~ 14~2046~ 16~846~, 17~3754~ 19~2962~ 20~2192~ 21~5532~ 23~846~.'),
  (30147, 58, 9, 26, 'For then must he often have suffered since the foundation of the world: but now once in the end of the world hath he appeared to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself.', '1~1893~ 2~1163~ 3~846~ 4~4178~ 6~3958~ 7~575~ 9~2602~ 12~2889~: 13~1161~ 14~3568~ 15~530~ 16~1909~ 18~4930~ 21~165~ 24~5319~ 25~1519~ 27~115~ 28~266~ 29~1223~ 31~2378~ 33~846~.'),
  (9669, 12, 5, 14, 'Then went he down, and dipped himself seven times in Jordan, according to the saying of the man of God: and his flesh came again like unto the flesh of a little child, and he was clean.', '3~03381~, 5~02881~ 7~07651~ 8~06471~ 10~03383~, 14~01697~ 17~0376~ 19~0430~: 22~01320~ 24~07725~ 28~01320~ 31~06996~ 32~05288~, 36~02891~.'),
  (16770, 20, 13, 14, 'The law of the wise is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.', '&para; 1~08451~ 4~02450~ [5] 7~04726~ 9~02416~, 11~05493~ 14~04170~ 16~04194~.'),
  (5620, 5, 28, 3, 'Blessed shalt thou be in the city, and blessed shalt thou be in the field.', '0~01288~ [1] [3] 6~05892~, 8~01288~ [9] [11] 14~07704~.'),
  (280, 1, 11, 11, 'And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxad five hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.', '1~08035~ 2~02421~ 3~0310~ 5~03205~ 6~0775~ 7~02568~ 8~03967~ 9~08141~, 11~03205~ 12~01121~ 14~01323~.'),
  (13023, 18, 7, 6, 'My days are swifter than a weaver''s shuttle, and are spent without hope.', '1~03117~ 3~07043~ 7~0708~, 10~03615~ 11~0657~ 12~08615~.'),
  (1733, 2, 8, 18, 'And the magicians did so with their enchantments to bring forth lice, but they could not: so there were lice upon man, and upon beast.', '2~02748~ 3~06213~ 7~03909~ 10~03318~ 11~03654~, 14~03201~ 19~03654~ 21~0120~, 24~0929~.'),
  (13371, 18, 21, 7, 'Wherefore do the wicked live, become old, yea, are mighty in power?', '&para; 3~07563~ 4~02421~, 6~06275~, 9~01396~ 11~02428~?'),
  (23532, 40, 12, 33, 'Either make the tree good, and his fruit good; or else make the tree corrupt, and his fruit corrupt: for the tree is known by his fruit.', '0~2228~ 1~4160~ 3~1186~ 4~2570~, 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~2590~ 8~2570~; 10~2228~ 11~4160~ 13~1186~ 14~4550~, 15~2532~ 16~846~ 17~2590~ 18~4550~: 19~1063~ 21~1186~ 23~1097~ 24~1537~ [25] 26~2590~.'),
  (5941, 6, 5, 1, 'And it came to pass, when all the kings of the Amorites, which were on the side of Jordan westward, and all the kings of the Canaanites, which were by the sea, heard that the LORD had dried up the waters of Jordan from before the children of Israel, until we were passed over, that their heart melted, neither was there spirit in them any more, because of the children of Israel.', '&para; 8~04428~ 11~0567~, [13] 16~05676~ 18~03383~ 19~03220~, 23~04428~ 26~03669~, [28] 31~03220~, 32~08085~ 35~03068~ 38~03001~ 40~04325~ 42~03383~ 44~06440~ 46~01121~ 48~03478~, 53~05674~, 56~03824~ 57~04549~, 61~07307~ 66~06440~ 69~01121~ 71~03478~.'),
  (4442, 4, 23, 21, 'He hath not beheld iniquity in Jacob, neither hath he seen perverseness in Israel: the LORD his God is with him, and the shout of a king is among them.', '3~05027~ 4~0205~ 6~03290~, 10~07200~ 11~05999~ 13~03478~: 15~03068~ 17~0430~ [18] 23~08643~ 26~04428~ [27]'),
  (14838, 19, 62, 2, 'He only is my rock and my salvation; he is my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.', '[2] 4~06697~ 7~03444~; [8 9] 11~04869~; 16~07227~ 17~04131~.'),
  (15432, 19, 92, 12, 'The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.', '1~06662~ 3~06524~ 7~08558~: 10~07685~ 13~0730~ 15~03844~.'),
  (9762, 12, 8, 27, 'And he walked in the way of the house of Ahab, and did evil in the sight of the LORD, as did the house of Ahab: for he was the son in law of the house of Ahab.', '2~03212~ 5~01870~ 8~01004~ 10~0256~, 12~06213~ 13~07451~ 16~05869~ 19~03068~, [21] 23~01004~ 25~0256~: [28] 32~02860~ 35~01004~ 37~0256~.'),
  (21673, 26, 46, 9, 'But when the people of the land shall come before the LORD in the solemn feasts, he that entereth in by the way of the north gate to worship shall go out by the way of the south gate; and he that entereth by the way of the south gate shall go forth by the way of the north gate: he shall not return by the way of the gate whereby he came in, but shall go forth over against it.', '3~05971~ 6~0776~ 8~0935~ 9~06440~ 11~03068~ 15~04150~, 18~0935~ 22~01870~ 25~06828~ 26~08179~ 28~07812~ 31~03318~ 34~01870~ 37~05045~ 38~08179~; 42~0935~ 45~01870~ 48~05045~ 49~08179~ 52~03318~ 55~01870~ 58~06828~ 59~08179~: 63~07725~ 66~01870~ 69~08179~ 73~0935~, 77~03318~ 79~05226~'),
  (30322, 59, 2, 13, 'For he shall have judgment without mercy, that hath shewed no mercy; and mercy rejoiceth against judgment.', '0~1063~ 4~2920~ 6~448~, 9~4160~ 10~3361~ 11~1656~; 12~2532~ 13~1656~ 15~2620~ 16~2920~.'),
  (12462, 16, 7, 33, 'The men of the other Nebo, fifty and two.', '1~0582~ 4~0312~ 5~05015~, 6~02572~ 8~08147~.'),
  (6949, 7, 15, 13, 'And they spake unto him, saying, No; but we will bind thee fast, and deliver thee into their hand: but surely we will not kill thee. And they bound him with two new cords, and brought him up from the rock.', '2~0559~ 5~0559~, 10~0631~ 12~0631~, 14~05414~ 18~03027~: 20~04191~ 24~04191~ 28~0631~ 31~08147~ 32~02319~ 33~05688~, 37~05927~ 40~05553~.'),
  (5353, 5, 16, 5, 'Thou mayest not sacrifice the passover within any of thy gates, which the LORD thy God giveth thee:', '1~03201~ 3~02076~ 5~06453~ 7~0259~ 10~08179~, 13~03068~ 15~0430~ 16~05414~'),
  (23913, 40, 22, 31, 'But as touching the resurrection of the dead, have ye not read that which was spoken unto you by God, saying,', '0~1161~ 2~4012~ 4~386~ 7~3498~, 9~314~ 10~3756~ 11~314~ 13~3588~ 15~4483~ 17~5213~ 18~5259~ 19~2316~, 20~3004~,'),
  (1348, 1, 44, 19, 'My lord asked his servants, saying, Have ye a father, or a brother?', '1~0113~ 2~07592~ 4~05650~, 5~0559~, 6~03426~ 9~01~, 12~0251~?'),
  (21123, 26, 26, 14, 'And I will make thee like the top of a rock: thou shalt be a place to spread nets upon; thou shalt be built no more: for I the LORD have spoken it, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~05414~ 7~06706~ 10~05553~: [14 15] 17~04894~ 18~02764~ 19~04894~; 23~01129~ 29~03068~ 31~01696~ [32] 33~05002~ 35~0136~ 36~03069~.'),
  (8651, 10, 22, 41, 'Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies, that I might destroy them that hate me.', '3~05414~ 6~06203~ 9~0341~, 13~06789~ 16~08130~'),
  (11082, 13, 25, 28, 'The one and twentieth to Hothir, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~0259~ 3~06242~ 5~01956~, [6] 8~01121~, 11~0251~, [12] 13~06240~ 14~08147~:*'),
  (30157, 58, 10, 8, 'Above when he said, Sacrifice and offering and burnt offerings and offering for sin thou wouldest not, neither hadst pleasure therein; which are offered by the law;', '0~511~ 3~3004~ 4~3754~,* 5~2378~ 6~2532~ 7~4376~ 8~2532~ 10~3646~ 11~2532~ [12] 13~4012~ 14~266~ 16~2309~ 17~3756~, 18~3761~ 20~2106~ [21] 22~3748~ 24~4374~ 25~2596~ 27~3551~;'),
  (924, 1, 31, 47, 'And Laban called it Jegarsahadutha: but Jacob called it Galeed.', '1~03837~ 2~07121~ 4~03026~: 6~03290~ 7~07121~ 9~01567~.'),
  (8890, 11, 5, 4, 'But now the LORD my God hath given me rest on every side, so that there is neither adversary nor evil occurrent.', '3~03068~ 5~0430~ 9~05117~ 12~05439~, [13 16] 18~07854~ 20~07451~ 21~06294~.'),
  (12436, 16, 7, 7, 'Who came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah. The number, I say, of the men of the people of Israel was this;', '1~0935~ 3~02216~, 4~03442~, 5~05166~, 6~05838~, 7~07485~, 8~05167~, 9~04782~, 10~01114~, 11~04559~, 12~0902~, 13~05149~, 14~01196~. 16~04557~, [17 18] 21~0582~ 24~05971~ 26~03478~ [27 28]'),
  (17451, 21, 7, 13, 'Consider the work of God: for who can make that straight, which he hath made crooked?', '0~07200~ 2~04639~ 4~0430~: 7~03201~ [9] 10~08626~, 15~05791~?'),
  (18109, 23, 24, 5, 'The earth also is defiled under the inhabitants thereof; because they have transgressed the laws, changed the ordinance, broken the everlasting covenant.', '1~0776~ 4~02610~ 7~03427~ 12~05674~ 14~08451~, 15~02498~ 17~02706~, 18~06565~ 20~05769~ 21~01285~.'),
  (26382, 43, 7, 39, '(But this spake he of the Spirit, which they that believe on him should receive: for the Holy Ghost was not yet given; because that Jesus was not yet glorified.)', '0~1161~* 2~5124~ 4~2036~ 5~4012~ 7~4151~, 8~3739~ 11~4100~ 12~1519~ 13~846~ 14~3195~ 15~2983~: 16~1063~ 18~40~ 19~4151~ 20~2258~ 22~3768~ [23] 24~3754~ 26~2424~ 27~1392~ 29~3764~ 30~1392~.)'),
  (29915, 56, 1, 7, 'For a bishop must be blameless, as the steward of God; not selfwilled, not soon angry, not given to wine, no striker, not given to filthy lucre;', '0~1063~ 2~1985~ 3~1163~ 4~1511~ 5~410~, 6~5613~ 8~3623~ 10~2316~; 11~3361~ 12~829~, 13~3361~ 15~3711~, 16~3361~ 19~3943~, 20~3361~ 21~4131~, 22~3361~ 26~146~;'),
  (20739, 26, 13, 22, 'Because with lies ye have made the heart of the righteous sad, whom I have not made sad; and strengthened the hands of the wicked, that he should not return from his wicked way, by promising him life:', '2~08267~ 7~03820~ 10~06662~ 11~03512~, 17~03510~; 19~02388~ 21~03027~ 24~07451~, 29~07725~ 32~07563~ 33~01870~, 37~02421~:'),
  (17641, 22, 7, 5, 'Thine head upon thee is like Carmel, and the hair of thine head like purple; the king is held in the galleries.', '1~07218~ [4] 6~03760~, 9~01803~ 12~07218~ 14~0713~; 16~04428~ [17] 18~0631~ 21~07298~.'),
  (8688, 10, 23, 27, 'Abiezer the Anethothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite,', '0~044~ 2~06069~, 3~04012~ 5~02843~,'),
  (1747, 2, 8, 32, 'And Pharaoh hardened his heart at this time also, neither would he let the people go.', '1~06547~ 2~03513~ 4~03820~ 7~06471~ 14~05971~ 15~07971~.'),
  (2248, 2, 26, 8, 'The length of one curtain shall be thirty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four cubits: and the eleven curtains shall be all of one measure.', '1~0753~ 3~0259~ 4~03407~ [5 6] 7~07970~ 8~0520~, 11~07341~ 13~0259~ 14~03407~ 15~0702~ 16~0520~: 19~06240~ 20~06249~* 21~03407~ [22 24] 26~0259~ 27~04060~.'),
  (2398, 2, 30, 11, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (26302, 43, 6, 30, 'They said therefore unto him, What sign shewest thou then, that we may see, and believe thee? what dost thou work?', '1~2036~ 2~3767~ 4~846~, 5~5101~ 6~4592~ 7~4160~ 8~4771~ 9~3767~, 10~2443~ 13~1492~, 14~2532~ 15~4100~ 16~4671~? 17~5101~ 20~2038~?'),
  (5216, 5, 11, 2, 'And know ye this day: for I speak not with your children which have not known, and which have not seen the chastisement of the LORD your God, his greatness, his mighty hand, and his stretched out arm,', '1~03045~ 4~03117~: [6 7] 11~01121~ 15~03045~, 20~07200~ 22~04148~ 25~03068~ 27~0430~, 29~01433~, 31~02389~ 32~03027~, 36~05186~ 37~02220~,'),
  (4955, 5, 2, 11, 'Which also were accounted giants, as the Anakims; but the Moabites call them Emims.', '0~01992~ 3~02803~ 4~07497~, 7~06062~; 10~04125~ 11~07121~ 13~0368~.'),
  (13122, 18, 11, 5, 'But oh that God would speak, and open his lips against thee;', '0~0199~ 2~05414~ 3~0433~ 5~01696~, 7~06605~ 9~08193~'),
  (3576, 3, 27, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (18815, 23, 59, 6, 'Their webs shall not become garments, neither shall they cover themselves with their works: their works are works of iniquity, and the act of violence is in their hands.', '1~06980~ 5~0899~, 9~03680~ 13~04639~: 15~04639~ [16] 17~04639~ 19~0205~, 22~06467~ 24~02555~ [25] 28~03709~.'),
  (8275, 10, 11, 9, 'But Uriah slept at the door of the king''s house with all the servants of his lord, and went not down to his house.', '1~0223~ 2~07901~ 5~06607~ 8~04428~ 9~01004~ 13~05650~ 16~0113~, 20~03381~ 23~01004~.'),
  (8960, 11, 7, 18, 'And he made the pillars, and two rows round about upon the one network, to cover the chapiters that were upon the top, with pomegranates: and so did he for the other chapiter.', '2~06213~ 4~05982~, 6~08147~ 7~02905~ 9~05439~ 12~0259~ 13~07639~, 15~03680~ 17~03805~ [19] 22~07218~, 24~07416~: 27~06213~ 31~08145~ 32~03805~.'),
  (1296, 1, 43, 1, 'And the famine was sore in the land.', '&para; 2~07458~ [3] 4~03515~ 7~0776~.'),
  (975, 1, 33, 10, 'And Jacob said, Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found grace in thy sight, then receive my present at my hand: for therefore I have seen thy face, as though I had seen the face of God, and thou wast pleased with me.', '1~03290~ 2~0559~, 11~04672~ 12~02580~ 15~05869~, 17~03947~ 19~04503~ 22~03027~: 27~07200~ 29~06440~, 34~07200~ 36~06440~ 38~0430~, 44~07521~.'),
  (24216, 40, 28, 11, 'Now when they were going, behold, some of the watch came into the city, and shewed unto the chief priests all the things that were done.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~4198~, 5~2400~, 6~5100~ 9~2892~ 10~2064~ 11~1519~ 13~4172~, 15~518~ 19~749~ 22~537~ 25~1096~.'),
  (7861, 9, 24, 15, 'The LORD therefore be judge, and judge between me and thee, and see, and plead my cause, and deliver me out of thine hand.', '1~03068~ 4~01781~, 6~08199~ 12~07200~, 14~07378~ 16~07379~, 18~08199~ 23~03027~.'),
  (14370, 19, 32, 6, 'For this shall every one that is godly pray unto thee in a time when thou mayest be found: surely in the floods of great waters they shall not come nigh unto him.', '7~02623~ 8~06419~ 13~06256~ 18~04672~: 22~07858~ 24~07227~ 25~04325~ 30~05060~'),
  (8218, 10, 8, 2, 'And he smote Moab, and measured them with a line, casting them down to the ground; even with two lines measured he to put to death, and with one full line to keep alive. And so the Moabites became David''s servants, and brought gifts.', '2~05221~ 3~04124~, 5~04058~ 9~02256~, 12~07901~ 15~0776~; 18~08147~ 19~02256~ 20~04058~ 25~04191~, 29~04393~ 30~02256~ 33~02421~. [35] 37~04124~ 39~01732~ 40~05650~, [41] 42~05375~ 43~04503~.'),
  (22486, 30, 7, 13, 'But prophesy not again any more at Bethel: for it is the king''s chapel, and it is the king''s court.', '1~05012~ 3~03254~ 7~01008~: [10] 12~04428~ 13~04720~, [16] 18~04467~ 19~01004~.'),
  (5193, 5, 10, 1, 'At that time the LORD said unto me, Hew thee two tables of stone like unto the first, and come up unto me into the mount, and make thee an ark of wood.', '&para; 2~06256~ 4~03068~ 5~0559~ 8~06458~ 10~08147~ 11~03871~ 13~068~ 17~07223~, 20~05927~ 25~02022~, 27~06213~ 30~0727~ 32~06086~.'),
  (26664, 43, 13, 19, 'Now I tell you before it come, that, when it is come to pass, ye may believe that I am he.', '0~737~ 1~575~ 2~3004~ 3~5213~ 4~4253~ 6~1096~, 7~2443~, 8~3752~ 13~1096~, 16~4100~ 17~3754~ 18~1473~ 19~1510~ [20]'),
  (3307, 3, 19, 21, 'And he shall bring his trespass offering unto the LORD, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, even a ram for a trespass offering.', '3~0935~ 6~0817~ 9~03068~, 12~06607~ 15~0168~ 18~04150~, [19] 21~0352~ 25~0817~.'),
  (13016, 18, 6, 29, 'Return, I pray you, let it not be iniquity; yea, return again, my righteousness is in it.', '0~07725~, 8~05766~; 11~07725~, 13~06664~ [14]'),
  (28046, 45, 4, 8, 'Blessed is the man to whom the Lord will not impute sin.', '0~3107~ [1] 3~435~ 5~3739~ 7~2962~ 8~3049~ 9~3364~ 10~3049~ 11~266~.'),
  (19164, 24, 8, 2, 'And they shall spread them before the sun, and the moon, and all the host of heaven, whom they have loved, and whom they have served, and after whom they have walked, and whom they have sought, and whom they have worshipped: they shall not be gathered, nor be buried; they shall be for dung upon the face of the earth.', '3~07849~ 7~08121~, 10~03394~, 14~06635~ 16~08064~, 20~0157~, 25~05647~, 27~0310~ 31~01980~, 36~01875~, 41~07812~: 46~0622~, 49~06912~; 54~01828~ 57~06440~ 60~0127~.'),
  (10023, 12, 17, 32, 'So they feared the LORD, and made unto themselves of the lowest of them priests of the high places, which sacrificed for them in the houses of the high places.', '2~03373~ 4~03068~, 6~06213~ 11~07098~ 14~03548~ 18~01116~, 20~06213~ 25~01004~ 29~01116~.'),
  (24184, 40, 27, 45, 'Now from the sixth hour there was darkness over all the land unto the ninth hour.', '0~1161~ 1~575~ 3~1623~ 4~5610~ 6~1096~ 7~4655~ 8~1909~ 9~3956~ 11~1093~ 12~2193~ 14~1766~ 15~5610~.'),
  (13044, 18, 8, 6, 'If thou wert pure and upright; surely now he would awake for thee, and make the habitation of thy righteousness prosperous.', '[2] 3~02134~ 5~03477~; 10~05782~ 16~05116~ 19~06664~ 20~07999~.'),
  (19832, 24, 34, 22, 'Behold, I will command, saith the LORD, and cause them to return to this city; and they shall fight against it, and take it, and burn it with fire: and I will make the cities of Judah a desolation without an inhabitant.', '3~06680~, 4~05002~ 6~03068~, 11~07725~ 14~05892~; 18~03898~ 22~03920~ 25~08313~ 28~0784~: 32~05414~ 34~05892~ 36~03063~ 38~08077~ 41~03427~.'),
  (9864, 12, 12, 6, 'But it was so, that in the three and twentieth year of king Jehoash the priests had not repaired the breaches of the house.', '[3 4] 7~08141~ 8~07969~ 9~06242~ 10~08141~ 12~04428~ 13~03060~ 15~03548~ 18~02388~ 20~0919~ 23~01004~.'),
  (9112, 11, 10, 25, 'And they brought every man his present, vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and garments, and armour, and spices, horses, and mules, a rate year by year.', '2~0935~ 4~0376~ 6~04503~, 7~03627~ 9~03701~, 11~03627~ 13~02091~, 15~08008~, 17~05402~, 19~01314~, 20~05483~, 22~06505~, 24~01697~ 25~08141~ 27~08141~.'),
  (13251, 18, 16, 4, 'I also could speak as ye do: if your soul were in my soul''s stead, I could heap up words against you, and shake mine head at you.', '3~01696~ [6] 7~03863~ 9~05315~ 10~03426~ 13~05315~ 18~02266~ 19~04405~ 23~05128~ 25~07218~ 26~01119~'),
  (19649, 24, 29, 5, 'Build ye houses, and dwell in them; and plant gardens, and eat the fruit of them;', '0~01129~ 2~01004~, 4~03427~ [5 6] 8~05193~ 9~01593~, 11~0398~ 13~06529~'),
  (4738, 4, 32, 14, 'And, behold, ye are risen up in your fathers'' stead, an increase of sinful men, to augment yet the fierce anger of the LORD toward Israel.', '5~06965~ 8~01~ 11~08635~ 13~02400~ 14~0582~, 16~05595~ 19~02740~ 20~0639~ 23~03068~ 25~03478~.'),
  (7543, 9, 14, 28, 'Then answered one of the people, and said, Thy father straitly charged the people with an oath, saying, Cursed be the man that eateth any food this day. And the people were faint.', '1~06030~ 2~0376~ 5~05971~, 7~0559~, 9~01~ 10~07650~ 11~07650~ 13~05971~ 16~07650~, 17~0559~, 18~0779~ [19] 21~0376~ 23~0398~ [24] 25~03899~ 27~03117~. 30~05971~ 32~05774~.'),
  (13515, 18, 28, 2, 'Iron is taken out of the earth, and brass is molten out of the stone.', '0~01270~ 2~03947~ 6~06083~, 8~05154~ [9] 10~06694~ [11 12] 14~068~.'),
  (23219, 40, 3, 17, 'And lo a voice from heaven, saying, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.', '0~2532~ 1~2400~ 3~5456~ 4~1537~ 5~3772~, 6~3004~, 7~3778~ 8~2076~ 9~3450~ 10~27~ 11~5207~, 12~1722~ 13~3739~ 17~2106~.'),
  (30063, 58, 6, 3, 'And this will we do, if God permit.', '0~2532~ 1~5124~ 4~4160~, 5~4007~ 6~1437~* 7~2316~ 8~2010~.'),
  (19345, 24, 15, 21, 'And I will deliver thee out of the hand of the wicked, and I will redeem thee out of the hand of the terrible.', '3~05337~ 8~03027~ 11~07451~, 15~06299~ 20~03709~ 23~06184~.'),
  (14211, 19, 21, 11, 'For they intended evil against thee: they imagined a mischievous device, which they are not able to perform.', '2~05186~ 3~07451~ 7~02803~ 10~04209~, [11] 15~03201~ [16 17]'),
  (22582, 32, 4, 5, 'So Jonah went out of the city, and sat on the east side of the city, and there made him a booth, and sat under it in the shadow, till he might see what would become of the city.', '&para; 1~03124~ 3~03318~ 6~05892~, 8~03427~ 12~06924~ 15~05892~, 18~06213~ 21~05521~, 23~03427~ 28~06738~, 32~07200~ 38~05892~.'),
  (5231, 5, 11, 17, 'And then the LORD''S wrath be kindled against you, and he shut up the heaven, that there be no rain, and that the land yield not her fruit; and lest ye perish quickly from off the good land which the LORD giveth you.', '[1] 3~03068~ 4~0639~ 6~02734~ 12~06113~ 14~08064~, 19~04306~, 23~0127~ 24~05414~ 27~02981~; [29] 31~06~ 32~04120~ 36~02896~ 37~0776~ 40~03068~ 41~05414~'),
  (25379, 42, 10, 4, 'Carry neither purse, nor scrip, nor shoes: and salute no man by the way.', '0~941~ 1~3361~ 2~905~, 3~3361~ 4~4082~, 5~3366~ 6~5266~: 7~2532~ 8~782~ 10~3367~ 11~2596~ 13~3598~.'),
  (5147, 5, 8, 4, 'Thy raiment waxed not old upon thee, neither did thy foot swell, these forty years.', '1~08071~ 4~01086~ 10~07272~ 11~01216~, 13~0705~ 14~08141~.'),
  (9265, 11, 15, 8, 'And Abijam slept with his fathers; and they buried him in the city of David: and Asa his son reigned in his stead.', '1~038~ 2~07901~ 5~01~; 8~06912~ 12~05892~ 14~01732~: 16~0609~ 18~01121~ 19~04427~'),
  (17331, 21, 1, 7, 'All the rivers run into the sea; yet the sea is not full; unto the place from whence the rivers come, thither they return again.', '2~05158~ 3~01980~ 6~03220~; 9~03220~ [10] 12~04392~; 15~04725~ 19~05158~ 20~01980~, 23~07725~ 24~03212~.'),
  (9410, 11, 19, 15, 'And the LORD said unto him, Go, return on thy way to the wilderness of Damascus: and when thou comest, anoint Hazael to be king over Syria:', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~03212~, 7~07725~ 10~01870~ 13~04057~ 15~01834~: 19~0935~, 20~04886~ 21~02371~ [22 23] 24~04428~ 26~0758~:'),
  (16714, 20, 11, 17, 'The merciful man doeth good to his own soul: but he that is cruel troubleth his own flesh.', '&para; 1~02617~ 2~0376~ 4~01580~ 8~05315~: [10 12] 13~0394~ 14~05916~ 17~07607~.'),
  (29735, 54, 2, 3, 'For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Saviour;', '0~1063~ 1~5124~ [2] 3~2570~ 4~2532~ 5~587~ 8~1799~ 10~2316~ 11~2257~ 12~4990~;'),
  (23308, 40, 6, 16, 'Moreover when ye fast, be not, as the hypocrites, of a sad countenance: for they disfigure their faces, that they may appear unto men to fast. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3752~ 3~3522~, 4~1096~ 5~3361~, 6~5618~ 8~5273~, 12~4659~: 13~1063~ 15~853~ 16~846~ 17~4383~, 18~3704~ 21~5316~ 23~444~ 25~3522~. 26~281~ 28~3004~ 30~5213~ 31~3754~,* 33~568~ 34~846~ 35~3408~.'),
  (4143, 4, 14, 30, 'Doubtless ye shall not come into the land, concerning which I sware to make you dwell therein, save Caleb the son of Jephunneh, and Joshua the son of Nun.', '3~0518~ 4~0935~ 7~0776~, [8] 11~05375~ 12~03027~* 16~07931~ 19~03612~ 21~01121~ 23~03312~, 25~03091~ 27~01121~ 29~05126~.'),
  (13231, 18, 15, 19, 'Unto whom alone the earth was given, and no stranger passed among them.', '4~0776~ 6~05414~, 9~02114~ 10~05674~ 11~08432~'),
  (24958, 42, 1, 53, 'He hath filled the hungry with good things; and the rich he hath sent empty away.', '2~1705~ 4~3983~ 7~18~; 8~2532~ 10~4147~ 13~1821~ 14~2756~ 15~1821~.'),
  (20133, 24, 48, 44, 'He that fleeth from the fear shall fall into the pit; and he that getteth up out of the pit shall be taken in the snare: for I will bring upon it, even upon Moab, the year of their visitation, saith the LORD.', '2~05127~ 3~06440~ 5~06343~ 7~05307~ 10~06354~; 15~05927~ 19~06354~ 22~03920~ 25~06341~: 29~0935~ [32] 34~04124~, 36~08141~ 39~06486~, 40~05002~ 42~03068~.'),
  (6867, 7, 11, 31, 'Then it shall be, that whatsoever cometh forth of the doors of my house to meet me, when I return in peace from the children of Ammon, shall surely be the LORD''S, and I will offer it up for a burnt offering.', '5~03318~ 7~03318~ 10~01817~ 13~01004~ 15~07125~ 19~07725~ 21~07965~ 24~01121~ 26~05983~, 31~03068~, 37~05927~ 41~05930~.'),
  (15010, 19, 72, 1, 'A Psalm for Solomon. Give the king thy judgments, O God, and thy righteousness unto the king''s son.', '&para; [0 1] 3] 3~08010~ 4~05414~ 6~04428~ 8~04941~, 10~0430~, 13~06666~ 16~04428~ 17~01121~.'),
  (4537, 4, 26, 42, 'These are the sons of Dan after their families: of Shuham, the family of the Shuhamites. These are the families of Dan after their families.', '[1] 3~01121~ 5~01835~ 8~04940~: 10~07748~, 12~04940~ 15~07749~. [17] 19~04940~ 21~01835~ 24~04940~.'),
  (20855, 26, 17, 21, 'And all his fugitives with all his bands shall fall by the sword, and they that remain shall be scattered toward all winds: and ye shall know that I the LORD have spoken it.', '3~04015~ 7~0102~ 9~05307~ 12~02719~, 16~07604~ 19~06566~ 22~07307~: 26~03045~ 30~03068~ 32~01696~ [33]'),
  (24430, 41, 6, 13, 'And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick, and healed them.', '0~2532~ 3~1544~ 4~4183~ 5~1140~, 6~2532~ 7~218~ 9~1637~ 10~4183~ 13~732~, 14~2532~ 15~2323~ [16]'),
  (13525, 18, 28, 12, 'But where shall wisdom be found? and where is the place of understanding?', '1~0370~ 3~02451~ 5~04672~? [8] 10~04725~ 12~0998~?'),
  (13818, 18, 38, 16, 'Hast thou entered into the springs of the sea? or hast thou walked in the search of the depth?', '2~0935~ 5~05033~ 8~03220~? 12~01980~ 15~02714~ 18~08415~?'),
  (15227, 19, 81, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Gittith, A Psalm of Asaph. Sing aloud unto God our strength: make a joyful noise unto the God of Jacob.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~01665~, [6 7] 9] 9~0623~ 11~07442~ 13~0430~ 15~05797~: 19~07321~ 22~0430~ 24~03290~.'),
  (147, 1, 6, 9, 'These are the generations of Noah: Noah was a just man and perfect in his generations, and Noah walked with God.', '[1] 3~08435~ 5~05146~: 6~05146~ 9~06662~ 10~0376~ [11] 12~08549~ 15~01755~, [16] 17~05146~ 18~01980~ 20~0430~.'),
  (24489, 41, 7, 15, 'There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can defile him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that defile the man.', '1~2076~ 2~3762~ 4~1855~ 6~444~, 7~3739~ 8~1531~ 9~1519~ 10~846~ 11~1410~ 12~2840~ 13~846~: 14~235~ 18~1607~ 20~575~ 21~846~, 22~1565~ 24~2076~ 26~2840~ 28~444~.'),
  (2312, 2, 28, 14, 'And two chains of pure gold at the ends; of wreathen work shalt thou make them, and fasten the wreathen chains to the ouches.', '1~08147~ 2~08333~ [3] 4~02889~ 5~02091~ 8~04020~; [9] 10~05688~ 11~04639~ 14~06213~ 17~05414~ 19~05688~ 20~08333~ 23~04865~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (29967, 57, 1, 13, 'Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:', '0~3739~ 1~1473~ 2~1014~ 4~2722~ 5~4314~ 6~1683~, 7~2443~ 9~4675~ 10~5228~ 14~1247~ 16~3427~ 17~1722~ 19~1199~ 22~2098~:'),
  (9959, 12, 15, 26, 'And the rest of the acts of Pekahiah, and all that he did, behold, they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel.', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~06494~, 12~06213~, [15] 16~03789~ 19~05612~ 22~03117~ 23~01697~ 25~04428~ 27~03478~.'),
  (13266, 18, 16, 19, 'Also now, behold, my witness is in heaven, and my record is on high.', '4~05707~ [5] 7~08064~, 10~07717~ [11] 13~04791~.'),
  (5554, 5, 25, 1, 'If there be a controversy between men, and they come unto judgment, that the judges may judge them; then they shall justify the righteous, and condemn the wicked.', '&para; 4~07379~ 6~0582~, 9~05066~ 11~04941~, [13 14] 16~08199~ 21~06663~ 23~06662~, 25~07561~ 27~07563~.'),
  (9306, 11, 16, 15, 'In the twenty and seventh year of Asa king of Judah did Zimri reign seven days in Tirzah. And the people were encamped against Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines.', '&para; 2~08141~ 3~06242~ 4~07651~ 5~08141~ 7~0609~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~ 12~02174~ 13~04427~ 14~07651~ 15~03117~ 17~08656~. 20~05971~ [21] 22~02583~ 24~01405~, [26] 29~06430~.'),
  (5750, 5, 31, 16, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Behold, thou shalt sleep with thy fathers; and this people will rise up, and go a whoring after the gods of the strangers of the land, whither they go to be among them, and will forsake me, and break my covenant which I have made with them.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 9~07901~ 12~01~; 15~05971~ 18~06965~, 22~02181~ 23~0310~ 25~0430~ 28~05236~ 31~0776~, 34~0935~ [35 36] 37~07130~ 41~05800~ 44~06565~ 46~01285~ 50~03772~'),
  (18539, 23, 43, 25, 'I, even I, am he that blotteth out thy transgressions for mine own sake, and will not remember thy sins.', '[1] [3] 7~04229~ 9~06588~ 17~02142~ 19~02403~.'),
  (3434, 3, 23, 27, 'Also on the tenth day of this seventh month there shall be a day of atonement: it shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall afflict your souls, and offer an offering made by fire unto the LORD.', '0~0389~ 3~06218~ [4] 7~07637~ 8~02320~ [9 11] 13~03117~ 15~03725~: 20~06944~ 21~04744~ 27~06031~ 29~05315~, 31~07126~ 36~0801~ 39~03068~.'),
  (19821, 24, 34, 11, 'But afterward they turned, and caused the servants and the handmaids, whom they had let go free, to return, and brought them into subjection for servants and for handmaids.', '1~0310~ 3~07725~, 7~05650~ 10~08198~, 15~07971~ 16~02670~, 18~07725~, 23~03533~ 25~05650~ 28~08198~.'),
  (10763, 13, 12, 35, 'And of the Danites expert in war twenty and eight thousand and six hundred.', '3~01839~ 4~06186~ 6~04421~ 7~06242~ 9~08083~ 10~0505~ 12~08337~ 13~03967~.'),
  (21829, 27, 3, 13, 'Then Nebuchadnezzar in his rage and fury commanded to bring Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego. Then they brought these men before the king.', '0~0116~ 1~05020~ [3] 4~07266~ 6~02528~ 7~0560~ 9~0858~ 10~07715~, 11~04336~, 13~05665~. 14~0116~ 16~0858~ 17~0479~ 18~01400~ 19~06925~ 21~04430~.'),
  (17738, 23, 3, 22, 'The changeable suits of apparel, and the mantles, and the wimples, and the crisping pins,', '4~04254~, 7~04595~, 10~04304~, 14~02754~,'),
  (29804, 54, 5, 25, 'Likewise also the good works of some are manifest beforehand; and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.', '0~5615~ 1~2532~ 3~2570~ 4~2041~ [5 6] 7~2076~ 9~4271~; 10~2532~ 13~2192~ 14~247~ 15~1410~ 16~3756~* 18~2928~.'),
  (18147, 23, 26, 8, 'Yea, in the way of thy judgments, O LORD, have we waited for thee; the desire of our soul is to thy name, and to the remembrance of thee.', '3~0734~ 6~04941~, 8~03068~, 11~06960~ 15~08378~ [17] 18~05315~ [19] 22~08034~, 26~02143~'),
  (3815, 4, 5, 18, 'And the priest shall set the woman before the LORD, and uncover the woman''s head, and put the offering of memorial in her hands, which is the jealousy offering: and the priest shall have in his hand the bitter water that causeth the curse:', '2~03548~ 4~05975~ 6~0802~ 7~06440~ 9~03068~, 11~06544~ 13~0802~ 14~07218~, 16~05414~ 18~04503~ 20~02146~ 23~03709~, [25] 27~07068~ 28~04503~: 31~03548~ 36~03027~ 38~04751~ 39~04325~ 43~0779~:'),
  (21427, 26, 37, 21, 'And say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will take the children of Israel from among the heathen, whither they be gone, and will gather them on every side, and bring them into their own land:', '1~01696~ 5~0559~ 7~0136~ 8~03069~; 12~03947~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 18~0996~ 20~01471~, 24~01980~, 27~06908~ 31~05439~, 33~0935~ 38~0127~:'),
  (15390, 19, 90, 3, 'Thou turnest man to destruction; and sayest, Return, ye children of men.', '1~07725~ 2~0582~ 4~01793~; 6~0559~, 7~07725~, 9~01121~ 11~0120~.'),
  (17256, 20, 29, 23, 'A man''s pride shall bring him low: but honour shall uphold the humble in spirit.', '&para; 1~0120~ 2~01346~ 6~08213~: 8~03519~ 10~08551~ 12~08217~ 14~07307~.'),
  (8155, 10, 5, 16, 'And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphalet.', '1~0476~, 3~0450~, 5~0467~.'),
  (21948, 27, 7, 6, 'After this I beheld, and lo another, like a leopard, which had upon the back of it four wings of a fowl; the beast had also four heads; and dominion was given to it.', '0~0870~ 1~01836~ 3~01934~ 4~02370~,* 6~0718~ 7~0317~, 10~05245~, 13~05922~ 15~01355~ 18~0703~ 19~01611~ 22~05776~; 24~02423~ 27~0703~ 28~07217~; 30~07985~ 32~03052~'),
  (25484, 42, 12, 12, 'For the Holy Ghost shall teach you in the same hour what ye ought to say.', '0~1063~ 2~40~ 3~4151~ 5~1321~ 6~5209~ 7~1722~ 9~846~ 10~5610~ 11~3739~ 13~1163~ 15~2036~.'),
  (6352, 6, 19, 24, 'And the fifth lot came out for the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families.', '&para; 2~02549~ 3~01486~ 5~03318~ 8~04294~ 11~01121~ 13~0836~ 17~04940~.'),
  (19366, 24, 16, 21, 'Therefore, behold, I will this once cause them to know, I will cause them to know mine hand and my might; and they shall know that my name is The LORD.', '5~06471~ 9~03045~, 15~03045~ 17~03027~ 20~01369~; 24~03045~ 27~08034~ [28] 30~03068~.'),
  (7156, 8, 1, 22, 'So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabitess, her daughter in law, with her, which returned out of the country of Moab: and they came to Bethlehem in the beginning of barley harvest.', '1~05281~ 2~07725~, 4~07327~ 6~04125~, 10~03618~, 14~07725~ 18~07704~ 20~04124~: 23~0935~ 25~01035~ 28~08462~ 30~08184~ 31~07105~.'),
  (15749, 19, 107, 41, 'Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh him families like a flock.', '4~034~ 6~07682~ 8~06040~, 10~07760~ [11] 12~04940~ 15~06629~.'),
  (3547, 3, 26, 18, 'And if ye will not yet for all this hearken unto me, then I will punish you seven times more for your sins.', '5~05704~ 9~08085~ 15~03256~ 18~07651~ 19~03254~ 22~02403~.'),
  (24582, 41, 9, 33, 'And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them, What was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way?', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~1519~ 4~2584~: 5~2532~ 6~1096~ 7~1722~ 9~3614~ 11~1905~ 12~846~, 13~5101~ 18~1260~ 19~4314~ 20~1438~ 21~1722~ 23~3598~?'),
  (12270, 15, 10, 9, 'Then all the men of Judah and Benjamin gathered themselves together unto Jerusalem within three days. It was the ninth month, on the twentieth day of the month; and all the people sat in the street of the house of God, trembling because of this matter, and for the great rain.', '3~0582~ 5~03063~ 7~01144~ 10~06908~ 12~03389~ 14~07969~ 15~03117~. [17] 19~08671~ 20~02320~, 23~06242~ [24] 27~02320~; 31~05971~ 32~03427~ 35~07339~ 38~01004~ 40~0430~, 41~07460~ [44] 45~01697~, 50~01653~.'),
  (2086, 2, 21, 4, 'If his master have given him a wife, and she have born him sons or daughters; the wife and her children shall be her master''s, and he shall go out by himself.', '2~0113~ 4~05414~ 7~0802~, 11~03205~ 13~01121~ 15~01323~; 17~0802~ 20~03206~ 24~0113~, 29~03318~ 31~01610~.'),
  (24245, 41, 1, 20, 'And straightway he called them: and they left their father Zebedee in the ship with the hired servants, and went after him.', '0~2532~ 1~2112~ 3~2564~ 4~846~: 5~2532~ 7~863~ 8~846~ 9~3962~ 10~2199~ 11~1722~ 13~4143~ 14~3326~ 17~3411~, 19~565~ 20~3694~ 21~846~.'),
  (7540, 9, 14, 25, 'And all they of the land came to a wood; and there was honey upon the ground.', '[2 3] 5~0776~ 6~0935~ 9~03293~; 13~01706~ 14~06440~ 16~07704~.'),
  (28821, 47, 1, 5, 'For as the sufferings of Christ abound in us, so our consolation also aboundeth by Christ.', '0~3754~ 1~2531~ 3~3804~ 5~5547~ 6~4052~ 7~1519~ 8~2248~, 9~3779~ 10~2257~ 11~3874~ 12~2532~ 13~4052~ 14~1223~ 15~5547~.'),
  (4033, 4, 11, 4, 'And the mixed multitude that was among them fell a lusting: and the children of Israel also wept again, and said, Who shall give us flesh to eat?', '&para; 3~0628~ [5] 6~07130~ 10~0183~ 11~08378~:* 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 18~01058~ 19~07725~, 21~0559~, 26~01320~ 28~0398~?'),
  (19648, 24, 29, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel, unto all that are carried away captives, whom I have caused to be carried away from Jerusalem unto Babylon;', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 16~01473~, 24~01540~ 26~03389~ 28~0894~;'),
  (19771, 24, 32, 31, 'For this city hath been to me as a provocation of mine anger and of my fury from the day that they built it even unto this day; that I should remove it from before my face,', '2~05892~ [7] 12~0639~ 16~02534~ 19~03117~ 22~01129~ 27~03117~; 31~05493~ 36~06440~,'),
  (3200, 3, 15, 27, 'And whosoever toucheth those things shall be unclean, and shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even.', '2~05060~ 7~02930~, 10~03526~ 12~0899~, 14~07364~ [15] 17~04325~, 20~02930~ 23~06153~.'),
  (18944, 23, 66, 13, 'As one whom his mother comforteth, so will I comfort you; and ye shall be comforted in Jerusalem.', '1~0376~ 4~0517~ 5~05162~, 9~05162~ 15~05162~ 17~03389~.'),
  (20321, 25, 1, 2, 'She weepeth sore in the night, and her tears are on her cheeks: among all her lovers she hath none to comfort her: all her friends have dealt treacherously with her, they are become her enemies.', '1~01058~ 2~01058~ 5~03915~, 8~01832~ [9] 12~03895~: 16~0157~ 21~05162~ [22] 25~07453~ 28~0898~ 35~0341~.'),
  (28824, 47, 1, 8, 'For we would not, brethren, have you ignorant of our trouble which came to us in Asia, that we were pressed out of measure, above strength, insomuch that we despaired even of life:', '0~1063~ 2~2309~ 3~3756~, 4~80~, 5~50~ 6~5209~ 7~50~ 8~5228~ 9~2257~ 10~2347~ 11~3588~ 12~1096~ 14~2254~ 15~1722~ 16~773~, 17~3754~ 20~2596~ 21~916~ 23~5236~, 24~5228~ 25~1411~, 26~5620~ 28~2248~ 29~1820~ 30~2532~ 32~2198~:'),
  (7054, 7, 19, 23, 'And the man, the master of the house, went out unto them, and said unto them, Nay, my brethren, nay, I pray you, do not so wickedly; seeing that this man is come into mine house, do not this folly.', '2~0376~, 4~01167~ 7~01004~, 9~03318~ 13~0559~ 16~0408~, 18~0251~, [19] [25] 26~07489~; 27~0310~ 30~0376~ 32~0935~ 35~01004~, 36~06213~ 39~05039~.'),
  (13428, 18, 22, 30, 'He shall deliver the island of the innocent: and it is delivered by the pureness of thine hands.', '2~04422~ 4~0336~ 7~05355~: 11~04422~ 14~01252~ 17~03709~.'),
  (1270, 1, 42, 13, 'And they said, Thy servants are twelve brethren, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan; and, behold, the youngest is this day with our father, and one is not.', '2~0559~, 4~05650~ [5] 6~06240~ 7~08147~* 8~0251~, 10~01121~ 12~0259~ 13~0376~ 16~0776~ 18~03667~; 22~06996~ [23] 25~03117~ 28~01~, 30~0259~ [31]'),
  (27508, 44, 16, 9, 'And a vision appeared to Paul in the night; There stood a man of Macedonia, and prayed him, saying, Come over into Macedonia, and help us.', '0~2532~ 2~3705~ 3~3700~ 5~3972~ 6~1223~ 8~3571~; 10~2258~ 11~2476~* 13~435~ 14~5100~ 15~3110~, 17~3870~ 18~846~ 19~2532~,* 20~3004~, 22~1224~ 23~1519~ 24~3109~, 26~997~ 27~2254~.'),
  (4139, 4, 14, 26, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~0175~, 9~0559~,'),
  (17537, 21, 12, 5, 'Also when they shall be afraid of that which is high, and fears shall be in the way, and the almond tree shall flourish, and the grasshopper shall be a burden, and desire shall fail: because man goeth to his long home, and the mourners go about the streets:', '[1] 5~03372~ [7 9] 10~01364~, 12~02849~ [13 14] 17~01870~, 21~08247~ 23~05006~, 26~02284~ 30~05445~, 32~035~ 34~06565~: 36~0120~ 37~01980~ 40~05769~ 41~01004~, 44~05594~ 46~05437~ 48~07784~:'),
  (7602, 9, 15, 35, 'And Samuel came no more to see Saul until the day of his death: nevertheless Samuel mourned for Saul: and the LORD repented that he had made Saul king over Israel.', '1~08050~ 4~03254~ 6~07200~ 7~07586~ 10~03117~ 13~04194~: 14~03588~ 15~08050~ 16~056~ 18~07586~: 21~03068~ 22~05162~ 27~07586~ 28~04427~ 30~03478~.'),
  (17933, 23, 13, 18, 'Their bows also shall dash the young men to pieces; and they shall have no pity on the fruit of the womb; their eye shall not spare children.', '[0] 1~07198~ 4~07376~ 7~05288~ 9~07376~; 15~07355~ 18~06529~ 21~0990~; 23~05869~ 26~02347~ 27~01121~.'),
  (21931, 27, 6, 17, 'And a stone was brought, and laid upon the mouth of the den; and the king sealed it with his own signet, and with the signet of his lords; that the purpose might not be changed concerning Daniel.', '1~02298~ 2~069~ 4~0858~, 6~07761~ 7~05922~ 9~06433~ 12~01358~; 15~04430~ 16~02857~ 21~05824~, 25~05824~ 28~07261~; 31~06640~ 33~03809~ 35~08133~ 37~01841~.'),
  (28768, 46, 15, 34, 'Awake to righteousness, and sin not; for some have not the knowledge of God: I speak this to your shame.', '0~1594~ 2~1346~, 3~2532~ 4~264~ 5~3361~; 6~1063~ 7~5100~ 8~2192~ 11~56~ 13~2316~: 15~3004~ [16] 17~4314~ 18~5213~ 19~1791~.'),
  (140, 1, 6, 2, 'That the sons of God saw the daughters of men that they were fair; and they took them wives of all which they chose.', '2~01121~ 4~0430~ 5~07200~ 7~01323~ 9~0120~ 11~02007~ [12] 13~02896~; 16~03947~ 18~0802~ 23~0977~.'),
  (29562, 51, 4, 4, 'That I may make it manifest, as I ought to speak.', '0~2443~ 3~5319~ 4~846~ 5~5319~, 6~5613~ 7~3165~ 8~1163~ 10~2980~.'),
  (12135, 15, 4, 16, 'We certify the king that, if this city be builded again, and the walls thereof set up, by this means thou shalt have no portion on this side the river.', '0~0586~ 1~03046~ 3~04430~ 5~02006~ 6~01791~ 7~07149~ 9~01124~ [10] 13~07792~ 16~03635~, 18~01836~ 19~06903~ 22~0383~ 23~03809~ 24~02508~ 27~05675~ 29~05103~.'),
  (5825, 5, 33, 9, 'Who said unto his father and to his mother, I have not seen him; neither did he acknowledge his brethren, nor knew his own children: for they have observed thy word, and kept thy covenant.', '1~0559~ 4~01~ 8~0517~, 12~07200~ 17~05234~ 19~0251~, 21~03045~ 24~01121~: 28~08104~ 30~0565~, 32~05341~ 34~01285~.'),
  (18343, 23, 36, 4, 'And Rabshakeh said unto them, Say ye now to Hezekiah, Thus saith the great king, the king of Assyria, What confidence is this wherein thou trustest?', '1~07262~ 2~0559~ 5~0559~ 9~02396~, 11~0559~ 13~01419~ 14~04428~, 16~04428~ 18~0804~, 20~0986~ [21] 25~0982~?'),
  (26131, 43, 2, 21, 'But he spake of the temple of his body.', '0~1161~ 1~1565~ 2~3004~ 3~4012~ 5~3485~ 7~846~ 8~4983~.'),
  (7222, 9, 1, 3, 'And this man went up out of his city yearly to worship and to sacrifice unto the LORD of hosts in Shiloh. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, the priests of the LORD, were there.', '1~01931~ 2~0376~ 4~05927~ 8~05892~ 9~03117~ 10~03117~ 11~07812~ 14~02076~ 17~03068~ 19~06635~ 21~07887~. 24~08147~ 25~01121~ 27~05941~, 28~02652~ 30~06372~, 32~03548~ 35~03068~, [36]'),
  (2344, 2, 29, 3, 'And thou shalt put them into one basket, and bring them in the basket, with the bullock and the two rams.', '3~05414~ 6~0259~ 7~05536~, 9~07126~ 13~05536~, 16~06499~ 19~08147~ 20~0352~.'),
  (322, 1, 13, 1, 'And Abram went up out of Egypt, he, and his wife, and all that he had, and Lot with him, into the south.', '&para; 1~087~ 3~05927~ 6~04714~, 10~0802~, 17~03876~ 22~05045~.'),
  (20763, 26, 14, 23, 'And they shall comfort you, when ye see their ways and their doings: and ye shall know that I have not done without cause all that I have done in it, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~05162~ 7~07200~ 9~01870~ 12~05949~: 16~03045~ 21~06213~ 23~02600~ 28~06213~ 31~05002~ 33~0136~ 34~03069~.'),
  (28555, 46, 8, 12, 'But when ye sin so against the brethren, and wound their weak conscience, ye sin against Christ.', '0~1161~ 3~264~ 4~3779~ 5~1519~ 7~80~, 8~2532~ 9~5180~ 10~846~ 11~770~ 12~4893~, 14~264~ 15~1519~ 16~5547~.'),
  (17305, 20, 31, 12, 'She will do him good and not evil all the days of her life.', '2~01580~ 4~02896~ 7~07451~ 10~03117~ 13~02416~.'),
  (2346, 2, 29, 5, 'And thou shalt take the garments, and put upon Aaron the coat, and the robe of the ephod, and the ephod, and the breastplate, and gird him with the curious girdle of the ephod:', '3~03947~ 5~0899~, 7~03847~ 9~0175~ 11~03801~, 14~04598~ 17~0646~, 20~0646~, 23~02833~, 25~0640~ 30~02805~ 33~0646~:'),
  (6709, 7, 7, 8, 'So the people took victuals in their hand, and their trumpets: and he sent all the rest of Israel every man unto his tent, and retained those three hundred men: and the host of Midian was beneath him in the valley.', '2~05971~ 3~03947~ 4~06720~ 7~03027~, 10~07782~: 13~07971~ 14~0376~ [15 17] 18~03478~ 20~0376~ 23~0168~, 25~02388~ 27~07969~ 28~03967~ 29~0376~: 32~04264~ 34~04080~ 40~06010~.'),
  (26843, 43, 19, 3, 'And said, Hail, King of the Jews! and they smote him with their hands.', '0~2532~ 1~3004~, 2~5463~, 3~935~ 6~2453~! 7~2532~ 9~1325~ 10~846~ 13~4475~.'),
  (11800, 14, 28, 27, 'And Ahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city, even in Jerusalem: but they brought him not into the sepulchres of the kings of Israel: and Hezekiah his son reigned in his stead.', '1~0271~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 8~06912~ 12~05892~, [13] 15~03389~: 18~0935~ 23~06913~ 26~04428~ 28~03478~: 30~03169~ 32~01121~ 33~04427~'),
  (26681, 43, 13, 36, 'Simon Peter said unto him, Lord, whither goest thou? Jesus answered him, Whither I go, thou canst not follow me now; but thou shalt follow me afterwards.', '&para; 0~4613~ 1~4074~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 6~4226~ 7~5217~ 9~2424~ 10~611~ 11~846~, 12~3699~ 14~5217~, 16~1410~ 17~3756~ 18~190~ 19~3427~ 20~3568~; 21~1161~ 24~190~ 25~3427~ 26~5305~.'),
  (27655, 44, 20, 13, 'And we went before to ship, and sailed unto Assos, there intending to take in Paul: for so had he appointed, minding himself to go afoot.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2249~ 3~4281~ 4~1909~ 5~4143~, 7~321~ 8~1519~ 9~789~, 10~1564~ 11~3195~ 14~353~ 15~3972~: 16~1063~ 17~3779~ 19~2258~ 20~1299~, 21~3195~ 22~846~ 25~3978~.'),
  (13672, 18, 33, 13, 'Why dost thou strive against him? for he giveth not account of any of his matters.', '3~07378~ 10~06030~ 15~01697~.'),
  (7970, 9, 28, 21, 'And the woman came unto Saul, and saw that he was sore troubled, and said unto him, Behold, thine handmaid hath obeyed thy voice, and I have put my life in my hand, and have hearkened unto thy words which thou spakest unto me.', '2~0802~ 3~0935~ 5~07586~, 7~07200~ 11~03966~ 12~0926~, 14~0559~ 19~08198~ 21~08085~ 23~06963~, 27~07760~ 29~05315~ 32~03709~, 35~08085~ 38~01697~ 41~01696~'),
  (15357, 19, 89, 22, 'The enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him.', '1~0341~ 4~05378~ 9~01121~ 11~05766~ 12~06031~'),
  (11524, 14, 16, 6, 'Then Asa the king took all Judah; and they carried away the stones of Ramah, and the timber thereof, wherewith Baasha was building; and he built therewith Geba and Mizpah.', '1~0609~ 3~04428~ 4~03947~ 6~03063~; 10~05375~ 12~068~ 14~07414~, 17~06086~ 20~01201~ 22~01129~; 25~01129~ 27~01387~ 29~04709~.'),
  (25076, 42, 4, 1, 'And Jesus being full of the Holy Ghost returned from Jordan, and was led by the Spirit into the wilderness,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2424~ 3~4134~ 6~40~ 7~4151~ 8~5290~ 9~575~ 10~2446~, 11~2532~ 13~71~ 14~1722~ 16~4151~ 17~1519~ 19~2048~,'),
  (25273, 42, 8, 16, 'No man, when he hath lighted a candle, covereth it with a vessel, or putteth it under a bed; but setteth it on a candlestick, that they which enter in may see the light.', '0~1161~ 1~3762~, 5~681~ 7~3088~, 8~2572~ 9~846~ 12~4632~, 13~2228~ 14~5087~ [15] 16~5270~ 18~2825~; 19~235~ 20~2007~ [21] 22~1909~ 24~3087~, 25~2443~ 29~1531~ 31~991~ 33~5457~.'),
  (21710, 26, 47, 22, 'And it shall come to pass, that ye shall divide it by lot for an inheritance unto you, and to the strangers that sojourn among you, which shall beget children among you: and they shall be unto you as born in the country among the children of Israel; they shall have inheritance with you among the tribes of Israel.', '[6] 9~05307~ 15~05159~ 21~01616~ 23~01481~ 24~08432~ 28~03205~ 29~01121~ 30~08432~ 39~0249~ 42~0249~ 45~01121~ 47~03478~; 50~05307~ 51~05159~ 54~08432~ 56~07626~ 58~03478~.'),
  (1484, 1, 49, 6, 'O my soul, come not thou into their secret; unto their assembly, mine honour, be not thou united: for in their anger they slew a man, and in their selfwill they digged down a wall.', '2~05315~, 3~0935~ 8~05475~; 11~06951~, 13~03519~, 17~03161~: 21~0639~ 23~02026~ 25~0376~, 29~07522~ 32~06131~ 34~07794~.'),
  (12739, 17, 2, 6, 'Who had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captivity which had been carried away with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away.', '4~01540~ 6~03389~ 9~01473~ 14~01540~ 16~03204~ 17~04428~ 19~03063~, 21~05019~ 23~04428~ 25~0894~ 28~01540~.'),
  (373, 1, 15, 9, 'And he said unto him, Take me an heifer of three years old, and a she goat of three years old, and a ram of three years old, and a turtledove, and a young pigeon.', '2~0559~ 5~03947~ 8~05697~ 12~08027~, 16~05795~ 20~08027~, 23~0352~ 27~08027~, 30~08449~, 34~01469~.'),
  (5272, 5, 12, 26, 'Only thy holy things which thou hast, and thy vows, thou shalt take, and go unto the place which the LORD shall choose.', '3~06944~ 9~05088~, 12~05375~, 14~0935~ 17~04725~ 20~03068~ 22~0977~:'),
  (26329, 43, 6, 57, 'As the living Father hath sent me, and I live by the Father: so he that eateth me, even he shall live by me.', '0~2531~ 2~2198~ 3~3962~ 5~649~ 6~3165~, 8~2504~ 9~2198~ 10~1223~ 12~3962~: 13~2532~ 16~5176~ 17~3165~, 19~2548~ 21~2198~ 22~1223~ 23~1691~.'),
  (6576, 7, 3, 1, 'Now these are the nations which the LORD left, to prove Israel by them, even as many of Israel as had not known all the wars of Canaan;', '&para; [2] 4~01471~ 7~03068~ 8~03240~, 10~05254~ 11~03478~ [14] [17 18] 22~03045~ 25~04421~ 27~03667~;'),
  (30500, 61, 1, 5, 'And beside this, giving all diligence, add to your faith virtue; and to virtue knowledge;', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2532~* 2~846~ 3~5124~, 4~3923~ 5~3956~ 6~4710~, 7~2023~ 8~1722~ 9~5216~ 10~4102~ 11~703~; 12~1161~ 13~1722~ 14~703~ 15~1108~;'),
  (14057, 19, 10, 7, 'His mouth is full of cursing and deceit and fraud: under his tongue is mischief and vanity.', '1~06310~ 3~04390~ 5~0423~ 7~04820~ 9~08496~: 12~03956~ [13] 14~05999~ 16~0205~.'),
  (18357, 23, 36, 18, 'Beware lest Hezekiah persuade you, saying, The LORD will deliver us. Hath any of the gods of the nations delivered his land out of the hand of the king of Assyria?', '[0] 2~02396~ 3~05496~ 5~0559~, 7~03068~ 9~05337~ 12~0376~ 15~0430~ 18~01471~ 19~05337~ 21~0776~ 25~03027~ 28~04428~ 30~0804~?'),
  (4061, 4, 11, 32, 'And the people stood up all that day, and all that night, and all the next day, and they gathered the quails: he that gathered least gathered ten homers: and they spread them all abroad for themselves round about the camp.', '2~05971~ 4~06965~ 7~03117~, [10] 11~03915~, 15~04283~ 16~03117~, 19~0622~ 21~07958~: 25~04591~ 26~0622~ 27~06235~ 28~02563~: 31~07849~ [32] 34~07849~ 38~05439~ 40~04264~.'),
  (7257, 9, 2, 10, 'The adversaries of the LORD shall be broken to pieces; out of heaven shall he thunder upon them: the LORD shall judge the ends of the earth; and he shall give strength unto his king, and exalt the horn of his anointed.', '1~07378~ 4~03068~ 9~02865~; 12~08064~ 15~07481~ 19~03068~ 21~01777~ 23~0657~ 26~0776~; 30~05414~ 31~05797~ 34~04428~, 36~07311~ 38~07161~ 41~04899~.'),
  (28041, 45, 4, 3, 'For what saith the scripture? Abraham believed God, and it was counted unto him for righteousness.', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ 2~3004~ 4~1124~ 5~1161?~* 6~11~ 7~4100~ 8~2316~, 9~2532~ 12~3049~ 14~846~ 15~1519~ 16~1343~.'),
  (421, 1, 17, 20, 'And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly; twelve princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.', '3~03458~, 7~08085~: 11~01288~ 17~06509~, 20~07235~ 22~03966~ 23~03966~;* 24~08147~ 25~06240~* 26~05387~ 29~03205~, 34~05414~ 36~01419~ 37~01471~.'),
  (21772, 27, 2, 5, 'The king answered and said to the Chaldeans, The thing is gone from me: if ye will not make known unto me the dream, with the interpretation thereof, ye shall be cut in pieces, and your houses shall be made a dunghill.', '1~04430~ 2~06032~ 4~0560~ 7~03779~, 9~04406~ 11~0230~ 13~04481~: 14~02006~ 17~03809~ 19~03046~ 23~02493~, 26~06591~ 31~05648~ 33~01917~, 36~01005~ 39~07761~ 41~05122~.'),
  (4900, 5, 1, 2, '(There are eleven days'' journey from Horeb by the way of mount Seir unto Kadeshbarnea.)', '[0 1] 2~06240~ 3~0259~* 4~03117~ [5] 7~02722~ 10~01870~ 12~02022~ 13~08165~ 15~06947~)'),
  (8067, 10, 2, 11, 'And the time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah was seven years and six months.', '2~03117~ 3~04557~ 4~01732~ 6~04428~ 8~02275~ 11~01004~ 13~03063~ 15~07651~ 16~08141~ 18~08337~ 19~02320~.'),
  (6157, 6, 12, 21, 'The king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one;', '1~04428~ 3~08590~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~04023~, 9~0259~;'),
  (20659, 26, 10, 17, 'When they stood, these stood; and when they were lifted up, these lifted up themselves also: for the spirit of the living creature was in them.', '2~05975~, [3] 4~05975~; 10~07311~, [11] 13~07426~ [15] 18~07307~ 22~02416~ [23]'),
  (1522, 1, 50, 11, 'And when the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning in the floor of Atad, they said, This is a grievous mourning to the Egyptians: wherefore the name of it was called Abelmizraim, which is beyond Jordan.', '3~03427~ 6~0776~, 8~03669~, 9~07200~ 11~060~ 14~01637~ 16~0329~, 18~0559~, [20] 22~03515~ 23~060~ 26~04714~: 31~08034~ 33~07121~ 34~067~, [36] 37~05676~ 38~03383~.'),
  (20601, 26, 7, 15, 'The sword is without, and the pestilence and the famine within: he that is in the field shall die with the sword; and he that is in the city, famine and pestilence shall devour him.', '1~02719~ [2] 3~02351~, 6~01698~ 9~07458~ 10~01004~: [13] 16~07704~ 18~04191~ 21~02719~; [25] 28~05892~, 29~07458~ 31~01698~ 33~0398~'),
  (28876, 47, 4, 1, 'Therefore seeing we have this ministry, as we have received mercy, we faint not;', '&para; 1~5124~ 2~1223~ 3~2192~ 4~5026~ 5~1248~, 6~2531~ 10~1653~, 12~1573~ 13~3756~;'),
  (14653, 19, 48, 10, 'According to thy name, O God, so is thy praise unto the ends of the earth: thy right hand is full of righteousness.', '3~08034~, 5~0430~, [7] 9~08416~ 12~07099~ 15~0776~: 18~03225~ 20~04390~ 22~06664~.'),
  (5535, 5, 24, 4, 'Her former husband, which sent her away, may not take her again to be his wife, after that she is defiled; for that is abomination before the LORD: and thou shalt not cause the land to sin, which the LORD thy God giveth thee for an inheritance.', '1~07223~ 2~01167~, 6~07971~, 7~03201~ 9~03947~ 11~07725~ 15~0802~, 16~0310~ 20~02930~; [23] 24~08441~ 25~06440~ 27~03068~: 34~0776~ 36~02398~, 39~03068~ 41~0430~ 42~05414~ [44] 46~05159~.'),
  (24779, 41, 14, 14, 'And wheresoever he shall go in, say ye to the goodman of the house, The Master saith, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 2~3699~ 5~1525~, 7~2036~ 13~3617~ 14~3754~,* 16~1320~ 17~3004~, 18~4226~ 19~2076~ 21~2646~, 22~3699~ 25~5315~ 27~3957~ 28~3326~ 29~3450~ 30~3101~?'),
  (7377, 9, 8, 1, 'And it came to pass, when Samuel was old, that he made his sons judges over Israel.', '&para; 6~08050~ 8~02204~, 11~07760~ 13~01121~ 14~08199~ 16~03478~.'),
  (19121, 24, 6, 23, 'They shall lay hold on bow and spear; they are cruel, and have no mercy; their voice roareth like the sea; and they ride upon horses, set in array as men for war against thee, O daughter of Zion.', '3~02388~ 5~07198~ 7~03591~; [9] 10~0394~, 14~07355~; 16~06963~ 17~01993~ 20~03220~; 23~07392~ 25~05483~, 28~06186~ 30~0376~ 32~04421~ 36~01323~ 38~06726~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (10857, 13, 16, 29, 'Give unto the LORD the glory due unto his name: bring an offering, and come before him: worship the LORD in the beauty of holiness.', '0~03051~ 3~03068~ 5~03519~ [6] 9~08034~: 10~05375~ 12~04503~, 14~0935~ 15~06440~ 17~07812~ 19~03068~ 22~01927~ 24~06944~.'),
  (18063, 23, 22, 2, 'Thou that art full of stirs, a tumultuous city, a joyous city: thy slain men are not slain with the sword, nor dead in battle.', '3~04392~ 5~08663~, 7~01993~ 8~05892~, 10~05947~ 11~07151~: 13~02491~ [14 15] 17~02491~ 20~02719~, 22~04191~ 24~04421~.'),
  (1597, 2, 3, 13, 'And Moses said unto God, Behold, when I come unto the children of Israel, and shall say unto them, The God of your fathers hath sent me unto you; and they shall say to me, What is his name? what shall I say unto them?', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~0430~, [6] 8~0935~ 11~01121~ 13~03478~, 16~0559~ 20~0430~ 23~01~ 25~07971~ 32~0559~ [36] 38~08034~? 42~0559~'),
  (29370, 49, 6, 17, 'And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God:', '0~2532~ 1~1209~ 3~4030~ 5~4992~, 6~2532~ 8~3162~ 11~4151~, 13~3603~ 15~4487~ 17~2316~:'),
  (4846, 4, 34, 24, 'And the prince of the tribe of the children of Ephraim, Kemuel the son of Shiphtan.', '2~05387~ 5~04294~ 8~01121~ 10~0669~, 11~07055~ 13~01121~ 15~08204~.'),
  (16077, 19, 119, 170, 'Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.', '2~08467~ 3~0935~ 4~06440~ 6~05337~ 11~0565~.'),
  (8878, 11, 4, 26, 'And Solomon had forty thousand stalls of horses for his chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen.', '1~08010~ 3~0705~ 4~0505~ 5~0723~ 7~05483~ 10~04817~, 12~06240~ 13~08147~* 14~0505~ 15~06571~.'),
  (2593, 2, 36, 22, 'One board had two tenons, equally distant one from another: thus did he make for all the boards of the tabernacle.', '0~0259~ 1~07175~ 3~08147~ 4~03027~, 6~07947~ 7~0259~ 8~0413~ 9~0259~: 13~06213~ 17~07175~ 20~04908~.'),
  (10860, 13, 16, 32, 'Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof: let the fields rejoice, and all that is therein.', '2~03220~ 3~07481~, 6~04393~ 10~07704~ 11~05970~, [15]'),
  (17114, 20, 24, 26, 'Every man shall kiss his lips that giveth a right answer.', '[0 1] 3~05401~ [4] 5~08193~ 7~07725~ 9~05228~ 10~01697~.'),
  (26316, 43, 6, 44, 'No man can come to me, except the Father which hath sent me draw him: and I will raise him up at the last day.', '1~3762~ 2~1410~ 3~2064~ 4~4314~ 5~3165~, 6~3362~ 8~3962~ 9~3588~ 11~3992~ 12~3165~ 13~1670~ 14~846~: 15~2532~ 16~1473~ 18~450~ 19~846~ 20~450~ 23~2078~ 24~2250~.'),
  (14521, 19, 38, 22, 'Make haste to help me, O Lord my salvation.', '1~02363~ 3~05833~ 6~0136~ 8~08668~.'),
  (8850, 11, 3, 26, 'Then spake the woman whose the living child was unto the king, for her bowels yearned upon her son, and she said, O my lord, give her the living child, and in no wise slay it. But the other said, Let it be neither mine nor thine, but divide it.', '1~0559~ 3~0802~ 6~02416~ 7~01121~ [8] 11~04428~, 14~07356~ 15~03648~ 18~01121~, 21~0559~, 22~0994~ 24~0113~, 25~05414~ 28~02416~ 29~03205~, 33~04191~ 34~04191~ 39~0559~, [47] 48~01504~ [49]'),
  (15702, 19, 106, 42, 'Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.', '1~0341~ 3~03905~ 10~03665~ 13~03027~.'),
  (29432, 50, 2, 25, 'Yet I supposed it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, and companion in labour, and fellowsoldier, but your messenger, and he that ministered to my wants.', '0~1161~ 2~2233~ 4~316~ 6~3992~ 7~4314~ 8~5209~ 9~1891~, 10~3450~ 11~80~, 12~2532~ 15~4904~, 16~2532~ 17~4961~, 18~1161~ 19~5216~ 20~652~, 21~2532~ 24~3011~ 26~3450~ 27~5532~.'),
  (18220, 23, 29, 18, 'And in that day shall the deaf hear the words of the book, and the eyes of the blind shall see out of obscurity, and out of darkness.', '3~03117~ 6~02795~ 7~08085~ 9~01697~ 12~05612~, 15~05869~ 18~05787~ 20~07200~ 23~0652~, 27~02822~.'),
  (64, 1, 3, 8, 'And they heard the voice of the LORD God walking in the garden in the cool of the day: and Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the LORD God amongst the trees of the garden.', '2~08085~ 4~06963~ 7~03068~ 8~0430~ 9~01980~ 12~01588~ 15~07307~ 18~03117~: 20~0120~ 23~0802~ 25~02244~ 28~06440~ 31~03068~ 32~0430~ 33~08432~ 35~06086~ 38~01588~.'),
  (2523, 2, 34, 22, 'And thou shalt observe the feast of weeks, of the firstfruits of wheat harvest, and the feast of ingathering at the year''s end.', '3~06213~ 5~02282~ 7~07620~, 10~01061~ 12~02406~ 13~07105~, 16~02282~ 18~0614~ 21~08141~ 22~08622~.'),
  (8048, 10, 1, 19, 'The beauty of Israel is slain upon thy high places: how are the mighty fallen!', '1~06643~ 3~03478~ 5~02491~ 9~01116~: 13~01368~ 14~05307~!'),
  (10978, 13, 22, 6, 'Then he called for Solomon his son, and charged him to build an house for the LORD God of Israel.', '&para; 2~07121~ 4~08010~ 6~01121~, 8~06680~ 11~01129~ 13~01004~ 16~03068~ 17~0430~ 19~03478~.'),
  (9356, 11, 18, 7, 'And as Obadiah was in the way, behold, Elijah met him: and he knew him, and fell on his face, and said, Art thou that my lord Elijah?', '2~05662~ 6~01870~, 8~0452~ 9~07125~ 13~05234~ 16~05307~ 19~06440~, 21~0559~, [22] 26~0113~ 27~0452~?'),
  (23966, 40, 23, 38, 'Behold, your house is left unto you desolate.', '0~2400~, 1~5216~ 2~3624~ 4~863~ 6~5213~ 7~2048~.'),
  (17213, 20, 28, 8, 'He that by usury and unjust gain increaseth his substance, he shall gather it for him that will pity the poor.', '&para; 3~05392~ 6~08636~ 7~07235~ 9~01952~, 12~06908~ 18~02603~ 20~01800~.'),
  (1170, 1, 39, 16, 'And she laid up his garment by her, until his lord came home.', '3~03240~ 5~0899~ 7~0681~, 10~0113~ 11~0935~ 12~01004~.'),
  (9239, 11, 14, 13, 'And all Israel shall mourn for him, and bury him: for he only of Jeroboam shall come to the grave, because in him there is found some good thing toward the LORD God of Israel in the house of Jeroboam.', '2~03478~ 4~05594~ 8~06912~ 14~03379~ 16~0935~ 19~06913~, 25~04672~ [26] 27~02896~ 28~01697~ 31~03068~ 32~0430~ 34~03478~ 37~01004~ 39~03379~.'),
  (19204, 24, 9, 20, 'Yet hear the word of the LORD, O ye women, and let your ear receive the word of his mouth, and teach your daughters wailing, and every one her neighbour lamentation.', '1~08085~ 3~01697~ 6~03068~, 9~0802~, 13~0241~ 14~03947~ 16~01697~ 19~06310~, 21~03925~ 23~01323~ 24~05092~, 27~0802~ 29~07468~ 30~07015~.'),
  (15817, 19, 112, 5, 'A good man sheweth favour, and lendeth: he will guide his affairs with discretion.', '1~02896~ 2~0376~ 4~02603~, 6~03867~: 9~03557~ 11~01697~ 13~04941~.'),
  (13346, 18, 20, 11, 'His bones are full of the sin of his youth, which shall lie down with him in the dust.', '1~06106~ 3~04390~ [4 6] 9~05934~, 13~07901~ 18~06083~.'),
  (4175, 4, 15, 17, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (11462, 14, 12, 16, 'And Rehoboam slept with his fathers, and was buried in the city of David: and Abijah his son reigned in his stead.', '1~07346~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 8~06912~ 11~05892~ 13~01732~: 15~029~ 17~01121~ 18~04427~'),
  (29654, 52, 5, 17, 'Pray without ceasing.', '0~4336~ 2~89~.'),
  (15819, 19, 112, 7, 'He shall not be afraid of evil tidings: his heart is fixed, trusting in the LORD.', '4~03372~ 6~07451~ 7~08052~: 9~03820~ 11~03559~, 12~0982~ 15~03068~.'),
  (8591, 10, 21, 3, 'Wherefore David said unto the Gibeonites, What shall I do for you? and wherewith shall I make the atonement, that ye may bless the inheritance of the LORD?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 5~01393~, 9~06213~ 18~03722~, 22~01288~ 24~05159~ 27~03068~?'),
  (7173, 8, 2, 17, 'So she gleaned in the field until even, and beat out that she had gleaned: and it was about an ephah of barley.', '&para; 2~03950~ 5~07704~ 7~06153~, 10~02251~ 14~03950~: 20~0374~ 22~08184~.'),
  (9006, 11, 8, 13, 'I have surely built thee an house to dwell in, a settled place for thee to abide in for ever.', '2~01129~ 3~01129~ 6~01004~ 9~02073~, 12~04349~ 17~03427~ 19~05769~.'),
  (28062, 45, 4, 24, 'But for us also, to whom it shall be imputed, if we believe on him that raised up Jesus our Lord from the dead;', '0~235~ 1~1223~ 2~2248~ 3~2532~, 5~3739~ 8~3195~ 9~3049~, 12~4100~ 13~1909~ 17~1453~ 18~2424~ 19~2257~ 20~2962~ 21~1537~ 23~3498~;'),
  (21592, 26, 43, 11, 'And if they be ashamed of all that they have done, shew them the form of the house, and the fashion thereof, and the goings out thereof, and the comings in thereof, and all the forms thereof, and all the ordinances thereof, and all the forms thereof, and all the laws thereof: and write it in their sight, that they may keep the whole form thereof, and all the ordinances thereof, and do them.', '4~03637~ 10~06213~, 11~03045~ 14~06699~ 17~01004~, 20~08498~ 25~04161~ 29~04126~ 35~06699~ 40~02708~ 45~06699~ 50~08451~ 53~03789~ [54] 57~05869~, 61~08104~ 64~06699~ 69~02708~ 72~06213~'),
  (28923, 47, 6, 9, 'As unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and, behold, we live; as chastened, and not killed;', '0~5613~ 1~50~, 2~2532~ [3] 5~1921~; 6~5613~ 7~599~, 8~2532~, 9~2400~, 11~2198~; 12~5613~ 13~3811~, 14~2532~ 15~3361~ 16~2289~;'),
  (22871, 37, 2, 7, 'And I will shake all nations, and the desire of all nations shall come: and I will fill this house with glory, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~07493~ 5~01471~, 8~02532~ 11~01471~ 13~0935~: 17~04390~ 19~01004~ 21~03519~, 22~0559~ 24~03068~ 26~06635~.'),
  (6899, 7, 13, 8, 'Then Manoah entreated the LORD, and said, O my Lord, let the man of God which thou didst send come again unto us, and teach us what we shall do unto the child that shall be born.', '&para; 1~04495~ 2~06279~ 4~03068~, 6~0559~, 7~0994~ 9~0136~, 10~04994~ 12~0376~ 14~0430~ 18~07971~ 20~0935~ 24~03384~ 29~06213~ 32~05288~ 36~03205~.'),
  (9275, 11, 15, 18, 'Then Asa took all the silver and the gold that were left in the treasures of the house of the LORD, and the treasures of the king''s house, and delivered them into the hand of his servants: and king Asa sent them to Benhadad, the son of Tabrimon, the son of Hezion, king of Syria, that dwelt at Damascus, saying,', '1~0609~ 2~03947~ 5~03701~ 8~02091~ [9 10] 11~03498~ 14~0214~ 17~01004~ 20~03068~, 23~0214~ 26~04428~ 27~01004~, 29~05414~ 33~03027~ 36~05650~: 38~04428~ 39~0609~ 40~07971~ 43~01130~, 45~01121~ 47~02886~, 49~01121~ 51~02383~, 52~04428~ 54~0758~, 56~03427~ 58~01834~, 59~0559~,'),
  (5583, 5, 26, 11, 'And thou shalt rejoice in every good thing which the LORD thy God hath given unto thee, and unto thine house, thou, and the Levite, and the stranger that is among you.', '3~08055~ 6~02896~ [7] 10~03068~ 12~0430~ 14~05414~ 20~01004~, 24~03881~, 27~01616~ [29] 30~07130~'),
  (20593, 26, 7, 7, 'The morning is come unto thee, O thou that dwellest in the land: the time is come, the day of trouble is near, and not the sounding again of the mountains.', '1~06843~ 3~0935~ 9~03427~ 12~0776~: 14~06256~ 16~0935~ 18~03117~ 20~04103~ [21] 22~07138~, 27~01906~ 30~02022~.'),
  (16599, 20, 7, 15, 'Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.', '3~03318~ 5~07125~ 9~07836~ 11~06440~, 15~04672~'),
  (3044, 3, 11, 42, 'Whatsoever goeth upon the belly, and whatsoever goeth upon all four, or whatsoever hath more feet among all creeping things that creep upon the earth, them ye shall not eat; for they are an abomination.', '1~01980~ 4~01512~, 7~01980~ [9] 10~0702~, 14~07235~ 15~07272~ 19~08318~ 21~08317~ 24~0776~, 29~0398~; [32] 34~08263~.'),
  (1717, 2, 8, 2, 'And if thou refuse to let them go, behold, I will smite all thy borders with frogs:', '3~03986~ [6] 7~07971~, 11~05062~ 14~01366~ 16~06854~:'),
  (23230, 40, 4, 11, 'Then the devil leaveth him, and, behold, angels came and ministered unto him.', '0~5119~ 2~1228~ 3~863~ 4~846~, 5~2532~, 6~2400~, 7~32~ 8~4334~ 9~2532~ 10~1247~ 12~846~.'),
  (10330, 13, 2, 16, 'Whose sisters were Zeruiah, and Abigail. And the sons of Zeruiah; Abishai, and Joab, and Asahel, three.', '1~0269~ [2] 3~06870~, 5~026~. 8~01121~ 10~06870~; 11~052~, 13~03097~, 15~06214~, 16~07969~.'),
  (22763, 35, 2, 6, 'Shall not all these take up a parable against him, and a taunting proverb against him, and say, Woe to him that increaseth that which is not his! how long? and to him that ladeth himself with thick clay!', '5~05375~ 7~04912~ 12~04426~ 13~02420~ 17~0559~, 18~01945~ 22~07235~ [23 25] 34~03513~ 38~05671~!'),
  (15606, 19, 104, 26, 'There go the ships: there is that leviathan, whom thou hast made to play therein.', '1~01980~ 3~0591~: [4 5] 7~03882~, [8] 11~03335~ 13~07832~'),
  (2435, 2, 31, 10, 'And the cloths of service, and the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons, to minister in the priest''s office,', '2~0899~ 4~08278~, 7~06944~ 8~0899~ 10~0175~ 12~03548~, 15~0899~ 18~01121~, 24~03547~,'),
  (6291, 6, 17, 9, 'And the coast descended unto the river Kanah, southward of the river: these cities of Ephraim are among the cities of Manasseh: the coast of Manasseh also was on the north side of the river, and the outgoings of it were at the sea:', '2~01366~ 3~03381~ 6~05158~ 7~07071~, 8~05045~ 11~05158~: 13~05892~ 15~0669~ [16] 17~08432~ 19~05892~ 21~04519~: 23~01366~ 25~04519~ [27] 31~06828~ 34~05158~, 37~08444~ 43~03220~:'),
  (2787, 3, 3, 4, 'And the two kidneys, and the fat that is on them, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away.', '2~08147~ 3~03629~, 6~02459~ [8] [12] 15~03689~, 18~03508~ 21~03516~, 24~03629~, 29~05493~.'),
  (18573, 23, 45, 3, 'And I will give thee the treasures of darkness, and hidden riches of secret places, that thou mayest know that I, the LORD, which call thee by thy name, am the God of Israel.', '3~05414~ 6~0214~ 8~02822~, 11~04301~ 14~04565~, 18~03045~ 22~03068~, 24~07121~ [25] 28~08034~, [29] 31~0430~ 33~03478~.'),
  (22119, 28, 2, 5, 'For their mother hath played the harlot: she that conceived them hath done shamefully: for she said, I will go after my lovers, that give me my bread and my water, my wool and my flax, mine oil and my drink.', '2~0517~ 6~02181~: 9~02029~ 13~03001~: 16~0559~, 19~03212~ 20~0310~ 22~0157~, 24~05414~ [25] 27~03899~ 30~04325~, 32~06785~ 35~06593~, 37~08081~ 40~08250~.'),
  (12744, 17, 2, 11, 'And Mordecai walked every day before the court of the women''s house, to know how Esther did, and what should become of her.', '1~04782~ 2~01980~ 4~03117~ 5~06440~ 7~02691~ 10~0802~ 11~01004~, 13~03045~ 15~0635~ 16~07965~, 20~06213~'),
  (16043, 19, 119, 136, 'Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.', '&para; 0~06388~ 2~04325~ 4~03381~ 6~05869~, 9~08104~ 12~08451~.'),
  (5191, 5, 9, 28, 'Lest the land whence thou broughtest us out say, Because the LORD was not able to bring them into the land which he promised them, and because he hated them, he hath brought them out to slay them in the wilderness.', '2~0776~ 7~03318~ 8~0559~, 11~03068~ 14~03201~ 16~0935~ 20~0776~ 23~01696~ 28~08135~ 34~03318~ 36~04191~ 40~04057~.'),
  (18635, 23, 48, 12, 'Hearken unto me, O Jacob and Israel, my called; I am he; I am the first, I also am the last.', '0~08085~ 4~03290~ 6~03478~, 8~07121~; [10] [13] 15~07223~, [18] 20~0314~.'),
  (23044, 38, 11, 7, 'And I will feed the flock of slaughter, even you, O poor of the flock. And I took unto me two staves; the one I called Beauty, and the other I called Bands; and I fed the flock.', '3~07462~ 5~06629~ 7~02028~, [8] 9~03651~, 11~06041~ 14~06629~. 17~03947~ 20~08147~ 21~04731~; 23~0259~ 25~07121~ 26~05278~, 29~0259~ 31~07121~ 32~02254~; 35~07462~ 37~06629~.'),
  (20199, 24, 50, 24, 'I have laid a snare for thee, and thou art also taken, O Babylon, and thou wast not aware: thou art found, and also caught, because thou hast striven against the LORD.', '4~03369~ 11~03920~, 13~0894~, 18~03045~: 21~04672~, 24~08610~, 28~01624~ 31~03068~.'),
  (5475, 5, 21, 22, 'And if a man have committed a sin worthy of death, and he be to be put to death, and thou hang him on a tree:', '3~0376~ 7~02399~ 9~04941~ 10~04194~, 18~04191~, 21~08518~ 25~06086~:'),
  (1299, 1, 43, 4, 'If thou wilt send our brother with us, we will go down and buy thee food:', '2~03426~ 3~07971~ 5~0251~ 11~03381~ 13~07666~ 15~0400~:'),
  (11723, 14, 25, 10, 'Then Amaziah separated them, to wit, the army that was come to him out of Ephraim, to go home again: wherefore their anger was greatly kindled against Judah, and they returned home in great anger.', '1~0558~ 2~0914~ [4 5] 7~01416~ 10~0935~ 15~0669~, 17~03212~ 18~04725~ 19~03212~: 22~0639~ 24~03966~ 25~02734~ 27~03063~, 30~07725~ 31~04725~ 33~02750~ 34~0639~.'),
  (27501, 44, 16, 2, 'Which was well reported of by the brethren that were at Lystra and Iconium.', '0~3739~ 3~3140~ 5~5259~ 7~80~ 10~1722~ 11~3082~ 12~2532~ 13~2430~.'),
  (20062, 24, 46, 8, 'Egypt riseth up like a flood, and his waters are moved like the rivers; and he saith, I will go up, and will cover the earth; I will destroy the city and the inhabitants thereof.', '0~04714~ 2~05927~ 5~02975~, [7] 8~04325~ 10~01607~ 13~05104~; 16~0559~, 20~05927~, [21] 23~03680~ 25~0776~; 28~06~ 30~05892~ 33~03427~'),
  (4814, 4, 33, 48, 'And they departed from the mountains of Abarim, and pitched in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho.', '2~05265~ 5~02022~ 7~05682~, 9~02583~ 12~06160~ 14~04124~ 16~03383~ [17] 18~03405~.'),
  (21353, 26, 34, 31, 'And ye my flock, the flock of my pasture, are men, and I am your God, saith the Lord GOD.', '1~0859~ 3~06629~, 5~06629~ 8~04830~, [9] 10~0120~, [11] [13] 15~0430~, 16~05002~ 18~0136~ 19~03069~.'),
  (1500, 1, 49, 22, 'Joseph is a fruitful bough, even a fruitful bough by a well; whose branches run over the wall:', '&para; 0~03130~ [1] 3~06509~ 4~01121~, [5] 7~06509~ 8~01121~ 11~05869~; [12] 13~01323~ 14~06805~ 17~07791~:'),
  (25548, 42, 13, 17, 'And when he had said these things, all his adversaries were ashamed: and all the people rejoiced for all the glorious things that were done by him.', '0~2532~ 2~846~ 4~3004~ 6~5023~, 7~3956~ 8~846~ 9~480~ 11~2617~: 12~2532~ 13~3956~ 15~3793~ 16~5463~ 17~1909~ 18~3956~ 21~1741~ 24~1096~ 25~5259~ 26~846~.'),
  (837, 1, 30, 3, 'And she said, Behold my maid Bilhah, go in unto her; and she shall bear upon my knees, that I may also have children by her.', '2~0559~, 5~0519~ 6~01090~, 8~0935~ 14~03205~ 17~01290~, 23~01129~'),
  (15214, 19, 80, 7, 'Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.', '2~07725~, 4~0430~ 6~06635~, 10~06440~ 12~0215~; 17~03467~.'),
  (13163, 18, 13, 1, 'Lo, mine eye hath seen all this, mine ear hath heard and understood it.', '&para; 2~05869~ 4~07200~ [6] 8~0241~ 10~08085~ 12~0995~'),
  (18582, 23, 45, 12, 'I have made the earth, and created man upon it: I, even my hands, have stretched out the heavens, and all their host have I commanded.', '2~06213~ 4~0776~, 6~01254~ 7~0120~ [11] 13~03027~, 16~05186~ 18~08064~, 22~06635~ 25~06680~.'),
  (28763, 46, 15, 29, 'Else what shall they do which are baptized for the dead, if the dead rise not at all? why are they then baptized for the dead?', '0~1893~ 1~5101~ 4~4160~ 7~907~ 8~5228~ 10~3498~, 11~1487~ 13~3498~ 14~1453~ 15~3756~ 17~3654~? 18~2532~ 19~5101~ 22~907~ 23~5228~ 25~3498~?'),
  (30717, 66, 1, 4, 'John to the seven churches which are in Asia: Grace be unto you, and peace, from him which is, and which was, and which is to come; and from the seven Spirits which are before his throne;', '0~2491~ 3~2033~ 4~1577~ 5~3588~ 7~1722~ 8~773~: 9~5485~ [10] 12~5213~, 13~2532~ 14~1515~, 15~575~ 17~3588~ 18~5607~ 19~2532~ 20~3588~ 21~2258~ 22~2532~ 23~3588~ 26~2064~ 27~2532~ 28~575~ 30~2033~ 31~4151~ 32~3739~ 33~2076~ 34~1799~ 35~846~ 36~2362~;'),
  (25090, 42, 4, 15, 'And he taught in their synagogues, being glorified of all.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~1321~ 3~1722~ 4~846~ 5~4864~, 7~1392~ 8~5259~ 9~3956~.'),
  (9436, 11, 20, 20, 'And they slew every one his man: and the Syrians fled; and Israel pursued them: and Benhadad the king of Syria escaped on an horse with the horsemen.', '2~05221~ 4~0376~ 6~0376~: 9~0758~ 10~05127~; 12~03478~ 13~07291~ 16~01130~ 18~04428~ 20~0758~ 21~04422~ 24~05483~ 27~06571~.'),
  (26505, 43, 10, 9, 'I am the door: by me if any man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.', '0~1473~ 1~1510~ 3~2374~: 4~1223~ 5~1700~ 6~1437~ 8~5100~ 10~1525~, 14~4982~, 15~2532~ 18~1525~ 19~2532~ 20~1831~, 21~2532~ 22~2147~ 23~3542~.'),
  (21987, 27, 8, 17, 'So he came near where I stood: and when he came, I was afraid, and fell upon my face: but he said unto me, Understand, O son of man: for at the time of the end shall be the vision.', '2~0935~ 3~0681~ 6~05977~: 10~0935~, 13~01204~, 15~05307~ 18~06440~: 21~0559~ 24~0995~, 26~01121~ 28~0120~: 32~06256~ 35~07093~ [36 37] 39~02377~.'),
  (30614, 62, 3, 19, 'And hereby we know that we are of the truth, and shall assure our hearts before him.', '0~2532~ 1~5129~ 2~1722~ 3~1097~ 4~3754~ 6~2070~ 7~1537~ 9~225~, 10~2532~ 12~3982~ 13~2257~ 14~2588~ 15~1715~ 16~846~.'),
  (12277, 15, 10, 16, 'And the children of the captivity did so. And Ezra the priest, with certain chief of the fathers, after the house of their fathers, and all of them by their names, were separated, and sat down in the first day of the tenth month to examine the matter.', '2~01121~ 5~01473~ 7~06213~. 9~05830~ 11~03548~, [12] 13~0582~ 14~07218~ 17~01~, 20~01004~ 23~01~, [29] 30~08034~, 32~0914~, 35~03427~ 38~0259~ 39~03117~ 42~06224~ 43~02320~ 45~01875~ 47~01697~.'),
  (29618, 52, 3, 12, 'And the Lord make you to increase and abound in love one toward another, and toward all men, even as we do toward you:', '0~1161~ 2~2962~ 3~4121~ 4~5209~ 6~4121~ 7~2532~ 8~4052~ 10~26~ 11~240~ 12~1519~ 13~240~, 14~2532~ 15~1519~ 16~3956~ [17] 18~2532~ 19~2509~ 20~2249~ [21] 22~1519~ 23~5209~:'),
  (13607, 18, 31, 10, 'Then let my wife grind unto another, and let others bow down upon her.', '[0] 3~0802~ 4~02912~ 6~0312~, 9~0312~ 11~03766~'),
  (15510, 19, 99, 2, 'The LORD is great in Zion; and he is high above all the people.', '1~03068~ [2] 3~01419~ 5~06726~; [8] 9~07311~ 13~05971~.'),
  (19711, 24, 31, 11, 'For the LORD hath redeemed Jacob, and ransomed him from the hand of him that was stronger than he.', '2~03068~ 4~06299~ 5~03290~, 7~01350~ 11~03027~ [13 15] 16~02389~'),
  (24080, 40, 26, 16, 'And from that time he sought opportunity to betray him.', '0~2532~ 1~575~ 3~5119~ 5~2212~ 6~2120~ 7~2443~ 8~3860~ 9~846~.'),
  (20612, 26, 7, 26, 'Mischief shall come upon mischief, and rumour shall be upon rumour; then shall they seek a vision of the prophet; but the law shall perish from the priest, and counsel from the ancients.', '0~01943~ 2~0935~ 4~01943~, 6~08052~ 10~08052~; 14~01245~ 16~02377~ 19~05030~; 22~08451~ 24~06~ 27~03548~, 29~06098~ 32~02205~.'),
  (5149, 5, 8, 6, 'Therefore thou shalt keep the commandments of the LORD thy God, to walk in his ways, and to fear him.', '3~08104~ 5~04687~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~, 12~03212~ 15~01870~, 18~03372~'),
  (14866, 19, 64, 7, 'But God shall shoot at them with an arrow; suddenly shall they be wounded.', '&para; 1~0430~ 3~03384~ [6] 8~02671~; 9~06597~ 13~04347~.'),
  (23250, 40, 5, 6, 'Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness: for they shall be filled.', '0~3107~ [1] 3~3588~ 5~3983~ 6~2532~ 7~1372~ 9~1343~: 10~3754~ 11~846~ 14~5526~.'),
  (1606, 2, 3, 22, 'But every woman shall borrow of her neighbour, and of her that sojourneth in her house, jewels of silver, and jewels of gold, and raiment: and ye shall put them upon your sons, and upon your daughters; and ye shall spoil the Egyptians.', '2~0802~ 4~07592~ 7~07934~, 12~01481~ 15~01004~, 16~03627~ 18~03701~, 20~03627~ 22~02091~, 24~08071~: 28~07760~ [29] 32~01121~, 36~01323~; 40~05337~ 42~04714~.'),
  (2454, 2, 32, 11, 'And Moses besought the LORD his God, and said, LORD, why doth thy wrath wax hot against thy people, which thou hast brought forth out of the land of Egypt with great power, and with a mighty hand?', '1~04872~ 2~02470~ 3~06440~* 5~03068~ 7~0430~, 9~0559~, 10~03068~, 14~0639~ 16~02734~ 19~05971~, 24~03318~ 28~0776~ 30~04714~ 32~01419~ 33~03581~, 37~02389~ 38~03027~?'),
  (26241, 43, 5, 16, 'And therefore did the Jews persecute Jesus, and sought to slay him, because he had done these things on the sabbath day.', '0~2532~ 1~5124~ 2~1223~* 3~1377~ 5~2453~ 6~1377~ 7~2424~, 8~2532~ 9~2212~ 11~615~ 12~846~, 13~3754~ 16~4160~ 18~5023~ 19~1722~ 22~4521~.'),
  (17415, 21, 5, 9, 'Moreover the profit of the earth is for all: the king himself is served by the field.', '&para; 2~03504~ 5~0776~ 10~04428~ [11] 13~05647~ 16~07704~.'),
  (24821, 41, 14, 56, 'For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together.', '0~1063~ 1~4183~ 4~5576~ 5~2596~ 6~846~, 7~2532~ 9~3141~ 10~2258~ 11~3756~ 12~2470~* 13~2258~.'),
  (12054, 15, 2, 18, 'The children of Jorah, an hundred and twelve.', '1~01121~ 3~03139~, 5~03967~ 7~06240~ 8~08147~.*'),
  (23681, 40, 15, 38, 'And they that did eat were four thousand men, beside women and children.', '0~1161~ 4~2068~ 5~2258~ 7~5070~ 8~435~, 9~5565~ 10~1135~ 11~2532~ 12~3813~.'),
  (1513, 1, 50, 2, 'And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father: and the physicians embalmed Israel.', '1~03130~ 2~06680~ 4~05650~ 6~07495~ 8~02590~ 10~01~: 13~07495~ 14~02590~ 15~03478~.'),
