  (24571, 41, 9, 22, 'And ofttimes it hath cast him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but if thou canst do any thing, have compassion on us, and help us.', '0~2532~ 1~4178~ 4~906~ 5~846~ 6~1519~ 7~2532~ 8~4442~, 9~2532~ 10~1519~ 12~5204~, 13~2443~ 14~622~ 15~846~: 16~235~ 17~1536~ 19~1410~ 22~1536~, 24~4697~ 25~1909~ 26~2248~, 28~997~ 29~2254~.'),
  (3941, 4, 7, 86, 'The golden spoons were twelve, full of incense, weighing ten shekels apiece, after the shekel of the sanctuary: all the gold of the spoons was an hundred and twenty shekels.', '1~02091~ 2~03709~ [3] 4~08147~ 5~06240~,* 6~04392~ 8~07004~, [9] 10~06235~ [11] 12~03709~, 15~08255~ 18~06944~: 21~02091~ 24~03709~ [25] 27~03967~ 29~06242~ [30]'),
  (15571, 19, 103, 13, 'Like as a father pitieth his children, so the LORD pitieth them that fear him.', '3~01~ 4~07355~ [5] 6~01121~, [7] 9~03068~ 10~07355~ 13~03373~'),
  (25100, 42, 4, 25, 'But I tell you of a truth, many widows were in Israel in the days of Elias, when the heaven was shut up three years and six months, when great famine was throughout all the land;', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 3~5213~ 4~1909~ 6~225~, 7~4183~ 8~5503~ 9~2258~ 10~1722~ 11~2474~ 12~1722~ 14~2250~ 16~2243~, 17~3753~ 19~3772~ 22~2808~ 23~1909~* 24~5140~ 25~2094~ 26~2532~ 27~1803~ 28~3376~, 29~5613~ 30~3173~ 31~3042~ 32~1096~ 33~1909~ 34~3956~ 36~1093~;'),
  (3666, 4, 2, 3, 'And on the east side toward the rising of the sun shall they of the standard of the camp of Judah pitch throughout their armies: and Nahshon the son of Amminadab shall be captain of the children of Judah.', '&para; 4~06924~ 7~04217~ 15~01714~ 18~04264~ 20~03063~ 21~02583~ 24~06635~: 26~05177~ 28~01121~ 30~05992~ [31 32] 33~05387~ 36~01121~ 38~03063~.'),
  (6007, 6, 7, 25, 'And Joshua said, Why hast thou troubled us? the LORD shall trouble thee this day. And all Israel stoned him with stones, and burned them with fire, after they had stoned them with stones.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~, 3~04100~ 6~05916~ 9~03068~ 11~05916~ 14~03117~. 17~03478~ 18~07275~ 21~068~, 23~08313~ 26~0784~, 30~05619~ 33~068~.'),
  (24795, 41, 14, 30, 'And Jesus saith unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this day, even in this night, before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~281~ 7~3004~ 9~4671~, 10~3754~ 12~4594~, [13] 14~1722~ 15~5026~ 16~3571~, 17~2228~ 18~4250~ 19~220~ 20~5455~ 21~1364~, 24~533~ 25~3165~ 26~5151~.'),
  (18747, 23, 54, 15, 'Behold, they shall surely gather together, but not by me: whosoever shall gather together against thee shall fall for thy sake.', '3~01481~ 5~01481~, [6] 7~0657~ 10~04310~ 13~01481~ 17~05307~'),
  (25183, 42, 6, 25, 'Woe unto you that are full! for ye shall hunger. Woe unto you that laugh now! for ye shall mourn and weep.', '0~3759~ 2~5213~ 5~1705~! 6~3754~ 9~3983~. 10~3759~ 12~5213~ 14~1070~ 15~3568~! 16~3754~ 19~3996~ 20~2532~ 21~2799~.'),
  (21998, 27, 9, 1, 'In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus, of the seed of the Medes, which was made king over the realm of the Chaldeans;', '&para; 2~0259~ 3~08141~ 5~01867~ 7~01121~ 9~0325~, 12~02233~ 15~04074~, 19~04427~ 22~04438~ 25~03778~;'),
  (6927, 7, 14, 11, 'And it came to pass, when they saw him, that they brought thirty companions to be with him.', '7~07200~ 11~03947~ 12~07970~ 13~04828~'),
  (9770, 12, 9, 6, 'And he arose, and went into the house; and he poured the oil on his head, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD God of Israel, I have anointed thee king over the people of the LORD, even over Israel.', '2~06965~, 4~0935~ 7~01004~; 10~03332~ 12~08081~ 15~07218~, 17~0559~ 21~0559~ 23~03068~ 24~0430~ 26~03478~, 29~04886~ 31~04428~ 34~05971~ 37~03068~, [38] 40~03478~.'),
  (9565, 12, 2, 6, 'And Elijah said unto him, Tarry, I pray thee, here; for the LORD hath sent me to Jordan. And he said, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. And they two went on.', '1~0452~ 2~0559~ 5~03427~, 12~03068~ 14~07971~ 17~03383~. 20~0559~, [21] 23~03068~ 24~02416~, [26] 28~05315~ 29~02416~, 33~05800~ 37~08147~ 39~03212~.'),
  (2073, 2, 20, 17, 'Thou shalt not covet thy neighbour''s house, thou shalt not covet thy neighbour''s wife, nor his manservant, nor his maidservant, nor his ox, nor his ass, nor any thing that is thy neighbour''s.', '3~02530~ 5~07453~ 6~01004~, 10~02530~ 12~07453~ 13~0802~, 16~05650~, 19~0519~, 22~07794~, 25~02543~, [30] 32~07453~.'),
  (17160, 20, 26, 10, 'The great God that formed all things both rewardeth the fool, and rewardeth transgressors.', '&para; 1~07227~ [2] 4~02342~ [6] 8~07936~ 10~03684~, 12~07936~ 13~05674~.'),
  (2680, 2, 39, 11, 'And the second row, an emerald, a sapphire, and a diamond.', '2~08145~ 3~02905~, 5~05306~, 7~05601~, 10~03095~.'),
  (3116, 3, 13, 59, 'This is the law of the plague of leprosy in a garment of woollen or linen, either in the warp, or woof, or any thing of skins, to pronounce it clean, or to pronounce it unclean.', '[1] 3~08451~ 6~05061~ 8~06883~ 11~0899~ 13~06785~ 15~06593~, 19~08359~, 21~06154~, 24~03627~ 26~05785~, 30~02891~, 35~02930~.'),
  (22364, 29, 3, 12, 'Let the heathen be wakened, and come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat: for there will I sit to judge all the heathen round about.', '2~01471~ 4~05782~, 7~05927~ 10~06010~ 12~03092~: 17~03427~ 19~08199~ 22~01471~ 24~05439~.'),
  (10819, 13, 15, 20, 'And Zechariah, and Aziel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, and Unni, and Eliab, and Maaseiah, and Benaiah, with psalteries on Alamoth;', '1~02148~, 3~05815~, 5~08070~, 7~03171~, 9~06042~, 11~0446~, 13~04641~, 15~01141~, 17~05035~ 19~05961~;'),
  (16066, 19, 119, 159, 'Consider how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O LORD, according to thy lovingkindness.', '&para; 0~07200~ 3~0157~ 5~06490~: 6~02421~ 9~03068~, 13~02617~.'),
  (15388, 19, 90, 1, 'A Prayer of Moses the man of God. LORD, thou hast been our dwelling place in all generations.', '&para; [0 1~08605~ 3~04872~ 5~0376~ 7] 7~0430~ 8~0136~, 14~04583~ 16~01755~ 17~01755~.'),
  (30024, 58, 3, 13, 'But exhort one another daily, while it is called To day; lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.', '0~235~ 1~3870~ 3~1438~ 4~2250~ 5~2596~* 6~1538~,* 7~3739~ 8~891~ 10~2564~ 12~4594~; 13~3363~ 14~5100~ 15~1537~ 16~5216~ 18~4645~ 21~539~ 23~266~.'),
  (3334, 3, 20, 11, 'And the man that lieth with his father''s wife hath uncovered his father''s nakedness: both of them shall surely be put to death; their blood shall be upon them.', '2~0376~ 4~07901~ 7~01~ 8~0802~ 10~01540~ 12~01~ 13~06172~: 14~08147~ 18~04191~ 22~04191~; 24~01818~ [25 26]'),
  (16668, 20, 10, 3, 'The LORD will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish: but he casteth away the substance of the wicked.', '1~03068~ 4~07456~ 6~05315~ 9~06662~ 11~07456~: 15~01920~ 17~01942~ 20~07563~.'),
  (24605, 41, 10, 6, 'But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female.', '0~1161~ 1~575~ 3~746~ 6~2937~ 7~2316~ 8~4160~ 9~846~ 10~730~ 11~2532~ 12~2338~.'),
  (13243, 18, 15, 31, 'Let not him that is deceived trust in vanity: for vanity shall be his recompense.', '5~08582~ 6~0539~ 8~07723~: 10~07723~ 14~08545~.'),
  (15635, 19, 105, 20, 'The king sent and loosed him; even the ruler of the people, and let him go free.', '1~04428~ 2~07971~ 4~05425~ [6] 8~04910~ 11~05971~, 16~06605~.'),
  (1520, 1, 50, 9, 'And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen: and it was a very great company.', '3~05927~ 7~07393~ 9~06571~: 14~03966~ 15~03515~ 16~04264~.'),
  (20778, 26, 16, 7, 'I have caused thee to multiply as the bud of the field, and thou hast increased and waxen great, and thou art come to excellent ornaments: thy breasts are fashioned, and thine hair is grown, whereas thou wast naked and bare.', '2~05414~ 5~07233~ 8~06780~ 11~07704~, 15~07235~ 18~01431~, 22~0935~ 24~05716~ 25~05716~: [26] 27~07699~ 29~03559~, 32~08181~ 34~06779~, [37] 38~05903~ 40~06181~.'),
  (19851, 24, 35, 19, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; Jonadab the son of Rechab shall not want a man to stand before me for ever.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~, 8~0430~ 10~03478~; 11~03122~ 13~01121~ 15~07394~ 18~03772~ 20~0376~ 22~05975~ 23~06440~ 26~03117~.'),
  (4100, 4, 13, 20, 'And what the land is, whether it be fat or lean, whether there be wood therein, or not. And be ye of good courage, and bring of the fruit of the land. Now the time was the time of the firstripe grapes.', '3~0776~ [4] [7] 8~08082~ 10~07330~, 13~03426~ 14~06086~ 23~02388~, 25~03947~ 28~06529~ 31~0776~. 34~03117~ [35] 37~03117~ 40~01061~ 41~06025~.'),
  (166, 1, 7, 6, 'And Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.', '1~05146~ [2] 3~08337~ 4~03967~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 9~03999~ 11~04325~ 15~0776~.'),
  (1557, 2, 1, 20, 'Therefore God dealt well with the midwives: and the people multiplied, and waxed very mighty.', '1~0430~ 3~03190~ 6~03205~: 9~05971~ 10~07235~, 13~03966~ 14~06105~.'),
  (11363, 14, 8, 9, 'But of the children of Israel did Solomon make no servants for his work; but they were men of war, and chief of his captains, and captains of his chariots and horsemen.', '3~01121~ 5~03478~ 7~08010~ 8~05414~ 10~05650~ 13~04399~; [16] 17~0582~ 19~04421~, 21~08269~ 24~07991~, 26~08269~ 29~07393~ 31~06571~.'),
  (22430, 30, 4, 11, 'I have overthrown some of you, as God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah, and ye were as a firebrand plucked out of the burning: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.', '2~02015~ [3] 7~0430~ 8~04114~ 9~05467~ 11~06017~, 17~0181~ 19~05337~ 22~08316~: 27~07725~ 30~05002~ 32~03068~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (17894, 23, 11, 1, 'And there shall come forth a rod out of the stem of Jesse, and a Branch shall grow out of his roots:', '&para; 4~03318~ 6~02415~ 10~01503~ 12~03448~, 15~05342~ 17~06509~ 21~08328~:'),
  (835, 1, 30, 1, 'And when Rachel saw that she bare Jacob no children, Rachel envied her sister; and said unto Jacob, Give me children, or else I die.', '&para; 2~07354~ 3~07200~ 6~03205~ 7~03290~ 10~07354~ 11~07065~ 13~0269~; 15~0559~ 17~03290~, 18~03051~ 20~01121~, 22~0369~ 24~04191~.'),
  (6803, 7, 9, 42, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that the people went out into the field; and they told Abimelech.', '7~04283~, 10~05971~ 12~03318~ 15~07704~; 18~05046~ 19~040~.'),
  (132, 1, 5, 26, 'And Methuselah lived after he begat Lamech seven hundred eighty and two years, and begat sons and daughters:', '1~04968~ 2~02421~ 3~0310~ 5~03205~ 6~03929~ 7~07651~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~* 10~08084~ 12~08147~ 13~08141~, 15~03205~ 16~01121~ 18~01323~:'),
  (27138, 44, 7, 6, 'And God spake on this wise, That his seed should sojourn in a strange land; and that they should bring them into bondage, and entreat them evil four hundred years.', '0~1161~ 1~2316~ 2~2980~ 5~3779~, 6~3754~ 7~846~ 8~4690~ 9~2071~ 10~3941~ 11~1722~ 13~245~ 14~1093~; 15~2532~ 19~1402~ 20~846~ 22~1402~, 23~2532~ [25] 26~2559~ 28~5071~ 29~2094~.'),
  (21293, 26, 33, 4, 'Then whosoever heareth the sound of the trumpet, and taketh not warning; if the sword come, and take him away, his blood shall be upon his own head.', '1~08085~ 2~08085~ 4~06963~ 7~07782~, 11~02094~; 14~02719~ 15~0935~, 19~03947~, 21~01818~ 27~07218~.'),
  (28134, 45, 8, 2, 'For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus hath made me free from the law of sin and death.', '0~1063~ 2~3551~ 5~4151~ 7~2222~ 8~1722~ 9~5547~ 10~2424~ 12~1659~ 13~3165~ 14~1659~ 15~575~ 17~3551~ 19~266~ 20~2532~ 21~2288~.'),
  (15505, 19, 98, 6, 'With trumpets and sound of cornet make a joyful noise before the LORD, the King.', '1~02689~ 3~06963~ 5~07782~ 9~07321~ 10~06440~ 12~03068~, 14~04428~.'),
  (24586, 41, 9, 37, 'Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me, receiveth not me, but him that sent me.', '0~1437~ 1~3739~ 2~1209~ 3~1520~ 5~5108~ 6~3813~ 7~1909~ 8~3450~ 9~3686~, 10~1209~ 11~1691~: 12~2532~ 13~1437~ 14~3739~ 15~1209~ 16~1691~, 17~1209~ 18~3756~ 19~1691~, 20~235~ 23~649~ 24~3165~.'),
  (28050, 45, 4, 12, 'And the father of circumcision to them who are not of the circumcision only, but who also walk in the steps of that faith of our father Abraham, which he had being yet uncircumcised.', '0~2532~ 2~3962~ 4~4061~ 9~3756~ 10~1537~ 12~4061~ 13~3440~, 14~235~ 16~2532~ 17~4748~ 20~2487~ 23~4102~ 25~2257~ 26~3962~ 27~11~, [29 30] 31~1722~ [32] 33~203~.'),
  (3131, 3, 14, 15, 'And the priest shall take some of the log of oil, and pour it into the palm of his own left hand:', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ [5] 8~03849~ 10~08081~, 12~03332~ [13] 16~03709~ 19~03548~ 21~08042~:'),
  (22663, 33, 6, 6, 'Wherewith shall I come before the LORD, and bow myself before the high God? shall I come before him with burnt offerings, with calves of a year old?', '&para; 4~06923~ 6~03068~, [7] 8~03721~ 12~04791~ 13~0430~? 17~06923~ 21~05930~, 23~05695~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~?'),
  (23273, 40, 5, 29, 'And if thy right eye offend thee, pluck it out, and cast it from thee: for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~4675~ 3~1188~ 4~3788~ 5~4624~ 6~4571~, 7~1807~ 8~846~ 9~1807~, 10~2532~ 11~906~ [12] 13~575~ 14~4675~: 15~1063~ 18~4851~ 20~4671~ 21~2443~ 22~1520~ 24~4675~ 25~3196~ 27~622~, 28~2532~ 29~3361~ [30] 31~4675~ 32~3650~ 33~4983~ 36~906~ 37~1519~ 38~1067~.'),
  (6835, 7, 10, 17, 'Then the children of Ammon were gathered together, and encamped in Gilead. And the children of Israel assembled themselves together, and encamped in Mizpeh.', '2~01121~ 4~05983~ 7~06817~, 9~02583~ 11~01568~. 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 19~0622~, 21~02583~ 23~04709~.'),
  (3968, 4, 8, 24, 'This is it that belongeth unto the Levites: from twenty and five years old and upward they shall go in to wait upon the service of the tabernacle of the congregation:', '[1 2] [4] 7~03881~: 9~06242~ 11~02568~ 12~08141~ 13~01121~ 15~04605~ 19~0935~ 21~06633~ 22~06635~* 25~05656~ 28~0168~ 31~04150~:'),
  (19143, 24, 7, 15, 'And I will cast you out of my sight, as I have cast out all your brethren, even the whole seed of Ephraim.', '5~07993~ 8~06440~, 13~07993~ 16~0251~, [17] 20~02233~ 22~0669~.'),
  (21268, 26, 32, 11, 'For thus saith the Lord GOD; The sword of the king of Babylon shall come upon thee.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 7~02719~ 10~04428~ 12~0894~ 14~0935~'),
  (9235, 11, 14, 9, 'But hast done evil above all that were before thee: for thou hast gone and made thee other gods, and molten images, to provoke me to anger, and hast cast me behind thy back:', '2~06213~ 3~07489~ 8~06440~ 13~03212~ 15~06213~ 17~0312~ 18~0430~, 21~04541~, 26~03707~, 29~07993~ 31~0310~ 33~01458~:'),
  (22525, 31, 1, 6, 'How are the things of Esau searched out! how are his hidden things sought up!', '[2 3] 5~06215~ 7~02664~! [8] 11~04710~ 14~01158~!'),
  (10948, 13, 21, 6, 'But Levi and Benjamin counted he not among them: for the king''s word was abominable to Joab.', '1~03878~ 3~01144~ 4~06485~ 7~08432~ 11~04428~ 12~01697~ 14~08581~ 16~03097~.'),
  (9325, 11, 16, 34, 'In his days did Hiel the Bethelite build Jericho: he laid the foundation thereof in Abiram his firstborn, and set up the gates thereof in his youngest son Segub, according to the word of the LORD, which he spake by Joshua the son of Nun.', '2~03117~ 4~02419~ 6~01017~ 7~01129~ 8~03405~: 12~03245~ 15~048~ 17~01060~, 20~05324~ 22~01817~ 26~06810~ [27] 28~07687~, 32~01697~ 35~03068~, 38~01696~ 39~03027~ 40~03091~ 42~01121~ 44~05126~.'),
  (13959, 19, 2, 5, 'Then shall he speak unto them in his wrath, and vex them in his sore displeasure.', '3~01696~ 8~0639~, 10~0926~ 15~02740~.'),
  (12758, 17, 3, 2, 'And all the king''s servants, that were in the king''s gate, bowed, and reverenced Haman: for the king had so commanded concerning him. But Mordecai bowed not, nor did him reverence.', '3~04428~ 4~05650~, [6] 9~04428~ 10~08179~, 11~03766~, 13~07812~ 14~02001~: 17~04428~ 20~06680~ 24~04782~ 25~03766~ [29] 30~07812~.'),
  (16030, 19, 119, 123, 'Mine eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.', '&para; 1~05869~ 2~03615~ 5~03444~, 9~0565~ 12~06664~.'),
  (1240, 1, 41, 40, 'Thou shalt be over my house, and according unto thy word shall all my people be ruled: only in the throne will I be greater than thou.', '2~01961~ 5~01004~, 10~06310~ 14~05971~ 16~05401~: 20~03678~ 24~01431~'),
  (19596, 24, 26, 15, 'But know ye for certain, that if ye put me to death, ye shall surely bring innocent blood upon yourselves, and upon this city, and upon the inhabitants thereof: for of a truth the LORD hath sent me unto you to speak all these words in your ears.', '1~03045~ 4~03045~, 11~04191~, 15~05414~ 16~05355~ 17~01818~ 23~05892~, 27~03427~ 32~0571~ 34~03068~ 36~07971~ 41~01696~ 44~01697~ 47~0241~.'),
  (7761, 9, 20, 24, 'So David hid himself in the field: and when the new moon was come, the king sat him down to eat meat.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~05641~ 6~07704~: 11~02320~ 15~04428~ 18~03427~ 20~0398~ 21~03899~.'),
  (15485, 19, 96, 11, 'Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof.', '2~08064~ 3~08055~, 7~0776~ 9~01523~; 12~03220~ 13~07481~, 16~04393~'),
  (27651, 44, 20, 9, 'And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead.', '0~1161~ 2~2521~ 3~1909~ 5~2376~ 7~5100~ 9~3494~ 10~3686~ 11~2161~, 13~2702~ 16~901~ 17~5258~: 20~3972~ 22~4119~ 23~1909~* 24~1256~, 27~2702~ 28~575~ 29~5258~, 32~4098~ 33~2736~* 34~575~ 37~5152~, 38~2532~ 41~142~ 42~3498~.'),
  (8711, 10, 24, 11, 'For when David was up in the morning, the word of the LORD came unto the prophet Gad, David''s seer, saying,', '2~01732~ 4~06965~ 7~01242~, 9~01697~ 12~03068~ 16~05030~ 17~01410~, 18~01732~ 19~02374~, 20~0559~,'),
  (21558, 26, 41, 23, 'And the temple and the sanctuary had two doors.', '2~01964~ 5~06944~ 7~08147~ 8~01817~.'),
  (15763, 19, 108, 12, 'Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.', '0~03051~ 2~05833~ 4~06862~: 6~07723~ [7] 9~08668~ 11~0120~.'),
  (19073, 24, 5, 6, 'Wherefore a lion out of the forest shall slay them, and a wolf of the evenings shall spoil them, a leopard shall watch over their cities: every one that goeth out thence shall be torn in pieces: because their transgressions are many, and their backslidings are increased.', '2~0738~ 6~03293~ 8~05221~ [10] 12~02061~ 15~06160~ 17~07703~ 20~05246~ 22~08245~ 25~05892~: 30~03318~ 32~02007~ 36~02963~: 39~06588~ 41~07231~, [42] 44~04878~ 46~06105~.'),
  (9649, 12, 4, 38, 'And Elisha came again to Gilgal: and there was a dearth in the land; and the sons of the prophets were sitting before him: and he said unto his servant, Set on the great pot, and seethe pottage for the sons of the prophets.', '&para; 1~0477~ 3~07725~ 5~01537~: [7 8] 10~07458~ 13~0776~; 16~01121~ 19~05030~ [20] 21~03427~ 22~06440~ 26~0559~ 29~05288~, 30~08239~ 33~01419~ 34~05518~, 36~01310~ 37~05138~ 40~01121~ 43~05030~.'),
  (27980, 45, 2, 2, 'But we are sure that the judgment of God is according to truth against them which commit such things.', '0~1161~ 3~1492~ 4~3754~ 6~2917~ 8~2316~ 9~2076~ 10~2596~ 12~225~ 13~1909~ 16~4238~ 18~5108~.'),
  (7765, 9, 20, 28, 'And Jonathan answered Saul, David earnestly asked leave of me to go to Bethlehem:', '1~03083~ 2~06030~ 3~07586~, 4~01732~ 5~07592~ 6~07592~ [7] 9~05978~ [10 11] 13~01035~:'),
  (22347, 29, 2, 27, 'And ye shall know that I am in the midst of Israel, and that I am the LORD your God, and none else: and my people shall never be ashamed.', '3~03045~ [6] 9~07130~ 11~03478~, [13] [15] 17~03068~ 19~0430~, 25~05971~ 27~05769~ 29~0954~.'),
  (19179, 24, 8, 17, 'For, behold, I will send serpents, cockatrices, among you, which will not be charmed, and they shall bite you, saith the LORD.', '4~07971~ 5~05175~, 6~06848~, [10] [12] 13~03908~, 17~05391~ 19~05002~ 21~03068~.'),
  (20766, 26, 15, 3, 'Shall wood be taken thereof to do any work? or will men take a pin of it to hang any vessel thereon?', '1~06086~ 3~03947~ 6~06213~ 8~04399~? [11] 12~03947~ 14~03489~ 18~08518~ 20~03627~'),
  (8773, 11, 1, 48, 'And also thus said the king, Blessed be the LORD God of Israel, which hath given one to sit on my throne this day, mine eyes even seeing it.', '3~0559~ 5~04428~, 6~01288~ [7] 9~03068~ 10~0430~ 12~03478~, 15~05414~ [16] 18~03427~ 21~03678~ 23~03117~, 25~05869~ 27~07200~ [28]'),
  (1611, 2, 4, 5, 'That they may believe that the LORD God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, hath appeared unto thee.', '3~0539~ 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 10~01~, 12~0430~ 14~085~, 16~0430~ 18~03327~, 21~0430~ 23~03290~, 25~07200~'),
  (23946, 40, 23, 18, 'And, Whosoever shall swear by the altar, it is nothing; but whosoever sweareth by the gift that is upon it, he is guilty.', '0~2532~, 1~1437~ 2~3739~ 3~3660~ 4~1722~ 6~2379~, 8~2076~ 9~3762~; 10~1161~ 11~302~ 12~3739~* 13~3660~ 14~1722~ 16~1435~ 19~1883~ 20~846~, 23~3784~.'),
  (6315, 6, 18, 15, 'And the south quarter was from the end of Kirjathjearim, and the border went out on the west, and went out to the well of waters of Nephtoah:', '2~05045~ 3~06285~ [4] 7~07097~ 9~07157~, 12~01366~ 14~03318~ 17~03220~, 20~03318~ 23~04599~ 25~04325~ 27~05318~:'),
  (22676, 33, 7, 3, 'That they may do evil with both hands earnestly, the prince asketh, and the judge asketh for a reward; and the great man, he uttereth his mischievous desire: so they wrap it up.', '4~07451~ 7~03709~ 8~03190~, 10~08269~ 11~07592~, 14~08199~ [15] 18~07966~; 21~01419~ [22] 24~01696~ 26~01942~ 27~05315~: 32~05686~.'),
  (25332, 42, 9, 19, 'They answering said, John the Baptist; but some say, Elias; and others say, that one of the old prophets is risen again.', '0~1161~ 1~611~ 2~2036~, 3~2491~ 5~910~; 6~1161~ 7~243~ [8] 9~2243~; 10~1161~ 11~243~ [12] 13~3754~ 14~5100~ 17~744~ 18~4396~ 21~450~.'),
  (675, 1, 25, 13, 'And these are the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names, according to their generations: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebajoth; and Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,', '[2] 4~08034~ 7~01121~ 9~03458~, 12~08034~, 16~08435~: 18~01060~ 20~03458~, 21~05032~; 23~06938~, 25~0110~, 27~04017~,'),
  (22508, 30, 9, 4, 'And though they go into captivity before their enemies, thence will I command the sword, and it shall slay them: and I will set mine eyes upon them for evil, and not for good.', '3~03212~ 5~07628~ 6~06440~ 8~0341~, 12~06680~ 14~02719~, 18~02026~ 23~07760~ 25~05869~ 29~07451~, 33~02896~.'),
  (19110, 24, 6, 12, 'And their houses shall be turned unto others, with their fields and wives together: for I will stretch out my hand upon the inhabitants of the land, saith the LORD.', '2~01004~ 5~05437~ 7~0312~, [8 9] 10~07704~ 12~0802~ 13~03162~: 18~05186~ 20~03027~ 23~03427~ 26~0776~, 27~05002~ 29~03068~.'),
  (1108, 1, 37, 20, 'Come now therefore, and let us slay him, and cast him into some pit, and we will say, Some evil beast hath devoured him: and we shall see what will become of his dreams.', '0~03212~ 6~02026~ 9~07993~ 12~0259~ 13~0953~, 17~0559~, 19~07451~ 20~02416~ 22~0398~ 27~07200~ 33~02472~.'),
  (82, 1, 4, 2, 'And she again bare his brother Abel. And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.', '2~03254~ 3~03205~ 5~0251~ 6~01893~. 8~01893~ 11~07462~ 13~06629~, 15~07014~ 18~05647~ 21~0127~.'),
  (3539, 3, 26, 10, 'And ye shall eat old store, and bring forth the old because of the new.', '3~0398~ 5~03462~, 8~03318~ 10~03465~ 11~06440~ 14~02319~.'),
  (24602, 41, 10, 3, 'And he answered and said unto them, What did Moses command you?', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 7~5101~ 9~3475~ 10~1781~ 11~5213~?'),
  (495, 1, 19, 34, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that the firstborn said unto the younger, Behold, I lay yesternight with my father: let us make him drink wine this night also; and go thou in, and lie with him, that we may preserve seed of our father.', '7~04283~, 10~01067~ 11~0559~ 14~06810~, 17~07901~ 18~0570~ 21~01~: 26~08248~ 27~03196~ 29~03915~ 34~0935~, [35] 36~07901~ 42~02421~ 43~02233~ 46~01~.'),
  (29418, 50, 2, 11, 'And that every tongue should confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.', '0~2532~ [1] 2~3956~ 3~1100~ 5~1843~ 6~3754~ 7~2424~ 8~5547~ [9] 10~2962~, 11~1519~ 13~1391~ 15~2316~ 17~3962~.'),
  (12921, 18, 3, 8, 'Let them curse it that curse the day, who are ready to raise up their mourning.', '2~05344~ 5~0779~ 7~03117~, 10~06264~ 13~05782~ 15~03882~.'),
  (18418, 23, 38, 19, 'The living, the living, he shall praise thee, as I do this day: the father to the children shall make known thy truth.', '1~02416~, 3~02416~, 6~03034~ [10] 12~03117~: 14~01~ 17~01121~ 20~03045~ 22~0571~.'),
  (29520, 51, 2, 10, 'And ye are complete in him, which is the head of all principality and power:', '0~2532~ 2~2075~ 3~4137~ 4~1722~ 5~846~, 6~3739~ 7~2076~ 9~2776~ 11~3956~ 12~746~ 13~2532~ 14~1849~:'),
  (7718, 9, 19, 5, 'For he did put his life in his hand, and slew the Philistine, and the LORD wrought a great salvation for all Israel: thou sawest it, and didst rejoice: wherefore then wilt thou sin against innocent blood, to slay David without a cause?', '3~07760~ 5~05315~ 8~03709~, 10~05221~ 12~06430~, 15~03068~ 16~06213~ 18~01419~ 19~08668~ 22~03478~: 24~07200~ [25] 28~08055~: 33~02398~ 35~05355~ 36~01818~, 38~04191~ 39~01732~ 42~02600~?'),
  (26142, 43, 3, 7, 'Marvel not that I said unto thee, Ye must be born again.', '0~2296~ 1~3361~ 2~3754~ 4~2036~ 6~4671~, 7~5209~ 8~1163~ 10~1080~ 11~509~.'),
  (29665, 52, 5, 28, 'The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you. Amen.', '1~5485~ 3~2257~ 4~2962~ 5~2424~ 6~5547~ [7] 8~3326~ 9~5216~. 10~281~. [11 12~4413~ [13] 14~4314~ 16~2331~ 18~1125~ 19~575~ 20] 20~116~'),
  (724, 1, 26, 28, 'And they said, We saw certainly that the LORD was with thee: and we said, Let there be now an oath betwixt us, even betwixt us and thee, and let us make a covenant with thee;', '2~0559~, 4~07200~ 5~07200~ 8~03068~ 14~0559~, 20~0423~ 21~0996~ [23] 24~0996~ 31~03772~ 33~01285~'),
  (25827, 42, 20, 34, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, The children of this world marry, and are given in marriage:', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 7~5207~ 9~5127~ 10~165~ 11~1060~, 12~2532~ 16~1548~:'),
  (5589, 5, 26, 17, 'Thou hast avouched the LORD this day to be thy God, and to walk in his ways, and to keep his statutes, and his commandments, and his judgments, and to hearken unto his voice:', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~03117~ 10~0430~, 13~03212~ 16~01870~, 19~08104~ 21~02706~, 24~04687~, 27~04941~, 30~08085~ 33~06963~:'),
  (2476, 2, 32, 33, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Whosoever hath sinned against me, him will I blot out of my book.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0834~ 8~02398~ 15~04229~ 18~05612~.'),
  (16857, 20, 16, 8, 'Better is a little with righteousness than great revenues without right.', '&para; 0~02896~ [1] 3~04592~ 5~06666~ 7~07230~ 8~08393~ 10~04941~.'),
  (14568, 19, 42, 4, 'When I remember these things, I pour out my soul in me: for I had gone with the multitude, I went with them to the house of God, with the voice of joy and praise, with a multitude that kept holyday.', '2~02142~ [4] 7~08210~ 9~05315~ 15~05674~ 18~05519~, 20~01718~ 25~01004~ 27~0430~, 30~06963~ 32~07440~ 34~08426~, 37~01995~ 40~02287~.'),
  (16046, 19, 119, 139, 'My zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words.', '&para; 1~07068~ 3~06789~ 7~06862~ 9~07911~ 11~01697~.'),
  (25630, 42, 15, 29, 'And he answering said to his father, Lo, these many years do I serve thee, neither transgressed I at any time thy commandment: and yet thou never gavest me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends:', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ [5] 6~3962~, 7~2400~, 9~5118~ 10~2094~ 13~1398~ 14~4671~, 15~3763~ 17~3928~ 20~3763~ 21~4675~ 22~1785~: 23~2532~ 24~2532~ 25~1325~ 26~3763~ 27~1325~ 28~1698~ 30~2056~, 31~2443~ 35~2165~ 36~3326~ 37~3450~ 38~5384~:'),
  (3090, 3, 13, 33, 'He shall be shaven, but the scall shall he not shave; and the priest shall shut up him that hath the scall seven days more:', '3~01548~, 6~05424~ 10~01548~; 13~03548~ 15~05462~ [17 19] 21~05424~ 22~07651~ 23~03117~ 24~08145~:'),
  (1194, 1, 40, 17, 'And in the uppermost basket there was of all manner of bakemeats for Pharaoh; and the birds did eat them out of the basket upon my head.', '3~05945~ 4~05536~ [5 6] 9~03978~ 11~0644~ 12~04639~* 14~06547~; 17~05775~ 19~0398~ 24~05536~ 25~05921~ 27~07218~.'),
  (12809, 17, 6, 7, 'And Haman answered the king, For the man whom the king delighteth to honour,', '1~02001~ 2~0559~ 4~04428~, 7~0376~ 10~04428~ 11~02654~ 13~03366~,'),
  (19677, 24, 30, 1, 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 8~03068~, 9~0559~,'),
  (12720, 17, 1, 9, 'Also Vashti the queen made a feast for the women in the royal house which belonged to king Ahasuerus.', '1~02060~ 3~04436~ 4~06213~ 6~04960~ 9~0802~ [10] 12~04438~ 13~01004~ [15] 17~04428~ 18~0325~.'),
  (3342, 3, 20, 19, 'And thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy mother''s sister, nor of thy father''s sister: for he uncovereth his near kin: they shall bear their iniquity.', '4~01540~ 6~06172~ 9~0517~ 10~0269~, 14~01~ 15~0269~: 18~06168~ 21~07607~: 24~05375~ 26~05771~.'),
  (8343, 10, 13, 19, 'And Tamar put ashes on her head, and rent her garment of divers colours that was on her, and laid her hand on her head, and went on crying.', '1~08559~ 2~03947~ 3~0665~ 6~07218~, 8~07167~ 10~03801~ 13~06446~ [15] 19~07760~ 21~03027~ 24~07218~, 26~03212~ 27~01980~ 28~02199~.'),
  (17838, 23, 8, 22, 'And they shall look unto the earth; and behold trouble and darkness, dimness of anguish; and they shall be driven to darkness.', '3~05027~ 6~0776~; 9~06869~ 11~02825~, 12~04588~ 14~06695~; [16 18] 19~05080~ 21~0653~.'),
  (28631, 46, 11, 15, 'But if a woman have long hair, it is a glory to her: for her hair is given her for a covering.', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 3~1135~ 6~2863~, 8~2076~ 10~1391~ 12~846~: 13~3754~ [14] 15~2864~ 17~1325~ 18~846~ 19~473~ 21~4018~.'),
  (6444, 6, 22, 11, 'And the children of Israel heard say, Behold, the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the half tribe of Manasseh have built an altar over against the land of Canaan, in the borders of Jordan, at the passage of the children of Israel.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~08085~ 6~0559~, 9~01121~ 11~07205~ 14~01121~ 16~01410~ 19~02677~ 20~07626~ 22~04519~ 24~01129~ 26~04196~ 28~04136~ 30~0776~ 32~03667~, 35~01552~ 37~03383~, 40~05676~ 43~01121~ 45~03478~.'),
  (11000, 13, 23, 9, 'The sons of Shimei; Shelomith, and Haziel, and Haran, three. These were the chief of the fathers of Laadan.', '1~01121~ 3~08096~; 4~08019~ 5~08013~,* 7~02381~, 9~02039~, 10~07969~. [12] 14~07218~ 17~01~ 19~03936~.'),
  (5171, 5, 9, 8, 'Also in Horeb ye provoked the LORD to wrath, so that the LORD was angry with you to have destroyed you.', '2~02722~ 4~07107~ 6~03068~ 8~07107~, 12~03068~ 14~0599~ 19~08045~'),
  (5346, 5, 15, 21, 'And if there be any blemish therein, as if it be lame, or blind, or have any ill blemish, thou shalt not sacrifice it unto the LORD thy God.', '[4] 5~03971~ [7 10] 11~06455~, 13~05787~, [14 15] 17~07451~ 18~03971~, 22~02076~ 26~03068~ 28~0430~.'),
  (19256, 24, 11, 21, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD of the men of Anathoth, that seek thy life, saying, Prophesy not in the name of the LORD, that thou die not by our hand:', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 7~0582~ 9~06068~, 11~01245~ 13~05315~, 14~0559~, 15~05012~ 19~08034~ 22~03068~, 25~04191~ 29~03027~:'),
  (14099, 19, 15, 3, 'He that backbiteth not with his tongue, nor doeth evil to his neighbour, nor taketh up a reproach against his neighbour.', '[0 1] 2~07270~ 6~03956~, 8~06213~ 9~07451~ 12~07453~, 15~05375~ 17~02781~ 20~07138~.'),
  (30485, 60, 5, 4, 'And when the chief Shepherd shall appear, ye shall receive a crown of glory that fadeth not away.', '0~2532~ 4~750~ 6~5319~, 9~2865~ 11~4735~ 13~1391~ 17~262~.'),
  (1201, 1, 41, 1, 'And it came to pass at the end of two full years, that Pharaoh dreamed: and, behold, he stood by the river.', '&para; 7~07093~ 10~03117~ 11~08141~, 13~06547~ 14~02492~: 18~05975~ 21~02975~.'),
  (23246, 40, 5, 2, 'And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,', '0~2532~ 2~455~ 3~846~ 4~4750~, 6~1321~ 7~846~, 8~3004~,'),
  (5485, 5, 22, 9, 'Thou shalt not sow thy vineyard with divers seeds: lest the fruit of thy seed which thou hast sown, and the fruit of thy vineyard, be defiled.', '3~02232~ 5~03754~ 8~03610~: 11~04395~ 14~02233~ 18~02232~, 21~08393~ 24~03754~, 26~06942~.'),
  (23617, 40, 14, 10, 'And he sent, and beheaded John in the prison.', '0~2532~ 2~3992~, 4~607~ 5~2491~ 6~1722~ 8~5438~.'),
  (21989, 27, 8, 19, 'And he said, Behold, I will make thee know what shall be in the last end of the indignation: for at the time appointed the end shall be.', '2~0559~, 8~03045~ 15~0319~ 18~02195~: 23~04150~ 25~07093~ [26 27]'),
  (27283, 44, 10, 8, 'And when he had declared all these things unto them, he sent them to Joppa.', '0~2532~ 4~1834~ [6] 7~537~ 9~846~, 11~649~ 12~846~ 13~1519~ 14~2445~.'),
  (23223, 40, 4, 4, 'But he answered and said, It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God.', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 4~2036~, 7~1125~, 8~444~ 9~2198~ 10~3756~ 11~2198~ 12~1909~ 13~740~ 14~3441~, 15~235~ 16~1909~ 17~3956~ 18~4487~ 20~1607~ 22~1223~ 24~4750~ 26~2316~.'),
  (28002, 45, 2, 24, 'For the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles through you, as it is written.', '0~1063~ 2~3686~ 4~2316~ 6~987~ 7~1722~ 9~1484~ 10~1223~ 11~5209~, 12~2531~ 15~1125~.'),
  (13139, 18, 12, 2, 'No doubt but ye are the people, and wisdom shall die with you.', '1~0551~ [4] 6~05971~, 8~02451~ 10~04191~'),
  (395, 1, 16, 10, 'And the angel of the LORD said unto her, I will multiply thy seed exceedingly, that it shall not be numbered for multitude.', '&para; 2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~0559~ 11~07235~ 13~02233~ 14~07235~, 20~05608~ 22~07230~.'),
  (20112, 24, 48, 23, 'And upon Kiriathaim, and upon Bethgamul, and upon Bethmeon,', '2~07156~, 5~01014~, 8~01010~,'),
  (26621, 43, 12, 26, 'If any man serve me, let him follow me; and where I am, there shall also my servant be: if any man serve me, him will my Father honour.', '0~1437~ 2~5100~ 3~1247~ 4~1698~, 7~190~ 8~1698~; 9~2532~ 10~3699~ 11~1473~ 12~1510~, 13~1563~ 14~2071~ 15~2532~ 16~1699~ 17~1249~ 18~2071~ 19~2532~:* 20~1437~ 22~5100~ 23~1247~ 24~1698~, 25~846~ 26~5091~ [27] 28~3962~ 29~5091~.'),
  (6841, 7, 11, 5, 'And it was so, that when the children of Ammon made war against Israel, the elders of Gilead went to fetch Jephthah out of the land of Tob:', '7~01121~ 9~05983~ 11~03898~ 13~03478~, 15~02205~ 17~01568~ 18~03212~ 20~03947~ 21~03316~ 25~0776~ 27~02897~:'),
  (18499, 23, 42, 10, 'Sing unto the LORD a new song, and his praise from the end of the earth, ye that go down to the sea, and all that is therein; the isles, and the inhabitants thereof.', '0~07891~ 3~03068~ 5~02319~ 6~07892~, [7] 9~08416~ 12~07097~ 15~0776~, 19~03381~ 22~03220~, 27~04393~; 29~0339~, 32~03427~'),
  (3663, 4, 1, 54, 'And the children of Israel did according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so did they.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 11~03068~ 12~06680~ 13~04872~, 15~06213~'),
  (30239, 58, 12, 11, 'Now no chastening for the present seemeth to be joyous, but grievous: nevertheless afterward it yieldeth the peaceable fruit of righteousness unto them which are exercised thereby.', '0~1161~ 1~3756~ 2~3956~* 3~3809~ 4~3303~ 5~4314~ 6~3918~ 7~1380~ 9~1511~ 10~5479~, 11~235~ 12~3077~: 13~1161~ 14~5305~ 16~591~ 18~1516~ 19~2590~ 21~1343~ 26~1128~ 27~846~ 28~1223~.*');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (1450, 1, 47, 25, 'And they said, Thou hast saved our lives: let us find grace in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh''s servants.', '2~0559~, 7~02421~: 10~04672~ 11~02580~ 14~05869~ 17~0113~, 22~06547~ 23~05650~.'),
  (20473, 25, 5, 22, 'But thou hast utterly rejected us; thou art very wroth against us.', '3~03988~ 4~03988~ 8~03966~ 9~07107~'),
  (22316, 29, 1, 16, 'Is not the meat cut off before our eyes, yea, joy and gladness from the house of our God?', '3~0400~ 5~03772~ 8~05869~, [9] 10~08057~ 12~01524~ 15~01004~ 18~0430~?'),
  (10265, 13, 1, 5, 'The sons of Japheth; Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshech, and Tiras.', '1~01121~ 3~03315~; 4~01586~, 6~04031~, 8~04074~, 10~03120~, 12~08422~, 14~04902~, 16~08494~.'),
  (20826, 26, 16, 55, 'When thy sisters, Sodom and her daughters, shall return to their former estate, and Samaria and her daughters shall return to their former estate, then thou and thy daughters shall return to your former estate.', '2~0269~, 3~05467~ 6~01323~, 8~07725~ 12~06927~, 14~08111~ 17~01323~ 19~07725~ 23~06927~, 28~01323~ 30~07725~ 34~06927~.'),
  (1031, 1, 35, 15, 'And Jacob called the name of the place where God spake with him, Bethel.', '1~03290~ 2~07121~ 4~08034~ 7~04725~ 9~0430~ 10~01696~ 13~01008~.'),
  (4663, 4, 30, 9, 'But every vow of a widow, and of her that is divorced, wherewith they have bound their souls, shall stand against her.', '2~05088~ 5~0490~, 11~01644~, 15~0631~ 17~05315~, 19~06965~'),
  (20245, 24, 51, 24, 'And I will render unto Babylon and to all the inhabitants of Chaldea all their evil that they have done in Zion in your sight, saith the LORD.', '3~07999~ 5~0894~ 10~03427~ 12~03778~ 15~07451~ 19~06213~ 21~06726~ 24~05869~, 25~05002~ 27~03068~.'),
  (16845, 20, 15, 29, 'The LORD is far from the wicked: but he heareth the prayer of the righteous.', '&para; 1~03068~ [2] 3~07350~ 6~07563~: 9~08085~ 11~08605~ 14~06662~.'),
  (3979, 4, 9, 9, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (20620, 26, 8, 7, 'And he brought me to the door of the court; and when I looked, behold a hole in the wall.', '&para; 2~0935~ 6~06607~ 9~02691~; 13~07200~, 15~0259~ 16~02356~ 19~07023~.'),
  (10677, 13, 10, 10, 'And they put his armour in the house of their gods, and fastened his head in the temple of Dagon.', '2~07760~ 4~03627~ 7~01004~ 10~0430~, 12~08628~ 14~01538~ 17~01004~ 19~01712~.'),
  (14505, 19, 38, 6, 'I am troubled; I am bowed down greatly; I go mourning all the day long.', '2~05753~; 6~07817~ 7~03966~; 9~01980~ 10~06937~ 13~03117~'),
  (13886, 18, 40, 13, 'Hide them in the dust together; and bind their faces in secret.', '0~02934~ 4~06083~ 5~03162~; [6] 7~02280~ 9~06440~ 11~02934~.'),
  (19575, 24, 25, 32, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts, Behold, evil shall go forth from nation to nation, and a great whirlwind shall be raised up from the coasts of the earth.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 7~07451~ 10~03318~ 12~01471~ 14~01471~, 17~01419~ 18~05591~ 22~05782~ 25~03411~ 28~0776~.'),
  (3298, 3, 19, 12, 'And ye shall not swear by my name falsely, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the LORD.', '4~07650~ 7~08034~ 8~08267~, 12~02490~ 14~08034~ 17~0430~: [19] 21~03068~.'),
  (1006, 1, 34, 21, 'These men are peaceable with us; therefore let them dwell in the land, and trade therein; for the land, behold, it is large enough for them; let us take their daughters to us for wives, and let us give them our daughters.', '1~0582~ [2] 3~08003~ 4~0854~ 9~03427~ 12~0776~, 14~05503~ 18~0776~, [20 21] 22~07342~ 23~03027~ 25~06440~; 28~03947~ 30~01323~ 34~0802~, 38~05414~ 41~01323~.'),
  (17162, 20, 26, 12, 'Seest thou a man wise in his own conceit? there is more hope of a fool than of him.', '&para; 0~07200~ 3~0376~ 4~02450~ 8~05869~? [9 10] 12~08615~ 15~03684~'),
  (12321, 16, 2, 5, 'And I said unto the king, If it please the king, and if thy servant have found favour in thy sight, that thou wouldest send me unto Judah, unto the city of my fathers'' sepulchres, that I may build it.', '2~0559~ 5~04428~, 8~02895~ 10~04428~, 14~05650~ 17~03190~ 20~06440~, 24~07971~ 27~03063~, 30~05892~ 33~01~ 34~06913~, 38~01129~'),
  (11218, 14, 1, 16, 'And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the king''s merchants received the linen yarn at a price.', '1~08010~ 3~05483~ 4~04161~ 7~04714~, 10~04723~: 12~04428~ 13~05503~ 14~03947~ 17~04723~ 20~04242~.'),
  (10069, 12, 18, 37, 'Then came Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, which was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder, to Hezekiah with their clothes rent, and told him the words of Rabshakeh.', '1~0935~ 2~0471~ 4~01121~ 6~02518~, [8] 11~01004~, 13~07644~ 15~05608~, 17~03098~ 19~01121~ 21~0623~ 23~02142~, 25~02396~ [27] 28~0899~ 29~07167~, 31~05046~ 34~01697~ 36~07262~.'),
  (27159, 44, 7, 27, 'But he that did his neighbour wrong thrust him away, saying, Who made thee a ruler and a judge over us?', '0~1161~ 3~91~ 5~4139~ 6~91~ 7~683~ 8~846~ 9~683~, 10~2036~, 11~5101~ 12~2525~ 13~4571~ 15~758~ 16~2532~ 18~1348~ 19~1909~ 20~2248~?'),
  (2845, 3, 5, 10, 'And he shall offer the second for a burnt offering, according to the manner: and the priest shall make an atonement for him for his sin which he hath sinned, and it shall be forgiven him.', '3~06213~ 5~08145~ [6] 9~05930~, 13~04941~: 16~03548~ 20~03722~ 25~02403~ 29~02398~, 34~05545~'),
  (12863, 17, 9, 20, 'And Mordecai wrote these things, and sent letters unto all the Jews that were in all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, both nigh and far,', '&para; 1~04782~ 2~03789~ 4~01697~, 6~07971~ 7~05612~ 11~03064~ [13] 17~04082~ 20~04428~ 21~0325~, [22] 23~07138~ 25~07350~,'),
  (21256, 26, 31, 17, 'They also went down into hell with him unto them that be slain with the sword; and they that were his arm, that dwelt under his shadow in the midst of the heathen.', '3~03381~ 5~07585~ [9 11] 12~02491~ 15~02719~; [17 19] 21~02220~, [22] 23~03427~ 26~06738~ 29~08432~ 32~01471~.'),
  (9252, 11, 14, 26, 'And he took away the treasures of the house of the LORD, and the treasures of the king''s house; he even took away all: and he took away all the shields of gold which Solomon had made.', '3~03947~ 5~0214~ 8~01004~ 11~03068~, 14~0214~ 17~04428~ 18~01004~; 22~03947~ 27~03947~ 30~04043~ 32~02091~ 34~08010~ 36~06213~.'),
  (13012, 18, 6, 25, 'How forcible are right words! but what doth your arguing reprove?', '1~04834~ 3~03476~ 4~0561~! 9~03198~ 10~03198~?'),
  (13652, 18, 32, 15, 'They were amazed, they answered no more: they left off speaking.', '&para; 2~02865~, 4~06030~ 9~06275~ 10~04405~.'),
  (18878, 23, 63, 3, 'I have trodden the winepress alone; and of the people there was none with me: for I will tread them in mine anger, and trample them in my fury; and their blood shall be sprinkled upon my garments, and I will stain all my raiment.', '2~01869~ 4~06333~ 9~05971~ [10 11] 12~0376~ 18~01869~ 22~0639~, 24~07429~ 28~02534~; 31~05332~ 34~05137~ 37~0899~, 41~01351~ 44~04403~.'),
  (17137, 20, 25, 15, 'By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.', '&para; 1~0753~ 2~0639~ 5~07101~ 6~06601~, 9~07390~ 10~03956~ 11~07665~ 13~01634~.'),
  (1121, 1, 37, 33, 'And he knew it, and said, It is my son''s coat; an evil beast hath devoured him; Joseph is without doubt rent in pieces.', '3~05234~, 5~0559~, [6 7] 9~01121~ 10~03801~; 12~07451~ 13~02416~ 15~0398~ 17~03130~ 20~02963~ 23~02963~.'),
  (27433, 44, 14, 3, 'Long time therefore abode they speaking boldly in the Lord, which gave testimony unto the word of his grace, and granted signs and wonders to be done by their hands.', '0~2425~ 1~5550~ 2~3767~ 3~3303~ 4~1304~ 6~3955~ 7~1909~ 9~2962~, 10~3588~ 12~3140~ 15~3056~ 17~846~ 18~5485~, 19~2532~ 20~1325~ 21~4592~ 22~2532~ 23~5059~ 26~1096~ 27~1223~ 28~846~ 29~5495~.'),
  (22153, 28, 4, 11, 'Whoredom and wine and new wine take away the heart.', '0~02184~ 2~03196~ 5~08492~ 7~03947~ 9~03820~.'),
  (17713, 23, 2, 19, 'And they shall go into the holes of the rocks, and into the caves of the earth, for fear of the LORD, and for the glory of his majesty, when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth.', '3~0935~ 6~04631~ 9~06697~, 13~04247~ 16~06083~, 17~06440~ 18~06343~ 21~03068~, 25~01926~ 28~01347~, 31~06965~ 34~06206~ 36~0776~.'),
  (14883, 19, 66, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Song or Psalm. Make a joyful noise unto God, all ye lands:', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~07892~ [6] 7] 7~04210~ 11~07321~ 13~0430~, 16~0776~:'),
  (22826, 36, 2, 12, 'Ye Ethiopians also, ye shall be slain by my sword.', '&para; 1~03569~ 3~01992~ [4 5] 6~02491~ 9~02719~.'),
  (3223, 3, 16, 17, 'And there shall be no man in the tabernacle of the congregation when he goeth in to make an atonement in the holy place, until he come out, and have made an atonement for himself, and for his household, and for all the congregation of Israel.', '5~0120~ 8~0168~ 11~04150~ 14~0935~ 19~03722~ 22~06944~ [23] 27~03318~, 32~03722~ 38~01004~, 43~06951~ 45~03478~.'),
  (26528, 43, 10, 32, 'Jesus answered them, Many good works have I shewed you from my Father; for which of those works do ye stone me?', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~846~, 3~4183~ 4~2570~ 5~2041~ 8~1166~ 9~5213~ 10~1537~ 11~3450~ 12~3962~; 13~1223~ 14~4169~ 16~846~ 17~2041~ 20~3034~ 21~3165~?'),
  (22490, 30, 7, 17, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Thy wife shall be an harlot in the city, and thy sons and thy daughters shall fall by the sword, and thy land shall be divided by line; and thou shalt die in a polluted land: and Israel shall surely go into captivity forth of his land.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~; 6~0802~ 10~02181~ 13~05892~, 16~01121~ 19~01323~ 21~05307~ 24~02719~, 27~0127~ 30~02505~ 32~02256~; 36~04191~ 37~05921~ 39~02931~ 40~0127~: 42~03478~ 44~01540~ 47~01540~ 51~0127~.'),
  (15342, 19, 89, 7, 'God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them that are about him.', '0~0410~ 2~07227~ 5~06206~ 8~05475~ 11~06918~, 17~03372~ [20 22] 23~05439~'),
  (19526, 24, 23, 33, 'And when this people, or the prophet, or a priest, shall ask thee, saying, What is the burden of the LORD? thou shalt then say unto them, What burden? I will even forsake you, saith the LORD.', '&para; 3~05971~, 6~05030~, 9~03548~, 11~07592~ 13~0559~, [15] 17~04853~ 20~03068~? 24~0559~ 28~04853~? 32~05203~ 34~05002~ 36~03068~.'),
  (27669, 44, 20, 27, 'For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.', '0~1063~ 2~5288~ 3~3361~ 4~3756~* 5~5288~ 7~312~ 9~5213~ 10~3956~ 12~1012~ 14~2316~.'),
  (10195, 12, 23, 22, 'Surely there was not holden such a passover from the days of the judges that judged Israel, nor in all the days of the kings of Israel, nor of the kings of Judah;', '4~06213~ 7~06453~ 10~03117~ 13~08199~ 15~08199~ 16~03478~, 21~03117~ 24~04428~ 26~03478~, 30~04428~ 32~03063~;'),
  (19284, 24, 13, 9, 'Thus saith the LORD, After this manner will I mar the pride of Judah, and the great pride of Jerusalem.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 9~07843~ 11~01347~ 13~03063~, 16~07227~ 17~01347~ 19~03389~.'),
  (24103, 40, 26, 39, 'And he went a little farther, and fell on his face, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from me: nevertheless not as I will, but as thou wilt.', '0~2532~ 2~4281~ 4~3397~ 5~4281~, 7~4098~ 8~1909~ 9~846~ 10~4383~, 11~2532~ 12~4336~, 13~3004~, 15~3450~ 16~3962~, 17~1487~ 19~2076~ 20~1415~, 21~3928~ 22~5124~ 23~4221~ 24~3928~ 25~575~ 26~1700~: 27~4133~ 28~3756~ 29~5613~ 30~1473~ 31~2309~, 32~235~ 33~5613~ 34~4771~ [35]'),
  (25865, 42, 21, 25, 'And there shall be signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars; and upon the earth distress of nations, with perplexity; the sea and the waves roaring;', '0~2532~ 3~2071~ 4~4592~ 5~1722~ 7~2246~, 8~2532~ 11~4582~, 12~2532~ 15~798~; 16~2532~ 17~1909~ 19~1093~ 20~4928~ 22~1484~, 23~1722~ 24~640~; 26~2281~ 27~2532~ 29~4535~ 30~2278~;'),
  (19344, 24, 15, 20, 'And I will make thee unto this people a fenced brazen wall: and they shall fight against thee, but they shall not prevail against thee: for I am with thee to save thee and to deliver thee, saith the LORD.', '3~05414~ 7~05971~ 9~01219~ 10~05178~ 11~02346~: 15~03898~ 22~03201~ [27] 31~03467~ 35~05337~ 37~05002~ 39~03068~.'),
  (18128, 23, 25, 1, 'O LORD, thou art my God; I will exalt thee, I will praise thy name; for thou hast done wonderful things; thy counsels of old are faithfulness and truth.', '&para; 1~03068~, [3] 5~0430~; 8~07311~ 12~03034~ 14~08034~; 18~06213~ 19~06382~ [20 21] 22~06098~ 24~07350~ [25] 26~0530~ [27] 28~0544~.'),
  (1129, 1, 38, 5, 'And she yet again conceived, and bare a son; and called his name Shelah: and he was at Chezib, when she bare him.', '4~03254~, 6~03205~ 8~01121~; 10~07121~ 12~08034~ 13~07956~: 18~03580~, 21~03205~'),
  (27421, 44, 13, 43, 'Now when the congregation was broken up, many of the Jews and religious proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas: who, speaking to them, persuaded them to continue in the grace of God.', '0~1161~ 3~4864~ 6~3089~, 7~4183~ 10~2453~ 11~2532~ 12~4576~ 13~4339~ 14~190~ 15~3972~ 16~2532~ 17~921~: 18~3748~, 19~4354~ 21~846~, 22~3982~ 23~846~ 25~1961~ 28~5485~ 30~2316~.'),
  (13855, 18, 39, 12, 'Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather it into thy barn?', '2~0539~ 8~07725~ 10~02233~, 12~0622~ [13 14] 16~01637~?'),
  (12162, 15, 6, 2, 'And there was found at Achmetha, in the palace that is in the province of the Medes, a roll, and therein was a record thus written:', '3~07912~ 5~0307~, 8~01001~ [10] 13~04083~ 16~04076~, 17~02298~ 18~04040~, 20~01459~ [21] 23~01799~ 24~03652~ 25~03790~:'),
  (4850, 4, 34, 28, 'And the prince of the tribe of the children of Naphtali, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.', '2~05387~ 5~04294~ 8~01121~ 10~05321~, 11~06300~ 13~01121~ 15~05989~.'),
  (17330, 21, 1, 6, 'The wind goeth toward the south, and turneth about unto the north; it whirleth about continually, and the wind returneth again according to his circuits.', '1~07307~ 2~01980~ 5~01864~, 8~05437~ 11~06828~; 15~01980~, 18~07307~ 20~07725~ 24~05439~.'),
  (7297, 9, 3, 14, 'And therefore I have sworn unto the house of Eli, that the iniquity of Eli''s house shall not be purged with sacrifice nor offering for ever.', '4~07650~ 7~01004~ 9~05941~, 12~05771~ 14~05941~ 15~01004~ 19~03722~ 21~02077~ 23~04503~ 24~05704~ 25~05769~.'),
  (1507, 1, 49, 29, 'And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered unto my people: bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,', '2~06680~ 5~0559~ 12~0622~ 15~05971~: 16~06912~ 20~01~ 23~04631~ [25] 28~07704~ 30~06085~ 32~02850~,'),
  (9059, 11, 8, 66, 'On the eighth day he sent the people away: and they blessed the king, and went unto their tents joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that the LORD had done for David his servant, and for Israel his people.', '2~08066~ 3~03117~ 5~07971~ 7~05971~ 8~07971~: 11~01288~ 13~04428~, 15~03212~ 18~0168~ 19~08056~ 21~02896~ 23~03820~ 27~02896~ 30~03068~ 32~06213~ 34~01732~ 36~05650~, 39~03478~ 41~05971~.'),
  (10290, 13, 1, 30, 'Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema,', '0~04927~, 2~01746~, 3~04854~, 4~02301~, 6~08485~,'),
  (26480, 43, 9, 25, 'He answered and said, Whether he be a sinner or no, I know not: one thing I know, that, whereas I was blind, now I see.', '0~3767~* 1~1565~ 2~611~ 3~2532~ 4~2036~, 5~1487~ 7~2076~ 9~268~ [10 11] 13~1492~ 14~3756~: 16~1520~ 18~1492~, 19~3754~, 22~5607~ 23~5185~, 24~737~ 26~991~.'),
  (15169, 19, 78, 47, 'He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycamore trees with frost.', '1~02026~ 3~01612~ 5~01259~, 9~08256~ 11~02602~.'),
  (2830, 3, 4, 30, 'And the priest shall take of the blood thereof with his finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and shall pour out all the blood thereof at the bottom of the altar.', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 7~01818~ 11~0676~, 13~05414~ [14] 17~07161~ 20~04196~ 23~05930~, 27~08210~ 30~01818~ 34~03247~ 37~04196~.'),
  (8826, 11, 3, 2, 'Only the people sacrificed in high places, because there was no house built unto the name of the LORD, until those days.', '2~05971~ 3~02076~ 6~01116~, 11~01004~ 12~01129~ 15~08034~ 18~03068~, 21~03117~.'),
  (18803, 23, 58, 8, 'Then shall thy light break forth as the morning, and thine health shall spring forth speedily: and thy righteousness shall go before thee; the glory of the LORD shall be thy rereward.', '&para; 3~0216~ 5~01234~ 8~07837~, 11~0724~ 14~06779~ 15~04120~: 18~06664~ 20~01980~ 21~06440~ 24~03519~ 27~03068~ 31~0622~.'),
  (180, 1, 7, 20, 'Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail; and the mountains were covered.', '0~02568~ 1~06240~* 2~0520~ 3~04605~ 6~04325~ 7~01396~; 10~02022~ 12~03680~.'),
  (14748, 19, 55, 7, 'Lo, then would I wander far off, and remain in the wilderness. Selah.', '[1] 4~05074~ 6~07368~, [7] 8~03885~ 11~04057~. 12~05542~.'),
  (10035, 12, 18, 3, 'And he did that which was right in the sight of the LORD, according to all that David his father did.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~03477~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 17~01732~ 19~01~ 20~06213~.'),
  (15090, 19, 75, 10, 'All the horns of the wicked also will I cut off; but the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.', '2~07161~ 5~07563~ 10~01438~; [11] 13~07161~ 16~06662~ 19~07311~.'),
  (3257, 3, 18, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (6175, 6, 13, 14, 'Only unto the tribe of Levi he gave none inheritance; the sacrifices of the LORD God of Israel made by fire are their inheritance, as he said unto them.', '3~07626~ 5~03878~ 7~05414~ 9~05159~; 11~0801~ 14~03068~ 15~0430~ 17~03478~ 20~0801~ [21] 23~05159~, 26~01696~'),
  (24961, 42, 1, 56, 'And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house.', '0~1161~ 1~3137~ 2~3306~ 3~4862~ 4~846~ 5~5616~ 6~5140~ 7~3376~, 8~2532~ 9~5290~ 10~1519~ 12~846~ 13~3624~.'),
  (3906, 4, 7, 51, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (8772, 11, 1, 47, 'And moreover the king''s servants came to bless our lord king David, saying, God make the name of Solomon better than thy name, and make his throne greater than thy throne. And the king bowed himself upon the bed.', '3~04428~ 4~05650~ 5~0935~ 7~01288~ 9~0113~ 10~04428~ 11~01732~, 12~0559~, 13~0430~ 16~08034~ 18~08010~ 19~03190~ 22~08034~, 24~01431~ 26~03678~ 27~01431~ 30~03678~. 33~04428~ 34~07812~ 38~04904~.'),
  (14332, 19, 30, 4, 'Sing unto the LORD, O ye saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.', '0~02167~ 3~03068~, 6~02623~ 11~03034~ 14~02143~ 17~06944~.'),
  (17418, 21, 5, 12, 'The sleep of a labouring man is sweet, whether he eat little or much: but the abundance of the rich will not suffer him to sleep.', '1~08142~ 5~05647~ [6] 7~04966~, 10~0398~ 11~04592~ 13~07235~: 16~07647~ 19~06223~ 22~03240~ 25~03462~.'),
  (2495, 2, 33, 17, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, I will do this thing also that thou hast spoken: for thou hast found grace in my sight, and I know thee by name.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 8~06213~ 10~01697~ 15~01696~: 19~04672~ 20~02580~ 23~05869~, 26~03045~ 29~08034~.'),
  (30580, 62, 2, 14, 'I have written unto you, fathers, because ye have known him that is from the beginning. I have written unto you, young men, because ye are strong, and the word of God abideth in you, and ye have overcome the wicked one.', '2~1125~ 4~5213~, 5~3962~, 6~3754~ 9~1097~ [11 12] 13~575~ 15~746~. 18~1125~ 20~5213~, 22~3495~, 23~3754~ 25~2075~ 26~2478~, 27~2532~ 29~3056~ 31~2316~ 32~3306~ 33~1722~ 34~5213~, 35~2532~ 38~3528~ 41~4190~.'),
  (15849, 19, 115, 10, 'O house of Aaron, trust in the LORD: he is their help and their shield.', '1~01004~ 3~0175~, 4~0982~ 7~03068~: [9] 11~05828~ 14~04043~.'),
  (21339, 26, 34, 17, 'And as for you, O my flock, thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I judge between cattle and cattle, between the rams and the he goats.', '&para; [1 2] 3~0859~, 6~06629~, 8~0559~ 10~0136~ 11~03069~; 14~08199~ 16~07716~ 18~07716~, 21~0352~ 25~06260~.'),
  (2039, 2, 19, 8, 'And all the people answered together, and said, All that the LORD hath spoken we will do. And Moses returned the words of the people unto the LORD.', '3~05971~ 4~06030~ 5~03162~, 7~0559~, 11~03068~ 13~01696~ 16~06213~. 18~04872~ 19~07725~ 21~01697~ 24~05971~ 27~03068~.'),
  (112, 1, 5, 6, 'And Seth lived an hundred and five years, and begat Enos:', '&para; 1~08352~ 2~02421~ 4~08141~ 5~03967~ 6~02568~ 7~08141~, 9~03205~ 10~0583~:'),
  (3737, 4, 3, 40, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Number all the firstborn of the males of the children of Israel from a month old and upward, and take the number of their names.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~06485~ 9~01060~ 12~02145~ 15~01121~ 17~03478~ 20~02320~ 21~01121~ 23~04605~, 25~05375~ 27~04557~ 30~08034~.'),
  (29163, 48, 4, 16, 'Am I therefore become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?', '1~1096~ 2~5620~ 3~1096~ 4~5216~ 5~2190~, 8~226~ 9~5213~ 11~226~?'),
  (17003, 20, 21, 10, 'The soul of the wicked desireth evil: his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.', '&para; 1~05315~ 4~07563~ 5~0183~ 6~07451~: 8~07453~ 11~02603~ 14~05869~.'),
  (899, 1, 31, 22, 'And it was told Laban on the third day that Jacob was fled.', '3~05046~ 4~03837~ 7~07992~ 8~03117~ 10~03290~ 12~01272~.'),
  (900, 1, 31, 23, 'And he took his brethren with him, and pursued after him seven days'' journey; and they overtook him in the mount Gilead.', '2~03947~ 4~0251~ 8~07291~ 10~0310~ 11~07651~ 12~03117~ 13~01870~; 16~01692~ 20~02022~ 21~01568~.'),
  (20773, 26, 16, 2, 'Son of man, cause Jerusalem to know her abominations,', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 4~03389~ 6~03045~ 8~08441~,'),
  (24381, 41, 5, 7, 'And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not.', '0~2532~ 1~2896~ 4~3173~ 5~5456~, 7~2036~, 8~5101~ 10~1698~ 12~2532~ 14~4671~, 15~2424~, [16] 17~5207~ 21~5310~ 22~2316~? 24~3726~ 25~4571~ 27~2316~, 30~928~ 31~3165~ 32~3361~.'),
  (21194, 26, 29, 2, 'Son of man, set thy face against Pharaoh king of Egypt, and prophesy against him, and against all Egypt:', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 3~07760~ 5~06440~ 7~06547~ 8~04428~ 10~04714~, 12~05012~ 18~04714~:'),
  (19424, 24, 19, 8, 'And I will make this city desolate, and an hissing; every one that passeth thereby shall be astonished and hiss because of all the plagues thereof.', '3~07760~ 5~05892~ 6~08047~, 9~08322~; 13~05674~ 17~08074~ 19~08319~ 24~04347~'),
  (15361, 19, 89, 26, 'He shall cry unto me, Thou art my father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.', '2~07121~ [6] 8~01~, 10~0410~, 13~06697~ 16~03444~.'),
  (24205, 40, 27, 66, 'So they went, and made the sepulchre sure, sealing the stone, and setting a watch.', '0~1161~ 2~4198~, 4~805~ 6~5028~ 7~805~, 8~4972~ 10~3037~, 12~3326~ 14~2892~.'),
  (3303, 3, 19, 17, 'Thou shalt not hate thy brother in thine heart: thou shalt in any wise rebuke thy neighbour, and not suffer sin upon him.', '3~08130~ 5~0251~ 8~03824~: 13~03198~ 14~03198~ 16~05997~, 19~05375~ 20~02399~'),
  (19866, 24, 36, 15, 'And they said unto him, Sit down now, and read it in our ears. So Baruch read it in their ears.', '2~0559~ 6~03427~ 9~07121~ 13~0241~. 15~01263~ 16~07121~ [17] 20~0241~.'),
  (27662, 44, 20, 20, 'And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have shewed you, and have taught you publicly, and from house to house,', '[0] 1~5613~ 4~5288~ 5~3762~ 8~4851~ [9 10] 11~3361~ 13~312~ 14~5213~, 15~2532~ 17~1321~ 18~5209~ 19~1219~, 20~2532~ 21~2596~ 24~3624~,'),
  (27805, 44, 24, 20, 'Or else let these same here say, if they have found any evil doing in me, while I stood before the council,', '1~2228~ 2~2036~ 3~846~ 4~3778~ [5] 6~2036~, 7~1536~ 10~2147~ 11~1536~ 13~92~ 14~1722~ 15~1698~, 17~3450~ 18~2476~ 19~1909~ 21~4892~,'),
  (18209, 23, 29, 7, 'And the multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel, even all that fight against her and her munition, and that distress her, shall be as a dream of a night vision.', '2~01995~ 6~01471~ 8~06633~ 10~0740~, 14~06638~ 19~04685~, 22~06693~ 28~02472~ 31~03915~ 32~02377~.'),
  (29779, 54, 4, 16, 'Take heed unto thyself, and unto the doctrine; continue in them: for in doing this thou shalt both save thyself, and them that hear thee.', '1~1907~ 3~4572~, 4~2532~ 7~1319~; 8~1961~ 10~846~: 11~1063~ 13~4160~ 14~5124~ 16~4982~ 17~2532~ 18~4982~ 19~4572~, 20~2532~ 23~191~ 24~4675~.'),
