VALUES
  (10880, 13, 17, 9, 'Also I will ordain a place for my people Israel, and will plant them, and they shall dwell in their place, and shall be moved no more; neither shall the children of wickedness waste them any more, as at the beginning,', '3~07760~ 5~04725~ 8~05971~ 9~03478~, 12~05193~ 17~07931~ 24~07264~ 30~01121~ 32~05766~ 33~01086~ 36~03254~, 40~07223~,'),
  (24833, 41, 14, 68, 'But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crew.', '0~1161~ 2~720~, 3~3004~, 5~1492~ 6~3756~, 7~3761~ 9~1987~ 10~5101~ 11~4771~ 12~3004~. 13~2532~ 15~1831~ 16~1854~ 17~1519~ 19~4259~; 20~2532~ 22~220~ 23~5455~.'),
  (14004, 19, 6, 10, 'Let all mine enemies be ashamed and sore vexed: let them return and be ashamed suddenly.', '3~0341~ 5~0954~ 7~03966~ 8~0926~: 11~07725~ [12] 14~0954~ 15~07281~.'),
  (8903, 11, 5, 17, 'And the king commanded, and they brought great stones, costly stones, and hewed stones, to lay the foundation of the house.', '2~04428~ 3~06680~, 6~05265~ 7~01419~ 8~068~, 9~03368~ 10~068~, [11] 12~01496~ 13~068~, 17~03245~ 20~01004~.'),
  (23578, 40, 13, 29, 'But he said, Nay; lest while ye gather up the tares, ye root up also the wheat with them.', '0~1161~ 2~5346~, 3~3756~; 4~3379~ 8~4816~ 10~2215~, 13~1610~ 16~4621~ 17~260~ 18~846~.'),
  (15103, 19, 77, 1, 'To the chief Musician, to Jeduthun, A Psalm of Asaph. I cried unto God with my voice, even unto God with my voice; and he gave ear unto me.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~03038~, 7~04210~ 9] 9~0623~ 11~06817~ 13~0430~ 16~06963~, [17] 19~0430~ 22~06963~; 26~0238~'),
  (20517, 26, 3, 6, 'Not to many people of a strange speech and of an hard language, whose words thou canst not understand. Surely, had I sent thee to them, they would have hearkened unto thee.', '2~07227~ 3~05971~ 6~06012~ 7~08193~ 11~03515~ 12~03956~, 14~01697~ 18~08085~. 22~07971~ 29~08085~'),
  (8310, 10, 12, 17, 'And the elders of his house arose, and went to him, to raise him up from the earth: but he would not, neither did he eat bread with them.', '2~02205~ 5~01004~ 6~06965~, [7 8] 14~06965~ 17~0776~: 20~014~ 25~01262~ 26~03899~'),
  (30563, 62, 1, 7, 'But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship one with another, and the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin.', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 3~4043~ 4~1722~ 6~5457~, 7~5613~ 8~846~ 9~2076~ 10~1722~ 12~5457~, 14~2192~ 15~2842~ 18~240~ 19~3326~,* 20~2532~ 22~129~ 24~2424~ 25~5547~ 26~846~ 27~5207~ 28~2511~ 29~2248~ 30~575~ 31~3956~ 32~266~.'),
  (14543, 19, 40, 9, 'I have preached righteousness in the great congregation: lo, I have not refrained my lips, O LORD, thou knowest.', '2~01319~ 3~06664~ 6~07227~ 7~06951~: 12~03607~ 14~08193~, 16~03068~, 18~03045~.'),
  (6326, 6, 18, 26, 'And Mizpeh, and Chephirah, and Mozah,', '1~04708~, 3~03716~, 5~04681~,'),
  (27332, 44, 11, 9, 'But the voice answered me again from heaven, What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common.', '0~1161~ 2~5456~ 3~611~ 4~3427~ 5~1208~ 6~1537~* 7~1537~ 8~3772~, 9~3739~ 10~2316~ 12~2511~, [13] 14~2840~ 15~3361~ 16~4771~ 17~2840~.'),
  (11069, 13, 25, 15, 'The eighth to Jeshaiah, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~08066~ 3~03470~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (30144, 58, 9, 23, 'It was therefore necessary that the patterns of things in the heavens should be purified with these; but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.', '&para; [0 1] 2~3767~ 3~318~ 6~5262~ 8~3303~ 9~1722~ 11~3772~ 14~2511~ 16~5125~; 17~1161~ 20~2032~ 21~846~ 23~2909~ 24~2378~ 25~3844~ 26~5025~.'),
  (6586, 7, 3, 11, 'And the land had rest forty years. And Othniel the son of Kenaz died.', '2~0776~ 4~08252~ 5~0705~ 6~08141~. 8~06274~ 10~01121~ 12~07073~ 13~04191~.'),
  (27334, 44, 11, 11, 'And, behold, immediately there were three men already come unto the house where I was, sent from Caesarea unto me.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 2~1824~ 4~2186~ 5~5140~ 6~435~ 7~1824~ 8~2186~ 9~1909~ 11~3614~ 12~3739~ 13~1722~* 14~3739~ 15~2252~, 16~649~ 17~575~ 18~2542~ 19~4314~ 20~3165~.'),
  (1895, 2, 14, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (6779, 7, 9, 18, 'And ye are risen up against my father''s house this day, and have slain his sons, threescore and ten persons, upon one stone, and have made Abimelech, the son of his maidservant, king over the men of Shechem, because he is your brother;)', '4~06965~ 7~01~ 8~01004~ 10~03117~, 13~02026~ 15~01121~, 18~07657~ 19~0376~, 21~0259~ 22~068~, 26~040~, 28~01121~ 31~0519~, 32~04427~ 35~01167~ 37~07927~, [40] 42~0251~;)'),
  (22242, 28, 10, 8, 'The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.', '2~01116~ 5~0206~, 7~02403~ 9~03478~, 12~08045~: 14~06975~ 17~01863~ 20~05927~ 23~04196~; 27~0559~ 30~02022~, 31~03680~ 36~01389~, 37~05307~'),
  (26206, 43, 4, 35, 'Say not ye, There are yet four months, and then cometh harvest? behold, I say unto you, Lift up your eyes, and look on the fields; for they are white already to harvest.', '0~3004~ 1~3756~ 2~5210~, 3~3754~ 4~2076~ 5~2089~ 7~5072~, 8~2532~ [9] 10~2064~ 11~2326~? 12~2400~, 14~3004~ 16~5213~, 18~1869~ 19~5216~ 20~3788~, 21~2532~ 23~2300~ 25~5561~; 26~3754~ 28~1526~ 29~3022~ 30~2235~ 31~4314~ 32~2326~.'),
  (30594, 62, 2, 28, 'And now, little children, abide in him; that, when he shall appear, we may have confidence, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3568~, 3~5040~, 4~3306~ 5~1722~ 6~846~; 7~2443~, 8~3752~ 11~5319~, 14~2192~ 15~3954~, 16~2532~ 17~3361~ 19~153~ 20~575~ 21~846~ 22~1722~ 23~846~ 24~3952~.'),
  (10081, 12, 19, 12, 'Have the gods of the nations delivered them which my fathers have destroyed; as Gozan, and Haran, and Rezeph, and the children of Eden which were in Thelasar?', '2~0430~ 5~01471~ 6~05337~ 10~01~ 12~07843~; [13] 14~01470~, 16~02771~, 18~07530~, 21~01121~ 23~05729~ [25] 27~08515~?'),
  (17266, 20, 30, 6, 'Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.', '0~03254~ 5~01697~, 8~03198~ 15~03576~.'),
  (6086, 6, 10, 16, 'But these five kings fled, and hid themselves in a cave at Makkedah.', '2~02568~ 3~04428~ 4~05127~, 6~02244~ 10~04631~ 12~04719~.'),
  (878, 1, 31, 1, 'And he heard the words of Laban''s sons, saying, Jacob hath taken away all that was our father''s; and of that which was our father''s hath he gotten all this glory.', '&para; 2~08085~ 4~01697~ 6~03837~ 7~01121~, 8~0559~, 9~03290~ 12~03947~ [15] 17~01~; [20] [22] 24~01~ 27~06213~ 30~03519~.'),
  (4199, 4, 15, 41, 'I am the LORD your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD your God.', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~, 9~03318~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~, 18~0430~: [20] 22~03068~ 24~0430~.'),
  (13838, 18, 38, 36, 'Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts? or who hath given understanding to the heart?', '2~07896~ 3~02451~ 7~02910~? 11~05414~ 12~0998~ 15~07907~?'),
  (23964, 40, 23, 36, 'Verily I say unto you, All these things shall come upon this generation.', '0~281~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3956~ 7~5023~ 9~2240~ 10~1909~ 11~5026~ 12~1074~.'),
  (6393, 6, 21, 5, 'And the rest of the children of Kohath had by lot out of the families of the tribe of Ephraim, and out of the tribe of Dan, and out of the half tribe of Manasseh, ten cities.', '2~03498~ 5~01121~ 7~06955~ [8] 10~01486~ 14~04940~ 17~04294~ 19~0669~, 24~04294~ 26~01835~, 31~02677~ 32~04294~ 34~04519~, 35~06235~ 36~05892~.'),
  (4913, 5, 1, 15, 'So I took the chief of your tribes, wise men, and known, and made them heads over you, captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, and captains over fifties, and captains over tens, and officers among your tribes.', '2~03947~ 4~07218~ 7~07626~, 8~02450~ 9~0582~, 11~03045~, 13~05414~ 15~07218~ 18~08269~ 20~0505~, 22~08269~ 24~03967~, 26~08269~ 28~02572~, 30~08269~ 32~06235~, 34~07860~ 37~07626~.'),
  (15273, 19, 84, 5, 'Blessed is the man whose strength is in thee; in whose heart are the ways of them.', '0~0835~ [1] 3~0120~ 5~05797~ [6] 11~03824~ [12] 14~04546~ [15 16]'),
  (15869, 19, 116, 12, 'What shall I render unto the LORD for all his benefits toward me?', '3~07725~ 6~03068~ [7] 10~08408~'),
  (10173, 12, 22, 20, 'Behold therefore, I will gather thee unto thy fathers, and thou shalt be gathered into thy grave in peace; and thine eyes shall not see all the evil which I will bring upon this place. And they brought the king word again.', '4~0622~ 8~01~, 13~0622~ 16~06913~ 18~07965~; 21~05869~ 24~07200~ 27~07451~ 31~0935~ 34~04725~. 37~07725~ 39~04428~ 40~01697~ 41~07725~.'),
  (22135, 28, 2, 21, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, I will hear, saith the LORD, I will hear the heavens, and they shall hear the earth;', '8~03117~, 11~06030~, 12~05002~ 14~03068~, 17~06030~ 19~08064~, 23~06030~ 25~0776~;'),
  (179, 1, 7, 19, 'And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth; and all the high hills, that were under the whole heaven, were covered.', '2~04325~ 3~01396~ 4~03966~ 5~03966~ 7~0776~; 11~01364~ 12~02022~, [14] 15~08478~ 18~08064~, 20~03680~.'),
  (12939, 18, 3, 26, 'I was not in safety, neither had I rest, neither was I quiet; yet trouble came.', '4~07951~, 8~08252~, 12~05117~; 14~07267~ 15~0935~.'),
  (7362, 9, 7, 3, 'And Samuel spake unto all the house of Israel, saying, If ye do return unto the LORD with all your hearts, then put away the strange gods and Ashtaroth from among you, and prepare your hearts unto the LORD, and serve him only: and he will deliver you out of the hand of the Philistines.', '&para; 1~08050~ 2~0559~ 6~01004~ 8~03478~, 9~0559~, 13~07725~ 16~03068~ 20~03824~, [21] 23~05493~ 25~05236~ 26~0430~ 28~06252~ 30~08432~ 33~03559~ 35~03824~ 38~03068~, 40~05647~ 46~05337~ 51~03027~ 54~06430~.'),
  (5800, 5, 32, 36, 'For the LORD shall judge his people, and repent himself for his servants, when he seeth that their power is gone, and there is none shut up, or left.', '2~03068~ 4~01777~ 6~05971~, 8~05162~ 12~05650~, 15~07200~ [17] 18~03027~ 20~0235~, [22 23] 24~0657~ 26~06113~, 28~05800~.'),
  (24595, 41, 9, 46, 'Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.', '0~3699~ 1~846~ 2~4663~ 3~5053~ 4~3756~, 5~2532~ 7~4442~ 8~4570~ 9~3756~ 10~4570~.'),
  (1872, 2, 12, 51, 'And it came to pass the selfsame day, that the LORD did bring the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt by their armies.', '6~06106~ 7~03117~, [8] 10~03068~ 12~03318~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 20~0776~ 22~04714~ 25~06635~.'),
  (21589, 26, 43, 8, 'In their setting of their threshold by my thresholds, and their post by my posts, and the wall between me and them, they have even defiled my holy name by their abominations that they have committed: wherefore I have consumed them in mine anger.', '2~05414~ 5~05592~ 8~05592~, 11~04201~ 12~0681~ 14~04201~, 17~07023~ 25~02930~ 27~06944~ 28~08034~ 31~08441~ 35~06213~: 39~03615~ 43~0639~.'),
  (9123, 11, 11, 7, 'Then did Solomon build an high place for Chemosh, the abomination of Moab, in the hill that is before Jerusalem, and for Molech, the abomination of the children of Ammon.', '2~08010~ 3~01129~ 6~01116~ 8~03645~, 10~08251~ 12~04124~, 15~02022~ [17] 18~06440~ 19~03389~, 22~04432~, 24~08251~ 27~01121~ 29~05983~.'),
  (11521, 14, 16, 3, 'There is a league between me and thee, as there was between my father and thy father: behold, I have sent thee silver and gold; go, break thy league with Baasha king of Israel, that he may depart from me.', '[0 1] 3~01285~ [9 10] 13~01~ 16~01~: 20~07971~ 22~03701~ 24~02091~; 25~03212~, 26~06565~ 28~01285~ 30~01201~ 31~04428~ 33~03478~, 37~05927~'),
  (556, 1, 22, 5, 'And Abraham said unto his young men, Abide ye here with the ass; and I and the lad will go yonder and worship, and come again to you.', '1~085~ 2~0559~ 6~05288~, 7~03427~ 12~02543~; 17~05288~ 19~03212~ 20~03541~ 22~07812~, 25~07725~'),
  (1480, 1, 49, 2, 'Gather yourselves together, and hear, ye sons of Jacob; and hearken unto Israel your father.', '2~06908~, 4~08085~, 6~01121~ 8~03290~; 10~08085~ 12~03478~ 14~01~.'),
  (1540, 2, 1, 3, 'Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,', '0~03485~, 1~02074~, 3~01144~,'),
  (12913, 18, 2, 13, 'So they sat down with him upon the ground seven days and seven nights, and none spake a word unto him: for they saw that his grief was very great.', '3~03427~ 8~0776~ 9~07651~ 10~03117~ 12~07651~ 13~03915~, 16~01696~ 18~01697~ 23~07200~ [25] 26~03511~ 28~03966~ 29~01431~.'),
  (17942, 23, 14, 5, 'The LORD hath broken the staff of the wicked, and the sceptre of the rulers.', '1~03068~ 3~07665~ 5~04294~ 8~07563~, [9] 11~07626~ 14~04910~.'),
  (18596, 23, 46, 1, 'Bel boweth down, Nebo stoopeth, their idols were upon the beasts, and upon the cattle: your carriages were heavy loaden; they are a burden to the weary beast.', '&para; 0~01078~ 2~03766~, 3~05015~ 4~07164~, 6~06091~ 10~02416~, 14~0929~: 16~05385~ [17] 19~06006~; [20 21] 23~04853~ 26~05889~ [27]'),
  (26818, 43, 18, 18, 'And the servants and officers stood there, who had made a fire of coals; for it was cold: and they warmed themselves: and Peter stood with them, and warmed himself.', '0~1161~ 2~1401~ 3~2532~ 4~5257~ 6~2476~, 9~4160~ 13~439~; 14~3754~ 16~2258~ 17~5592~: 18~2532~ 21~2328~: 22~1161~ 23~4074~ 24~2258~ 25~2476~* 26~3326~ 27~846~, 28~2532~ 30~2328~.'),
  (30787, 66, 4, 3, 'And he that sat was to look upon like a jasper and a sardine stone: and there was a rainbow round about the throne, in sight like unto an emerald.', '0~2532~ 3~2521~ 4~2258~ 7~3706~ 8~3664~ 10~2393~ 11~2532~ 13~4555~ 14~3037~: 15~2532~ [16 17] 19~2463~ 21~2943~ 23~2362~, 25~3706~ 26~3664~ 29~4664~.'),
  (21220, 26, 30, 7, 'And they shall be desolate in the midst of the countries that are desolate, and her cities shall be in the midst of the cities that are wasted.', '4~08074~ 7~08432~ 10~0776~ [11 12] 13~08074~, 16~05892~ 21~08432~ 24~05892~ [25 26] 27~02717~.'),
  (18111, 23, 24, 7, 'The new wine mourneth, the vine languisheth, all the merryhearted do sigh.', '2~08492~ 3~056~, 5~01612~ 6~0535~, 9~03820~ 10~08056~ 11~0584~.'),
  (9158, 11, 11, 42, 'And the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years.', '2~03117~ 4~08010~ 5~04427~ 7~03389~ 10~03478~ [11] 12~0705~ 13~08141~.'),
  (3948, 4, 8, 4, 'And this work of the candlestick was of beaten gold, unto the shaft thereof, unto the flowers thereof, was beaten work: according unto the pattern which the LORD had shewed Moses, so he made the candlestick.', '2~04639~ 5~04501~ [6 7] 8~04749~ 9~02091~, 12~03409~ 16~06525~ [18] 20~04749~: 24~04758~ 27~03068~ 29~07200~ 30~04872~, 33~06213~ 35~04501~.'),
  (3845, 4, 6, 17, 'And he shall offer the ram for a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the LORD, with the basket of unleavened bread: the priest shall offer also his meat offering, and his drink offering.', '3~06213~ 5~0352~ [6] 8~02077~ 11~08002~ 14~03068~, 17~05536~ 20~04682~: 22~03548~ 24~06213~ 28~04503~, 32~05262~.'),
  (2909, 3, 7, 25, 'For whosoever eateth the fat of the beast, of which men offer an offering made by fire unto the LORD, even the soul that eateth it shall be cut off from his people.', '2~0398~ 4~02459~ 7~0929~, 11~07126~ 16~0801~ 19~03068~, 22~05315~ 24~0398~ [25] 29~03772~ 32~05971~.'),
  (26739, 43, 15, 25, 'But this cometh to pass, that the word might be fulfilled that is written in their law, They hated me without a cause.', '0~235~ [1 4] 5~2443~ 7~3056~ 10~4137~ 13~1125~ 14~1722~ 15~846~ 16~3551~ 17~3754~,* 19~3404~ 20~3165~ 23~1432~.'),
  (5666, 5, 28, 49, 'The LORD shall bring a nation against thee from far, from the end of the earth, as swift as the eagle flieth; a nation whose tongue thou shalt not understand;', '1~03068~ 3~05375~ 5~01471~ 9~07350~, 12~07097~ 15~0776~, [16 17] 20~05404~ 21~01675~; 23~01471~ 25~03956~ 29~08085~;'),
  (5414, 5, 19, 2, 'Thou shalt separate three cities for thee in the midst of thy land, which the LORD thy God giveth thee to possess it.', '2~0914~ 3~07969~ 4~05892~ 9~08432~ 12~0776~, 15~03068~ 17~0430~ 18~05414~ 21~03423~'),
  (13592, 18, 30, 26, 'When I looked for good, then evil came unto me: and when I waited for light, there came darkness.', '2~06960~ 4~02896~, 6~07451~ 7~0935~ [8 9] 13~03176~ 15~0216~, 17~0935~ 18~0652~.'),
  (4426, 4, 23, 5, 'And the LORD put a word in Balaam''s mouth, and said, Return unto Balak, and thus thou shalt speak.', '2~03068~ 3~07760~ 5~01697~ 7~01109~ 8~06310~, 10~0559~, 11~07725~ 13~01111~, 18~01696~.'),
  (19274, 24, 12, 16, 'And it shall come to pass, if they will diligently learn the ways of my people, to swear by my name, The LORD liveth; as they taught my people to swear by Baal; then shall they be built in the midst of my people.', '9~03925~ 10~03925~ 12~01870~ 15~05971~, 17~07650~ 20~08034~, 22~03068~ 23~02416~; 26~03925~ 28~05971~ 30~07650~ 32~01168~; 37~01129~ 40~08432~ 43~05971~.'),
  (8751, 11, 1, 26, 'But me, even me thy servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and thy servant Solomon, hath he not called.', '[2] 5~05650~, 7~06659~ 9~03548~, 11~01141~ 13~01121~ 15~03077~, 18~05650~ 19~08010~, 23~07121~.'),
  (9425, 11, 20, 9, 'Wherefore he said unto the messengers of Benhadad, Tell my lord the king, All that thou didst send for to thy servant at the first I will do: but this thing I may not do. And the messengers departed, and brought him word again.', '2~0559~ 5~04397~ 7~01130~, 8~0559~ 10~0113~ 12~04428~, 17~07971~ 21~05650~ 24~07223~ 27~06213~: 30~01697~ 32~03201~ 34~06213~. 37~04397~ 38~03212~, 40~07725~ 42~01697~ 43~07725~.'),
  (1822, 2, 12, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~ 7~0175~ 10~0776~ 12~04714~, 13~0559~,'),
  (2049, 2, 19, 18, 'And mount Sinai was altogether on a smoke, because the LORD descended upon it in fire: and the smoke thereof ascended as the smoke of a furnace, and the whole mount quaked greatly.', '1~02022~ 2~05514~ 7~06225~, 8~0834~ 9~06440~ 10~03068~ 11~03381~ 15~0784~: 18~06227~ 20~05927~ 23~06227~ 26~03536~, 30~02022~ 31~02729~ 32~03966~.'),
  (24661, 41, 11, 10, 'Blessed be the kingdom of our father David, that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest.', '0~2127~ [1] 3~932~ 5~2257~ 6~3962~ 7~1138~, 9~2064~ 10~1722~ 12~3686~ 15~2962~: 16~5614~ 17~1722~ 19~5310~.'),
  (8337, 10, 13, 13, 'And I, whither shall I cause my shame to go? and as for thee, thou shalt be as one of the fools in Israel. Now therefore, I pray thee, speak unto the king; for he will not withhold me from thee.', '7~02781~ 9~03212~? 18~0259~ 21~05036~ 23~03478~. 29~01696~ 32~04428~; 37~04513~'),
  (14799, 19, 58, 11, 'So that a man shall say, Verily there is a reward for the righteous: verily he is a God that judgeth in the earth.', '3~0120~ 5~0559~, [7 8] 10~06529~ 13~06662~: 16~03426~ 18~0430~ 20~08199~ 23~0776~.'),
  (8696, 10, 23, 35, 'Hezrai the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite,', '0~02695~ 2~03761~, 3~06474~ 5~0701~,'),
  (22933, 38, 4, 2, 'And said unto me, What seest thou? And I said, I have looked, and behold a candlestick all of gold, with a bowl upon the top of it, and his seven lamps thereon, and seven pipes to the seven lamps, which are upon the top thereof:', '1~0559~ 5~07200~ 9~0559~, 12~07200~, 16~04501~ [18] 19~02091~, 22~01531~ 25~07218~ 30~07651~ 31~05216~ 34~07651~ 35~04166~ 38~07651~ 39~05216~, [41] 44~07218~'),
  (6107, 6, 10, 37, 'And they took it, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and the king thereof, and all the cities thereof, and all the souls that were therein; he left none remaining, according to all that he had done to Eglon; but destroyed it utterly, and all the souls that were therein.', '2~03920~ 5~05221~ 9~06310~ 12~02719~, 15~04428~ 20~05892~ 25~05315~ [27] 30~07604~ 32~08300~, 39~06213~ 41~05700~; 43~02763~ 49~05315~ [51]'),
  (27108, 44, 5, 33, 'When they heard that, they were cut to the heart, and took counsel to slay them.', '0~1161~ 2~191~ [3] 6~1282~ [7 9] 10~2532~ 12~1011~ 14~337~ 15~846~.'),
  (3856, 4, 7, 1, 'And it came to pass on the day that Moses had fully set up the tabernacle, and had anointed it, and sanctified it, and all the instruments thereof, both the altar and all the vessels thereof, and had anointed them, and sanctified them;', '&para; 7~03117~ 9~04872~ 11~03615~ 13~06965~ 15~04908~, 18~04886~ 21~06942~ 26~03627~ 30~04196~ 34~03627~ 38~04886~ 41~06942~'),
  (13481, 18, 26, 5, 'Dead things are formed from under the waters, and the inhabitants thereof.', '&para; 0~07496~ [1] 3~02342~ 7~04325~, 10~07931~'),
  (28513, 46, 7, 10, 'And unto the married I command, yet not I, but the Lord, Let not the wife depart from her husband:', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~1060~ 5~3853~, [6] 7~3756~ 8~1473~, 9~235~ 11~2962~, 12~5563~ 13~3361~ 15~1135~ 16~5563~ 17~575~ [18] 19~435~:'),
  (19616, 24, 27, 11, 'But the nations that bring their neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and serve him, those will I let remain still in their own land, saith the LORD; and they shall till it, and dwell therein.', '2~01471~ 4~0935~ 6~06677~ 9~05923~ 12~04428~ 14~0894~, 16~05647~ 23~03240~ 27~0127~, 28~05002~ 30~03068~; 34~05647~ 37~03427~'),
  (10457, 13, 5, 21, 'And they took away their cattle; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of asses two thousand, and of men an hundred thousand.', '3~07617~ 5~04735~; 8~01581~ 9~02572~ 10~0505~, 13~06629~ 15~03967~ 17~02572~ 18~0505~, 21~02543~ 23~0505~, 26~05315~ 27~0120~ 28~03967~ 29~0505~.'),
  (24417, 41, 5, 43, 'And he charged them straitly that no man should know it; and commanded that something should be given her to eat.', '0~2532~ 2~1291~ 3~846~ 4~4183~ 5~2443~ 7~3367~ 9~1097~ 10~5124~; 11~2532~ 12~2036~ 17~1325~ 18~846~ 20~5315~.'),
  (13512, 18, 27, 22, 'For God shall cast upon him, and not spare: he would fain flee out of his hand.', '[1] 3~07993~ 8~02550~: 11~01272~ 12~01272~ 16~03027~.'),
  (20204, 24, 50, 29, 'Call together the archers against Babylon: all ye that bend the bow, camp against it round about; let none thereof escape: recompense her according to her work; according to all that she hath done, do unto her: for she hath been proud against the LORD, against the Holy One of Israel.', '1~08085~ 3~07228~ 5~0894~: 9~01869~ 11~07198~, 12~02583~ 16~05439~; 20~06413~: 21~07999~ 26~06467~; 33~06213~, 34~06213~ 41~02102~ 44~03068~, 48~06918~ 50~03478~.'),
  (10283, 13, 1, 23, 'And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.', '1~0211~, 3~02341~, 5~03103~. [8] 10~01121~ 12~03355~.'),
  (9579, 12, 2, 20, 'And he said, Bring me a new cruse, and put salt therein. And they brought it to him.', '2~0559~, 3~03947~ 6~02319~ 7~06746~, 9~07760~ 10~04417~ 14~03947~ [15]'),
  (13717, 18, 34, 25, 'Therefore he knoweth their works, and he overturneth them in the night, so that they are destroyed.', '2~05234~ 4~04566~, 7~02015~ [8] 11~03915~, 16~01792~.'),
  (19987, 24, 42, 3, 'That the LORD thy God may shew us the way wherein we may walk, and the thing that we may do.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~05046~ 9~01870~ 13~03212~, 16~01697~ 20~06213~.'),
  (5199, 5, 10, 7, 'From thence they journeyed unto Gudgodah; and from Gudgodah to Jotbath, a land of rivers of waters.', '3~05265~ 5~01412~; 8~01412~ 10~03193~, 12~0776~ 14~05158~ 16~04325~.'),
  (7899, 9, 25, 31, 'That this shall be no grief unto thee, nor offence of heart unto my lord, either that thou hast shed blood causeless, or that my lord hath avenged himself: but when the LORD shall have dealt well with my lord, then remember thine handmaid.', '5~06330~ 9~04383~ 11~03820~ 14~0113~, 19~08210~ 20~01818~ 21~02600~, 25~0113~ 27~03467~ 32~03068~ 36~03190~ 39~0113~, 41~02142~ 43~0519~.'),
  (13955, 19, 2, 1, 'Why do the heathen rage, and the people imagine a vain thing?', '&para; 3~01471~ 4~07283~, 7~03816~ 8~01897~ 11~07385~?'),
  (24104, 40, 26, 40, 'And he cometh unto the disciples, and findeth them asleep, and saith unto Peter, What, could ye not watch with me one hour?', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~4314~ 5~3101~, 6~2532~ 7~2147~ 8~846~ 9~2518~, 10~2532~ 11~3004~ 13~4074~, 14~3779~, 16~2480~ 17~3756~ 18~1127~ 19~3326~ 20~1700~ 21~3391~ 22~5610~?'),
  (30513, 61, 1, 18, 'And this voice which came from heaven we heard, when we were with him in the holy mount.', '0~2532~ 1~5026~ 2~5456~ 4~5342~ 5~1537~ 6~3772~ 7~2249~ 8~191~, 11~5607~ 12~4862~ 13~846~ 14~1722~ 16~40~ 17~3735~.'),
  (19774, 24, 32, 34, 'But they set their abominations in the house, which is called by my name, to defile it.', '2~07760~ 4~08251~ 7~01004~, 10~07121~ 13~08034~, 15~02930~'),
  (14660, 19, 49, 3, 'My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.', '1~06310~ 3~01696~ 5~02454~; 8~01900~ 11~03820~ [12 13] 15~08394~.'),
  (23024, 38, 9, 16, 'And the LORD their God shall save them in that day as the flock of his people: for they shall be as the stones of a crown, lifted up as an ensign upon his land.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~03467~ 10~03117~ 13~06629~ 16~05971~: [19 21] 23~068~ 26~05145~, 31~05264~ 34~0127~.'),
  (5681, 5, 28, 64, 'And the LORD shall scatter thee among all people, from the one end of the earth even unto the other; and there thou shalt serve other gods, which neither thou nor thy fathers have known, even wood and stone.', '2~03068~ 4~06327~ 8~05971~, 12~07097~ 15~0776~ 19~07097~; 24~05647~ 25~0312~ 26~0430~, 32~01~ 34~03045~, [35] 36~06086~ 38~068~.'),
  (25838, 42, 20, 45, 'Then in the audience of all the people he said unto his disciples,', '0~1161~ 3~191~ 5~3956~ 7~2992~ 9~2036~ 11~846~ 12~3101~,'),
  (5600, 5, 27, 9, 'And Moses and the priests the Levites spake unto all Israel, saying, Take heed, and hearken, O Israel; this day thou art become the people of the LORD thy God.', '1~04872~ 4~03548~ 6~03881~ 7~01696~ 10~03478~, 11~0559~, 13~05535~, 15~08085~, 17~03478~; 19~03117~ 22~01961~ 24~05971~ 27~03068~ 29~0430~.'),
  (9731, 12, 7, 16, 'And the people went out, and spoiled the tents of the Syrians. So a measure of fine flour was sold for a shekel, and two measures of barley for a shekel, according to the word of the LORD.', '2~05971~ 4~03318~, 6~0962~ 8~04264~ 11~0758~. 14~05429~ 17~05560~ [19] 22~08255~, 25~05429~ 27~08184~ 30~08255~, 34~01697~ 37~03068~.'),
  (17815, 23, 7, 24, 'With arrows and with bows shall men come thither; because all the land shall become briers and thorns.', '1~02671~ 4~07198~ [6] 7~0935~ 12~0776~ 15~08068~ 17~07898~.'),
  (24538, 41, 8, 27, 'And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2424~ 3~1831~, 4~2532~ 5~846~ 6~3101~, 7~1519~ 9~2968~ 11~2542~ 12~5376~: 13~2532~ 14~1722~ 16~3598~ 18~1905~ 19~846~ 20~3101~, 21~3004~ 23~846~, 24~5101~ 25~3004~ 26~444~ 27~3004~ 29~3165~ 30~1511~?');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (17212, 20, 28, 7, 'Whoso keepeth the law is a wise son: but he that is a companion of riotous men shameth his father.', '&para; 1~05341~ 3~08451~ [4] 6~0995~ 7~01121~: 13~07462~ 15~02151~ [16] 17~03637~ 19~01~.'),
  (30180, 58, 10, 31, 'It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God.', '[0 1] 4~5398~ 6~1706~ 7~1519~ 9~5495~ 12~2198~ 13~2316~.'),
  (24193, 40, 27, 54, 'Now when the centurion, and they that were with him, watching Jesus, saw the earthquake, and those things that were done, they feared greatly, saying, Truly this was the Son of God.', '0~1161~ 3~1543~, 4~2532~ 8~3326~ 9~846~, 10~5083~ 11~2424~, 12~1492~ 14~4578~, 15~2532~ 20~1096~, 22~5399~ 23~4970~, 24~3004~, 25~230~ 26~3778~ 27~2258~ 29~5207~ 31~2316~.'),
  (4627, 4, 29, 13, 'And ye shall offer a burnt offering, a sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD; thirteen young bullocks, two rams, and fourteen lambs of the first year; they shall be without blemish:', '3~07126~ 6~05930~, 11~0801~, 14~05207~ 15~07381~ 18~03068~; 19~06240~ 20~07969~* 21~01121~ 22~01241~* 23~06499~, 24~08147~ 25~0352~, [26] 27~06240~ 28~0702~* 29~03532~ 32~01121~ 33~08141~; 38~08549~:'),
  (13695, 18, 34, 3, 'For the ear trieth words, as the mouth tasteth meat.', '2~0241~ 3~0974~ 4~04405~, 7~02441~ 8~02938~ 9~0398~.'),
  (25411, 42, 10, 36, 'Which now of these three, thinkest thou, was neighbour unto him that fell among the thieves?', '0~5101~ 1~3767~ 3~5130~ 4~5140~, 5~1380~ 6~4671~, 7~1096~ 8~4139~ 12~1706~ 13~1519~ 15~3027~?'),
  (20853, 26, 17, 19, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; As I live, surely mine oath that he hath despised, and my covenant that he hath broken, even it will I recompense upon his own head.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; [6] 8~02416~, 11~0423~ 15~0959~, 18~01285~ 22~06331~, 27~05414~ 31~07218~.'),
  (7709, 9, 18, 26, 'And when his servants told David these words, it pleased David well to be the king''s son in law: and the days were not expired.', '3~05650~ 4~05046~ 5~01732~ 7~01697~, 9~03474~ 10~05869~* 11~01697~)01732 16~04428~ 19~02859~: 22~03117~ 25~04390~.'),
  (15435, 19, 92, 15, 'To shew that the LORD is upright: he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.', '1~05046~ 4~03068~ [5] 6~03477~: [7 8] 10~06697~, [12 13] 15~05766~ 16~05766~*'),
  (5006, 5, 3, 25, 'I pray thee, let me go over, and see the good land that is beyond Jordan, that goodly mountain, and Lebanon.', '6~05674~, 8~07200~ 10~02896~ 11~0776~ [13] 14~05676~ 15~03383~, 17~02896~ 18~02022~, 20~03844~.'),
  (21335, 26, 34, 13, 'And I will bring them out from the people, and gather them from the countries, and will bring them to their own land, and feed them upon the mountains of Israel by the rivers, and in all the inhabited places of the country.', '5~03318~ 8~05971~, 10~06908~ 14~0776~, 17~0935~ 22~0127~, 24~07462~ 28~02022~ 30~03478~ 33~0650~, 39~04186~ 42~0776~.'),
  (24879, 41, 15, 42, 'And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2235~ 4~3798~ 6~1096~, 7~1893~ 9~2258~ 11~3904~, 12~3603~ 13~2076~, 18~4315~,'),
  (13965, 19, 2, 11, 'Serve the LORD with fear, and rejoice with trembling.', '0~05647~ 2~03068~ 4~03374~, 6~01523~ 8~07461~.'),
  (14249, 19, 23, 5, 'Thou preparest a table before me in the presence of mine enemies: thou anointest my head with oil; my cup runneth over.', '1~06186~ 3~07979~ 4~06440~ 11~06887~: 13~01878~ 15~07218~ 17~08081~; 19~03563~ 21~07310~.'),
  (15655, 19, 105, 40, 'The people asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.', '[0 1] 2~07592~, 5~0935~ 6~07958~, 8~07646~ 12~03899~ 14~08064~.'),
  (744, 1, 27, 13, 'And his mother said unto him, Upon me be thy curse, my son: only obey my voice, and go fetch me them.', '2~0517~ 3~0559~ [8] 10~07045~, 12~01121~: 14~08085~ 16~06963~, 18~03212~ 19~03947~ [21]'),
  (25388, 42, 10, 13, 'Woe unto thee, Chorazin! woe unto thee, Bethsaida! for if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon, which have been done in you, they had a great while ago repented, sitting in sackcloth and ashes.', '0~3759~ 2~4671~, 3~5523~! 4~3759~ 6~4671~, 7~966~! 8~3754~ 9~1487~ 12~1411~ 15~1096~ 16~1722~ 17~5184~ 18~2532~ 19~4605~, 20~3588~ 23~1096~ 24~1722~ 25~5213~, 27~3340~ 31~3819~ 32~3340~, 33~2521~ 34~1722~ 35~302~* 36~4526~ 37~2532~ 38~4700~.'),
  (2836, 3, 5, 1, 'And if a soul sin, and hear the voice of swearing, and is a witness, whether he hath seen or known of it; if he do not utter it, then he shall bear his iniquity.', '&para; 3~05315~ 4~02398~, 6~08085~ 8~06963~ 10~0423~, [12] 14~05707~, 15~0176~ 18~07200~ 20~03045~ [21 22] 27~05046~ [28] 32~05375~ 34~05771~.'),
  (30410, 60, 1, 20, 'Who verily was foreordained before the foundation of the world, but was manifest in these last times for you,', '1~3303~ 3~4267~ 4~4253~ 6~2602~ 9~2889~, 10~1161~ 12~5319~ 13~1909~ 15~2078~ 16~5550~ 17~1223~ 18~5209~,'),
  (10385, 13, 3, 16, 'And the sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son.', '2~01121~ 4~03079~: 5~03204~ 7~01121~, 8~06667~ 10~01121~.'),
  (13732, 18, 35, 3, 'For thou saidst, What advantage will it be unto thee? and, What profit shall I have, if I be cleansed from my sin?', '2~0559~, 4~05532~ [10] 12~03276~ [16 19] 22~02403~?'),
  (6010, 6, 8, 2, 'And thou shalt do to Ai and her king as thou didst unto Jericho and her king: only the spoil thereof, and the cattle thereof, shall ye take for a prey unto yourselves: lay thee an ambush for the city behind it.', '3~06213~ 5~05857~ 8~04428~ 11~06213~ 13~03405~ 16~04428~: 19~07998~ 23~0929~ 30~0962~ 33~07760~ 36~0693~ 39~05892~ 40~0310~'),
  (9771, 12, 9, 7, 'And thou shalt smite the house of Ahab thy master, that I may avenge the blood of my servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants of the LORD, at the hand of Jezebel.', '3~05221~ 5~01004~ 7~0256~ 9~0113~, 13~05358~ 15~01818~ 18~05650~ 20~05030~, 23~01818~ 27~05650~ 30~03068~, 33~03027~ 35~0348~.'),
  (9713, 12, 6, 31, 'Then he said, God do so and more also to me, if the head of Elisha the son of Shaphat shall stand on him this day.', '2~0559~, 3~0430~ 4~06213~ 7~03254~ 13~07218~ 15~0477~ 17~01121~ 19~08202~ 21~05975~ 25~03117~.'),
  (19452, 24, 21, 3, 'Then said Jeremiah unto them, Thus shall ye say to Zedekiah:', '1~0559~ 2~03414~ 8~0559~ 10~06667~:'),
  (3986, 4, 9, 16, 'So it was alway: the cloud covered it by day, and the appearance of fire by night.', '3~08548~: 5~06051~ 6~03680~ [8 9] 12~04758~ 14~0784~ 16~03915~.'),
  (20193, 24, 50, 18, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will punish the king of Babylon and his land, as I have punished the king of Assyria.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~, 8~0430~ 10~03478~; 14~06485~ 16~04428~ 18~0894~ 21~0776~, 25~06485~ 27~04428~ 29~0804~.'),
  (11190, 13, 29, 18, 'O LORD God of Abraham, Isaac, and of Israel, our fathers, keep this for ever in the imagination of the thoughts of the heart of thy people, and prepare their heart unto thee:', '1~03068~ 2~0430~ 4~085~, 5~03327~, 8~03478~, 10~01~, 11~08104~ 14~05769~ 17~03336~ 20~04284~ 23~03824~ 26~05971~, 28~03559~ 30~03824~'),
  (22294, 28, 14, 3, 'Asshur shall not save us; we will not ride upon horses: neither will we say any more to the work of our hands, Ye are our gods: for in thee the fatherless findeth mercy.', '0~0804~ 3~03467~ 8~07392~ 10~05483~: 14~0559~ 19~04639~ 22~03027~, [23 24] 26~0430~: 31~03490~ 33~07355~.'),
  (18205, 23, 29, 3, 'And I will camp against thee round about, and will lay siege against thee with a mount, and I will raise forts against thee.', '3~02583~ 7~01754~, 11~06696~ 16~04674~, 20~06965~ 21~04694~'),
  (30246, 58, 12, 18, 'For ye are not come unto the mount that might be touched, and that burned with fire, nor unto blackness, and darkness, and tempest,', '&para; 0~1063~ 2~4334~ 3~3756~ 4~4334~ 7~3735~ 11~5584~, 12~2532~ 14~2545~ 16~4442~, 17~2532~ 19~1105~, 20~2532~ 21~4655~, 22~2532~ 23~2366~,'),
  (18632, 23, 48, 9, 'For my name''s sake will I defer mine anger, and for my praise will I refrain for thee, that I cut thee not off.', '&para; 2~08034~ 6~0748~ 8~0639~, 12~08416~ 15~02413~ 23~03772~.'),
  (4156, 4, 14, 43, 'For the Amalekites and the Canaanites are there before you, and ye shall fall by the sword: because ye are turned away from the LORD, therefore the LORD will not be with you.', '2~06003~ 5~03669~ [6] 8~06440~ 13~05307~ 16~02719~: 20~07725~ 21~0310~ 24~03068~, 27~03068~'),
  (21889, 27, 5, 6, 'Then the king''s countenance was changed, and his thoughts troubled him, so that the joints of his loins were loosed, and his knees smote one against another.', '0~0116~ 2~04430~ 3~02122~ 5~08133~, 8~07476~ 9~0927~ 14~07001~ 17~02783~ 19~08271~, 22~0755~ 23~05368~ 24~01668~ 26~01668~.'),
  (15827, 19, 113, 5, 'Who is like unto the LORD our God, who dwelleth on high,', '[1] 5~03068~ 7~0430~, 9~03427~ 11~01361~,'),
  (17741, 23, 3, 25, 'Thy men shall fall by the sword, and thy mighty in the war.', '1~04962~ 3~05307~ 6~02719~, 9~01369~ 12~04421~.'),
  (8633, 10, 22, 23, 'For all his judgments were before me: and as for his statutes, I did not depart from them.', '3~04941~ [4] [8 9] 11~02708~, 15~05493~'),
  (22397, 30, 2, 9, 'Yet destroyed I the Amorite before them, whose height was like the height of the cedars, and he was strong as the oaks; yet I destroyed his fruit from above, and his roots from beneath.', '&para; 1~08045~ 4~0567~ 5~06440~ 8~01363~ [9] 12~01363~ 15~0730~, [18] 19~02634~ 22~0437~; 25~08045~ 27~06529~ 29~04605~, 32~08328~'),
  (25942, 42, 22, 64, 'And when they had blindfolded him, they struck him on the face, and asked him, saying, Prophesy, who is it that smote thee?', '0~2532~ 4~4028~ 5~846~, 7~5180~ 8~846~ 11~4383~, 12~2532~ 13~1905~ 14~846~, 15~3004~, 16~4395~, 17~5101~ 19~2076~ 21~3817~ 22~4571~?'),
  (6773, 7, 9, 12, 'Then said the trees unto the vine, Come thou, and reign over us.', '1~0559~ 3~06086~ 6~01612~, 7~03212~ [9] 10~04427~'),
  (19791, 24, 33, 7, 'And I will cause the captivity of Judah and the captivity of Israel to return, and will build them, as at the first.', '5~07622~ 7~03063~ 10~07622~ 12~03478~ 14~07725~, 17~01129~ 22~07223~.'),
  (7565, 9, 14, 50, 'And the name of Saul''s wife was Ahinoam, the daughter of Ahimaaz: and the name of the captain of his host was Abner, the son of Ner, Saul''s uncle.', '2~08034~ 4~07586~ 5~0802~ [6] 7~0293~, 9~01323~ 11~0290~: 14~08034~ 17~08269~ 20~06635~ [21] 22~074~, 24~01121~ 26~05369~, 27~07586~ 28~01730~.'),
  (16182, 19, 134, 1, 'A Song of degrees. Behold, bless ye the LORD, all ye servants of the LORD, which by night stand in the house of the LORD.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3] 3~04609~ 5~01288~ 8~03068~, [10] 11~05650~ 14~03068~, 17~03915~ 18~05975~ 21~01004~ 24~03068~.'),
  (4402, 4, 22, 22, 'And God''s anger was kindled because he went: and the angel of the LORD stood in the way for an adversary against him. Now he was riding upon his ass, and his two servants were with him.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0639~ 4~02734~ 7~01980~: 10~04397~ 13~03068~ 14~03320~ 17~01870~ 20~07854~ 26~07392~ 29~0860~, 32~08147~ 33~05288~ [34]'),
  (25029, 42, 2, 44, 'But they, supposing him to have been in the company, went a day''s journey; and they sought him among their kinsfolk and acquaintance.', '0~1161~ 2~3543~ 3~846~ 6~1511~ 7~1722~ 9~4923~, 10~2064~ 12~2250~ 13~3598~; 14~2532~ 16~327~ 17~846~ 18~1722~ [19] 20~4773~ 21~1722~ 22~2532~* 23~1110~.'),
  (12749, 17, 2, 16, 'So Esther was taken unto king Ahasuerus into his house royal in the tenth month, which is the month Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign.', '1~0635~ 3~03947~ 5~04428~ 6~0325~ 9~01004~ 10~04438~ 13~06224~ 14~02320~, [16] 18~02320~ 19~02887~, 22~07651~ 23~08141~ 26~04438~.'),
  (2659, 2, 38, 21, 'This is the sum of the tabernacle, even of the tabernacle of testimony, as it was counted, according to the commandment of Moses, for the service of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar, son to Aaron the priest.', '&para; 0~0428~ 3~06485~ 6~04908~, [7] 10~04908~ 12~05715~, 16~06485~, 20~06310~ 22~04872~, [23] 25~05656~ 28~03881~, 31~03027~ 33~0385~, 34~01121~ 36~0175~ 38~03548~.'),
  (24691, 41, 12, 7, 'But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.', '0~1161~ 1~1565~ 2~1092~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 5~1438~, 6~3778~ 7~3754~* 8~2076~ 10~2818~; 11~1205~, 14~615~ 15~846~, 16~2532~ 18~2817~ 20~2071~ 21~2257~.'),
  (7896, 9, 25, 28, 'I pray thee, forgive the trespass of thine handmaid: for the LORD will certainly make my lord a sure house; because my lord fighteth the battles of the LORD, and evil hath not been found in thee all thy days.', '3~05375~ 5~06588~ 8~0519~: 11~03068~ 13~06213~ 14~06213~ 16~0113~ 18~0539~ 19~01004~; 22~0113~ 23~03898~ 25~04421~ 28~03068~, 30~07451~ 34~04672~ [37] 39~03117~.'),
  (29290, 49, 4, 2, 'With all lowliness and meekness, with longsuffering, forbearing one another in love;', '&para; 0~3326~ 1~3956~ 2~5012~ 3~2532~ 4~4236~, 5~3326~ 6~3115~, 7~430~ 9~240~ 10~1722~ 11~26~;'),
  (4346, 4, 21, 1, 'And when king Arad the Canaanite, which dwelt in the south, heard tell that Israel came by the way of the spies; then he fought against Israel, and took some of them prisoners.', '&para; [1] 2~04428~ 3~06166~ 5~03669~, 7~03427~ 10~05045~, 11~08085~ 14~03478~ 15~0935~ 18~01870~ 21~0871~; 24~03898~ 26~03478~, 28~07617~ [29] 32~07628~.'),
  (19986, 24, 42, 2, 'And said unto Jeremiah the prophet, Let, we beseech thee, our supplication be accepted before thee, and pray for us unto the LORD thy God, even for all this remnant; (for we are left but a few of many, as thine eyes do behold us:)', '1~0559~ 3~03414~ 5~05030~, 11~08467~ 13~05307~ 14~06440~ 17~06419~ 22~03068~ 24~0430~, [25] 29~07611~; 33~07604~ [34] 36~04592~ 38~07235~, 41~05869~ 43~07200~'),
  (3721, 4, 3, 24, 'And the chief of the house of the father of the Gershonites shall be Eliasaph the son of Lael.', '2~05387~ 5~01004~ 8~01~ 11~01649~ [12 13] 14~0460~ 16~01121~ 18~03815~.'),
  (19372, 24, 17, 6, 'For he shall be like the heath in the desert, and shall not see when good cometh; but shall inhabit the parched places in the wilderness, in a salt land and not inhabited.', '6~06199~ 9~06160~, 13~07200~ 15~02896~ 16~0935~; 19~07931~ 22~02788~ 25~04057~, [26] 28~04420~ 29~0776~ 32~03427~.'),
  (20578, 26, 6, 6, 'In all your dwellingplaces the cities shall be laid waste, and the high places shall be desolate; that your altars may be laid waste and made desolate, and your idols may be broken and cease, and your images may be cut down, and your works may be abolished.', '3~04186~ 5~05892~ 9~02717~, 13~01116~ 16~03456~; 19~04196~ 23~02717~ 26~0816~, 29~01544~ 32~07665~ 34~07673~, 37~02553~ 41~01438~, 44~04639~ 47~04229~.'),
  (29293, 49, 4, 5, 'One Lord, one faith, one baptism,', '0~1520~ 1~2962~, 2~1520~ 3~4102~, 4~3391~ 5~908~,'),
  (13872, 18, 39, 29, 'From thence she seeketh the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.', '3~02658~ 5~0400~, [6] 8~05869~ 9~05027~ 11~07350~.'),
  (1798, 2, 10, 16, 'Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron in haste; and he said, I have sinned against the LORD your God, and against you.', '1~06547~ 2~07121~ 4~04872~ 6~0175~ 8~04116~; 11~0559~, 14~02398~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~,'),
  (27919, 44, 28, 4, 'And when the barbarians saw the venomous beast hang on his hand, they said among themselves, No doubt this man is a murderer, whom, though he hath escaped the sea, yet vengeance suffereth not to live.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 3~915~ 4~1492~ [6] 7~2342~ 8~2910~ 9~1537~ 10~846~ 11~5495~, 13~3004~ 14~4314~ 15~240~, 17~3843~ 18~3778~ 19~444~ 20~2076~ 22~5406~, 23~3739~, 27~1295~ 28~1537~* 30~2281~, 32~1349~ 33~1439~ 34~3756~ 36~2198~.'),
  (4623, 4, 29, 9, 'And their meat offering shall be of flour mingled with oil, three tenth deals to a bullock, and two tenth deals to one ram,', '3~04503~ [4 6] 7~05560~ 8~01101~ 10~08081~, 11~07969~ 13~06241~ 16~06499~, [17] 18~08147~ 20~06241~ 22~0259~ 23~0352~,'),
  (18016, 23, 19, 3, 'And the spirit of Egypt shall fail in the midst thereof; and I will destroy the counsel thereof: and they shall seek to the idols, and to the charmers, and to them that have familiar spirits, and to the wizards.', '2~07307~ 4~04714~ 6~01238~ 9~07130~ 14~01104~ 16~06098~ 21~01875~ 24~0457~, 28~0328~, 35~0178~, 39~03049~.'),
  (7961, 9, 28, 12, 'And when the woman saw Samuel, she cried with a loud voice: and the woman spake to Saul, saying, Why hast thou deceived me? for thou art Saul.', '3~0802~ 4~07200~ 5~08050~, 7~02199~ 10~01419~ 11~06963~: 14~0802~ 15~0559~ 17~07586~, 18~0559~, 22~07411~ [26] 27~07586~.'),
  (18402, 23, 38, 3, 'And said, Remember now, O LORD, I beseech thee, how I have walked before thee in truth and with a perfect heart, and have done that which is good in thy sight. And Hezekiah wept sore.', '1~0559~, 2~02142~ 5~03068~, 7~0577~ 12~01980~ 13~06440~ 16~0571~ 20~08003~ 21~03820~, 24~06213~ [25 27] 28~02896~ 31~05869~. 33~02396~ 34~01058~ 35~01065~* 36~01419~.'),
  (22381, 30, 1, 8, 'And I will cut off the inhabitant from Ashdod, and him that holdeth the sceptre from Ashkelon, and I will turn mine hand against Ekron: and the remnant of the Philistines shall perish, saith the Lord GOD.', '4~03772~ 6~03427~ 8~0795~, 12~08551~ 14~07626~ 16~0831~, 20~07725~ 22~03027~ 24~06138~: 27~07611~ 30~06430~ 32~06~, 33~0559~ 35~0136~ 36~03069~.'),
  (29240, 49, 1, 18, 'The eyes of your understanding being enlightened; that ye may know what is the hope of his calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,', '1~3788~ 3~5216~ 4~1271~ 6~5461~; 7~1519~ 8~5209~ 10~1492~ 11~5101~ 12~2076~ 14~1680~ 16~846~ 17~2821~, 18~2532~ 19~5101~ 21~4149~ 24~1391~ 26~846~ 27~2817~ 28~1722~ 30~40~,'),
  (737, 1, 27, 6, 'And Rebekah spake unto Jacob her son, saying, Behold, I heard thy father speak unto Esau thy brother, saying,', '&para; 1~07259~ 2~0559~ 4~03290~ 6~01121~, 7~0559~, 10~08085~ 12~01~ 13~01696~ 15~06215~ 17~0251~, 18~0559~,'),
  (12608, 16, 11, 11, 'Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, was the ruler of the house of God.', '0~08304~ 2~01121~ 4~02518~, 6~01121~ 8~04918~, 10~01121~ 12~06659~, 14~01121~ 16~04812~, 18~01121~ 20~0285~, [21] 23~05057~ 26~01004~ 28~0430~.'),
  (6282, 6, 16, 10, 'And they drave not out the Canaanites that dwelt in Gezer: but the Canaanites dwell among the Ephraimites unto this day, and serve under tribute.', '4~03423~ 6~03669~ 8~03427~ 10~01507~: 13~03669~ 14~03427~ 15~07130~ 17~0669~ 20~03117~, 22~05647~ 24~04522~.'),
  (18832, 23, 60, 2, 'For, behold, the darkness shall cover the earth, and gross darkness the people: but the LORD shall arise upon thee, and his glory shall be seen upon thee.', '3~02822~ 5~03680~ 7~0776~, 10~06205~ 12~03816~: 15~03068~ 17~02224~ 22~03519~ 25~07200~'),
  (26566, 43, 11, 28, 'And when she had so said, she went her way, and called Mary her sister secretly, saying, The Master is come, and calleth for thee.', '0~2532~ 3~2036~ 4~5023~ 5~2036~, 9~565~, 10~2532~ 11~5455~ 12~3137~ 13~846~ 14~79~ 15~2977~, 16~2036~, 18~1320~ 20~3918~, 21~2532~ 23~5455~ 24~4571~.'),
  (7632, 9, 17, 7, 'And the staff of his spear was like a weaver''s beam; and his spear''s head weighed six hundred shekels of iron: and one bearing a shield went before him.', '2~06086~ 3~02671~* 6~02595~ [7] 10~0707~ 11~04500~; 14~02595~ 15~03852~ [16] 17~08337~ 18~03967~ 19~08255~ 21~01270~: 24~05375~ 26~06793~ 27~01980~ 28~06440~'),
  (2863, 3, 6, 9, 'Command Aaron and his sons, saying, This is the law of the burnt offering: It is the burnt offering, because of the burning upon the altar all night unto the morning, and the fire of the altar shall be burning in it.', '0~06680~ 1~0175~ 4~01121~, 5~0559~, [7] 9~08451~ 13~05930~: [15] 18~05930~, 22~04169~ 25~04196~ 27~03915~ 30~01242~, 33~0784~ 36~04196~ 39~03344~'),
  (921, 1, 31, 44, 'Now therefore come thou, let us make a covenant, I and thou; and let it be for a witness between me and thee.', '3~03212~, 6~03772~ 8~01285~, 18~05707~'),
  (21245, 26, 31, 6, 'All the fowls of heaven made their nests in his boughs, and under his branches did all the beasts of the field bring forth their young, and under his shadow dwelt all great nations.', '2~05775~ 4~08064~ 7~07077~ 10~05589~, 14~06288~ 18~02416~ 21~07704~ 25~03205~, 29~06738~ 30~03427~ 32~07227~ 33~01471~.'),
  (29009, 47, 11, 4, 'For if he that cometh preacheth another Jesus, whom we have not preached, or if ye receive another spirit, which ye have not received, or another gospel, which ye have not accepted, ye might well bear with him.', '0~1063~ 1~3303~ 2~1487~ 4~2064~ 5~2784~ 6~243~ 7~2424~, 8~3739~ 10~2784~ 11~3756~ 12~2784~, 13~2228~ [14] 16~2983~ 17~2087~ 18~4151~, 19~3739~ 21~2983~ 22~3756~ 23~2983~, 24~2228~ 25~2087~ 26~2098~, 27~3739~ 29~1209~ 30~3756~ 31~1209~, 33~430~ 34~2573~ 36~430~ [37]'),
  (17788, 23, 6, 10, 'Make the heart of this people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; lest they see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and convert, and be healed.', '2~03820~ 5~05971~ 6~08080~, 10~0241~ 11~03513~, 13~08173~ 15~05869~; 18~07200~ 21~05869~, 23~08085~ 26~0241~, 28~0995~ 31~03824~, 33~07725~, 36~07495~.'),
  (2865, 3, 6, 11, 'And he shall put off his garments, and put on other garments, and carry forth the ashes without the camp unto a clean place.', '4~06584~ 6~0899~, 9~03847~ 10~0312~ 11~0899~, 14~03318~ 16~01880~ 17~02351~ 19~04264~ 22~02889~ 23~04725~.'),
  (7146, 8, 1, 12, 'Turn again, my daughters, go your way; for I am too old to have an husband. If I should say, I have hope, if I should have an husband also to night, and should also bear sons;', '1~07725~, 3~01323~, 4~03212~ [5 6] 11~02204~ 15~0376~. 19~0559~, 21~03426~ 22~08615~, [23] 28~0376~ 31~03915~, 35~03205~ 36~01121~;'),
  (27289, 44, 10, 14, 'But Peter said, Not so, Lord; for I have never eaten any thing that is common or unclean.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~2036~, 4~3365~, 5~2962~; 6~3754~ 8~5315~ 9~3763~ 10~5315~ 12~3956~ 15~2839~ 16~2228~ 17~169~.'),
  (12258, 15, 9, 12, 'Now therefore give not your daughters unto their sons, neither take their daughters unto your sons, nor seek their peace or their wealth for ever: that ye may be strong, and eat the good of the land, and leave it for an inheritance to your children for ever.', '2~05414~ 5~01323~ 8~01121~, 10~05375~ 12~01323~ 15~01121~, 17~01875~ 19~07965~ 22~02896~ 23~05704~ 24~05769~: 29~02388~, 31~0398~ 33~02898~ 36~0776~, [39] 42~03423~ 45~01121~ 47~05769~.'),
  (27125, 44, 6, 8, 'And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and miracles among the people.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~4736~, 2~4134~ 4~4102~ 5~2532~ 6~1411~, 7~4160~ 8~3173~ 9~5059~ 10~2532~ 11~4592~ 12~1722~ 14~2992~.'),
  (28326, 45, 15, 7, 'Wherefore receive ye one another, as Christ also received us to the glory of God.', '&para; 0~1352~ 2~4355~ 4~240~, 5~2531~ 6~2532~* 7~5547~ 8~2531~ 9~4355~ 10~2248~ 11~1519~ 13~1391~ 15~2316~.'),
  (14109, 19, 16, 8, 'I have set the LORD always before me: because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.', '&para; 2~07737~ 4~03068~ 5~08548~ [9 10] 14~03225~, 19~04131~.'),
  (8447, 10, 16, 14, 'And the king, and all the people that were with him, came weary, and refreshed themselves there.', '2~04428~, 6~05971~ [8] 11~0935~ 12~05889~, 14~05314~'),
  (15795, 19, 109, 31, 'For he shall stand at the right hand of the poor, to save him from those that condemn his soul.', '3~05975~ 7~03225~ 10~034~, 12~03467~ [13] 17~08199~ 19~05315~.'),
  (11920, 14, 33, 3, 'For he built again the high places which Hezekiah his father had broken down, and he reared up altars for Baalim, and made groves, and worshipped all the host of heaven, and served them.', '2~01129~ 3~07725~ 6~01116~ 8~03169~ 10~01~ 13~05422~, 17~06965~ 18~04196~ 20~01168~, 22~06213~ 23~0842~, 25~07812~ 28~06635~ 30~08064~, 32~05647~'),
  (25535, 42, 13, 4, 'Or those eighteen, upon whom the tower in Siloam fell, and slew them, think ye that they were sinners above all men that dwelt in Jerusalem?', '0~2228~ 1~1565~ 2~3638~ 3~1176~* 4~2532~,* 5~1909~ 6~3739~ 8~4444~ 9~1722~ 10~4611~ 11~4098~, 12~2532~ 13~615~ 14~846~, 16~1380~ 17~3754~ 18~3778~ 19~1096~ 20~3781~ 21~3844~ 22~3956~ 23~444~ 25~2730~ 26~1722~ 27~2419~?'),
  (26165, 43, 3, 30, 'He must increase, but I must decrease.', '0~1565~ 1~1163~ 2~837~, 3~1161~ 4~1691~ [5] 6~1642~.'),
  (22622, 33, 3, 5, 'Thus saith the LORD concerning the prophets that make my people err, that bite with their teeth, and cry, Peace; and he that putteth not into their mouths, they even prepare war against him.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 6~05030~ 10~05971~ 11~08582~, 13~05391~ 16~08127~, 18~07121~, 19~07965~; 23~05414~ 27~06310~, 30~06942~ 31~04421~'),
  (2009, 2, 18, 5, 'And Jethro, Moses'' father in law, came with his sons and his wife unto Moses into the wilderness, where he encamped at the mount of God:', '1~03503~, 2~04872~ 5~02859~, 6~0935~ 9~01121~ 12~0802~ 14~04872~ 17~04057~, 20~02583~ 23~02022~ 25~0430~:'),
  (16568, 20, 6, 19, 'A false witness that speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.', '1~08267~ 2~05707~ [3] 4~06315~ 5~03577~, 9~07971~ 10~04090~ 12~0251~.'),
  (967, 1, 33, 2, 'And he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and Leah and her children after, and Rachel and Joseph hindermost.', '2~07760~ 4~08198~ 7~03206~ 8~07223~, 10~03812~ 13~03206~ 14~0314~, 16~07354~ 18~03130~ 19~0314~.'),
  (6179, 6, 13, 18, 'And Jahaza, and Kedemoth, and Mephaath,', '1~03096~, 3~06932~, 5~04158~,'),
  (26765, 43, 16, 24, 'Hitherto have ye asked nothing in my name: ask, and ye shall receive, that your joy may be full.', '0~737~ 1~2193~ 3~154~ 4~3762~ 5~3756~* 6~1722~ 7~3450~ 8~3686~: 9~154~, 10~2532~ 13~2983~, 14~2443~ 15~5216~ 16~5479~ 18~5600~ 19~4137~.'),
  (7013, 7, 18, 13, 'And they passed thence unto mount Ephraim, and came unto the house of Micah.', '2~05674~ 5~02022~ 6~0669~, 8~0935~ 11~01004~ 13~04318~.'),
  (30934, 66, 13, 10, 'He that leadeth into captivity shall go into captivity: he that killeth with the sword must be killed with the sword. Here is the patience and the faith of the saints.', '1~1536~ 2~4863~ 4~161~ 6~5217~ 7~1519~ 8~161~: 10~1536~ 11~615~ 12~1722~ 14~3162~ 15~1163~ 17~615~ 18~1722~ 20~3162~. 21~5602~ 22~2076~ 24~5281~ 25~2532~ 27~4102~ 30~40~.'),
  (14508, 19, 38, 9, 'Lord, all my desire is before thee; and my groaning is not hid from thee.', '0~0136~, 3~08378~ [4] 9~0585~ 12~05641~'),
  (18845, 23, 60, 15, 'Whereas thou hast been forsaken and hated, so that no man went through thee, I will make thee an eternal excellency, a joy of many generations.', '&para; 0~08478~ 4~05800~ 6~08130~, 12~05674~ [13] 16~07760~ 19~05769~ 20~01347~, 22~04885~ 24~01755~ 25~01755~.'),
  (4369, 4, 21, 24, 'And Israel smote him with the edge of the sword, and possessed his land from Arnon unto Jabbok, even unto the children of Ammon: for the border of the children of Ammon was strong.', '1~03478~ 2~05221~ 6~06310~ 9~02719~, 11~03423~ 13~0776~ 15~0769~ 17~02999~, 21~01121~ 23~05983~: 26~01366~ 29~01121~ 31~05983~ [32] 33~05794~.'),
  (7664, 9, 17, 39, 'And David girded his sword upon his armour, and he assayed to go; for he had not proved it. And David said unto Saul, I cannot go with these; for I have not proved them. And David put them off him.', '1~01732~ 2~02296~ 4~02719~ 7~04055~, 10~02974~ 12~03212~; 17~05254~ [18] 20~01732~ 21~0559~ 23~07586~, 25~03201~ 26~03212~ 33~05254~ [34] 36~01732~ 37~05493~');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (28508, 46, 7, 5, 'Defraud ye not one the other, except it be with consent for a time, that ye may give yourselves to fasting and prayer; and come together again, that Satan tempt you not for your incontinency.', '1~650~ 2~3361~ 5~240~, 6~302~ [7 7~1509~ 8] 8~5100~ 9~1537~ 10~4859~ 11~4314~ 13~2540~, 14~2443~ 18~4980~ 20~3521~ 21~2532~ 22~4335~; 23~2532~ 24~4905~ 25~846~ 26~1909~* 27~3825~, 28~3363~ 29~4567~ 30~3985~ 31~5209~ 32~3363~ 33~1223~ 34~5216~ 35~192~.'),
  (1011, 1, 34, 26, 'And they slew Hamor and Shechem his son with the edge of the sword, and took Dinah out of Shechem''s house, and went out.', '2~02026~ 3~02544~ 5~07927~ 7~01121~ 10~06310~ 13~02719~, 15~03947~ 16~01783~ 17~03947~ 19~07927~ 20~01004~, 23~03318~.'),
  (22234, 28, 9, 17, 'My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him: and they shall be wanderers among the nations.', '1~0430~ 5~03988~, 10~08085~ 17~05074~ 20~01471~.'),
  (5361, 5, 16, 13, 'Thou shalt observe the feast of tabernacles seven days, after that thou hast gathered in thy corn and thy wine:', '2~06213~ 4~02282~ 6~05521~ 7~07651~ 8~03117~, 13~0622~ 16~01637~ 19~03342~:'),
  (9017, 11, 8, 24, 'Who hast kept with thy servant David my father that thou promisedst him: thou spakest also with thy mouth, and hast fulfilled it with thine hand, as it is this day.', '2~08104~ 5~05650~ 6~01732~ 8~01~ 11~01696~ 14~01696~ 18~06310~, 21~04390~ [22] 25~03027~, [27 28] 30~03117~.'),
  (6581, 7, 3, 6, 'And they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their daughters to their sons, and served their gods.', '2~03947~ 4~01323~ 8~0802~, 10~05414~ 12~01323~ 15~01121~, 17~05647~ 19~0430~.'),
  (21138, 26, 27, 8, 'The inhabitants of Zidon and Arvad were thy mariners: thy wise men, O Tyrus, that were in thee, were thy pilots.', '1~03427~ 3~06721~ 5~0719~ 8~07751~: 10~02450~ [11] 13~06865~, [14] 20~02259~.'),
  (4491, 4, 25, 15, 'And the name of the Midianitish woman that was slain was Cozbi, the daughter of Zur; he was head over a people, and of a chief house in Midian.', '2~08034~ 5~04084~ 6~0802~ 9~05221~ [10] 11~03579~, 13~01323~ 15~06698~; [17] 18~07218~ 21~0523~, [22] 25~01~ 26~01004~ 28~04080~.'),
  (21078, 26, 24, 13, 'In thy filthiness is lewdness: because I have purged thee, and thou wast not purged, thou shalt not be purged from thy filthiness any more, till I have caused my fury to rest upon thee.', '2~02932~ [3] 4~02154~: 8~02891~ 14~02891~, 19~02891~ 22~02932~ 30~02534~ 32~05117~'),
  (29339, 49, 5, 19, 'Speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;', '0~2980~ 2~1438~ 4~5568~ 5~2532~ 6~5215~ 7~2532~ 8~4152~ 9~5603~, 10~103~ 11~2532~ 13~5567~ 14~1722~ 15~5216~ 16~2588~ 19~2962~;'),
  (15076, 19, 74, 19, 'O deliver not the soul of thy turtledove unto the multitude of the wicked: forget not the congregation of thy poor for ever.', '1~05414~ 4~05315~ 7~08449~ 10~02416~ [11 13] 14~07911~ 17~02416~ 20~06041~ 22~05331~.'),
  (5991, 6, 7, 9, 'For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land shall hear of it, and shall environ us round, and cut off our name from the earth: and what wilt thou do unto thy great name?', '2~03669~ 6~03427~ 9~0776~ 11~08085~ [12 13] 18~05437~, 21~03772~ 23~08034~ 26~0776~: 31~06213~ 34~01419~ 35~08034~?'),
  (25227, 42, 7, 20, 'When the men were come unto him, they said, John Baptist hath sent us unto thee, saying, Art thou he that should come? or look we for another?', '0~1161~ 2~435~ 4~3854~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 8~2036~, 9~2491~ 10~910~ 12~649~ 13~2248~ 14~4314~ 15~4571~, 16~3004~, 17~1488~ 18~4771~ 22~2064~? 23~2228~ 26~4328~ 27~243~?'),
  (7802, 9, 22, 8, 'That all of you have conspired against me, and there is none that sheweth me that my son hath made a league with the son of Jesse, and there is none of you that is sorry for me, or sheweth unto me that my son hath stirred up my servant against me, to lie in wait, as at this day?', '5~07194~ [9 10] 13~01540~ 14~0241~* 18~01121~ 22~03772~ 25~01121~ 27~03448~, [29 30] 36~02470~ 40~01540~ 41~0241~* 46~01121~ 49~06965~ 51~05650~ 57~0693~, 61~03117~?'),
  (19556, 24, 25, 13, 'And I will bring upon that land all my words which I have pronounced against it, even all that is written in this book, which Jeremiah hath prophesied against all the nations.', '3~0935~ 6~0776~ 9~01697~ 13~01696~ [16] 20~03789~ 23~05612~, 25~03414~ 27~05012~ 31~01471~.'),
  (11282, 14, 5, 6, 'Also king Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel that were assembled unto him before the ark, sacrificed sheep and oxen, which could not be told nor numbered for multitude.', '1~04428~ 2~08010~, 6~05712~ 8~03478~ 11~03259~ 14~06440~ 16~0727~, 17~02076~ 18~06629~ 20~01241~, 25~05608~ 27~04487~ 29~07230~.'),
  (18551, 23, 44, 9, 'They that make a graven image are all of them vanity; and their delectable things shall not profit; and they are their own witnesses; they see not, nor know; that they may be ashamed.', '&para; 2~03335~ 5~06459~ [6] 10~08414~; 14~02530~ 17~03276~; [20] 23~05707~; 25~07200~ 28~03045~; 33~0954~.'),
  (2119, 2, 22, 1, 'If a man shall steal an ox, or a sheep, and kill it, or sell it; he shall restore five oxen for an ox, and four sheep for a sheep.', '&para; 2~0376~ 4~01589~ 6~07794~, 9~07716~, 11~02873~ 14~04376~ 18~07999~ 19~02568~ 20~01241~ 23~07794~, 25~0702~ 26~06629~ 29~07716~.'),
  (29814, 54, 6, 10, 'For the love of money is the root of all evil: which while some coveted after, they have erred from the faith, and pierced themselves through with many sorrows.', '0~1063~ 4~5365~ 5~2076~ 7~4491~ 9~3956~ 10~2556~: 11~3739~ 13~5100~ 15~3713~, 18~635~ 19~575~ 21~4102~, 22~2532~ 23~4044~ 24~1438~ 25~4044~ 27~4183~ 28~3601~.'),
  (5314, 5, 14, 18, 'And the stork, and the heron after her kind, and the lapwing, and the bat.', '2~02624~, 5~0601~ 8~04327~, 11~01744~, 14~05847~.'),
  (16512, 20, 4, 13, 'Take fast hold of instruction; let her not go: keep her; for she is thy life.', '2~02388~ 4~04148~; [6] 8~07503~: 9~05341~ [13] 15~02416~.'),
  (1528, 1, 50, 17, 'So shall ye say unto Joseph, Forgive, I pray thee now, the trespass of thy brethren, and their sin; for they did unto thee evil: and now, we pray thee, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of thy father. And Joseph wept when they spake unto him.', '3~0559~ 5~03130~, 6~05375~, 9~0577~ 12~06588~ 15~0251~, 18~02403~; 21~01580~ 24~07451~: 30~05375~ 32~06588~ 35~05650~ 38~0430~ 41~01~. 43~03130~ 44~01058~ 47~01696~'),
  (3095, 3, 13, 38, 'If a man also or a woman have in the skin of their flesh bright spots, even white bright spots;', '&para; 2~0376~ 6~0802~ 10~05785~ 13~01320~ 15~0934~, [16] 17~03836~ 19~0934~;'),
  (11285, 14, 5, 9, 'And they drew out the staves of the ark, that the ends of the staves were seen from the ark before the oracle; but they were not seen without. And there it is unto this day.', '3~0748~ 5~0905~ [6 8] 11~07218~ 14~0905~ 16~07200~ 19~0727~ 20~06440~ 22~01687~; 27~07200~ 28~02351~. 35~03117~.'),
  (17596, 22, 4, 5, 'Thy two breasts are like two young roes that are twins, which feed among the lilies.', '1~08147~ 2~07699~ [3] 5~08147~ 6~06082~ 7~06646~ 10~08380~, 12~07462~ 15~07799~.'),
  (26753, 43, 16, 12, 'I have yet many things to say unto you, but ye cannot bear them now.', '1~2192~ 2~2089~ 4~4183~ 6~3004~ 8~5213~, 9~235~ 11~1410~ 12~3756~* 14~941~ 15~737~.'),
  (14945, 19, 69, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Shoshannim, A Psalm of David. Save me, O God; for the waters are come in unto my soul.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~07799~, [6 7] 9] 9~01732~ 10~03467~ 13~0430~; 16~04325~ 18~0935~ [21] 22~05315~.'),
  (9323, 11, 16, 32, 'And he reared up an altar for Baal in the house of Baal, which he had built in Samaria.', '3~06965~ 5~04196~ 7~01168~ 10~01004~ 12~01168~, 16~01129~ 18~08111~.'),
  (16134, 19, 127, 4, 'As arrows are in the hand of a mighty man; so are children of the youth.', '1~02671~ [2] 5~03027~ 9~01368~; [11] 12~01121~ 15~05271~.'),
  (29876, 55, 3, 7, 'Ever learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.', '0~3842~ 1~3129~, 2~2532~ 3~3368~ 4~1410~ 6~2064~ 7~1519~ 9~1922~ 12~225~.'),
  (18707, 23, 52, 2, 'Shake thyself from the dust; arise, and sit down, O Jerusalem: loose thyself from the bands of thy neck, O captive daughter of Zion.', '0~05287~ 4~06083~; 5~06965~, [6] 8~03427~, 10~03389~: 11~06605~ 15~04147~ 18~06677~, 20~07628~ 21~01323~ 23~06726~.'),
  (664, 1, 25, 2, 'And she bare him Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah.', '2~03205~ 4~02175~, 6~03370~, 8~04091~, 10~04080~, 12~03435~, 14~07744~.'),
  (3031, 3, 11, 29, 'These also shall be unclean unto you among the creeping things that creep upon the earth; the weasel, and the mouse, and the tortoise after his kind,', '[2 3] 4~02931~ 10~08318~ 12~08317~ 15~0776~; 17~02467~, 20~05909~, 23~06632~ 26~04327~,'),
  (8530, 10, 19, 11, 'And king David sent to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, saying, Speak unto the elders of Judah, saying, Why are ye the last to bring the king back to his house? seeing the speech of all Israel is come to the king, even to his house.', '1~04428~ 2~01732~ 3~07971~ 5~06659~ 8~054~ 10~03548~, 11~0559~, 12~01696~ 15~02205~ 17~03063~, 18~0559~, 23~0314~ 25~07725~ 27~04428~ 28~07725~ 31~01004~? 34~01697~ 37~03478~ 39~0935~ 42~04428~, [43] 46~01004~.'),
  (11402, 14, 9, 30, 'And Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years.', '1~08010~ 2~04427~ 4~03389~ 7~03478~ 8~0705~ 9~08141~.'),
  (9818, 12, 10, 17, 'And when he came to Samaria, he slew all that remained unto Ahab in Samaria, till he had destroyed him, according to the saying of the LORD, which he spake to Elijah.', '3~0935~ 5~08111~, 7~05221~ 10~07604~ 12~0256~ 14~08111~, 18~08045~ 23~01697~ 26~03068~, 29~01696~ 31~0452~.'),
  (25095, 42, 4, 20, 'And he closed the book, and he gave it again to the minister, and sat down. And the eyes of all them that were in the synagogue were fastened on him.', '0~2532~ 2~4428~ 4~975~, [8] 9~591~ 12~5257~, 15~2523~. 16~2532~ 18~3788~ 21~3956~ 23~2258~ 24~1722~ 26~4864~ 28~816~ 30~846~.'),
  (17693, 23, 1, 30, 'For ye shall be as an oak whose leaf fadeth, and as a garden that hath no water.', '6~0424~ 8~05929~ 9~05034~, 13~01593~ 17~04325~.'),
  (1703, 2, 7, 13, 'And he hardened Pharaoh''s heart, that he hearkened not unto them; as the LORD had said.', '2~02388~ 3~06547~ 4~03820~, 7~08085~ 13~03068~ 15~01696~.'),
  (10115, 12, 20, 9, 'And Isaiah said, This sign shalt thou have of the LORD, that the LORD will do the thing that he hath spoken: shall the shadow go forward ten degrees, or go back ten degrees?', '1~03470~ 2~0559~, 4~0226~ 10~03068~, 13~03068~ 15~06213~ 17~01697~ 21~01696~: 24~06738~ 26~01980~ 27~06235~ 28~04609~, 31~07725~ 32~06235~ 33~04609~?'),
  (19657, 24, 29, 13, 'And ye shall seek me, and find me, when ye shall search for me with all your heart.', '3~01245~ 6~04672~ [7] 11~01875~ 17~03824~.'),
  (16249, 19, 139, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. O LORD, thou hast searched me, and known me.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 9~03068~, 12~02713~ 15~03045~ [16]'),
  (13815, 18, 38, 13, 'That it might take hold of the ends of the earth, that the wicked might be shaken out of it?', '4~0270~ 7~03671~ 10~0776~, 13~07563~ 17~05287~'),
  (4660, 4, 30, 6, 'And if she had at all an husband, when she vowed, or uttered ought out of her lips, wherewith she bound her soul;', '7~0376~, 10~05088~, 12~04008~ 17~08193~, 20~0631~ 22~05315~;'),
  (11859, 14, 30, 23, 'And the whole assembly took counsel to keep other seven days: and they kept other seven days with gladness.', '3~06951~ 5~03289~ 7~06213~ 8~0312~ 9~07651~ 10~03117~: 13~06213~ [14] 15~07651~ 16~03117~ 18~08057~.'),
  (30099, 58, 7, 19, 'For the law made nothing perfect, but the bringing in of a better hope did; by the which we draw nigh unto God.', '0~1063~ 2~3551~ 3~5048~ 4~3762~ 5~5048~, 6~1161~ 9~1898~ 12~2909~ 13~1680~ [14] 15~1223~ 17~3739~ 20~1448~ 22~2316~.'),
  (16251, 19, 139, 3, 'Thou compassest my path and my lying down, and art acquainted with all my ways.', '1~02219~ 3~0734~ 7~07252~, 10~05532~ [11] 14~01870~.'),
  (9065, 11, 9, 6, 'But if ye shall at all turn from following me, ye or your children, and will not keep my commandments and my statutes which I have set before you, but go and serve other gods, and worship them:', '[0] 5~07725~ 6~07725~ 8~0310~ 13~01121~, 17~08104~ 19~04687~ [20] 22~02708~ 26~05414~ 27~06440~ 30~01980~ 32~05647~ 33~0312~ 34~0430~, 36~07812~'),
  (7582, 9, 15, 15, 'And Saul said, They have brought them from the Amalekites: for the people spared the best of the sheep and of the oxen, to sacrifice unto the LORD thy God; and the rest we have utterly destroyed.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~, 5~0935~ 9~06003~: 12~05971~ 13~02550~ 15~04315~ 18~06629~ 22~01241~, 24~02076~ 27~03068~ 29~0430~; 32~03498~ 36~02763~.'),
  (9475, 11, 21, 16, 'And it came to pass, when Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, that Ahab rose up to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.', '6~0256~ 7~08085~ 9~05022~ 11~04191~, 13~0256~ 15~06965~ 18~03381~ 21~03754~ 23~05022~ 25~03158~, 28~03423~'),
  (28529, 46, 7, 26, 'I suppose therefore that this is good for the present distress, I say, that it is good for a man so to be.', '1~3543~ 2~3767~ 4~5124~ 5~5225~ 6~2570~ 7~1223~ 9~1764~ 10~318~, [11 12] 13~3754~ [14 15] 16~2570~ 19~444~ 20~3779~ 22~1511~.'),
  (22505, 30, 9, 1, 'I saw the Lord standing upon the altar: and he said, Smite the lintel of the door, that the posts may shake: and cut them in the head, all of them; and I will slay the last of them with the sword: he that fleeth of them shall not flee away, and he that escapeth of them shall not be delivered.', '&para; 1~07200~ 3~0136~ 4~05324~ 7~04196~: 10~0559~, 11~05221~ 16~03730~, 19~05592~ 21~07493~: 23~01214~ 27~07218~, 34~02026~ 36~0319~ 41~02719~: 44~05127~ 50~05127~, 54~06412~ 60~04422~.'),
  (29384, 50, 1, 7, 'Even as it is meet for me to think this of you all, because I have you in my heart; inasmuch as both in my bonds, and in the defence and confirmation of the gospel, ye all are partakers of my grace.', '&para; 1~2531~ 3~2076~ 4~1342~ 6~1698~ 8~5426~ 9~5124~ 10~5228~ 11~5216~ 12~3956~, 13~1223~ 15~2192~ 16~5209~ 17~1722~ 18~3165~ 19~2588~; 22~5037~ 23~1722~ 24~3450~ 25~1199~, 26~2532~ 29~627~ 30~2532~ 31~951~ 34~2098~, 35~5209~ 36~3956~ 37~5607~ 38~4791~ 40~3450~ 41~5485~.'),
  (23315, 40, 6, 23, 'But if thine eye be evil, thy whole body shall be full of darkness. If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness, how great is that darkness!', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 2~4675~ 3~3788~ 4~5600~ 5~4190~, 6~4675~ 7~3650~ 8~4983~ 10~2071~ 13~4652~. 14~1487~ 15~3767~ 17~5457~ 19~2076~ 20~1722~ 21~4671~ 23~4655~, 25~4214~ [26] 28~4655~!'),
  (7741, 9, 20, 4, 'Then said Jonathan unto David, Whatsoever thy soul desireth, I will even do it for thee.', '1~0559~ 2~03083~ 4~01732~, 7~05315~ 8~0559~, 12~06213~ [13]'),
  (9741, 12, 8, 6, 'And when the king asked the woman, she told him. So the king appointed unto her a certain officer, saying, Restore all that was hers, and all the fruits of the field since the day that she left the land, even until now.', '3~04428~ 4~07592~ 6~0802~, 8~05608~ 12~04428~ 13~05414~ 17~0259~ 18~05631~, 19~0559~, 20~07725~ [23] 28~08393~ 31~07704~ 34~03117~ 37~05800~ 39~0776~,'),
  (6040, 6, 8, 32, 'And he wrote there upon the stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he wrote in the presence of the children of Israel.', '2~03789~ 6~068~ 8~04932~ 11~08451~ 13~04872~, 16~03789~ 19~06440~ 22~01121~ 24~03478~.'),
  (21069, 26, 24, 4, 'Gather the pieces thereof into it, even every good piece, the thigh, and the shoulder; fill it with the choice bones.', '0~0622~ 2~05409~ [6] 8~02896~ 9~05409~, 11~03409~, 14~03802~; 15~04390~ [16] 19~04005~ 20~06106~.'),
  (17098, 20, 24, 10, 'If thou faint in the day of adversity, thy strength is small.', '&para; [0] 2~07503~ 5~03117~ 7~06869~, 9~03581~ [10] 11~06862~.'),
  (3569, 3, 26, 40, 'If they shall confess their iniquity, and the iniquity of their fathers, with their trespass which they trespassed against me, and that also they have walked contrary unto me;', '&para; 3~03034~ 5~05771~, 8~05771~ 11~01~, 14~04604~ 17~04603~ 25~01980~ 26~07147~'),
  (2249, 2, 26, 9, 'And thou shalt couple five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves, and shalt double the sixth curtain in the forefront of the tabernacle.', '3~02266~ 4~02568~ 5~03407~ 9~08337~ 10~03407~ 15~03717~ 17~08345~ 18~03407~ 21~06440~ 22~04136~ 24~0168~.'),
  (23686, 40, 16, 4, 'A wicked and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign; and there shall no sign be given unto it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas. And he left them, and departed.', '1~4190~ 2~2532~ 3~3428~ 4~1074~ 6~1934~ 8~4592~; 9~2532~ 12~3756~ 13~4592~ 15~1325~ 17~846~, 18~1508~ 20~4592~ 23~4396~ 24~2495~. 25~2532~ 27~2641~ 28~846~, 30~565~.'),
  (10790, 13, 14, 8, 'And when the Philistines heard that David was anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up to seek David. And David heard of it, and went out against them.', '&para; 3~06430~ 4~08085~ 6~01732~ 8~04886~ 9~04428~ 12~03478~, 15~06430~ 17~05927~ 19~01245~ 20~01732~. 22~01732~ 23~08085~ [24 25] 28~03318~ 29~06440~'),
  (23206, 40, 3, 4, 'And the same John had his raiment of camel''s hair, and a leathern girdle about his loins; and his meat was locusts and wild honey.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~2491~ 4~2192~ 5~846~ 6~1742~ 7~575~ 8~2574~ 9~2359~, 10~2532~ 12~1193~ 13~2223~ 14~4012~ 15~846~ 16~3751~; 17~1161~ 18~846~ 19~5160~ 20~2258~ 21~200~ 22~2532~ 23~66~ 24~3192~.'),
  (16040, 19, 119, 133, 'Order my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.', '&para; 0~03559~ 2~06471~ 5~0565~: 10~0205~ 12~07980~'),
  (5723, 5, 30, 9, 'And the LORD thy God will make thee plenteous in every work of thine hand, in the fruit of thy body, and in the fruit of thy cattle, and in the fruit of thy land, for good: for the LORD will again rejoice over thee for good, as he rejoiced over thy fathers:', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 8~03498~ 11~04639~ 14~03027~, 17~06529~ 20~0990~, 24~06529~ 27~0929~, 31~06529~ 34~0127~, 36~02896~: 39~03068~ 41~07725~ 42~07797~ 46~02896~, 49~07797~ 52~01~:'),
  (6715, 7, 7, 14, 'And his fellow answered and said, This is nothing else save the sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel: for into his hand hath God delivered Midian, and all the host.', '2~07453~ 3~06030~ 5~0559~, [7] 12~02719~ 14~01439~ 16~01121~ 18~03101~, 20~0376~ 22~03478~: [23] 26~03027~ 28~0430~ 29~05414~ 30~04080~, 34~04264~.'),
  (3302, 3, 19, 16, 'Thou shalt not go up and down as a talebearer among thy people: neither shalt thou stand against the blood of thy neighbour: I am the LORD.', '3~03212~ [7] 9~07400~ 12~05971~: 16~05975~ 19~01818~ 22~07453~: [24] 26~03068~.'),
  (19054, 24, 4, 18, 'Thy way and thy doings have procured these things unto thee; this is thy wickedness, because it is bitter, because it reacheth unto thine heart.', '1~01870~ 4~04611~ 6~06213~ [8] [12] 14~07451~, 18~04751~, 21~05060~ 24~03820~.'),
  (22570, 32, 3, 3, 'So Jonah arose, and went unto Nineveh, according to the word of the LORD. Now Nineveh was an exceeding great city of three days'' journey.', '1~03124~ 2~06965~, 4~03212~ 6~05210~, 10~01697~ 13~03068~. 15~05210~ 18~0430~ 19~01419~ 20~05892~ 22~07969~ 23~03117~ 24~04109~.'),
  (13215, 18, 15, 3, 'Should he reason with unprofitable talk? or with speeches wherewith he can do no good?', '2~03198~ 4~05532~ 5~01697~? 8~04405~ 14~03276~?'),
  (16478, 20, 3, 14, 'For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.', '2~05504~ [5] 6~02896~ 9~05505~ 11~03701~, 14~08393~ 18~02742~.'),
  (6105, 6, 10, 35, 'And they took it on that day, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and all the souls that were therein he utterly destroyed that day, according to all that he had done to Lachish.', '2~03920~ 6~03117~, 8~05221~ 12~06310~ 15~02719~, 19~05315~ [21] 25~02763~ 27~03117~, 34~06213~ 36~03923~.'),
  (19116, 24, 6, 18, 'Therefore hear, ye nations, and know, O congregation, what is among them.', '&para; 1~08085~, 3~01471~, 5~03045~, 7~05712~, [9]'),
  (23491, 40, 11, 22, 'But I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the day of judgment, than for you.', '0~4133~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 7~2071~ 9~414~ 11~5184~ 12~2532~ 13~4605~ 14~1722~ 16~2250~ 18~2920~, 19~2228~ 21~5213~.'),
  (20929, 26, 20, 25, 'Wherefore I gave them also statutes that were not good, and judgments whereby they should not live;', '2~05414~ 5~02706~ [6 7] 9~02896~, 11~04941~ 16~02421~;'),
  (5930, 6, 4, 14, 'On that day the LORD magnified Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and they feared him, as they feared Moses, all the days of his life.', '2~03117~ 4~03068~ 5~01431~ 6~03091~ 9~05869~ 12~03478~; 15~03372~ 19~03372~ 20~04872~, 23~03117~ 26~02416~.'),
  (1825, 2, 12, 4, 'And if the household be too little for the lamb, let him and his neighbour next unto his house take it according to the number of the souls; every man according to his eating shall make your count for the lamb.', '3~01004~ 4~01961~ 6~04591~ 9~07716~, 14~07934~ 15~07138~ 18~01004~ 19~03947~ [20] 24~04373~ 27~05315~; 29~0376~ 30~06310~ 33~0400~ 37~03699~ 40~07716~.'),
  (12183, 15, 7, 1, 'Now after these things, in the reign of Artaxerxes king of Persia, Ezra the son of Seraiah, the son of Azariah, the son of Hilkiah,', '&para; 1~0310~ 3~01697~, 6~04438~ 8~0783~ 9~04428~ 11~06539~, 12~05830~ 14~01121~ 16~08304~, 18~01121~ 20~05838~, 22~01121~ 24~02518~,'),
  (27912, 44, 27, 41, 'And falling into a place where two seas met, they ran the ship aground; and the forepart stuck fast, and remained unmoveable, but the hinder part was broken with the violence of the waves.', '0~1161~ 1~4045~ 2~1519~ 4~5117~ 8~1337~, 10~2027~ 12~3491~ 13~2027~; 14~2532~ 16~3303~ 17~4408~ 18~2043~, 20~3306~ 21~761~, 22~1161~ 25~4403~ 27~3089~ 28~5259~ 30~970~ 33~2949~.'),
  (20489, 26, 1, 16, 'The appearance of the wheels and their work was like unto the colour of a beryl: and they four had one likeness: and their appearance and their work was as it were a wheel in the middle of a wheel.', '1~04758~ 4~0212~ 7~04639~ [8] 12~05869~ 15~08658~: 18~0702~ 20~0259~ 21~01823~: 24~04758~ 27~04639~ [28] 33~0212~ 36~08432~ 39~0212~.'),
  (5281, 5, 13, 3, 'Thou shalt not hearken unto the words of that prophet, or that dreamer of dreams: for the LORD your God proveth you, to know whether ye love the LORD your God with all your heart and with all your soul.', '3~08085~ 6~01697~ 9~05030~, 12~02492~ 14~02472~: 17~03068~ 19~0430~ 20~05254~ 23~03045~ 25~03426~ 26~0157~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~ 34~03824~ 39~05315~.'),
  (21807, 27, 2, 40, 'And the fourth kingdom shall be strong as iron: forasmuch as iron breaketh in pieces and subdueth all things: and as iron that breaketh all these, shall it break in pieces and bruise.', '2~07244~ 3~04437~ 5~01934~ 6~08624~ 8~06523~: 11~06523~ 14~01855~ 16~02827~ 17~03606~ [18] 20~06903~ 21~06523~ 23~07490~ 24~03606~ 25~0459~, 30~01855~ 32~07490~.'),
  (2022, 2, 18, 18, 'Thou wilt surely wear away, both thou, and this people that is with thee: for this thing is too heavy for thee; thou art not able to perform it thyself alone.', '2~05034~ 4~05034~, 9~05971~ [11] 16~01697~ [17] 19~03515~ 25~03201~ 27~06213~'),
  (26003, 42, 23, 54, 'And that day was the preparation, and the sabbath drew on.', '0~2532~ 2~2250~ 3~2258~ 5~3904~, 6~2532~ 8~4521~ 10~2020~.'),
  (1404, 1, 46, 13, 'And the sons of Issachar; Tola, and Phuvah, and Job, and Shimron.', '2~01121~ 4~03485~; 5~08439~, 7~06312~, 9~03102~, 11~08110~.'),
  (15642, 19, 105, 27, 'They shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.', '1~07760~ 3~01697~ 4~0226~ 7~04159~ 10~0776~ 12~02526~.'),
  (13631, 18, 31, 34, 'Did I fear a great multitude, or did the contempt of families terrify me, that I kept silence, and went not out of the door?', '2~06206~ 4~07227~ 5~01995~, 9~0937~ 11~04940~ 12~02865~ 17~01826~, [18] 21~03318~ 24~06607~?'),
  (19063, 24, 4, 27, 'For thus hath the LORD said, The whole land shall be desolate; yet will I not make a full end.', '4~03068~ 5~0559~, 8~0776~ 11~08077~; 16~06213~ 19~03617~.'),
  (29235, 49, 1, 13, 'In whom ye also trusted, after that ye heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye believed, ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise,', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~5210~ 3~2532~ [4] 8~191~ 10~3056~ 12~225~, 14~2098~ 16~5216~ 17~4991~: 18~1722~ 19~3739~ 20~2532~ 24~4100~, 28~4972~ 30~40~ 31~4151~ 33~1860~,'),
  (135, 1, 5, 29, 'And he called his name Noah, saying, This same shall comfort us concerning our work and toil of our hands, because of the ground which the LORD hath cursed.', '2~07121~ 4~08034~ 5~05146~, 6~0559~, [8] 10~05162~ 14~04639~ 16~06093~ 19~03027~, 20~04480~ 23~0127~ 26~03068~ 28~0779~.'),
  (25551, 42, 13, 20, 'And again he said, Whereunto shall I liken the kingdom of God?', '0~2532~ 1~3825~ 3~2036~, 4~5101~ 7~3666~ 9~932~ 11~2316~?'),
  (9895, 12, 13, 16, 'And he said to the king of Israel, Put thine hand upon the bow. And he put his hand upon it: and Elisha put his hands upon the king''s hands.', '2~0559~ 5~04428~ 7~03478~, 8~07392~ 10~03027~ 13~07198~. 16~07392~ 18~03027~ [19 20] 22~0477~ 23~07760~ 25~03027~ 28~04428~ 29~03027~.'),
  (26944, 44, 1, 5, 'For John truly baptized with water; but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost not many days hence.', '0~3754~ 1~2491~ 2~3303~ 3~907~ 5~5204~; 6~1161~ 7~5210~ 10~907~ 11~1722~ 13~40~ 14~4151~ 15~3756~ 16~4183~ 17~3326~* 18~2250~ 19~5025~.'),
  (22437, 30, 5, 5, 'But seek not Bethel, nor enter into Gilgal, and pass not to Beersheba: for Gilgal shall surely go into captivity, and Bethel shall come to nought.', '1~01875~ 3~01008~, 5~0935~ 7~01537~, 9~05674~ 12~0884~: 14~01537~ 16~01540~ 19~01540~, 21~01008~ 25~0205~.'),
  (31062, 66, 20, 8, 'And shall go out to deceive the nations which are in the four quarters of the earth, Gog and Magog, to gather them together to battle: the number of whom is as the sand of the sea.', '0~2532~ 3~1831~ 5~4105~ 7~1484~ 8~3588~ 10~1722~ 12~5064~ 13~1137~ 16~1093~, 17~1136~ 18~2532~ 19~3098~, 21~4863~ 22~846~ 23~4863~ 24~1519~ 25~4171~: 27~706~ 29~3739~ [30] 31~5613~ 33~285~ 36~2281~.'),
  (12756, 17, 2, 23, 'And when inquisition was made of the matter, it was found out; therefore they were both hanged on a tree: and it was written in the book of the chronicles before the king.', '2~01245~ 7~01697~, 11~04672~; 15~08147~ 16~08518~ 19~06086~: 23~03789~ 26~05612~ 29~03117~ 30~01697~* 31~06440~ 33~04428~.'),
  (30065, 58, 6, 5, 'And have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come,', '0~2532~ 2~1089~ 4~2570~ 5~4487~ 7~2316~, 8~5037~ 10~1411~ 13~165~ 15~3195~,'),
  (14043, 19, 9, 13, 'Have mercy upon me, O LORD; consider my trouble which I suffer of them that hate me, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:', '1~02603~ 5~03068~; 6~07200~ 8~06040~ [9 11] 15~08130~ 21~07311~ 24~08179~ 26~04194~:'),
  (15949, 19, 119, 42, 'So shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me: for I trust in thy word.', '4~01697~ 6~06030~ 9~02778~ 13~0982~ 16~01697~.');
