VALUES
  (20041, 24, 44, 22, 'So that the LORD could no longer bear, because of the evil of your doings, and because of the abominations which ye have committed; therefore is your land a desolation, and an astonishment, and a curse, without an inhabitant, as at this day.', '3~03068~ 4~03201~ 7~05375~, 8~06440~ 11~07455~ 14~04611~, [15] 16~06440~ 19~08441~ 23~06213~; 27~0776~ 29~02723~, 32~08047~, 35~07045~, 38~03427~, 42~03117~.'),
  (24312, 41, 3, 14, 'And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,', '0~2532~ 2~4160~ 3~1427~, 4~2443~ 7~5600~ 8~3326~ 9~846~, 10~2532~ 11~2443~ 14~649~ 15~846~ 16~649~ 18~2784~,'),
  (21089, 26, 24, 24, 'Thus Ezekiel is unto you a sign: according to all that he hath done shall ye do: and when this cometh, ye shall know that I am the Lord GOD.', '1~03168~ 6~04159~: 13~06213~ 16~06213~: 20~0935~, 23~03045~ [26] 28~0136~ 29~03069~.'),
  (5602, 5, 27, 11, 'And Moses charged the people the same day, saying,', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~06680~ 4~05971~ 7~03117~, 8~0559~,'),
  (23706, 40, 16, 24, 'Then said Jesus unto his disciples, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.', '&para; 0~5119~ 1~2036~ 2~2424~ 4~846~ 5~3101~, 7~1536~ [8] 9~2309~ 10~2064~ 11~3694~ 12~3450~, 15~533~ 16~1438~, 17~2532~ 19~142~ 20~846~ 21~4716~, 22~2532~ 23~190~ 24~3427~.'),
  (2128, 2, 22, 10, 'If a man deliver unto his neighbour an ass, or an ox, or a sheep, or any beast, to keep; and it die, or be hurt, or driven away, no man seeing it:', '2~0376~ 3~05414~ 6~07453~ 8~02543~, 11~07794~, 14~07716~, 17~0929~, 19~08104~; 22~04191~, 25~07665~, 28~07617~, 31~07200~ [32]'),
  (5742, 5, 31, 8, 'And the LORD, he it is that doth go before thee; he will be with thee, he will not fail thee, neither forsake thee: fear not, neither be dismayed.', '2~03068~, [4 5] 8~01980~ 9~06440~ 19~07503~ 22~05800~ 24~03372~ 28~02865~.'),
  (26678, 43, 13, 33, 'Little children, yet a little while I am with you. Ye shall seek me: and as I said unto the Jews, Whither I go, ye cannot come; so now I say to you.', '1~5040~, 2~2089~ 5~3397~ 7~1510~ 8~3326~ 9~5216~. 12~2212~ 13~3165~: 14~2532~ 15~2531~ 17~2036~ 20~2453~ 21~3754~,* 22~3699~ 23~1473~ 24~5217~, 25~5210~ 26~1410~ 27~3756~* 28~2064~; 29~2532~ 30~737~ 32~3004~ 34~5213~.'),
  (17907, 23, 11, 14, 'But they shall fly upon the shoulders of the Philistines toward the west; they shall spoil them of the east together: they shall lay their hand upon Edom and Moab; and the children of Ammon shall obey them.', '3~05774~ 6~03802~ 9~06430~ 12~03220~; 15~0962~ 16~01121~ 19~06924~ 20~03162~: 23~04916~ 25~03027~ 27~0123~ 29~04124~; 32~01121~ 34~05983~ 36~04928~'),
  (25268, 42, 8, 11, 'Now the parable is this: The seed is the word of God.', '0~1161~ 2~3850~ 3~2076~ 4~3778~: 6~4703~ 7~2076~ 9~3056~ 11~2316~.'),
  (12525, 16, 9, 5, 'Then the Levites, Jeshua, and Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabniah, Sherebiah, Hodijah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah, said, Stand up and bless the LORD your God for ever and ever: and blessed be thy glorious name, which is exalted above all blessing and praise.', '2~03881~, 3~03442~, 5~06934~, 6~01137~, 7~02813~, 8~08274~, 9~01941~, 10~07645~, [11] 12~06611~, 13~0559~, 15~06965~ [16] 17~01288~ 19~03068~ 21~0430~ 23~05769~ 25~05769~: 27~01288~ 30~03519~ 31~08034~, 34~07311~ 37~01293~ 39~08416~.'),
  (2456, 2, 32, 13, 'Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, thy servants, to whom thou swarest by thine own self, and saidst unto them, I will multiply your seed as the stars of heaven, and all this land that I have spoken of will I give unto your seed, and they shall inherit it for ever.', '0~02142~ 1~085~, 2~03327~, 4~03478~, 6~05650~, 10~07650~ 16~01696~ 21~07235~ 23~02233~ 26~03556~ 28~08064~, 32~0776~ 36~0559~ 40~05414~ 43~02233~, 47~05157~ [48] 50~05769~.'),
  (2035, 2, 19, 4, 'Ye have seen what I did unto the Egyptians, and how I bare you on eagles'' wings, and brought you unto myself.', '2~07200~ 5~06213~ 8~04714~, [10] 12~05375~ 15~05404~ 16~03671~, 18~0935~'),
  (22026, 27, 10, 2, 'In those days I Daniel was mourning three full weeks.', '2~03117~ 4~01840~ 6~056~ 7~07969~ 8~03117~ 9~07620~.'),
  (22591, 33, 1, 3, 'For, behold, the LORD cometh forth out of his place, and will come down, and tread upon the high places of the earth.', '3~03068~ 5~03318~ 9~04725~, 13~03381~, 15~01869~ 19~01116~ 22~0776~.'),
  (10092, 12, 19, 23, 'By thy messengers thou hast reproached the Lord, and hast said, With the multitude of my chariots I am come up to the height of the mountains, to the sides of Lebanon, and will cut down the tall cedar trees thereof, and the choice fir trees thereof: and I will enter into the lodgings of his borders, and into the forest of his Carmel.', '0~03027~ 2~04397~ 5~02778~ 7~0136~, 10~0559~, 13~07230~ 16~07393~ 17~07393~* 21~05927~ 24~04791~ 27~02022~, 30~03411~ 32~03844~, 36~03772~ 38~06967~ 40~0730~ [42] 44~04004~ 46~01265~ 51~0935~ 54~04411~ 57~07093~, [58 59] 61~03293~ 64~03760~.'),
  (5465, 5, 21, 12, 'Then thou shalt bring her home to thine house; and she shall shave her head, and pare her nails;', '3~0935~ 5~08432~ 8~01004~; 12~01548~ 14~07218~, 16~06213~ 18~06856~;'),
  (12705, 16, 13, 25, 'And I contended with them, and cursed them, and smote certain of them, and plucked off their hair, and made them swear by God, saying, Ye shall not give your daughters unto their sons, nor take their daughters unto your sons, or for yourselves.', '2~07378~ 6~07043~ 9~05221~ 10~0582~ 17~04803~, 21~07650~ 23~0430~, [24] 28~05414~ 30~01323~ 33~01121~, 35~05375~ 37~01323~ 40~01121~,'),
  (8389, 10, 14, 26, 'And when he polled his head, (for it was at every year''s end that he polled it: because the hair was heavy on him, therefore he polled it:) he weighed the hair of his head at two hundred shekels after the king''s weight.', '3~01548~ 5~07218~, 11~03117~ 12~03117~* 13~07093~ 16~01548~ [17] [19 20] 22~03513~ 27~01548~ 30~08254~ 32~08181~ 35~07218~ 38~03967~ 39~08255~ 42~04428~ 43~068~.'),
  (22198, 28, 7, 11, 'Ephraim also is like a silly dove without heart: they call to Egypt, they go to Assyria.', '0~0669~ 5~06601~ 6~03123~ 8~03820~: 10~07121~ 12~04714~, 14~01980~ 16~0804~.'),
  (24173, 40, 27, 34, 'They gave him vinegar to drink mingled with gall: and when he had tasted thereof, he would not drink.', '1~1325~ 2~846~ 3~3690~ 5~4095~ 6~3396~ 7~3326~ 8~5521~: 9~2532~ 13~1089~ [14] 16~2309~ 17~3756~ 18~4095~.'),
  (21738, 26, 48, 27, 'And by the border of Zebulun, from the east side unto the west side, Gad a portion.', '3~01366~ 5~02074~, 8~06921~ 9~06285~ 12~03220~ 13~06285~, 14~01410~ 15~0259~ [16]'),
  (12439, 16, 7, 10, 'The children of Arah, six hundred fifty and two.', '1~01121~ 3~0733~, 4~08337~ 5~03967~ 6~02572~ 8~08147~.'),
  (17611, 22, 5, 4, 'My beloved put in his hand by the hole of the door, and my bowels were moved for him.', '1~01730~ 3~07971~ 5~03027~ 6~04480~ 8~02356~ [9 11] 14~04578~ 16~01993~'),
  (3112, 3, 13, 55, 'And the priest shall look on the plague, after that it is washed: and, behold, if the plague have not changed his colour, and the plague be not spread; it is unclean; thou shalt burn it in the fire; it is fret inward, whether it be bare within or without.', '2~03548~ 4~07200~ 7~05061~, 8~0310~ 12~03526~: [15] 17~05061~ 20~02015~ 22~05869~, 25~05061~ 28~06581~; [30] 31~02931~; 34~08313~ 38~0784~; [40] 41~06356~ [43] [45] 47~07146~ 49~01372~.'),
  (3987, 4, 9, 17, 'And when the cloud was taken up from the tabernacle, then after that the children of Israel journeyed: and in the place where the cloud abode, there the children of Israel pitched their tents.', '1~06310~ 3~06051~ 6~05927~ 9~0168~, 11~0310~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 17~05265~: 21~04725~ 24~06051~ 25~07931~, 28~01121~ 30~03478~ 33~02583~.'),
  (9248, 11, 14, 22, 'And Judah did evil in the sight of the LORD, and they provoked him to jealousy with their sins which they had committed, above all that their fathers had done.', '1~03063~ 2~06213~ 3~07451~ 6~05869~ 9~03068~, 15~07065~ 18~02403~ 22~02398~, 27~01~ 29~06213~.'),
  (25937, 42, 22, 59, 'And about the space of one hour after another confidently affirmed, saying, Of a truth this fellow also was with him: for he is a Galilaean.', '0~2532~ 1~5616~ 3~1339~ 5~3391~ 6~5610~ 8~5100~ 9~243~ 10~1340~, 11~3004~, 12~1909~ 14~225~ 15~3778~ [16] 17~2532~ 18~2258~ 19~3326~ 20~846~: 21~2532~ 22~1063~ 23~2076~ 25~1057~.'),
  (10096, 12, 19, 27, 'But I know thy abode, and thy going out, and thy coming in, and thy rage against me.', '2~03045~ 4~03427~, 8~03318~, 12~0935~, 15~07264~'),
  (30964, 66, 15, 2, 'And I saw as it were a sea of glass mingled with fire: and them that had gotten the victory over the beast, and over his image, and over his mark, and over the number of his name, stand on the sea of glass, having the harps of God.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 5~5613~ 7~2281~ 9~5193~ 10~3396~ 12~4442~: 13~2532~ 19~3528~ 20~1537~ 22~2342~, 23~2532~ 24~1537~ 25~846~ 26~1504~, 27~2532~ 28~1537~ 29~846~ 30~5480~, [31] 32~1537~ 34~706~ 36~846~ 37~3686~, 38~2476~ 39~1909~ 41~2281~ 43~5193~, 44~2192~ 46~2788~ 48~2316~.'),
  (30275, 58, 13, 18, 'Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.', '&para; 0~4336~ 1~4012~ 2~2257~: 3~3754~ 4~1063~ 5~3982~ 7~2192~ 9~2570~ 10~4893~, 11~1722~ 13~3956~ 14~2309~ 16~390~ 17~2573~.'),
  (18662, 23, 49, 17, 'Thy children shall make haste; thy destroyers and they that made thee waste shall go forth of thee.', '1~01121~ 4~04116~; 6~02040~ 12~02717~ 15~03318~'),
  (19735, 24, 31, 35, 'Thus saith the LORD, which giveth the sun for a light by day, and the ordinances of the moon and of the stars for a light by night, which divideth the sea when the waves thereof roar; The LORD of hosts is his name:', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~05414~ 7~08121~ 10~0216~ 12~03119~, [13] 15~02708~ 18~03394~ 22~03556~ 25~0216~ 27~03915~, 29~07280~ 31~03220~ 34~01530~ 36~01993~; 38~03068~ 40~06635~ [41] 43~08034~:'),
  (2509, 2, 34, 8, 'And Moses made haste, and bowed his head toward the earth, and worshipped.', '1~04872~ 3~04116~, 7~06915~ 10~0776~, 12~07812~.'),
  (7691, 9, 18, 8, 'And Saul was very wroth, and the saying displeased him; and he said, They have ascribed unto David ten thousands, and to me they have ascribed but thousands: and what can he have more but the kingdom?', '1~07586~ 3~03966~ 4~02734~, 7~01697~ 8~03415~ 9~05869~* 13~0559~, 16~05414~ 18~01732~ 20~07233~, 26~05414~ [27] 28~0505~: [30] 37~04410~?'),
  (28069, 45, 5, 6, 'For when we were yet without strength, in due time Christ died for the ungodly.', '&para; 0~1063~ 2~2257~ 3~5607~ 4~2089~ 6~772~, 8~2596~ 9~2540~ 10~5547~ 11~599~ 12~5228~ 14~765~.'),
  (460, 1, 18, 32, 'And he said, Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak yet but this once: Peradventure ten shall be found there. And he said, I will not destroy it for ten''s sake.', '2~0559~, 7~0136~ 9~02734~, 13~01696~ 14~0389~ 17~06471~: 19~06235~ 22~04672~ 26~0559~, 30~07843~ [31] 33~06235~'),
  (20141, 24, 49, 5, 'Behold, I will bring a fear upon thee, saith the Lord GOD of hosts, from all those that be about thee; and ye shall be driven out every man right forth; and none shall gather up him that wandereth.', '3~0935~ 5~06343~ 8~05002~ 10~0136~ 11~03069~ 13~06635~, 19~05439~ 26~05080~ 28~0376~ 30~06440~; 35~06908~ 38~05074~.'),
  (8097, 10, 3, 9, 'So do God to Abner, and more also, except, as the LORD hath sworn to David, even so I do to him;', '1~06213~ 2~0430~ 4~074~, 7~03254~, 11~03068~ 13~07650~ 15~01732~, 19~06213~'),
  (4341, 4, 20, 25, 'Take Aaron and Eleazar his son, and bring them up unto mount Hor:', '0~03947~ 1~0175~ 3~0499~ 5~01121~, 9~05927~ 11~02022~ 12~02023~:'),
  (20430, 25, 4, 1, 'How is the gold become dim! how is the most fine gold changed! the stones of the sanctuary are poured out in the top of every street.', '&para; 3~02091~ 5~06004~! [6] 9~02896~ 11~03800~ 12~08132~! 14~068~ 17~06944~ 20~08210~ 23~07218~ 26~02351~.'),
  (16546, 20, 5, 20, 'And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?', '5~01121~, 7~07686~ 11~02114~, 13~02263~ 15~02436~ 18~05237~?'),
  (18211, 23, 29, 9, 'Stay yourselves, and wonder; cry ye out, and cry: they are drunken, but not with wine; they stagger, but not with strong drink.', '&para; 0~04102~ 3~08539~; 6~08173~, 8~08173~: 11~07937~, 15~03196~; 17~05128~, 22~07941~.'),
  (26911, 43, 20, 28, 'And Thomas answered and said unto him, My Lord and my God.', '0~2532~ 1~2381~ 2~611~ 3~2532~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 7~3450~ 8~2962~ 9~2532~ 10~3450~ 11~2316~.'),
  (10191, 12, 23, 18, 'And he said, Let him alone; let no man move his bones. So they let his bones alone, with the bones of the prophet that came out of Samaria.', '2~0559~, 5~03240~; 8~0376~ 9~05128~ 11~06106~. 16~06106~ 17~04422~, 20~06106~ 23~05030~ 26~0935~ 28~08111~.'),
  (4162, 4, 15, 4, 'Then shall he that offereth his offering unto the LORD bring a meat offering of a tenth deal of flour mingled with the fourth part of an hin of oil.', '4~07126~ 6~07133~ 9~03068~ 10~07126~ 13~04503~ 17~06241~ 19~05560~ 20~01101~ 23~07243~ [24] 27~01969~ 29~08081~.'),
  (19462, 24, 21, 13, 'Behold, I am against thee, O inhabitant of the valley, and rock of the plain, saith the LORD; which say, Who shall come down against us? or who shall enter into our habitations?', '[2] 6~03427~ 9~06010~, [10] 11~06697~ 14~04334~, 15~05002~ 17~03068~; 19~0559~, 23~05181~ 29~0935~ 32~04585~?'),
  (24975, 42, 1, 70, 'As he spake by the mouth of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began:', '0~2531~ 2~2980~ 3~1223~ 5~4750~ 7~846~ 8~40~ 9~4396~, 10~3588~ 13~575~ 16~165~:'),
  (24530, 41, 8, 19, 'When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? They say unto him, Twelve.', '0~3753~ 2~2806~ 4~4002~ 5~740~ 6~1519~ 8~4000~, 10~4214~ 11~2894~ 12~4134~ 14~2801~ 17~142~? 19~3004~ 21~846~, 22~1427~.'),
  (15995, 19, 119, 88, 'Quicken me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.', '&para; 0~02421~ 4~02617~; 8~08104~ 10~05715~ 13~06310~.'),
  (9082, 11, 9, 23, 'These were the chief of the officers that were over Solomon''s work, five hundred and fifty, which bare rule over the people that wrought in the work.', '[1] 3~08269~ 6~05324~ [8] 10~08010~ 11~04399~, 12~02568~ 13~03967~ 15~02572~, 18~07287~ 21~05971~ 23~06213~ 26~04399~.'),
  (15476, 19, 96, 2, 'Sing unto the LORD, bless his name; shew forth his salvation from day to day.', '0~07891~ 3~03068~, 4~01288~ 6~08034~; 8~01319~ 10~03444~ 12~03117~ 14~03117~.'),
  (29672, 53, 1, 7, 'And to you who are troubled rest with us, when the Lord Jesus shall be revealed from heaven with his mighty angels,', '0~2532~ 2~5213~ 5~2346~ 6~425~ 7~3326~ 8~2257~, 9~1722~ 11~2962~ 12~2424~ 15~602~ 16~575~ 17~3772~ 18~3326~ 19~846~ 20~1411~ 21~32~,'),
  (26941, 44, 1, 2, 'Until the day in which he was taken up, after that he through the Holy Ghost had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen:', '0~891~ 2~2250~ 4~3739~ 8~353~, 12~1223~ 14~40~ 15~4151~ 18~1781~ 21~652~ 22~3739~ 25~1586~:'),
  (1440, 1, 47, 15, 'And when money failed in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came unto Joseph, and said, Give us bread: for why should we die in thy presence? for the money faileth.', '2~03701~ 3~08552~ 6~0776~ 8~04714~, 12~0776~ 14~03667~, 17~04714~ 18~0935~ 20~03130~, 22~0559~, 23~03051~ 25~03899~: 30~04191~ 36~03701~ 37~0656~.'),
  (11609, 14, 20, 13, 'And all Judah stood before the LORD, with their little ones, their wives, and their children.', '2~03063~ 3~05975~ 4~06440~ 6~03068~, 7~01571~ 10~02945~, 12~0802~, 15~01121~.'),
  (14097, 19, 15, 1, 'A Psalm of David. LORD, who shall abide in thy tabernacle? who shall dwell in thy holy hill?', '&para; [0 1~04210~ 3] 3~01732~ 4~03068~, 7~01481~ 10~0168~? 13~07931~ 16~06944~ 17~02022~?'),
  (23792, 40, 19, 20, 'The young man saith unto him, All these things have I kept from my youth up: what lack I yet?', '2~3495~ 3~3004~ 5~846~, 6~3956~ 8~5023~ 11~5442~ 12~1537~ 13~3450~ 15~3503~: 16~5101~ 17~5302~ 19~2089~?'),
  (8612, 10, 22, 2, 'And he said, The LORD is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer;', '&para; 2~0559~, 4~03068~ [5] 7~05553~, 10~04686~, 13~06403~;'),
  (10138, 12, 21, 11, 'Because Manasseh king of Judah hath done these abominations, and hath done wickedly above all that the Amorites did, which were before him, and hath made Judah also to sin with his idols:', '1~04519~ 2~04428~ 4~03063~ 6~06213~ 8~08441~, [9] 12~07489~ 17~0567~ 18~06213~, [20] 21~06440~ 26~03063~ 29~02398~ 32~01544~:'),
  (23444, 40, 10, 17, 'But beware of men: for they will deliver you up to the councils, and they will scourge you in their synagogues;', '0~1161~ 1~4337~ 2~575~ 3~444~: 4~1063~ 7~3860~ 8~5209~ 9~3860~ 10~1519~ 12~4892~, 13~2532~ 16~3146~ 17~5209~ 18~1722~ 19~846~ 20~4864~;'),
  (1732, 2, 8, 17, 'And they did so; for Aaron stretched out his hand with his rod, and smote the dust of the earth, and it became lice in man, and in beast; all the dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt.', '2~06213~ 5~0175~ 7~05186~ 9~03027~ 12~04294~, 14~05221~ 16~06083~ 19~0776~, 23~03654~ 25~0120~, 28~0929~; 31~06083~ 34~0776~ 36~03654~ 40~0776~ 42~04714~.'),
  (5848, 5, 34, 3, 'And the south, and the plain of the valley of Jericho, the city of palm trees, unto Zoar.', '2~05045~, 5~03603~ 8~01237~ 10~03405~, 12~05892~ 15~08558~ 16~05899~,* 18~06820~.'),
  (11287, 14, 5, 11, 'And it came to pass, when the priests were come out of the holy place: (for all the priests that were present were sanctified, and did not then wait by course:', '&para; 7~03548~ 10~03318~ 13~06944~ [14] 18~03548~ [19 20] 21~04672~ 23~06942~, [24] [27] 28~08104~ 30~04256~:'),
  (26127, 43, 2, 17, 'And his disciples remembered that it was written, The zeal of thine house hath eaten me up.', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 2~3101~ 3~3415~ 4~3754~ 6~2076~ 7~1125~, 9~2205~ 11~4675~ 12~3624~ 14~2719~ 15~3165~ 16~2719~.'),
  (27367, 44, 12, 14, 'And when she knew Peter''s voice, she opened not the gate for gladness, but ran in, and told how Peter stood before the gate.', '0~2532~ 3~1921~ 4~4074~ 5~5456~, 7~455~ 8~3756~ 10~4440~ 11~575~ 12~5479~, 13~1161~ 15~1532~, 18~518~ 19~4074~ 20~2476~ 21~4253~ 23~4440~.'),
  (27510, 44, 16, 11, 'Therefore loosing from Troas, we came with a straight course to Samothracia, and the next day to Neapolis;', '0~3767~ 1~321~ 2~575~ 3~5174~, 9~2113~ 10~1519~ 11~4543~, 12~5037~ 14~1966~ [15] 16~1519~ 17~3496~;'),
  (1670, 2, 6, 10, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (2634, 2, 37, 25, 'And he made the incense altar of shittim wood: the length of it was a cubit, and the breadth of it a cubit; it was foursquare; and two cubits was the height of it; the horns thereof were of the same.', '&para; 2~06213~ 4~07004~ 5~04196~ [6] 7~07848~ 8~06086~: 10~0753~ [13] 15~0520~, 18~07341~ 22~0520~; [23 24] 25~07251~; 28~0520~ [29] 31~06967~ 35~07161~'),
  (18404, 23, 38, 5, 'Go, and say to Hezekiah, Thus saith the LORD, the God of David thy father, I have heard thy prayer, I have seen thy tears: behold, I will add unto thy days fifteen years.', '0~01980~, 2~0559~ 4~02396~, 6~0559~ 8~03068~, 10~0430~ 12~01732~ 14~01~, 17~08085~ 19~08605~, 22~07200~ 24~01832~: 28~03254~ 31~03117~ 32~06240~ 33~02568~* 34~08141~.'),
  (8412, 10, 15, 16, 'And the king went forth, and all his household after him. And the king left ten women, which were concubines, to keep the house.', '2~04428~ 4~03318~, 8~01004~ 9~07272~ 13~04428~ 14~05800~ 15~06235~ 16~0802~, [17 18] 19~06370~, 21~08104~ 23~01004~.'),
  (27314, 44, 10, 39, 'And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they slew and hanged on a tree:', '0~2532~ 1~2249~ 2~2070~ 3~3144~ 6~3956~ 7~3739~ 9~4160~ 10~5037~ 11~1722~ 13~5561~ 16~2453~, 17~2532~ 18~1722~ 19~2419~; 20~3739~ 22~337~ 24~2910~ 25~1909~ 27~3586~:'),
  (4854, 4, 35, 3, 'And the cities shall they have to dwell in; and the suburbs of them shall be for their cattle, and for their goods, and for all their beasts.', '2~05892~ 8~03427~; 11~04054~ 18~0929~, 22~07399~, 27~02416~.'),
  (15651, 19, 105, 36, 'He smote also all the firstborn in their land, the chief of all their strength.', '1~05221~ 5~01060~ 8~0776~, 10~07225~ 14~0202~.'),
  (28036, 45, 3, 29, 'Is he the God of the Jews only? is he not also of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:', '[0 1] 1~2228~ 3~2316~ 6~2453~ 7~3440~? [8 9] 10~3780~ 11~2532~ 12~1161~ 14~1484~? 15~3483~, 18~1484~ 19~2532~:'),
  (8414, 10, 15, 18, 'And all his servants passed on beside him; and all the Cherethites, and all the Pelethites, and all the Gittites, six hundred men which came after him from Gath, passed on before the king.', '3~05650~ 5~05674~ 6~03027~ 11~03774~, 15~06432~, 19~01663~, 20~08337~ 21~03967~ 22~0376~ 24~0935~ 25~07272~ 28~01661~, 30~05674~ 31~06440~ 33~04428~.'),
  (2273, 2, 26, 33, 'And thou shalt hang up the veil under the taches, that thou mayest bring in thither within the veil the ark of the testimony: and the veil shall divide unto you between the holy place and the most holy.', '4~05414~ 6~06532~ 9~07165~, 13~0935~ 16~01004~ 18~06532~ 20~0727~ 23~05715~: 26~06532~ 28~0914~ 33~06944~ [34] 37~06944~ 38~06944~.'),
  (6228, 6, 15, 19, 'Who answered, Give me a blessing; for thou hast given me a south land; give me also springs of water. And he gave her the upper springs, and the nether springs.', '1~0559~, 2~05414~ 5~01293~; 9~05414~ 12~05045~ 13~0776~; 14~05414~ 17~01543~ 19~04325~. 22~05414~ 25~05942~ 26~01543~, 29~08482~ 30~01543~.'),
  (25016, 42, 2, 31, 'Which thou hast prepared before the face of all people;', '0~3739~ 3~2090~ 4~2596~ 6~4383~ 8~3956~ 9~2992~;'),
  (5658, 5, 28, 41, 'Thou shalt beget sons and daughters, but thou shalt not enjoy them; for they shall go into captivity.', '2~03205~ 3~01121~ 5~01323~, 15~03212~ 17~07628~.'),
  (16008, 19, 119, 101, 'I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.', '&para; 2~03607~ 4~07272~ 7~07451~ 8~0734~, 12~08104~ 14~01697~.'),
  (25561, 42, 13, 30, 'And, behold, there are last which shall be first, and there are first which shall be last.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~1526~ 4~2078~ 5~3739~ 7~2071~ 8~4413~, 9~2532~ 11~1526~ 12~4413~ 13~3739~ 15~2071~ 16~2078~.'),
  (4978, 5, 2, 34, 'And we took all his cities at that time, and utterly destroyed the men, and the women, and the little ones, of every city, we left none to remain:', '2~03920~ 5~05892~ 8~06256~, 11~02763~ 13~04962~, 16~0802~, 20~02945~, 23~05892~, 25~07604~ 28~08300~:'),
  (6456, 6, 22, 23, 'That we have built us an altar to turn from following the LORD, or if to offer thereon burnt offering or meat offering, or if to offer peace offerings thereon, let the LORD himself require it;', '3~01129~ 6~04196~ 8~07725~ 10~0310~ 12~03068~, 16~05927~ 19~05930~ 22~04503~, 26~06213~ 27~08002~ 28~02077~ 32~03068~ 34~01245~ [35]'),
  (25243, 42, 7, 36, 'And one of the Pharisees desired him that he would eat with him. And he went into the Pharisee''s house, and sat down to meat.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5100~ 4~5330~ 5~2065~ 6~846~ 7~2443~ 10~5315~ 11~3326~ 12~846~. 13~2532~ 15~1525~ 16~1519~ 18~5330~ 19~3614~, 24~347~.'),
  (19209, 24, 9, 25, 'Behold, the days come, saith the LORD, that I will punish all them which are circumcised with the uncircumcised;', '2~03117~ 3~0935~, 4~05002~ 6~03068~, 10~06485~ [12 14] 15~04135~ 18~06190~;'),
  (25648, 42, 16, 15, 'And he said unto them, Ye are they which justify yourselves before men; but God knoweth your hearts: for that which is highly esteemed among men is abomination in the sight of God.', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~5210~ 6~2075~ 9~1344~ 10~1438~ 11~1799~ 12~444~; 13~1161~ 14~2316~ 15~1097~ 16~5216~ 17~2588~: 18~3754~ 23~5308~ 24~1722~ 25~444~ 26~2076~ 27~946~ 30~1799~ 32~2316~.'),
  (22448, 30, 5, 16, 'Therefore the LORD, the God of hosts, the Lord, saith thus; Wailing shall be in all streets; and they shall say in all the highways, Alas! alas! and they shall call the husbandman to mourning, and such as are skilful of lamentation to wailing.', '&para; 2~03068~, 4~0430~ 6~06635~, 8~0136~, 9~0559~ 11~04553~ [12 13] 16~07339~; 20~0559~ 24~02351~, 25~01930~! 26~01930~! 30~07121~ 32~0406~ 34~060~, 39~03045~ 41~05092~ 43~04553~.'),
  (8148, 10, 5, 9, 'So David dwelt in the fort, and called it the city of David. And David built round about from Millo and inward.', '1~01732~ 2~03427~ 5~04686~, 7~07121~ 10~05892~ 12~01732~. 14~01732~ 15~01129~ 17~05439~ 19~04407~ 21~01004~.'),
  (10181, 12, 23, 8, 'And he brought all the priests out of the cities of Judah, and defiled the high places where the priests had burned incense, from Geba to Beersheba, and brake down the high places of the gates that were in the entering in of the gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which were on a man''s left hand at the gate of the city.', '2~0935~ 5~03548~ 9~05892~ 11~03063~, 13~02930~ 16~01116~ 19~03548~ 22~06999~, 24~01387~ 26~0884~, 29~05422~ 32~01116~ 35~08179~ [37] 41~06607~ 44~08179~ 46~03091~ 48~08269~ 51~05892~, [53] 56~0376~ 58~08040~ 61~08179~ 64~05892~.'),
  (10445, 13, 5, 9, 'And eastward he inhabited unto the entering in of the wilderness from the river Euphrates: because their cattle were multiplied in the land of Gilead.', '1~04217~ 3~03427~ 6~0935~ 10~04057~ 13~05104~ 14~06578~: 17~04735~ 19~07235~ 22~0776~ 24~01568~.'),
  (2644, 2, 38, 6, 'And he made the staves of shittim wood, and overlaid them with brass.', '2~06213~ 4~0905~ [5] 6~07848~ 7~06086~, 9~06823~ 12~05178~.'),
  (17642, 22, 7, 6, 'How fair and how pleasant art thou, O love, for delights!', '1~03302~ 4~05276~ 8~0160~, 10~08588~!'),
  (3183, 3, 15, 10, 'And whosoever toucheth any thing that was under him shall be unclean until the even: and he that beareth any of those things shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even.', '2~05060~ 11~02930~ 14~06153~: 18~05375~ [19 20] 24~03526~ 26~0899~, 28~07364~ [29] 31~04325~, 34~02930~ 37~06153~.'),
  (410, 1, 17, 9, 'And God said unto Abraham, Thou shalt keep my covenant therefore, thou, and thy seed after thee in their generations.', '1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~085~, 7~08104~ 9~01285~ 14~02233~ 16~0310~ 19~01755~.'),
  (22817, 36, 2, 3, 'Seek ye the LORD, all ye meek of the earth, which have wrought his judgment; seek righteousness, seek meekness: it may be ye shall be hid in the day of the LORD''S anger.', '0~01245~ 3~03068~, 6~06035~ 9~0776~, 12~06466~ 14~04941~; 15~01245~ 16~06664~, 17~01245~ 18~06038~: 21~0194~ 25~05641~ 28~03117~ 31~03068~ 32~0639~.'),
  (11244, 14, 3, 7, 'He overlaid also the house, the beams, the posts, and the walls thereof, and the doors thereof, with gold; and graved cherubims on the walls.', '1~02645~ 4~01004~, 6~06982~, 8~05592~, 11~07023~ 15~01817~ 18~02091~; 20~06605~ 21~03742~ 24~07023~.'),
  (16501, 20, 4, 2, 'For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.', '2~05414~ 4~02896~ 5~03948~, 6~05800~ 10~08451~.'),
  (15825, 19, 113, 3, 'From the rising of the sun unto the going down of the same the Lord''s name is to be praised.', '2~04217~ 5~08121~ 9~03996~ 14~03068~ 15~08034~ [16] 19~01984~.'),
  (30472, 60, 4, 10, 'As every man hath received the gift, even so minister the same one to another, as good stewards of the manifold grace of God.', '0~2531~ 2~1538~ 4~2983~ 6~5486~, [7 8] 9~1247~ 11~846~ 14~1438~ 15~1519~,* 16~5613~ 17~2570~ 18~3623~ 21~4164~ 22~5485~ 24~2316~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (3885, 4, 7, 30, 'On the fourth day Elizur the son of Shedeur, prince of the children of Reuben, did offer:', '2~07243~ 3~03117~ 4~0468~ 6~01121~ 8~07707~, 9~05387~ 12~01121~ 14~07205~, [15 16]'),
  (17165, 20, 26, 15, 'The slothful hideth his hand in his bosom; it grieveth him to bring it again to his mouth.', '&para; 1~06102~ 2~02934~ 4~03027~ [6] 7~06747~; 9~03811~ 14~07725~ 17~06310~.'),
  (25053, 42, 3, 16, 'John answered, saying unto them all, I indeed baptize you with water; but one mightier than I cometh, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose: he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost and with fire:', '0~2491~ 1~611~, 2~3004~ [4] 5~537~, 6~1473~ 7~3303~ 8~907~ 9~5209~ 11~5204~; 12~1161~ 15~2478~ 16~3450~ 17~2064~, 19~2438~ 21~846~ 22~3739~* 23~5266~ 25~1510~ 26~3756~ 27~2425~ 29~3089~: 30~846~ 32~907~ 33~5209~ 34~1722~ 36~40~ 37~4151~ 38~2532~ 40~4442~:'),
  (13709, 18, 34, 17, 'Shall even he that hateth right govern? and wilt thou condemn him that is most just?', '4~08130~ 5~04941~ 6~02280~? 10~07561~ 14~03524~ 15~06662~?'),
  (16069, 19, 119, 162, 'I rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.', '&para; 1~07797~ 4~0565~, 8~04672~ 9~07227~ 10~07998~.'),
  (4489, 4, 25, 13, 'And he shall have it, and his seed after him, even the covenant of an everlasting priesthood; because he was zealous for his God, and made an atonement for the children of Israel.', '7~02233~ 8~0310~ [10] 12~01285~ 15~05769~ 16~03550~; 17~0834~ 20~07065~ 23~0430~, 27~03722~ 30~01121~ 32~03478~.'),
  (21258, 26, 32, 1, 'And it came to pass in the twelfth year, in the twelfth month, in the first day of the month, that the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 7~06240~ 8~08147~* 9~08141~, 13~02320~, 16~0259~ [17] 20~02320~, [21] 23~01697~ 26~03068~ 30~0559~,'),
  (20226, 24, 51, 5, 'For Israel hath not been forsaken, nor Judah of his God, of the LORD of hosts; though their land was filled with sin against the Holy One of Israel.', '1~03478~ [2] [4] 5~0488~, 7~03063~ 10~0430~, 13~03068~ 15~06635~; 18~0776~ 20~04390~ 22~0817~ 26~06918~ 28~03478~.'),
  (4582, 4, 27, 22, 'And Moses did as the LORD commanded him: and he took Joshua, and set him before Eleazar the priest, and before all the congregation:', '1~04872~ 2~06213~ 5~03068~ 6~06680~ 10~03947~ 11~03091~, 13~05975~ 15~06440~ 16~0499~ 18~03548~, 20~06440~ 23~05712~:'),
  (761, 1, 27, 30, 'And it came to pass, as soon as Isaac had made an end of blessing Jacob, and Jacob was yet scarce gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came in from his hunting.', '&para; 8~03327~ 12~03615~ 14~01288~ 15~03290~, 17~03290~ 19~0389~ 20~03318~ 22~03318~ 25~06440~ 27~03327~ 29~01~, 31~06215~ 33~0251~ 35~0935~ 38~06718~.'),
  (2084, 2, 21, 2, 'If thou buy an Hebrew servant, six years he shall serve: and in the seventh he shall go out free for nothing.', '2~07069~ 4~05680~ 5~05650~, 6~08337~ 7~08141~ 10~05647~: 14~07637~ 18~03318~ 19~02670~ 21~02600~.'),
  (11754, 14, 26, 13, 'And under their hand was an army, three hundred thousand and seven thousand and five hundred, that made war with mighty power, to help the king against the enemy.', '3~03027~ [4] 6~06635~ 7~02428~,* 8~07969~ 9~03967~ 10~0505~ 12~07651~ 13~0505~ 15~02568~ 16~03967~, 18~06213~ 19~04421~ 21~02428~ 22~03581~, 24~05826~ 26~04428~ 29~0341~.'),
  (22880, 37, 2, 16, 'Since those days were, when one came to an heap of twenty measures, there were but ten: when one came to the pressfat for to draw out fifty vessels out of the press, there were but twenty.', '[2] [5] 6~0935~ 9~06194~ 11~06242~ [12] [15] 16~06235~: [18] 19~0935~ 22~03342~ 26~02834~ 27~02572~ [28] 32~06333~, [35] 36~06242~.'),
  (18363, 23, 37, 2, 'And he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and the elders of the priests covered with sackcloth, unto Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz.', '2~07971~ 3~0471~, [5] 8~01004~, 10~07644~ 12~05608~, 15~02205~ 18~03548~ 19~03680~ 21~08242~, 23~03470~ 25~05030~ 27~01121~ 29~0531~.'),
  (1402, 1, 46, 11, 'And the sons of Levi; Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.', '2~01121~ 4~03878~; 5~01648~, 6~06955~, 8~04847~.'),
  (7238, 9, 1, 19, 'And they rose up in the morning early, and worshipped before the LORD, and returned, and came to their house to Ramah: and Elkanah knew Hannah his wife; and the LORD remembered her.', '&para; 3~07925~ 6~01242~ 7~07925~, 9~07812~ 10~06440~ 12~03068~, 14~07725~, 16~0935~ 19~01004~ 21~07414~: 23~0511~ 24~03045~ 25~02584~ 27~0802~; 30~03068~ 31~02142~'),
  (729, 1, 26, 33, 'And he called it Shebah: therefore the name of the city is Beersheba unto this day.', '2~07121~ 4~07656~: 7~08034~ 10~05892~ [11] 12~0884~ 15~03117~.'),
  (27558, 44, 17, 19, 'And they took him, and brought him unto Areopagus, saying, May we know what this new doctrine, whereof thou speakest, is?', '0~5037~ 2~1949~ 3~846~, 6~71~ 7~1909~ 8~697~, 9~3004~, 10~1410~ 12~1097~ 13~5101~ 14~3778~ 15~2537~ 16~1322~, 17~5259~ 18~4675~ 19~2980~, [20]'),
  (21750, 27, 1, 4, 'Children in whom was no blemish, but well favoured, and skilful in all wisdom, and cunning in knowledge, and understanding science, and such as had ability in them to stand in the king''s palace, and whom they might teach the learning and the tongue of the Chaldeans.', '0~03206~ [3] 5~03971~ 6~03971~,* 8~02896~ 9~04758~, 11~07919~ 14~02451~, 16~03045~ 18~01847~, 20~0995~ 21~04093~, [25] 26~03581~ 30~05975~ 33~04428~ 34~01964~, 39~03925~ 41~05612~ 44~03956~ 47~03778~.'),
  (28601, 46, 10, 18, 'Behold Israel after the flesh: are not they which eat of the sacrifices partakers of the altar?', '0~991~ 1~2474~ 2~2596~ 4~4561~: 5~1526~ 6~3780~ 7~1526~ 9~2068~ 12~2378~ 13~2844~ 16~2379~?'),
  (15944, 19, 119, 37, 'Turn away mine eyes from beholding vanity; and quicken thou me in thy way.', '&para; 1~05674~ 3~05869~ 5~07200~ 6~07723~; [7] 8~02421~ 13~01870~.'),
  (25033, 42, 2, 48, 'And when they saw him, they were amazed: and his mother said unto him, Son, why hast thou thus dealt with us? behold, thy father and I have sought thee sorrowing.', '0~2532~ 3~1492~ 4~846~, 7~1605~: 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~3384~ 11~2036~ 12~4314~ 13~846~, 14~5043~, 15~5101~ 17~4160~ 18~3779~ 19~4160~ 21~2254~? 22~2400~, 23~4675~ 24~3962~ 26~2504~ 28~2212~ 29~4571~ 30~3600~.'),
  (28517, 46, 7, 14, 'For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the husband: else were your children unclean; but now are they holy.', '0~1063~ 2~571~ 3~435~ 5~37~ 6~1722~ 8~1135~, 9~2532~ 11~571~ 12~1135~ 14~37~ 15~1722~ 17~435~: 18~1893~ 19~686~* 20~2076~ 21~5216~ 22~5043~ 23~169~; 24~1161~ 25~3568~ 27~2076~ 28~40~.'),
  (23111, 39, 1, 13, 'Ye said also, Behold, what a weariness is it! and ye have snuffed at it, saith the LORD of hosts; and ye brought that which was torn, and the lame, and the sick; thus ye brought an offering: should I accept this of your hand? saith the LORD.', '1~0559~ 6~04972~ [7 8] 12~05301~ 15~0559~ 17~03068~ 19~06635~; 22~0935~ [23 25] 26~01497~, 29~06455~, 32~02470~; 35~0935~ 37~04503~: 40~07521~ 44~03027~? 45~0559~ 47~03068~.'),
  (23728, 40, 17, 18, 'And Jesus rebuked the devil; and he departed out of him: and the child was cured from that very hour.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2008~ 4~1140~; 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~1831~ 9~575~ 10~846~: 11~2532~ 13~3816~ 15~2323~ 16~575~ 18~1565~ 19~5610~.'),
  (7268, 9, 2, 21, 'And the LORD visited Hannah, so that she conceived, and bare three sons and two daughters. And the child Samuel grew before the LORD.', '0~03588~ 2~03068~ 3~06485~ 4~02584~, 8~02029~, 10~03205~ 11~07969~ 12~01121~ 14~08147~ 15~01323~. 18~05288~ 19~08050~ 20~01431~ 21~05973~ 23~03068~.'),
  (4289, 4, 18, 27, 'And this your heave offering shall be reckoned unto you, as though it were the corn of the threshingfloor, and as the fulness of the winepress.', '[1] 4~08641~ 7~02803~ [12 13] 15~01715~ 18~01637~, 22~04395~ 25~03342~.'),
  (19592, 24, 26, 11, 'Then spake the priests and the prophets unto the princes and to all the people, saying, This man is worthy to die; for he hath prophesied against this city, as ye have heard with your ears.', '1~0559~ 3~03548~ 6~05030~ 9~08269~ 14~05971~, 15~0559~, 17~0376~ [18] 19~04941~ 21~04194~; 25~05012~ 28~05892~, 32~08085~ 35~0241~.'),
  (21726, 26, 48, 15, 'And the five thousand, that are left in the breadth over against the five and twenty thousand, shall be a profane place for the city, for dwelling, and for suburbs: and the city shall be in the midst thereof.', '2~02568~ 3~0505~, 6~03498~ 9~07341~ 11~06440~ 13~02568~ 15~06242~ 16~0505~, 20~02455~ [21] 24~05892~, 26~04186~, 29~04054~: 32~05892~ 37~08432~'),
  (10111, 12, 20, 5, 'Turn again, and tell Hezekiah the captain of my people, Thus saith the LORD, the God of David thy father, I have heard thy prayer, I have seen thy tears: behold, I will heal thee: on the third day thou shalt go up unto the house of the LORD.', '1~07725~, 3~0559~ 4~02396~ 6~05057~ 9~05971~, 11~0559~ 13~03068~, 15~0430~ 17~01732~ 19~01~, 22~08085~ 24~08605~, 27~07200~ 29~01832~: 33~07495~ 37~07992~ 38~03117~ 42~05927~ 45~01004~ 48~03068~.'),
  (22970, 38, 6, 14, 'And the crowns shall be to Helem, and to Tobijah, and to Jedaiah, and to Hen the son of Zephaniah, for a memorial in the temple of the LORD.', '2~05850~ 6~02494~, 9~02900~, 12~03048~, 15~02581~ 17~01121~ 19~06846~, 22~02146~ 25~01964~ 28~03068~.'),
  (11372, 14, 8, 18, 'And Huram sent him by the hands of his servants ships, and servants that had knowledge of the sea; and they went with the servants of Solomon to Ophir, and took thence four hundred and fifty talents of gold, and brought them to king Solomon.', '1~02361~ 2~07971~ 6~03027~ 9~05650~ 10~0591~ 11~0591~,* 13~05650~ 16~03045~ 19~03220~; 22~0935~ 25~05650~ 27~08010~ 29~0211~, 31~03947~ 33~0702~ 34~03967~ 36~02572~ 37~03603~ 39~02091~, 41~0935~ [42] 44~04428~ 45~08010~.'),
  (9789, 12, 9, 25, 'Then said Jehu to Bidkar his captain, Take up, and cast him in the portion of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite: for remember how that, when I and thou rode together after Ahab his father, the LORD laid this burden upon him;', '1~0559~ [2] 4~0920~ 6~07991~, 8~05375~, [9] 10~07993~ 14~02513~ 17~07704~ 19~05022~ 21~03158~: 23~02142~ 30~07392~ 31~06776~ 32~0310~ 33~0256~ 35~01~, 37~03068~ 38~05375~ 40~04853~'),
  (14410, 19, 34, 13, 'Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile.', '0~05341~ 2~03956~ 4~07451~, 7~08193~ 9~01696~ 10~04820~.'),
  (13229, 18, 15, 17, 'I will shew thee, hear me; and that which I have seen I will declare;', '&para; 2~02331~ 4~08085~ [8] 11~02372~ 14~05608~;'),
  (16465, 20, 3, 1, 'My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:', '&para; 1~01121~, 2~07911~ 5~08451~; 9~03820~ 10~05341~ 12~04687~:'),
  (1769, 2, 9, 22, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch forth thine hand toward heaven, that there may be hail in all the land of Egypt, upon man, and upon beast, and upon every herb of the field, throughout the land of Egypt.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~05186~ 9~03027~ 11~08064~, 16~01259~ 20~0776~ 22~04714~, 24~0120~, 27~0929~, 31~06212~ 34~07704~, 37~0776~ 39~04714~.'),
  (19954, 24, 40, 4, 'And now, behold, I loose thee this day from the chains which were upon thine hand. If it seem good unto thee to come with me into Babylon, come; and I will look well unto thee: but if it seem ill unto thee to come with me into Babylon, forbear: behold, all the land is before thee: whither it seemeth good and convenient for thee to go, thither go.', '4~06605~ 7~03117~ 10~0246~ [12] 15~03027~. 19~05869~ 20~02896~ 23~0935~ 27~0894~, 28~0935~; 33~07760~ 34~05869~* 41~07489~ 42~05869~* 46~0935~ 50~0894~, 51~02308~: 52~07200~, 55~0776~ [56] 57~06440~ 61~0413~ 62~02896~ 64~05869~ 65~03477~ 68~03212~, 70~03212~.'),
  (8141, 10, 5, 2, 'Also in time past, when Saul was king over us, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the LORD said to thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be a captain over Israel.', '3~08032~ 4~0865~,* 6~07586~ 8~04428~ 16~03318~ 19~0935~ 20~03478~: 23~03068~ 24~0559~ 29~07462~ 31~05971~ 32~03478~, 38~05057~ 40~03478~.'),
  (15924, 19, 119, 17, 'GIMEL. Deal bountifully with thy servant, that I may live, and keep thy word.', '&para; 2~01580~ 5~05650~, [6] 9~02421~, 11~08104~ 13~01697~.'),
  (22023, 27, 9, 26, 'And after threescore and two weeks shall Messiah be cut off, but not for himself: and the people of the prince that shall come shall destroy the city and the sanctuary; and the end thereof shall be with a flood, and unto the end of the war desolations are determined.', '1~0310~ 2~08346~ 4~08147~ 5~07620~ 7~04899~ 10~03772~, 17~05971~ 20~05057~ 23~0935~ 25~07843~ 27~05892~ 30~06944~; 33~07093~ [35 36] 39~07858~, 43~07093~ 46~04421~ 47~08074~ 49~02782~.'),
  (16196, 19, 135, 12, 'And gave their land for an heritage, an heritage unto Israel his people.', '1~05414~ 3~0776~ [4] 6~05159~, 8~05159~ 10~03478~ 12~05971~.'),
  (19507, 24, 23, 14, 'I have seen also in the prophets of Jerusalem an horrible thing: they commit adultery, and walk in lies: they strengthen also the hands of evildoers, that none doth return from his wickedness: they are all of them unto me as Sodom, and the inhabitants thereof as Gomorrah.', '2~07200~ 6~05030~ 8~03389~ 11~08186~: 14~05003~, 16~01980~ 18~08267~: 20~02388~ 23~03027~ 25~07489~, 27~0376~ 29~07725~ 32~07451~: 41~05467~, 44~03427~ 47~06017~.'),
  (10065, 12, 18, 33, 'Hath any of the gods of the nations delivered at all his land out of the hand of the king of Assyria?', '1~0376~ 4~0430~ 7~01471~ 8~05337~ 10~05337~ 12~0776~ 16~03027~ 19~04428~ 21~0804~?'),
  (28237, 45, 11, 12, 'Now if the fall of them be the riches of the world, and the diminishing of them the riches of the Gentiles; how much more their fulness?', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 3~3900~ 5~846~ [6] 8~4149~ 11~2889~, 12~2532~ 14~2275~ 16~846~ 18~4149~ 21~1484~; 22~4214~ 24~3123~ 25~846~ 26~4138~?'),
  (8145, 10, 5, 6, 'And the king and his men went to Jerusalem unto the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land: which spake unto David, saying, Except thou take away the blind and the lame, thou shalt not come in hither: thinking, David cannot come in hither.', '&para; 2~04428~ 5~0582~ 6~03212~ 8~03389~ 11~02983~, 13~03427~ 16~0776~: 18~0559~ 20~01732~, 21~0559~, 25~05493~ 27~05787~ 30~06455~, 35~0935~ 37~0559~, 38~01732~ 41~0935~'),
  (22786, 35, 3, 9, 'Thy bow was made quite naked, according to the oaths of the tribes, even thy word. Selah. Thou didst cleave the earth with rivers.', '1~07198~ 4~06181~ 5~05783~, [6] 9~07621~ 12~04294~, [13 14] 15~0562~. 16~05542~. 19~01234~ 21~0776~ 23~05104~.'),
  (19631, 24, 28, 4, 'And I will bring again to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah, with all the captives of Judah, that went into Babylon, saith the LORD: for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.', '4~07725~ 7~04725~ 8~03204~ 10~01121~ 12~03079~ 13~04428~ 15~03063~, 19~01546~ 21~03063~, 23~0935~ 25~0894~, 26~05002~ 28~03068~: 32~07665~ 34~05923~ 37~04428~ 39~0894~.'),
  (21248, 26, 31, 9, 'I have made him fair by the multitude of his branches: so that all the trees of Eden, that were in the garden of God, envied him.', '2~06213~ 4~03303~ 7~07230~ 10~01808~: 15~06086~ 17~05731~, [19] 22~01588~ 24~0430~, 25~07065~'),
  (9244, 11, 14, 18, 'And they buried him; and all Israel mourned for him, according to the word of the LORD, which he spake by the hand of his servant Ahijah the prophet.', '2~06912~ 6~03478~ 7~05594~ 13~01697~ 16~03068~, 19~01696~ 22~03027~ 25~05650~ 26~0281~ 28~05030~.'),
  (2133, 2, 22, 15, 'But if the owner thereof be with it, he shall not make it good: if it be an hired thing, it came for his hire.', '[0] 3~01167~ [5] [12] 13~07999~: [16] 18~07916~ [19] 21~0935~ 24~07939~.'),
  (24655, 41, 11, 4, 'And they went their way, and found the colt tied by the door without in a place where two ways met; and they loose him.', '0~1161~ 4~565~, 5~2532~ 6~2147~ 8~4454~ 9~1210~ 10~4314~ 12~2374~ 13~1854~ 14~1909~ 20~296~; 21~2532~ 23~3089~ 24~846~.'),
  (7175, 8, 2, 19, 'And her mother in law said unto her, Where hast thou gleaned to day? and where wroughtest thou? blessed be he that did take knowledge of thee. And she shewed her mother in law with whom she had wrought, and said, The man''s name with whom I wrought to day is Boaz.', '4~02545~ 5~0559~ 11~03950~ 13~03117~? 15~0375~ 16~06213~ 18~01288~ 24~05234~ 29~05046~ 33~02545~ 38~06213~, 40~0559~, 42~0376~ 43~08034~ 47~06213~ 49~03117~ [50] 51~01162~.'),
  (24002, 40, 24, 35, 'Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.', '0~3772~ 1~2532~ 2~1093~ 5~3928~, 6~1161~ 7~3450~ 8~3056~ 9~3928~ 10~3364~ 12~3928~.'),
  (25790, 42, 19, 45, 'And he went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold therein, and them that bought;', '0~2532~ 2~1525~ 3~1519~ 5~2411~, 7~756~ 10~1544~ 13~4453~ 14~846~ 15~1722~,* 16~2532~ 19~59~;'),
  (1249, 1, 41, 49, 'And Joseph gathered corn as the sand of the sea, very much, until he left numbering; for it was without number.', '1~03130~ 2~06651~ 3~01250~ 6~02344~ 9~03220~, 10~03966~ 11~07235~, 14~02308~ 15~05608~; [17 18] 19~0369~ 20~04557~.'),
  (23400, 40, 9, 11, 'And when the Pharisees saw it, they said unto his disciples, Why eateth your Master with publicans and sinners?', '0~2532~ 3~5330~ 4~1492~ [5] 7~2036~ 9~846~ 10~3101~, 11~1302~ 12~2068~ 13~5216~ 14~1320~ 15~3326~ 16~5057~ 17~2532~ 18~268~?'),
  (19544, 24, 25, 1, 'The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, that was the first year of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon;', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 9~05971~ 11~03063~ 14~07243~ 15~08141~ 17~03079~ 19~01121~ 21~02977~ 22~04428~ 24~03063~, [26] 28~07224~ 29~08141~ 31~05019~ 32~04428~ 34~0894~;'),
  (1649, 2, 5, 12, 'So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead of straw.', '2~05971~ 5~06327~ 9~0776~ 11~04714~ 13~07197~ 14~07179~ 17~08401~.'),
  (682, 1, 25, 20, 'And Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah to wife, the daughter of Bethuel the Syrian of Padanaram, the sister to Laban the Syrian.', '1~03327~ 3~0705~ 4~08141~ 5~01121~ 8~03947~ 9~07259~ 11~0802~, 13~01323~ 15~01328~ 17~0761~ 19~06307~, 21~0269~ 23~03837~ 25~0761~.'),
  (4092, 4, 13, 12, 'Of the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli.', '2~04294~ 4~01835~, 5~05988~ 7~01121~ 9~01582~.'),
  (25050, 42, 3, 13, 'And he said unto them, Exact no more than that which is appointed you.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~4238~ 6~3367~ 7~4119~ 8~3844~ 12~1299~ 13~5213~.'),
  (1079, 1, 36, 34, 'And Jobab died, and Husham of the land of Temani reigned in his stead.', '1~03103~ 2~04191~, 4~02367~ 7~0776~ 9~08489~ 10~04427~'),
  (29862, 55, 2, 19, 'Nevertheless the foundation of God standeth sure, having this seal, The Lord knoweth them that are his. And, Let every one that nameth the name of Christ depart from iniquity.', '&para; 0~3305~ 2~2310~ 4~2316~ 5~2476~ 6~4731~, 7~2192~ 8~5026~ 9~4973~, 11~2962~ 12~1097~ 15~5607~ 16~846~. 17~2532~, 18~868~ 20~3956~ 22~3687~ 24~3686~ 26~5547~ 27~868~ 28~575~ 29~93~.'),
  (13386, 18, 21, 22, 'Shall any teach God knowledge? seeing he judgeth those that are high.', '[1] 2~03925~ 3~0410~ 4~01847~? 7~08199~ 11~07311~.'),
  (19333, 24, 15, 9, 'She that hath borne seven languisheth: she hath given up the ghost; her sun is gone down while it was yet day: she hath been ashamed and confounded: and the residue of them will I deliver to the sword before their enemies, saith the LORD.', '3~03205~ 4~07651~ 5~0535~: 9~05301~ 11~05315~; 13~08121~ 15~0935~ [18 19] 21~03119~ 22~03117~:* 26~0954~ 28~02659~: 31~07611~ 36~05414~ 39~02719~ 40~06440~ 42~0341~, 43~05002~ 45~03068~.'),
  (29971, 57, 1, 17, 'If thou count me therefore a partner, receive him as myself.', '0~1487~ 2~2192~ 3~1691~ 4~3767~ 6~2844~, 7~4355~ 8~846~ 9~5613~ 10~1691~.'),
  (8095, 10, 3, 7, 'And Saul had a concubine, whose name was Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah: and Ishbosheth said to Abner, Wherefore hast thou gone in unto my father''s concubine?', '&para; 1~07586~ 4~06370~, 6~08034~ [7] 8~07532~, 10~01323~ 12~0345~: [14] 15~0559~ 17~074~, 22~0935~ 25~01~ 26~06370~?'),
  (26577, 43, 11, 39, 'Jesus said, Take ye away the stone. Martha, the sister of him that was dead, saith unto him, Lord, by this time he stinketh: for he hath been dead four days.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~, 4~142~ 6~3037~. 7~3136~, 9~79~ 14~2348~, 15~3004~ 17~846~, 18~2962~, 21~2235~ 23~3605~: 24~1063~ 27~2076~ [28] 30~5066~.'),
  (30110, 58, 8, 2, 'A minister of the sanctuary, and of the true tabernacle, which the Lord pitched, and not man.', '1~3011~ 4~39~, 5~2532~ 8~228~ 9~4633~, 10~3739~ 12~2962~ 13~4078~, 14~2532~ 15~3756~ 16~444~.'),
  (1297, 1, 43, 2, 'And it came to pass, when they had eaten up the corn which they had brought out of Egypt, their father said unto them, Go again, buy us a little food.', '9~03615~ 10~0398~* 12~07668~ 17~0935~ 19~04714~, 21~01~ 22~0559~ 26~07725~, 27~07666~ 30~04592~ 31~0400~.'),
  (26252, 43, 5, 27, 'And hath given him authority to execute judgment also, because he is the Son of man.', '0~2532~ 2~1325~ 3~846~ 4~1849~ 6~4160~ 7~2920~ 8~2532~, 9~3754~ 11~2076~ 13~5207~ 15~444~.'),
  (6048, 6, 9, 5, 'And old shoes and clouted upon their feet, and old garments upon them; and all the bread of their provision was dry and mouldy.', '1~01087~ 2~05275~ 4~02921~ 7~07272~, 9~01087~ 10~08008~ 16~03899~ 19~06718~ 21~03001~ [22] 23~05350~.'),
  (2984, 3, 10, 2, 'And there went out fire from the LORD, and devoured them, and they died before the LORD.', '3~03318~ 4~0784~ 7~03068~, 9~0398~ 13~04191~ 14~06440~ 16~03068~.'),
  (17345, 21, 2, 3, 'I sought in mine heart to give myself unto wine, yet acquainting mine heart with wisdom; and to lay hold on folly, till I might see what was that good for the sons of men, which they should do under the heaven all the days of their life.', '1~08446~ 4~03820~ 6~04900~ 7~01320~ 9~03196~, 11~05090~ 13~03820~ 15~02451~; 19~0270~ 21~05531~, 25~07200~ [27] 29~02896~ 32~01121~ 34~0120~, 38~06213~ 41~08064~ 42~04557~ 44~03117~ 47~02416~.'),
  (14995, 19, 71, 10, 'For mine enemies speak against me; and they that lay wait for my soul take counsel together,', '2~0341~ 3~0559~ 10~08104~ 13~05315~ 15~03289~ 16~03162~,'),
  (16481, 20, 3, 17, 'Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.', '1~01870~ [2] 3~01870~ 5~05278~, 9~05410~ [10] 11~07965~.'),
  (26063, 43, 1, 5, 'And the light shineth in darkness; and the darkness comprehended it not.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5457~ 3~5316~ 4~1722~ 5~4653~; 6~2532~ 8~4653~ 9~2638~ 10~846~ 11~3756~.'),
  (3617, 4, 1, 8, 'Of Issachar; Nethaneel the son of Zuar.', '1~03485~; 2~05417~ 4~01121~ 6~06686~.'),
  (2260, 2, 26, 20, 'And for the second side of the tabernacle on the north side there shall be twenty boards:', '3~08145~ 4~06763~ 7~04908~ 10~06828~ 11~06285~ [12 14] 15~06242~ 16~07175~:'),
  (13277, 18, 17, 8, 'Upright men shall be astonied at this, and the innocent shall stir up himself against the hypocrite.', '0~03477~ [1] 4~08074~ 9~05355~ 12~05782~ 16~02611~.'),
  (20007, 24, 43, 1, 'And it came to pass, that when Jeremiah had made an end of speaking unto all the people all the words of the LORD their God, for which the LORD their God had sent him to them, even all these words,', '&para; [5] 7~03414~ 11~03615~ 13~01696~ 17~05971~ 20~01697~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~, 29~03068~ 31~0430~ 33~07971~ [37] 40~01697~,'),
  (13192, 18, 14, 2, 'He cometh forth like a flower, and is cut down: he fleeth also as a shadow, and continueth not.', '2~03318~ 5~06731~, 9~05243~: 11~01272~ 15~06738~, 17~05975~'),
  (3893, 4, 7, 38, 'One golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense:', '0~0259~ 1~02091~ 2~03709~ 4~06235~ [5] 6~04392~ 8~07004~:'),
  (8817, 11, 2, 39, 'And it came to pass at the end of three years, that two of the servants of Shimei ran away unto Achish son of Maachah king of Gath. And they told Shimei, saying, Behold, thy servants be in Gath.', '7~07093~ 9~07969~ 10~08141~, 12~08147~ 15~05650~ 17~08096~ 19~01272~ 21~0397~ 22~01121~ 24~04601~ 25~04428~ 27~01661~. 30~05046~ 31~08096~, 32~0559~, 35~05650~ [36] 38~01661~.'),
  (18305, 23, 33, 17, 'Thine eyes shall see the king in his beauty: they shall behold the land that is very far off.', '1~05869~ 3~02372~ 5~04428~ 8~03308~: 11~07200~ 13~0776~ 18~04801~.'),
  (29088, 48, 1, 15, 'But when it pleased God, who separated me from my mother''s womb, and called me by his grace,', '0~1161~ 1~3753~ 3~2106~ 4~2316~, 5~3588~ 6~873~ 7~3165~ 8~1537~ 9~3450~ 10~3384~ 11~2836~, 12~2532~ 13~2564~ [14] 15~1223~ 16~846~ 17~5485~,'),
  (6858, 7, 11, 22, 'And they possessed all the coasts of the Amorites, from Arnon even unto Jabbok, and from the wilderness even unto Jordan.', '2~03423~ 5~01366~ 8~0567~, 10~0769~ 13~02999~, 17~04057~ 20~03383~.'),
  (11426, 14, 11, 3, 'Speak unto Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying,', '0~0559~ 2~07346~ 4~01121~ 6~08010~, 7~04428~ 9~03063~, 13~03478~ 15~03063~ 17~01144~, 18~0559~,'),
  (5619, 5, 28, 2, 'And all these blessings shall come on thee, and overtake thee, if thou shalt hearken unto the voice of the LORD thy God.', '3~01293~ 5~0935~ 9~05381~ 14~08085~ 17~06963~ 20~03068~ 22~0430~.'),
  (5793, 5, 32, 29, 'O that they were wise, that they understood this, that they would consider their latter end!', '1~03863~ 4~02449~, [5] 7~07919~ [9] 12~0995~ 15~0319~!'),
  (19708, 24, 31, 8, 'Behold, I will bring them from the north country, and gather them from the coasts of the earth, and with them the blind and the lame, the woman with child and her that travaileth with child together: a great company shall return thither.', '3~0935~ 7~06828~ 8~0776~, 10~06908~ 14~03411~ 17~0776~, [18] 22~05787~ 25~06455~, 29~02030~ 35~03205~ 36~03162~: 38~01419~ 39~06951~ 41~07725~'),
  (14549, 19, 40, 15, 'Let them be desolate for a reward of their shame that say unto me, Aha, aha.', '3~08074~ 6~06118~ 9~01322~ 11~0559~ 14~01889~, 15~01889~.'),
  (30919, 66, 12, 12, 'Therefore rejoice, ye heavens, and ye that dwell in them. Woe to the inhabiters of the earth and of the sea! for the devil is come down unto you, having great wrath, because he knoweth that he hath but a short time.', '&para; 0~5124~ 1~1223~* 2~2165~, [3] 4~3772~, 5~2532~ 8~4637~ 9~1722~ 10~846~. 11~3759~ 14~2730~ 17~1093~ 18~2532~ 21~2281~! 22~3754~ 24~1228~ 27~2597~ 28~4314~ 29~5209~, 30~2192~ 31~3173~ 32~2372~, 35~1492~ 36~3754~ 38~2192~ 41~3641~ 42~2540~.'),
  (2267, 2, 26, 27, 'And five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle, for the two sides westward.', '1~02568~ 2~01280~ 5~07175~ 8~08145~ 9~06763~ 12~04908~, 14~02568~ 15~01280~ 18~07175~ 21~06763~ 24~04908~, 28~03411~ 29~03220~.'),
  (23702, 40, 16, 20, 'Then charged he his disciples that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ.', '0~5119~ 2~1291~ 3~846~ 4~3101~ 5~2443~ 8~2036~ 10~3367~ 11~3754~ 12~846~ 13~2076~ 14~2424~ 16~5547~.'),
  (5940, 6, 4, 24, 'That all the people of the earth might know the hand of the LORD, that it is mighty: that ye might fear the LORD your God for ever.', '3~05971~ 6~0776~ 8~03045~ 10~03027~ 13~03068~, [16] 17~02389~: 21~03372~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~ 27~03117~.'),
  (24049, 40, 25, 31, 'When the Son of man shall come in his glory, and all the holy angels with him, then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory:', '&para; 0~3752~ 1~1161~ 2~5207~ 4~444~ 6~2064~ 7~1722~ 8~846~ 9~1391~, 10~2532~ 11~3956~ 13~40~ 14~32~ 15~3326~ 16~846~, 17~5119~ 20~2523~ 21~1909~ 23~2362~ 25~846~ 26~1391~:'),
  (22439, 30, 5, 7, 'Ye who turn judgment to wormwood, and leave off righteousness in the earth,', '2~02015~ 3~04941~ 5~03939~, 8~03240~ 9~06666~ 12~0776~,'),
  (27699, 44, 21, 19, 'And when he had saluted them, he declared particularly what things God had wrought among the Gentiles by his ministry.', '0~2532~ 4~782~ 5~846~, 7~1834~ 8~1538~ 9~2596~* 10~1520~ 11~3739~ 12~2316~ 14~4160~ 15~1722~ 17~1484~ 18~1223~ 19~846~ 20~1248~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (24108, 40, 26, 44, 'And he left them, and went away again, and prayed the third time, saying the same words.', '0~2532~ 2~863~ 3~846~, 6~565~ 7~3825~, 9~4336~ 10~1537~* 13~5154~, 14~2036~ 16~846~ 17~3056~.'),
  (28714, 46, 14, 20, 'Brethren, be not children in understanding: howbeit in malice be ye children, but in understanding be men.', '0~80~, 1~1096~ 2~3361~ 3~3813~ 5~5424~: 6~235~ 8~2549~ 11~3515~, 12~1161~ 14~5424~ 15~1096~ 16~5046~.'),
  (13609, 18, 31, 12, 'For it is a fire that consumeth to destruction, and would root out all mine increase.', '[2] 4~0784~ [5] 6~0398~ 8~011~, 12~08327~ 15~08393~.'),
  (990, 1, 34, 5, 'And Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah his daughter: now his sons were with his cattle in the field: and Jacob held his peace until they were come.', '1~03290~ 2~08085~ 6~02930~ 7~01783~ 9~01323~: 12~01121~ 16~04735~ 19~07704~: 21~03290~ 24~02790~ 28~0935~.'),
  (20822, 26, 16, 51, 'Neither hath Samaria committed half of thy sins; but thou hast multiplied thine abominations more than they, and hast justified thy sisters in all thine abominations which thou hast done.', '2~08111~ 3~02398~ 4~02677~ 7~02403~; 11~07235~ 13~08441~ 16~02007~, 19~06663~ 21~0269~ 25~08441~ 29~06213~.'),
  (27066, 44, 4, 28, 'For to do whatsoever thy hand and thy counsel determined before to be done.', '2~4160~ 3~3745~ 4~4675~ 5~5495~ 6~2532~ 7~4675~ 8~1012~ 10~4309~ 13~1096~.'),
  (7274, 9, 2, 27, 'And there came a man of God unto Eli, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Did I plainly appear unto the house of thy father, when they were in Egypt in Pharaoh''s house?', '&para; 2~0935~ 4~0376~ 6~0430~ 8~05941~, 10~0559~ 14~0559~ 16~03068~, 19~01540~ 20~01540~ 23~01004~ 26~01~, 31~04714~ 33~06547~ 34~01004~?'),
  (18983, 24, 2, 9, 'Wherefore I will yet plead with you, saith the LORD, and with your children''s children will I plead.', '&para; 4~07378~ 7~05002~ 9~03068~, 13~01121~ 14~01121~ 17~07378~.'),
  (30671, 63, 1, 10, 'If there come any unto you, and bring not this doctrine, receive him not into your house, neither bid him God speed:', '&para; 0~1536~ 2~2064~ 3~5100~ 4~1536~* 5~4314~ 6~5209~, 7~2532~ 8~5342~ 9~3756~ 10~5026~ 11~1322~, 12~2983~ 13~846~ 14~3361~ 15~1519~ [16] 17~3614~, 18~3361~ 19~2532~* 20~3004~ 21~846~ 23~5463~:'),
  (1971, 2, 16, 19, 'And Moses said, Let no man leave of it till the morning.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~, 5~0376~ 6~03498~ 11~01242~.'),
  (20734, 26, 13, 17, 'Likewise, thou son of man, set thy face against the daughters of thy people, which prophesy out of their own heart; and prophesy thou against them,', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~0120~, 5~07760~ 7~06440~ 10~01323~ 13~05971~, 15~05012~ 20~03820~; 22~05012~'),
  (22757, 35, 1, 17, 'Shall they therefore empty their net, and not spare continually to slay the nations?', '3~07324~ 5~02764~, 8~02550~ 9~08548~ 11~02026~ 13~01471~?'),
  (10731, 13, 12, 3, 'The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, the sons of Shemaah the Gibeathite; and Jeziel, and Pelet, the sons of Azmaveth; and Berachah, and Jehu the Antothite,', '1~07218~ [2] 3~0295~, 5~03101~, 7~01121~ 9~08094~ 11~01395~; 13~03149~, 15~06404~, 17~01121~ 19~05820~; 21~01294~, 23~03058~ 25~06069~,'),
  (21306, 26, 33, 17, 'Yet the children of thy people say, The way of the Lord is not equal: but as for them, their way is not equal.', '2~01121~ 5~05971~ 6~0559~, 8~01870~ 11~0136~ 14~08505~: 20~01870~ 23~08505~.'),
  (1574, 2, 2, 15, 'Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian: and he sat down by a well.', '2~06547~ 3~08085~ 5~01697~, 7~01245~ 9~02026~ 10~04872~. 12~04872~ 13~01272~ 16~06440~ 18~06547~, 20~03427~ 23~0776~ 25~04080~: 29~03427~ 32~0875~.'),
  (5125, 5, 7, 8, 'But because the LORD loved you, and because he would keep the oath which he had sworn unto your fathers, hath the LORD brought you out with a mighty hand, and redeemed you out of the house of bondmen, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt.', '3~03068~ 4~0160~ 10~08104~ 12~07621~ 16~07650~ 19~01~, 22~03068~ 25~03318~ 28~02389~ 29~03027~, 31~06299~ 36~01004~ 38~05650~, 41~03027~ 43~06547~ 44~04428~ 46~04714~.'),
  (20977, 26, 21, 24, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Because ye have made your iniquity to be remembered, in that your transgressions are discovered, so that in all your doings your sins do appear; because, I say, that ye are come to remembrance, ye shall be taken with the hand.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 11~05771~ 14~02142~, 18~06588~ 20~01540~, 26~05949~ 28~02403~ 30~07200~; [32 33] 39~02142~, 43~08610~ 46~03709~.'),
  (17823, 23, 8, 7, 'Now therefore, behold, the Lord bringeth up upon them the waters of the river, strong and many, even the king of Assyria, and all his glory: and he shall come up over all his channels, and go over all his banks:', '4~0136~ 6~05927~ 10~04325~ 13~05104~, 14~06099~ 16~07227~, [17] 19~04428~ 21~0804~, 25~03519~: 30~05927~ 34~0650~, 37~01980~ 40~01415~:'),
  (4300, 4, 19, 6, 'And the priest shall take cedar wood, and hyssop, and scarlet, and cast it into the midst of the burning of the heifer.', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 5~0730~ 6~06086~, 8~0231~, 10~08144~ 11~08438~,* 13~07993~ [14] 17~08432~ 20~08316~ 23~06510~.'),
  (21097, 26, 25, 5, 'And I will make Rabbah a stable for camels, and the Ammonites a couchingplace for flocks: and ye shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~05414~ 4~07237~ 6~05116~ 8~01581~, 11~05983~ 12~01121~ 13~04769~ 15~06629~: 19~03045~ [22] 24~03068~.'),
  (11949, 14, 34, 7, 'And when he had broken down the altars and the groves, and had beaten the graven images into powder, and cut down all the idols throughout all the land of Israel, he returned to Jerusalem.', '5~05422~ 7~04196~ 10~0842~, 13~03807~ 16~06456~ 18~01854~, 21~01438~ 24~02553~ 28~0776~ 30~03478~, 32~07725~ 34~03389~.'),
  (14930, 19, 68, 21, 'But God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses.', '1~0430~ 3~04272~ 5~07218~ 8~0341~, [9] 11~08181~ 12~06936~ 20~01980~ 23~0817~.'),
  (14336, 19, 30, 8, 'I cried to thee, O LORD; and unto the LORD I made supplication.', '1~07121~ 5~03068~; 9~03068~ 12~02603~.'),
  (21070, 26, 24, 5, 'Take the choice of the flock, and burn also the bones under it, and make it boil well, and let them seethe the bones of it therein.', '0~03947~ 2~04005~ 5~06629~, 7~01754~ 10~06106~ [13] 16~07570~ 17~07571~, 21~01310~ 23~06106~ 26~08432~.'),
  (3843, 4, 6, 15, 'And a basket of unleavened bread, cakes of fine flour mingled with oil, and wafers of unleavened bread anointed with oil, and their meat offering, and their drink offerings.', '2~05536~ 5~04682~, 6~02471~ 9~05560~ 10~01101~ 12~08081~, 14~07550~ 17~04682~ 18~04886~ 20~08081~, 24~04503~, 28~05262~.'),
  (452, 1, 18, 24, 'Peradventure there be fifty righteous within the city: wilt thou also destroy and not spare the place for the fifty righteous that are therein?', '2~03426~ 3~02572~ 4~06662~ 5~08432~ 7~05892~: 11~05595~ 14~05375~ 16~04725~ 17~04616~ 19~02572~ 20~06662~ [22] 23~07130~?'),
  (17643, 22, 7, 7, 'This thy stature is like to a palm tree, and thy breasts to clusters of grapes.', '2~06967~ 4~01819~ 8~08558~, 11~07699~ 13~0811~ [14 15]'),
  (12801, 17, 5, 13, 'Yet all this availeth me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king''s gate.', '3~07737~ 8~06256~ 10~07200~ 11~04782~ 13~03064~ 14~03427~ 17~04428~ 18~08179~.'),
  (11598, 14, 20, 2, 'Then there came some that told Jehoshaphat, saying, There cometh a great multitude against thee from beyond the sea on this side Syria; and, behold, they be in Hazazontamar, which is Engedi.', '2~0935~ 5~05046~ 6~03092~, 7~0559~, 9~0935~ 11~07227~ 12~01995~ 16~05676~ 18~03220~ 22~0758~; [26] 28~02688~, [30] 31~05872~.'),
  (27578, 44, 18, 5, 'And when Silas and Timotheus were come from Macedonia, Paul was pressed in the spirit, and testified to the Jews that Jesus was Christ.', '0~1161~ 1~5037~ 2~5613~* 3~4609~ 4~2532~ 5~5095~ 7~2718~ 8~575~ 9~3109~, 10~3972~ 12~4912~ 15~4151~, 17~1263~ 20~2453~ [21] 22~2424~ [23] 24~5547~.'),
  (3369, 3, 21, 19, 'Or a man that is brokenfooted, or brokenhanded,', '2~0376~ 5~07272~ 6~07667~,* 8~03027~ 9~07667~,*'),
  (13328, 18, 19, 22, 'Why do ye persecute me as God, and are not satisfied with my flesh?', '3~07291~ 6~0410~, 10~07646~ 13~01320~?'),
  (21714, 26, 48, 3, 'And by the border of Asher, from the east side even unto the west side, a portion for Naphtali.', '3~01366~ 5~0836~, 8~06921~ 9~06285~ 13~03220~ 14~06285~, 15~0259~ [16 17] 18~05321~.'),
  (9718, 12, 7, 3, 'And there were four leprous men at the entering in of the gate: and they said one to another, Why sit we here until we die?', '&para; 3~0702~ 4~06879~ 5~0582~ 9~06607~ 12~08179~: 15~0559~ 16~0376~ 18~07453~, 20~03427~ 25~04191~?'),
  (13477, 18, 26, 1, 'But Job answered and said,', '&para; 1~0347~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~,'),
  (14089, 19, 13, 6, 'I will sing unto the LORD, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.', '2~07891~ 5~03068~, 10~01580~'),
  (19320, 24, 14, 18, 'If I go forth into the field, then behold the slain with the sword! and if I enter into the city, then behold them that are sick with famine! yea, both the prophet and the priest go about into a land that they know not.', '3~03318~ 6~07704~, 10~02491~ 13~02719~! 17~0935~ 20~05892~, 26~08463~ 28~07458~! 32~05030~ 35~03548~ 37~05503~ 40~0776~ 43~03045~'),
  (17619, 22, 5, 12, 'His eyes are as the eyes of doves by the rivers of waters, washed with milk, and fitly set.', '1~05869~ [2] [4 5] 7~03123~ 10~0650~ 12~04325~, 13~07364~ 15~02461~, [16] 18~03427~ 19~04402~.*'),
  (1659, 2, 5, 22, 'And Moses returned unto the LORD, and said, Lord, wherefore hast thou so evil entreated this people? why is it that thou hast sent me?', '1~04872~ 2~07725~ 5~03068~, 7~0559~, 8~0136~, [12] 14~07489~ 16~05971~? [18] [20] 23~07971~'),
  (27830, 44, 25, 18, 'Against whom when the accusers stood up, they brought none accusation of such things as I supposed:', '0~4012~ 1~3739~ 4~2725~ 6~2476~, 8~2018~ 9~3762~ 10~156~ 14~3739~ 15~1473~ 16~5282~:'),
  (23928, 40, 22, 46, 'And no man was able to answer him a word, neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions.', '0~2532~ 2~3762~ 4~1410~ 6~611~ 7~846~ 9~3056~, 10~3761~ 11~5111~ 12~5100~ [13] 14~575~ 15~1565~ 16~2250~ 18~1905~ 19~846~ 21~3765~ [22]'),
  (18183, 23, 28, 10, 'For precept must be upon precept, precept upon precept; line upon line, line upon line; here a little, and there a little:', '1~06673~ [2 3] 5~06673~, 6~06673~ 8~06673~; 9~06957~ 11~06957~, 12~06957~ 14~06957~; 17~02191~, [18] 21~02191~:'),
  (15316, 19, 87, 6, 'The LORD shall count, when he writeth up the people, that this man was born there. Selah.', '1~03068~ 3~05608~, 7~03789~ 9~05971~, [10] [12] 14~03205~ 16~05542~.'),
  (23268, 40, 5, 24, 'Leave there thy gift before the altar, and go thy way; first be reconciled to thy brother, and then come and offer thy gift.', '0~863~ 1~1563~ 2~4675~ 3~1435~ 4~1715~ 6~2379~, 7~2532~ 10~5217~; 11~4412~ 13~1259~ 15~4675~ 16~80~, 17~2532~ 18~5119~ 19~2064~ 21~4374~ 22~4675~ 23~1435~.'),
  (3753, 4, 4, 5, 'And when the camp setteth forward, Aaron shall come, and his sons, and they shall take down the covering veil, and cover the ark of testimony with it:', '3~04264~ 5~05265~, 6~0175~ 8~0935~, 11~01121~, 16~03381~ 18~04539~ 19~06532~, 21~03680~ 23~0727~ 25~05715~'),
  (27416, 44, 13, 38, 'Be it known unto you therefore, men and brethren, that through this man is preached unto you the forgiveness of sins:', '1~2077~ 2~1110~ 4~5213~ 5~3767~, 6~435~ [7] 8~80~, 9~3754~ 10~1223~ 12~5127~ 14~2605~ 16~5213~ 18~859~ 20~266~:'),
  (22937, 38, 4, 6, 'Then he answered and spake unto me, saying, This is the word of the LORD unto Zerubbabel, saying, Not by might, nor by power, but by my spirit, saith the LORD of hosts.', '2~06030~ 4~0559~ 7~0559~, [9] 11~01697~ 14~03068~ 16~02216~, 17~0559~, 20~02428~, 23~03581~, 27~07307~, 28~0559~ 30~03068~ 32~06635~.'),
  (15780, 19, 109, 16, 'Because that he remembered not to shew mercy, but persecuted the poor and needy man, that he might even slay the broken in heart.', '3~02142~ 6~06213~ 7~02617~, 9~07291~ 11~06041~ 13~034~ 14~0376~, 19~04191~ 21~03512~ 23~03824~.'),
  (19891, 24, 37, 8, 'And the Chaldeans shall come again, and fight against this city, and take it, and burn it with fire.', '2~03778~ 5~07725~, 7~03898~ 10~05892~, 12~03920~ 15~08313~ 18~0784~.'),
  (28343, 45, 15, 24, 'Whensoever I take my journey into Spain, I will come to you: for I trust to see you in my journey, and to be brought on my way thitherward by you, if first I be somewhat filled with your company.', '0~1437~ 1~5613~ 4~4198~ 5~1519~ 6~4681~, 9~2064~ 10~4314~ 11~5209~: 12~1063~ 14~1679~ 16~2300~ 17~5209~ 20~1279~, 21~2532~ 27~4311~ 28~1563~ 29~5259~ 30~5216~, 31~1437~ 32~4412~ 34~1705~ 35~3313~ 36~1705~ 37~575~ 38~5216~ [39]'),
  (10662, 13, 9, 39, 'And Ner begat Kish; and Kish begat Saul; and Saul begat Jonathan, and Malchishua, and Abinadab, and Eshbaal.', '1~05369~ 2~03205~ 3~07027~; 5~07027~ 6~03205~ 7~07586~; 9~07586~ 10~03205~ 11~03083~, 13~04444~, 15~041~, 17~0792~.'),
  (24336, 41, 4, 3, 'Hearken; Behold, there went out a sower to sow:', '0~191~; 1~2400~, 4~1831~ 6~4687~ 8~4687~:'),
  (26288, 43, 6, 16, 'And when even was now come, his disciples went down unto the sea,', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 2~3798~ [4] 5~1096~, 6~846~ 7~3101~ 9~2597~ 10~1909~ 12~2281~,'),
  (19773, 24, 32, 33, 'And they have turned unto me the back, and not the face: though I taught them, rising up early and teaching them, yet they have not hearkened to receive instruction.', '3~06437~ 7~06203~, 11~06440~: 14~03925~ 18~07925~ 20~03925~ [21] 26~08085~ 28~03947~ 29~04148~.'),
  (18615, 23, 47, 7, 'And thou saidst, I shall be a lady for ever: so that thou didst not lay these things to thy heart, neither didst remember the latter end of it.', '&para; 2~0559~, 7~01404~ 9~05769~: [10] 15~07760~ [17] 20~03820~, 23~02142~ 26~0319~'),
  (1667, 2, 6, 7, 'And I will take you to me for a people, and I will be to you a God: and ye shall know that I am the LORD your God, which bringeth you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.', '3~03947~ 9~05971~, 17~0430~: 21~03045~ [24] 26~03068~ 28~0430~, 30~03318~ 36~05450~ 39~04714~.'),
  (27815, 44, 25, 3, 'And desired favour against him, that he would send for him to Jerusalem, laying wait in the way to kill him.', '1~154~ 2~5485~ 3~2596~ 4~846~, 5~3704~ 9~3343~ 10~846~ 11~1519~ 12~2419~, 13~4160~ 14~1747~ 15~2596~ 17~3598~ 19~337~ 20~846~.'),
  (14295, 19, 27, 1, 'A Psalm of David. The LORD is my light and my salvation; whom shall I fear? the LORD is the strength of my life; of whom shall I be afraid?', '&para; [0 1] 3] 3~01732~ 5~03068~ [6] 8~0216~ 11~03468~; 15~03372~? 17~03068~ [18] 20~04581~ 23~02416~; 29~06342~?'),
  (5318, 5, 14, 22, 'Thou shalt truly tithe all the increase of thy seed, that the field bringeth forth year by year.', '&para; 2~06237~ 3~06237~ 6~08393~ 9~02233~, 12~07704~ 14~03318~ 15~08141~ 17~08141~.'),
  (17814, 23, 7, 23, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that every place shall be, where there were a thousand vines at a thousand silverlings, it shall even be for briers and thorns.', '8~03117~, [9] 11~04725~ 18~0505~ 19~01612~ 22~0505~ 23~03701~, [26] 29~08068~ 31~07898~.'),
  (8558, 10, 19, 39, 'And all the people went over Jordan. And when the king was come over, the king kissed Barzillai, and blessed him; and he returned unto his own place.', '3~05971~ 5~05674~ 6~03383~. 10~04428~ 13~05674~, 15~04428~ 16~05401~ 17~01271~, 19~01288~ 23~07725~ 27~04725~.'),
  (2029, 2, 18, 25, 'And Moses chose able men out of all Israel, and made them heads over the people, rulers of thousands, rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens.', '1~04872~ 2~0977~ 3~02428~ 4~0582~ 8~03478~, 10~05414~ 12~07218~ 15~05971~, 16~08269~ 18~0505~, 19~08269~ 21~03967~, 22~08269~ 24~02572~, 26~08269~ 28~06235~.'),
  (9528, 11, 22, 40, 'So Ahab slept with his fathers; and Ahaziah his son reigned in his stead.', '1~0256~ 2~07901~ 5~01~; 7~0274~ 9~01121~ 10~04427~'),
  (10754, 13, 12, 26, 'Of the children of Levi four thousand and six hundred.', '2~01121~ 4~03878~ 5~0702~ 6~0505~ 8~08337~ 9~03967~.'),
  (26922, 43, 21, 8, 'And the other disciples came in a little ship; (for they were not far from land, but as it were two hundred cubits,) dragging the net with fishes.', '0~1161~ 2~243~ 3~3101~ 4~2064~ 8~4142~; 9~1063~* 12~2258~ 13~3756~ 14~3112~ 15~575~ 16~1093~, 17~235~ 20~575~ 21~5613~ 22~1250~ 23~4083~,) 24~4951~ 26~1350~ 28~2486~.'),
  (15595, 19, 104, 15, 'And wine that maketh glad the heart of man, and oil to make his face to shine, and bread which strengtheneth man''s heart.', '1~03196~ [2] 4~08055~ 6~03824~ 8~0582~, [9] 10~08081~ [13] 14~06440~ 16~06670~, 18~03899~ [19] 20~05582~ 21~0582~ 22~03824~.'),
  (3351, 3, 21, 1, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Speak unto the priests the sons of Aaron, and say unto them, There shall none be defiled for the dead among his people:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~ 9~03548~ 11~01121~ 13~0175~, 15~0559~ 22~02930~ 25~05315~ 28~05971~:'),
  (9298, 11, 16, 7, 'And also by the hand of the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani came the word of the LORD against Baasha, and against his house, even for all the evil that he did in the sight of the LORD, in provoking him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house of Jeroboam; and because he killed him.', '4~03027~ 7~05030~ 8~03058~ 10~01121~ 12~02607~ 15~01697~ 18~03068~ 20~01201~, 24~01004~, 29~07451~ 32~06213~ 35~05869~ 38~03068~, 43~03707~ 46~04639~ 49~03027~, 54~01004~ 56~03379~; 60~05221~'),
  (19262, 24, 12, 4, 'How long shall the land mourn, and the herbs of every field wither, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein? the beasts are consumed, and the birds; because they said, He shall not see our last end.', '4~0776~ 5~056~, 8~06212~ 11~07704~ 12~03001~, 15~07451~ 19~03427~ 22~0929~ 24~05595~, 27~05775~; 30~0559~, 34~07200~ 37~0319~.'),
  (775, 1, 27, 44, 'And tarry with him a few days, until thy brother''s fury turn away;', '1~03427~ 5~0259~ 6~03117~, 7~0834~ 9~0251~ 10~02534~ 12~07725~;'),
  (15171, 19, 78, 49, 'He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending evil angels among them.', '1~07971~ 5~02740~ 8~0639~, 9~05678~, 11~02195~, 13~06869~, 15~04917~ 16~07451~ 17~04397~ [18 19]'),
  (10469, 13, 6, 7, 'Meraioth begat Amariah, and Amariah begat Ahitub,', '0~04812~ 1~03205~ 2~0568~, 4~0568~ 5~03205~ 6~0285~,'),
  (15515, 19, 99, 7, 'He spake unto them in the cloudy pillar: they kept his testimonies, and the ordinance that he gave them.', '1~01696~ 6~06051~ 7~05982~: 9~08104~ 11~05713~, 14~02706~ [15] 17~05414~'),
  (3799, 4, 5, 2, 'Command the children of Israel, that they put out of the camp every leper, and every one that hath an issue, and whosoever is defiled by the dead:', '0~06680~ 2~01121~ 4~03478~, 8~07971~ 11~04264~ 13~06879~, 20~02100~, 24~02931~ 27~05315~:'),
  (6598, 7, 3, 23, 'Then Ehud went forth through the porch, and shut the doors of the parlour upon him, and locked them.', '1~0164~ 3~03318~ 6~04528~, 8~05462~ 10~01817~ 13~05944~ 17~05274~'),
  (25414, 42, 10, 39, 'And she had a sister called Mary, which also sat at Jesus'' feet, and heard his word.', '0~2532~ 1~3592~ 2~2258~ 4~79~ 5~2564~ 6~3137~, 7~3739~ 8~2532~ 9~3869~ 10~3844~ 11~2424~ 12~4228~, 14~191~ 15~846~ 16~3056~.'),
  (4236, 4, 16, 37, 'Speak unto Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest, that he take up the censers out of the burning, and scatter thou the fire yonder; for they are hallowed.', '0~0559~ 2~0499~ 4~01121~ 6~0175~ 8~03548~, 12~07311~ 14~04289~ 15~0996~ 18~08316~, 20~02219~ 23~0784~ 24~01973~; 28~06942~.'),
  (9243, 11, 14, 17, 'And Jeroboam''s wife arose, and departed, and came to Tirzah: and when she came to the threshold of the door, the child died;', '1~03379~ 2~0802~ 3~06965~, 5~03212~, 7~0935~ 9~08656~: [10] 13~0935~ 16~05592~ 19~01004~, 21~05288~ 22~04191~;'),
  (15200, 19, 79, 6, 'Pour out thy wrath upon the heathen that have not known thee, and upon the kingdoms that have not called upon thy name.', '&para; 1~08210~ 3~02534~ 6~01471~ 10~03045~ 15~04467~ 19~07121~ 22~08034~.'),
  (17910, 23, 12, 1, 'And in that day thou shalt say, O LORD, I will praise thee: though thou wast angry with me, thine anger is turned away, and thou comfortedst me.', '&para; 3~03117~ 6~0559~, 8~03068~, 11~03034~ 16~0599~ 20~0639~ 23~07725~, 26~05162~'),
  (3003, 3, 11, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and to Aaron, saying unto them,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~0175~, 9~0559~'),
  (31017, 66, 18, 8, 'Therefore shall her plagues come in one day, death, and mourning, and famine; and she shall be utterly burned with fire: for strong is the Lord God who judgeth her.', '0~1223~ 1~5124~* 2~2240~ 3~846~ 4~4127~ 5~2240~ 6~1722~ 7~3391~ 8~2250~, 9~2288~, 10~2532~ 11~3997~, 12~2532~ 13~3042~; 14~2532~ 19~2618~ 20~1722~ 21~4442~: 22~3754~ 23~2478~ [24] 26~2962~ 27~2316~ 28~3588~ 29~2919~ 30~846~.'),
  (2607, 2, 36, 36, 'And he made thereunto four pillars of shittim wood, and overlaid them with gold: their hooks were of gold; and he cast for them four sockets of silver.', '2~06213~ 4~0702~ 5~05982~ [6] 7~07848~ [8] 10~06823~ 13~02091~: 15~02053~ [16 17] 18~02091~; 21~03332~ 24~0702~ 25~0134~ 27~03701~.'),
  (712, 1, 26, 16, 'And Abimelech said unto Isaac, Go from us; for thou art much mightier than we.', '1~040~ 2~0559~ 4~03327~, 5~03212~ 11~03966~ 12~06105~'),
  (4574, 4, 27, 14, 'For ye rebelled against my commandment in the desert of Zin, in the strife of the congregation, to sanctify me at the water before their eyes: that is the water of Meribah in Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.', '2~04784~ 5~06310~ 8~04057~ 10~06790~, 13~04808~ 16~05712~, 18~06942~ 22~04325~ 25~05869~: [27] 29~04325~ 31~04809~ 33~06946~ 36~04057~ 38~06790~.'),
  (405, 1, 17, 4, 'As for me, behold, my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations.', '&para; 2~0589~, 5~01285~ [6] 14~01~ 16~01995~ 17~01471~.'),
  (17486, 21, 9, 2, 'All things come alike to all: there is one event to the righteous, and to the wicked; to the good and to the clean, and to the unclean; to him that sacrificeth, and to him that sacrificeth not: as is the good, so is the sinner; and he that sweareth, as he that feareth an oath.', '[1 2] [6 7] 8~0259~ 9~04745~ 12~06662~, 16~07563~; 19~02896~ 23~02889~, 27~02931~; 31~02076~, 35~0834~ 36~02076~ [39] 41~02896~, [43] 45~02398~; [46] 49~07650~, [51] 53~03373~ 55~07621~.'),
  (2542, 2, 35, 6, 'And blue, and purple, and scarlet, and fine linen, and goats'' hair,', '1~08504~, 3~0713~, 5~08438~ 6~08144~,* 9~08336~, 11~05795~ [12]'),
  (1456, 1, 47, 31, 'And he said, Swear unto me. And he sware unto him. And Israel bowed himself upon the bed''s head.', '2~0559~, 3~07650~ 8~07650~ 12~03478~ 13~07812~ 17~04296~ 18~07218~.'),
  (21253, 26, 31, 14, 'To the end that none of all the trees by the waters exalt themselves for their height, neither shoot up their top among the thick boughs, neither their trees stand up in their height, all that drink water: for they are all delivered unto death, to the nether parts of the earth, in the midst of the children of men, with them that go down to the pit.', '8~06086~ 11~04325~ 12~01361~ 16~06967~, 19~05414~ 21~06788~ 25~05688~, 28~0352~ 30~05975~ 33~01363~, 36~08354~ 37~04325~: 42~05414~ 44~04194~, 48~08482~ 51~0776~, 54~08432~ 57~01121~ 59~0120~, 64~03381~ 67~0953~.'),
  (24829, 41, 14, 64, 'Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.', '2~191~ 4~988~: 5~5101~ 6~5316~ 7~5213~? 8~1161~ 10~3956~ 11~2632~ 12~846~ 14~1511~ 15~1777~ 17~2288~.'),
  (21655, 26, 45, 16, 'All the people of the land shall give this oblation for the prince in Israel.', '2~05971~ 5~0776~ 9~08641~ 12~05387~ 14~03478~.'),
  (19823, 24, 34, 13, 'Thus saith the LORD, the God of Israel; I made a covenant with your fathers in the day that I brought them forth out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondmen, saying,', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~0430~ 7~03478~; 9~03772~ 11~01285~ 14~01~ 17~03117~ 22~03318~ 26~0776~ 28~04714~, 32~01004~ 34~05650~, 35~0559~,'),
  (15799, 19, 110, 4, 'The LORD hath sworn, and will not repent, Thou art a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek.', '1~03068~ 3~07650~, 7~05162~, [9] 11~03548~ 13~05769~ 16~01700~ 18~04442~.'),
  (24438, 41, 6, 21, 'And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief estates of Galilee;', '0~2532~ 3~2121~ 4~2250~ 6~1096~, 7~3753~ 8~2264~ 10~846~ 11~1077~ 12~4160~ 14~1173~ 16~846~ 17~3175~ 18~2532~,* 20~5506~, 21~2532~ 22~4413~ [23] 25~1056~;'),
  (3852, 4, 6, 24, 'The LORD bless thee, and keep thee:', '1~03068~ 2~01288~ 5~08104~'),
  (20253, 24, 51, 32, 'And that the passages are stopped, and the reeds they have burned with fire, and the men of war are affrighted.', '3~04569~ 5~08610~, 8~098~ 11~08313~ 13~0784~, 16~0582~ 18~04421~ 20~0926~.'),
  (28336, 45, 15, 17, 'I have therefore whereof I may glory through Jesus Christ in those things which pertain to God.', '&para; 1~2192~ 3~3767~ 6~2746~ 7~1722~ 8~2424~ 9~5547~ 15~4314~ 16~2316~.'),
  (28042, 45, 4, 4, 'Now to him that worketh is the reward not reckoned of grace, but of debt.', '0~1161~ 4~2038~ 5~3049~ 7~3408~ 8~3756~ 9~3049~ 10~2596~ 11~5485~, 12~235~ 13~2596~ 14~3783~.'),
  (18696, 23, 51, 14, 'The captive exile hasteneth that he may be loosed, and that he should not die in the pit, nor that his bread should fail.', '2~06808~ 3~04116~ 8~06605~, 14~04191~ 17~07845~, 21~03899~ 23~02637~.');
