VALUES
  (30223, 58, 11, 35, 'Women received their dead raised to life again: and others were tortured, not accepting deliverance; that they might obtain a better resurrection:', '0~1135~ 1~2983~ 2~846~ 3~3498~ 7~386~ 8~1537~:* 9~1161~ 10~243~ 12~5178~, 13~3756~ 14~4327~ 15~629~; 16~2443~ 19~5177~ 21~2909~ 22~386~:'),
  (1955, 2, 16, 3, 'And the children of Israel said unto them, Would to God we had died by the hand of the LORD in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the flesh pots, and when we did eat bread to the full; for ye have brought us forth into this wilderness, to kill this whole assembly with hunger.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~ 10~05414~ 11~04310~* 14~04191~ 17~03027~ 20~03068~ 23~0776~ 25~04714~, 28~03427~ 31~01320~ 32~05518~, [33] 37~0398~ 38~03899~ 41~07648~; 47~03318~ 50~04057~, 52~04191~ 55~06951~ 57~07458~.'),
  (14826, 19, 60, 10, 'Wilt not thou, O God, which hadst cast us off? and thou, O God, which didst not go out with our armies?', '[0] 4~0430~, [5] 9~02186~? [11] 13~0430~, [14] 18~03318~ 21~06635~?'),
  (11022, 13, 23, 31, 'And to offer all burnt sacrifices unto the LORD in the sabbaths, in the new moons, and on the set feasts, by number, according to the order commanded unto them, continually before the LORD:', '2~05927~ 5~05930~ 8~03068~ 11~07676~, 15~02320~, 20~04150~, 22~04557~, 26~04941~ 30~08548~ 31~06440~ 33~03068~:'),
  (13894, 18, 40, 21, 'He lieth under the shady trees, in the covert of the reed, and fens.', '1~07901~ 5~06628~, 8~05643~ 11~07070~, 13~01207~.'),
  (4282, 4, 18, 20, 'And the LORD spake unto Aaron, Thou shalt have no inheritance in their land, neither shalt thou have any part among them: I am thy part and thine inheritance among the children of Israel.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~0175~, 10~05157~ 13~0776~, 19~02506~ 20~08432~ [23] 25~02506~ 28~05159~ 29~08432~ 31~01121~ 33~03478~.'),
  (979, 1, 33, 14, 'Let my lord, I pray thee, pass over before his servant: and I will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me and the children be able to endure, until I come unto my lord unto Seir.', '2~0113~, 7~05674~ 8~06440~ 10~05650~: 15~05095~ 16~0328~, 18~07272~ 20~04399~ 24~06440~ 27~03206~ 31~07272~, 34~0935~ 37~0113~ 39~08165~.'),
  (26445, 43, 8, 49, 'Jesus answered, I have not a devil; but I honour my Father, and ye do dishonour me.', '0~2424~ 1~611~, 2~1473~ 3~2192~ 4~3756~ 6~1140~; 7~235~ 9~5091~ 10~3450~ 11~3962~, 12~2532~ 13~5210~ 15~818~ 16~3165~.'),
  (6243, 6, 15, 34, 'And Zanoah, and Engannim, Tappuah, and Enam,', '1~02182~, 3~05873~, 4~08599~, 6~05879~,'),
  (17836, 23, 8, 20, 'To the law and to the testimony: if they speak not according to this word, it is because there is no light in them.', '2~08451~ 6~08584~: 9~0559~ 14~01697~, [15 16] [18 19] 21~07837~'),
  (10997, 13, 23, 6, 'And David divided them into courses among the sons of Levi, namely, Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.', '1~01732~ 2~02505~ 5~04256~ 8~01121~ 10~03878~, [11] 12~01648~, 13~06955~, 15~04847~.'),
  (4524, 4, 26, 30, 'These are the sons of Gilead: of Jeezer, the family of the Jeezerites: of Helek, the family of the Helekites:', '[1] 3~01121~ 5~01568~: [6] 7~0372~, 9~04940~ 12~0373~: 14~02507~, 16~04940~ 19~02516~:'),
  (27771, 44, 23, 21, 'But do not thou yield unto them: for there lie in wait for him of them more than forty men, which have bound themselves with an oath, that they will neither eat nor drink till they have killed him: and now are they ready, looking for a promise from thee.', '0~3767~ 1~3982~ 2~3361~ 3~4771~ 4~3982~ 6~846~: 7~1063~ 12~1748~ 13~846~ 14~1537~ 15~846~ 17~4119~ 18~5062~ 19~435~, 20~3748~ 22~332~ 23~1438~ 26~332~, 29~5315~ 30~3383~ 31~5315~ 32~3383~ 33~4095~ 34~3739~ 35~2193~ 37~337~ 38~846~: 39~2532~ 40~3568~ 42~1526~ 43~2092~, 45~4327~ 47~1860~ 48~575~ 49~4675~.'),
  (1992, 2, 17, 4, 'And Moses cried unto the LORD, saying, What shall I do unto this people? they be almost ready to stone me.', '1~04872~ 2~06817~ 5~03068~, 6~0559~, 10~06213~ 13~05971~? 16~04592~ 19~05619~'),
  (20320, 25, 1, 1, 'How doth the city sit solitary, that was full of people! how is she become as a widow! she that was great among the nations, and princess among the provinces, how is she become tributary!', '&para; 3~05892~ 4~03427~ 5~0910~, [6 7] 8~07227~ 10~05971~! [11] 17~0490~! [19 20] 21~07227~ 24~01471~, [25] 26~08282~ 29~04082~, [30] 34~04522~!'),
  (30611, 62, 3, 16, 'Hereby perceive we the love of God, because he laid down his life for us: and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.', '0~5129~ 1~1722~ 2~1097~ 4~26~ [5 6] 7~3754~ 8~1565~ 10~5087~ 11~846~ 12~5590~ 13~5228~ 14~2257~: 15~2532~ 16~2249~ 17~3784~ 20~5087~ [21] 22~5590~ 23~5228~ 25~80~.'),
  (6780, 7, 9, 19, 'If ye then have dealt truly and sincerely with Jerubbaal and with his house this day, then rejoice ye in Abimelech, and let him also rejoice in you:', '4~06213~ 5~0571~ 7~08549~ 9~03378~ 13~01004~ 15~03117~, [16] 17~08055~ 20~040~, 25~08055~'),
  (98, 1, 4, 18, 'And unto Enoch was born Irad: and Irad begat Mehujael: and Mehujael begat Methusael: and Methusael begat Lamech.', '2~02585~ 4~03205~ 5~05897~: 7~05897~ 8~03205~ 9~04232~: 11~04232~ 12~03205~ 13~04967~: 15~04967~ 16~03205~ 17~03929~.'),
  (914, 1, 31, 37, 'Whereas thou hast searched all my stuff, what hast thou found of all thy household stuff? set it here before my brethren and thy brethren, that they may judge betwixt us both.', '0~03588~ 3~04959~ 6~03627~, 10~04672~ 14~01004~ 15~03627~? 16~07760~ [17] 18~03541~ 21~0251~ 24~0251~, 28~03198~ 29~0996~ 31~08147~.'),
  (15701, 19, 106, 41, 'And he gave them into the hand of the heathen; and they that hated them ruled over them.', '2~05414~ 6~03027~ 9~01471~; 13~08130~ 15~04910~'),
  (10550, 13, 7, 7, 'And the sons of Bela; Ezbon, and Uzzi, and Uzziel, and Jerimoth, and Iri, five; heads of the house of their fathers, mighty men of valour; and were reckoned by their genealogies twenty and two thousand and thirty and four.', '2~01121~ 4~01106~; 5~0675~, 7~05813~, 9~05816~, 11~03406~, 13~05901~, 14~02568~; 15~07218~ 18~01004~ [20] 21~01~, 22~01368~ 25~02428~; 31~03187~ 32~06242~ 34~08147~ 35~0505~ 37~07970~ 39~0702~.'),
  (25867, 42, 21, 27, 'And then shall they see the Son of man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.', '0~2532~ 1~5119~ 4~3700~ 6~5207~ 8~444~ 9~2064~ 10~1722~ 12~3507~ 13~3326~ 14~1411~ 15~2532~ 16~4183~ 17~1391~.'),
  (23113, 39, 2, 1, 'And now, O ye priests, this commandment is for you.', '&para; 4~03548~, 6~04687~ [7]'),
  (19067, 24, 4, 31, 'For I have heard a voice as of a woman in travail, and the anguish as of her that bringeth forth her first child, the voice of the daughter of Zion, that bewaileth herself, that spreadeth her hands, saying, Woe is me now! for my soul is wearied because of murderers.', '3~08085~ 5~06963~ 11~02470~, [12] 14~06869~ 23~01069~, 25~06963~ 28~01323~ 30~06726~, [31] 32~03306~ [34] 35~06566~ 37~03709~, [38] 39~0188~ [40] 45~05315~ 47~05888~ 50~02026~.'),
  (4291, 4, 18, 29, 'Out of all your gifts ye shall offer every heave offering of the LORD, of all the best thereof, even the hallowed part thereof out of it.', '4~04979~ 7~07311~ 10~08641~ 13~03068~, 17~02459~ [19] 22~04720~'),
  (13839, 18, 38, 37, 'Who can number the clouds in wisdom? or who can stay the bottles of heaven,', '2~05608~ 4~07834~ 6~02451~? 10~07901~ 12~05035~ 14~08064~,'),
  (22189, 28, 7, 2, 'And they consider not in their hearts that I remember all their wickedness: now their own doings have beset them about; they are before my face.', '2~0559~ 6~03824~ [7] 9~02142~ 12~07451~: 16~04611~ 20~05437~; 25~06440~.'),
  (15456, 19, 94, 16, 'Who will rise up for me against the evildoers? or who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?', '3~06965~ 8~07489~? [9] 13~03320~ 18~06466~ 20~0205~?'),
  (21150, 26, 27, 20, 'Dedan was thy merchant in precious clothes for chariots.', '0~01719~ [1] 3~07402~ 5~02667~ 6~0899~ 8~07396~.'),
  (10494, 13, 6, 32, 'And they ministered before the dwelling place of the tabernacle of the congregation with singing, until Solomon had built the house of the LORD in Jerusalem: and then they waited on their office according to their order.', '2~08334~ 3~06440~ 5~04908~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~ 14~07892~, 16~08010~ 18~01129~ 20~01004~ 23~03068~ 25~03389~: [27] 29~05975~ 32~05656~ 36~04941~.'),
  (27595, 44, 18, 22, 'And when he had landed at Caesarea, and gone up, and saluted the church, he went down to Antioch.', '0~2532~ 4~2718~ 5~1519~ 6~2542~, 9~305~, 10~2532~ 11~782~ 13~1577~, 16~2597~ 17~1519~ 18~490~.'),
  (16221, 19, 136, 16, 'To him which led his people through the wilderness: for his mercy endureth for ever.', '3~03212~ 5~05971~ 8~04057~: 11~02617~ [12] 14~05769~.'),
  (21963, 27, 7, 21, 'I beheld, and the same horn made war with the saints, and prevailed against them;', '1~01934~ 2~02370~,* 5~01797~ 6~07162~ 7~05648~ 8~07129~ 9~05974~ 11~06922~, 13~03202~'),
  (26296, 43, 6, 24, 'When the people therefore saw that Jesus was not there, neither his disciples, they also took shipping, and came to Capernaum, seeking for Jesus.', '0~3753~ 2~3793~ 3~3767~ 4~1492~ 5~3754~ 6~2424~ 7~2076~ 8~3756~ 9~1563~, 10~3761~ 11~846~ 12~3101~, 13~846~ 14~2532~ 15~1684~ 16~1519~* 17~4143~, 18~2532~ 19~2064~ 20~1519~ 21~2584~, 23~2212~ 24~2424~.'),
  (21789, 27, 2, 22, 'He revealeth the deep and secret things: he knoweth what is in the darkness, and the light dwelleth with him.', '1~01541~ 3~05994~ 6~05642~: 8~03046~ 9~04101~ [10] 13~02816~, 16~05094~ 17~08271~ 19~05974~.'),
  (27515, 44, 16, 16, 'And it came to pass, as we went to prayer, a certain damsel possessed with a spirit of divination met us, which brought her masters much gain by soothsaying:', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 6~2257~ 7~4198~ 8~1519~ 9~4335~, 11~5100~ 12~3814~ 13~2192~ 16~4151~ 18~4436~ 19~528~ 20~2254~, 21~3748~ 22~3930~ 23~846~ 24~2962~ 25~4183~ 26~2039~ 28~3132~:'),
  (15709, 19, 107, 1, 'O give thanks unto the LORD, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.', '&para; 2~03034~ 5~03068~, [7 8] 9~02896~: 12~02617~ [13] 15~05769~.'),
  (19014, 24, 3, 3, 'Therefore the showers have been withholden, and there hath been no latter rain; and thou hadst a whore''s forehead, thou refusedst to be ashamed.', '2~07241~ 5~04513~, 12~04456~; 17~02181~ 18~0802~* 19~04696~, 21~03985~ 24~03637~.'),
  (7635, 9, 17, 10, 'And the Philistine said, I defy the armies of Israel this day; give me a man, that we may fight together.', '2~06430~ 3~0559~, 5~02778~ 7~04634~ 9~03478~ 11~03117~; 12~05414~ 15~0376~, 19~03898~ 20~03162~.'),
  (16996, 20, 21, 3, 'To do justice and judgment is more acceptable to the LORD than sacrifice.', '&para; 1~06213~ 2~06666~ 4~04941~ [5] 7~0977~ 10~03068~ 12~02077~.'),
  (21448, 26, 38, 14, 'Therefore, son of man, prophesy and say unto Gog, Thus saith the Lord GOD; In that day when my people of Israel dwelleth safely, shalt thou not know it?', '&para; 1~01121~ 3~0120~, 4~05012~ 6~0559~ 8~01463~, 10~0559~ 12~0136~ 13~03069~; 16~03117~ 19~05971~ 21~03478~ 22~03427~ 23~0983~, 27~03045~ [28]'),
  (27209, 44, 8, 17, 'Then laid they their hands on them, and they received the Holy Ghost.', '0~5119~ 2~2007~ [3] 4~5495~ 5~1909~ 6~846~, 7~2532~ 9~2983~ 11~40~ 12~4151~.'),
  (2276, 2, 26, 36, 'And thou shalt make an hanging for the door of the tent, of blue, and purple, and scarlet, and fine twined linen, wrought with needlework.', '3~06213~ 5~04539~ 8~06607~ 11~0168~, [12] 13~08504~, 15~0713~, 17~08144~ 18~08438~,* 21~07806~ 22~08336~, 23~04639~ 25~07551~.'),
  (16362, 19, 147, 2, 'The LORD doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel.', '1~03068~ 4~01129~ 5~03389~: 8~03664~ 10~01760~ 12~03478~.'),
  (13498, 18, 27, 8, 'For what is the hope of the hypocrite, though he hath gained, when God taketh away his soul?', '[2] 4~08615~ 7~02611~, 11~01214~, 13~0433~ 15~07953~ 17~05315~?'),
  (28063, 45, 4, 25, 'Who was delivered for our offences, and was raised again for our justification.', '0~3739~ 2~3860~ 3~1223~ 4~2257~ 5~3900~, 6~2532~ 9~1453~ 10~1223~ 11~2257~ 12~1347~.'),
  (20649, 26, 10, 7, 'And one cherub stretched forth his hand from between the cherubims unto the fire that was between the cherubims, and took thereof, and put it into the hands of him that was clothed with linen: who took it, and went out.', '[1] 2~03742~ 4~07971~ 6~03027~ 10~03742~ 13~0784~ [15] 18~03742~, 20~05375~ [21] 23~05414~ [24] 27~02651~ [29 31] 32~03847~ 34~0906~: 36~03947~ [37] 40~03318~.'),
  (1810, 2, 10, 28, 'And Pharaoh said unto him, Get thee from me, take heed to thyself, see my face no more; for in that day thou seest my face thou shalt die.', '1~06547~ 2~0559~ 5~03212~ 10~08104~ 13~07200~ 15~06440~ 17~03254~; [20] 21~03117~ 23~07200~ 25~06440~ 28~04191~.'),
  (18687, 23, 51, 5, 'My righteousness is near; my salvation is gone forth, and mine arms shall judge the people; the isles shall wait upon me, and on mine arm shall they trust.', '1~06664~ [2] 3~07138~; 5~03468~ 8~03318~, 11~02220~ 13~08199~ 15~05971~; 17~0339~ 19~06960~ 25~02220~ 28~03176~.'),
  (17516, 21, 10, 14, 'A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him?', '1~05530~ 4~07235~ 6~01697~: 8~0120~ 10~03045~ 18~0310~ 22~05046~'),
  (4604, 4, 28, 21, 'A several tenth deal shalt thou offer for every lamb, throughout the seven lambs:', '3~06241~ 6~06213~ 8~0259~ 9~03532~, 12~07651~ 13~03532~:'),
  (446, 1, 18, 18, 'Seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him?', '2~085~ 7~01419~ 9~06099~ 10~01471~, 14~01471~ 17~0776~ 20~01288~'),
  (3984, 4, 9, 14, 'And if a stranger shall sojourn among you, and will keep the passover unto the LORD; according to the ordinance of the passover, and according to the manner thereof, so shall he do: ye shall have one ordinance, both for the stranger, and for him that was born in the land.', '3~01616~ 5~01481~ 10~06213~ 12~06453~ 15~03068~; 19~02708~ 22~06453~, 27~04941~ 32~06213~: 36~0259~ 37~02708~, 41~01616~, 47~0249~ 50~0776~.'),
  (532, 1, 21, 15, 'And the water was spent in the bottle, and she cast the child under one of the shrubs.', '2~04325~ 4~03615~ 5~04480~ 7~02573~, 10~07993~ 12~03206~ 14~0259~ 17~07880~.'),
  (16393, 19, 148, 13, 'Let them praise the name of the LORD: for his name alone is excellent; his glory is above the earth and heaven.', '2~01984~ 4~08034~ 7~03068~: 10~08034~ 13~07682~; 15~01935~ [16] 19~0776~ 21~08064~.'),
  (7316, 9, 4, 12, 'And there ran a man of Benjamin out of the army, and came to Shiloh the same day with his clothes rent, and with earth upon his head.', '&para; 2~07323~ 4~0376~ 6~01144~ 10~04634~, 12~0935~ 14~07887~ 17~03117~ 20~04055~ 21~07167~, 24~0127~ 27~07218~.'),
  (5333, 5, 15, 8, 'But thou shalt open thine hand wide unto him, and shalt surely lend him sufficient for his need, in that which he wanteth.', '3~06605~ 5~03027~ 6~06605~ 11~05670~ 12~05670~ 14~01767~ 17~04270~, [18 19] 22~02637~.'),
  (4125, 4, 14, 12, 'I will smite them with the pestilence, and disinherit them, and will make of thee a greater nation and mightier than they.', '2~05221~ 6~01698~, 8~03423~ 12~06213~ 16~01419~ 17~01471~ 19~06099~'),
  (791, 1, 28, 14, 'And thy seed shall be as the dust of the earth, and thou shalt spread abroad to the west, and to the east, and to the north, and to the south: and in thee and in thy seed shall all the families of the earth be blessed.', '2~02233~ 7~06083~ 10~0776~, 15~06555~ 18~03220~, 22~06924~, 26~06828~, 30~05045~: 37~02233~ 41~04940~ 44~0127~ 46~01288~.'),
  (17768, 23, 5, 20, 'Woe unto them that call evil good, and good evil; that put darkness for light, and light for darkness; that put bitter for sweet, and sweet for bitter!', '0~01945~ 4~0559~ 5~07451~ 6~02896~, 8~02896~ 9~07451~; 11~07760~ 12~02822~ 14~0216~, 16~0216~ 18~02822~; 20~07760~ 21~04751~ 23~04966~, 25~04966~ 27~04751~!'),
  (15745, 19, 107, 37, 'And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.', '1~02232~ 3~07704~, 5~05193~ 6~03754~, 9~06213~ 10~06529~ 12~08393~.'),
  (1953, 2, 16, 1, 'And they took their journey from Elim, and all the congregation of the children of Israel came unto the wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai, on the fifteenth day of the second month after their departing out of the land of Egypt.', '&para; 4~05265~ 6~0362~, 10~05712~ 13~01121~ 15~03478~ 16~0935~ 19~04057~ 21~05512~, [23] 25~0362~ 27~05514~, 30~06240~ 31~02568~* 32~03117~ 35~08145~ 36~02320~ 40~03318~ 43~0776~ 45~04714~.'),
  (12093, 15, 2, 57, 'The children of Shephatiah, the children of Hattil, the children of Pochereth of Zebaim, the children of Ami.', '1~01121~ 3~08203~, 5~01121~ 7~02411~, 9~01121~ 13~06380~, 15~01121~ 17~0532~.'),
  (10992, 13, 23, 1, 'So when David was old and full of days, he made Solomon his son king over Israel.', '&para; 2~01732~ 4~02204~ 6~07646~ 8~03117~, 11~08010~ 13~01121~ 14~04427~ 16~03478~.'),
  (30938, 66, 13, 14, 'And deceiveth them that dwell on the earth by the means of those miracles which he had power to do in the sight of the beast; saying to them that dwell on the earth, that they should make an image to the beast, which had the wound by a sword, and did live.', '0~2532~ 1~4105~ 4~2730~ 5~1909~ 7~1093~ 8~1223~ [9 11] 13~4592~ 14~3739~ 15~846~ 17~1325~ 19~4160~ 22~1799~ 25~2342~; 26~3004~ 30~2730~ 31~1909~ 33~1093~, 37~4160~ 39~1504~ 42~2342~, 43~3739~ 44~2192~ 46~4127~ 49~3162~, 50~2532~ 52~2198~.'),
  (12655, 16, 12, 22, 'The Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, and Johanan, and Jaddua, were recorded chief of the fathers: also the priests, to the reign of Darius the Persian.', '1~03881~ 4~03117~ 6~0475~, 7~03111~, 9~03110~, 11~03037~, [12] 13~03789~ 14~07218~ 17~01~: 20~03548~, 23~04438~ 25~01867~ 27~06542~.'),
  (17168, 20, 26, 18, 'As a mad man who casteth firebrands, arrows, and death,', '&para; 2~03856~ [3] 5~03384~ 6~02131~, 7~02671~, 9~04194~,'),
  (29286, 49, 3, 19, 'And to know the love of Christ, which passeth knowledge, that ye might be filled with all the fulness of God.', '0~5037~ 2~1097~ 4~26~ 6~5547~, 8~5235~ 9~1108~, 10~2443~ 14~4137~ 15~1519~ 16~3956~ 18~4138~ 20~2316~.'),
  (24125, 40, 26, 61, 'And said, This fellow said, I am able to destroy the temple of God, and to build it in three days.', '1~2036~, 2~3778~ [3] 4~5346~, 7~1410~ 9~2647~ 11~3485~ 13~2316~, 14~2532~ 16~3618~ 17~846~ 18~1223~ 19~5140~ 20~2250~.'),
  (27638, 44, 19, 37, 'For ye have brought hither these men, which are neither robbers of churches, nor yet blasphemers of your goddess.', '0~1063~ 4~71~ 5~5128~ 6~435~, 9~3777~ 12~2417~, 14~3777~ 15~987~ 17~5216~ 18~2299~.'),
  (17045, 20, 22, 21, 'That I might make thee know the certainty of the words of truth; that thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee?', '5~03045~ 7~07189~ 10~0561~ 12~0571~; 16~07725~ 18~0561~ 20~0571~ 24~07971~'),
  (14288, 19, 26, 6, 'I will wash mine hands in innocency: so will I compass thine altar, O LORD:', '&para; 2~07364~ 4~03709~ 6~05356~: 10~05437~ 12~04196~, 14~03068~:'),
  (8159, 10, 5, 20, 'And David came to Baalperazim, and David smote them there, and said, The LORD hath broken forth upon mine enemies before me, as the breach of waters. Therefore he called the name of that place Baalperazim.', '1~01732~ 2~0935~ 4~01188~, 6~01732~ 7~05221~ 11~0559~, 13~03068~ 16~06555~ 19~0341~ 20~06440~ 24~06556~ 26~04325~. 29~07121~ 31~08034~ 34~04725~ 35~01188~.'),
  (19524, 24, 23, 31, 'Behold, I am against the prophets, saith the LORD, that use their tongues, and say, He saith.', '[2] 5~05030~, 6~05002~ 8~03068~, 10~03947~ 12~03956~, 14~05001~, 16~05002~.'),
  (542, 1, 21, 25, 'And Abraham reproved Abimelech because of a well of water, which Abimelech''s servants had violently taken away.', '1~085~ 2~03198~ 3~040~ 4~0182~ 7~0875~ 9~04325~, 11~040~ 12~05650~ 16~01497~.'),
  (24333, 41, 3, 35, 'For whosoever shall do the will of God, the same is my brother, and my sister, and mother.', '0~1063~ 1~302~ 2~3739~ 3~4160~ 5~2307~ 7~2316~, 9~3778~ 10~2076~ 11~3450~ 12~80~, 13~2532~ 14~3450~ 15~79~, 16~2532~ 17~3384~.'),
  (16797, 20, 14, 16, 'A wise man feareth, and departeth from evil: but the fool rageth, and is confident.', '&para; 1~02450~ [2] 3~03373~, 5~05493~ 7~07451~: 10~03684~ 11~05674~, 14~0982~.'),
  (9608, 12, 3, 24, 'And when they came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites rose up and smote the Moabites, so that they fled before them: but they went forward smiting the Moabites, even in their country.', '3~0935~ 6~04264~ 8~03478~, 10~03478~ 12~06965~ 14~05221~ 16~04124~, 20~05127~ 21~06440~ 26~05221~ 27~05221~ 29~04124~, [32]'),
  (14683, 19, 50, 6, 'And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God is judge himself. Selah.', '2~08064~ 4~05046~ 6~06664~: 8~0430~ [9] 10~08199~ 12~05542~.'),
  (17869, 23, 10, 10, 'As my hand hath found the kingdoms of the idols, and whose graven images did excel them of Jerusalem and of Samaria:', '2~03027~ 4~04672~ 6~04467~ 9~0457~, 13~06456~ 18~03389~ 21~08111~;'),
  (28487, 46, 6, 4, 'If then ye have judgments of things pertaining to this life, set them to judge who are least esteemed in the church.', '0~1437~ 1~3767~ 2~3303~ 3~2192~ 4~2922~ 10~982~, 11~2523~ 12~5128~ 18~1848~ 19~1722~ 21~1577~.'),
  (10401, 13, 4, 8, 'And Coz begat Anub, and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.', '1~06976~ 2~03205~ 3~06036~, 5~06637~, 8~04940~ 10~0316~ 12~01121~ 14~02037~.'),
  (15451, 19, 94, 11, 'The LORD knoweth the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.', '1~03068~ 2~03045~ 4~04284~ 6~0120~, [9] 10~01892~.'),
  (18247, 23, 30, 21, 'And thine ears shall hear a word behind thee, saying, This is the way, walk ye in it, when ye turn to the right hand, and when ye turn to the left.', '2~0241~ 4~08085~ 6~01697~ 7~0310~ 9~0559~, [11] 13~01870~, 17~03212~, 24~0541~, 31~08041~.'),
  (14069, 19, 11, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. In the LORD put I my trust: how say ye to my soul, Flee as a bird to your mountain?', '&para; [0 3~05329~, [4 5] 7] 7~01732~ 10~03068~ 14~02620~: 16~0559~ 20~05315~, 21~05110~ [22] 24~06833~ 27~02022~?'),
  (13808, 18, 38, 6, 'Whereupon are the foundations thereof fastened? or who laid the corner stone thereof;', '3~0134~ 5~02883~? 8~03384~ 10~06438~ 11~068~'),
  (30613, 62, 3, 18, 'My little children, let us not love in word, neither in tongue; but in deed and in truth.', '0~3450~ 2~5040~, 4~25~ 5~3361~ 6~25~ 8~3056~, 9~3366~ 11~1100~; 12~235~ 14~2041~ 15~2532~ 17~225~.'),
  (22777, 35, 2, 20, 'But the LORD is in his holy temple: let all the earth keep silence before him.', '2~03068~ [3] 6~06944~ 7~01964~: 11~0776~ 13~02013~ 14~06440~'),
  (4228, 4, 16, 29, 'If these men die the common death of all men, or if they be visited after the visitation of all men; then the LORD hath not sent me.', '3~04191~ 6~04194~ 9~0120~, 14~06485~ 17~06486~ 20~0120~; [21] 23~03068~ 26~07971~'),
  (281, 1, 11, 12, 'And Arphaxad lived five and thirty years, and begat Salah:', '1~0775~ 2~02425~ 3~02568~ 5~07970~ 6~08141~, 8~03205~ 9~07974~:'),
  (10346, 13, 2, 32, 'And the sons of Jada the brother of Shammai; Jether, and Jonathan: and Jether died without children.', '2~01121~ 4~03047~ 6~0251~ 8~08060~; 9~03500~, 11~03129~: 13~03500~ 14~04191~ 16~01121~.'),
  (16272, 19, 139, 24, 'And see if there be any wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.', '1~07200~ [3 5] 6~06090~ 7~01870~ 11~05148~ 15~01870~ 16~05769~.'),
  (25839, 42, 20, 46, 'Beware of the scribes, which desire to walk in long robes, and love greetings in the markets, and the highest seats in the synagogues, and the chief rooms at feasts;', '0~4337~ 1~575~ 3~1122~, 4~3588~ 5~2309~ 7~4043~ 8~1722~ 10~4749~, 11~2532~ 12~5368~ 13~783~ 14~1722~ 16~58~, 17~2532~ 20~4410~ 21~1722~ 23~4864~, 24~2532~ 27~4411~ 28~1722~ 29~1173~;'),
  (5148, 5, 8, 5, 'Thou shalt also consider in thine heart, that, as a man chasteneth his son, so the LORD thy God chasteneth thee.', '3~03045~ 4~05973~ 6~03824~, 10~0376~ 11~03256~ 13~01121~, [14] 16~03068~ 18~0430~ 19~03256~'),
  (27459, 44, 15, 1, 'And certain men which came down from Judaea taught the brethren, and said, Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses, ye cannot be saved.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5100~ 5~2718~ 6~575~ 7~2449~ 8~1321~ 10~80~, [11 12] 12~3754~, 13~3362~ 16~4059~ 19~1485~ 21~3475~, 23~1410~ 24~3756~* 26~4982~.'),
  (2126, 2, 22, 8, 'If the thief be not found, then the master of the house shall be brought unto the judges, to see whether he have put his hand unto his neighbour''s goods.', '2~01590~ 4~03808~ 5~04672~, 8~01167~ 11~01004~ 14~07126~ 17~0430~, [18 19] 23~07971~ 25~03027~ 28~07453~ 29~04399~.'),
  (22279, 28, 13, 4, 'Yet I am the LORD thy God from the land of Egypt, and thou shalt know no god but me: for there is no saviour beside me.', '[2] 4~03068~ 6~0430~ 9~0776~ 11~04714~, 15~03045~ 17~0430~ 19~02108~: [21 22] 24~03467~ 26~01115~.'),
  (29822, 54, 6, 18, 'That they do good, that they be rich in good works, ready to distribute, willing to communicate;', '3~14~, 7~4147~ 8~1722~ 9~2570~ 10~2041~, 13~1511~ 14~2130~,* 17~2843~;'),
  (4915, 5, 1, 17, 'Ye shall not respect persons in judgment; but ye shall hear the small as well as the great; ye shall not be afraid of the face of man; for the judgment is God''s: and the cause that is too hard for you, bring it unto me, and I will hear it.', '3~05234~ 4~06440~ 6~04941~; [7] 10~08085~ 12~06996~ 17~01419~; 22~01481~ 25~06440~ 27~0376~; 30~04941~ [31] 32~0430~: 35~01697~ 39~07185~ 42~07126~ [43] 49~08085~'),
  (14840, 19, 62, 4, 'They only consult to cast him down from his excellency: they delight in lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.', '2~03289~ [5] 6~05080~ 9~07613~: 11~07521~ 13~03577~: 15~01288~ 18~06310~, 21~07043~ 22~07130~. 23~05542~.');
