VALUES
  (26567, 43, 11, 29, 'As soon as she heard that, she arose quickly, and came unto him.', '2~5613~ 3~1565~ 4~191~ [5] 7~1453~ 8~5035~, 9~2532~ 10~2064~ 11~4314~ 12~846~.'),
  (7996, 9, 30, 11, 'And they found an Egyptian in the field, and brought him to David, and gave him bread, and he did eat; and they made him drink water;', '2~04672~ 4~04713~ 5~0376~ 7~07704~, 9~03947~ 12~01732~, 14~05414~ 16~03899~, 20~0398~; 25~08248~ 26~04325~;'),
  (2864, 3, 6, 10, 'And the priest shall put on his linen garment, and his linen breeches shall he put upon his flesh, and take up the ashes which the fire hath consumed with the burnt offering on the altar, and he shall put them beside the altar.', '2~03548~ 4~03847~ 7~0906~ 8~04055~, 11~0906~ 12~04370~ 15~03847~ 18~01320~, 21~07311~ 23~01880~ 26~0784~ 28~0398~ 32~05930~ 35~04196~, 39~07760~ 41~0681~ 43~04196~.'),
  (7552, 9, 14, 37, 'And Saul asked counsel of God, Shall I go down after the Philistines? wilt thou deliver them into the hand of Israel? But he answered him not that day.', '1~07586~ 2~07592~ 5~0430~, 9~03381~ 10~0310~ 12~06430~? 15~05414~ 19~03027~ 21~03478~? 24~06030~ 28~03117~.'),
  (20676, 26, 11, 12, 'And ye shall know that I am the LORD: for ye have not walked in my statutes, neither executed my judgments, but have done after the manners of the heathen that are round about you.', '3~03045~ [6] 8~03068~: 13~01980~ 16~02706~, 18~06213~ 20~04941~, 23~06213~ 26~04941~ 29~01471~ [31] 33~05439~'),
  (17450, 21, 7, 12, 'For wisdom is a defence, and money is a defence: but the excellency of knowledge is, that wisdom giveth life to them that have it.', '1~02451~ [2] 4~06738~, [5] 6~03701~ [7] 9~06738~: 12~03504~ 14~01847~ [15 16] 17~02451~ 19~02421~ 23~01167~'),
  (29966, 57, 1, 12, 'Whom I have sent again: thou therefore receive him, that is, mine own bowels:', '0~3739~ 4~375~: 5~4771~ 6~1161~ 7~4355~ 8~846~, 10~5123~, 12~1699~ 13~4698~:'),
  (26817, 43, 18, 17, 'Then saith the damsel that kept the door unto Peter, Art not thou also one of this man''s disciples? He saith, I am not.', '0~3767~ 1~3004~ 3~3814~ 7~2377~ 9~4074~, 10~1488~ 11~3361~ 12~4771~ 13~2532~ [14] 15~1537~ 16~5127~ 17~444~ 18~3101~? 19~1565~ 20~3004~, 22~1510~ 23~3756~.'),
  (8745, 11, 1, 20, 'And thou, my lord, O king, the eyes of all Israel are upon thee, that thou shouldest tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.', '3~0113~, 5~04428~, 7~05869~ 10~03478~ [11] 17~05046~ 21~03427~ 24~03678~ 27~0113~ 29~04428~ 30~0310~'),
  (3701, 4, 3, 4, 'And Nadab and Abihu died before the LORD, when they offered strange fire before the LORD, in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children: and Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest''s office in the sight of Aaron their father.', '1~05070~ 3~030~ 4~04191~ 5~06440~ 7~03068~, 10~07126~ 11~02114~ 12~0784~ 13~06440~ 15~03068~, 18~04057~ 20~05514~, 25~01121~: 27~0499~ 29~0385~ 34~03547~ 37~06440~ 39~0175~ 41~01~.'),
  (13178, 18, 13, 16, 'He also shall be my salvation: for an hypocrite shall not come before him.', '[2 3] 5~03444~: 8~02611~ 11~0935~ 12~06440~'),
  (4981, 5, 2, 37, 'Only unto the land of the children of Ammon thou camest not, nor unto any place of the river Jabbok, nor unto the cities in the mountains, nor unto whatsoever the LORD our God forbad us.', '3~0776~ 6~01121~ 8~05983~ 10~07126~ [12] 15~03027~ 18~05158~ 19~02999~, 23~05892~ 26~02022~, 31~03068~ 33~0430~ 34~06680~'),
  (9712, 12, 6, 30, 'And it came to pass, when the king heard the words of the woman, that he rent his clothes; and he passed by upon the wall, and the people looked, and, behold, he had sackcloth within upon his flesh.', '7~04428~ 8~08085~ 10~01697~ 13~0802~, 16~07167~ 18~0899~; 22~05674~ 25~02346~, 28~05971~ 29~07200~, [32 33] 34~08242~ 35~01004~ 38~01320~.'),
  (23920, 40, 22, 38, 'This is the first and great commandment.', '0~3778~ 1~2076~ 3~4413~ 4~2532~ 5~3173~ 6~1785~.'),
  (21161, 26, 27, 31, 'And they shall make themselves utterly bald for thee, and gird them with sackcloth, and they shall weep for thee with bitterness of heart and bitter wailing.', '5~07144~ 6~07139~ 10~02296~ 13~08242~, 17~01058~ 21~04751~ 23~05315~ [24] 25~04751~ 26~04553~.'),
  (3009, 3, 11, 7, 'And the swine, though he divide the hoof, and be clovenfooted, yet he cheweth not the cud; he is unclean to you.', '2~02386~, 5~06536~ 7~06541~, 10~08156~ 11~08157~,* 14~01641~ 17~01625~; [19] 20~02931~'),
  (28183, 45, 9, 12, 'It was said unto her, The elder shall serve the younger.', '0~3754~ 2~4483~ 4~846~, 6~3187~ 8~1398~ 10~1640~.'),
  (23546, 40, 12, 47, 'Then one said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to speak with thee.', '0~1161~ 1~5100~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~2400~, 6~4675~ 7~3384~ 8~2532~ 9~4675~ 10~80~ 11~2476~ 12~1854~, 13~2212~ 15~2980~ 17~4671~.'),
  (17859, 23, 9, 21, 'Manasseh, Ephraim; and Ephraim, Manasseh: and they together shall be against Judah. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.', '0~04519~, 1~0669~; 3~0669~, 4~04519~: [5] 7~03162~ [8 9] 11~03063~. 16~0639~ 20~07725~, 23~03027~ [24] 27~05186~.'),
  (14591, 19, 44, 11, 'Thou hast given us like sheep appointed for meat; and hast scattered us among the heathen.', '2~05414~ 5~06629~ [6] 8~03978~; 11~02219~ 15~01471~.'),
  (30079, 58, 6, 19, 'Which hope we have as an anchor of the soul, both sure and stedfast, and which entereth into that within the veil;', '0~3739~ [1] 3~2192~ 4~5613~ 6~45~ 9~5590~, 10~5037~ 11~804~ 12~2532~ 13~949~, 14~2532~ 16~1525~ 17~1519~ 19~2082~ 21~2665~;'),
  (27470, 44, 15, 12, 'Then all the multitude kept silence, and gave audience to Barnabas and Paul, declaring what miracles and wonders God had wrought among the Gentiles by them.', '0~1161~ 1~3956~ 3~4128~ 5~4601~, 6~2532~ 8~191~ 10~921~ 11~2532~ 12~3972~, 13~1834~ 14~3745~ 15~4592~ 16~2532~ 17~5059~ 18~2316~ 20~4160~ 21~1722~ 23~1484~ 24~1223~ 25~846~.'),
  (18178, 23, 28, 5, 'In that day shall the LORD of hosts be for a crown of glory, and for a diadem of beauty, unto the residue of his people,', '2~03117~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~ 11~05850~ 13~06643~, 17~06843~ 19~08597~, 22~07605~ 25~05971~,'),
  (26440, 43, 8, 44, 'Ye are of your father the devil, and the lusts of your father ye will do. He was a murderer from the beginning, and abode not in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaketh a lie, he speaketh of his own: for he is a liar, and the father of it.', '0~5210~ 1~2075~ 2~1537~ [3] 4~3962~ 6~1228~, 7~2532~ 9~1939~ 11~5216~ 12~3962~ 14~2309~ 15~4160~. 16~1565~ 17~2258~ 19~443~ 20~575~ 22~746~, 23~2532~ 24~2476~ 25~3756~ 26~1722~ 28~225~, 29~3754~ 31~2076~ 32~3756~ 33~225~ 34~1722~ 35~846~. 36~3752~ 38~2980~ 40~5579~, 42~2980~ 43~1537~ 45~2398~: 46~3754~ 48~2076~ 50~5583~, 51~2532~ 53~3962~ 55~846~.'),
  (15936, 19, 119, 29, 'Remove from me the way of lying: and grant me thy law graciously.', '0~05493~ 4~01870~ 6~08267~: 11~08451~ 12~02603~.'),
  (24606, 41, 10, 7, 'For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and cleave to his wife;', '2~5127~ 3~1752~* 4~2641~ 6~444~ 7~2641~ 8~846~ 9~3962~ 10~2532~ 11~3384~, 12~2532~ 13~4347~ 14~4314~ 15~846~ 16~1135~;'),
  (14313, 19, 28, 5, 'Because they regard not the works of the LORD, nor the operation of his hands, he shall destroy them, and not build them up.', '2~0995~ 5~06468~ 8~03068~, 11~04639~ 14~03027~, 17~02040~ 23~01129~.'),
  (25136, 42, 5, 17, 'And it came to pass on a certain day, as he was teaching, that there were Pharisees and doctors of the law sitting by, which were come out of every town of Galilee, and Judaea, and Jerusalem: and the power of the Lord was present to heal them.', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 7~3391~ 8~2250~, 9~2532~ 10~846~ 11~2258~ 12~1321~, 13~2532~ 15~2258~ 16~5330~ 17~2532~ 21~3547~ 23~2521~, 24~3739~ 25~2258~ 26~2064~ 28~1537~ 29~3956~ 30~2968~ 32~1056~, 33~2532~ 34~2449~, 35~2532~ 36~2419~: 37~2532~ 39~1411~ 42~2962~ 43~2258~ [44] 45~1519~ 46~2390~ 47~846~.'),
  (30850, 66, 8, 7, 'The first angel sounded, and there followed hail and fire mingled with blood, and they were cast upon the earth: and the third part of trees was burnt up, and all green grass was burnt up.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~4413~ 3~32~ 4~4537~, 5~2532~ 7~1096~ 8~5464~ 9~2532~ 10~4442~ 11~3396~ 13~129~, 14~2532~ 17~906~ 18~1519~ 20~1093~: 21~2532~ 24~5154~ 26~1186~ 29~2618~, 30~2532~ 31~3956~ 32~5515~ 33~5528~ 36~2618~.'),
  (11663, 14, 22, 10, 'But when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the seed royal of the house of Judah.', '&para; 2~06271~ 4~0517~ 6~0274~ 7~07200~ 10~01121~ 12~04191~, 14~06965~ 16~01696~ 19~02233~ 20~04467~ 23~01004~ 25~03063~.'),
  (6638, 7, 5, 8, 'They chose new gods; then was war in the gates: was there a shield or spear seen among forty thousand in Israel?', '1~0977~ 2~02319~ 3~0430~; [5] 6~03901~ 9~08179~: 13~04043~ 15~07420~ 16~07200~ 18~0705~ 19~0505~ 21~03478~?'),
  (8038, 10, 1, 9, 'He said unto me again, Stand, I pray thee, upon me, and slay me: for anguish is come upon me, because my life is yet whole in me.', '1~0559~ 5~05975~, 12~04191~ 15~07661~ 17~0270~ 22~05315~ [23]'),
  (30310, 59, 2, 1, 'My brethren, have not the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with respect of persons.', '&para; 0~3450~ 1~80~, 2~2192~ 3~3361~ 5~4102~ 7~2257~ 8~2962~ 9~2424~ 10~5547~, [11 12] 14~1391~, 15~1722~ 18~4382~.'),
  (26720, 43, 15, 6, 'If a man abide not in me, he is cast forth as a branch, and is withered; and men gather them, and cast them into the fire, and they are burned.', '0~3362~ 2~5100~ 3~3306~ 4~3362~ 5~1722~ 6~1698~, 9~906~ 10~1854~ 11~5613~ 13~2814~, 14~2532~ 16~3583~; 17~2532~ 19~4863~ 20~846~, 21~2532~ 22~906~ [23] 24~1519~ 26~4442~, 27~2532~ 30~2545~.'),
  (22238, 28, 10, 4, 'They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.', '2~01696~ 3~01697~, 4~0422~ 5~07723~ 7~03772~ 9~01285~: 11~04941~ 13~06524~ 15~07219~ 18~08525~ 21~07704~.'),
  (30853, 66, 8, 10, 'And the third angel sounded, and there fell a great star from heaven, burning as it were a lamp, and it fell upon the third part of the rivers, and upon the fountains of waters;', '0~2532~ 2~5154~ 3~32~ 4~4537~, 5~2532~ 7~4098~ 9~3173~ 10~792~ 11~1537~ 12~3772~, 13~2545~ 16~5613~ 18~2985~, 19~2532~ 21~4098~ 22~1909~ 25~5154~ 28~4215~, 29~2532~ 30~1909~ 32~4077~ 34~5204~;'),
  (15264, 19, 83, 14, 'As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire;', '2~0784~ 3~01197~ 5~03293~, 9~03852~ 10~03857~ 12~02022~ 14~03857~;'),
  (7460, 9, 11, 8, 'And when he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.', '3~06485~ 6~0966~, 8~01121~ 10~03478~ 12~07969~ 13~03967~ 14~0505~, 17~0376~ 19~03063~ 20~07970~ 21~0505~.'),
  (29205, 48, 6, 1, 'Brethren, if a man be overtaken in a fault, ye which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit of meekness; considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted.', '&para; 0~80~, 1~2532~ 2~1437~ 3~444~ 5~4301~ 6~1722~ 7~5100~ 8~3900~, 9~5210~ 10~3588~ 12~4152~, 13~2675~ 16~5108~ 17~1722~ 19~4151~ 21~4236~; 22~4648~ 23~4572~, 24~3361~ 25~4771~ 26~2532~ 28~3985~.'),
  (22271, 28, 12, 10, 'I have also spoken by the prophets, and I have multiplied visions, and used similitudes, by the ministry of the prophets.', '3~01696~ 6~05030~, 10~07235~ 11~02377~, 14~01819~, 17~03027~ 20~05030~.'),
  (26668, 43, 13, 23, 'Now there was leaning on Jesus'' bosom one of his disciples, whom Jesus loved.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~345~ 4~1722~ 5~2424~ 6~2859~ 7~1520~ 9~846~ 10~3101~, 11~3739~ 12~2424~ 13~25~.'),
  (30610, 62, 3, 15, 'Whosoever hateth his brother is a murderer: and ye know that no murderer hath eternal life abiding in him.', '0~3956~ 1~3404~ 2~846~ 3~80~ 4~2076~ 6~443~: 7~2532~ 9~1492~ 10~3754~ 11~3956~ 12~3756~* 13~443~ 14~2192~ 15~166~ 16~2222~ 17~3306~ 18~1722~ 19~846~.'),
  (21265, 26, 32, 8, 'All the bright lights of heaven will I make dark over thee, and set darkness upon thy land, saith the Lord GOD.', '2~03974~ 3~0216~ 5~08064~ 9~06937~ 13~05414~ 14~02822~ 17~0776~, 18~05002~ 20~0136~ 21~03069~.'),
  (26151, 43, 3, 16, 'For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 2~3779~ 3~25~ 5~2889~, 6~5620~ 8~1325~ 9~846~ 11~3439~ 12~5207~, 13~2443~ 14~3956~ 15~4100~ 16~1519~ 17~846~ 18~622~ 19~3361~ 20~622~, 21~235~ 22~2192~ 23~166~ 24~2222~.'),
  (30090, 58, 7, 10, 'For he was yet in the loins of his father, when Melchisedec met him.', '0~1063~ 2~2258~ 3~2089~ 4~1722~ 6~3751~ 9~3962~, 10~3753~ 11~3198~ 12~4876~ 13~846~.'),
  (26069, 43, 1, 11, 'He came unto his own, and his own received him not.', '1~2064~ 2~1519~ 4~2398~, 5~2532~ 7~2398~ 8~3880~ 9~846~ 10~3756~.'),
  (26234, 43, 5, 9, 'And immediately the man was made whole, and took up his bed, and walked: and on the same day was the sabbath.', '0~2532~ 1~2112~ 3~444~ 5~1096~ 6~5199~, 7~2532~ 9~142~ 10~846~ 11~2895~, 12~2532~ 13~4043~: 14~1161~ 15~1722~ 17~1565~ 18~2250~ 19~2258~ 21~4521~.'),
  (12131, 15, 4, 12, 'Be it known unto the king, that the Jews which came up from thee to us are come unto Jerusalem, building the rebellious and the bad city, and have set up the walls thereof, and joined the foundations.', '1~01934~ 2~03046~ 5~04430~, 8~03062~ 9~01768~ 11~05559~ 12~04481~ 13~03890~ 15~05922~ 17~0858~ 19~03390~, 20~01124~ 22~04779~ 25~0873~ 26~07149~, 30~03635~ 32~07792~ [33] 35~02338~ 37~0787~.'),
  (6194, 6, 13, 33, 'But unto the tribe of Levi Moses gave not any inheritance: the LORD God of Israel was their inheritance, as he said unto them.', '3~07626~ 5~03878~ 6~04872~ 7~05414~ [9] 10~05159~: 12~03068~ 13~0430~ 15~03478~ [16] 18~05159~, 21~01696~'),
  (19652, 24, 29, 8, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; Let not your prophets and your diviners, that be in the midst of you, deceive you, neither hearken to your dreams which ye cause to be dreamed.', '&para; 2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~, 8~0430~ 10~03478~; 14~05030~ 17~07080~, [19] 22~07130~ 25~05377~ 28~08085~ 31~02472~ 37~02492~.'),
  (16217, 19, 136, 12, 'With a strong hand, and with a stretched out arm: for his mercy endureth for ever.', '2~02389~ 3~03027~, 8~05186~ 9~02220~: 12~02617~ [13] 15~05769~.'),
  (13780, 18, 37, 2, 'Hear attentively the noise of his voice, and the sound that goeth out of his mouth.', '0~08085~ 1~08085~ 3~07267~ 6~06963~, 9~01899~ [10] 12~03318~ 15~06310~.'),
  (20728, 26, 13, 11, 'Say unto them which daub it with untempered mortar, that it shall fall: there shall be an overflowing shower; and ye, O great hailstones, shall fall; and a stormy wind shall rend it.', '0~0559~ 4~02902~ [5] 7~08602~ [8] 12~05307~: 17~07857~ 18~01653~; 20~0859~, 23~068~ 24~0417~,* 26~05307~; 29~05591~ 30~07307~ 32~01234~ [33]'),
  (28054, 45, 4, 16, 'Therefore it is of faith, that it might be by grace; to the end the promise might be sure to all the seed; not to that only which is of the law, but to that also which is of the faith of Abraham; who is the father of us all,', '0~5124~ [1 1~1223~ 2] 3~1537~ 4~4102~, 5~2443~ [6 8] 9~2596~ 10~5485~; 13~1519~ 15~1860~ 17~1511~ 18~949~ 20~3956~ 22~4690~; 23~3756~ 26~3440~ 29~1537~ 31~3551~, 32~235~ 35~2532~ 38~1537~ 40~4102~ 42~11~; 43~3739~ 44~2076~ 46~3962~ 48~2257~ 49~3956~,'),
  (6756, 7, 8, 30, 'And Gideon had threescore and ten sons of his body begotten: for he had many wives.', '1~01439~ 5~07657~ 6~01121~ 9~03409~ 10~03318~: 14~07227~ 15~0802~.'),
  (18403, 23, 38, 4, 'Then came the word of the LORD to Isaiah, saying,', '3~01697~ 6~03068~ 8~03470~, 9~0559~,'),
  (8320, 10, 12, 27, 'And Joab sent messengers to David, and said, I have fought against Rabbah, and have taken the city of waters.', '1~03097~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 5~01732~, 7~0559~, 10~03898~ 12~07237~, 15~03920~ 17~05892~ 19~04325~.'),
  (14355, 19, 31, 15, 'My times are in thy hand: deliver me from the hand of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me.', '1~06256~ [2] 5~03027~: 6~05337~ 10~03027~ 13~0341~, 18~07291~'),
  (28263, 45, 12, 2, 'And be not conformed to this world: but be ye transformed by the renewing of your mind, that ye may prove what is that good, and acceptable, and perfect, will of God.', '0~2532~ 1~4964~ 2~3361~ 3~4964~ 5~5129~ 6~165~: 7~235~ 10~3339~ 13~342~ 15~5216~ 16~3563~, 17~1519~ 18~5209~ 20~1381~ 21~5101~ [22] 24~18~, 25~2532~ 26~2101~, 27~2532~ 28~5046~, 29~2307~ 31~2316~.'),
  (20412, 25, 3, 49, 'Mine eye trickleth down, and ceaseth not, without any intermission,', '1~05869~ 3~05064~, 5~01820~ 9~02014~,'),
  (12225, 15, 8, 15, 'And I gathered them together to the river that runneth to Ahava; and there abode we in tents three days: and I viewed the people, and the priests, and found there none of the sons of Levi.', '4~06908~ 7~05104~ 9~0935~ 11~0163~; 17~02583~ 18~07969~ 19~03117~: 22~0995~ 24~05971~, 27~03548~, 29~04672~ 34~01121~ 36~03878~.'),
  (16716, 20, 11, 19, 'As righteousness tendeth to life: so he that pursueth evil pursueth it to his own death.', '&para; 1~06666~ [2] 4~02416~: 8~07291~ 9~07451~ [10 11] 15~04194~.'),
  (28831, 47, 1, 15, 'And in this confidence I was minded to come unto you before, that ye might have a second benefit;', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5026~ 3~4006~ 6~1014~ 8~2064~ 9~4314~ 10~5209~ 11~4386~, 12~2443~ 15~2192~ 17~1208~ 18~5485~;'),
  (7471, 9, 12, 4, 'And they said, Thou hast not defrauded us, nor oppressed us, neither hast thou taken ought of any man''s hand.', '2~0559~, 6~06231~ 9~07533~ 14~03947~ 15~03972~ 18~0376~ 19~03027~.'),
  (20674, 26, 11, 10, 'Ye shall fall by the sword; I will judge you in the border of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the LORD.', '2~05307~ 5~02719~; 8~08199~ 12~01366~ 14~03478~; 18~03045~ [21] 23~03068~.'),
  (18652, 23, 49, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD, the Redeemer of Israel, and his Holy One, to him whom man despiseth, to him whom the nation abhorreth, to a servant of rulers, Kings shall see and arise, princes also shall worship, because of the LORD that is faithful, and the Holy One of Israel, and he shall choose thee.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~01350~ 7~03478~, [8] 11~06918~, 15~05315~ 16~0960~, 21~01471~ 22~08581~, 25~05650~ 27~04910~, 28~04428~ 30~07200~ 32~06965~, 33~08269~ 36~07812~, 40~03068~ 43~0539~, [44] 47~06918~ 49~03478~, 53~0977~'),
  (4176, 4, 15, 18, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye come into the land whither I bring you,', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 7~0559~ 12~0935~ 15~0776~ 18~0935~'),
  (12792, 17, 5, 4, 'And Esther answered, If it seem good unto the king, let the king and Haman come this day unto the banquet that I have prepared for him.', '1~0635~ 2~0559~, [4 5] 6~02895~ 9~04428~, 12~04428~ 14~02001~ 15~0935~ 17~03117~ 20~04960~ 24~06213~'),
  (1609, 2, 4, 3, 'And he said, Cast it on the ground. And he cast it on the ground, and it became a serpent; and Moses fled from before it.', '2~0559~, 3~07993~ 7~0776~. 10~07993~ 14~0776~, 19~05175~; 21~04872~ 22~05127~ 24~06440~'),
  (14641, 19, 47, 7, 'For God is the King of all the earth: sing ye praises with understanding.', '1~0430~ [2] 4~04428~ 8~0776~: 11~02167~ 13~07919~.'),
  (1246, 1, 41, 46, 'And Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh, and went throughout all the land of Egypt.', '&para; 1~03130~ [2] 3~07970~ 4~08141~ 5~01121~ 8~05975~ 9~06440~ 10~06547~ 11~04428~ 13~04714~. 15~03130~ 17~03318~ 20~06440~ 22~06547~, 25~05674~ 28~0776~ 30~04714~.'),
  (11919, 14, 33, 2, 'But did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD, like unto the abominations of the heathen, whom the LORD had cast out before the children of Israel.', '1~06213~ [2 4] 5~07451~ 8~05869~ 11~03068~, 15~08441~ 18~01471~, 21~03068~ 24~03423~ 25~06440~ 27~01121~ 29~03478~.'),
  (10844, 13, 16, 16, 'Even of the covenant which he made with Abraham, and of his oath unto Isaac;', '[0 3] 6~03772~ 8~085~, 12~07621~ 14~03327~;'),
  (20949, 26, 20, 45, 'Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (18260, 23, 31, 1, 'Woe to them that go down to Egypt for help; and stay on horses, and trust in chariots, because they are many; and in horsemen, because they are very strong; but they look not unto the Holy One of Israel, neither seek the LORD!', '&para; 0~01945~ 5~03381~ 7~04714~ 9~05833~; 11~08172~ 13~05483~, 15~0982~ 17~07393~, [19 20] 21~07227~; 24~06571~, 28~03966~ 29~06105~; 32~08159~ 37~06918~ 39~03478~, 41~01875~ 43~03068~!'),
  (25649, 42, 16, 16, 'The law and the prophets were until John: since that time the kingdom of God is preached, and every man presseth into it.', '1~3551~ 2~2532~ 4~4396~ [5] 6~2193~ 7~2491~: 8~575~ 10~5119~ 12~932~ 14~2316~ 16~2097~, 17~2532~ 19~3956~ 20~971~ 21~1519~ 22~846~.'),
  (21128, 26, 26, 19, 'For thus saith the Lord GOD; When I shall make thee a desolate city, like the cities that are not inhabited; when I shall bring up the deep upon thee, and great waters shall cover thee;', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 9~05414~ 12~02717~ 13~05892~, 16~05892~ 20~03427~; 25~05927~ 27~08415~ 31~07227~ 32~04325~ 34~03680~'),
  (150, 1, 6, 12, 'And God looked upon the earth, and, behold, it was corrupt; for all flesh had corrupted his way upon the earth.', '1~0430~ 2~07200~ 5~0776~, 10~07843~; 13~01320~ 15~07843~ 17~01870~ 20~0776~.'),
  (16910, 20, 17, 28, 'Even a fool, when he holdeth his peace, is counted wise: and he that shutteth his lips is esteemed a man of understanding.', '2~0191~, 7~02790~, 9~02803~ 10~02450~: [11] 14~0331~ 16~08193~ [17 18] 22~0995~.'),
  (2747, 2, 40, 35, 'And Moses was not able to enter into the tent of the congregation, because the cloud abode thereon, and the glory of the LORD filled the tabernacle.', '1~04872~ 4~03201~ 6~0935~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~, 15~06051~ 16~07931~ 20~03519~ 23~03068~ 24~04390~ 26~04908~.'),
  (3673, 4, 2, 10, 'On the south side shall be the standard of the camp of Reuben according to their armies: and the captain of the children of Reuben shall be Elizur the son of Shedeur.', '3~08486~ [4 5] 7~01714~ 10~04264~ 12~07205~ 16~06635~: 19~05387~ 22~01121~ 24~07205~ [25 26] 27~0468~ 29~01121~ 31~07707~.'),
  (14699, 19, 50, 22, 'Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I tear you in pieces, and there be none to deliver.', '1~0995~ 5~07911~ 6~0433~, [10] 12~02963~, [14 15] 18~05337~.'),
  (7342, 9, 6, 4, 'Then said they, What shall be the trespass offering which we shall return to him? They answered, Five golden emerods, and five golden mice, according to the number of the lords of the Philistines: for one plague was on you all, and on your lords.', '1~0559~ [4 5] 8~0817~ 12~07725~ 16~0559~, 17~02568~ 18~02091~ 19~02914~ 20~06076~,* 22~02568~ 23~02091~ 24~05909~, [25 26] 28~04557~ 31~05633~ 34~06430~: 36~0259~ 37~04046~ [38] 45~05633~.'),
  (2544, 2, 35, 8, 'And oil for the light, and spices for anointing oil, and for the sweet incense,', '1~08081~ 4~03974~, 6~01314~ 8~04888~ 9~08081~, 13~05561~ 14~07004~,'),
  (29281, 49, 3, 14, 'For this cause I bow my knees unto the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,', '&para; 1~5127~ 2~5484~ 4~2578~ 5~3450~ 6~1119~ 7~4314~ 9~3962~ 11~2257~ 12~2962~ 13~2424~ 14~5547~,'),
  (28564, 46, 9, 8, 'Say I these things as a man? or saith not the law the same also?', '1~2980~ 3~5023~ 4~2596~ 5~3361~ 6~444~? 7~2228~ 8~3004~ 9~3780~ 11~3551~ 13~5023~ 14~2532~?'),
  (13445, 18, 23, 17, 'Because I was not cut off before the darkness, neither hath he covered the darkness from my face.', '5~06789~ 6~06440~ 8~02822~, [9] 12~03680~ 14~0652~ 17~06440~.'),
  (30276, 58, 13, 19, 'But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.', '0~1161~ 2~3870~ [3] 5~4056~ 7~4160~ 8~5124~, 9~2443~ 13~600~ 15~5213~ 17~5032~.'),
  (30473, 60, 4, 11, 'If any man speak, let him speak as the oracles of God; if any man minister, let him do it as of the ability which God giveth: that God in all things may be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom be praise and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.', '2~1536~ 3~2980~, [4 6] 7~5613~ 9~3051~ 11~2316~; 14~1536~ 15~1247~, [16 19] 20~5613~ 21~1537~ 23~2479~ 24~3739~ 25~2316~ 26~5524~: 27~2443~ 28~2316~ 29~1722~ 31~3956~ 34~1392~ 35~1223~ 36~2424~ 37~5547~, 39~3739~ 40~2076~ 41~1391~ 42~2532~ 43~2904~ 44~1519~ 45~165~ 47~165~. 48~281~.'),
  (9104, 11, 10, 17, 'And he made three hundred shields of beaten gold; three pound of gold went to one shield: and the king put them in the house of the forest of Lebanon.', '[1 2] 3~07969~ 4~03967~ 5~04043~ [6] 7~07820~ 8~02091~; 9~07969~ 10~04488~ 12~02091~ 13~05927~ 15~0259~ 16~04043~: 19~04428~ 20~05414~ 24~01004~ 27~03293~ 29~03844~.'),
  (27497, 44, 15, 39, 'And the contention was so sharp between them, that they departed asunder one from the other: and so Barnabas took Mark, and sailed unto Cyprus;', '0~3767~ 2~3948~ 3~1096~ 5~3948~ 7~846~, 8~5620~ 11~673~ 15~240~ 16~575~:* 18~5037~ 19~921~ 20~3880~ 21~3138~, 23~1602~ 24~1519~ 25~2954~;'),
  (4158, 4, 14, 45, 'Then the Amalekites came down, and the Canaanites which dwelt in that hill, and smote them, and discomfited them, even unto Hormah.', '2~06003~ 4~03381~, 7~03669~ 9~03427~ 12~02022~, 14~05221~ 17~03807~ [19] 21~02767~.'),
  (8753, 11, 1, 28, 'Then king David answered and said, Call me Bathsheba. And she came into the king''s presence, and stood before the king.', '1~04428~ 2~01732~ 3~06030~ 5~0559~, 6~07121~ 8~01339~. 11~0935~ 14~04428~ 15~06440~, 17~05975~ 18~06440~ 20~04428~.'),
  (15102, 19, 76, 12, 'He shall cut off the spirit of princes: he is terrible to the kings of the earth.', '3~01219~ 5~07307~ 7~05057~: [8 9] 10~03372~ 13~04428~ 16~0776~.'),
  (26416, 43, 8, 20, 'These words spake Jesus in the treasury, as he taught in the temple: and no man laid hands on him; for his hour was not yet come.', '0~5023~ 1~4487~ 2~2980~ 3~2424~ 4~1722~ 6~1049~, 9~1321~ 10~1722~ 12~2411~: 13~2532~ 15~3762~ 17~4084~ 19~846~; 20~3754~ 21~846~ 22~5610~ 23~2064~ 25~3768~ 26~2064~.'),
  (20256, 24, 51, 35, 'The violence done to me and to my flesh be upon Babylon, shall the inhabitant of Zion say; and my blood upon the inhabitants of Chaldea, shall Jerusalem say.', '1~02555~ 8~07607~ [9] 11~0894~, 14~03427~ 16~06726~ 17~0559~; 20~01818~ 23~03427~ 25~03778~, 27~03389~ 28~0559~.'),
  (22123, 28, 2, 9, 'Therefore will I return, and take away my corn in the time thereof, and my wine in the season thereof, and will recover my wool and my flax given to cover her nakedness.', '3~07725~, 6~03947~ 8~01715~ 11~06256~ 15~08492~ 18~04150~ 22~05337~ 24~06785~ 27~06593~ [28] 30~03680~ 32~06172~.'),
  (13683, 18, 33, 24, 'Then he is gracious unto him, and saith, Deliver him from going down to the pit: I have found a ransom.', '3~02603~ 7~0559~, 8~06308~ 12~03381~ 15~07845~: 18~04672~ 20~03724~.'),
  (7983, 9, 29, 9, 'And Achish answered and said to David, I know that thou art good in my sight, as an angel of God: notwithstanding the princes of the Philistines have said, He shall not go up with us to the battle.', '1~0397~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~ 6~01732~, 8~03045~ [11] 12~02896~ 15~05869~, 18~04397~ 20~0430~: 23~08269~ 26~06430~ 28~0559~, 33~05927~ 38~04421~.'),
  (4734, 4, 32, 10, 'And the LORD''S anger was kindled the same time, and he sware, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~0639~ 5~02734~ 8~03117~, 11~07650~, 12~0559~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (13803, 18, 38, 1, 'Then the LORD answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~06030~ 4~0347~ 8~05591~, 10~0559~,'),
  (30608, 62, 3, 13, 'Marvel not, my brethren, if the world hate you.', '0~2296~ 1~3361~, 2~3450~ 3~80~, 4~1487~ 6~2889~ 7~3404~ 8~5209~.'),
  (21434, 26, 37, 28, 'And the heathen shall know that I the LORD do sanctify Israel, when my sanctuary shall be in the midst of them for evermore.', '2~01471~ 4~03045~ 8~03068~ 10~06942~ 11~03478~, 14~04720~ 19~08432~ 23~05769~.'),
  (11200, 13, 29, 28, 'And he died in a good old age, full of days, riches, and honour: and Solomon his son reigned in his stead.', '2~04191~ 5~02896~ 7~07872~, 8~07649~ 10~03117~, 11~06239~, 13~03519~: 15~08010~ 17~01121~ 18~04427~'),
  (28255, 45, 11, 30, 'For as ye in times past have not believed God, yet have now obtained mercy through their unbelief:', '0~1063~ 1~2532~ 2~5618~* 3~5210~ 6~4218~ 9~544~ 10~2316~, 11~1161~ 12~1653~ 13~3568~ 15~1653~ 16~5130~ 18~543~:'),
  (9349, 11, 17, 24, 'And the woman said to Elijah, Now by this I know that thou art a man of God, and that the word of the LORD in thy mouth is truth.', '2~0802~ 3~0559~ 5~0452~, 8~02088~ 10~03045~ [13] 15~0376~ 17~0430~, [18] 21~01697~ 24~03068~ 27~06310~ [28] 29~0571~.'),
  (10400, 13, 4, 7, 'And the sons of Helah were, Zereth, and Jezoar, and Ethnan.', '2~01121~ 4~02458~ [5] 6~06889~, 8~06714~ 9~03328~,* 11~0869~.'),
  (16267, 19, 139, 19, 'Surely thou wilt slay the wicked, O God: depart from me therefore, ye bloody men.', '3~06991~ 5~07563~, 7~0433~: 8~05493~ 13~01818~ 14~0582~.'),
  (2797, 3, 3, 14, 'And he shall offer thereof his offering, even an offering made by fire unto the LORD; the fat that covereth the inwards, and all the fat that is upon the inwards,', '3~07126~ 6~07133~, [7] 12~0801~ 15~03068~; 17~02459~ 19~03680~ 21~07130~, 25~02459~ [27] 30~07130~,'),
  (7081, 7, 20, 20, 'And the men of Israel went out to battle against Benjamin; and the men of Israel put themselves in array to fight against them at Gibeah.', '2~0376~ 4~03478~ 6~03318~ 8~04421~ 10~01144~; 13~0376~ 15~03478~ 19~06186~ 21~04421~ 25~01390~.'),
  (12045, 15, 2, 9, 'The children of Zaccai, seven hundred and threescore.', '1~01121~ 3~02140~, 4~07651~ 5~03967~ 7~08346~.'),
  (17383, 21, 3, 15, 'That which hath been is now; and that which is to be hath already been; and God requireth that which is past.', '5~03528~; 13~03528~ 16~0430~ 17~01245~ 21~07291~.'),
  (25091, 42, 4, 16, 'And he came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up: and, as his custom was, he went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and stood up for to read.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~1519~ 4~3478~, 5~3757~ 8~2258~ 10~5142~: 11~2532~, 12~2596~ 13~846~ 14~1486~ 15~2596~, 17~1525~ 18~1519~ 20~4864~ 21~1722~ 23~4521~ 24~2250~, 25~2532~ 27~450~ 30~314~.'),
  (18555, 23, 44, 13, 'The carpenter stretcheth out his rule; he marketh it out with a line; he fitteth it with planes, and he marketh it out with the compass, and maketh it after the figure of a man, according to the beauty of a man; that it may remain in the house.', '1~06086~ 2~02796~ 3~05186~ [4] 5~06957~; 9~08388~ 12~08279~; 14~06213~ 17~04741~, 22~08388~ 25~04230~, 27~06213~ 31~08403~ 34~0376~, 38~08597~ 41~0120~; 45~03427~ 48~01004~.'),
  (2123, 2, 22, 5, 'If a man shall cause a field or vineyard to be eaten, and shall put in his beast, and shall feed in another man''s field; of the best of his own field, and of the best of his own vineyard, shall he make restitution.', '2~0376~ 6~07704~ 8~03754~ 11~01197~, 14~07971~ 17~01165~, 20~01197~ 23~0312~ 24~07704~; 27~04315~ 31~07704~, 35~04315~ 39~03754~, 43~07999~.'),
  (26209, 43, 4, 38, 'I sent you to reap that whereon ye bestowed no labour: other men laboured, and ye are entered into their labours.', '0~1473~ 1~649~ 2~5209~ 4~2325~ 6~3739~ 7~5210~ 8~2872~ 9~3756~ 10~2872~: 12~243~ 13~2872~, 14~2532~ 15~5210~ 17~1525~ 18~1519~ 19~846~ 20~2873~.'),
  (3251, 3, 17, 11, 'For the life of the flesh is in the blood: and I have given it to you upon the altar to make an atonement for your souls: for it is the blood that maketh an atonement for the soul.', '2~05315~ 5~01320~ [6] 9~01818~: 13~05414~ 19~04196~ 23~03722~ 26~05315~: [29] 31~01818~ [32] 35~03722~ 38~05315~.'),
  (9207, 11, 13, 15, 'Then he said unto him, Come home with me, and eat bread.', '2~0559~ 5~03212~ 6~01004~ 10~0398~ 11~03899~.'),
  (18708, 23, 52, 3, 'For thus saith the LORD, Ye have sold yourselves for nought; and ye shall be redeemed without money.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 7~04376~ 10~02600~; 15~01350~ 17~03701~.'),
  (665, 1, 25, 3, 'And Jokshan begat Sheba, and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, and Letushim, and Leummim.', '1~03370~ 2~03205~ 3~07614~, 5~01719~. 8~01121~ 10~01719~ 12~0805~, 14~03912~, 16~03817~.'),
  (19503, 24, 23, 10, 'For the land is full of adulterers; for because of swearing the land mourneth; the pleasant places of the wilderness are dried up, and their course is evil, and their force is not right.', '2~0776~ 4~04390~ 6~05003~; 8~06440~ 10~0423~ 12~0776~ 13~056~; 16~04999~ 19~04057~ 22~03001~, 25~04794~ 27~07451~, 30~01369~ [31]'),
  (26783, 43, 17, 9, 'I pray for them: I pray not for the world, but for them which thou hast given me; for they are thine.', '0~1473~ 1~2065~ 2~4012~ 3~846~: 5~2065~ 6~3756~ 7~4012~ 9~2889~, 10~235~ 11~4012~ 13~3739~ 16~1325~ 17~3427~; 18~3754~ 20~1526~ 21~4674~.'),
  (20239, 24, 51, 18, 'They are vanity, the work of errors: in the time of their visitation they shall perish.', '[1] 2~01892~, 4~04639~ 6~08595~: 9~06256~ 12~06486~ 15~06~.'),
  (2127, 2, 22, 9, 'For all manner of trespass, whether it be for ox, for ass, for sheep, for raiment, or for any manner of lost thing, which another challengeth to be his, the cause of both parties shall come before the judges; and whom the judges shall condemn, he shall pay double unto his neighbour.', '2~01697~ 4~06588~, [5 7] 9~07794~, 11~02543~, 13~07716~, 15~08008~, [16] 22~09~, [24] 25~0559~ 30~01697~ 33~08147~ 35~0935~ 38~0430~; [39] 42~0430~ 44~07561~, 47~07999~ 48~08147~ 51~07453~.'),
  (25642, 42, 16, 9, 'And I say unto you, Make to yourselves friends of the mammon of unrighteousness; that, when ye fail, they may receive you into everlasting habitations.', '1~2504~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~4160~ 7~1438~ 8~5384~ 9~1537~ 11~3126~ 13~93~; 14~2443~, 15~3752~ 17~1587~, 20~1209~ 21~5209~ 22~1519~ 23~166~ 24~4633~.'),
  (30014, 58, 3, 3, 'For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who hath builded the house hath more honour than the house.', '0~1063~ 1~3778~ [2] 5~515~ 7~4119~ 8~1391~ 9~3844~ 10~3475~, 12~3745~ 13~2596~ 16~2680~ 18~3624~ 20~4119~ 21~5092~ 22~2192~ 24~846~.'),
  (11677, 14, 23, 12, 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising the king, she came to the people into the house of the LORD:', '&para; 2~06271~ 3~08085~ 5~06963~ 8~05971~ 9~07323~ 11~01984~ 13~04428~, 15~0935~ 18~05971~ 21~01004~ 24~03068~:'),
  (19474, 24, 22, 11, 'For thus saith the LORD touching Shallum the son of Josiah king of Judah, which reigned instead of Josiah his father, which went forth out of this place; He shall not return thither any more:', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 5~0413~ 6~07967~ 8~01121~ 10~02977~ 11~04428~ 13~03063~, 15~04427~ 18~02977~ 20~01~, 23~03318~ 27~04725~; 31~07725~'),
  (3730, 4, 3, 33, 'Of Merari was the family of the Mahlites, and the family of the Mushites: these are the families of Merari.', '1~04847~ [2] 4~04940~ 7~04250~, 10~04940~ 13~04188~: [15] 17~04940~ 19~04847~.'),
  (27400, 44, 13, 22, 'And when he had removed him, he raised up unto them David to be their king; to whom also he gave testimony, and said, I have found David the son of Jesse, a man after mine own heart, which shall fulfil all my will.', '0~2532~ 4~3179~ 5~846~, 8~1453~ 10~846~ 11~1138~ 13~1519~ 15~935~; 17~3739~ 18~2532~ 21~3140~, 23~2036~, 26~2147~ 27~1138~ [29] 31~2421~, 33~435~ 34~2596~ 36~3450~ 37~2588~, 38~3739~ 40~4160~ 41~3956~ 42~3450~ 43~2307~.'),
  (30896, 66, 11, 8, 'And their dead bodies shall lie in the street of the great city, which spiritually is called Sodom and Egypt, where also our Lord was crucified.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 3~4430~ [4 5] 6~1909~ 8~4113~ 11~3173~ 12~4172~, 13~3748~ 14~4153~ 16~2564~ 17~4670~ 18~2532~ 19~125~, 20~3699~ 21~2532~ 22~2257~ 23~2962~ 25~4717~.'),
  (15736, 19, 107, 28, 'Then they cry unto the LORD in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.', '2~06817~ 5~03068~ 8~06862~, 13~03318~ 16~04691~.'),
  (24141, 40, 27, 2, 'And when they had bound him, they led him away, and delivered him to Pontius Pilate the governor.', '0~2532~ 4~1210~ 5~846~, [8] 9~520~, 10~2532~ 11~3860~ 12~846~ 14~4194~ 15~4091~ 17~2232~.'),
  (13001, 18, 6, 14, 'To him that is afflicted pity should be shewed from his friend; but he forsaketh the fear of the Almighty.', '&para; 4~04523~ 5~02617~ [6 8] 11~07453~; 14~05800~ 16~03374~ 19~07706~.'),
  (12229, 15, 8, 19, 'And Hashabiah, and with him Jeshaiah of the sons of Merari, his brethren and their sons, twenty;', '1~02811~, 5~03470~ 8~01121~ 10~04847~, 12~0251~ 15~01121~, 16~06242~;'),
  (26625, 43, 12, 30, 'Jesus answered and said, This voice came not because of me, but for your sakes.', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~2532~ 3~2036~, 4~3778~ 5~5456~ 6~1096~ 7~3756~ 9~1223~ 10~1691~, 11~235~ 12~1223~ 14~1223~ 15~5209~.*'),
  (14502, 19, 38, 3, 'There is no soundness in my flesh because of thine anger; neither is there any rest in my bones because of my sin.', '[0 1] 3~04974~ 6~01320~ 7~06440~ 10~02195~; [12 14] 15~07965~ 18~06106~ 19~06440~ 22~02403~.'),
  (24881, 41, 15, 44, 'And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.', '0~1161~ 1~4091~ 2~2296~ 3~1487~ 5~2348~ 6~2235~ 7~2348~: 8~2532~ 9~4341~ [10 11] 13~2760~, 15~1905~ 16~846~ 17~1487~ 20~599~ 22~3819~ 23~599~.'),
  (25990, 42, 23, 41, 'And we indeed justly; for we receive the due reward of our deeds: but this man hath done nothing amiss.', '0~2532~ 1~2249~ 2~3303~ 3~1346~; 4~1063~ 6~618~ 9~514~ 11~3739~ 12~4238~: 13~1161~ 15~3778~ 17~4238~ 18~3762~ 19~824~.'),
  (1909, 2, 14, 15, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Wherefore criest thou unto me? speak unto the children of Israel, that they go forward:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~06817~ 11~01696~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~, 20~05265~:'),
  (1612, 2, 4, 6, 'And the LORD said furthermore unto him, Put now thine hand into thy bosom. And he put his hand into his bosom: and when he took it out, behold, his hand was leprous as snow.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 4~05750~ 7~0935~ 10~03027~ 13~02436~. 16~0935~ 18~03027~ 21~02436~: 25~03318~ 30~03027~ [31] 32~06879~ 34~07950~.'),
  (4210, 4, 16, 11, 'For which cause both thou and all thy company are gathered together against the LORD: and what is Aaron, that ye murmur against him?', '2~03651~ [3] 8~05712~ [9] 11~03259~ 14~03068~: [17] 18~0175~, 21~03885~'),
  (5920, 6, 4, 4, 'Then Joshua called the twelve men, whom he had prepared of the children of Israel, out of every tribe a man:', '1~03091~ 2~07121~ 4~06240~ 5~08147~* 6~0376~, 10~03559~ 13~01121~ 15~03478~, 18~0259~ 19~07626~ 21~0376~:'),
  (21856, 27, 4, 10, 'Thus were the visions of mine head in my bed; I saw, and behold, a tree in the midst of the earth, and the height thereof was great.', '[1] 3~02376~ 6~07217~ 7~05922~ 9~04903~; 11~01934~ 12~02370~,* 14~0431~ 16~0363~ 19~01459~ 22~0772~, 25~07314~ [27] 28~07690~.'),
  (10875, 13, 17, 4, 'Go and tell David my servant, Thus saith the LORD, Thou shalt not build me an house to dwell in:', '0~03212~ 2~0559~ 3~01732~ 5~05650~, 7~0559~ 9~03068~, 13~01129~ 16~01004~ 19~03427~:'),
  (25508, 42, 12, 36, 'And ye yourselves like unto men that wait for their lord, when he will return from the wedding; that when he cometh and knocketh, they may open unto him immediately.', '0~2532~ 2~5210~ 3~3664~ 5~444~ 7~4327~ 9~1438~ 10~2962~, 11~4219~ 14~360~ 15~1537~ 17~1062~; 18~2443~ 21~2064~ 22~2532~ 23~2925~, 26~455~ 28~846~ 29~2112~.'),
  (1182, 1, 40, 5, 'And they dreamed a dream both of them, each man his dream in one night, each man according to the interpretation of his dream, the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, which were bound in the prison.', '&para; 2~02492~ 4~02472~ 7~08147~, 9~0376~ 11~02472~ 13~0259~ 14~03915~, 16~0376~ 20~06623~ 23~02472~, 25~08248~ 28~0644~ 31~04428~ 33~04714~, [35] 36~0631~ 39~05470~ 40~01004~.*'),
  (30022, 58, 3, 11, 'So I sware in my wrath, They shall not enter into my rest.)', '0~5613~ 2~3660~ 3~1722~ 4~3450~ 5~3709~, 7~1525~ 8~1487~ 9~1525~ 10~1519~ 11~3450~ 12~2663~)'),
  (20833, 26, 16, 62, 'And I will establish my covenant with thee; and thou shalt know that I am the LORD:', '3~06965~ 5~01285~ 11~03045~ [14] 16~03068~:'),
  (12591, 16, 10, 33, 'For the shewbread, and for the continual meat offering, and for the continual burnt offering, of the sabbaths, of the new moons, for the set feasts, and for the holy things, and for the sin offerings to make an atonement for Israel, and for all the work of the house of our God.', '2~03899~ 3~04635~,* 7~08548~ 9~04503~, 13~08548~ 15~05930~, 18~07676~, 22~02320~, 26~04150~, 30~06944~ [31] 36~02403~ 40~03722~ 42~03478~, [44] 47~04399~ 50~01004~ 53~0430~.'),
  (8779, 11, 2, 1, 'Now the days of David drew nigh that he should die; and he charged Solomon his son, saying,', '&para; 2~03117~ 4~01732~ 6~07126~ 10~04191~; 13~06680~ 14~08010~ 16~01121~, 17~0559~,'),
  (25452, 42, 11, 35, 'Take heed therefore that the light which is in thee be not darkness.', '1~4648~ 2~3767~ 5~5457~ 6~3588~ 8~1722~ 9~4671~ 10~2076~ 11~3361~ 12~4655~.'),
  (10963, 13, 21, 21, 'And as David came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw David, and went out of the threshingfloor, and bowed himself to David with his face to the ground.', '2~01732~ 3~0935~ 5~0771~, 6~0771~ 7~05027~ 9~07200~ 10~01732~, 13~03318~ 16~01637~, 18~07812~ 21~01732~ [23] 24~0639~ 27~0776~.'),
  (12922, 18, 3, 9, 'Let the stars of the twilight thereof be dark; let it look for light, but have none; neither let it see the dawning of the day:', '2~03556~ 5~05399~ 8~02821~; 11~06960~ 13~0216~, [15] 20~07200~ 22~06079~ 25~07837~:'),
  (20836, 26, 17, 2, 'Son of man, put forth a riddle, and speak a parable unto the house of Israel;', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 4~02330~ 6~02420~, 8~04911~ 10~04912~ 13~01004~ 15~03478~;'),
  (8839, 11, 3, 15, 'And Solomon awoke; and, behold, it was a dream. And he came to Jerusalem, and stood before the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and offered up burnt offerings, and offered peace offerings, and made a feast to all his servants.', '1~08010~ 2~03364~; [5 6] 8~02472~. 11~0935~ 13~03389~, 15~05975~ 16~06440~ 18~0727~ 21~01285~ 24~03068~, 27~05927~ 29~05930~, 31~06213~ 33~08002~, 35~06213~ 37~04960~ 41~05650~.'),
  (20225, 24, 51, 4, 'Thus the slain shall fall in the land of the Chaldeans, and they that are thrust through in her streets.', '2~02491~ 4~05307~ 7~0776~ 10~03778~, [12 14] 16~01856~ 19~02351~.'),
  (5020, 5, 4, 10, 'Specially the day that thou stoodest before the LORD thy God in Horeb, when the LORD said unto me, Gather me the people together, and I will make them hear my words, that they may learn to fear me all the days that they shall live upon the earth, and that they may teach their children.', '[0] 2~03117~ 5~05975~ 6~06440~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~ 12~02722~, 15~03068~ 16~0559~ 19~06950~ 22~05971~ 23~06950~, 29~08085~ 31~01697~, 35~03925~ 37~03372~ 41~03117~ 45~02416~ 48~0127~, [50] 53~03925~ 55~01121~.'),
  (29111, 48, 2, 14, 'But when I saw that they walked not uprightly according to the truth of the gospel, I said unto Peter before them all, If thou, being a Jew, livest after the manner of Gentiles, and not as do the Jews, why compellest thou the Gentiles to live as do the Jews?', '0~235~ 1~3753~ 3~1492~ 4~3754~ 6~3716~ 7~3756~ 8~3716~ 10~4314~ 12~225~ 15~2098~, 17~2036~ 19~4074~ 20~1715~ [21] 22~3956~, 23~1487~ 24~4771~, 25~5225~ 27~2453~, 28~2198~ 33~1483~, 34~2532~ 35~3756~ 39~2452~, 40~5101~ 42~315~ 44~1484~ 50~2450~?'),
  (11305, 14, 6, 15, 'Thou which hast kept with thy servant David my father that which thou hast promised him; and spakest with thy mouth, and hast fulfilled it with thine hand, as it is this day.', '3~08104~ 6~05650~ 7~01732~ 9~01~ 14~01696~ 17~01696~ 20~06310~, 23~04390~ [24] 27~03027~, [29 30] 32~03117~.'),
  (4871, 4, 35, 20, 'But if he thrust him of hatred, or hurl at him by laying of wait, that he die;', '3~01920~ 6~08135~, 8~07993~ 14~06660~, 17~04191~;'),
  (6439, 6, 22, 6, 'So Joshua blessed them, and sent them away: and they went unto their tents.', '1~03091~ 2~01288~ 7~07971~: 10~03212~ 13~0168~.'),
  (27434, 44, 14, 4, 'But the multitude of the city was divided: and part held with the Jews, and part with the apostles.', '0~1161~ 2~4128~ 5~4172~ 7~4977~: 8~2532~ 9~3303~ 10~2258~ 11~4862~ 13~2453~, 14~1161~ 16~4862~ 18~652~.'),
  (19983, 24, 41, 17, 'And they departed, and dwelt in the habitation of Chimham, which is by Bethlehem, to go to enter into Egypt,', '2~03212~, 5~03427~ 7~01628~ 9~03643~, 12~0681~ 13~01035~, 15~03212~ 17~0935~ 19~04714~,'),
  (18940, 23, 66, 9, 'Shall I bring to the birth, and not cause to bring forth? saith the LORD: shall I cause to bring forth, and shut the womb? saith thy God.', '5~07665~, 11~03205~? 12~0559~ 14~03068~: 16~0589~ 20~03205~, 22~06113~ [23 24] 25~0559~ 27~0430~.'),
  (27110, 44, 5, 35, 'And said unto them, Ye men of Israel, take heed to yourselves what ye intend to do as touching these men.', '0~5037~ 1~2036~ 2~4314~ 3~846~, 5~435~ 7~2475~, 9~4337~ 11~1438~ 12~5101~ 14~3195~ 16~4238~ 18~1909~ 19~5125~ 20~444~.'),
  (13979, 19, 4, 5, 'Offer the sacrifices of righteousness, and put your trust in the LORD.', '0~02076~ 2~02077~ 4~06664~, 8~0982~ 11~03068~.'),
  (4068, 4, 12, 4, 'And the LORD spake suddenly unto Moses, and unto Aaron, and unto Miriam, Come out ye three unto the tabernacle of the congregation. And they three came out.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 4~06597~ 6~04872~, 9~0175~, 12~04813~, 14~03318~ 16~07969~ 19~0168~ 22~04150~. 25~07969~ 27~03318~.'),
  (21636, 26, 44, 28, 'And it shall be unto them for an inheritance: I am their inheritance: and ye shall give them no possession in Israel: I am their possession.', '8~05159~: [10] 12~05159~: 16~05414~ 19~0272~ 21~03478~: [23] 25~0272~.'),
  (22013, 27, 9, 16, 'O Lord, according to all thy righteousness, I beseech thee, let thine anger and thy fury be turned away from thy city Jerusalem, thy holy mountain: because for our sins, and for the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and thy people are become a reproach to all that are about us.', '1~0136~, 6~06666~, 12~0639~ 15~02534~ 18~07725~ 21~05892~ 22~03389~, 24~06944~ 25~02022~: 29~02399~, 33~05771~ 36~01~, 37~03389~ 40~05971~ [41 42] 44~02781~ [47 48] 49~05439~'),
  (26530, 43, 10, 34, 'Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are gods?', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~846~, 4~2076~ 5~3756~ 6~1125~ 7~1722~ 8~5216~ 9~3551~, 10~1473~ 11~2036~, 13~2075~ 14~2316~?'),
  (29585, 52, 1, 9, 'For they themselves shew of us what manner of entering in we had unto you, and how ye turned to God from idols to serve the living and true God;', '0~1063~ 1~518~ 2~846~ 3~518~ 4~4012~ 5~2257~ 7~3697~ 10~1529~ 12~2192~ 13~4314~ 14~5209~, 15~2532~ 16~4459~ 18~1994~ 19~4314~ 20~2316~ 21~575~ 22~1497~ 24~1398~ 26~2198~ 27~2532~ 28~228~ 29~2316~;'),
  (13574, 18, 30, 8, 'They were children of fools, yea, children of base men: they were viler than the earth.', '[0 1] 2~01121~ 4~05036~, 6~01121~ 9~08034~: 12~05217~ 15~0776~.'),
  (18096, 23, 23, 10, 'Pass through thy land as a river, O daughter of Tarshish: there is no more strength.', '0~05674~ 3~0776~ 6~02975~, 8~01323~ 10~08659~: [11 12] 15~04206~.'),
  (22099, 27, 12, 9, 'And he said, Go thy way, Daniel: for the words are closed up and sealed till the time of the end.', '2~0559~, 5~03212~, 6~01840~: 9~01697~ [10] 12~05640~ 14~02856~ 17~06256~ 20~07093~.'),
  (1832, 2, 12, 11, 'And thus shall ye eat it; with your loins girded, your shoes on your feet, and your staff in your hand; and ye shall eat it in haste: it is the LORD''S passover.', '1~03602~ 4~0398~ [6] 8~04975~ 9~02296~, 11~05275~ 14~07272~, 17~04731~ 20~03027~; 24~0398~ 27~02649~: [29] 31~03068~ 32~06453~.'),
  (16434, 20, 1, 25, 'But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:', '5~06544~ 8~06098~, 10~014~ 14~08433~:'),
  (13902, 18, 41, 5, 'Wilt thou play with him as with a bird? or wilt thou bind him for thy maidens?', '2~07832~ [6] 8~06833~? 12~07194~ 16~05291~?'),
  (7383, 9, 8, 7, 'And the LORD said unto Samuel, Hearken unto the voice of the people in all that they say unto thee: for they have not rejected thee, but they have rejected me, that I should not reign over them.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~08050~, 6~08085~ 9~06963~ 12~05971~ 17~0559~ 24~03988~ 29~03988~ 35~04427~'),
  (9324, 11, 16, 33, 'And Ahab made a grove; and Ahab did more to provoke the LORD God of Israel to anger than all the kings of Israel that were before him.', '1~0256~ 2~06213~ 4~0842~; 6~0256~ 7~06213~ 8~03254~ 12~03068~ 13~0430~ 15~03478~ 17~03707~ 21~04428~ 23~03478~ 26~06440~'),
  (16135, 19, 127, 5, 'Happy is the man that hath his quiver full of them: they shall not be ashamed, but they shall speak with the enemies in the gate.', '0~0835~ [1] 3~01397~ 7~0827~ 8~04390~ 15~0954~, 19~01696~ 22~0341~ 25~08179~.'),
  (19838, 24, 35, 6, 'But they said, We will drink no wine: for Jonadab the son of Rechab our father commanded us, saying, Ye shall drink no wine, neither ye, nor your sons for ever:', '2~0559~, 5~08354~ 7~03196~: 9~03122~ 11~01121~ 13~07394~ 15~01~ 16~06680~ 18~0559~, 21~08354~ 23~03196~, [24 25] 28~01121~ 29~05704~ 30~05769~:'),
  (30516, 61, 1, 21, 'For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but holy men of God spake as they were moved by the Holy Ghost.', '0~1063~ 2~4394~ 3~5342~ 4~3756~ 7~4218~ 10~2307~ 12~444~: 13~235~ 14~40~ 15~444~ 17~2316~ 18~2980~ [19 21] 22~5342~ 23~5259~ 25~40~ 26~4151~.'),
  (12667, 16, 12, 34, 'Judah, and Benjamin, and Shemaiah, and Jeremiah,', '0~03063~, 2~01144~, 4~08098~, 6~03414~,'),
  (29959, 57, 1, 5, 'Hearing of thy love and faith, which thou hast toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all saints;', '0~191~ 2~4675~ 3~26~ 4~2532~ 5~4102~, 6~3739~ 8~2192~ 9~4314~ 11~2962~ 12~2424~, 13~2532~ 14~1519~ 15~3956~ 16~40~;'),
  (7679, 9, 17, 54, 'And David took the head of the Philistine, and brought it to Jerusalem; but he put his armour in his tent.', '1~01732~ 2~03947~ 4~07218~ 7~06430~, 9~0935~ 12~03389~; 15~07760~ 17~03627~ 20~0168~.'),
  (1935, 2, 15, 10, 'Thou didst blow with thy wind, the sea covered them: they sank as lead in the mighty waters.', '2~05398~ 5~07307~, 7~03220~ 8~03680~ 11~06749~ 13~05777~ 16~0117~ 17~04325~.'),
  (15222, 19, 80, 15, 'And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch that thou madest strong for thyself.', '2~03661~ 3~03657~* 7~03225~ 9~05193~, 12~01121~ [13] 16~0553~'),
  (26867, 43, 19, 27, 'Then saith he to the disciple, Behold thy mother! And from that hour that disciple took her unto his own home.', '0~1534~ 2~3004~ 5~3101~, 6~2400~ 7~4675~ 8~3384~! 9~2532~ 10~575~ 11~1565~ 12~5610~ 14~3101~ 15~2983~ 16~846~ 17~1519~ 19~2398~ [20]'),
  (10232, 12, 25, 2, 'And the city was besieged unto the eleventh year of king Zedekiah.', '2~05892~ 4~0935~ 5~04692~* 8~06240~ 9~06249~* 10~08141~ 12~04428~ 13~06667~.'),
  (26013, 42, 24, 8, 'And they remembered his words,', '0~2532~ 2~3415~ 3~846~ 4~4487~,'),
  (16086, 19, 120, 3, 'What shall be given unto thee? or what shall be done unto thee, thou false tongue?', '3~05414~ 10~03254~ 14~07423~ 15~03956~?'),
  (4205, 4, 16, 6, 'This do; Take you censers, Korah, and all his company;', '1~06213~; 2~03947~ 4~04289~, 5~07141~, 9~05712~;'),
  (14274, 19, 25, 14, 'The secret of the LORD is with them that fear him; and he will shew them his covenant.', '1~05475~ 4~03068~ [5] 9~03373~ 14~03045~ 17~01285~.'),
  (30212, 58, 11, 24, 'By faith Moses, when he was come to years, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh''s daughter;', '1~4102~ 2~3475~, 6~1096~ 8~3173~, 9~720~ 12~3004~ 14~5207~ 16~5328~ 17~2364~;'),
  (4389, 4, 22, 9, 'And God came unto Balaam, and said, What men are these with thee?', '1~0430~ 2~0935~ 4~01109~, 6~0559~, 8~0582~ [9]'),
  (25017, 42, 2, 32, 'A light to lighten the Gentiles, and the glory of thy people Israel.', '1~5457~ 2~1519~ 3~602~ 5~1484~, 6~2532~ 8~1391~ 10~4675~ 11~2992~ 12~2474~.'),
  (24288, 41, 2, 18, 'And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees used to fast: and they come and say unto him, Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast, but thy disciples fast not?', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~3101~ 4~2491~ 5~2532~ 8~5330~ 9~2258~ 11~3522~: 12~2532~ 14~2064~ 15~2532~ 16~3004~ 18~846~, 20~3522~ 21~1302~* 23~3101~ 25~2491~ 26~2532~ 29~5330~ 30~3522~, 31~1161~ 32~4674~ 33~3101~ 34~3522~ 35~3756~?'),
  (28922, 47, 6, 8, 'By honour and dishonour, by evil report and good report: as deceivers, and yet true;', '0~1223~ 1~1391~ 2~2532~ 3~819~, 4~1223~ 6~1426~ 7~2532~ 9~2162~: 10~5613~ 11~4108~, 12~2532~ [13] 14~227~;'),
  (7555, 9, 14, 40, 'Then said he unto all Israel, Be ye on one side, and I and Jonathan my son will be on the other side. And the people said unto Saul, Do what seemeth good unto thee.', '1~0559~ 5~03478~, 9~0259~ 10~05676~, 14~03129~ 16~01121~ 21~0259~ 22~05676~. 25~05971~ 26~0559~ 28~07586~, 29~06213~ 31~05869~ 32~02896~');
