VALUES
  (12916, 18, 3, 3, 'Let the day perish wherein I was born, and the night in which it was said, There is a man child conceived.', '2~03117~ 3~06~ 7~03205~, 10~03915~ [11 12] 15~0559~, 20~01397~ 21~02029~.'),
  (18081, 23, 22, 20, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that I will call my servant Eliakim the son of Hilkiah:', '8~03117~, 12~07121~ 14~05650~ 15~0471~ 17~01121~ 19~02518~:'),
  (3639, 4, 1, 30, 'Of the children of Zebulun, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~02074~, 7~08435~, 10~04940~, 13~01004~ 16~01~, 20~04557~ 23~08034~, 25~06242~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~ 29~04605~, 36~03318~ 38~06635~;'),
  (788, 1, 28, 11, 'And he lighted upon a certain place, and tarried there all night, because the sun was set; and he took of the stones of that place, and put them for his pillows, and lay down in that place to sleep.', '2~06293~ 6~04725~, 11~03885~, 14~08121~ 16~0935~; 19~03947~ 22~068~ 25~04725~, 27~07760~ [28 29] 31~04763~, 34~07901~ 37~04725~ 39~07901~.'),
  (9714, 12, 6, 32, 'But Elisha sat in his house, and the elders sat with him; and the king sent a man from before him: but ere the messenger came to him, he said to the elders, See ye how this son of a murderer hath sent to take away mine head? look, when the messenger cometh, shut the door, and hold him fast at the door: is not the sound of his master''s feet behind him?', '1~0477~ 2~03427~ 5~01004~, 8~02205~ 9~03427~ [13 14] 15~07971~ 17~0376~ 19~06440~ 24~04397~ 25~0935~ 29~0559~ 32~02205~, 33~07200~ 37~01121~ 40~07523~ 42~07971~ 45~05493~ 47~07218~? 48~07200~, 51~04397~ 52~0935~, 53~05462~ 55~01817~, 59~03905~ 62~01817~: [63] 66~06963~ 69~0113~ 70~07272~ 71~0310~'),
  (26356, 43, 7, 13, 'Howbeit no man spake openly of him for fear of the Jews.', '0~3305~ 2~3762~ 3~2980~ 4~3954~ 5~4012~ 6~846~ 7~1223~ 8~5401~ 11~2453~.'),
  (10564, 13, 7, 21, 'And Zabad his son, and Shuthelah his son, and Ezer, and Elead, whom the men of Gath that were born in that land slew, because they came down to take away their cattle.', '1~02066~ 3~01121~, 5~07803~ 7~01121~, 9~05827~, 11~0496~, 14~0582~ 16~01661~ [17 18] 19~03205~ [21] 22~0776~ 23~02026~, 27~03381~ 30~03947~ 32~04735~.'),
  (457, 1, 18, 29, 'And he spake unto him yet again, and said, Peradventure there shall be forty found there. And he said, I will not do it for forty''s sake.', '2~01696~ 6~03254~, 8~0559~, 13~0705~ 14~04672~ 18~0559~, 22~06213~ [23] 25~0705~'),
  (30706, 65, 1, 18, 'How that they told you there should be mockers in the last time, who should walk after their own ungodly lusts.', '0~3754~ 1~3754~ 3~3004~ 4~5213~ 7~2071~ 8~1703~ 9~1722~ 11~2078~ 12~5550~, 15~4198~ 16~2596~ 18~1438~ 19~763~ 20~1939~.'),
  (19130, 24, 7, 2, 'Stand in the gate of the Lord''s house, and proclaim there this word, and say, Hear the word of the LORD, all ye of Judah, that enter in at these gates to worship the LORD.', '0~05975~ 3~08179~ 6~03068~ 7~01004~, 9~07121~ 12~01697~, 14~0559~, 15~08085~ 17~01697~ 20~03068~, [22 23] 24~03063~, 27~0935~ 30~08179~ 32~07812~ 34~03068~.'),
  (20095, 24, 48, 6, 'Flee, save your lives, and be like the heath in the wilderness.', '0~05127~, 1~04422~ 3~05315~, 5~01961~ 8~06176~ 11~04057~.'),
  (3017, 3, 11, 15, 'Every raven after his kind;', '1~06158~ 4~04327~;'),
  (8065, 10, 2, 9, 'And made him king over Gilead, and over the Ashurites, and over Jezreel, and over Ephraim, and over Benjamin, and over all Israel.', '3~04427~ 5~01568~, 9~0805~, 12~03157~, 15~0669~, 18~01144~, 22~03478~.'),
  (28537, 46, 7, 34, 'There is difference also between a wife and a virgin. The unmarried woman careth for the things of the Lord, that she may be holy both in body and in spirit: but she that is married careth for the things of the world, how she may please her husband.', '[3] 4~3307~ 6~1135~ 7~2532~ 9~3933~. 12~22~ 14~3309~ 16~3588~ 19~2962~, 20~2443~ 23~5600~ 24~40~ 25~2532~ 27~4983~ 28~2532~ 30~4151~: 31~1161~ 35~1060~ 36~3309~ 39~3588~ 42~2889~, 43~4459~ 46~700~ [47] 48~435~.'),
  (1047, 1, 36, 2, 'Esau took his wives of the daughters of Canaan; Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite, and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibeon the Hivite;', '0~06215~ 1~03947~ 3~0802~ 6~01323~ 8~03667~; 9~05711~ 11~01323~ 13~0356~ 15~02850~, 17~0173~ 19~01323~ 21~06034~ 23~01323~ 25~06649~ 27~02340~;'),
  (20867, 26, 18, 9, 'Hath walked in my statutes, and hath kept my judgments, to deal truly; he is just, he shall surely live, saith the Lord GOD.', '1~01980~ 4~02708~, 7~08104~ 9~04941~, 11~06213~ 12~0571~; [14] 15~06662~, 18~02421~ 19~02421~, 20~05002~ 22~0136~ 23~03069~.'),
  (8573, 10, 20, 11, 'And one of Joab''s men stood by him, and said, He that favoureth Joab, and he that is for David, let him go after Joab.', '1~0376~ 3~03097~ 4~05288~ 5~05975~ 9~0559~, 10~04310~ 12~02654~ 13~03097~, [17] 19~01732~, [20 22] 23~0310~ 24~03097~.'),
  (4811, 4, 33, 45, 'And they departed from Iim, and pitched in Dibongad.', '2~05265~ 4~05864~, 6~02583~ 8~01769~.'),
  (20689, 26, 11, 25, 'Then I spake unto them of the captivity all the things that the LORD had shewed me.', '2~01696~ 7~01473~ 10~01697~ 13~03068~ 15~07200~'),
  (17044, 20, 22, 20, 'Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and knowledge,', '3~03789~ 5~08032~ 7~07991~ 9~04156~ 11~01847~,'),
  (18698, 23, 51, 16, 'And I have put my words in thy mouth, and I have covered thee in the shadow of mine hand, that I may plant the heavens, and lay the foundations of the earth, and say unto Zion, Thou art my people.', '3~07760~ 5~01697~ 8~06310~, 12~03680~ 16~06738~ 19~03027~, 23~05193~ 25~08064~, 29~03245~ 32~0776~, 34~0559~ 36~06726~, [38] 40~05971~.'),
  (27358, 44, 12, 5, 'Peter therefore was kept in prison: but prayer was made without ceasing of the church unto God for him.', '&para; 0~3303~ 1~4074~* 2~3767~ 4~5083~ 5~1722~ 6~5438~: 7~1161~ 8~4335~ 9~2258~ 10~1096~ 12~1618~ 13~5259~ 15~1577~ 16~4314~ 17~2316~ 18~5228~ 19~846~.'),
  (10658, 13, 9, 35, 'And in Gibeon dwelt the father of Gibeon, Jehiel, whose wife''s name was Maachah:', '&para; 2~01391~ 3~03427~ 5~01~ 7~01391~ 8~025~,* 9~03273~, 11~0802~ 12~08034~ [13] 14~04601~:'),
  (4647, 4, 29, 33, 'And their meat offering and their drink offerings for the bullocks, for the rams, and for the lambs, shall be according to their number, after the manner:', '3~04503~ 7~05262~ 10~06499~, 13~0352~, 17~03532~, [18 19] 23~04557~, 26~04941~:'),
  (19854, 24, 36, 3, 'It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the evil which I purpose to do unto them; that they may return every man from his evil way; that I may forgive their iniquity and their sin.', '5~01004~ 7~03063~ 9~08085~ 12~07451~ 15~02803~ 17~06213~ 23~07725~ 25~0376~ 28~07451~ 29~01870~; 33~05545~ 35~05771~ 38~02403~.'),
  (25430, 42, 11, 13, 'If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children: how much more shall your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to them that ask him?', '0~1487~ 1~5210~ 2~3767~, 3~5225~ 4~4190~, 5~1492~ 8~1325~ 9~18~ 10~1390~ 12~5216~ 13~5043~: 15~4214~ 16~3123~ 17~1325~ [18] 19~3772~ 20~1537~ 21~3962~* 22~1325~ 24~40~ 25~4151~ 29~154~ 30~846~?'),
  (25918, 42, 22, 40, 'And when he was at the place, he said unto them, Pray that ye enter not into temptation.', '0~1161~ 3~1096~ 4~1909~ 6~5117~, 8~2036~ 10~846~, 11~4336~ 14~1525~ 15~3361~ 16~1519~ 17~3986~.'),
  (16430, 20, 1, 21, 'She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, saying,', '1~07121~ 5~07218~ 7~01993~, 10~06607~ 13~08179~: 16~05892~ 18~0559~ 20~0561~, [21]'),
  (9548, 12, 1, 7, 'And he said unto them, What manner of man was he which came up to meet you, and told you these words?', '2~01696~ 6~04941~ 8~0376~ [9 10] 13~05927~ 15~07125~ 18~01696~ 21~01697~?'),
  (15915, 19, 119, 8, 'I will keep thy statutes: O forsake me not utterly.', '2~08104~ 4~02706~: 6~05800~ 9~03966~.'),
  (30117, 58, 8, 9, 'Not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt; because they continued not in my covenant, and I regarded them not, saith the Lord.', '0~3756~ 2~2596~ 4~1242~ 5~3739~ 8~4160~ 9~846~ 10~3962~ 11~1722~ 13~2250~ 16~1949~ 17~846~ 20~5495~ 21~3450~ 22~1806~ 23~846~ 25~1537~ 27~1093~ 29~125~; 30~3754~ 31~846~ 32~1696~ 33~3756~ 34~1722~ 35~3450~ 36~1242~, 38~2504~ 39~272~ 40~846~ 41~272~, 42~3004~ 44~2962~.'),
  (27390, 44, 13, 12, 'Then the deputy, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord.', '0~5119~ 2~446~, 5~1492~ 8~1096~, 9~4100~, 11~1605~ 12~1909~ 14~1322~ 17~2962~.'),
  (1961, 2, 16, 9, 'And Moses spake unto Aaron, Say unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, Come near before the LORD: for he hath heard your murmurings.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~0175~, 5~0559~ 9~05712~ 12~01121~ 14~03478~, 16~07126~ 17~06440~ 19~03068~: 23~08085~ 25~08519~.'),
  (12072, 15, 2, 36, 'The priests: the children of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred seventy and three.', '&para; 1~03548~: 3~01121~ 5~03048~, 8~01004~ 10~03442~, 11~08672~ 12~03967~ 13~07657~ 15~07969~.'),
  (14547, 19, 40, 13, 'Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me: O LORD, make haste to help me.', '1~07521~, 3~03068~, 5~05337~ 8~03068~, 10~02363~ 12~05833~'),
  (9085, 11, 9, 26, 'And king Solomon made a navy of ships in Eziongeber, which is beside Eloth, on the shore of the Red sea, in the land of Edom.', '1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~06213~ 7~0590~ 9~06100~, [11] 13~0359~, 16~08193~ 19~05488~ 20~03220~, 23~0776~ 25~0123~.'),
  (10606, 13, 8, 23, 'And Abdon, and Zichri, and Hanan,', '1~05658~, 3~02147~, 5~02605~,'),
  (23878, 40, 21, 42, 'Jesus saith unto them, Did ye never read in the scriptures, The stone which the builders rejected, the same is become the head of the corner: this is the Lord''s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 5~314~ 6~3763~ 7~314~ 8~1722~ 10~1124~, 12~3037~ 13~3739~ 15~3618~ 16~593~, 18~3778~ 20~1096~ 21~1519~* 23~2776~ 26~1137~: 27~3778~ 28~3844~ 30~2962~ 31~1096~, 32~2532~ 34~2076~ 35~2298~ 36~1722~ 37~2257~ 38~3788~?'),
  (4198, 4, 15, 40, 'That ye may remember, and do all my commandments, and be holy unto your God.', '3~02142~, 5~06213~ 8~04687~, 10~01961~ 11~06918~ 14~0430~.'),
  (6304, 6, 18, 4, 'Give out from among you three men for each tribe: and I will send them, and they shall rise, and go through the land, and describe it according to the inheritance of them; and they shall come again to me.', '1~03051~ 5~07969~ 6~0582~ [8] 9~07626~: 13~07971~ 18~06965~, 20~01980~ 23~0776~, 25~03789~ 27~06310~ 30~05159~ 36~0935~ [37]'),
  (26562, 43, 11, 24, 'Martha saith unto him, I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection at the last day.', '0~3136~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 5~1492~ 6~3754~ 10~450~ 11~1722~ 13~386~ 14~1722~ 16~2078~ 17~2250~.'),
  (27777, 44, 23, 27, 'This man was taken of the Jews, and should have been killed of them: then came I with an army, and rescued him, having understood that he was a Roman.', '0~5126~ 1~435~ 3~4815~ 4~5259~ 6~2453~, 7~2532~ 8~3195~ 11~337~ 12~5259~ 13~846~: 16~2186~ 17~4862~ 19~4753~, 21~1807~ 22~846~, 24~3129~ 25~3754~ 27~2076~ 29~4514~.'),
  (27921, 44, 28, 6, 'Howbeit they looked when he should have swollen, or fallen down dead suddenly: but after they had looked a great while, and saw no harm come to him, they changed their minds, and said that he was a god.', '0~1161~ 2~4328~ 4~846~ 5~3195~ 7~4092~, 8~2228~ 10~2667~ 11~3498~ 12~869~: 13~1161~ 15~846~ 17~4328~ 20~4183~ 21~1909~,* 22~2532~ 23~2334~ 24~3367~ 25~824~ 26~1096~ 27~1519~ 28~846~, 32~3328~, 34~3004~ 36~846~ 37~1511~ 39~2316~.'),
  (2195, 2, 24, 13, 'And Moses rose up, and his minister Joshua: and Moses went up into the mount of God.', '1~04872~ 3~06965~, 6~08334~ 7~03091~: 9~04872~ 11~05927~ 14~02022~ 16~0430~.'),
  (3136, 3, 14, 20, 'And the priest shall offer the burnt offering and the meat offering upon the altar: and the priest shall make an atonement for him, and he shall be clean.', '2~03548~ 4~05927~ 7~05930~ 11~04503~ 14~04196~: 17~03548~ 21~03722~ 28~02891~.'),
  (18891, 23, 63, 16, 'Doubtless thou art our father, though Abraham be ignorant of us, and Israel acknowledge us not: thou, O LORD, art our father, our redeemer; thy name is from everlasting.', '0~03588~ [2] 4~01~, 6~085~ 8~03045~ 9~03808~* 13~03478~ 14~05234~ 19~03068~, [20] 22~01~, 24~01350~; 26~08034~ [27] 29~05769~.'),
  (9357, 11, 18, 8, 'And he answered him, I am: go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah is here.', '2~0559~ [5] 6~03212~, 7~0559~ 9~0113~, 11~0452~ [12 13]'),
  (27728, 44, 22, 8, 'And I answered, Who art thou, Lord? And he said unto me, I am Jesus of Nazareth, whom thou persecutest.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~611~, 3~5101~ 5~1488~, 6~2962~? 7~5037~ 9~2036~ 10~4314~ 11~3165~, 12~1473~ 13~1510~ 14~2424~ 16~3480~, 17~3739~ 18~4771~ 19~1377~.'),
  (5322, 5, 14, 26, 'And thou shalt bestow that money for whatsoever thy soul lusteth after, for oxen, or for sheep, or for wine, or for strong drink, or for whatsoever thy soul desireth: and thou shalt eat there before the LORD thy God, and thou shalt rejoice, thou, and thine household,', '3~05414~ 5~03701~ 9~05315~ 11~0183~, 13~01241~, 16~06629~, 19~03196~, 23~07941~, 28~05315~ 29~07592~: 33~0398~ 35~06440~ 37~03068~ 39~0430~, 43~08055~, 47~01004~,'),
  (16085, 19, 120, 2, 'Deliver my soul, O LORD, from lying lips, and from a deceitful tongue.', '0~05337~ 2~05315~, 4~03068~, 6~08267~ 7~08193~, [8] 11~07423~ 12~03956~.'),
  (28496, 46, 6, 13, 'Meats for the belly, and the belly for meats: but God shall destroy both it and them. Now the body is not for fornication, but for the Lord; and the Lord for the body.', '0~1033~ 3~2836~, 4~2532~ 6~2836~ 8~1033~: 9~1161~ 10~2316~ 12~2673~ 13~2532~ 14~5026~ 15~2532~ 16~5023~. 17~1161~ 19~4983~ [20] 21~3756~ 23~4202~, 24~235~ 27~2962~; 28~2532~ 30~2962~ 33~4983~.'),
  (9359, 11, 18, 10, 'As the LORD thy God liveth, there is no nation or kingdom, whither my lord hath not sent to seek thee: and when they said, He is not there; he took an oath of the kingdom and nation, that they found thee not.', '[0] 2~03068~ 4~0430~ 5~02416~, 8~03426~ 9~01471~ 11~04467~, 12~0834~ 14~0113~ 17~07971~ 19~01245~ 24~0559~, [25 26] [28] 32~07650~ 35~04467~ 37~01471~, 40~04672~'),
  (2806, 3, 4, 6, 'And the priest shall dip his finger in the blood, and sprinkle of the blood seven times before the LORD, before the veil of the sanctuary.', '2~03548~ 4~02881~ 6~0676~ 9~01818~, 11~05137~ 14~01818~ 15~07651~ 16~06471~ 17~06440~ 19~03068~, 20~06440~ 22~06532~ 25~06944~.'),
  (6653, 7, 5, 23, 'Curse ye Meroz, said the angel of the LORD, curse ye bitterly the inhabitants thereof; because they came not to the help of the LORD, to the help of the LORD against the mighty.', '0~0779~ 2~04789~, 3~0559~ 5~04397~ 8~03068~, 9~0779~ 11~0779~ 13~03427~ 17~0935~ 21~05833~ 24~03068~, 27~05833~ 30~03068~ 33~01368~.'),
  (25473, 42, 12, 1, 'In the mean time, when there were gathered together an innumerable multitude of people, insomuch that they trode one upon another, he began to say unto his disciples first of all, Beware ye of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.', '&para; 0~1722~ 3~3739~, 8~1996~ 11~3461~ 13~3793~, 15~5620~ 17~2662~ 20~240~, 22~756~ 24~3004~ 25~4314~ 26~846~ 27~3101~ 30~4412~, 31~4337~ 32~1438~ 33~575~ 35~2219~ 38~5330~, 39~3748~ 40~2076~ 41~5272~.'),
  (23173, 40, 1, 19, 'Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to make her a public example, was minded to put her away privily.', '0~1161~ 1~2501~ 2~846~ 3~435~, 4~5607~ 6~1342~ [7] 8~2532~ 9~3361~ 10~2309~ 12~3856~ 13~846~ 16~3856~, 18~1014~ 20~630~ 21~846~ 22~630~ 23~2977~.'),
  (16443, 20, 2, 1, 'My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and hide my commandments with thee;', '&para; 1~01121~, 5~03947~ 7~0561~, 9~06845~ 11~04687~'),
  (26016, 42, 24, 11, 'And their words seemed to them as idle tales, and they believed them not.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~4487~ 3~5316~ 4~1799~ 5~846~ 6~5616~ 8~3026~, 9~2532~ 11~569~ 12~846~ 13~569~.'),
  (5437, 5, 20, 4, 'For the LORD your God is he that goeth with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ [5] 8~01980~ 12~03898~ 17~0341~, 19~03467~'),
  (6870, 7, 11, 34, 'And Jephthah came to Mizpeh unto his house, and, behold, his daughter came out to meet him with timbrels and with dances: and she was his only child; beside her he had neither son nor daughter.', '1~03316~ 2~0935~ 4~04709~ 7~01004~, 11~01323~ 13~03318~ 15~07125~ 18~08596~ 21~04246~: [24 25] 27~03173~; 33~01121~ 34~0176~ 35~01323~.'),
  (26136, 43, 3, 1, 'There was a man of the Pharisees, named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews:', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2258~ 4~444~ 5~1537~ 7~5330~, 8~846~ 9~3686~* 10~3530~, 12~758~ 15~2453~:'),
  (19662, 24, 29, 18, 'And I will persecute them with the sword, with the famine, and with the pestilence, and will deliver them to be removed to all the kingdoms of the earth, to be a curse, and an astonishment, and an hissing, and a reproach, among all the nations whither I have driven them:', '3~07291~ 4~0310~ 7~02719~, 10~07458~, 14~01698~, 17~05414~ 21~02189~ 22~02113~* 26~04467~ 29~0776~, 33~0423~, 36~08047~, 39~08322~, 42~02781~, 46~01471~ 50~05080~'),
  (26081, 43, 1, 23, 'He said, I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, Make straight the way of the Lord, as said the prophet Esaias.', '1~5346~, 2~1473~ [3] 5~5456~ 8~994~ 9~1722~ 11~2048~, 13~2116~ 15~3598~ 18~2962~, 19~2531~ 20~2036~ 22~4396~ 23~2268~.'),
  (22898, 38, 1, 11, 'And they answered the angel of the LORD that stood among the myrtle trees, and said, We have walked to and fro through the earth, and, behold, all the earth sitteth still, and is at rest.', '2~06030~ 4~04397~ 7~03068~ 9~05975~ 13~01918~, 15~0559~, 21~01980~ 24~0776~, 29~0776~ 31~03427~, 35~08252~.'),
  (8625, 10, 22, 15, 'And he sent out arrows, and scattered them; lightning, and discomfited them.', '3~07971~ 4~02671~, 6~06327~ 8~01300~, 10~02000~'),
  (10649, 13, 9, 26, 'For these Levites, the four chief porters, were in their set office, and were over the chambers and treasuries of the house of God.', '2~03881~, 4~0702~ 5~01368~ 6~07778~, [9] 11~0530~, 16~03957~ 18~0214~ 21~01004~ 23~0430~.'),
  (11326, 14, 6, 36, 'If they sin against thee, (for there is no man which sinneth not,) and thou be angry with them, and deliver them over before their enemies, and they carry them away captives unto a land far off or near;', '2~02398~ [6 7] 9~0120~ 11~02398~ 16~0599~ 20~05414~ 23~06440~ [24] 25~0341~, 30~07617~ 31~07617~ 34~0776~ 36~07350~ 38~07138~;'),
  (3146, 3, 14, 30, 'And he shall offer the one of the turtledoves, or of the young pigeons, such as he can get;', '3~06213~ 5~0259~ 8~08449~, 12~01121~ 13~03123~, 15~0834~ 18~05381~ 19~03027~;*'),
  (18112, 23, 24, 8, 'The mirth of tabrets ceaseth, the noise of them that rejoice endeth, the joy of the harp ceaseth.', '1~04885~ 3~08596~ 4~07673~, 6~07588~ 10~05947~ 11~02308~, 13~04885~ 16~03658~ 17~07673~.'),
  (3705, 4, 3, 8, 'And they shall keep all the instruments of the tabernacle of the congregation, and the charge of the children of Israel, to do the service of the tabernacle.', '3~08104~ 6~03627~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~, 15~04931~ 18~01121~ 20~03478~, 22~05647~ 24~05656~ 27~04908~.'),
  (1005, 1, 34, 20, 'And Hamor and Shechem his son came unto the gate of their city, and communed with the men of their city, saying,', '1~02544~ 3~07927~ 5~01121~ 6~0935~ 9~08179~ 12~05892~, 14~01696~ 17~0582~ 20~05892~, 21~0559~,'),
  (23259, 40, 5, 15, 'Neither do men light a candle, and put it under a bushel, but on a candlestick; and it giveth light unto all that are in the house.', '0~3761~ 3~2545~ 5~3088~, 6~2532~ 7~5087~ 8~846~ 9~5259~ 11~3426~, 12~235~ 13~1909~ 15~3087~; 16~2532~ 19~2989~ 21~3956~ 24~1722~ 26~3614~.'),
  (11627, 14, 20, 31, 'And Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah: he was thirty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty and five years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.', '&para; 1~03092~ 2~04427~ 4~03063~: [5 6] 7~07970~ 9~02568~ 10~08141~ 11~01121~ 16~04427~, 19~04427~ 20~06242~ 22~02568~ 23~08141~ 25~03389~. 28~0517~ 29~08034~ [30] 31~05806~ 33~01323~ 35~07977~.'),
  (16821, 20, 15, 5, 'A fool despiseth his father''s instruction: but he that regardeth reproof is prudent.', '&para; 1~0191~ 2~05006~ 4~01~ 5~04148~: 9~08104~ 10~08433~ 12~06191~.'),
  (16257, 19, 139, 9, 'If I take the wings of the morning, and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea;', '[0] 2~05375~ 4~03671~ 7~07837~, [8] 9~07931~ 13~0319~ 16~03220~;'),
  (30906, 66, 11, 18, 'And the nations were angry, and thy wrath is come, and the time of the dead, that they should be judged, and that thou shouldest give reward unto thy servants the prophets, and to the saints, and them that fear thy name, small and great; and shouldest destroy them which destroy the earth.', '0~2532~ 2~1484~ 4~3710~, 5~2532~ 6~4675~ 7~3709~ 9~2064~, 10~2532~ 12~2540~ 15~3498~, 20~2919~, 21~2532~ 25~1325~ 26~3408~ 28~4675~ 29~1401~ 31~4396~, 32~2532~ 35~40~, 36~2532~ 39~5399~ 40~4675~ 41~3686~, 42~3398~ 43~2532~ 44~3173~; 45~2532~ 47~1311~ 50~1311~ 52~1093~.'),
  (4215, 4, 16, 16, 'And Moses said unto Korah, Be thou and all thy company before the LORD, thou, and they, and Aaron, to morrow:', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~07141~, 10~05712~ 11~06440~ 13~03068~, 18~0175~, 20~04279~:'),
  (17646, 22, 7, 10, 'I am my beloved''s, and his desire is toward me.', '&para; [1] 3~01730~, 6~08669~ [7]'),
  (25512, 42, 12, 40, 'Be ye therefore ready also: for the Son of man cometh at an hour when ye think not.', '0~1096~ 1~5210~ 2~3767~ 3~2092~ 4~2532~: 5~3739~ 6~3754~ 7~5207~ 9~444~ 10~2064~ 13~5610~ 16~1380~ 17~3756~.'),
  (14144, 19, 18, 17, 'He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me.', '1~05337~ 5~05794~ 6~0341~, 11~08130~ 17~0553~'),
  (16504, 20, 4, 5, 'Get wisdom, get understanding: forget it not; neither decline from the words of my mouth.', '0~07069~ 1~02451~, 2~07069~ 3~0998~: 4~07911~ [5] 8~05186~ 11~0561~ 14~06310~.'),
  (28249, 45, 11, 24, 'For if thou wert cut out of the olive tree which is wild by nature, and wert grafted contrary to nature into a good olive tree: how much more shall these, which be the natural branches, be grafted into their own olive tree?', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 2~4771~ 4~1581~ 6~1537~ 12~65~ 13~2596~ 14~5449~, 15~2532~ 17~1461~ 19~3844~ 20~5449~ 21~1519~ 25~2565~: 27~4214~ 28~3123~ 30~3778~, 34~5449~ [35] 35~2596~, 38~1461~ 40~2398~ 42~1636~?'),
  (21716, 26, 48, 5, 'And by the border of Manasseh, from the east side unto the west side, a portion for Ephraim.', '3~01366~ 5~04519~, 8~06921~ 9~06285~ 12~03220~ 13~06285~, 14~0259~ [15 16] 17~0669~.'),
  (20958, 26, 21, 5, 'That all flesh may know that I the LORD have drawn forth my sword out of his sheath: it shall not return any more.', '2~01320~ 4~03045~ 8~03068~ 11~03318~ 13~02719~ 17~08593~: 21~07725~'),
  (5048, 5, 4, 38, 'To drive out nations from before thee greater and mightier than thou art, to bring thee in, to give thee their land for an inheritance, as it is this day.', '2~03423~ 3~01471~ 5~06440~ 7~01419~ 9~06099~ [12] 14~0935~ 18~05414~ 21~0776~ [22] 24~05159~, [26 27] 29~03117~.'),
  (1333, 1, 44, 4, 'And when they were gone out of the city, and not yet far off, Joseph said unto his steward, Up, follow after the men; and when thou dost overtake them, say unto them, Wherefore have ye rewarded evil for good?', '[0] 5~03318~ 8~05892~, [9] [11] 13~07368~, 14~03130~ 15~0559~ 18~01004~, 19~06965~, 20~07291~ 21~0310~ 23~0582~; 28~05381~ 30~0559~ 36~07999~ 37~07451~ 39~02896~?'),
  (2657, 2, 38, 19, 'And their pillars were four, and their sockets of brass four; their hooks of silver, and the overlaying of their chapiters and their fillets of silver.', '2~05982~ [3] 4~0702~, 7~0134~ [8] 9~05178~ 10~0702~; 12~02053~ [13] 14~03701~, 17~06826~ 20~07218~ 23~02838~ [24] 25~03701~.'),
  (12213, 15, 8, 3, 'Of the sons of Shechaniah, of the sons of Pharosh; Zechariah: and with him were reckoned by genealogy of the males an hundred and fifty.', '2~01121~ 4~07935~, 7~01121~ 9~06551~; 10~02148~: 17~03187~ 20~02145~ 22~03967~ 24~02572~.'),
  (23326, 40, 6, 34, 'Take therefore no thought for the morrow: for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself. Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof.', '0~3309~ 1~3767~ 2~3361~ 3~3309~ 4~1519~ 6~839~: 7~1063~ 9~839~ 12~3309~ 15~3588~ 17~1438~. 18~713~ 21~2250~ [22] 24~2549~ 25~846~.'),
  (18851, 23, 60, 21, 'Thy people also shall be all righteous: they shall inherit the land for ever, the branch of my planting, the work of my hands, that I may be glorified.', '1~05971~ [3 4] 6~06662~: 9~03423~ 11~0776~ 13~05769~, 15~05342~ 18~04302~, 20~04639~ 23~03027~, 28~06286~.'),
  (1925, 2, 14, 31, 'And Israel saw that great work which the LORD did upon the Egyptians: and the people feared the LORD, and believed the LORD, and his servant Moses.', '1~03478~ 2~07200~ 4~01419~ 5~03027~ 8~03068~ 9~06213~ 12~04714~: 15~05971~ 16~03372~ 18~03068~, 20~0539~ 22~03068~, 25~05650~ 26~04872~.'),
  (7646, 9, 17, 21, 'For Israel and the Philistines had put the battle in array, army against army.', '1~03478~ 4~06430~ 10~06186~, 11~04634~ 12~07125~ 13~04634~.'),
  (1302, 1, 43, 7, 'And they said, The man asked us straitly of our state, and of our kindred, saying, Is your father yet alive? have ye another brother? and we told him according to the tenor of these words: could we certainly know that he would say, Bring your brother down?', '2~0559~, 4~0376~ 5~07592~ 7~07592~ 14~04138~, 15~0559~, [16] 18~01~ 20~02416~? 22~03426~ [23] 24~0251~? 27~05046~ 29~05921~ 32~06310~ 35~01697~: 38~03045~ 39~03045~ 43~0559~, 44~03381~ 46~0251~ 47~03381~?'),
  (27967, 45, 1, 21, 'Because that, when they knew God, they glorified him not as God, neither were thankful; but became vain in their imaginations, and their foolish heart was darkened.', '0~1360~ 4~1097~ 5~2316~, 7~1392~ [8] 9~3756~ 10~5613~ 11~2316~, 12~2228~ 14~2168~; 15~235~ 17~3154~ 18~1722~ 19~846~ 20~1261~, 21~2532~ 22~846~ 23~801~ 24~2588~ 26~4654~.'),
  (22211, 28, 8, 8, 'Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a vessel wherein is no pleasure.', '&para; 0~03478~ 3~01104~: 10~01471~ 13~03627~ [15] 17~02656~.'),
  (29057, 47, 12, 19, 'Again, think ye that we excuse ourselves unto you? we speak before God in Christ: but we do all things, dearly beloved, for your edifying.', '0~3825~, 2~1380~ 3~3754~ 6~626~ 8~5213~? 10~2980~ 11~2714~ 12~2316~ 13~1722~ 14~5547~: 15~1161~ [16 17] 19~3956~, 21~27~, 22~5228~ 23~5216~ 24~3619~.'),
  (16377, 19, 147, 17, 'He casteth forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?', '2~07993~ 4~07140~ 6~06595~: 9~05975~ 10~06440~ 12~07135~?'),
  (25491, 42, 12, 19, 'And I will say to my soul, Soul, thou hast much goods laid up for many years; take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry.', '0~2532~ 3~2046~ 5~3450~ 6~5590~, 7~5590~, 9~2192~ 10~4183~ 11~18~ 13~2749~ 14~1519~ 15~4183~ 16~2094~; 19~373~, 20~5315~, 21~4095~, [22] 24~2165~.'),
  (28971, 47, 8, 23, 'Whether any do inquire of Titus, he is my partner and fellowhelper concerning you: or our brethren be inquired of, they are the messengers of the churches, and the glory of Christ.', '0~1535~ [1 3] 4~5228~ 5~5103~, [6 7] 8~1699~ 9~2844~ 10~2532~ 11~4904~ 12~1519~ 13~5209~: 14~1535~ 15~2257~ 16~80~ [17 21] 23~652~ 26~1577~, [27] 29~1391~ 31~5547~.'),
