  (27100, 44, 5, 25, 'Then came one and told them, saying, Behold, the men whom ye put in prison are standing in the temple, and teaching the people.', '1~3854~ 2~5100~ 3~1161~ 4~518~ 5~846~, 6~3004~ 7~3754~,* 8~2400~, 10~435~ 11~3739~ 13~5087~ 14~1722~ 15~5438~ 16~1526~ 17~2476~ 18~1722~ 20~2411~, 21~2532~ 22~1321~ 24~2992~.'),
  (1778, 2, 9, 31, 'And the flax and the barley was smitten: for the barley was in the ear, and the flax was bolled.', '2~06594~ 5~08184~ 7~05221~: 10~08184~ [11] 14~024~, 17~06594~ [18] 19~01392~.'),
  (24520, 41, 8, 9, 'And they that had eaten were about four thousand: and he sent them away.', '0~1161~ 4~5315~ 5~2258~ 6~5613~ 8~5070~: 9~2532~ 11~630~ 12~846~ 13~630~.'),
  (20307, 24, 52, 22, 'And a chapiter of brass was upon it; and the height of one chapiter was five cubits, with network and pomegranates upon the chapiters round about, all of brass. The second pillar also and the pomegranates were like unto these.', '2~03805~ 4~05178~ [5] 10~06967~ 12~0259~ 13~03805~ [14] 15~02568~ 16~0520~, 18~07639~ 20~07416~ 23~03805~ 25~05439~, [27] 28~05178~. 30~08145~ 31~05982~ 35~07416~ [36]'),
  (2170, 2, 23, 21, 'Beware of him, and obey his voice, provoke him not; for he will not pardon your transgressions: for my name is in him.', '0~08104~ 1~06440~ 4~08085~ 6~06963~, 7~04843~ 14~05375~ 16~06588~: 19~08034~ [20] 22~07130~.'),
  (2321, 2, 28, 23, 'And thou shalt make upon the breastplate two rings of gold, and shalt put the two rings on the two ends of the breastplate.', '3~06213~ 6~02833~ 7~08147~ 8~02885~ 10~02091~, 13~05414~ 15~08147~ 16~02885~ 19~08147~ 20~07098~ 23~02833~.'),
  (4394, 4, 22, 14, 'And the princes of Moab rose up, and they went unto Balak, and said, Balaam refuseth to come with us.', '2~08269~ 4~04124~ 6~06965~, 9~0935~ 11~01111~, 13~0559~, 14~01109~ 15~03985~ 17~01980~'),
  (25509, 42, 12, 37, 'Blessed are those servants, whom the lord when he cometh shall find watching: verily I say unto you, that he shall gird himself, and make them to sit down to meat, and will come forth and serve them.', '0~3107~ [1] 2~1565~ 3~1401~, 4~3739~ 6~2962~ 9~2064~ 11~2147~ 12~1127~: 13~281~ 15~3004~ 17~5213~, 18~3754~ 22~4024~, 23~2532~ 24~347~ 25~846~ 30~347~, 31~2532~ 34~3928~ 36~1247~ 37~846~.'),
  (1620, 2, 4, 14, 'And the anger of the LORD was kindled against Moses, and he said, Is not Aaron the Levite thy brother? I know that he can speak well. And also, behold, he cometh forth to meet thee: and when he seeth thee, he will be glad in his heart.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~04872~, 12~0559~, [13] 15~0175~ 17~03881~ 19~0251~? 21~03045~ 25~01696~ 26~01696~. 32~03318~ 34~07125~ 39~07200~ 44~08055~ 47~03820~.'),
  (30304, 59, 1, 22, 'But be ye doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.', '0~1161~ 2~1096~ 3~4163~ 6~3056~, 7~2532~ 8~3361~ 9~202~ 10~3440~, 11~3884~ 14~1438~.'),
  (13842, 18, 38, 40, 'When they couch in their dens, and abide in the covert to lie in wait?', '2~07817~ [4] 5~04585~, [6] 7~03427~ 10~05521~ 11~03926~ 14~0695~?'),
  (19762, 24, 32, 22, 'And hast given them this land, which thou didst swear to their fathers to give them, a land flowing with milk and honey;', '2~05414~ 5~0776~, 9~07650~ 12~01~ 14~05414~ 17~0776~ 18~02100~ 20~02461~ 22~01706~;'),
  (30416, 60, 2, 1, 'Wherefore laying aside all malice, and all guile, and hypocrisies, and envies, and all evil speakings,', '&para; 0~3767~ 2~659~ 3~3956~ 4~2549~, 5~2532~ 6~3956~ 7~1388~, 8~2532~ 9~5272~, 10~2532~ 11~5355~, 12~2532~ 13~3956~ 15~2636~,'),
  (8571, 10, 20, 9, 'And Joab said to Amasa, Art thou in health, my brother? And Joab took Amasa by the beard with the right hand to kiss him.', '1~03097~ 2~0559~ 4~06021~, [5] 8~07965~, 10~0251~? 12~03097~ 13~0270~ 14~06021~ 17~02206~ 20~03225~ 21~03027~ 23~05401~'),
  (27022, 44, 3, 10, 'And they knew that it was he which sat for alms at the Beautiful gate of the temple: and they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened unto him.', '0~5037~ 2~1921~ 3~3754~ 4~846~ 5~2258~ 6~3778~ 7~3588~ 8~2521~ 9~4314~ 10~1654~ 11~1909~ 13~5611~ 14~4439~ 17~2411~: 18~2532~ 21~4130~ 23~2285~ 24~2532~ 25~1611~ 26~1909~ 30~4819~ 32~846~.'),
  (30559, 62, 1, 3, 'That which we have seen and heard declare we unto you, that ye also may have fellowship with us: and truly our fellowship is with the Father, and with his Son Jesus Christ.', '1~3739~ 4~3708~ 5~2532~ 6~191~ 7~518~ 10~5213~, 11~2443~ 12~5210~ 13~2532~ 15~2192~ 16~2842~ 17~3326~ 18~2257~: 19~2532~ 21~2251~ 22~2842~ 23~1161~* [24] 25~3326~ 27~3962~, 28~2532~ 29~3326~ 30~846~ 31~5207~ 32~2424~ 33~5547~.'),
  (1823, 2, 12, 2, 'This month shall be unto you the beginning of months: it shall be the first month of the year to you.', '1~02320~ [2 3] 7~07218~ 9~02320~: [11 12] 14~07223~ 15~02320~ 18~08141~'),
  (26689, 43, 14, 6, 'Jesus saith unto him, I am the way, the truth, and the life: no man cometh unto the Father, but by me.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1473~ 5~1510~ 7~3598~ 8~2532~,* 10~225~, 11~2532~ 13~2222~: 15~3762~ 16~2064~ 17~4314~ 19~3962~, 20~1508~ 21~1223~ 22~1700~.'),
  (6495, 6, 24, 12, 'And I sent the hornet before you, which drave them out from before you, even the two kings of the Amorites; but not with thy sword, nor with thy bow.', '2~07971~ 4~06880~ 5~06440~ 10~01644~ 12~06440~ [14] 16~08147~ 17~04428~ 20~0567~; [21] 25~02719~, 29~07198~.'),
  (3509, 3, 25, 35, 'And if thy brother be waxen poor, and fallen in decay with thee; then thou shalt relieve him: yea, though he be a stranger, or a sojourner; that he may live with thee.', '3~0251~ 6~04134~, 10~04131~ 12~03027~; 16~02388~ [18 21] 23~01616~, 26~08453~; 30~02416~'),
  (17833, 23, 8, 17, 'And I will wait upon the LORD, that hideth his face from the house of Jacob, and I will look for him.', '3~02442~ 6~03068~, 8~05641~ 10~06440~ 13~01004~ 15~03290~, 19~06960~'),
  (15420, 19, 91, 16, 'With long life will I satisfy him, and shew him my salvation.', '1~0753~ 2~03117~ 5~07646~ 8~07200~ 11~03444~.'),
  (16794, 20, 14, 13, 'Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth is heaviness.', '&para; 2~07814~ 4~03820~ 6~03510~; 9~0319~ 12~08057~ [13] 14~08424~.'),
  (26498, 43, 10, 2, 'But he that entereth in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.', '0~1161~ 4~1525~ 5~1223~ 7~2374~ 8~2076~ 10~4166~ 13~4263~.'),
  (4462, 4, 24, 11, 'Therefore now flee thou to thy place: I thought to promote thee unto great honour; but, lo, the LORD hath kept thee back from honour.', '2~01272~ 6~04725~: 8~0559~ 10~03513~ 13~03513~ 14~03513~; 18~03068~ 22~04513~ 24~03519~.'),
  (2793, 3, 3, 10, 'And the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon them, which is by the flanks, and the caul above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away.', '2~08147~ 3~03629~, 6~02459~ [8] [12] 15~03689~, 18~03508~ 21~03516~, 24~03629~, 29~05493~.'),
  (20433, 25, 4, 4, 'The tongue of the sucking child cleaveth to the roof of his mouth for thirst: the young children ask bread, and no man breaketh it unto them.', '1~03956~ 5~03243~ 6~01692~ 12~02441~ 14~06772~: 17~05768~ 18~07592~ 19~03899~, [20] 23~06566~ [24]'),
  (13657, 18, 32, 20, 'I will speak, that I may be refreshed: I will open my lips and answer.', '2~01696~, 7~07304~: 10~06605~ 12~08193~ 14~06030~.'),
