  (29723, 54, 1, 11, 'According to the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which was committed to my trust.', '0~2596~ 3~1391~ 4~2098~ 7~3107~ 8~2316~, 9~3739~ 12~4100~ 13~1473~ 14~4100~.'),
  (24359, 41, 4, 26, 'And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man should cast seed into the ground;', '0~2532~ 2~3004~, 3~3779~ 4~2076~ 6~932~ 8~2316~, 9~5613~ 10~1437~ 12~444~ 14~906~ 15~4703~ 16~1909~ 18~1093~;'),
  (28309, 45, 14, 13, 'Let us not therefore judge one another any more: but judge this rather, that no man put a stumblingblock or an occasion to fall in his brother''s way.', '1~2919~ 3~3767~ 4~2919~ 6~240~ 8~3371~: 9~235~ 10~2919~ 11~5124~ 12~3123~, 15~3361~ 16~5087~ 18~4348~ 19~2228~ 23~4625~ [25] 27~80~.'),
  (17529, 21, 11, 7, 'Truly the light is sweet, and a pleasant thing it is for the eyes to behold the sun:', '&para; 2~0216~ [3] 4~04966~, 7~02896~ [8 10] 13~05869~ 15~07200~ 17~08121~:'),
  (14735, 19, 54, 1, 'To the chief Musician on Neginoth, Maschil, A Psalm of David, when the Ziphims came and said to Saul, Doth not David hide himself with us? Save me, O God, by thy name, and judge me by thy strength.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~05058~, 6~04905~, [7 8] 10~01732~, 13~02130~ 14~0935~ 16~0559~ 18~07586~, 21~01732~ 22~05641~ 25] 26~03467~ 29~0430~, 32~08034~, 34~01777~ 38~01369~.'),
  (8637, 10, 22, 27, 'With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself unsavoury.', '2~01305~ 7~01305~; 11~06141~ 16~06617~.'),
  (19889, 24, 37, 6, 'Then came the word of the LORD unto the prophet Jeremiah, saying,', '3~01697~ 6~03068~ 9~05030~ 10~03414~, 11~0559~,'),
