VALUES
  (29516, 51, 2, 6, 'As ye have therefore received Christ Jesus the Lord, so walk ye in him:', '0~5613~ 2~3880~ 3~3767~ 4~3880~ 5~5547~ 6~2424~ 8~2962~, [9] 11~4043~ 12~1722~ 13~846~:'),
  (10349, 13, 2, 35, 'And Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant to wife; and she bare him Attai.', '1~08348~ 2~05414~ 4~01323~ 6~03398~ 8~05650~ 10~0802~; 13~03205~ 15~06262~.'),
  (18020, 23, 19, 7, 'The paper reeds by the brooks, by the mouth of the brooks, and every thing sown by the brooks, shall wither, be driven away, and be no more.', '2~06169~ 5~02975~, 8~06310~ 11~02975~, 15~04218~ 18~02975~, 20~03001~, 23~05086~, [27]'),
  (24232, 41, 1, 7, 'And preached, saying, There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.', '0~2532~ 1~2784~, 2~3004~, 4~2064~ 7~2478~ 8~3450~ 9~3694~ 10~3450~, 12~2438~ 14~3739~ 15~5266~ 16~846~ 17~1510~ 18~3756~ 19~2425~ 22~2955~ 24~3089~.'),
  (23735, 40, 17, 25, 'He saith, Yes. And when he was come into the house, Jesus prevented him, saying, What thinkest thou, Simon? of whom do the kings of the earth take custom or tribute? of their own children, or of strangers?', '1~3004~, 2~3483~. 3~2532~ 4~3753~ 7~1525~ 8~1519~ 10~3614~, 11~2424~ 12~4399~ 13~846~, 14~3004~, 15~5101~ 16~1380~ 17~4671~, 18~4613~? 19~575~ 20~5101~ 21~2983~ 23~935~ 26~1093~ 27~2983~ 28~5056~ 29~2228~ 30~2778~? 31~575~ 33~846~ 34~5207~, 35~2228~ 36~575~ 37~245~?'),
  (12550, 16, 9, 30, 'Yet many years didst thou forbear them, and testifiedst against them by thy spirit in thy prophets: yet would they not give ear: therefore gavest thou them into the hand of the people of the lands.', '1~07227~ 2~08141~ 5~04900~ 8~05749~ 13~07307~ 14~03027~ 16~05030~: 22~0238~: 24~05414~ 29~03027~ 32~05971~ 35~0776~.'),
  (19413, 24, 18, 20, 'Shall evil be recompensed for good? for they have digged a pit for my soul. Remember that I stood before thee to speak good for them, and to turn away thy wrath from them.', '1~07451~ 3~07999~ 5~02896~? 9~03738~ 11~07745~ 14~05315~. 15~02142~ 18~05975~ 19~06440~ 22~01696~ 23~02896~ [26] 29~07725~ 31~02534~'),
  (8919, 11, 6, 15, 'And he built the walls of the house within with boards of cedar, both the floor of the house, and the walls of the ceiling: and he covered them on the inside with wood, and covered the floor of the house with planks of fir.', '&para; 2~01129~ 4~07023~ 7~01004~ 8~01004~ 10~06763~ 12~0730~, 15~07172~ 18~01004~, 21~07023~ 24~05604~: [25] 27~06823~ [28] 31~01004~ 33~06086~, 35~06823~ 37~07172~ 40~01004~ 42~06763~ 44~01265~.'),
  (27345, 44, 11, 22, 'Then tidings of these things came unto the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem: and they sent forth Barnabas, that he should go as far as Antioch.', '0~1161~ 1~3056~ 2~4012~ 4~846~ 5~191~ 6~1519~ 8~3775~ 11~1577~ 12~3588~ 14~1722~ 15~2414~: 16~2532~ 19~1821~ 20~921~, 24~1330~ 27~2193~ 28~490~.'),
  (30839, 66, 7, 13, 'And one of the elders answered, saying unto me, What are these which are arrayed in white robes? and whence came they?', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~1520~ 2~1537~ 4~4245~ 5~611~, 6~3004~ 8~3427~, 9~5101~ 10~1526~ 11~3778~ 12~3588~ 15~4016~ 16~3022~ 17~4749~? 18~2532~ 19~4159~ 21~2064~?'),
  (19265, 24, 12, 7, 'I have forsaken mine house, I have left mine heritage; I have given the dearly beloved of my soul into the hand of her enemies.', '&para; 2~05800~ 4~01004~, 7~05203~ 9~05159~; 12~05414~ 15~03033~ 18~05315~ 21~03709~ 24~0341~.'),
  (20302, 24, 52, 17, 'Also the pillars of brass that were in the house of the LORD, and the bases, and the brazen sea that was in the house of the LORD, the Chaldeans brake, and carried all the brass of them to Babylon.', '2~05982~ 4~05178~ [6] 9~01004~ 12~03068~, 15~04350~, 18~05178~ 19~03220~ [21] 24~01004~ 27~03068~, 29~03778~ 30~07665~, 32~05375~ 35~05178~ 39~0894~.'),
  (21822, 27, 3, 6, 'And whoso falleth not down and worshippeth shall the same hour be cast into the midst of a burning fiery furnace.', '1~04479~ 2~05308~ 3~03809~ 4~05308~ 6~05457~ 10~08160~ 12~07412~ 15~01459~ 18~03345~ 19~05135~ 20~0861~.'),
  (30899, 66, 11, 11, 'And after three days and an half the Spirit of life from God entered into them, and they stood upon their feet; and great fear fell upon them which saw them.', '0~2532~ 1~3326~ 2~5140~ 3~2250~ 4~2532~ 6~2255~ 8~4151~ 10~2222~ 11~1537~ 12~2316~ 13~1525~ 14~1909~ 15~846~, 16~2532~ 18~2476~ 19~1909~ 20~846~ 21~4228~; 22~2532~ 23~3173~ 24~5401~ 25~4098~ 26~1909~ 29~2334~ 30~846~.'),
  (5156, 5, 8, 13, 'And when thy herds and thy flocks multiply, and thy silver and thy gold is multiplied, and all that thou hast is multiplied;', '[1] 3~01241~ 6~06629~ 7~07235~, 10~03701~ 13~02091~ 15~07235~, 22~07235~;'),
  (12288, 15, 10, 27, 'And of the sons of Zattu; Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, and Jeremoth, and Zabad, and Aziza.', '3~01121~ 5~02240~; 6~0454~, 7~0475~, 8~04983~, 10~03406~, 12~02066~, 14~05819~.'),
  (4603, 4, 28, 20, 'And their meat offering shall be of flour mingled with oil: three tenth deals shall ye offer for a bullock, and two tenth deals for a ram;', '3~04503~ [4 6] 7~05560~ 8~01101~ 10~08081~: 11~07969~ 13~06241~ 16~06213~ 19~06499~, 21~08147~ 23~06241~ 26~0352~;'),
  (256, 1, 10, 21, 'Unto Shem also, the father of all the children of Eber, the brother of Japheth the elder, even to him were children born.', '&para; 1~08035~ 4~01~ 8~01121~ 10~05677~, 12~0251~ 14~03315~ 16~01419~, [21] 22~03205~.'),
  (18444, 23, 40, 15, 'Behold, the nations are as a drop of a bucket, and are counted as the small dust of the balance: behold, he taketh up the isles as a very little thing.', '2~01471~ [3] 6~04752~ 9~01805~, 12~02803~ 16~07834~ 19~03976~: 23~05190~ 25~0339~ 30~01851~.'),
  (4273, 4, 18, 11, 'And this is thine; the heave offering of their gift, with all the wave offerings of the children of Israel: I have given them unto thee, and to thy sons and to thy daughters with thee, by a statute for ever: every one that is clean in thy house shall eat of it.', '[2] 6~08641~ 9~04976~, 14~08573~ 17~01121~ 19~03478~: 22~05414~ 29~01121~ 33~01323~ 38~02706~ 40~05769~: 45~02889~ 48~01004~ 50~0398~'),
  (1582, 2, 2, 23, 'And it came to pass in process of time, that the king of Egypt died: and the children of Israel sighed by reason of the bondage, and they cried, and their cry came up unto God by reason of the bondage.', '&para; 6~07227~ 7~01992~ 8~03117~, 11~04428~ 13~04714~ 14~04191~: 17~01121~ 19~03478~ 20~0584~ 23~04480~ 25~05656~, 28~02199~, 31~07775~ 33~05927~ 35~0430~ 40~05656~.'),
  (16255, 19, 139, 7, 'Whither shall I go from thy spirit? or whither shall I flee from thy presence?', '&para; 3~03212~ 6~07307~? 11~01272~ 14~06440~?'),
  (13858, 18, 39, 15, 'And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.', '1~07911~ 4~07272~ 6~02115~ 11~07704~ 12~02416~ 14~01758~'),
  (17370, 21, 3, 2, 'A time to be born, and a time to die; a time to plant, and a time to pluck up that which is planted;', '1~06256~ 4~03205~, 7~06256~ 9~04191~; 11~06256~ 13~05193~, 16~06256~ 19~06131~ [20 22] 23~05193~;'),
  (30219, 58, 11, 31, 'By faith the harlot Rahab perished not with them that believed not, when she had received the spies with peace.', '1~4102~ 3~4204~ 4~4460~ 5~4881~ 6~3756~ 11~544~, 15~1209~ 17~2685~ 18~3326~ 19~1515~.'),
  (22847, 36, 3, 18, 'I will gather them that are sorrowful for the solemn assembly, who are of thee, to whom the reproach of it was a burden.', '2~0622~ [3 5] 6~03013~ 10~04150~, [11] [15 16] 18~02781~ [21] 23~04864~.'),
  (5073, 5, 5, 14, 'But the seventh day is the sabbath of the LORD thy God: in it thou shalt not do any work, thou, nor thy son, nor thy daughter, nor thy manservant, nor thy maidservant, nor thine ox, nor thine ass, nor any of thy cattle, nor thy stranger that is within thy gates; that thy manservant and thy maidservant may rest as well as thou.', '2~07637~ 3~03117~ [4] 6~07676~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~: [12 13] 17~06213~ 19~04399~, 23~01121~, 26~01323~, 29~05650~, 32~0519~, 35~07794~, 38~02543~, 43~0929~, 46~01616~ [48] 51~08179~; 54~05650~ 57~0519~ 59~05117~'),
  (24326, 41, 3, 28, 'Verily I say unto you, All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme:', '0~281~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~ 5~3754~,* 6~3956~ 7~265~ 10~863~ 13~5207~ 15~444~, 16~2532~ 17~988~ 18~3745~ 19~302~ 22~987~:'),
  (28248, 45, 11, 23, 'And they also, if they abide not still in unbelief, shall be grafted in: for God is able to graft them in again.', '0~1161~ 1~1565~ 2~2532~, 3~3362~ 5~1961~ 6~3362~ 9~570~, 13~1461~: 14~1063~ 15~2316~ 16~2076~ 17~1415~ 19~1461~ 20~846~ 21~1461~ 22~3825~.'),
  (19132, 24, 7, 4, 'Trust ye not in lying words, saying, The temple of the LORD, The temple of the LORD, The temple of the LORD, are these.', '0~0982~ 4~08267~ 5~01697~, 6~0559~, 8~01964~ 11~03068~, 13~01964~ 16~03068~, 18~01964~ 21~03068~, [22]'),
  (11691, 14, 24, 5, 'And he gathered together the priests and the Levites, and said to them, Go out unto the cities of Judah, and gather of all Israel money to repair the house of your God from year to year, and see that ye hasten the matter. Howbeit the Levites hastened it not.', '3~06908~ 5~03548~ 8~03881~, 10~0559~ 14~03318~ 17~05892~ 19~03063~, 21~06908~ 24~03478~ 25~03701~ 27~02388~ 29~01004~ 32~0430~ 33~01767~ 34~08141~ 36~08141~, 41~04116~ 43~01697~. 46~03881~ 47~04116~ [48]'),
  (25739, 42, 18, 37, 'And they told him, that Jesus of Nazareth passeth by.', '0~1161~ 2~518~ 3~846~, 4~3754~ 5~2424~ 7~3480~ 9~3928~.'),
  (18908, 23, 65, 2, 'I have spread out my hands all the day unto a rebellious people, which walketh in a way that was not good, after their own thoughts;', '3~06566~ 5~03027~ 8~03117~ 11~05637~ 12~05971~, 14~01980~ 17~01870~ [18 19] 21~02896~, 22~0310~ 25~04284~;'),
  (9831, 12, 10, 30, 'And the LORD said unto Jehu, Because thou hast done well in executing that which is right in mine eyes, and hast done unto the house of Ahab according to all that was in mine heart, thy children of the fourth generation shall sit on the throne of Israel.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~03058~, 10~02895~ 12~06213~ [13 15] 16~03477~ 19~05869~, [20] 22~06213~ 25~01004~ 27~0256~ [32] 35~03824~, 37~01121~ 40~07243~ [41] 43~03427~ 46~03678~ 48~03478~.'),
  (24242, 41, 1, 17, 'And Jesus said unto them, Come ye after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 6~1205~ 7~3694~ 8~3450~, 9~2532~ 12~4160~ 13~5209~ 15~1096~ 16~231~ 18~444~.'),
  (15966, 19, 119, 59, 'I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.', '&para; 1~02803~ 4~01870~, 6~07725~ 8~07272~ 11~05713~.'),
  (21260, 26, 32, 3, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; I will therefore spread out my net over thee with a company of many people; and they shall bring thee up in my net.', '1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 9~06566~ 11~07568~ 16~06951~ 18~07227~ 19~05971~; 25~05927~ 28~02764~.'),
  (9256, 11, 14, 30, 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all their days.', '3~04421~ 5~07346~ 7~03379~ [9] 10~03117~.'),
  (502, 1, 20, 3, 'But God came to Abimelech in a dream by night, and said to him, Behold, thou art but a dead man, for the woman which thou hast taken; for she is a man''s wife.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0935~ 4~040~ 7~02472~ 9~03915~, 11~0559~ [16 17] 20~04191~, 23~0802~ 27~03947~; [30] 32~01167~ 33~01166~.'),
  (15832, 19, 114, 1, 'When Israel went out of Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of strange language;', '&para; 1~03478~ 3~03318~ 5~04714~, 7~01004~ 9~03290~ 12~05971~ 15~03937~;'),
  (7186, 8, 3, 7, 'And when Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was merry, he went to lie down at the end of the heap of corn: and she came softly, and uncovered his feet, and laid her down.', '2~01162~ 4~0398~ 6~08354~, 9~03820~ 11~03190~, 13~0935~ 16~07901~ 19~07097~ 24~06194~: 27~0935~ 28~03909~, 30~01540~ 32~04772~, 36~07901~.'),
  (28878, 47, 4, 3, 'But if our gospel be hid, it is hid to them that are lost:', '0~1161~ 1~1499~ 2~2257~ 3~2098~ 4~2076~ 5~2572~, 7~2076~ 8~2572~ 9~1722~ 13~622~:'),
  (11904, 14, 32, 20, 'And for this cause Hezekiah the king, and the prophet Isaiah the son of Amoz, prayed and cried to heaven.', '[3] 4~03169~ 6~04428~, 9~05030~ 10~03470~ 12~01121~ 14~0531~, 15~06419~ 17~02199~ 19~08064~.'),
  (543, 1, 21, 26, 'And Abimelech said, I wot not who hath done this thing: neither didst thou tell me, neither yet heard I of it, but to day.', '1~040~ 2~0559~, 4~03045~ 8~06213~ 10~01697~: 11~03808~ 14~05046~ 16~03808~ 18~08085~ [20 21] 22~01115~ 24~03117~.'),
  (7434, 9, 10, 9, 'And it was so, that when he had turned his back to go from Samuel, God gave him another heart: and all those signs came to pass that day.', '&para; [3] 8~06437~ 10~07926~ 12~03212~ 14~08050~, 15~0430~ 16~02015~ 18~0312~ 19~03820~: 23~0226~ 24~0935~ 28~03117~.'),
  (28880, 47, 4, 5, 'For we preach not ourselves, but Christ Jesus the Lord; and ourselves your servants for Jesus'' sake.', '0~1063~ 2~2784~ 3~3756~ 4~1438~, 5~235~ 6~5547~ 7~2424~ 9~2962~; 10~1161~ 11~1438~ 12~5216~ 13~1401~ 14~1223~ 15~2424~ 16~1223~.'),
  (7624, 9, 16, 22, 'And Saul sent to Jesse, saying, Let David, I pray thee, stand before me; for he hath found favour in my sight.', '1~07586~ 2~07971~ 4~03448~, 5~0559~, 7~01732~, 11~05975~ 12~06440~ 17~04672~ 18~02580~ 21~05869~.'),
  (23137, 39, 3, 7, 'Even from the days of your fathers ye are gone away from mine ordinances, and have not kept them. Return unto me, and I will return unto you, saith the LORD of hosts. But ye said, Wherein shall we return?', '&para; 3~03117~ 6~01~ 10~05493~ 13~02706~, 17~08104~ [18] 19~07725~ 25~07725~ 28~0559~ 30~03068~ 32~06635~. 35~0559~, 39~07725~?'),
  (27506, 44, 16, 7, 'After they were come to Mysia, they assayed to go into Bithynia: but the Spirit suffered them not.', '3~2064~ 4~2596~ 5~3465~, 7~3985~ 9~4198~ 10~2596~ 11~978~: 12~2532~ 14~4151~ 15~1439~ 16~846~ 17~3756~.'),
  (1128, 1, 38, 4, 'And she conceived again, and bare a son; and she called his name Onan.', '2~02029~ 5~03205~ 7~01121~; 10~07121~ 12~08034~ 13~0209~.'),
  (11001, 13, 23, 10, 'And the sons of Shimei were, Jahath, Zina, and Jeush, and Beriah. These four were the sons of Shimei.', '2~01121~ 4~08096~ [5] 6~03189~, 7~02126~, 9~03266~, 11~01283~. 13~0702~ [14] 16~01121~ 18~08096~.'),
  (18218, 23, 29, 16, 'Surely your turning of things upside down shall be esteemed as the potter''s clay: for shall the work say of him that made it, He made me not? or shall the thing framed say of him that framed it, He had no understanding?', '6~02017~ 9~02803~ 12~03335~ 13~02563~: 17~04639~ 18~0559~ 22~06213~ 25~06213~ 32~03336~ 33~0559~ 37~03335~ 42~0995~?'),
  (7356, 9, 6, 18, 'And the golden mice, according to the number of all the cities of the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both of fenced cities, and of country villages, even unto the great stone of Abel, whereon they set down the ark of the LORD: which stone remaineth unto this day in the field of Joshua, the Bethshemite.', '2~02091~ 3~05909~, [4 5] 7~04557~ 11~05892~ 14~06430~ [15] 18~02568~ 19~05633~, [20] 22~04013~ 23~05892~, 26~06521~ 27~03724~, 31~01419~ [32 33] 34~059~, 38~03240~ 40~0727~ 43~03068~: [44 46] 49~03117~ 52~07704~ 54~03091~, 56~01030~.'),
  (1964, 2, 16, 12, 'I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel: speak unto them, saying, At even ye shall eat flesh, and in the morning ye shall be filled with bread; and ye shall know that I am the LORD your God.', '2~08085~ 4~08519~ 7~01121~ 9~03478~: 10~01696~ 13~0559~, 15~06153~ 16~0996~ 18~0398~ 19~01320~, 23~01242~ 27~07646~ 29~03899~; 33~03045~ [36] 38~03068~ 40~0430~.'),
  (27751, 44, 23, 1, 'And Paul, earnestly beholding the council, said, Men and brethren, I have lived in all good conscience before God until this day.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3972~, 3~816~ 5~4892~, 6~2036~, 7~435~ [8] 9~80~, 10~1473~ 12~4176~ 14~3956~ 15~18~ 16~4893~ 18~2316~ 19~891~ 20~5026~ 21~2250~.'),
  (14715, 19, 51, 15, 'O Lord, open thou my lips; and my mouth shall shew forth thy praise.', '1~0136~, 2~06605~ 5~08193~; 8~06310~ 11~05046~ 13~08416~.'),
  (7246, 9, 1, 27, 'For this child I prayed; and the LORD hath given me my petition which I asked of him:', '2~05288~ 4~06419~; 7~03068~ 9~05414~ 12~07596~ 15~07592~'),
  (5824, 5, 33, 8, 'And of Levi he said, Let thy Thummim and thy Urim be with thy holy one, whom thou didst prove at Massah, and with whom thou didst strive at the waters of Meribah;', '&para; 2~03878~ 4~0559~, [5] 7~08550~ 10~0224~ [11] 14~02623~ 15~0376~, 19~05254~ 21~04532~, [22 23] 27~07378~ 30~04325~ 32~04809~;'),
  (16137, 19, 128, 2, 'For thou shalt eat the labour of thine hands: happy shalt thou be, and it shall be well with thee.', '3~0398~ 5~03018~ 8~03709~: 9~0835~ [10] [12] [14 16] 17~02896~'),
  (11078, 13, 25, 24, 'The seventeenth to Joshbekashah, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~06240~ 2~07651~ 3~03436~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (23028, 38, 10, 3, 'Mine anger was kindled against the shepherds, and I punished the goats: for the LORD of hosts hath visited his flock the house of Judah, and hath made them as his goodly horse in the battle.', '1~0639~ 3~02734~ 6~07462~, 9~06485~ 11~06260~: 14~03068~ 16~06635~ 18~06485~ 20~05739~ 22~01004~ 24~03063~, 27~07760~ 31~01935~ 32~05483~ 35~04421~.'),
  (1346, 1, 44, 17, 'And he said, God forbid that I should do so: but the man in whose hand the cup is found, he shall be my servant; and as for you, get you up in peace unto your father.', '2~0559~, 4~02486~ 8~06213~ 9~02063~: [10] 12~0376~ 15~03027~ 17~01375~ 19~04672~, 24~05650~; 31~05927~ 33~07965~ 36~01~.'),
  (14300, 19, 27, 6, 'And now shall mine head be lifted up above mine enemies round about me: therefore will I offer in his tabernacle sacrifices of joy; I will sing, yea, I will sing praises unto the LORD.', '4~07218~ 7~07311~ 10~0341~ 12~05439~ 17~02076~ 20~0168~ 21~02077~ 23~08643~; 26~07891~, 31~02167~ 34~03068~.'),
  (8171, 10, 6, 7, 'And the anger of the LORD was kindled against Uzzah; and God smote him there for his error; and there he died by the ark of God.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~05798~; 11~0430~ 12~05221~ [16] 17~07944~; 21~04191~ 24~0727~ 26~0430~.'),
  (6679, 7, 6, 18, 'Depart not hence, I pray thee, until I come unto thee, and bring forth my present, and set it before thee. And he said, I will tarry until thou come again.', '0~04185~ 8~0935~ 13~03318~ 15~04503~, 17~03240~ [18] 19~06440~ 23~0559~, 26~03427~ 30~07725~.'),
  (25500, 42, 12, 28, 'If then God so clothe the grass, which is to day in the field, and to morrow is cast into the oven; how much more will he clothe you, O ye of little faith?', '0~1487~ 1~1161~ 2~2316~ 3~3779~ 4~294~ 6~5528~, 7~5607~ 10~4594~ 11~1722~ 13~68~, 14~2532~ 16~839~ 18~906~ 19~1519~ 21~2823~; 23~4214~ 24~3123~ [25 27] 28~5209~, 33~3640~?'),
  (2931, 3, 8, 9, 'And he put the mitre upon his head; also upon the mitre, even upon his forefront, did he put the golden plate, the holy crown; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '2~07760~ 4~04701~ 7~07218~; 11~04701~, [12] 15~04136~ 16~06440~,* 19~07760~ 21~02091~ 22~06731~, 24~06944~ 25~05145~; 28~03068~ 29~06680~ 30~04872~.'),
  (22949, 38, 5, 4, 'I will bring it forth, saith the LORD of hosts, and it shall enter into the house of the thief, and into the house of him that sweareth falsely by my name: and it shall remain in the midst of his house, and shall consume it with the timber thereof and the stones thereof.', '4~03318~, 5~05002~ 7~03068~ 9~06635~, 13~0935~ 16~01004~ 19~01590~, 23~01004~ 27~07650~ 28~08267~ 31~08034~: 35~03885~ 38~08432~ 41~01004~, 44~03615~ 48~06086~ 52~068~'),
  (10036, 12, 18, 4, 'He removed the high places, and brake the images, and cut down the groves, and brake in pieces the brazen serpent that Moses had made: for unto those days the children of Israel did burn incense to it: and he called it Nehushtan.', '1~05493~ 4~01116~, 6~07665~ 8~04676~, 11~03772~ 13~0842~, 17~03807~ 19~05178~ 20~05175~ 22~04872~ 24~06213~: 28~03117~ 30~01121~ 32~03478~ 35~06999~ 40~07121~ 42~05180~.'),
  (12374, 16, 4, 6, 'So built we the wall; and all the wall was joined together unto the half thereof: for the people had a mind to work.', '1~01129~ 4~02346~; 8~02346~ 11~07194~ 14~02677~ 18~05971~ 21~03820~ 23~06213~.'),
  (1676, 2, 6, 16, 'And these are the names of the sons of Levi according to their generations; Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari: and the years of the life of Levi were an hundred thirty and seven years.', '[2] 4~08034~ 7~01121~ 9~03878~ 13~08435~; 14~01648~, 16~06955~, 18~04847~: 21~08141~ 24~02416~ 26~03878~ [27] 29~03967~ 30~07970~ 32~07651~ 33~08141~.'),
  (2567, 2, 35, 31, 'And he hath filled him with the spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding, and in knowledge, and in all manner of workmanship;', '3~04390~ 7~07307~ 9~0430~, 11~02451~, 13~08394~, 16~01847~, 22~04399~;'),
  (28269, 45, 12, 8, 'Or he that exhorteth, on exhortation: he that giveth, let him do it with simplicity; he that ruleth, with diligence; he that sheweth mercy, with cheerfulness.', '0~1535~ 3~3870~, 4~1722~ 5~3874~: 8~3330~, [9 12] 13~1722~ 14~572~; 17~4291~, 18~1722~ 19~4710~; 23~1653~, 24~1722~ 25~2432~.'),
  (14277, 19, 25, 17, 'The troubles of my heart are enlarged: O bring thou me out of my distresses.', '1~06869~ 4~03824~ 6~07337~: [7] 11~03318~ 14~04691~.'),
  (18898, 23, 64, 4, 'For since the beginning of the world men have not heard, nor perceived by the ear, neither hath the eye seen, O God, beside thee, what he hath prepared for him that waiteth for him.', '6~05769~ [7] 10~08085~, 15~0238~, 19~05869~ 20~07200~, 22~0430~, 23~02108~ [25] 28~06213~ 32~02442~'),
  (816, 1, 29, 17, 'Leah was tender eyed; but Rachel was beautiful and well favoured.', '0~03812~ [1] 2~07390~ 3~05869~; 5~07354~ 7~08389~ 8~03303~ 9~03303~ 10~04758~.'),
  (22143, 28, 4, 1, 'Hear the word of the LORD, ye children of Israel: for the LORD hath a controversy with the inhabitants of the land, because there is no truth, nor mercy, nor knowledge of God in the land.', '&para; 0~08085~ 2~01697~ 5~03068~, 7~01121~ 9~03478~: 12~03068~ 15~07379~ 18~03427~ 21~0776~, [23 24] 26~0571~, 28~02617~, 30~01847~ 32~0430~ 35~0776~.'),
  (19079, 24, 5, 12, 'They have belied the LORD, and said, It is not he; neither shall evil come upon us; neither shall we see sword nor famine:', '2~03584~ 4~03068~, 6~0559~, [7 8] 13~07451~ 14~0935~ 20~07200~ 21~02719~ 23~07458~:'),
  (11775, 14, 28, 2, 'For he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and made also molten images for Baalim.', '3~03212~ 5~01870~ 8~04428~ 10~03478~, 12~06213~ 15~04541~ 17~01168~.'),
  (749, 1, 27, 18, 'And he came unto his father, and said, My father: and he said, Here am I; who art thou, my son?', '&para; 2~0935~ 5~01~, 7~0559~, 9~01~: 12~0559~, [14] [17] 20~01121~?'),
  (1218, 1, 41, 18, 'And, behold, there came up out of the river seven kine, fatfleshed and well favoured; and they fed in a meadow:', '4~05927~ 8~02975~ 9~07651~ 10~06510~, 11~01320~ 12~01277~ 13~03303~ 14~08389~; 17~07462~ 20~0260~:'),
  (3988, 4, 9, 18, 'At the commandment of the LORD the children of Israel journeyed, and at the commandment of the LORD they pitched: as long as the cloud abode upon the tabernacle they rested in their tents.', '2~06310~ 5~03068~ 7~01121~ 9~03478~ 10~05265~, 14~06310~ 17~03068~ 19~02583~: 22~03117~ 24~06051~ 25~07931~ 28~04908~ 30~02583~'),
  (27604, 44, 19, 3, 'And he said unto them, Unto what then were ye baptized? And they said, Unto John''s baptism.', '0~5037~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~1519~ 6~5101~ 7~3767~ 10~907~? 11~1161~ 13~2036~, 14~1519~ 15~2491~ 16~908~.'),
  (6548, 7, 1, 32, 'But the Asherites dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land: for they did not drive them out.', '2~0843~ 3~03427~ 4~07130~ 6~03669~, 8~03427~ 11~0776~: 18~03423~.'),
  (6318, 6, 18, 18, 'And passed along toward the side over against Arabah northward, and went down unto Arabah:', '2~05674~ 5~03802~ 7~04136~ 8~06160~ 9~06828~, 12~03381~ 14~06160~:'),
  (14479, 19, 37, 20, 'But the wicked shall perish, and the enemies of the LORD shall be as the fat of lambs: they shall consume; into smoke shall they consume away.', '2~07563~ 4~06~, 7~0341~ 10~03068~ [11 12] 15~03368~ 17~03733~: 20~03615~; 22~06227~ 26~03615~.'),
  (5358, 5, 16, 10, 'And thou shalt keep the feast of weeks unto the LORD thy God with a tribute of a freewill offering of thine hand, which thou shalt give unto the LORD thy God, according as the LORD thy God hath blessed thee:', '3~06213~ 5~02282~ 7~07620~ 10~03068~ 12~0430~ 15~04530~ 19~05071~ 22~03027~, 26~05414~ [27 31] 35~03068~ 37~0430~ 39~01288~'),
  (20056, 24, 46, 2, 'Against Egypt, against the army of Pharaohnecho king of Egypt, which was by the river Euphrates in Carchemish, which Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon smote in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah.', '1~04714~, 4~02428~ 6~06549~ 7~04428~ 9~04714~, 14~05104~ 15~06578~ 17~03751~, 19~05019~ 20~04428~ 22~0894~ 23~05221~ 26~07243~ 27~08141~ 29~03079~ 31~01121~ 33~02977~ 34~04428~ 36~03063~.'),
  (10098, 12, 19, 29, 'And this shall be a sign unto thee, Ye shall eat this year such things as grow of themselves, and in the second year that which springeth of the same; and in the third year sow ye, and reap, and plant vineyards, and eat the fruits thereof.', '[2 3] 5~0226~ 10~0398~ 12~08141~ 16~05599~ 22~08145~ 23~08141~ 26~07823~ 33~07992~ 34~08141~ 35~02232~ 38~07114~, 40~05193~ 41~03754~, 43~0398~ 45~06529~'),
  (10304, 13, 1, 44, 'And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.', '2~01106~ 4~04191~, 5~03103~ 7~01121~ 9~02226~ 11~01224~ 12~04427~'),
  (2883, 3, 6, 29, 'All the males among the priests shall eat thereof: it is most holy.', '2~02145~ 5~03548~ 7~0398~ [10] 11~06944~ 12~06944~.'),
  (3122, 3, 14, 6, 'As for the living bird, he shall take it, and the cedar wood, and the scarlet, and the hyssop, and shall dip them and the living bird in the blood of the bird that was killed over the running water:', '3~02416~ 4~06833~, 7~03947~ 11~0730~ 12~06086~, 15~08438~ 16~08144~,* 19~0231~, 22~02881~ 26~02416~ 27~06833~ 30~01818~ 33~06833~ [34 35] 36~07819~ 39~02416~ 40~04325~:'),
  (25571, 42, 14, 5, 'And answered them, saying, Which of you shall have an ass or an ox fallen into a pit, and will not straightway pull him out on the sabbath day?', '0~2532~ 1~611~ 2~846~ 3~4314~,* 4~2036~, 5~5101~ 7~5216~ 11~3688~ 12~2228~ 14~1016~ 15~1706~ 16~1519~ 18~5421~, 19~2532~ 20~385~ 21~3756~ 22~2112~ 23~385~ 24~846~ 25~385~ 26~1722~ 28~4521~ 29~2250~?'),
  (9283, 11, 15, 26, 'And he did evil in the sight of the LORD, and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin wherewith he made Israel to sin.', '2~06213~ 3~07451~ 6~05869~ 9~03068~, 11~03212~ 14~01870~ 17~01~, 21~02403~ 25~03478~ 27~02398~.'),
  (15664, 19, 106, 4, 'Remember me, O LORD, with the favour that thou bearest unto thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;', '0~02142~ 3~03068~, 6~07522~ [7 10] 12~05971~: 14~06485~ 18~03444~;'),
  (9632, 12, 4, 21, 'And she went up, and laid him on the bed of the man of God, and shut the door upon him, and went out.', '3~05927~, 5~07901~ 9~04296~ 12~0376~ 14~0430~, 16~05462~ [17 18] 23~03318~.'),
  (23814, 40, 20, 12, 'Saying, These last have wrought but one hour, and thou hast made them equal unto us, which have borne the burden and heat of the day.', '0~3754~* 1~3004~, 2~3778~ 3~2078~ 5~4160~ [6] 7~3391~ 8~5610~, 9~2532~ 12~4160~ 13~846~ 14~2470~ 16~2254~, 17~3588~ 19~941~ 21~922~ 22~2532~ 23~2742~ 26~2250~.'),
  (6963, 7, 16, 7, 'And Samson said unto her, If they bind me with seven green withs that were never dried, then shall I be weak, and be as another man.', '1~08123~ 2~0559~ 7~0631~ 10~07651~ 11~03892~ 12~03499~ 16~02717~, 21~02470~, 25~0259~ 26~0120~.'),
  (27936, 44, 28, 21, 'And they said unto him, We neither received letters out of Judaea concerning thee, neither any of the brethren that came shewed or spake any harm of thee.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~2249~ 6~3777~ 7~1209~ 8~1121~ 10~575~ 11~2449~ 12~4012~ 13~4675~, 14~3777~ 15~5100~ 18~80~ 20~3854~ 21~518~ 22~2228~ 23~2980~ 24~5100~ 25~4190~ 26~4012~ 27~4675~.'),
  (5138, 5, 7, 21, 'Thou shalt not be affrighted at them: for the LORD thy God is among you, a mighty God and terrible.', '4~06206~ 5~06440~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~ [12] 13~07130~ 16~01419~ 17~0410~ 19~03372~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14373, 19, 32, 9, 'Be ye not as the horse, or as the mule, which have no understanding: whose mouth must be held in with bit and bridle, lest they come near unto thee.', '5~05483~, [6] 9~06505~, [10] 13~0995~: 15~05716~ 18~01102~ 21~04964~ 23~07448~, 24~01077~ 27~07126~'),
  (29425, 50, 2, 18, 'For the same cause also do ye joy, and rejoice with me.', '0~1161~ 3~846~ 4~2532~ 5~5463~ 6~5210~ 7~5463~, 8~2532~ 10~4796~ 11~3427~.'),
  (20372, 25, 3, 9, 'He hath enclosed my ways with hewn stone, he hath made my paths crooked.', '2~01443~ 4~01870~ 7~01496~, 12~05410~ 13~05753~.'),
  (11336, 14, 7, 4, 'Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the LORD.', '2~04428~ 6~05971~ 7~02076~ 8~02077~ 9~06440~ 11~03068~.'),
  (25315, 42, 9, 2, 'And he sent them to preach the kingdom of God, and to heal the sick.', '0~2532~ 2~649~ 3~846~ 5~2784~ 7~932~ 9~2316~, 10~2532~ 12~2390~ 14~770~.'),
  (14403, 19, 34, 6, 'This poor man cried, and the LORD heard him, and saved him out of all his troubles.', '2~06041~ 3~07121~, 6~03068~ 7~08085~ [8] 10~03467~ 16~06869~.'),
  (21410, 26, 37, 4, 'Again he said unto me, Prophesy upon these bones, and say unto them, O ye dry bones, hear the word of the LORD.', '2~0559~ 5~05012~ 8~06106~, 10~0559~ 15~03002~ 16~06106~, 17~08085~ 19~01697~ 22~03068~.'),
  (14601, 19, 44, 21, 'Shall not God search this out? for he knoweth the secrets of the heart.', '2~0430~ 5~02713~? 8~03045~ 10~08587~ 13~03820~.'),
  (20665, 26, 11, 1, 'Moreover the spirit lifted me up, and brought me unto the east gate of the LORD''S house, which looketh eastward: and behold at the door of the gate five and twenty men; among whom I saw Jaazaniah the son of Azur, and Pelatiah the son of Benaiah, princes of the people.', '&para; 2~07307~ 5~05375~, 7~0935~ 11~06931~ 12~08179~ 15~03068~ 16~01004~, 18~06437~ 19~06921~: 24~06607~ 27~08179~ 28~02568~ 30~06242~ 31~0376~; 32~08432~ 35~07200~ 36~02970~ 38~01121~ 40~05809~, 42~06410~ 44~01121~ 46~01141~, 47~08269~ 50~05971~.'),
  (6532, 7, 1, 16, 'And the children of the Kenite, Moses'' father in law, went up out of the city of palm trees with the children of Judah into the wilderness of Judah, which lieth in the south of Arad; and they went and dwelt among the people.', '2~01121~ 5~07017~, 6~04872~ 9~02859~, 11~05927~ 15~05892~ 18~08558~ 19~05899~* 22~01121~ 24~03063~ 27~04057~ 29~03063~, [31] 34~05045~ 36~06166~; 39~03212~ 41~03427~ 42~0854~ 44~05971~.'),
  (8848, 11, 3, 24, 'And the king said, Bring me a sword. And they brought a sword before the king.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~, 4~03947~ 7~02719~. 10~0935~ 12~02719~ 13~06440~ 15~04428~.'),
  (14833, 19, 61, 5, 'For thou, O God, hast heard my vows: thou hast given me the heritage of those that fear thy name.', '&para; 3~0430~, 5~08085~ 7~05088~: 10~05414~ [11] 13~03425~ 17~03373~ 19~08034~.'),
  (24784, 41, 14, 19, 'And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one, Is it I? and another said, Is it I?', '0~1161~ 2~756~ 5~3076~, 7~2532~ 8~3004~ 10~846~ 13~1527~ 14~3385~,* [15] 17~1473~? 18~2532~ 19~243~ [20 20~3385~, 21] 23~1473~?'),
  (431, 1, 18, 3, 'And said, My Lord, if now I have found favour in thy sight, pass not away, I pray thee, from thy servant:', '1~0559~, 3~0136~, 8~04672~ 9~02580~ 12~05869~, 15~05674~, 21~05650~:'),
  (20847, 26, 17, 13, 'And hath taken of the king''s seed, and made a covenant with him, and hath taken an oath of him: he hath also taken the mighty of the land:', '2~03947~ 5~04410~ 6~02233~, 8~03772~ 10~01285~ 15~0935~ 17~0423~ 23~03947~ 25~0352~ 28~0776~:'),
  (15508, 19, 98, 9, 'Before the LORD; for he cometh to judge the earth: with righteousness shall he judge the world, and the people with equity.', '0~06440~ 2~03068~; 5~0935~ 7~08199~ 9~0776~: 11~06664~ 14~08199~ 16~08398~, 19~05971~ 21~04339~.'),
  (23907, 40, 22, 25, 'Now there were with us seven brethren: and the first, when he had married a wife, deceased, and, having no issue, left his wife unto his brother:', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~3844~ 4~2254~ 5~2033~ 6~80~: 7~2532~ 9~4413~, 15~1060~, 16~5053~, 17~2532~, 18~2192~ 19~3361~ 20~4690~, 21~863~ 22~846~ 23~1135~ 25~846~ 26~80~:'),
  (6563, 7, 2, 11, 'And the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the LORD, and served Baalim:', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 14~05647~ 15~01168~:'),
  (26700, 43, 14, 17, 'Even the Spirit of truth; whom the world cannot receive, because it seeth him not, neither knoweth him: but ye know him; for he dwelleth with you, and shall be in you.', '[0] 2~4151~ 4~225~; 5~3739~ 7~2889~ 8~1410~ 9~3756~* 10~2983~, 11~3754~ 13~2334~ 14~846~ 15~3756~, 16~3761~ 17~1097~ 18~846~: 19~1161~ 20~5210~ 21~1097~ 22~846~; 23~3754~ 25~3306~ 26~3844~ 27~5213~, 28~2532~ 30~2071~ 31~1722~ 32~5213~.'),
  (6506, 6, 24, 23, 'Now therefore put away, said he, the strange gods which are among you, and incline your heart unto the LORD God of Israel.', '3~05493~, [4 5] 7~05236~ 8~0430~ [10] 11~07130~ 14~05186~ 16~03824~ 19~03068~ 20~0430~ 22~03478~.'),
  (10609, 13, 8, 26, 'And Shamsherai, and Shehariah, and Athaliah,', '1~08125~, 3~07841~, 5~06271~,'),
  (18769, 23, 56, 7, 'Even them will I bring to my holy mountain, and make them joyful in my house of prayer: their burnt offerings and their sacrifices shall be accepted upon mine altar; for mine house shall be called an house of prayer for all people.', '4~0935~ 7~06944~ 8~02022~, 12~08055~ 15~01004~ 17~08605~: 20~05930~ 23~02077~ [24 25] 26~07522~ 29~04196~; 32~01004~ 35~07121~ 37~01004~ 39~08605~ 42~05971~.'),
  (31037, 66, 19, 4, 'And the four and twenty elders and the four beasts fell down and worshipped God that sat on the throne, saying, Amen; Alleluia.', '0~2532~ 2~5064~ 3~2532~ 4~1501~ 5~4245~ 6~2532~ 8~5064~ 9~2226~ 11~4098~ 12~2532~ 13~4352~ 14~2316~ 16~2521~ 17~1909~ 19~2362~, 20~3004~, 21~281~; 22~239~.'),
  (18163, 23, 27, 3, 'I the LORD do keep it; I will water it every moment: lest any hurt it, I will keep it night and day.', '2~03068~ 4~05341~ 8~08248~ 11~07281~: [13] 14~06485~ 18~05341~ 20~03915~ 22~03117~.'),
  (31065, 66, 20, 11, 'And I saw a great white throne, and him that sat on it, from whose face the earth and the heaven fled away; and there was found no place for them.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1492~ 4~3173~ 5~3022~ 6~2362~, 7~2532~ 10~2521~ 11~1909~ 12~846~, 13~575~ 14~3739~ 15~4383~ 17~1093~ 18~2532~ 20~3772~ 22~5343~; 23~2532~ 26~2147~ 27~3756~ 28~5117~ 30~846~.'),
  (24875, 41, 15, 38, 'And the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom.', '0~2532~ 2~2665~ 5~3485~ 7~4977~ 8~1519~ 9~1417~ 10~575~ 12~509~ 13~2193~ 15~2736~.'),
  (5546, 5, 24, 15, 'At his day thou shalt give him his hire, neither shall the sun go down upon it; for he is poor, and setteth his heart upon it: lest he cry against thee unto the LORD, and it be sin unto thee.', '2~03117~ 5~05414~ [6] 8~07939~, 12~08121~ 14~0935~ [19] 20~06041~, 22~05375~ 24~05315~ 29~07121~ 34~03068~, 38~02399~'),
  (14581, 19, 44, 1, 'To the chief Musician for the sons of Korah, Maschil. We have heard with our ears, O God, our fathers have told us, what work thou didst in their days, in the times of old.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 6~01121~ 8~07141~, 9] 9~04905~.] 12~08085~ 15~0241~, 17~0430~, 19~01~ 21~05608~ [23] 24~06467~ 26~06466~ 29~03117~, 32~03117~ 34~06924~.'),
  (26295, 43, 6, 23, '(Howbeit there came other boats from Tiberias nigh unto the place where they did eat bread, after that the Lord had given thanks:)', '0~1161~* 2~235~ 3~2064~ 4~243~ 5~4142~ 6~1537~ 7~5085~ 8~1451~ 11~5117~ 12~3699~ 15~5315~ 16~740~, 20~2962~ 23~2168~:)'),
  (21788, 27, 2, 21, 'And he changeth the times and the seasons: he removeth kings, and setteth up kings: he giveth wisdom unto the wise, and knowledge to them that know understanding:', '2~08133~ 4~05732~ 7~02166~: 9~05709~ 10~04430~, 13~06966~ 14~04430~: 16~03052~ 17~02452~ 20~02445~, 22~04486~ 26~03046~ 27~0999~:'),
  (9033, 11, 8, 40, 'That they may fear thee all the days that they live in the land which thou gavest unto our fathers.', '3~03372~ 7~03117~ 10~02416~ 11~06440~ 13~0127~ 16~05414~ 19~01~.'),
  (16304, 19, 143, 2, 'And enter not into judgment with thy servant: for in thy sight shall no man living be justified.', '1~0935~ 4~04941~ 7~05650~: 11~06440~ 15~02416~ 17~06663~.'),
  (5915, 6, 3, 16, 'That the waters which came down from above stood and rose up upon an heap very far from the city Adam, that is beside Zaretan: and those that came down toward the sea of the plain, even the salt sea, failed, and were cut off: and the people passed over right against Jericho.', '2~04325~ 5~03381~ 7~04605~ 8~05975~ [9] 11~06965~ 13~0259~ 14~05067~ 15~03966~ 16~07368~ 19~05892~ 20~0121~, [22] 23~06654~ 24~06891~: 29~03381~ 32~03220~ 35~06160~, [36] 38~04417~ 39~03220~, 40~08552~, [41] 44~03772~: 47~05971~ 49~05674~ 52~03405~.'),
  (22252, 28, 11, 3, 'I taught Ephraim also to go, taking them by their arms; but they knew not that I healed them.', '1~08637~ 2~0669~ 5~08637~, 6~03947~ 10~02220~; 13~03045~ 17~07495~'),
  (25786, 42, 19, 41, 'And when he was come near, he beheld the city, and wept over it,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~5613~ 5~1448~, 7~1492~ 9~4172~, 11~2799~ 12~1909~ 13~846~,'),
  (14843, 19, 62, 7, 'In God is my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.', '1~0430~ [2] 4~03468~ 7~03519~: 9~06697~ 12~05797~, [13] 15~04268~, [16] 18~0430~.'),
  (15120, 19, 77, 18, 'The voice of thy thunder was in the heaven: the lightnings lightened the world: the earth trembled and shook.', '1~06963~ 4~07482~ [5] 8~01534~: 10~01300~ 11~0215~ 13~08398~: 15~0776~ 16~07264~ 18~07493~.'),
  (16844, 20, 15, 28, 'The heart of the righteous studieth to answer: but the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.', '&para; 1~03820~ 4~06662~ 5~01897~ 7~06030~: 10~06310~ 13~07563~ 14~05042~ 17~07451~.'),
  (1843, 2, 12, 22, 'And ye shall take a bunch of hyssop, and dip it in the blood that is in the basin, and strike the lintel and the two side posts with the blood that is in the basin; and none of you shall go out at the door of his house until the morning.', '3~03947~ 5~092~ 7~0231~, 9~02881~ [10] 13~01818~ [15] 18~05592~, 20~05060~ 22~04947~ 25~08147~ 27~04201~ 30~01818~ [32] 35~05592~; 37~0376~ 42~03318~ 45~06607~ 48~01004~ 51~01242~.'),
  (26272, 43, 5, 47, 'But if ye believe not his writings, how shall ye believe my words?', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 3~4100~ 4~3756~ 5~1565~ 6~1121~, 7~4459~ 10~4100~ 11~1699~ 12~4487~?'),
  (3908, 4, 7, 53, 'And for a sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he goats, five lambs of the first year: this was the offering of Elishama the son of Ammihud.', '3~02077~ 6~08002~, 7~08147~ 8~01241~, 9~02568~ 10~0352~, 11~02568~ 13~06260~, 14~02568~ 15~03532~ 18~01121~ 19~08141~: [21] 23~07133~ 25~0476~ 27~01121~ 29~05989~.'),
  (291, 1, 11, 22, 'And Serug lived thirty years, and begat Nahor:', '1~08286~ 2~02421~ 3~07970~ 4~08141~, 6~03205~ 7~05152~:'),
  (11270, 14, 4, 16, 'The pots also, and the shovels, and the fleshhooks, and all their instruments, did Huram his father make to king Solomon for the house of the LORD of bright brass.', '1~05518~ 5~03257~, 8~04207~, 12~03627~, 14~02361~ 16~01~ 17~06213~ 19~04428~ 20~08010~ 23~01004~ 26~03068~ 28~04838~ 29~05178~.'),
  (12379, 16, 4, 11, 'And our adversaries said, They shall not know, neither see, till we come in the midst among them, and slay them, and cause the work to cease.', '2~06862~ 3~0559~, 7~03045~, 9~07200~, 12~0935~ 15~08432~ 16~08432~ 19~02026~ 24~04399~ 26~07673~.'),
  (8894, 11, 5, 8, 'And Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, I have considered the things which thou sentest to me for: and I will do all thy desire concerning timber of cedar, and concerning timber of fir.', '1~02438~ 2~07971~ 4~08010~, 5~0559~, 8~08085~ 13~07971~ [17] 20~06213~ 23~02656~ 25~06086~ 27~0730~, 30~06086~ 32~01265~.'),
  (223, 1, 9, 17, 'And God said unto Noah, This is the token of the covenant, which I have established between me and all flesh that is upon the earth.', '1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~05146~, [6] 8~0226~ 11~01285~, 15~06965~ 20~01320~ [22] 25~0776~.'),
  (787, 1, 28, 10, 'And Jacob went out from Beersheba, and went toward Haran.', '&para; 1~03290~ 3~03318~ 5~0884~, 7~03212~ 9~02771~.'),
  (21399, 26, 36, 31, 'Then shall ye remember your own evil ways, and your doings that were not good, and shall loathe yourselves in your own sight for your iniquities and for your abominations.', '3~02142~ 6~07451~ 7~01870~, 10~04611~ [12] 14~02896~, 17~06962~ 22~06440~ 25~05771~ 29~08441~.'),
  (12032, 15, 1, 7, 'Also Cyrus the king brought forth the vessels of the house of the LORD, which Nebuchadnezzar had brought forth out of Jerusalem, and had put them in the house of his gods;', '1~03566~ 3~04428~ 5~03318~ 7~03627~ 10~01004~ 13~03068~, 15~05019~ 18~03318~ 21~03389~, 24~05414~ 28~01004~ 31~0430~;'),
  (23179, 40, 1, 25, 'And knew her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son: and he called his name JESUS.', '0~2532~ 1~1097~ 2~846~ 3~3756~ 4~3757~ 5~2193~ 8~5088~ 9~846~ 10~4416~ 11~5207~: 12~2532~ 14~2564~ 15~846~ 16~3686~ 17~2424~.'),
  (19156, 24, 7, 28, 'But thou shalt say unto them, This is a nation that obeyeth not the voice of the LORD their God, nor receiveth correction: truth is perished, and is cut off from their mouth.', '3~0559~ [7] 9~01471~ 11~08085~ 14~06963~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~, 21~03947~ 22~04148~: 23~0530~ 25~06~, 29~03772~ 32~06310~.'),
  (86, 1, 4, 6, 'And the LORD said unto Cain, Why art thou wroth? and why is thy countenance fallen?', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~07014~, 9~02734~? 14~06440~ 15~05307~?'),
  (19548, 24, 25, 5, 'They said, Turn ye again now every one from his evil way, and from the evil of your doings, and dwell in the land that the LORD hath given unto you and to your fathers for ever and ever:', '1~0559~, 4~07725~ 7~0376~ 10~07451~ 11~01870~, 15~07455~ 18~04611~, 20~03427~ 23~0127~ 26~03068~ 28~05414~ 34~01~ 35~05704~ 36~05769~ 38~05769~:'),
  (5103, 5, 6, 11, 'And houses full of all good things, which thou filledst not, and wells digged, which thou diggedst not, vineyards and olive trees, which thou plantedst not; when thou shalt have eaten and be full;', '1~01004~ 2~04392~ 5~02898~ [6] 9~04390~ 12~0953~ 13~02672~, 16~02672~ 18~03754~ 21~02132~, 24~05193~ 30~0398~ 33~07646~;'),
  (22792, 35, 3, 15, 'Thou didst walk through the sea with thine horses, through the heap of great waters.', '2~01869~ 5~03220~ 8~05483~, [9] 11~02563~ 13~07227~ 14~04325~.'),
  (16543, 20, 5, 17, 'Let them be only thine own, and not strangers'' with thee.', '8~02114~'''),
  (18695, 23, 51, 13, 'And forgettest the LORD thy maker, that hath stretched forth the heavens, and laid the foundations of the earth; and hast feared continually every day because of the fury of the oppressor, as if he were ready to destroy? and where is the fury of the oppressor?', '1~07911~ 3~03068~ 5~06213~, 9~05186~ 11~08064~, 15~03245~ 18~0776~; 21~06342~ 22~08548~ 24~03117~ 25~06440~ 28~02534~ 31~06693~, 33~0834~ 36~03559~ 38~07843~? [41] 43~02534~ 46~06693~?'),
  (9572, 12, 2, 13, 'He took up also the mantle of Elijah that fell from him, and went back, and stood by the bank of Jordan;', '&para; 2~07311~ 5~0155~ 7~0452~ 9~05307~ 14~07725~, 16~05975~ 19~08193~ 21~03383~;'),
  (23294, 40, 6, 2, 'Therefore when thou doest thine alms, do not sound a trumpet before thee, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have glory of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.', '0~3767~ 1~3752~ 3~4160~ [4] 5~1654~, 6~4537~ 7~3361~ 10~4537~ 11~1715~ 12~4675~, 13~5618~ 15~5273~ 16~4160~ 17~1722~ 19~4864~ 20~2532~ 21~1722~ 23~4505~, 24~3704~ 28~1392~ 29~5259~ 30~444~. 31~281~ 33~3004~ 35~5213~, 37~568~ 38~846~ 39~3408~.'),
  (26797, 43, 17, 23, 'I in them, and thou in me, that they may be made perfect in one; and that the world may know that thou hast sent me, and hast loved them, as thou hast loved me.', '0~1473~ 1~1722~ 2~846~, 3~2532~ 4~4771~ 5~1722~ 6~1698~, 7~2443~ 10~5600~ 12~5048~ 13~1519~ 14~1520~; 15~2532~ 16~2443~ 18~2889~ 20~1097~ 21~3754~ 22~4771~ 24~649~ 25~3165~, 26~2532~ 28~25~ 29~846~, 30~2531~ 33~25~ 34~1691~.'),
  (7618, 9, 16, 16, 'Let our lord now command thy servants, which are before thee, to seek out a man, who is a cunning player on an harp: and it shall come to pass, when the evil spirit from God is upon thee, that he shall play with his hand, and thou shalt be well.', '2~0113~ 4~0559~ 6~05650~, [7 8] 9~06440~ 13~01245~ 15~0376~, [16 17] 19~03045~ 20~05059~ 23~03658~: 32~07451~ 33~07307~ 35~0430~ 42~05059~ 45~03027~, 50~02895~.'),
  (20869, 26, 18, 11, 'And that doeth not any of those duties, but even hath eaten upon the mountains, and defiled his neighbour''s wife,', '2~06213~ [7] 11~0398~ 14~02022~, 16~02930~ 18~07453~ 19~0802~,'),
  (8400, 10, 15, 4, 'Absalom said moreover, Oh that I were made judge in the land, that every man which hath any suit or cause might come unto me, and I would do him justice!', '0~053~ 1~0559~ 7~07760~ 8~08199~ 11~0776~, 14~0376~ 18~07379~ 20~04941~ 22~0935~ 30~06663~!'),
  (17433, 21, 6, 7, 'All the labour of man is for his mouth, and yet the appetite is not filled.', '&para; 2~05999~ 4~0120~ [5] 8~06310~, 12~05315~ 15~04390~.'),
  (25945, 42, 22, 67, 'Art thou the Christ? tell us. And he said unto them, If I tell you, ye will not believe:', '0~1487~* 1~1488~ 2~4771~ 4~5547~? 5~2036~ 6~2254~. 7~1161~ 9~2036~ 11~846~, 12~1437~ 14~2036~ 15~5213~, 17~4100~ 18~3364~ 19~4100~:'),
  (13684, 18, 33, 25, 'His flesh shall be fresher than a child''s: he shall return to the days of his youth:', '1~01320~ 4~07375~ 7~05290~: 10~07725~ 13~03117~ 16~05934~:'),
  (3684, 4, 2, 21, 'And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were thirty and two thousand and two hundred.', '2~06635~, 7~06485~ [10] 11~07970~ 13~08147~ 14~0505~ 17~03967~.'),
  (25604, 42, 15, 3, 'And he spake this parable unto them, saying,', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~5026~ 4~3850~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 7~3004~,'),
  (8845, 11, 3, 21, 'And when I rose in the morning to give my child suck, behold, it was dead: but when I had considered it in the morning, behold, it was not my son, which I did bear.', '3~06965~ 6~01242~ 10~01121~ 11~03243~, 15~04191~: 20~0995~ 24~01242~, 30~01121~, 34~03205~.'),
  (30172, 58, 10, 23, 'Let us hold fast the profession of our faith without wavering; (for he is faithful that promised;)', '3~2722~ 5~3671~ [7] 8~1680~ 10~186~; 11~1063~* [14] 15~4103~ 17~1861~;)'),
  (5283, 5, 13, 5, 'And that prophet, or that dreamer of dreams, shall be put to death; because he hath spoken to turn you away from the LORD your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt, and redeemed you out of the house of bondage, to thrust thee out of the way which the LORD thy God commanded thee to walk in. So shalt thou put the evil away from the midst of thee.', '2~05030~, 5~02492~ 7~02472~, 12~04191~; 16~01696~ 18~05627~ [19] 23~03068~ 25~0430~, 29~03318~ 32~0776~ 34~04714~, 36~06299~ 41~01004~ 43~05650~, 45~05080~ 50~01870~ 53~03068~ 55~0430~ 56~06680~ 60~03212~. 64~01197~ 66~07451~ 67~01197~ 70~07130~'),
  (20664, 26, 10, 22, 'And the likeness of their faces was the same faces which I saw by the river of Chebar, their appearances and themselves: they went every one straight forward.', '2~01823~ 5~06440~ [6] 8~01992~ 9~06440~ 12~07200~ 15~05104~ 17~03529~, 19~04758~ 23~03212~ 25~0376~ 26~05676~ 27~06440~.'),
  (5027, 5, 4, 17, 'The likeness of any beast that is on the earth, the likeness of any winged fowl that flieth in the air,', '1~08403~ 4~0929~ [6] 9~0776~, 11~08403~ 14~03671~ 15~06833~ 17~05774~ 20~08064~,'),
  (20149, 24, 49, 13, 'For I have sworn by myself, saith the LORD, that Bozrah shall become a desolation, a reproach, a waste, and a curse; and all the cities thereof shall be perpetual wastes.', '3~07650~ 6~05002~ 8~03068~, 10~01224~ 14~08047~, 16~02781~, 18~02721~, 21~07045~; 25~05892~ 29~05769~ 30~02723~.'),
  (21523, 26, 40, 37, 'And the posts thereof were toward the utter court; and palm trees were upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side: and the going up to it had eight steps.', '2~0352~ [4] 7~02435~ 8~02691~; 11~08561~ [12] 15~0352~ 27~04608~ [30] 31~08083~ 32~04609~.'),
  (30175, 58, 10, 26, 'For if we sin wilfully after that we have received the knowledge of the truth, there remaineth no more sacrifice for sins,', '0~1063~ 2~2257~ 3~264~ 4~1596~ 5~3326~ 9~2983~ 11~1922~ 14~225~, 16~620~ 18~3765~ 19~2378~ 20~4012~ 21~266~,'),
  (14764, 19, 55, 23, 'But thou, O God, shalt bring them down into the pit of destruction: bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days; but I will trust in thee.', '3~0430~, 7~03381~ 10~0875~ 12~07845~: 13~01818~ 15~04820~ 16~0582~ 21~02673~ 23~03117~; 27~0982~'),
  (2857, 3, 6, 3, 'Or have found that which was lost, and lieth concerning it, and sweareth falsely; in any of all these that a man doeth, sinning therein:', '2~04672~ 6~09~, 8~03584~ 12~07650~ 13~08267~; 15~0259~ 21~0120~ 22~06213~, 23~02398~ 24~02007~:'),
  (28634, 46, 11, 18, 'For first of all, when ye come together in the church, I hear that there be divisions among you; and I partly believe it.', '0~3303~ 1~1063~ 3~4412~, 5~5216~ 7~4905~ 8~1722~ 10~1577~, 12~191~ 15~5225~ 16~4978~ 17~1722~ 18~5213~; 19~2532~ 21~3313~ 22~4100~ 23~5100~.'),
  (5542, 5, 24, 11, 'Thou shalt stand abroad, and the man to whom thou dost lend shall bring out the pledge abroad unto thee.', '2~05975~ 3~02351~, 6~0376~ 11~05383~ 14~03318~ 16~05667~ 17~02351~'),
  (18978, 24, 2, 4, 'Hear ye the word of the LORD, O house of Jacob, and all the families of the house of Israel:', '0~08085~ 3~01697~ 6~03068~, 8~01004~ 10~03290~, 14~04940~ 17~01004~ 19~03478~:'),
  (19749, 24, 32, 9, 'And I bought the field of Hanameel my uncle''s son, that was in Anathoth, and weighed him the money, even seventeen shekels of silver.', '2~07069~ 4~07704~ 6~02601~ 8~01730~ 9~01121~, [11] 13~06068~, 15~08254~ 18~03701~, [19] 20~06235~ 21~07651~* 22~08255~ 24~03701~.'),
  (23276, 40, 5, 32, 'But I say unto you, That whosoever shall put away his wife, saving for the cause of fornication, causeth her to commit adultery: and whosoever shall marry her that is divorced committeth adultery.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 6~302~ 7~3739~ 9~630~ 10~846~ 11~1135~, 12~3924~ 15~3056~ 17~4202~, 18~4160~ 19~846~ 22~3429~: 23~2532~ 24~1437~ 25~3739~ 26~1060~ 30~630~ 32~3429~.'),
  (7142, 8, 1, 8, 'And Naomi said unto her two daughters in law, Go, return each to her mother''s house: the LORD deal kindly with you, as ye have dealt with the dead, and with me.', '1~05281~ 2~0559~ 5~08147~ 8~03618~, 9~03212~, 10~07725~ 11~0802~ 14~0517~ 15~01004~: 17~03068~ 18~06213~ 19~02617~ 25~06213~ 28~04191~,'),
  (20073, 24, 46, 19, 'O thou daughter dwelling in Egypt, furnish thyself to go into captivity: for Noph shall be waste and desolate without an inhabitant.', '2~01323~ 3~03427~ 5~04714~, 6~06213~ 11~01473~ 12~03627~:* 14~05297~ 17~08047~ 19~03341~ 22~03427~.'),
  (27843, 44, 26, 4, 'My manner of life from my youth, which was at the first among mine own nation at Jerusalem, know all the Jews;', '0~3450~ 1~3767~ 2~3303~ 3~981~ 4~1537~ 6~3503~, 7~3588~ 8~1096~ 9~575~ 11~746~ 12~1722~ 13~3450~ 15~1484~ 16~1722~ 17~2414~, 18~2467~ 19~3956~ 21~2453~;'),
  (8472, 10, 17, 16, 'Now therefore send quickly, and tell David, saying, Lodge not this night in the plains of the wilderness, but speedily pass over; lest the king be swallowed up, and all the people that are with him.', '2~07971~ 3~04120~, 5~05046~ 6~01732~, 7~0559~, 8~03885~ 11~03915~ 14~06160~ 15~05679~* 18~04057~, 20~05674~ 22~05674~; 25~04428~ 28~01104~, 32~05971~ [34]'),
  (4264, 4, 18, 2, 'And thy brethren also of the tribe of Levi, the tribe of thy father, bring thou with thee, that they may be joined unto thee, and minister unto thee: but thou and thy sons with thee shall minister before the tabernacle of witness.', '2~0251~ 6~04294~ 8~03878~, 10~07626~ 13~01~, 14~07126~ 22~03867~ 26~08334~ 33~01121~ [36 37] 38~06440~ 40~0168~ 42~05715~.'),
  (2002, 2, 17, 14, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Write this for a memorial in a book, and rehearse it in the ears of Joshua: for I will utterly put out the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~03789~ [8] 10~02146~ 13~05612~, 15~07760~ [16] 19~0241~ 21~03091~: 25~04229~ 27~04229~ 29~02143~ 31~06002~ 34~08064~.'),
  (22616, 33, 2, 12, 'I will surely assemble, O Jacob, all of thee; I will surely gather the remnant of Israel; I will put them together as the sheep of Bozrah, as the flock in the midst of their fold: they shall make great noise by reason of the multitude of men.', '&para; 2~0622~ 3~0622~, 5~03290~, 11~06908~ 12~06908~ 14~07611~ 16~03478~; 19~07760~ 21~03162~ 24~06629~ 26~01223~ 27~01224~,* 30~05739~ 33~08432~ 36~01699~: 41~01949~ [45 47] 48~0120~.'),
  (29910, 56, 1, 2, 'In hope of eternal life, which God, that cannot lie, promised before the world began;', '0~1909~ 1~1680~ 3~166~ 4~2222~, 5~3739~ 6~2316~, 9~893~, 10~1861~ 11~4253~ 13~166~ 14~5550~;'),
  (18744, 23, 54, 12, 'And I will make thy windows of agates, and thy gates of carbuncles, and all thy borders of pleasant stones.', '3~07760~ 5~08121~ 7~03539~, 10~08179~ 12~0688~ 13~068~,* 17~01366~ 19~02656~ 20~068~.'),
  (4266, 4, 18, 4, 'And they shall be joined unto thee, and keep the charge of the tabernacle of the congregation, for all the service of the tabernacle: and a stranger shall not come nigh unto you.', '4~03867~ 8~08104~ 10~04931~ 13~0168~ 16~04150~, 20~05656~ 23~0168~: 26~02114~ 30~07126~'),
  (7909, 9, 25, 41, 'And she arose, and bowed herself on her face to the earth, and said, Behold, let thine handmaid be a servant to wash the feet of the servants of my lord.', '2~06965~, 4~07812~ [7] 8~0639~ 11~0776~, 13~0559~, [15] 17~0519~ [18] 20~08198~ 22~07364~ 24~07272~ 27~05650~ 30~0113~.'),
  (28381, 46, 1, 2, 'Unto the church of God which is at Corinth, to them that are sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, with all that in every place call upon the name of Jesus Christ our Lord, both theirs and ours:', '2~1577~ 4~2316~ 5~3588~ 6~5607~ 7~1722~ 8~2882~, 13~37~ 14~1722~ 15~5547~ 16~2424~, 17~2822~ [18 19] 20~40~, 21~4862~ 22~3956~ 24~1722~ 25~3956~ 26~5117~ 28~1941~ 30~3686~ 32~2424~ 33~5547~ 34~2257~ 35~2962~, 36~5037~ 37~846~ 38~2532~ 39~2257~:'),
  (13206, 18, 14, 16, 'For now thou numberest my steps: dost thou not watch over my sin?', '&para; 3~05608~ 5~06806~: 9~08104~ 12~02403~?'),
  (27953, 45, 1, 7, 'To all that be in Rome, beloved of God, called to be saints: Grace to you and peace from God our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ.', '1~3956~ 3~5607~ 4~1722~ 5~4516~, 6~27~ 8~2316~, 9~2822~ [10 11] 12~40~: 13~5485~ 15~5213~ 16~2532~ 17~1515~ 18~575~ 19~2316~ 20~2257~ 21~3962~, 22~2532~ 24~2962~ 25~2424~ 26~5547~.'),
  (29247, 49, 2, 2, 'Wherein in time past ye walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit that now worketh in the children of disobedience:', '0~3739~ 1~1722~ 3~4218~ 5~4043~ 7~2596~ 9~165~ 11~5127~ 12~2889~, 14~2596~ 16~758~ 19~1849~ 22~109~, 24~4151~ 26~3568~ 27~1754~ 28~1722~ 30~5207~ 32~543~:'),
  (15411, 19, 91, 7, 'A thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand; but it shall not come nigh thee.', '1~0505~ 3~05307~ 6~06654~, 9~07233~ 13~03225~; [14] 19~05066~'),
  (9387, 11, 18, 38, 'Then the fire of the LORD fell, and consumed the burnt sacrifice, and the wood, and the stones, and the dust, and licked up the water that was in the trench.', '2~0784~ 5~03068~ 6~05307~, 8~0398~ 11~05930~, 14~06086~, 17~068~, 20~06083~, 23~03897~ 25~04325~ [27] 30~08585~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (16998, 20, 21, 5, 'The thoughts of the diligent tend only to plenteousness; but of every one that is hasty only to want.', '&para; 1~04284~ 4~02742~ [5] 8~04195~; [13 14] 15~0213~ 18~04270~.'),
  (13324, 18, 19, 18, 'Yea, young children despised me; I arose, and they spake against me.', '2~05759~ 3~03988~ 6~06965~, 9~01696~'),
  (26409, 43, 8, 13, 'The Pharisees therefore said unto him, Thou bearest record of thyself; thy record is not true.', '1~5330~ 2~3767~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 6~4771~ 8~3140~ 9~4012~ 10~4572~; 11~4675~ 12~3141~ 13~2076~ 14~3756~ 15~227~.'),
  (3115, 3, 13, 58, 'And the garment, either warp, or woof, or whatsoever thing of skin it be, which thou shalt wash, if the plague be departed from them, then it shall be washed the second time, and shall be clean.', '2~0899~, 4~08359~, 6~06154~, 9~03627~ 11~05785~ [12 13] 17~03526~, 20~05061~ 22~05493~ 29~03526~ 31~08145~ 36~02891~.'),
  (7040, 7, 19, 9, 'And when the man rose up to depart, he, and his concubine, and his servant, his father in law, the damsel''s father, said unto him, Behold, now the day draweth toward evening, I pray you tarry all night: behold, the day groweth to an end, lodge here, that thine heart may be merry; and to morrow get you early on your way, that thou mayest go home.', '3~0376~ 5~06965~ 7~03212~, 11~06370~, 14~05288~, 18~02859~, 20~05291~ 21~01~, 22~0559~ 28~03117~ 29~07503~ 31~06150~, 37~03885~: 40~03117~ 44~02583~, 45~03885~ 49~03824~ 52~03190~; 55~04279~ 58~07925~ 61~01870~, 65~01980~ 66~0168~.'),
  (27631, 44, 19, 30, 'And when Paul would have entered in unto the people, the disciples suffered him not.', '0~1161~ 1~1014~ 2~3972~ 3~1014~ 5~1525~ 6~1519~ 9~1218~, 11~3101~ 12~1439~ 13~846~ 14~3756~.'),
  (7847, 9, 24, 1, 'And it came to pass, when Saul was returned from following the Philistines, that it was told him, saying, Behold, David is in the wilderness of Engedi.', '&para; 6~07586~ 8~07725~ 10~0310~ 12~06430~, 16~05046~ 18~0559~, 20~01732~ [21] 24~04057~ 26~05872~.'),
  (1008, 1, 34, 23, 'Shall not their cattle and their substance and every beast of theirs be ours? only let us consent unto them, and they will dwell with us.', '[0] 3~04735~ 6~07075~ 9~0929~ [12] 17~0225~ 23~03427~'),
  (15360, 19, 89, 25, 'I will set his hand also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers.', '2~07760~ 4~03027~ 8~03220~, 12~03225~ 15~05104~.'),
  (19725, 24, 31, 25, 'For I have satiated the weary soul, and I have replenished every sorrowful soul.', '3~07301~ 5~05889~ 6~05315~, 10~04390~ 12~01669~ 13~05315~.'),
  (5305, 5, 14, 9, 'These ye shall eat of all that are in the waters: all that have fins and scales shall ye eat:', '3~0398~ [7] 10~04325~: 14~05579~ 16~07193~ 19~0398~:'),
  (8516, 10, 18, 30, 'And the king said unto him, Turn aside, and stand here. And he turned aside, and stood still.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ [4 5] 7~05437~, [8] 9~03320~ 10~03541~. 14~05437~, 17~05975~.'),
  (29420, 50, 2, 13, 'For it is God which worketh in you both to will and to do of his good pleasure.', '0~1063~ 2~2076~ 3~2316~ 4~3588~ 5~1754~ 6~1722~ 7~5213~ 8~2532~ 10~2309~ 11~2532~ 13~1754~ 14~5228~ [15] 17~2107~.'),
  (2081, 2, 20, 25, 'And if thou wilt make me an altar of stone, thou shalt not build it of hewn stone: for if thou lift up thy tool upon it, thou hast polluted it.', '4~06213~ 7~04196~ 9~068~, 13~01129~ 17~01496~: 22~05130~ 24~02719~ 29~02490~'),
  (23129, 39, 2, 16, 'For the LORD, the God of Israel, saith that he hateth putting away: for one covereth violence with his garment, saith the LORD of hosts: therefore take heed to your spirit, that ye deal not treacherously.', '2~03068~, 4~0430~ 6~03478~, 7~0559~ 10~08130~ 12~07971~: [14] 15~03680~ 16~02555~ 19~03830~, 20~0559~ 22~03068~ 24~06635~: 27~08104~ 30~07307~, 35~0898~.'),
  (6268, 6, 15, 59, 'And Maarath, and Bethanoth, and Eltekon; six cities with their villages:', '1~04638~, 3~01042~, 5~0515~; 6~08337~ 7~05892~ 10~02691~:'),
  (9938, 12, 15, 5, 'And the LORD smote the king, so that he was a leper unto the day of his death, and dwelt in a several house. And Jotham the king''s son was over the house, judging the people of the land.', '2~03068~ 3~05060~ 5~04428~, 11~06879~ 14~03117~ 17~04194~, 19~03427~ 22~02669~ 23~01004~. 25~03147~ 27~04428~ 28~01121~ [29] 32~01004~, 33~08199~ 35~05971~ 38~0776~.'),
  (7429, 9, 10, 4, 'And they will salute thee, and give thee two loaves of bread; which thou shalt receive of their hands.', '2~07592~ 3~07965~ 6~05414~ 8~08147~ [9] 11~03899~; 15~03947~ 18~03027~.'),
  (22061, 27, 11, 16, 'But he that cometh against him shall do according to his own will, and none shall stand before him: and he shall stand in the glorious land, which by his hand shall be consumed.', '3~0935~ 7~06213~ 12~07522~, 16~05975~ 17~06440~ 22~05975~ 25~06643~ 26~0776~, 30~03027~ 33~03617~.'),
  (9399, 11, 19, 4, 'But he himself went a day''s journey into the wilderness, and came and sat down under a juniper tree: and he requested for himself that he might die; and said, It is enough; now, O LORD, take away my life; for I am not better than my fathers.', '3~01980~ 5~03117~ 6~01870~ 9~04057~, 11~0935~ 14~03427~ 16~0259~ 18~07574~: 21~07592~ 23~05315~ 27~04191~; 29~0559~, 32~07227~; 35~03068~, 37~03947~ 39~05315~; [42] 44~02896~ 47~01~.'),
  (22009, 27, 9, 12, 'And he hath confirmed his words, which he spake against us, and against our judges that judged us, by bringing upon us a great evil: for under the whole heaven hath not been done as hath been done upon Jerusalem.', '3~06965~ 5~01697~, 8~01696~ 14~08199~ 16~08199~ 19~0935~ 23~01419~ 24~07451~: 29~08064~ 33~06213~ 37~06213~ 39~03389~.'),
  (30225, 58, 11, 37, 'They were stoned, they were sawn asunder, were tempted, were slain with the sword: they wandered about in sheepskins and goatskins; being destitute, afflicted, tormented;', '2~3034~, 6~4249~, 8~3985~, 10~599~ 11~1722~ 13~3162~ 14~5408~:* 17~4022~ 18~1722~ 19~3374~ 20~1722~ 21~1192~ 22~122~;* 24~5302~, 25~2346~, 26~2558~;'),
  (15940, 19, 119, 33, 'HE. Teach me, O LORD, the way of thy statutes; and I shall keep it unto the end.', '&para; 1~03384~ 4~03068~, 6~01870~ 9~02706~; 13~05341~ [15] 17~06118~.'),
  (6854, 7, 11, 18, 'Then they went along through the wilderness, and compassed the land of Edom, and the land of Moab, and came by the east side of the land of Moab, and pitched on the other side of Arnon, but came not within the border of Moab: for Arnon was the border of Moab.', '3~03212~ 6~04057~, 8~05437~ 10~0776~ 12~0123~, 15~0776~ 17~04124~, 19~0935~ 23~08121~ 24~04217~ 26~0776~ 28~04124~, 30~02583~ 34~05676~ 36~0769~, 38~0935~ 42~01366~ 44~04124~: 46~0769~ [47] 49~01366~ 51~04124~.'),
  (8669, 10, 23, 8, 'These be the names of the mighty men whom David had: The Tachmonite that sat in the seat, chief among the captains; the same was Adino the Eznite: he lift up his spear against eight hundred, whom he slew at one time.', '&para; [1] 3~08034~ 7~01368~ 9~01732~ 12~08461~ 14~03427~ 17~07675~ 18~07218~ 21~07991~; [24] 25~05722~ 27~06112~: [28 32] 34~08083~ 35~03967~, 38~02491~ 40~0259~ 41~06471~.'),
  (20318, 24, 52, 33, 'And changed his prison garments: and he did continually eat bread before him all the days of his life.', '1~08138~ 3~03608~ 4~0899~: 8~08548~ 9~0398~ 10~03899~ 11~06440~ 15~03117~ 18~02416~.'),
  (12127, 15, 4, 8, 'Rehum the chancellor and Shimshai the scribe wrote a letter against Jerusalem to Artaxerxes the king in this sort:', '0~07348~ 2~02942~ 3~01169~ 4~08124~ 6~05613~ 7~03790~ 8~02298~ 9~0104~ 10~05922~ 11~03390~ 13~0783~ 15~04430~ 18~03660~:'),
  (19464, 24, 22, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD; Go down to the house of the king of Judah, and speak there this word,', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~03381~ 8~01004~ 11~04428~ 13~03063~, 15~01696~ 18~01697~,'),
  (3199, 3, 15, 26, 'Every bed whereon she lieth all the days of her issue shall be unto her as the bed of her separation: and whatsoever she sitteth upon shall be unclean, as the uncleanness of her separation.', '1~04904~ 4~07901~ 7~03117~ 10~02101~ 17~04904~ 20~05079~: 22~03627~ 24~03427~ 28~02931~, 31~02932~ 34~05079~.'),
  (30688, 64, 1, 14, 'But I trust I shall shortly see thee, and we shall speak face to face. Peace be to thee. Our friends salute thee. Greet the friends by name.', '0~1161~ 2~1679~ 4~1492~ 5~2112~ 6~1492~ 7~4571~, 8~2532~ 11~2980~ 12~4750~ 13~4314~ 14~4750~. 15~1515~ [16] 18~4671~. [19] 20~5384~ 21~782~ 22~4571~. 23~782~ 25~5384~ 26~2596~ 27~3686~.'),
  (6218, 6, 15, 9, 'And the border was drawn from the top of the hill unto the fountain of the water of Nephtoah, and went out to the cities of mount Ephron; and the border was drawn to Baalah, which is Kirjathjearim:', '2~01366~ 4~08388~ 7~07218~ 10~02022~ 13~04599~ 16~04325~ 18~05318~, 21~03318~ 24~05892~ 26~02022~ 27~06085~; 30~01366~ 32~08388~ 34~01173~, [36] 37~07157~:'),
  (17326, 21, 1, 2, 'Vanity of vanities, saith the Preacher, vanity of vanities; all is vanity.', '0~01892~ 2~01892~, 3~0559~ 5~06953~, 6~01892~ 8~01892~; [10] 11~01892~.'),
  (28257, 45, 11, 32, 'For God hath concluded them all in unbelief, that he might have mercy upon all.', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 3~4788~ 5~3956~ 6~1519~ 7~543~, 8~2443~ 12~1653~ 14~3956~.'),
  (4467, 4, 24, 16, 'He hath said, which heard the words of God, and knew the knowledge of the most High, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:', '2~05002~, 4~08085~ 6~0561~ 8~0410~, 10~03045~ 12~01847~ 16~05945~, [17] 18~02372~ 20~04236~ 23~07706~, 24~05307~ [25 27] 31~05869~ 32~01540~:'),
  (12130, 15, 4, 11, 'This is the copy of the letter that they sent unto him, even unto Artaxerxes the king; Thy servants the men on this side the river, and at such a time.', '0~01836~ [1] 3~06573~ 6~0104~ 7~01768~ 9~07972~ 11~05922~, [12] 14~0783~ 16~04430~; 18~05649~ 20~0606~ 23~05675~ 25~05103~, 30~03706~.'),
  (18554, 23, 44, 12, 'The smith with the tongs both worketh in the coals, and fashioneth it with hammers, and worketh it with the strength of his arms: yea, he is hungry, and his strength faileth: he drinketh no water, and is faint.', '1~02796~ 2~01270~ 4~04621~ 6~06466~ 9~06352~, 11~03335~ 14~04717~, 16~06466~ 20~03581~ 23~02220~: 27~07457~, 30~03581~ 31~0369~: 33~08354~ 35~04325~, 38~03286~.'),
  (27618, 44, 19, 17, 'And this was known to all the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus; and fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified.', '0~1161~ 1~5124~ 2~1096~ 3~1110~ 5~3956~ 7~2453~ 8~5037~ 9~1672~ 10~2532~ 11~2730~ 13~2181~; 14~2532~ 15~5401~ 16~1968~ 17~1909~ 18~846~ 19~3956~, 20~2532~ 22~3686~ 25~2962~ 26~2424~ 28~3170~.'),
  (15811, 19, 111, 9, 'He sent redemption unto his people: he hath commanded his covenant for ever: holy and reverend is his name.', '1~07971~ 2~06304~ 5~05971~: 8~06680~ 10~01285~ 12~05769~: 13~06918~ 15~03372~ [16] 18~08034~.'),
  (10198, 12, 23, 25, 'And like unto him was there no king before him, that turned to the LORD with all his heart, and with all his soul, and with all his might, according to all the law of Moses; neither after him arose there any like him.', '&para; 7~04428~ 8~06440~ 11~07725~ 14~03068~ 18~03824~, 23~05315~, 28~03966~, 33~08451~ 35~04872~; 37~0310~ 39~06965~ [41]'),
  (17873, 23, 10, 14, 'And my hand hath found as a nest the riches of the people: and as one gathereth eggs that are left, have I gathered all the earth; and there was none that moved the wing, or opened the mouth, or peeped.', '2~03027~ 4~04672~ 7~07064~ 9~02428~ 12~05971~: 16~0622~ 17~01000~ [18 19] 20~05800~, 23~0622~ 26~0776~; 32~05074~ 34~03671~, 36~06475~ 38~06310~, 40~06850~.'),
  (175, 1, 7, 15, 'And they went in unto Noah into the ark, two and two of all flesh, wherein is the breath of life.', '3~0935~ 5~05146~ 8~08392~, 9~08147~ 11~08147~ 14~01320~, 15~0834~ [16] 18~07307~ 20~02416~.'),
  (19623, 24, 27, 18, 'But if they be prophets, and if the word of the LORD be with them, let them now make intercession to the LORD of hosts, that the vessels which are left in the house of the LORD, and in the house of the king of Judah, and at Jerusalem, go not to Babylon.', '[3] 4~05030~, 8~01697~ 11~03068~ 12~03426~ 19~06293~ 22~03068~ 24~06635~, 27~03627~ 30~03498~ 33~01004~ 36~03068~, [38] 40~01004~ 43~04428~ 45~03063~, 48~03389~, 49~0935~ 52~0894~.'),
  (1767, 2, 9, 20, 'He that feared the word of the LORD among the servants of Pharaoh made his servants and his cattle flee into the houses:', '2~03373~ 4~01697~ 7~03068~ 10~05650~ 12~06547~ 15~05650~ 18~04735~ 19~05127~ 22~01004~:'),
  (4411, 4, 22, 31, 'Then the LORD opened the eyes of Balaam, and he saw the angel of the LORD standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and he bowed down his head, and fell flat on his face.', '2~03068~ 3~01540~ 5~05869~ 7~01109~, 10~07200~ 12~04397~ 15~03068~ 16~05324~ 19~01870~, 22~02719~ 23~08025~ 26~03027~: 30~06915~ 35~07812~ 38~0639~.'),
  (9468, 11, 21, 9, 'And she wrote in the letters, saying, Proclaim a fast, and set Naboth on high among the people:', '2~03789~ 5~05612~, 6~0559~, 7~07121~ 9~06685~, 11~03427~ 12~05022~ 14~07218~ 17~05971~:'),
  (12252, 15, 9, 6, 'And said, O my God, I am ashamed and blush to lift up my face to thee, my God: for our iniquities are increased over our head, and our trespass is grown up unto the heavens.', '1~0559~, 4~0430~, 7~0954~ 9~03637~ 12~07311~ 14~06440~ 18~0430~: 21~05771~ 23~07235~ 24~04605~ [25] 26~07218~, 29~0819~ 32~01431~ 35~08064~.'),
  (10697, 13, 11, 16, 'And David was then in the hold, and the Philistines'' garrison was then at Bethlehem.', '1~01732~ [2] 6~04686~, 9~06430~ 10~05333~ [11] 14~01035~.'),
  (18649, 23, 49, 4, 'Then I said, I have laboured in vain, I have spent my strength for nought, and in vain: yet surely my judgment is with the LORD, and my work with my God.', '2~0559~, 5~03021~ 7~07385~, 10~03615~ 12~03581~ 14~08414~, 17~01892~: [18] 19~0403~ 21~04941~ [22] 25~03068~, 28~06468~ 31~0430~.'),
  (3287, 3, 19, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (11035, 13, 24, 12, 'The eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim,', '1~06240~ 2~06249~ 3~0475~, 5~06240~ 6~08147~ 7~03356~,'),
  (20413, 25, 3, 50, 'Till the LORD look down, and behold from heaven.', '2~03068~ 4~08259~, 6~07200~ 8~08064~.'),
  (17025, 20, 22, 1, 'A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches, and loving favour rather than silver and gold.', '&para; [1] 2~08034~ [3] 7~0977~ 9~07227~ 10~06239~, [11] 12~02896~ 13~02580~ 16~03701~ 18~02091~.'),
  (14693, 19, 50, 16, 'But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?', '&para; 3~07563~ 4~0430~ 5~0559~, 12~05608~ 14~02706~, [16] 19~05375~ 21~01285~ 24~06310~?'),
  (5577, 5, 26, 5, 'And thou shalt speak and say before the LORD thy God, A Syrian ready to perish was my father, and he went down into Egypt, and sojourned there with a few, and became there a nation, great, mighty, and populous:', '3~06030~ 5~0559~ 6~06440~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~, 12~0761~ 15~06~ [16] 18~01~, 22~03381~ 24~04714~, 26~01481~ 28~04962~ 30~04592~, 35~01471~, 36~01419~, 37~06099~, 39~07227~:'),
  (12791, 17, 5, 3, 'Then said the king unto her, What wilt thou, queen Esther? and what is thy request? it shall be even given thee to the half of the kingdom.', '1~0559~ 3~04428~ 9~04436~ 10~0635~? [13] 15~01246~? 20~05414~ 24~02677~ 27~04438~.'),
  (30985, 66, 16, 15, 'Behold, I come as a thief. Blessed is he that watcheth, and keepeth his garments, lest he walk naked, and they see his shame.', '0~2400~, 2~2064~ 3~5613~ 5~2812~. 6~3107~ [7] 10~1127~, 11~2532~ 12~5083~ 13~846~ 14~2440~, 15~3363~ 17~4043~ 18~1131~, 19~2532~ 21~991~ 22~846~ 23~808~.'),
  (17027, 20, 22, 3, 'A prudent man foreseeth the evil, and hideth himself: but the simple pass on, and are punished.', '&para; 1~06175~ [2] 3~07200~ 5~07451~, 7~05641~ 11~06612~ 13~05674~, 16~06064~.'),
  (9983, 12, 16, 12, 'And when the king was come from Damascus, the king saw the altar: and the king approached to the altar, and offered thereon.', '3~04428~ 5~0935~ 7~01834~, 9~04428~ 10~07200~ 12~04196~: 15~04428~ 16~07126~ 19~04196~, 21~05927~'),
  (8417, 10, 15, 21, 'And Ittai answered the king, and said, As the LORD liveth, and as my lord the king liveth, surely in what place my lord the king shall be, whether in death or life, even there also will thy servant be.', '1~0863~ 2~06030~ 4~04428~, 6~0559~, [7] 9~03068~ 10~02416~, [12] 14~0113~ 16~04428~ 17~02416~, 21~04725~ 23~0113~ 25~04428~ 30~04194~ 32~02416~, 38~05650~'),
  (10354, 13, 2, 40, 'And Eleasah begat Sisamai, and Sisamai begat Shallum,', '1~0501~ 2~03205~ 3~05581~, 5~05581~ 6~03205~ 7~07967~,'),
  (29441, 50, 3, 4, 'Though I might also have confidence in the flesh. If any other man thinketh that he hath whereof he might trust in the flesh, I more:', '&para; 0~2539~ 1~1473~ 2~2192~ 3~2532~ 4~2192~ 5~4006~ 6~1722~ 8~4561~. 10~1536~ 12~243~ 13~1380~ 20~3982~ 21~1722~ 23~4561~, 24~1473~ 25~3123~:'),
  (23397, 40, 9, 8, 'But when the multitude saw it, they marvelled, and glorified God, which had given such power unto men.', '0~1161~ 3~3793~ 4~1492~ [5] 7~2296~, 8~2532~ 9~1392~ 10~2316~, 11~3588~ 13~1325~ 14~5108~ 15~1849~ 17~444~.'),
  (30270, 58, 13, 13, 'Let us go forth therefore unto him without the camp, bearing his reproach.', '3~1831~ 4~5106~ 5~4314~ 6~846~ 7~1854~ 9~3925~, 10~5342~ 11~846~ 12~3680~.'),
  (24433, 41, 6, 16, 'But when Herod heard thereof, he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he is risen from the dead.', '0~1161~ 2~2264~ 3~191~ [4] 6~2036~, 7~3778~ 8~2076~ 9~2491~, 10~3739~ 11~3754~* 12~1473~ 13~607~: 14~846~ 16~1453~ 17~1537~ 19~3498~.'),
  (8594, 10, 21, 6, 'Let seven men of his sons be delivered unto us, and we will hang them up unto the LORD in Gibeah of Saul, whom the LORD did choose. And the king said, I will give them.', '1~07651~ 2~0582~ 5~01121~ 7~05414~ 15~03363~ 18~03068~ 20~01390~ 22~07586~, [23] 25~03068~ 27~0972~. 30~04428~ 31~0559~, 34~05414~ [35]'),
  (10619, 13, 8, 36, 'And Ahaz begat Jehoadah; and Jehoadah begat Alemeth, and Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri begat Moza,', '1~0271~ 2~03205~ 3~03085~; 5~03085~ 6~03205~ 7~05964~, 9~05820~, 11~02174~; 13~02174~ 14~03205~ 15~04162~,'),
  (6900, 7, 13, 9, 'And God hearkened to the voice of Manoah; and the angel of God came again unto the woman as she sat in the field: but Manoah her husband was not with her.', '1~0430~ 2~08085~ 5~06963~ 7~04495~; 10~04397~ 12~0430~ 14~0935~ 17~0802~ 20~03427~ 23~07704~: 25~04495~ 27~0376~ [28]'),
  (8362, 10, 13, 38, 'So Absalom fled, and went to Geshur, and was there three years.', '1~053~ 2~01272~, 4~03212~ 6~01650~, 10~07969~ 11~08141~.'),
  (644, 1, 24, 49, 'And now if ye will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me: and if not, tell me; that I may turn to the right hand, or to the left.', '4~03426~ 5~06213~ 6~02617~ 8~0571~ 11~0113~, 12~05046~ 17~05046~ 22~06437~ 26~03225~, 27~0176~ 30~08040~.'),
  (24352, 41, 4, 19, 'And the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lusts of other things entering in, choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.', '0~2532~ 2~3308~ 4~5127~ 5~165~, 6~2532~ 8~539~ 10~4149~, 11~2532~ 13~1939~ 14~4012~ 16~3062~ 18~1531~, 19~4846~ 21~3056~, 22~2532~ 24~1096~ 25~175~.'),
  (11597, 14, 20, 1, 'It came to pass after this also, that the children of Moab, and the children of Ammon, and with them other beside the Ammonites, came against Jehoshaphat to battle.', '&para; 5~0310~ [7] 9~01121~ 11~04124~, 14~01121~ 16~05983~, [20] 23~05984~, 24~0935~ 26~03092~ 28~04421~.'),
  (24324, 41, 3, 26, 'And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand, but hath an end.', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 2~4567~ 4~450~ 5~1909~ 6~1438~, 7~2532~ 9~3307~, 11~1410~ 12~3756~* 13~2476~, 14~235~ 15~2192~ 17~5056~.'),
  (16788, 20, 14, 7, 'Go from the presence of a foolish man, when thou perceivest not in him the lips of knowledge.', '&para; 0~03212~ 3~05048~ 6~03684~ 7~0376~, 10~03045~ [12 13] 15~08193~ 17~01847~.'),
  (27469, 44, 15, 11, 'But we believe that through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ we shall be saved, even as they.', '0~235~ 2~4100~ 4~1223~ 6~5485~ 9~2962~ 10~2424~ 11~5547~ 15~4982~, 16~3739~ 17~2596~* 18~5158~ 19~2548~.'),
  (7560, 9, 14, 45, 'And the people said unto Saul, Shall Jonathan die, who hath wrought this great salvation in Israel? God forbid: as the LORD liveth, there shall not one hair of his head fall to the ground; for he hath wrought with God this day. So the people rescued Jonathan, that he died not.', '2~05971~ 3~0559~ 5~07586~, 7~03129~ 8~04191~, 11~06213~ 13~01419~ 14~03444~ 16~03478~? 18~02486~: [19] 21~03068~ 22~02416~, 27~08185~ 30~07218~ 31~05307~ 34~0776~; 38~06213~ 40~0430~ 42~03117~. 45~05971~ 46~06299~ 47~03129~, 50~04191~'),
  (4672, 4, 31, 2, 'Avenge the children of Israel of the Midianites: afterward shalt thou be gathered unto thy people.', '0~05358~ 1~05360~* 3~01121~ 5~03478~ 8~04084~: 9~0310~ 13~0622~ 16~05971~.'),
  (19865, 24, 36, 14, 'Therefore all the princes sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, the son of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, unto Baruch, saying, Take in thine hand the roll wherein thou hast read in the ears of the people, and come. So Baruch the son of Neriah took the roll in his hand, and came unto them.', '3~08269~ 4~07971~ 5~03065~ 7~01121~ 9~05418~, 11~01121~ 13~08018~, 15~01121~ 17~03570~, 19~01263~, 20~0559~, 21~03947~ 24~03027~ 26~04039~ 30~07121~ 33~0241~ 36~05971~, 38~03212~. 40~01263~ 42~01121~ 44~05374~ 45~03947~ 47~04039~ 50~03027~, 52~0935~'),
  (23460, 40, 10, 33, 'But whosoever shall deny me before men, him will I also deny before my Father which is in heaven.', '0~1161~ 1~3748~ 2~302~ 3~720~ 4~3165~ 5~1715~ 6~444~, 7~846~ 10~2504~ 11~720~ 12~1715~ 13~3450~ 14~3962~ 15~3588~ 17~1722~ 18~3772~.'),
  (14116, 19, 17, 4, 'Concerning the works of men, by the word of thy lips I have kept me from the paths of the destroyer.', '2~06468~ 4~0120~, 7~01697~ 10~08193~ 13~08104~ [14 15] 17~0734~ 20~06530~.'),
  (17287, 20, 30, 27, 'The locusts have no king, yet go they forth all of them by bands;', '1~0697~ 4~04428~, 8~03318~ 13~02686~;'),
  (6961, 7, 16, 5, 'And the lords of the Philistines came up unto her, and said unto her, Entice him, and see wherein his great strength lieth, and by what means we may prevail against him, that we may bind him to afflict him: and we will give thee every one of us eleven hundred pieces of silver.', '2~05633~ 5~06430~ 7~05927~ 11~0559~ 14~06601~ 17~07200~ 20~01419~ 21~03581~ [22] [26] 29~03201~ 35~0631~ 38~06031~ 43~05414~ 46~0376~ 50~03967~ [51] 51~0505~ 53~03701~.'),
  (19913, 24, 38, 9, 'My lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they have done to Jeremiah the prophet, whom they have cast into the dungeon; and he is like to die for hunger in the place where he is: for there is no more bread in the city.', '1~0113~ 3~04428~, 5~0582~ 8~07489~ 14~06213~ 16~03414~ 18~05030~, 22~07993~ 25~0953~; 31~04191~ 32~06440~ 33~07458~ 36~08478~ [41 42] 45~03899~ 48~05892~.'),
  (25055, 42, 3, 18, 'And many other things in his exhortation preached he unto the people.', '0~3767~ 1~2532~* 2~4183~ 3~2087~ 4~3303~ 5~4183~ 7~3870~ 8~2097~ 12~2992~.'),
  (21864, 27, 4, 18, 'This dream I king Nebuchadnezzar have seen. Now thou, O Belteshazzar, declare the interpretation thereof, forasmuch as all the wise men of my kingdom are not able to make known unto me the interpretation: but thou art able; for the spirit of the holy gods is in thee.', '0~01836~ 1~02493~ 2~0576~ 3~04430~ 4~05020~ 6~02370~. 8~0607~, 10~01096~, 11~0560~ 13~06591~ 16~06903~ 17~03606~ 19~02445~ [20] 23~04437~ 25~03809~ 26~03202~ 29~03046~ 33~06591~: 35~0607~ [36] 37~03546~; 40~07308~ 43~06922~ 44~0426~ [45]'),
  (6800, 7, 9, 39, 'And Gaal went out before the men of Shechem, and fought with Abimelech.', '1~01603~ 3~03318~ 4~06440~ 6~01167~ 8~07927~, 10~03898~ 12~040~.'),
  (2886, 3, 7, 2, 'In the place where they kill the burnt offering shall they kill the trespass offering: and the blood thereof shall he sprinkle round about upon the altar.', '2~04725~ 5~07819~ 8~05930~ 11~07819~ 14~0817~: 17~01818~ 21~02236~ 23~05439~ 26~04196~.'),
  (13128, 18, 11, 11, 'For he knoweth vain men: he seeth wickedness also; will he not then consider it?', '2~03045~ 3~07723~ 4~04962~: 6~07200~ 7~0205~ 13~0995~ [14]'),
  (28627, 46, 11, 11, 'Nevertheless neither is the man without the woman, neither the woman without the man, in the Lord.', '0~4133~ 1~3777~ 4~435~ 5~5565~ 7~1135~, 8~3777~ 10~1135~ 11~5565~ 13~435~, 14~1722~ 16~2962~.'),
  (21232, 26, 30, 19, 'Thus will I execute judgments in Egypt: and they shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~06213~ 4~08201~ 6~04714~: 10~03045~ [13] 15~03068~.'),
  (6611, 7, 4, 5, 'And she dwelt under the palm tree of Deborah between Ramah and Bethel in mount Ephraim: and the children of Israel came up to her for judgment.', '2~03427~ 6~08560~ 8~01683~ 10~07414~ 12~01008~ 14~02022~ 15~0669~: 18~01121~ 20~03478~ 22~05927~ 26~04941~.'),
  (22714, 34, 2, 6, 'The gates of the rivers shall be opened, and the palace shall be dissolved.', '1~08179~ 4~05104~ 7~06605~, 10~01964~ 13~04127~.'),
  (3092, 3, 13, 35, 'But if the scall spread much in the skin after his cleansing;', '3~05424~ 4~06581~ 5~06581~ 8~05785~ 9~0310~ 11~02893~;'),
  (27305, 44, 10, 30, 'And Cornelius said, Four days ago I was fasting until this hour; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,', '0~2532~ 1~2883~ 2~5346~, 3~5067~ 4~2250~ 5~575~ 7~2252~ 8~3522~ 9~3360~ 10~5026~ 11~5610~; 12~2532~ 15~1766~ 16~5610~ 18~4336~ 19~1722~ 20~3450~ 21~3624~, 22~2532~, 23~2400~, 25~435~ 26~2476~ 27~1799~ 28~3450~ 29~1722~ 30~2986~ 31~2066~,'),
  (2481, 2, 33, 3, 'Unto a land flowing with milk and honey: for I will not go up in the midst of thee; for thou art a stiffnecked people: lest I consume thee in the way.', '2~0776~ 3~02100~ 5~02461~ 7~01706~: 13~05927~ 16~07130~ [21] 23~06203~ 24~07186~* 25~05971~: 28~03615~ 32~01870~.'),
  (16511, 20, 4, 12, 'When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.', '2~03212~, 4~06806~ 8~03334~; 12~07323~, 16~03782~.'),
  (14518, 19, 38, 19, 'But mine enemies are lively, and they are strong: and they that hate me wrongfully are multiplied.', '2~0341~ [3] 4~02416~, [5] 8~06105~: 12~08130~ 14~08267~ 16~07231~.'),
  (19874, 24, 36, 23, 'And it came to pass, that when Jehudi had read three or four leaves, he cut it with the penknife, and cast it into the fire that was on the hearth, until all the roll was consumed in the fire that was on the hearth.', '[5] 7~03065~ 9~07121~ 10~07969~ 12~0702~ 13~01817~, 15~07167~ 19~05608~ 20~08593~,* 22~07993~ [23] 26~0784~ [28] 31~0254~, 35~04039~ 37~08552~ 40~0784~ [42] 45~0254~.'),
  (30118, 58, 8, 10, 'For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, saith the Lord; I will put my laws into their mind, and write them in their hearts: and I will be to them a God, and they shall be to me a people:', '0~3754~ 1~3778~ [2] 4~1242~ 5~3739~ 8~1303~ 11~3624~ 13~2474~ 14~3326~ 15~1565~ 16~2250~, 17~3004~ 19~2962~; 22~1325~ 23~3450~ 24~3551~ 25~1519~ 26~846~ 27~1271~, 28~2532~ 29~1924~ 30~846~ 31~1909~ 32~846~ 33~2588~: 34~2532~ 37~2071~ 38~1519~ 39~846~ 41~2316~, 42~2532~ 43~846~ 45~2071~ 46~1519~ 47~3427~ 49~2992~:'),
  (1305, 1, 43, 10, 'For except we had lingered, surely now we had returned this second time.', '1~03884~ 4~04102~, 9~07725~ 12~06471~.'),
  (26423, 43, 8, 27, 'They understood not that he spake to them of the Father.', '1~1097~ 2~3756~ 3~3754~ 5~3004~ 7~846~ 10~3962~.');
