VALUES
  (10777, 13, 13, 9, 'And when they came unto the threshingfloor of Chidon, Uzza put forth his hand to hold the ark; for the oxen stumbled.', '&para; 3~0935~ 6~01637~ 8~03592~, 9~05798~ 11~07971~ 13~03027~ 15~0270~ 17~0727~; 20~01241~ 21~08058~.'),
  (14973, 19, 69, 29, 'But I am poor and sorrowful: let thy salvation, O God, set me up on high.', '[2] 3~06041~ 5~03510~: 8~03444~, 10~0430~, 15~07682~.'),
  (23333, 40, 7, 7, 'Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you:', '&para; 0~154~, 1~2532~ 5~1325~ 6~5213~; 7~2212~, 8~2532~ 11~2147~; 12~2925~, 13~2532~ 17~455~ 19~5213~:'),
  (13691, 18, 33, 32, 'If thou hast any thing to say, answer me: speak, for I desire to justify thee.', '2~03426~ 6~04405~, 7~07725~ 9~01696~, 12~02654~ 14~06663~'),
  (30949, 66, 14, 7, 'Saying with a loud voice, Fear God, and give glory to him; for the hour of his judgment is come: and worship him that made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and the fountains of waters.', '0~3004~ 1~1722~ 3~3173~ 4~5456~, 5~5399~ 6~2316~, 7~2532~ 8~1325~ 9~1391~ 11~846~; 12~3754~ 14~5610~ 16~846~ 17~2920~ 19~2064~: 20~2532~ 21~4352~ 24~4160~ 25~3772~, 26~2532~ 27~1093~, 28~2532~ 30~2281~, 31~2532~ 33~4077~ 35~5204~.'),
  (14919, 19, 68, 10, 'Thy congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.', '1~02416~ 3~03427~ 7~0430~, 9~03559~ 12~02896~ 15~06041~.'),
  (16682, 20, 10, 17, 'He is in the way of life that keepeth instruction: but he that refuseth reproof erreth.', '&para; [1 2] 4~0734~ 6~02416~ 8~08104~ 9~04148~: 13~05800~ 14~08433~ 15~08582~.'),
  (20729, 26, 13, 12, 'Lo, when the wall is fallen, shall it not be said unto you, Where is the daubing wherewith ye have daubed it?', '3~07023~ 5~05307~, 10~0559~ [14] 16~02915~ 20~02902~ [21]'),
  (25206, 42, 6, 48, 'He is like a man which built an house, and digged deep, and laid the foundation on a rock: and when the flood arose, the stream beat vehemently upon that house, and could not shake it: for it was founded upon a rock.', '1~2076~ 2~3664~ 4~444~ 5~3739~ 6~3618~ 8~3614~, 9~2532~ 10~4626~ 11~900~, 12~2532~ 13~5087~ 15~2310~ 16~1909~ 18~4073~: 19~1161~ 22~4132~ 23~1096~, 25~4215~ 27~4366~ 29~1565~ 30~3614~, 31~2532~ 32~2480~ 33~3756~ 34~4531~ 35~846~: 36~1063~ 39~2311~ 40~1909~ 42~4073~.'),
  (22020, 27, 9, 23, 'At the beginning of thy supplications the commandment came forth, and I am come to shew thee; for thou art greatly beloved: therefore understand the matter, and consider the vision.', '2~08462~ 5~08469~ 7~01697~ 9~03318~, 13~0935~ 15~05046~ [16] [19] 21~02532~: 23~0995~ 25~01697~, 27~0995~ 29~04758~.'),
  (6508, 6, 24, 25, 'So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and set them a statute and an ordinance in Shechem.', '1~03091~ 2~03772~ 4~01285~ 7~05971~ 9~03117~, 11~07760~ 14~02706~ 17~04941~ 19~07927~.'),
  (24372, 41, 4, 39, 'And he arose, and rebuked the wind, and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.', '0~2532~ 2~1326~, 4~2008~ 6~417~, 7~2532~ 8~2036~ 11~2281~, 12~4623~, 14~5392~. 15~2532~ 17~417~ 18~2869~, 19~2532~ 21~1096~ 23~3173~ 24~1055~.'),
  (3208, 3, 16, 2, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Speak unto Aaron thy brother, that he come not at all times into the holy place within the veil before the mercy seat, which is upon the ark; that he die not: for I will appear in the cloud upon the mercy seat.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~01696~ 8~0175~ 10~0251~, 13~0935~ 17~06256~ 20~06944~ [21] 22~01004~ 24~06532~ 25~06440~ 28~03727~, [30] 33~0727~; 36~04191~ 41~07200~ 44~06051~ 47~03727~'),
  (27488, 44, 15, 30, 'So when they were dismissed, they came to Antioch: and when they had gathered the multitude together, they delivered the epistle:', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 4~630~, 6~2064~ 7~1519~ 8~490~: 9~2532~ 13~4863~ 15~4128~ 16~4863~, 18~1929~ 20~1992~:'),
  (27542, 44, 17, 3, 'Opening and alleging, that Christ must needs have suffered, and risen again from the dead; and that this Jesus, whom I preach unto you, is Christ.', '0~1272~ 1~2532~ 2~3908~, 3~3754~ 4~5547~ 6~1163~ 8~3958~, 9~2532~ 11~450~ 12~1537~ 14~3498~; 15~2532~ 16~3754~ 17~3778~ 18~2424~, 19~3739~ 20~1473~ 21~2605~ 23~5213~, 24~2076~ 25~5547~.'),
  (18864, 23, 62, 1, 'For Zion''s sake will I not hold my peace, and for Jerusalem''s sake I will not rest, until the righteousness thereof go forth as brightness, and the salvation thereof as a lamp that burneth.', '&para; 1~06726~ 8~02814~, 11~03389~ 16~08252~, 19~06664~ 22~03318~ 24~05051~, 27~03444~ 31~03940~ [32] 33~01197~.'),
  (26160, 43, 3, 25, 'Then there arose a question between some of John''s disciples and the Jews about purifying.', '0~3767~ 2~1096~ 4~2214~ 5~3326~ [6] 7~1537~ 8~2491~ 9~3101~ 12~2453~ 13~4012~ 14~2512~.'),
  (13465, 18, 24, 20, 'The womb shall forget him; the worm shall feed sweetly on him; he shall be no more remembered; and wickedness shall be broken as a tree.', '1~07358~ 3~07911~ 6~07415~ 9~04988~ 17~02142~; 19~05766~ 22~07665~ 25~06086~.'),
  (9707, 12, 6, 25, 'And there was a great famine in Samaria: and, behold, they besieged it, until an ass''s head was sold for fourscore pieces of silver, and the fourth part of a cab of dove''s dung for five pieces of silver.', '4~01419~ 5~07458~ 7~08111~: 11~06696~ 15~02543~ 16~07218~ [18] 20~08084~ [21] 23~03701~, 27~07255~ 30~06894~ 33~01686~ 34~02755~* 35~03123~ 36~02568~ [37] 39~03701~.'),
  (3105, 3, 13, 48, 'Whether it be in the warp, or woof; of linen, or of woollen; whether in a skin, or in any thing made of skin;', '[1 2] 5~08359~, 7~06154~; 9~06593~, 12~06785~; 16~05785~, 21~04399~ 23~05785~;'),
  (22924, 38, 3, 3, 'Now Joshua was clothed with filthy garments, and stood before the angel.', '1~03091~ 3~03847~ 5~06674~ 6~0899~, 8~05975~ 9~06440~ 11~04397~.'),
  (23481, 40, 11, 12, 'And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffereth violence, and the violent take it by force.', '0~1161~ 1~575~ 3~2250~ 5~2491~ 7~910~ 8~2193~ 9~737~ 11~932~ 13~3772~ 15~971~, 16~2532~ 18~973~ 19~726~ 20~846~ 22~726~.'),
  (11012, 13, 23, 21, 'The sons of Merari; Mahli, and Mushi. The sons of Mahli; Eleazar, and Kish.', '1~01121~ 3~04847~; 4~04249~, 6~04187~. 8~01121~ 10~04249~; 11~0499~, 13~07027~.'),
  (6371, 6, 19, 43, 'And Elon, and Thimnathah, and Ekron,', '1~0356~, 3~08553~, 5~06138~,'),
  (13645, 18, 32, 8, 'But there is a spirit in man: and the inspiration of the Almighty giveth them understanding.', '0~0403~ [1 2] 4~07307~ 6~0582~: 9~05397~ 12~07706~ 15~0995~.'),
  (9334, 11, 17, 9, 'Arise, get thee to Zarephath, which belongeth to Zidon, and dwell there: behold, I have commanded a widow woman there to sustain thee.', '0~06965~, 1~03212~ 4~06886~, [6] 8~06721~, 10~03427~ 15~06680~ 17~0490~ 18~0802~ 21~03557~'),
  (23095, 38, 14, 18, 'And if the family of Egypt go not up, and come not, that have no rain; there shall be the plague, wherewith the LORD will smite the heathen that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles.', '3~04940~ 5~04714~ 8~05927~, 10~0935~ [13] [15] 20~04046~, 23~03068~ 25~05062~ 27~01471~ 31~05927~ 33~02287~ 35~02282~ 37~05521~.'),
  (25302, 42, 8, 45, 'And Jesus said, Who touched me? When all denied, Peter and they that were with him said, Master, the multitude throng thee and press thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~, 3~5101~ 4~680~ 5~3450~? 6~1161~ 7~3956~ 8~720~, 9~4074~ 10~2532~ 14~3326~ 15~846~ 16~2036~, 17~1988~, 19~3793~ 20~4912~ 21~4571~ 22~2532~ 23~598~ [24] 25~2532~ 26~3004~ 28~5101~ 29~680~ 30~3450~?'),
  (23096, 38, 14, 19, 'This shall be the punishment of Egypt, and the punishment of all nations that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles.', '4~02403~ 6~04714~, 9~02403~ 12~01471~ 16~05927~ 18~02287~ 20~02282~ 22~05521~.'),
  (13383, 18, 21, 19, 'God layeth up his iniquity for his children: he rewardeth him, and he shall know it.', '0~0433~ 2~06845~ 4~0205~ 7~01121~: 9~07999~ 14~03045~ [15]'),
  (18569, 23, 44, 27, 'That saith to the deep, Be dry, and I will dry up thy rivers:', '1~0559~ 4~06683~, 6~02717~, 11~03001~ 13~05104~:'),
  (4484, 4, 25, 8, 'And he went after the man of Israel into the tent, and thrust both of them through, the man of Israel, and the woman through her belly. So the plague was stayed from the children of Israel.', '2~0935~ 3~0310~ 5~0376~ 7~03478~ 10~06898~, 12~01856~ 13~08147~ 18~0376~ 20~03478~, 23~0802~ 24~0413~ 26~06897~. 29~04046~ 31~06113~ 34~01121~ 36~03478~.'),
  (2432, 2, 31, 7, 'The tabernacle of the congregation, and the ark of the testimony, and the mercy seat that is thereupon, and all the furniture of the tabernacle,', '1~0168~ 4~04150~, 7~0727~ 10~05715~, 14~03727~ [16] 21~03627~ 24~0168~,'),
  (10124, 12, 20, 18, 'And of thy sons that shall issue from thee, which thou shalt beget, shall they take away; and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.', '3~01121~ 6~03318~ 12~03205~, 16~03947~; 21~05631~ 24~01964~ 27~04428~ 29~0894~.'),
  (26792, 43, 17, 18, 'As thou hast sent me into the world, even so have I also sent them into the world.', '0~2531~ 3~649~ 4~1691~ 5~1519~ 7~2889~, 9~2504~ 10~649~ 12~2504~ 13~649~ 14~846~ 15~1519~ 17~2889~.'),
  (11016, 13, 23, 25, 'For David said, The LORD God of Israel hath given rest unto his people, that they may dwell in Jerusalem for ever:', '1~01732~ 2~0559~, 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~03478~ 10~05117~ 13~05971~, 17~07931~ 19~03389~ 21~05769~:'),
  (1044, 1, 35, 28, 'And the days of Isaac were an hundred and fourscore years.', '2~03117~ 4~03327~ 7~08141~ 8~03967~ 9~08084~ 10~08141~.'),
  (124, 1, 5, 18, 'And Jared lived an hundred sixty and two years, and he begat Enoch:', '1~03382~ 2~02421~ 4~03967~ 5~08141~ 6~08346~ 7~08147~ 8~08141~, 11~03205~ 12~02585~:'),
  (19579, 24, 25, 36, 'A voice of the cry of the shepherds, and an howling of the principal of the flock, shall be heard: for the LORD hath spoiled their pasture.', '1~06963~ 4~06818~ 7~07462~, 10~03215~ 13~0117~ 16~06629~, [17 19] 22~03068~ 24~07703~ 26~04830~.'),
  (20541, 26, 4, 3, 'Moreover take thou unto thee an iron pan, and set it for a wall of iron between thee and the city: and set thy face against it, and it shall be besieged, and thou shalt lay siege against it. This shall be a sign to the house of Israel.', '1~03947~ 6~01270~ 7~04227~, 9~05414~ [11] 13~07023~ 15~01270~ 20~05892~: 22~03559~ 24~06440~ 31~04692~, 36~06696~ [40 41] 43~0226~ 46~01004~ 48~03478~.'),
  (3542, 3, 26, 13, 'I am the LORD your God, which brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, that ye should not be their bondmen; and I have broken the bands of your yoke, and made you go upright.', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~, 9~03318~ 13~0776~ 15~04714~, 22~05650~; 26~07665~ 28~04133~ 31~05923~, 35~03212~ 36~06968~.'),
  (9015, 11, 8, 22, 'And Solomon stood before the altar of the LORD in the presence of all the congregation of Israel, and spread forth his hands toward heaven:', '&para; 1~08010~ 2~05975~ 3~06440~ 5~04196~ 8~03068~ 12~05048~ 15~06951~ 17~03478~, 20~06566~ 22~03709~ 24~08064~:'),
  (28991, 47, 10, 4, '(For the weapons of our warfare are not carnal, but mighty through God to the pulling down of strong holds;)', '0~(1063~ 2~3696~ 4~2257~ 5~4752~ [6] 7~3756~ 8~4559~, 9~235~ 10~1415~ 12~2316~ 13~4314~ 16~2506~ 19~3794~;)'),
  (1590, 2, 3, 6, 'Moreover he said, I am the God of thy father, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob. And Moses hid his face; for he was afraid to look upon God.', '2~0559~, [4] 6~0430~ 9~01~, 11~0430~ 13~085~, 15~0430~ 17~03327~, 20~0430~ 22~03290~. 24~04872~ 25~05641~ 27~06440~; 31~03372~ 33~05027~ 35~0430~.'),
  (21348, 26, 34, 26, 'And I will make them and the places round about my hill a blessing; and I will cause the shower to come down in his season; there shall be showers of blessing.', '3~05414~ 9~05439~ 11~01389~ 13~01293~; 19~01653~ 22~03381~ 25~06256~; 29~01653~ 31~01293~.'),
  (9047, 11, 8, 54, 'And it was so, that when Solomon had made an end of praying all this prayer and supplication unto the LORD, he arose from before the altar of the LORD, from kneeling on his knees with his hands spread up to heaven.', '&para; [3] 6~08010~ 10~03615~ 12~06419~ 15~08605~ 17~08467~ 20~03068~, 22~06965~ 24~06440~ 26~04196~ 29~03068~, 31~03766~ 34~01290~ 37~03709~ 39~06566~ 41~08064~.'),
  (5278, 5, 12, 32, 'What thing soever I command you, observe to do it: thou shalt not add thereto, nor diminish from it.', '1~01697~ 4~06680~ 6~08104~ 8~06213~ 13~03254~ 16~01639~'),
  (21168, 26, 28, 2, 'Son of man, say unto the prince of Tyrus, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Because thine heart is lifted up, and thou hast said, I am a God, I sit in the seat of God, in the midst of the seas; yet thou art a man, and not God, though thou set thine heart as the heart of God:', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 3~0559~ 6~05057~ 8~06865~, 10~0559~ 12~0136~ 13~03069~; 16~03820~ [17] 19~01361~, 23~0559~, [25] 27~0410~, 29~03427~ [30] 32~04186~ 34~0430~, 37~03820~ 40~03220~; [43] 45~0120~, 48~0410~, 51~05414~ 53~03820~ 56~03820~ 58~0430~:'),
  (17528, 21, 11, 6, 'In the morning sow thy seed, and in the evening withhold not thine hand: for thou knowest not whether shall prosper, either this or that, or whether they both shall be alike good.', '2~01242~ 3~02232~ 5~02233~, 9~06153~ 10~03240~ 13~03027~: 16~03045~ 18~0335~ 20~03787~, 28~08147~ [29 30] 31~0259~ 32~02896~.'),
  (19162, 24, 7, 34, 'Then will I cause to cease from the cities of Judah, and from the streets of Jerusalem, the voice of mirth, and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom, and the voice of the bride: for the land shall be desolate.', '5~07673~ 8~05892~ 10~03063~, 14~02351~ 16~03389~, 18~06963~ 20~08342~, 23~06963~ 25~08057~, 27~06963~ 30~02860~, 33~06963~ 36~03618~: 39~0776~ 42~02723~.'),
  (27768, 44, 23, 18, 'So he took him, and brought him to the chief captain, and said, Paul the prisoner called me unto him, and prayed me to bring this young man unto thee, who hath something to say unto thee.', '0~3303~ 1~3767~ 2~3880~ 3~846~, 5~71~ [6] 7~4314~ 10~5506~, 11~2532~ 12~5346~, 13~3972~ 15~1198~ 16~4341~ 17~3165~ [19] 22~2065~ 24~71~ 25~5126~ 27~3494~ 28~4314~ 29~4571~, 31~2192~ 32~5100~ 34~2980~ 36~4671~.'),
  (11091, 13, 26, 6, 'Also unto Shemaiah his son were sons born, that ruled throughout the house of their father: for they were mighty men of valour.', '2~08098~ 4~01121~ 6~01121~ 7~03205~, 9~04474~ 12~01004~ 15~01~: [18] 20~01368~ 22~02428~.'),
  (5109, 5, 6, 17, 'Ye shall diligently keep the commandments of the LORD your God, and his testimonies, and his statutes, which he hath commanded thee.', '&para; 2~08104~ 3~08104~ 5~04687~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~, 13~05713~, 16~02706~, 20~06680~'),
  (20229, 24, 51, 8, 'Babylon is suddenly fallen and destroyed: howl for her; take balm for her pain, if so be she may be healed.', '0~0894~ 2~06597~ 3~05307~ 5~07665~: 6~03213~ 9~03947~ 10~06875~ 13~04341~, 20~07495~.'),
  (25889, 42, 22, 11, 'And ye shall say unto the goodman of the house, The Master saith unto thee, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?', '0~2532~ 3~2046~ 6~3617~ 9~3614~, 11~1320~ 12~3004~ 14~4671~, 15~4226~ 16~2076~ 18~2646~, 19~3699~ 22~5315~ 24~3957~ 25~3326~ 26~3450~ 27~3101~?'),
  (31029, 66, 18, 20, 'Rejoice over her, thou heaven, and ye holy apostles and prophets; for God hath avenged you on her.', '0~2165~ 1~1909~ 2~846~, [3] 4~3772~, 5~2532~ [6] 7~40~ 8~652~ 9~2532~ 10~4396~; 11~3754~ 12~2316~ 14~2919~ 15~2917~* 16~5216~ 17~1537~ 18~846~.'),
  (16735, 20, 12, 7, 'The wicked are overthrown, and are not: but the house of the righteous shall stand.', '&para; 1~07563~ 3~02015~, [5] 9~01004~ 12~06662~ 14~05975~.'),
  (9997, 12, 17, 6, 'In the ninth year of Hoshea the king of Assyria took Samaria, and carried Israel away into Assyria, and placed them in Halah and in Habor by the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes.', '2~08671~ 3~08141~ 5~01954~ 7~04428~ 9~0804~ 10~03920~ 11~08111~, 13~01540~ 14~03478~ 15~01540~ 17~0804~, 19~03427~ 22~02477~ 25~02249~ [26] 28~05104~ 30~01470~, 34~05892~ 37~04074~.'),
  (16348, 19, 145, 19, 'He will fulfil the desire of them that fear him: he also will hear their cry, and will save them.', '2~06213~ 4~07522~ 8~03373~ 13~08085~ 15~07775~, 18~03467~'),
  (30566, 62, 1, 10, 'If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.', '0~1437~ 2~2036~ 3~3754~ 5~264~ 6~3756~ 7~264~, 9~4160~ 10~846~ 12~5583~, 13~2532~ 14~846~ 15~3056~ 16~2076~ 17~3756~ 18~1722~ 19~2254~.'),
  (2518, 2, 34, 17, 'Thou shalt make thee no molten gods.', '2~06213~ 5~04541~ 6~0430~.'),
  (12541, 16, 9, 21, 'Yea, forty years didst thou sustain them in the wilderness, so that they lacked nothing; their clothes waxed not old, and their feet swelled not.', '1~0705~ 2~08141~ 5~03557~ 9~04057~, [10 11] 13~02637~ 16~08008~ 19~01086~, 22~07272~ 23~01216~'),
  (15399, 19, 90, 12, 'So teach us to number our days, that we may apply our hearts unto wisdom.', '&para; 1~03045~ [2] 4~04487~ 6~03117~, 10~0935~ [11] 12~03824~ 14~02451~.'),
  (9551, 12, 1, 10, 'And Elijah answered and said to the captain of fifty, If I be a man of God, then let fire come down from heaven, and consume thee and thy fifty. And there came down fire from heaven, and consumed him and his fifty.', '1~0452~ 2~06030~ 4~01696~ 7~08269~ 9~02572~, [12] 14~0376~ 16~0430~, 19~0784~ 21~03381~ 23~08064~, 25~0398~ 29~02572~. 33~03381~ 34~0784~ 36~08064~, 38~0398~ 42~02572~.'),
  (11058, 13, 25, 4, 'Of Heman: the sons of Heman; Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamtiezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth:', '1~01968~: 3~01121~ 5~01968~; 6~01232~, 7~04983~, 8~05816~, 9~07619~, 11~03406~, 12~02608~, 13~02607~, 14~0448~, 15~01437~, 17~07320~, 18~03436~, 19~04413~, 20~01956~, [21] 22~04238~:'),
  (24563, 41, 9, 14, 'And when he came to his disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them.', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~2064~ 4~4314~ [5] 6~3101~, 8~1492~ 10~4183~ 11~3793~ 12~4012~ 13~846~, 14~2532~ 16~1122~ 17~4802~ 19~846~.'),
  (6728, 7, 8, 2, 'And he said unto them, What have I done now in comparison of you? Is not the gleaning of the grapes of Ephraim better than the vintage of Abiezer?', '2~0559~ 8~06213~ [14] 17~05955~ 22~0669~ 23~02896~ 26~01210~ 28~044~?'),
  (27006, 44, 2, 41, 'Then they that gladly received his word were baptized: and the same day there were added unto them about three thousand souls.', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 3~780~ 4~588~ 5~846~ 6~3056~ 8~907~: 9~2532~ 11~1565~ 12~2250~ 15~4369~ [16 17] 18~5616~ 20~5153~ 21~5590~.'),
  (28461, 46, 4, 12, 'And labour, working with our own hands: being reviled, we bless; being persecuted, we suffer it:', '0~2532~ 1~2872~, 2~2038~ 5~2398~ 6~5495~: 8~3058~, 10~2127~; 12~1377~, 15~430~:'),
  (28171, 45, 8, 39, 'Nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.', '0~3777~ 1~5313~, 2~3777~ 3~899~, 4~3777~ 5~5100~ 6~2087~ 7~2937~, 10~1410~ 12~5563~ 13~2248~ 14~575~ 16~26~ 18~2316~, 21~1722~ 22~5547~ 23~2424~ 24~2257~ 25~2962~.'),
  (2768, 3, 2, 1, 'And when any will offer a meat offering unto the LORD, his offering shall be of fine flour; and he shall pour oil upon it, and put frankincense thereon:', '&para; 2~05315~ 4~07126~ 6~04503~ 7~07133~ 10~03068~, 12~07133~ [15] 17~05560~; 21~03332~ 22~08081~ 26~05414~ 27~03828~'),
  (3660, 4, 1, 51, 'And when the tabernacle setteth forward, the Levites shall take it down: and when the tabernacle is to be pitched, the Levites shall set it up: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.', '3~04908~ 5~05265~, 7~03881~ 11~03381~: 15~04908~ 19~02583~, 21~03881~ 25~06965~: 28~02114~ 31~07131~ 36~04191~.'),
  (19751, 24, 32, 11, 'So I took the evidence of the purchase, both that which was sealed according to the law and custom, and that which was open:', '2~03947~ 4~05612~ 7~04736~, [8] 12~02856~ [13] 16~04687~ 18~02706~, 23~01540~:'),
  (28406, 46, 1, 27, 'But God hath chosen the foolish things of the world to confound the wise; and God hath chosen the weak things of the world to confound the things which are mighty;', '0~235~ 1~2316~ 3~1586~ 6~3474~ 9~2889~ 10~2443~ 11~2617~ 13~4680~; 14~2532~ 15~2316~ 17~1586~ 20~772~ 23~2889~ 24~2443~ 25~2617~ 30~2478~;'),
  (16840, 20, 15, 24, 'The way of life is above to the wise, that he may depart from hell beneath.', '&para; 1~0734~ 3~02416~ [4] 5~04605~ 8~07919~, 12~05493~ 14~07585~ 15~04295~.'),
  (28949, 47, 8, 1, 'Moreover, brethren, we do you to wit of the grace of God bestowed on the churches of Macedonia;', '&para; 0~1161~, 1~80~, 3~1107~ 4~5213~ 6~1107~ 9~5485~ 11~2316~ 12~1325~ 13~1722~ 15~1577~ 17~3109~;'),
  (9821, 12, 10, 20, 'And Jehu said, Proclaim a solemn assembly for Baal. And they proclaimed it.', '1~03058~ 2~0559~, 3~06942~ 6~06116~ 8~01168~. 11~07121~ [12]'),
  (3321, 3, 19, 35, 'Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment, in meteyard, in weight, or in measure.', '2~06213~ 4~05766~ 6~04941~, 8~04060~, 10~04948~, 13~04884~.'),
  (7090, 7, 20, 29, 'And Israel set liers in wait round about Gibeah.', '1~03478~ 2~07760~ 5~0693~ 7~05439~ 8~01390~.'),
  (26351, 43, 7, 8, 'Go ye up unto this feast: I go not up yet unto this feast: for my time is not yet full come.', '0~305~ 1~5210~ 2~305~ 3~1519~ 4~5026~ 5~1859~: 6~1473~ 7~305~ 8~3768~ 9~305~ 10~3768~ 11~1519~ 12~5026~ 13~1859~; 14~3754~ 15~1699~ 16~2540~ 17~4137~ 19~3768~ 21~4137~.'),
  (28498, 46, 6, 15, 'Know ye not that your bodies are the members of Christ? shall I then take the members of Christ, and make them the members of an harlot? God forbid.', '1~1492~ 2~3756~ 3~3754~ 4~5216~ 5~4983~ 6~2076~ 8~3196~ 10~5547~? 12~142~ 13~3767~ 14~142~ 16~3196~ 18~5547~, 20~4160~ [21] 23~3196~ 26~4204~? 28~1096~ 29~3361~.*'),
  (16748, 20, 12, 20, 'Deceit is in the heart of them that imagine evil: but to the counsellors of peace is joy.', '&para; 0~04820~ [1] 4~03820~ 8~02790~ 9~07451~: 13~03289~ 15~07965~ [16] 17~08057~.'),
  (26433, 43, 8, 37, 'I know that ye are Abraham''s seed; but ye seek to kill me, because my word hath no place in you.', '1~1492~ 2~3754~ 4~2075~ 5~11~ 6~4690~; 7~235~ 9~2212~ 11~615~ 12~3165~, 13~3754~ 14~1699~ 15~3056~ 16~5562~ 17~3756~ 18~5562~ 19~1722~ 20~5213~.'),
  (5887, 6, 2, 12, 'Now therefore, I pray you, swear unto me by the LORD, since I have shewed you kindness, that ye will also shew kindness unto my father''s house, and give me a true token:', '5~07650~ 10~03068~, 11~03588~ 14~06213~ 16~02617~, 21~06213~ 22~02617~ 25~01~ 26~01004~, 28~05414~ 31~0571~ 32~0226~:'),
  (7712, 9, 18, 29, 'And Saul was yet the more afraid of David; and Saul became David''s enemy continually.', '1~07586~ 5~03254~ 6~03372~ 7~06440~ 8~01732~; 10~07586~ 12~01732~ 13~0341~ 14~03117~.'),
  (26571, 43, 11, 33, 'When Jesus therefore saw her weeping, and the Jews also weeping which came with her, he groaned in the spirit, and was troubled,', '&para; 0~5613~ 1~2424~ 2~3767~ 3~1492~ 4~846~ 5~2799~, 6~2532~ 8~2453~ 10~2799~ 12~4905~ 14~846~, 16~1690~ 19~4151~, 20~2532~ 22~5015~ 23~1438~,*'),
  (20418, 25, 3, 55, 'I called upon thy name, O LORD, out of the low dungeon.', '&para; 1~07121~ 4~08034~, 6~03068~, 10~08482~ 11~0953~.'),
  (26516, 43, 10, 20, 'And many of them said, He hath a devil, and is mad; why hear ye him?', '0~1161~ 1~4183~ 2~1537~ 3~846~ 4~3004~, 6~2192~ 8~1140~, 9~2532~ 11~3105~; 12~5101~ 14~191~ 15~846~?'),
  (24461, 41, 6, 44, 'And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men.', '0~2532~ 4~5315~ 7~740~ 8~2258~ 9~5616~ 11~4000~ 12~435~.'),
  (9098, 11, 10, 11, 'And the navy also of Hiram, that brought gold from Ophir, brought in from Ophir great plenty of almug trees, and precious stones.', '2~0590~ 5~02438~, 7~05375~ 8~02091~ 10~0211~, 12~0935~ 14~0211~ 15~03966~ 16~07235~ 18~0484~ 19~06086~, 21~03368~ 22~068~.'),
  (11525, 14, 16, 7, 'And at that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah, and said unto him, Because thou hast relied on the king of Syria, and not relied on the LORD thy God, therefore is the host of the king of Syria escaped out of thine hand.', '&para; 3~06256~ 4~02607~ 6~07200~ 7~0935~ 9~0609~ 10~04428~ 12~03063~, 14~0559~ 20~08172~ 23~04428~ 25~0758~, 28~08172~ 31~03068~ 33~0430~, 37~02428~ 40~04428~ 42~0758~ 43~04422~ 47~03027~.'),
  (11714, 14, 25, 1, 'Amaziah was twenty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty and nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem.', '&para; 0~0558~ [1] 2~06242~ 4~02568~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ [7] 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06242~ 17~08672~ 18~08141~ 20~03389~. 23~0517~ 24~08034~ [25] 26~03086~ 28~03389~.'),
  (3670, 4, 2, 7, 'Then the tribe of Zebulun: and Eliab the son of Helon shall be captain of the children of Zebulun.', '[0] 2~04294~ 4~02074~: 6~0446~ 8~01121~ 10~02497~ [11 12] 13~05387~ 16~01121~ 18~02074~.'),
  (18599, 23, 46, 4, 'And even to your old age I am he; and even to hoar hairs will I carry you: I have made, and I will bear; even I will carry, and will deliver you.', '[1] [3] 5~02209~ [7] [10] 13~07872~ 16~05445~ [17] 20~06213~, 24~05375~; 28~05445~, 31~04422~ [32]'),
  (4545, 4, 26, 50, 'These are the families of Naphtali according to their families: and they that were numbered of them were forty and five thousand and four hundred.', '[1] 3~04940~ 5~05321~ 9~04940~: 14~06485~ [17] 18~0705~ 20~02568~ 21~0505~ 23~0702~ 24~03967~.'),
  (3152, 3, 14, 36, 'Then the priest shall command that they empty the house, before the priest go into it to see the plague, that all that is in the house be not made unclean: and afterward the priest shall go in to see the house:', '2~03548~ 4~06680~ 7~06437~ 9~01004~, 12~03548~ 13~0935~ [14 15] 17~07200~ 19~05061~, [23] 26~01004~ 30~02930~: 32~0310~ 34~03548~ 36~0935~ 39~07200~ 41~01004~:'),
  (23714, 40, 17, 4, 'Then answered Peter, and said unto Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here: if thou wilt, let us make here three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.', '0~1161~ 1~611~ 2~4074~, 4~2036~ 6~2424~, 7~2962~, 9~2076~ 10~2570~ 12~2248~ 14~1511~ 15~5602~: 16~1487~ 18~2309~, 21~4160~ 22~5602~ 23~5140~ 24~4633~; 25~3391~ 27~4671~, 28~2532~ 29~3391~ 31~3475~, 32~2532~ 33~3391~ 35~2243~.'),
  (12089, 15, 2, 53, 'The children of Barkos, the children of Sisera, the children of Thamah,', '1~01121~ 3~01302~, 5~01121~ 7~05516~, 9~01121~ 11~08547~,'),
  (17315, 20, 31, 22, 'She maketh herself coverings of tapestry; her clothing is silk and purple.', '1~06213~ 5~04765~; 7~03830~ [8] 9~08336~ 11~0713~.'),
  (16541, 20, 5, 15, 'Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.', '&para; 0~08354~ 1~04325~ 6~0953~, 9~05140~ 11~08432~ 14~0875~.');
