  (23716, 40, 17, 6, 'And when the disciples heard it, they fell on their face, and were sore afraid.', '0~2532~ 3~3101~ 4~191~ [5] 7~4098~ 8~1909~ 9~846~ 10~4383~, 11~2532~ 13~4970~ 14~5399~.'),
  (9910, 12, 14, 6, 'But the children of the murderers he slew not: according unto that which is written in the book of the law of Moses, wherein the LORD commanded, saying, The fathers shall not be put to death for the children, nor the children be put to death for the fathers; but every man shall be put to death for his own sin.', '2~01121~ 5~05221~ 7~04191~ 14~03789~ 17~05612~ 20~08451~ 22~04872~, 25~03068~ 26~06680~, 27~0559~, 29~01~ 35~04191~ 38~01121~, 41~01121~ 45~04191~ 48~01~; 51~0376~ 56~04191~ 60~02399~.'),
  (25657, 42, 16, 23, 'And in hell he lift up his eyes, being in torments, and seeth Abraham afar off, and Lazarus in his bosom.', '0~2532~ 1~1722~ 2~86~ 5~1869~ 6~846~ 7~3788~, 8~5225~ 9~1722~ 10~931~, 12~3708~ 13~11~ 14~3113~ 15~575~, 16~2532~ 17~2976~ 18~1722~ 19~846~ 20~2859~.'),
  (27160, 44, 7, 28, 'Wilt thou kill me, as thou diddest the Egyptian yesterday?', '0~2309~ 1~3361~* 2~4771~ 3~337~ 4~3165~, 5~5158~ 6~3739~ 7~337~ 9~124~ 10~5504~?'),
  (6104, 6, 10, 34, 'And from Lachish Joshua passed unto Eglon, and all Israel with him; and they encamped against it, and fought against it:', '2~03923~ 3~03091~ 4~05674~ 6~05700~, 9~03478~ 14~02583~ 18~03898~'),
  (233, 1, 9, 27, 'God shall enlarge Japheth, and he shall dwell in the tents of Shem; and Canaan shall be his servant.', '0~0430~ 2~06601~ 3~03315~, 7~07931~ 10~0168~ 12~08035~; 14~03667~ 18~05650~.'),
  (16825, 20, 15, 9, 'The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the LORD: but he loveth him that followeth after righteousness.', '&para; 1~01870~ 4~07563~ [5] 7~08441~ 10~03068~: 13~0157~ 16~07291~ 18~06666~.'),
  (16234, 19, 137, 3, 'For there they that carried us away captive required of us a song; and they that wasted us required of us mirth, saying, Sing us one of the songs of Zion.', '7~07617~ 8~07592~ 12~07892~ 13~01697~;* 17~08437~ [19 21] 22~08057~, [23] 24~07891~ [26] 29~07892~ 31~06726~.'),
  (14258, 19, 24, 8, 'Who is this King of glory? The LORD strong and mighty, the LORD mighty in battle.', '[1] 3~04428~ 5~03519~? 7~03068~ 8~05808~ 10~01368~, 12~03068~ 13~01368~ 15~04421~.'),
  (27329, 44, 11, 6, 'Upon the which when I had fastened mine eyes, I considered, and saw fourfooted beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.', '0~1519~ 2~3739~ 8~816~, 10~2657~, 11~2532~ 12~1492~ 14~5074~ 17~1093~, 18~2532~ 20~2342~, 21~2532~ 23~2062~, 24~2532~ 25~4071~ 28~3772~.'),
  (19522, 24, 23, 29, 'Is not my word like as a fire? saith the LORD; and like a hammer that breaketh the rock in pieces?', '[0] 3~01697~ 4~03541~ 7~0784~? 8~05002~ 10~03068~; 14~06360~ [15] 16~06327~ 18~05553~ 20~06327~?'),
  (23493, 40, 11, 24, 'But I say unto you, That it shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment, than for thee.', '0~4133~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 8~2071~ 10~414~ 13~1093~ 15~4670~ 16~1722~ 18~2250~ 20~2920~, 21~2228~ 23~4671~.'),
  (12298, 15, 10, 37, 'Mattaniah, Mattenai, and Jaasau,', '0~04983~, 1~04982~, 3~03299~,'),
  (5023, 5, 4, 13, 'And he declared unto you his covenant, which he commanded you to perform, even ten commandments; and he wrote them upon two tables of stone.', '2~05046~ 6~01285~, 9~06680~ 12~06213~, [13] 14~06235~ 15~01697~; 18~03789~ 21~08147~ 22~03871~ 24~068~.'),
  (28253, 45, 11, 28, 'As concerning the gospel, they are enemies for your sakes: but as touching the election, they are beloved for the fathers'' sakes.', '1~3303~ 2~2596~ 3~2098~, [4 5] 6~2190~ 9~5209~ 10~1223~:* 11~1161~ 13~2596~ 15~1589~, [16 17] 18~27~ 19~1223~ 21~3962~ 22~1223~.'),
  (10221, 12, 24, 11, 'And Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came against the city, and his servants did besiege it.', '1~05019~ 2~04428~ 4~0894~ 5~0935~ 8~05892~, 11~05650~ 13~06696~'),
  (30199, 58, 11, 11, 'Through faith also Sara herself received strength to conceive seed, and was delivered of a child when she was past age, because she judged him faithful who had promised.', '1~4102~ 2~2532~ 3~4564~ 4~846~ 5~2983~ 6~1411~ 7~1519~ 8~2602~ 9~4690~, 10~2532~ 15~5088~ 19~3844~ 20~2244~ 21~2540~,* 22~1893~ 24~2233~ 26~4103~ 29~1861~.'),
  (17141, 20, 25, 19, 'Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.', '&para; 0~04009~ 4~0898~ 6~03117~ 8~06869~ [9 10] 12~07465~ 13~08127~, 16~07272~ 19~04154~.'),
  (5052, 5, 4, 42, 'That the slayer might flee thither, which should kill his neighbour unawares, and hated him not in times past; and that fleeing unto one of these cities he might live:', '2~07523~ 4~05127~ 8~07523~ 10~07453~ 11~01847~ 12~01097~,* 14~08130~ 18~08543~ 19~08032~; 22~05127~ 24~0259~ 26~0411~ 27~05892~ 30~02425~:'),
  (6328, 6, 18, 28, 'And Zelah, Eleph, and Jebusi, which is Jerusalem, Gibeath, and Kirjath; fourteen cities with their villages. This is the inheritance of the children of Benjamin according to their families.', '1~06762~, 2~0507~, 4~02983~, [6] 7~03389~, 8~01394~, [9] 10~07157~; 11~06240~ 12~0702~* 13~05892~ 16~02691~. [18] 20~05159~ 23~01121~ 25~01144~ 29~04940~.'),
  (622, 1, 24, 27, 'And he said, Blessed be the LORD God of my master Abraham, who hath not left destitute my master of his mercy and his truth: I being in the way, the LORD led me to the house of my master''s brethren.', '2~0559~, 3~01288~ [4] 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 10~0113~ 11~085~, 16~05800~ 17~05973~* 19~0113~ 22~02617~ 25~0571~: [27] 30~01870~, 32~03068~ 34~05148~ 37~01004~ 40~0113~ 41~0251~.'),
  (9667, 12, 5, 12, 'Are not Abana and Pharpar, rivers of Damascus, better than all the waters of Israel? may I not wash in them, and be clean? So he turned and went away in a rage.', '[0] 2~071~ 3~0549~* 5~06554~, 6~05104~ 8~01834~, 9~02896~ 13~04325~ 15~03478~? 19~07364~ 24~02891~? 27~06437~ 30~03212~ 33~02534~.'),
  (12454, 16, 7, 25, 'The children of Gibeon, ninety and five.', '1~01121~ 3~01391~, 4~08673~ 6~02568~.'),
  (26888, 43, 20, 6, 'Then cometh Simon Peter following him, and went into the sepulchre, and seeth the linen clothes lie,', '0~3767~ 1~2064~ 2~4613~ 3~4074~ 4~190~ 5~846~, 6~2532~ 7~1525~ 8~1519~ 10~3419~, 11~2532~ 12~2334~ 15~3608~ 16~2749~,'),
  (276, 1, 11, 9, 'Therefore is the name of it called Babel; because the LORD did there confound the language of all the earth: and from thence did the LORD scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth.', '5~08034~ 6~07121~ 7~0894~; 10~03068~ 13~01101~ 15~08193~ 19~0776~: 23~06327~ 25~03068~ 28~06327~ 31~06440~ 35~0776~.'),
  (5512, 5, 23, 6, 'Thou shalt not seek their peace nor their prosperity all thy days for ever.', '3~01875~ 5~07965~ 8~02896~ 11~03117~ 13~05769~.'),
  (15400, 19, 90, 13, 'Return, O LORD, how long? and let it repent thee concerning thy servants.', '0~07725~, 2~03068~, 8~05162~ 12~05650~.'),
  (8792, 11, 2, 14, 'He said moreover, I have somewhat to say unto thee. And she said, Say on.', '1~0559~ 7~01697~ 12~0559~, 14~01696~.'),
  (21988, 27, 8, 18, 'Now as he was speaking with me, I was in a deep sleep on my face toward the ground: but he touched me, and set me upright.', '4~01696~ 12~07290~ 15~06440~ 18~0776~: 21~05060~ 24~05975~ 26~05977~.'),
  (588, 1, 23, 13, 'And he spake unto Ephron in the audience of the people of the land, saying, But if thou wilt give it, I pray thee, hear me: I will give thee money for the field; take it of me, and I will bury my dead there.', '2~01696~ 4~06085~ 7~0241~ 10~05971~ 13~0776~, 14~0559~, [18 20] 23~03863~, 24~08085~ 28~05414~ 30~03701~ 33~07704~; 34~03947~ [35] 41~06912~ 43~04191~'),
  (3485, 3, 25, 11, 'A jubilee shall that fiftieth year be unto you: ye shall not sow, neither reap that which groweth of itself in it, nor gather the grapes in it of thy vine undressed.', '1~03104~ 4~08141~ 5~02572~* 6~08141~ 13~02232~, 15~07114~ 18~05599~ 24~01219~ [25 26] 32~05139~.'),
  (13431, 18, 23, 3, 'Oh that I knew where I might find him! that I might come even to his seat!', '1~05414~ 3~03045~ 7~04672~ [9] 12~0935~ [13] 16~08499~!'),
  (26479, 43, 9, 24, 'Then again called they the man that was blind, and said unto him, Give God the praise: we know that this man is a sinner.', '0~3767~ 1~1537~ 2~1208~ 3~5455~ 5~444~ 6~3739~ 7~2258~ 8~5185~, 9~2532~ 10~2036~ 12~846~, 13~1325~ 14~2316~ 16~1391~: 17~2249~ 18~1492~ 19~3754~ 20~3778~ 21~444~ 22~2076~ 24~268~.'),
  (11516, 14, 15, 17, 'But the high places were not taken away out of Israel: nevertheless the heart of Asa was perfect all his days.', '3~01116~ 7~05493~ 10~03478~: 13~03824~ 15~0609~ 17~08003~ 20~03117~.'),
  (20469, 25, 5, 18, 'Because of the mountain of Zion, which is desolate, the foxes walk upon it.', '3~02022~ 5~06726~, 8~08074~, 10~07776~ 11~01980~'),
  (22312, 29, 1, 12, 'The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languisheth; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy is withered away from the sons of men.', '1~01612~ 4~03001~, 8~08384~ 9~0535~; 11~07416~ 15~08558~ 20~08598~, [21] 24~06086~ 27~07704~, 29~03001~: 31~08342~ 34~03001~ 37~01121~ 39~0120~.'),
  (16652, 20, 9, 5, 'Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mingled.', '0~03212~, 1~03898~ 4~03899~, 6~08354~ 9~03196~ [10] 13~04537~.'),
  (29680, 53, 2, 3, 'Let no man deceive you by any means: for that day shall not come, except there come a falling away first, and that man of sin be revealed, the son of perdition;', '&para; 0~1818~ 1~3361~ 2~5100~ 3~1818~ 4~5209~ 5~2596~ 6~3367~ 7~5158~: 8~3754~ [9 13] 14~3362~ 16~2064~ 19~646~ 20~4412~, 21~2532~ 23~444~ 25~266~ 27~601~, 29~5207~ 31~684~;'),
  (6567, 7, 2, 15, 'Whithersoever they went out, the hand of the LORD was against them for evil, as the LORD had said, and as the LORD had sworn unto them: and they were greatly distressed.', '3~03318~, 5~03027~ 8~03068~ 13~07451~, 16~03068~ 18~01696~, 22~03068~ 24~07650~ 30~03966~ 31~03334~.'),
  (10438, 13, 5, 2, 'For Judah prevailed above his brethren, and of him came the chief ruler; but the birthright was Joseph''s:)', '1~03063~ 2~01396~ 5~0251~, [9] 12~05057~; 15~01062~ [16] 17~03130~:)'),
  (11490, 14, 14, 6, 'And he built fenced cities in Judah: for the land had rest, and he had no war in those years; because the LORD had given him rest.', '2~01129~ 3~04694~ 4~05892~ 6~03063~: 9~0776~ 11~08252~, 16~04421~ 19~08141~; 22~03068~ 26~05117~.'),
  (30576, 62, 2, 10, 'He that loveth his brother abideth in the light, and there is none occasion of stumbling in him.', '2~25~ 3~846~ 4~80~ 5~3306~ 6~1722~ 8~5457~, 9~2532~ 11~2076~ 12~3756~ 15~4625~ 16~1722~ 17~846~.'),
  (7842, 9, 23, 25, 'Saul also and his men went to seek him. And they told David: wherefore he came down into a rock, and abode in the wilderness of Maon. And when Saul heard that, he pursued after David in the wilderness of Maon.', '0~07586~ 4~0582~ 5~03212~ 7~01245~ [8] 11~05046~ 12~01732~: 16~03381~ 19~05553~, 21~03427~ 24~04057~ 26~04584~. 29~07586~ 30~08085~ [31] 33~07291~ 34~0310~ 35~01732~ 38~04057~ 40~04584~.'),
  (27150, 44, 7, 18, 'Till another king arose, which knew not Joseph.', '0~3757~ 1~891~* 2~2087~ 3~935~ 4~450~, 5~3739~ 6~1492~ 7~3756~ 8~2501~.'),
  (13584, 18, 30, 18, 'By the great force of my disease is my garment changed: it bindeth me about as the collar of my coat.', '2~07230~ 3~03581~ [4 6] 9~03830~ 10~02664~: 14~0247~ 17~06310~ 20~03801~.');
