VALUES
  (18106, 23, 24, 2, 'And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her mistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the lender, so with the borrower; as with the taker of usury, so with the giver of usury to him.', '7~05971~, 11~03548~; 15~05650~, 19~0113~; 23~08198~, 27~01404~; 31~07069~, 35~04376~; 39~03867~, 43~03867~; 49~05383~, 50~0834~ 55~05378~'),
  (8054, 10, 1, 25, 'How are the mighty fallen in the midst of the battle! O Jonathan, thou wast slain in thine high places.', '3~01368~ 4~05307~ 7~08432~ 10~04421~! 12~03083~, [13 14] 15~02491~ 19~01116~.'),
  (22169, 28, 5, 8, 'Blow ye the cornet in Gibeah, and the trumpet in Ramah: cry aloud at Bethaven, after thee, O Benjamin.', '&para; 0~08628~ 3~07782~ 5~01390~, [6] 8~02689~ 10~07414~: 12~07321~ [13] 14~01007~, 15~0310~ 18~01144~.'),
  (4120, 4, 14, 7, 'And they spake unto all the company of the children of Israel, saying, The land, which we passed through to search it, is an exceeding good land.', '2~0559~ 6~05712~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~, 12~0559~, 14~0776~, 17~05674~ 20~08446~ [22] 24~03966~ 25~03966~* 26~02896~ 27~0776~.'),
  (28531, 46, 7, 28, 'But and if thou marry, thou hast not sinned; and if a virgin marry, she hath not sinned. Nevertheless such shall have trouble in the flesh: but I spare you.', '0~1161~ 1~2532~ 2~1437~ 4~1060~, 6~264~ 7~3756~ 8~264~; 9~2532~ 10~1437~ 12~3933~ 13~1060~, 15~264~ 16~3756~ 17~264~. 18~1161~ 19~5108~ 21~2192~ 22~2347~ 25~4561~: 26~1161~ 27~1473~ 28~5339~ 29~5216~.'),
  (15658, 19, 105, 43, 'And he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness:', '3~03318~ 5~05971~ 7~08342~, [8] 10~0972~ 12~07440~:'),
  (10123, 12, 20, 17, 'Behold, the days come, that all that is in thine house, and that which thy fathers have laid up in store unto this day, shall be carried into Babylon: nothing shall be left, saith the LORD.', '2~03117~ 3~0935~, [7] 10~01004~, 15~01~ 20~0686~ 23~03117~, 26~05375~ 28~0894~: 29~01697~ 32~03498~, 33~0559~ 35~03068~.'),
  (1250, 1, 41, 50, 'And unto Joseph were born two sons before the years of famine came, which Asenath the daughter of Potipherah priest of On bare unto him.', '2~03130~ 4~03205~ 5~08147~ 6~01121~ 9~08141~ 11~07458~ 12~0935~, 14~0621~ 16~01323~ 18~06319~ 19~03548~ 21~0204~ 22~03205~'),
  (46, 1, 2, 15, 'And the LORD God took the man, and put him into the garden of Eden to dress it and to keep it.', '2~03068~ 3~0430~ 4~03947~ 6~0120~, 9~03240~ 12~01588~ 14~05731~ 16~05647~ 20~08104~'),
  (4007, 4, 10, 14, 'In the first place went the standard of the camp of the children of Judah according to their armies: and over his host was Nahshon the son of Amminadab.', '2~07223~ [3] 4~05265~ 6~01714~ 9~04264~ 12~01121~ 14~03063~ 18~06635~: [23] 24~05177~ 26~01121~ 28~05992~.'),
  (20335, 25, 1, 16, 'For these things I weep; mine eye, mine eye runneth down with water, because the comforter that should relieve my soul is far from me: my children are desolate, because the enemy prevailed.', '[2] 4~01058~; 6~05869~, 8~05869~ 10~03381~ 12~04325~, 15~05162~ 18~07725~ 20~05315~ 22~07368~ 26~01121~ 28~08074~, 31~0341~ 32~01396~.'),
  (25424, 42, 11, 7, 'And he from within shall answer and say, Trouble me not: the door is now shut, and my children are with me in bed; I cannot rise and give thee.', '1~2548~ 3~2081~ 5~611~ 7~2036~, 8~3930~ 9~2873~* 10~3427~ 11~3361~: 13~2374~ 14~2808~ 15~2235~ 16~2808~, 17~2532~ 18~3450~ 19~3813~ 20~1526~ 21~3326~ 22~1700~ 23~1519~ 24~2845~; 26~1410~ 27~3756~* 28~450~ 30~1325~ 31~4671~.'),
  (29487, 51, 1, 6, 'Which is come unto you, as it is in all the world; and bringeth forth fruit, as it doth also in you, since the day ye heard of it, and knew the grace of God in truth:', '0~3588~ 2~3918~ 3~1519~ 4~5209~, 5~2532~ [6 6~2531~ 7] 8~1722~ 9~3956~ 11~2889~; 12~2532~ 15~2076~ 16~2592~,* 17~2531~ [18 19] 20~2532~ 21~1722~ 22~5213~, 23~575~ 24~3739~ 25~2250~ 27~191~ [28 29] 30~2532~ 31~1921~ 33~5485~ 35~2316~ 36~1722~ 37~225~:'),
  (23618, 40, 14, 11, 'And his head was brought in a charger, and given to the damsel: and she brought it to her mother.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~2776~ 4~5342~ 5~1909~ 7~4094~, 8~2532~ 9~1325~ 12~2877~: 13~2532~ 15~5342~ [16] 18~846~ 19~3384~.'),
  (23267, 40, 5, 23, 'Therefore if thou bring thy gift to the altar, and there rememberest that thy brother hath ought against thee;', '0~3767~ 1~1437~ 3~4374~ 4~4675~ 5~1435~ 6~1909~ 8~2379~, 10~2546~ 11~3415~ 12~3754~ 13~4675~ 14~80~ 15~2192~ 16~5100~ 17~2596~ 18~4675~;'),
  (19536, 24, 24, 3, 'Then said the LORD unto me, What seest thou, Jeremiah? And I said, Figs; the good figs, very good; and the evil, very evil, that cannot be eaten, they are so evil.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 7~07200~ 9~03414~? 12~0559~, 13~08384~; 15~02896~ 16~08384~, 17~03966~ 18~02896~; 21~07451~, 22~03966~ 23~07451~, 27~0398~, 31~07455~.'),
  (24997, 42, 2, 12, 'And this shall be a sign unto you; Ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger.', '0~2532~ 1~5124~ [2 3] 5~4592~ 7~5213~; 10~2147~ 12~1025~ 16~4683~, 17~2749~ 18~1722~ 20~5336~.'),
  (24300, 41, 3, 2, 'And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the sabbath day; that they might accuse him.', '0~2532~ 2~3906~ 3~846~, 4~1487~ 7~2323~ 8~846~ 12~4521~; 13~2443~ 16~2723~ 17~846~.'),
  (21064, 26, 23, 48, 'Thus will I cause lewdness to cease out of the land, that all women may be taught not to do after your lewdness.', '4~02154~ 6~07673~ 10~0776~, 13~0802~ 16~03256~ 19~06213~ 22~02154~.'),
  (5870, 6, 1, 13, 'Remember the word which Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, saying, The LORD your God hath given you rest, and hath given you this land.', '0~02142~ 2~01697~ 4~04872~ 6~05650~ 9~03068~ 10~06680~ 12~0559~, 14~03068~ 16~0430~ 20~05117~, 23~05414~ 26~0776~.'),
  (3087, 3, 13, 30, 'Then the priest shall see the plague: and, behold, if it be in sight deeper than the skin; and there be in it a yellow thin hair; then the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a dry scall, even a leprosy upon the head or beard.', '2~03548~ 4~07200~ 6~05061~: [11] 13~04758~ 14~06013~ 17~05785~; [18 20] 24~06669~ 25~01851~ 26~08181~; 29~03548~ 33~02930~: [35] 38~05424~, [39] 41~06883~ 44~07218~ 46~02206~.'),
  (12964, 18, 5, 4, 'His children are far from safety, and they are crushed in the gate, neither is there any to deliver them.', '1~01121~ 3~07368~ 5~03468~, 9~01792~ 12~08179~, [14 15] 18~05337~ [19]'),
  (11437, 14, 11, 14, 'For the Levites left their suburbs and their possession, and came to Judah and Jerusalem: for Jeroboam and his sons had cast them off from executing the priest''s office unto the LORD:', '2~03881~ 3~05800~ 5~04054~ 8~0272~, 10~03212~ 12~03063~ 14~03389~: 16~03379~ 19~01121~ 23~02186~ 28~03547~ 31~03068~:'),
  (9473, 11, 21, 14, 'Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, Naboth is stoned, and is dead.', '2~07971~ 4~0348~, 5~0559~, 6~05022~ 8~05619~, 11~04191~.'),
  (12452, 16, 7, 23, 'The children of Bezai, three hundred twenty and four.', '1~01121~ 3~01209~, 4~07969~ 5~03967~ 6~06242~ 8~0702~.'),
  (15163, 19, 78, 41, 'Yea, they turned back and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.', '3~07725~ 5~05254~ 6~0410~, 8~08428~ 11~06918~ 13~03478~.'),
  (8655, 10, 22, 45, 'Strangers shall submit themselves unto me: as soon as they hear, they shall be obedient unto me.', '0~05236~ 1~01121~ 2~03584~ 10~08085~ 11~0241~,* 15~08085~'),
  (9960, 12, 15, 27, 'In the two and fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah Pekah the son of Remaliah began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and reigned twenty years.', '2~08141~ 3~08147~ 4~02572~ 5~08141~ 7~05838~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~ 11~06492~ 13~01121~ 15~07425~ 18~04427~ 20~03478~ 22~08111~, [23 24] 25~06242~ 26~08141~.'),
  (8427, 10, 15, 31, 'And one told David, saying, Ahithophel is among the conspirators with Absalom. And David said, O LORD, I pray thee, turn the counsel of Ahithophel into foolishness.', '&para; [1] 2~05046~ 3~01732~, 4~0559~, 5~0302~ [6] 9~07194~ 11~053~. 13~01732~ 14~0559~, 16~03068~, 22~06098~ 24~0302~ 26~05528~.'),
  (463, 1, 19, 2, 'And he said, Behold now, my lords, turn in, I pray you, into your servant''s house, and tarry all night, and wash your feet, and ye shall rise up early, and go on your ways. And they said, Nay; but we will abide in the street all night.', '2~0559~, 6~0113~, 8~05493~, 14~05650~ 15~01004~, 19~03885~, 21~07364~ 23~07272~, 29~07925~, 31~01980~ 34~01870~. 37~0559~, 42~03885~ 45~07339~ 47~03885~.'),
  (6765, 7, 9, 4, 'And they gave him threescore and ten pieces of silver out of the house of Baalberith, wherewith Abimelech hired vain and light persons, which followed him.', '2~05414~ 6~07657~ [7] 9~03701~ 13~01004~ 15~01170~, 17~040~ 18~07936~ 19~07386~ 21~06348~ 22~0582~, 24~03212~ 25~0310~.'),
  (30571, 62, 2, 5, 'But whoso keepeth his word, in him verily is the love of God perfected: hereby know we that we are in him.', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 2~5083~ 3~302~* 4~846~ 5~3056~, 6~1722~ 7~5129~ 8~230~ 9~5048~ 11~26~ 13~2316~ 14~5048~: 15~5129~ 16~1722~ 17~1097~ 18~3754~ 20~2070~ 21~1722~ 22~846~.'),
  (3255, 3, 17, 15, 'And every soul that eateth that which died of itself, or that which was torn with beasts, whether it be one of your own country, or a stranger, he shall both wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even: then shall he be clean.', '2~05315~ 4~0398~ 7~05038~ [8 9] 14~02966~ [15 19] 24~0249~, 27~01616~, 31~03526~ 33~0899~, 35~07364~ [36] 38~04325~, 41~02930~ 44~06153~: 49~02891~.'),
  (15009, 19, 71, 24, 'My tongue also shall talk of thy righteousness all the day long: for they are confounded, for they are brought unto shame, that seek my hurt.', '1~03956~ 4~01897~ 7~06666~ 10~03117~ 15~0954~, 21~02659~, 23~01245~ 25~07451~.'),
  (8467, 10, 17, 11, 'Therefore I counsel that all Israel be generally gathered unto thee, from Dan even to Beersheba, as the sand that is by the sea for multitude; and that thou go to battle in thine own person.', '2~03289~ 5~03478~ 7~0622~ 8~0622~ 12~01835~ 15~0884~, 18~02344~ [20] 23~03220~ 25~07230~; 29~01980~ 31~07128~ 35~06440~.'),
  (4082, 4, 13, 2, 'Send thou men, that they may search the land of Canaan, which I give unto the children of Israel: of every tribe of their fathers shall ye send a man, every one a ruler among them.', '0~07971~ 2~0582~, 6~08446~ 8~0776~ 10~03667~, 13~05414~ 16~01121~ 18~03478~: 20~0376~ 21~04294~ 24~01~ 27~07971~ 29~0259~, 33~05387~'),
  (20547, 26, 4, 9, 'Take thou also unto thee wheat, and barley, and beans, and lentiles, and millet, and fitches, and put them in one vessel, and make thee bread thereof, according to the number of the days that thou shalt lie upon thy side, three hundred and ninety days shalt thou eat thereof.', '&para; 0~03947~ 5~02406~, 7~08184~, 9~06321~, 11~05742~, 13~01764~, 15~03698~, 17~05414~ 20~0259~ 21~03627~, 23~06213~ 25~03899~ [27] 30~04557~ 33~03117~ 37~07901~ 40~06654~, 41~07969~ 42~03967~ 44~08673~ 45~03117~ 48~0398~'),
  (25688, 42, 17, 23, 'And they shall say to you, See here; or, see there: go not after them, nor follow them.', '0~2532~ 3~2046~ 5~5213~, 6~2400~ 7~5602~; 8~2228~, 9~2400~ 10~1563~: 11~565~ 12~3361~ 13~565~ [14] 15~3366~ 16~1377~ [17]'),
  (9238, 11, 14, 12, 'Arise thou therefore, get thee to thine own house: and when thy feet enter into the city, the child shall die.', '0~06965~ 3~03212~ 8~01004~: [9] 12~07272~ 13~0935~ 16~05892~, 18~03206~ 20~04191~.'),
  (16250, 19, 139, 2, 'Thou knowest my downsitting and mine uprising, thou understandest my thought afar off.', '1~03045~ 3~03427~ 6~06965~, 8~0995~ 10~07454~ 12~07350~.'),
  (16394, 19, 148, 14, 'He also exalteth the horn of his people, the praise of all his saints; even of the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Praise ye the LORD.', '2~07311~ 4~07161~ 7~05971~, 9~08416~ 13~02623~; [14] 17~01121~ 19~03478~, 21~05971~ 22~07138~ 25~01984~ 28~03050~.'),
  (30284, 59, 1, 2, 'My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into divers temptations;', '&para; 0~3450~ 1~80~, 3~2233~ 4~3956~ 5~5479~ 6~3752~ 8~4045~ 10~4164~ 11~3986~;'),
  (9645, 12, 4, 34, 'And he went up, and lay upon the child, and put his mouth upon his mouth, and his eyes upon his eyes, and his hands upon his hands: and he stretched himself upon the child; and the flesh of the child waxed warm.', '3~05927~, 5~07901~ 8~03206~, 10~07760~ 12~06310~ 15~06310~, 18~05869~ 21~05869~, 24~03709~ 27~03709~: 30~01457~ 37~01320~ 40~03206~ 42~02552~.'),
  (22426, 30, 4, 7, 'And also I have withholden the rain from you, when there were yet three months to the harvest: and I caused it to rain upon one city, and caused it not to rain upon another city: one piece was rained upon, and the piece whereupon it rained not withered.', '4~04513~ 6~01653~ [10 11] 13~07969~ 14~02320~ 17~07105~: 23~04305~ 25~0259~ 26~05892~, 32~04305~ 34~0259~ 35~05892~: 36~0259~ 37~02513~ 39~04305~ 43~02513~ 46~04305~ 48~03001~.'),
  (11395, 14, 9, 23, 'And all the kings of the earth sought the presence of Solomon, to hear his wisdom, that God had put in his heart.', '3~04428~ 6~0776~ 7~01245~ 9~06440~ 11~08010~, 13~08085~ 15~02451~, 17~0430~ 19~05414~ 22~03820~.'),
  (4242, 4, 16, 43, 'And Moses and Aaron came before the tabernacle of the congregation.', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 4~0935~ 5~06440~ 7~0168~ 10~04150~.'),
  (1948, 2, 15, 23, 'And when they came to Marah, they could not drink of the waters of Marah, for they were bitter: therefore the name of it was called Marah.', '3~0935~ 5~04785~, 7~03201~ 9~08354~ 12~04325~ 14~04785~, [17] 18~04751~: 21~08034~ 25~07121~ 26~04785~.'),
  (30049, 58, 5, 3, 'And by reason hereof he ought, as for the people, so also for himself, to offer for sins.', '0~2532~ 2~1223~ 3~5026~ 5~3784~, 6~2531~ 7~4012~ 9~2992~, 10~3779~ 11~2532~ 12~4012~ 13~1438~, 15~4374~ 16~5228~ 17~266~.'),
  (24033, 40, 25, 15, 'And unto one he gave five talents, to another two, and to another one; to every man according to his several ability; and straightway took his journey.', '0~2532~ 2~3303~ 3~3739~ 4~1325~ 5~4002~ 6~5007~ 7~1161~,* 9~3739~ 10~1417~, 11~1161~ 13~3739~ 14~1520~; 17~1538~ 18~2596~ 21~2398~ 22~1411~; 23~2532~ 24~2112~ 27~589~.'),
  (7916, 9, 26, 4, 'David therefore sent out spies, and understood that Saul was come in very deed.', '0~01732~ 3~07971~ 4~07270~, 6~03045~ 8~07586~ 10~0935~ 13~03559~.'),
  (14876, 19, 65, 7, 'Which stilleth the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.', '1~07623~ 3~07588~ 6~03220~, 8~07588~ 11~01530~, 14~01995~ 17~03816~.'),
  (7858, 9, 24, 12, 'The LORD judge between me and thee, and the LORD avenge me of thee: but mine hand shall not be upon thee.', '1~03068~ 2~08199~ 9~03068~ 10~05358~ 16~03027~'),
  (23459, 40, 10, 32, 'Whosoever therefore shall confess me before men, him will I confess also before my Father which is in heaven.', '0~3748~ 1~3956~* 2~3767~ 4~3670~ 5~1722~* 6~1698~ 7~1715~ 8~444~ 9~1722~,* 10~846~ 13~3670~ 14~2504~ 15~1715~ 16~3450~ 17~3962~ 18~3588~ 20~1722~ 21~3772~.'),
  (9658, 12, 5, 3, 'And she said unto her mistress, Would God my lord were with the prophet that is in Samaria! for he would recover him of his leprosy.', '2~0559~ 5~01404~, 6~0305~ 9~0113~ [10] 11~06440~ 13~05030~ [15] 17~08111~! 18~0227~ 21~0622~ 25~06883~.'),
  (10739, 13, 12, 11, 'Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh,', '0~06262~ 2~08345~, 3~0447~ 5~07637~,'),
  (19788, 24, 33, 4, 'For thus saith the LORD, the God of Israel, concerning the houses of this city, and concerning the houses of the kings of Judah, which are thrown down by the mounts, and by the sword;', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 6~0430~ 8~03478~, 11~01004~ 14~05892~, 18~01004~ 21~04428~ 23~03063~, 27~05422~ 30~05550~, 34~02719~;'),
  (4928, 5, 1, 30, 'The LORD your God which goeth before you, he shall fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before your eyes;', '1~03068~ 3~0430~ 5~01980~ 6~06440~ 10~03898~ 18~06213~ 22~04714~ 25~05869~;'),
  (30194, 58, 11, 6, 'But without faith it is impossible to please him: for he that cometh to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.', '0~1161~ 1~5565~ 2~4102~ [3 4] 5~102~ 7~2100~ [8] 9~1063~ 12~4334~ 14~2316~ 15~1163~ 16~4100~ 17~3754~ 19~2076~, 20~2532~ [21] 23~1096~ 25~3406~ 30~1567~ 31~846~.'),
  (13273, 18, 17, 4, 'For thou hast hid their heart from understanding: therefore shalt thou not exalt them.', '3~06845~ 5~03820~ 7~07922~: 12~07311~ [13]'),
  (30738, 66, 2, 5, 'Remember therefore from whence thou art fallen, and repent, and do the first works; or else I will come unto thee quickly, and will remove thy candlestick out of his place, except thou repent.', '0~3421~ 1~3767~ 3~4159~ 6~1601~, 7~2532~ 8~3340~, 9~2532~ 10~4160~ 12~4413~ 13~2041~; 15~1490~ 18~2064~ 20~4671~ 21~5035~, 22~2532~ 24~2795~ 25~4675~ 26~3087~ 28~1537~ 29~846~ 30~5117~, 31~3362~ 33~3340~.'),
  (27134, 44, 7, 2, 'And he said, Men, brethren, and fathers, hearken; The God of glory appeared unto our father Abraham, when he was in Mesopotamia, before he dwelt in Charran,', '0~1161~ 2~5346~, 3~435~, 4~80~, 5~2532~ 6~3962~, 7~191~; 9~2316~ 11~1391~ 12~3700~ 14~2257~ 15~3962~ 16~11~, 19~5607~ 20~1722~ 21~3318~, 22~2228~ 23~4250~* 24~846~ 25~2730~ 26~1722~ 27~5488~,'),
  (10909, 13, 18, 11, 'Them also king David dedicated unto the LORD, with the silver and the gold that he brought from all these nations; from Edom, and from Moab, and from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines, and from Amalek.', '2~04428~ 3~01732~ 4~06942~ 7~03068~, 10~03701~ 13~02091~ 16~05375~ [19] 20~01471~; 22~0123~, 25~04124~, 29~01121~ 31~05983~, 35~06430~, 38~06002~.'),
  (3054, 3, 12, 5, 'But if she bear a maid child, then she shall be unclean two weeks, as in her separation: and she shall continue in the blood of her purifying threescore and six days.', '3~03205~ 6~05347~, 11~02930~ 13~07620~, 17~05079~: 21~03427~ 24~01818~ 27~02893~ 28~08346~ 30~08337~ 31~03117~.'),
  (7311, 9, 4, 7, 'And the Philistines were afraid, for they said, God is come into the camp. And they said, Woe unto us! for there hath not been such a thing heretofore.', '2~06430~ 4~03372~, 7~0559~, 8~0430~ 10~0935~ 13~04264~. 16~0559~, 17~0188~ 28~08032~ 29~0865~.*'),
  (26146, 43, 3, 11, 'Verily, verily, I say unto thee, We speak that we do know, and testify that we have seen; and ye receive not our witness.', '0~281~, 1~281~, 3~3004~ 5~4671~, 7~2980~ 8~3739~ 9~3754~ 11~1492~, 12~2532~ 13~3140~ 14~3739~ 17~3708~; 18~2532~ 20~2983~ 21~3756~ 22~2257~ 23~3141~.'),
  (17322, 20, 31, 29, 'Many daughters have done virtuously, but thou excellest them all.', '0~07227~ 1~01323~ 3~06213~ 4~02428~, 7~05927~'),
  (1827, 2, 12, 6, 'And ye shall keep it up until the fourteenth day of the same month: and the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it in the evening.', '3~04931~ 8~06240~ 9~0702~* 10~03117~ 14~02320~: 17~03605~ 18~06951~ 21~05712~ 23~03478~ 25~07819~ 27~0996~ 29~06153~.'),
  (23353, 40, 7, 27, 'And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell: and great was the fall of it.', '0~2532~ 2~1028~ 3~2597~, 4~2532~ 6~4215~ 7~2064~, 8~2532~ 10~417~ 11~4154~, 12~2532~ 14~4350~ 15~1565~ 16~3614~; 17~2532~ 19~4098~: 20~2532~ 21~3173~ 22~2258~ 24~4431~ 26~846~.'),
  (13571, 18, 30, 5, 'They were driven forth from among men, (they cried after them as after a thief;)', '3~01644~ 5~01460~ [6] 8~07321~ [12] 14~01590~;)'),
  (29951, 56, 3, 12, 'When I shall send Artemas unto thee, or Tychicus, be diligent to come unto me to Nicopolis: for I have determined there to winter.', '0~3752~ 3~3992~ 4~734~ 5~4314~ 6~4571~, 7~2228~ 8~5190~, 10~4704~ 12~2064~ 13~4314~ 14~3165~ 15~1519~ 16~3533~: 17~1063~ 20~2919~ 21~1563~ 23~3914~.'),
  (18304, 23, 33, 16, 'He shall dwell on high: his place of defence shall be the munitions of rocks: bread shall be given him; his waters shall be sure.', '2~07931~ 4~04791~: 8~04869~ [9 10] 12~04679~ 14~05553~: 15~03899~ 18~05414~ 21~04325~ [22 23] 24~0539~.'),
  (24752, 41, 13, 24, 'But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,', '&para; 0~235~ 1~1722~ 2~1565~ 3~2250~, 4~3326~ 5~1565~ 6~2347~, 8~2246~ 11~4654~, 12~2532~ 14~4582~ 15~1325~ 16~3756~ 17~1325~ 18~846~ 19~5338~,'),
  (19166, 24, 8, 4, 'Moreover thou shalt say unto them, Thus saith the LORD; Shall they fall, and not arise? shall he turn away, and not return?', '&para; 3~0559~ 7~0559~ 9~03068~; 12~05307~, 15~06965~? 19~07725~, 22~07725~?'),
  (14886, 19, 66, 4, 'All the earth shall worship thee, and shall sing unto thee; they shall sing to thy name. Selah.', '2~0776~ 4~07812~ 8~02167~ 13~02167~ [14] 16~08034~. 17~05542~.'),
  (22774, 35, 2, 17, 'For the violence of Lebanon shall cover thee, and the spoil of beasts, which made them afraid, because of men''s blood, and for the violence of the land, of the city, and of all that dwell therein.', '2~02555~ 4~03844~ 6~03680~ 10~07701~ 12~0929~, [13] 16~02865~, 19~0120~ 20~01818~, 24~02555~ 27~0776~, 30~07151~, 35~03427~'),
  (24950, 42, 1, 45, 'And blessed is she that believed: for there shall be a performance of those things which were told her from the Lord.', '0~2532~ 1~3107~ [2] 5~4100~: 6~3754~ 9~2071~ 11~5050~ 17~2980~ 18~846~ 19~3844~ 21~2962~.'),
  (9580, 12, 2, 21, 'And he went forth unto the spring of the waters, and cast the salt in there, and said, Thus saith the LORD, I have healed these waters; there shall not be from thence any more death or barren land.', '3~03318~ 6~04161~ 9~04325~, 11~07993~ 13~04417~ 17~0559~, 19~0559~ 21~03068~, 24~07495~ 26~04325~; 35~04194~ 37~07921~ [38]'),
  (14209, 19, 21, 9, 'Thou shalt make them as a fiery oven in the time of thine anger: the LORD shall swallow them up in his wrath, and the fire shall devour them.', '2~07896~ 6~0784~ 7~08574~ 10~06256~ 13~06440~: 15~03068~ 19~01104~ 22~0639~, 25~0784~ 27~0398~'),
  (18796, 23, 58, 1, 'Cry aloud, spare not, lift up thy voice like a trumpet, and shew my people their transgression, and the house of Jacob their sins.', '&para; 0~07121~ 1~01627~, 2~02820~ 4~07311~ 7~06963~ 10~07782~, 12~05046~ 14~05971~ 16~06588~, 19~01004~ 21~03290~ 23~02403~.'),
  (28518, 46, 7, 15, 'But if the unbelieving depart, let him depart. A brother or a sister is not under bondage in such cases: but God hath called us to peace.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 3~571~ 4~5563~, 7~5563~. 9~80~ 10~2228~ 12~79~ 13~1402~ 14~3756~ 16~1402~ 17~1722~ 18~5108~ [19] 20~1161~ 21~2316~ 23~2564~ 24~2248~ 25~1722~ 26~1515~.'),
  (6331, 6, 19, 3, 'And Hazarshual, and Balah, and Azem,', '1~02705~, 3~01088~, 5~06107~,'),
  (20264, 24, 51, 43, 'Her cities are a desolation, a dry land, and a wilderness, a land wherein no man dwelleth, neither doth any son of man pass thereby.', '1~05892~ 4~08047~, 6~06723~ 7~0776~, 10~06160~, 12~0776~ 15~0376~ 16~03427~, [19] 20~01121~ 22~0120~ 23~05674~ 24~02004~.'),
  (2449, 2, 32, 6, 'And they rose up early on the morrow, and offered burnt offerings, and brought peace offerings; and the people sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up to play.', '4~07925~ 7~04283~, 9~05927~ 11~05930~, 13~05066~ 15~08002~; 18~05971~ 19~03427~ 22~0398~ 25~08354~, 28~06965~ 30~06711~.'),
  (16617, 20, 8, 6, 'Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and the opening of my lips shall be right things.', '0~08085~; 4~01696~ 7~05057~; 10~04669~ 13~08193~ [14 15] 17~04339~.'),
  (9615, 12, 4, 4, 'And when thou art come in, thou shalt shut the door upon thee and upon thy sons, and shalt pour out into all those vessels, and thou shalt set aside that which is full.', '5~0935~, 8~05462~ 10~01817~ 16~01121~, 20~03332~ 24~03627~, 29~05265~ 33~04392~.'),
  (24192, 40, 27, 53, 'And came out of the graves after his resurrection, and went into the holy city, and appeared unto many.', '0~2532~ 1~1831~ 3~1537~ 5~3419~ 6~3326~ 7~846~ 8~1454~, 10~1525~ 11~1519~ 13~40~ 14~4172~, 15~2532~ 16~1718~ 18~4183~.'),
  (3795, 4, 4, 47, 'From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old, every one that came to do the service of the ministry, and the service of the burden in the tabernacle of the congregation,', '1~07970~ 2~08141~ 3~01121~ 5~04605~ 8~02572~ 9~08141~ 10~01121~, 14~0935~ 16~05647~ 21~05656~, 24~05656~ 27~04853~ 30~0168~ 33~04150~,'),
  (29960, 57, 1, 6, 'That the communication of thy faith may become effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.', '0~3704~ 2~2842~ 4~4675~ 5~4102~ 7~1096~ 8~1756~ 9~1722~ 11~1922~ 13~3956~ 15~18~ 16~3588~ 18~1722~ 19~5213~ 20~1519~ 21~5547~ 22~2424~.'),
  (10809, 13, 15, 10, 'Of the sons of Uzziel; Amminadab the chief, and his brethren an hundred and twelve.', '2~01121~ 4~05816~; 5~05992~ 7~08269~, 10~0251~ 12~03967~ 14~06240~ 15~08147~.*'),
  (18498, 23, 42, 9, 'Behold, the former things are come to pass, and new things do I declare: before they spring forth I tell you of them.', '3~07223~ 7~0935~, 10~02319~ 13~05046~: 17~06779~ 19~08085~'),
  (24677, 41, 11, 26, 'But if ye do not forgive, neither will your Father which is in heaven forgive your trespasses.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~5210~ 3~863~ 4~3756~ 5~863~, 6~3761~ 7~863~ 8~5216~ 9~3962~ 10~3588~ 12~1722~ 13~3772~ 14~863~ 15~5216~ 16~3900~.'),
  (24167, 40, 27, 28, 'And they stripped him, and put on him a scarlet robe.', '0~2532~ 2~1562~ 3~846~, 6~4060~ 7~846~ 9~2847~ 10~5511~.'),
  (13029, 18, 7, 12, 'Am I a sea, or a whale, that thou settest a watch over me?', '[0] 3~03220~, 6~08577~, 9~07760~ 11~04929~'),
  (20187, 24, 50, 12, 'Your mother shall be sore confounded; she that bare you shall be ashamed: behold, the hindermost of the nations shall be a wilderness, a dry land, and a desert.', '1~0517~ 4~03966~ 5~0954~; 8~03205~ 12~02659~: 15~0319~ 18~01471~ [19 20] 22~04057~, 25~06723~, 28~06160~.'),
  (9384, 11, 18, 35, 'And the water ran round about the altar; and he filled the trench also with water.', '2~04325~ 3~03212~ 5~05439~ 7~04196~; 10~04390~ 12~08585~ 15~04325~.'),
  (28438, 46, 3, 12, 'Now if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble;', '0~1161~ 3~1536~ 4~2026~ 5~1909~ 6~5126~ 7~2310~ 8~5557~, 9~696~, 10~5093~ 11~3037~, 12~3586~, 13~5528~, 14~2562~;'),
  (288, 1, 11, 19, 'And Peleg lived after he begat Reu two hundred and nine years, and begat sons and daughters.', '1~06389~ 2~02421~ 3~0310~ 5~03205~ 6~07466~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~ 10~08672~ 11~08141~, 13~03205~ 14~01121~ 16~01323~.'),
  (20047, 24, 44, 28, 'Yet a small number that escape the sword shall return out of the land of Egypt into the land of Judah, and all the remnant of Judah, that are gone into the land of Egypt to sojourn there, shall know whose words shall stand, mine, or theirs.', '2~04962~ 3~04557~ 5~06412~ 7~02719~ 10~07725~ 13~0776~ 15~04714~ 18~0776~ 20~03063~, 24~07611~ 26~03063~, 29~0935~ 32~0776~ 34~04714~ 36~01481~ 39~03045~ 41~01697~ 43~06965~,'),
  (21036, 26, 23, 20, 'For she doted upon their paramours, whose flesh is as the flesh of asses, and whose issue is like the issue of horses.', '2~05689~ 5~06370~, 7~01320~ [8 9] 11~01320~ 13~02543~, 16~02231~ [17 18] 20~02231~ 22~05483~.'),
  (22285, 28, 13, 10, 'I will be thy king: where is any other that may save thee in all thy cities? and thy judges of whom thou saidst, Give me a king and princes?', '1~0165~ 4~04428~: 5~0645~ [6 8] 11~03467~ 16~05892~? 19~08199~ 23~0559~, 24~05414~ 27~04428~ 29~08269~?');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (6068, 6, 9, 25, 'And now, behold, we are in thine hand: as it seemeth good and right unto thee to do unto us, do.', '3~02009~ [4] 7~03027~: 10~05869~ 11~02896~ 13~03477~ 17~06213~ 20~06213~.'),
  (12767, 17, 3, 11, 'And the king said unto Haman, The silver is given to thee, the people also, to do with them as it seemeth good to thee.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 5~02001~, 7~03701~ [8] 9~05414~ 13~05971~ 16~06213~ 21~05869~ 22~02896~'),
  (5069, 5, 5, 10, 'And shewing mercy unto thousands of them that love me and keep my commandments.', '1~06213~ 2~02617~ 4~0505~ 8~0157~ 11~08104~ 13~04687~.'),
  (854, 1, 30, 20, 'And Leah said, God hath endued me with a good dowry; now will my husband dwell with me, because I have born him six sons: and she called his name Zebulun.', '1~03812~ 2~0559~, 3~0430~ 5~02064~ [7] 9~02896~ 10~02065~; 11~06471~ 14~0376~ 15~02082~ 21~03205~ 23~08337~ 24~01121~: 27~07121~ 29~08034~ 30~02074~.'),
  (19359, 24, 16, 14, 'Therefore, behold, the days come, saith the LORD, that it shall no more be said, The LORD liveth, that brought up the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt;', '&para; 3~03117~ 4~0935~, 5~05002~ 7~03068~, 14~0559~, 16~03068~ 17~02416~, 20~05927~ 22~01121~ 24~03478~ 28~0776~ 30~04714~;'),
  (4755, 4, 32, 31, 'And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered, saying, As the LORD hath said unto thy servants, so will we do.', '2~01121~ 4~01410~ 7~01121~ 9~07205~ 10~06030~, 11~0559~, 14~03068~ 16~01696~ 19~05650~, 23~06213~.'),
  (2682, 2, 39, 13, 'And the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper: they were enclosed in ouches of gold in their enclosings.', '2~07243~ 3~02905~, 5~08658~, 7~07718~, 10~03471~: [11 12] 13~04142~ 15~04865~ 17~02091~ 20~04396~.'),
  (16539, 20, 5, 13, 'And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!', '3~08085~ 5~06963~ 8~03384~, 10~05186~ 12~0241~ 16~03925~'),
  (14308, 19, 27, 14, 'Wait on the LORD: be of good courage, and he shall strengthen thine heart: wait, I say, on the LORD.', '0~06960~ 3~03068~: 7~02388~, 11~0553~ 13~03820~: 14~06960~, 19~03068~.'),
  (22146, 28, 4, 4, 'Yet let no man strive, nor reprove another: for thy people are as they that strive with the priest.', '3~0376~ 4~07378~, 6~03198~ 7~0376~: 10~05971~ [11] 15~07378~ 18~03548~.'),
  (30651, 62, 5, 11, 'And this is the record, that God hath given to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~2076~ 4~3141~, 5~3754~ 6~2316~ 8~1325~ 10~2254~ 11~166~ 12~2222~, 13~2532~ 14~3778~ 15~2222~ 16~2076~ 17~1722~ 18~846~ 19~5207~.'),
  (23291, 40, 5, 47, 'And if ye salute your brethren only, what do ye more than others? do not even the publicans so?', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~782~ 4~5216~ 5~80~ 6~3440~, 7~5101~ 8~4160~ 10~4053~ [11 12] 13~4160~ 14~3780~ 15~2532~ 17~5057~ 18~3779~?'),
  (5529, 5, 23, 23, 'That which is gone out of thy lips thou shalt keep and perform; even a freewill offering, according as thou hast vowed unto the LORD thy God, which thou hast promised with thy mouth.', '4~04161~ 7~08193~ 10~08104~ 12~06213~; [13] 16~05071~, 21~05087~ 24~03068~ 26~0430~, 30~01696~ 33~06310~.'),
  (24773, 41, 14, 8, 'She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying.', '2~4160~ 3~3739~ 4~3778~ 5~846~* 6~2192~: 10~4301~ 12~3462~ 13~3450~ 14~4983~ 15~1519~ 17~1780~.'),
  (9396, 11, 19, 1, 'And Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and withal how he had slain all the prophets with the sword.', '&para; 1~0256~ 2~05046~ 3~0348~ 6~0452~ 8~06213~, 14~02026~ 17~05030~ 20~02719~.'),
  (19581, 24, 25, 38, 'He hath forsaken his covert, as the lion: for their land is desolate because of the fierceness of the oppressor, and because of his fierce anger.', '2~05800~ 4~05520~, 7~03715~: 10~0776~ 12~08047~ 13~06440~ 16~02740~ 19~03238~, 21~06440~ 24~02740~ 25~0639~.'),
  (12151, 15, 5, 8, 'Be it known unto the king, that we went into the province of Judea, to the house of the great God, which is builded with great stones, and timber is laid in the walls, and this work goeth fast on, and prospereth in their hands.', '2~01934~ 3~03046~* 6~04430~, 9~0236~ 12~04083~ 14~03061~, 17~01005~ 20~07229~ 21~0426~, 24~01124~ 26~01560~ 27~069~, 29~0636~ 31~07761~ 34~03797~, 36~01791~ 37~05673~ 38~05648~ 39~0629~ 42~06744~ 45~03028~.'),
  (26171, 43, 3, 36, 'He that believeth on the Son hath everlasting life: and he that believeth not the Son shall not see life; but the wrath of God abideth on him.', '2~4100~ 3~1519~ 5~5207~ 6~2192~ 7~166~ 8~2222~: 9~1161~ 13~544~ 15~5207~ 16~3700~ 17~3756~ 18~3700~ 19~2222~; 20~235~ 22~3709~ 24~2316~ 25~3306~ 26~1909~ 27~846~.'),
  (3924, 4, 7, 69, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (10248, 12, 25, 18, 'And the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, and Zephaniah the second priest, and the three keepers of the door:', '2~07227~ 5~02876~ 6~03947~ 7~08304~ 9~07218~ 10~03548~, 12~06846~ 14~04932~ 15~03548~, 18~07969~ 19~08104~ 22~05592~:'),
  (24688, 41, 12, 4, 'And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded him in the head, and sent him away shamefully handled.', '0~2532~ 1~3825~ 3~649~ 4~4314~ 5~846~ 6~243~ 7~1401~; 10~2548~ 13~3036~, [16] 19~2775~, 20~2532~ [22] 23~649~ 25~821~.'),
  (16400, 19, 149, 6, 'Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;', '&para; [0] 2~07319~ [3] 5~0410~ [6] 9~01627~, 12~06374~ 13~02719~ 16~03027~;'),
  (21718, 26, 48, 7, 'And by the border of Reuben, from the east side unto the west side, a portion for Judah.', '3~01366~ 5~07205~, 8~06921~ 9~06285~ 12~03220~ 13~06285~, 14~0259~ [15 16] 17~03063~.'),
  (9722, 12, 7, 7, 'Wherefore they arose and fled in the twilight, and left their tents, and their horses, and their asses, even the camp as it was, and fled for their life.', '2~06965~ 4~05127~ 7~05399~, 9~05800~ 11~0168~, 14~05483~, 17~02543~, 20~04264~ [23] 25~05127~ 28~05315~.'),
  (1086, 1, 36, 41, 'Duke Aholibamah, duke Elah, duke Pinon,', '0~0441~ 1~0173~, 2~0441~ 3~0425~, 4~0441~ 5~06373~,'),
  (16264, 19, 139, 16, 'Thine eyes did see my substance, yet being unperfect; and in thy book all my members were written, which in continuance were fashioned, when as yet there was none of them.', '1~05869~ 3~07200~ 8~01564~; 12~05612~ [14 15] 17~03789~, [18] 20~03117~ 22~03335~, [24 27] 28~0259~'),
  (7595, 9, 15, 28, 'And Samuel said unto him, The LORD hath rent the kingdom of Israel from thee this day, and hath given it to a neighbour of thine, that is better than thou.', '1~08050~ 2~0559~ 6~03068~ 8~07167~ 10~04468~ 12~03478~ 16~03117~, 19~05414~ 23~07453~ [26 27] 28~02896~'),
  (29341, 49, 5, 21, 'Submitting yourselves one to another in the fear of God.', '&para; 1~5293~ 4~240~ 5~1722~ 7~5401~ 9~2316~.'),
  (12361, 16, 3, 25, 'Palal the son of Uzai, over against the turning of the wall, and the tower which lieth out from the king''s high house, that was by the court of the prison. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh.', '0~06420~ 2~01121~ 4~0186~, 8~04740~ [9 11] 14~04026~ 17~03318~ 20~04428~ 21~05945~ 22~01004~, [24] 27~02691~ 30~04307~. 31~0310~ 33~06305~ 35~01121~ 37~06551~.'),
  (1125, 1, 38, 1, 'And it came to pass at that time, that Judah went down from his brethren, and turned in to a certain Adullamite, whose name was Hirah.', '&para; 7~06256~, 9~03063~ 11~03381~ 14~0251~, 16~05186~ 20~0376~ 21~05726~, 23~08034~ [24] 25~02437~.'),
  (8253, 10, 10, 6, 'And when the children of Ammon saw that they stank before David, the children of Ammon sent and hired the Syrians of Bethrehob, and the Syrians of Zoba, twenty thousand footmen, and of king Maacah a thousand men, and of Ishtob twelve thousand men.', '&para; 3~01121~ 5~05983~ 6~07200~ 9~0887~ 11~01732~, 13~01121~ 15~05983~ 16~07971~ 18~07936~ 20~0758~ 22~01050~, 25~0758~ 27~06678~, 28~06242~ 29~0505~ 30~07273~, 33~04428~ 34~04601~ 36~0505~ 37~0376~, 40~0382~ 41~08147~ 42~06240~* 43~0505~ 44~0376~.'),
  (29343, 49, 5, 23, 'For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church: and he is the saviour of the body.', '0~3754~ 2~435~ 3~2076~ 5~2776~ 8~1135~, 9~2532~ 10~5613~ 11~5547~ 14~2776~ 17~1577~: 18~2532~ 19~846~ 20~2076~ 22~4990~ 25~4983~.'),
  (7987, 9, 30, 2, 'And had taken the women captives, that were therein: they slew not any, either great or small, but carried them away, and went on their way.', '4~0802~ 5~07617~, [7] 10~04191~ 12~0376~, 14~01419~ 16~06996~, [19] 20~05090~, 22~03212~ 25~01870~.'),
  (23584, 40, 13, 35, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying, I will open my mouth in parables; I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world.', '0~3704~ 4~4137~ 5~3588~ 7~4483~ 8~1223~ 10~4396~, 11~3004~, 14~455~ 15~3450~ 16~4750~ 17~1722~ 18~3850~; 21~2044~ 27~2928~ 28~575~ 30~2602~ 33~2889~.'),
  (27917, 44, 28, 2, 'And the barbarous people shewed us no little kindness: for they kindled a fire, and received us every one, because of the present rain, and because of the cold.', '0~1161~ 3~915~ 4~3930~ 5~2254~ 6~3756~ 7~5177~ 8~5363~: 9~1063~ 11~381~ 13~4443~, 15~4355~ 16~2248~ 18~3956~, 19~1223~ 22~2186~ 23~5205~, 24~2532~ 25~1223~ 28~5592~.'),
  (1666, 2, 6, 6, 'Wherefore say unto the children of Israel, I am the LORD, and I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will rid you out of their bondage, and I will redeem you with a stretched out arm, and with great judgments:', '0~03651~ 1~0559~ 4~01121~ 6~03478~, [8] 10~03068~, 14~03318~ 20~05450~ 23~04714~, 27~05337~ 32~05656~, 36~01350~ 40~05186~ 42~02220~, 45~01419~ 46~08201~:'),
  (11427, 14, 11, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD, Ye shall not go up, nor fight against your brethren: return every man to his house: for this thing is done of me. And they obeyed the words of the LORD, and returned from going against Jeroboam.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 8~05927~, 10~03898~ 13~0251~: 14~07725~ 16~0376~ 19~01004~: 22~01697~ 24~01961~ 29~08085~ 31~01697~ 34~03068~, 36~07725~ 38~03212~ 40~03379~.'),
  (18705, 23, 51, 23, 'But I will put it into the hand of them that afflict thee; which have said to thy soul, Bow down, that we may go over: and thou hast laid thy body as the ground, and as the street, to them that went over.', '3~07760~ 7~03027~ 11~03013~ 15~0559~ 18~05315~, 20~07812~, 25~05674~: 29~07760~ 31~01460~ 34~0776~, 38~02351~, 43~05674~.'),
  (7780, 9, 21, 1, 'Then came David to Nob to Ahimelech the priest: and Ahimelech was afraid at the meeting of David, and said unto him, Why art thou alone, and no man with thee?', '&para; 1~0935~ 2~01732~ 4~05011~ 6~0288~ 8~03548~: 10~0288~ 12~02729~ 15~07125~ 17~01732~, 19~0559~ [23] 28~0376~'),
  (2521, 2, 34, 20, 'But the firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with a lamb: and if thou redeem him not, then shalt thou break his neck. All the firstborn of thy sons thou shalt redeem. And none shall appear before me empty.', '2~06363~ 5~02543~ 8~06299~ 11~07716~: 15~06299~ [16] 23~06202~. 26~01060~ 29~01121~ 32~06299~. 36~07200~ 37~06440~ 39~07387~.'),
  (18918, 23, 65, 12, 'Therefore will I number you to the sword, and ye shall all bow down to the slaughter: because when I called, ye did not answer; when I spake, ye did not hear; but did evil before mine eyes, and did choose that wherein I delighted not.', '3~04487~ 7~02719~, 13~03766~ 16~02874~: 20~07121~, 24~06030~; 27~01696~, 31~08085~; 33~06213~ 34~07451~ 37~05869~, 40~0977~ [41] 44~02654~'),
  (15139, 19, 78, 17, 'And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.', '2~02398~ 4~03254~ 8~04784~ 11~05945~ 14~06723~.'),
  (7654, 9, 17, 29, 'And David said, What have I now done? Is there not a cause?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~, 7~06213~? [8 9] 12~01697~?'),
  (6281, 6, 16, 9, 'And the separate cities for the children of Ephraim were among the inheritance of the children of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages.', '2~03995~ 3~05892~ 6~01121~ 8~0669~ [9] 10~08432~ 12~05159~ 15~01121~ 17~04519~, 20~05892~ 23~02691~.'),
  (16900, 20, 17, 18, 'A man void of understanding striketh hands, and becometh surety in the presence of his friend.', '&para; 1~0120~ 2~02638~ 4~03820~ 5~08628~ 6~03709~, [7] 8~06148~ 9~06161~ 12~06440~ 15~07453~.'),
  (11517, 14, 15, 18, 'And he brought into the house of God the things that his father had dedicated, and that he himself had dedicated, silver, and gold, and vessels.', '2~0935~ 5~01004~ 7~0430~ 12~01~ 14~06944~, 20~06944~, 21~03701~, 23~02091~, 25~03627~.'),
  (23476, 40, 11, 7, 'And as they departed, Jesus began to say unto the multitudes concerning John, What went ye out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken with the wind?', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5130~ 3~4198~, 4~2424~ 5~756~ 7~3004~ 10~3793~ 11~4012~ 12~2491~, 13~5101~ 15~1831~ 17~1519~ 19~2048~ 21~2300~? 23~2563~ 24~4531~ 25~5259~ 27~417~?'),
  (1870, 2, 12, 49, 'One law shall be to him that is homeborn, and unto the stranger that sojourneth among you.', '0~0259~ 1~08451~ 8~0249~, 12~01616~ 14~01481~ 15~08432~'),
  (14747, 19, 55, 6, 'And I said, Oh that I had wings like a dove! for then would I fly away, and be at rest.', '2~0559~, 4~05414~ 7~083~ 10~03123~! [11 12] 16~05774~, 20~07931~.'),
  (8649, 10, 22, 39, 'And I have consumed them, and wounded them, that they could not arise: yea, they are fallen under my feet.', '3~03615~ 6~04272~ 12~06965~: 16~05307~ 19~07272~.'),
  (7116, 7, 21, 7, 'How shall we do for wives for them that remain, seeing we have sworn by the LORD that we will not give them of our daughters to wives?', '3~06213~ 5~0802~ 9~03498~, 13~07650~ 16~03068~ 21~05414~ 25~01323~ 27~0802~?'),
  (25958, 42, 23, 9, 'Then he questioned with him in many words; but he answered him nothing.', '0~1161~ 2~1905~ 4~846~ 5~1722~ 6~2425~ 7~3056~; 8~1161~ 9~846~ 10~611~ 11~846~ 12~3762~.'),
  (3457, 3, 24, 6, 'And thou shalt set them in two rows, six on a row, upon the pure table before the LORD.', '3~07760~ 6~08147~ 7~04634~, 8~08337~ 11~04635~, 14~02889~ 15~07979~ 16~06440~ 18~03068~.'),
  (23394, 40, 9, 5, 'For whether is easier, to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and walk?', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ 2~2076~ 3~2123~, 5~2036~, [6] 7~266~ 9~863~ 10~4671~; 11~2228~ 13~2036~, 14~1453~, 15~2532~ 16~4043~?'),
  (10470, 13, 6, 8, 'And Ahitub begat Zadok, and Zadok begat Ahimaaz,', '1~0285~ 2~03205~ 3~06659~, 5~06659~ 6~03205~ 7~0290~,'),
  (13321, 18, 19, 15, 'They that dwell in mine house, and my maids, count me for a stranger: I am an alien in their sight.', '2~01481~ 5~01004~, 8~0519~, 9~02803~ 13~02114~: 17~05237~ 20~05869~.'),
  (2201, 2, 25, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (3071, 3, 13, 14, 'But when raw flesh appeareth in him, he shall be unclean.', '1~03117~ 2~02416~ 3~01320~ 4~07200~ 10~02930~.'),
  (9417, 11, 20, 1, 'And Benhadad the king of Syria gathered all his host together: and there were thirty and two kings with him, and horses, and chariots: and he went up and besieged Samaria, and warred against it.', '&para; 1~01130~ 3~04428~ 5~0758~ 6~06908~ 9~02428~ 10~06908~: [12 13] 14~07970~ 16~08147~ 17~04428~ 21~05483~, 23~07393~: 27~05927~ 29~06696~ 30~08111~, 32~03898~'),
  (14724, 19, 52, 5, 'God shall likewise destroy thee for ever, he shall take thee away, and pluck thee out of thy dwelling place, and root thee out of the land of the living. Selah.', '0~0410~ 3~05422~ 6~05331~, 11~02846~, 15~05255~ [17] 19~0168~, 23~08327~ 26~0776~ 29~02416~. 30~05542~.'),
  (19758, 24, 32, 18, 'Thou shewest lovingkindness unto thousands, and recompensest the iniquity of the fathers into the bosom of their children after them: the Great, the Mighty God, the LORD of hosts, is his name,', '1~06213~ 2~02617~ 4~0505~, 6~07999~ 8~05771~ 11~01~ 14~02436~ 17~01121~ 18~0310~ 21~01419~, 23~01368~ 24~0410~, 26~03068~ 28~06635~, [29] 31~08034~,'),
  (1387, 1, 45, 24, 'So he sent his brethren away, and they departed: and he said unto them, See that ye fall not out by the way.', '2~07971~ 4~0251~ 5~07971~, 8~03212~: 11~0559~ 19~07264~ 22~01870~.'),
  (22594, 33, 1, 6, 'Therefore I will make Samaria as an heap of the field, and as plantings of a vineyard: and I will pour down the stones thereof into the valley, and I will discover the foundations thereof.', '3~07760~ 4~08111~ 7~05856~ 10~07704~, [11] 13~04302~ 16~03754~: 21~05064~ 23~068~ 27~01516~, 31~01540~ 33~03247~'),
  (19513, 24, 23, 20, 'The anger of the LORD shall not return, until he have executed, and till he have performed the thoughts of his heart: in the latter days ye shall consider it perfectly.', '1~0639~ 4~03068~ 7~07725~, 11~06213~, 16~06965~ 18~04209~ 21~03820~: 24~0319~ 25~03117~ 28~0995~ 30~0998~.'),
  (12708, 16, 13, 28, 'And one of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was son in law to Sanballat the Horonite: therefore I chased him from me.', '[1] 4~01121~ 6~03111~, 8~01121~ 10~0475~ 12~01419~ 13~03548~, [14] 17~02860~ 19~05571~ 21~02772~: 24~01272~'),
  (1322, 1, 43, 27, 'And he asked them of their welfare, and said, Is your father well, the old man of whom ye spake? Is he yet alive?', '2~07592~ [5] 6~07965~, 8~0559~, [9] 11~01~ 12~07965~, 15~02205~ 19~0559~? [20] 23~02416~?'),
  (2284, 2, 27, 7, 'And the staves shall be put into the rings, and the staves shall be upon the two sides of the altar, to bear it.', '2~0905~ 5~0935~ 8~02885~, 11~0905~ 16~08147~ 17~06763~ 20~04196~, 22~05375~'),
  (4305, 4, 19, 11, 'He that toucheth the dead body of any man shall be unclean seven days.', '&para; 2~05060~ 4~04191~ 5~05315~ 8~0120~ 11~02930~ 12~07651~ 13~03117~.'),
  (28012, 45, 3, 5, 'But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say? Is God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man)', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~2257~ 3~93~ 4~4921~ 6~1343~ 8~2316~, 9~5101~ 12~2046~ 13~3361~?* [14] 15~2316~ 16~94~ 18~2018~ 19~3709~? 21~3004~ 22~2596~ 24~444~)'),
  (6986, 7, 16, 30, 'And Samson said, Let me die with the Philistines. And he bowed himself with all his might; and the house fell upon the lords, and upon all the people that were therein. So the dead which he slew at his death were more than they which he slew in his life.', '1~08123~ 2~0559~, 5~04191~ 6~05315~* 9~06430~. 12~05186~ [15 16] 17~03581~; 20~01004~ 21~05307~ 24~05633~, 29~05971~ [31] 35~04191~ 38~04191~ 41~04194~ 43~07227~ [45] 48~04191~ 51~02416~.'),
  (6740, 7, 8, 14, 'And caught a young man of the men of Succoth, and inquired of him: and he described unto him the princes of Succoth, and the elders thereof, even threescore and seventeen men.', '1~03920~ 4~05288~ 7~0582~ 9~05523~, 11~07592~ 16~03789~ 20~08269~ 22~05523~, 25~02205~ [27] 30~07651~ 31~07657~* 32~0376~.'),
  (14904, 19, 67, 2, 'That thy way may be known upon earth, thy saving health among all nations.', '2~01870~ 5~03045~ 7~0776~, 10~03444~ 13~01471~.'),
  (5808, 5, 32, 44, 'And Moses came and spake all the words of this song in the ears of the people, he, and Hoshea the son of Nun.', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~0935~ 4~01696~ 7~01697~ 10~07892~ 13~0241~ 16~05971~, 19~01954~ 21~01121~ 23~05126~.'),
  (20483, 26, 1, 10, 'As for the likeness of their faces, they four had the face of a man, and the face of a lion, on the right side: and they four had the face of an ox on the left side; they four also had the face of an eagle.', '3~01823~ 6~06440~, 8~0702~ 11~06440~ 14~0120~, 17~06440~ 20~0738~, 24~03225~: 27~0702~ 30~06440~ 33~07794~ 37~08040~; 39~0702~ 43~06440~ 46~05404~.'),
  (10566, 13, 7, 23, 'And when he went in to his wife, she conceived, and bare a son, and he called his name Beriah, because it went evil with his house.', '4~0935~ 7~0802~, 9~02029~, 11~03205~ 13~01121~, 16~07121~ 18~08034~ 19~01283~, 23~07451~ 26~01004~.'),
  (10766, 13, 12, 38, 'All these men of war, that could keep rank, came with a perfect heart to Hebron, to make David king over all Israel: and all the rest also of Israel were of one heart to make David king.', '2~0582~ 4~04421~, 7~05737~ 8~04634~, 9~0935~ 12~08003~ 13~03820~ 15~02275~, 18~01732~ 19~04427~ 22~03478~: 26~07611~ 29~03478~ [30] 32~0259~ 33~03824~ 36~01732~ 37~04427~.'),
  (3405, 3, 22, 31, 'Therefore shall ye keep my commandments, and do them: I am the LORD.', '3~08104~ 5~04687~, 7~06213~ [10] 12~03068~.'),
  (3646, 4, 1, 37, 'Those that were numbered of them, even of the tribe of Benjamin, were thirty and five thousand and four hundred.', '3~06485~ [6] 9~04294~ 11~01144~, [12] 13~07970~ 15~02568~ 16~0505~ 18~0702~ 19~03967~.'),
  (26026, 42, 24, 21, 'But we trusted that it had been he which should have redeemed Israel: and beside all this, to day is the third day since these things were done.', '0~1161~ 1~2249~ 2~1679~ 3~3754~ 6~2076~ 7~846~ 9~3195~ 11~3084~ 12~2474~: 13~235~ 14~4862~ 15~1065~* 16~3956~ 17~5125~, 19~4594~ 20~71~ 21~5026~ 22~5154~ 23~2250~ 24~3739~ 25~575~ 26~5023~ 28~1096~.'),
  (9748, 12, 8, 13, 'And Hazael said, But what, is thy servant a dog, that he should do this great thing? And Elisha answered, The LORD hath shewed me that thou shalt be king over Syria.', '1~02371~ 2~0559~, [5] 7~05650~ 9~03611~, 13~06213~ 15~01419~ 16~01697~? 18~0477~ 19~0559~, 21~03068~ 23~07200~ [27 28] 29~04428~ 31~0758~.'),
  (10048, 12, 18, 16, 'At that time did Hezekiah cut off the gold from the doors of the temple of the LORD, and from the pillars which Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid, and gave it to the king of Assyria.', '2~06256~ 4~02396~ 6~07112~ [7 9] 11~01817~ 14~01964~ 17~03068~, [19] 21~0547~ 23~02396~ 24~04428~ 26~03063~ 28~06823~, 30~05414~ 34~04428~ 36~0804~.'),
  (24498, 41, 7, 24, 'And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house, and would have no man know it: but he could not be hid.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1564~ 4~450~, 6~565~ 7~1519~ 9~3181~ 11~5184~ 12~2532~ 13~4605~, 14~2532~ 15~1525~ 16~1519~ 18~3614~, 21~2309~ 23~3762~ 24~1097~ [25] 26~2532~ 28~1410~ 29~3756~ 31~2990~.'),
  (7374, 9, 7, 15, 'And Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life.', '1~08050~ 2~08199~ 3~03478~ 6~03117~ 9~02416~.'),
  (5591, 5, 26, 19, 'And to make thee high above all nations which he hath made, in praise, and in name, and in honour; and that thou mayest be an holy people unto the LORD thy God, as he hath spoken.', '2~05414~ 4~05945~ 7~01471~ 11~06213~, 13~08416~, 16~08034~, 19~08597~; 26~06918~ 27~05971~ 30~03068~ 32~0430~, 36~01696~.'),
  (14802, 19, 59, 3, 'For, lo, they lie in wait for my soul: the mighty are gathered against me; not for my transgression, nor for my sin, O LORD.', '5~0693~ 8~05315~: 10~05794~ 12~01481~ [16] 18~06588~, [20] 22~02403~, 24~03068~.'),
  (29869, 55, 2, 26, 'And that they may recover themselves out of the snare of the devil, who are taken captive by him at his will.', '0~2532~ [1] 5~366~ 7~1537~ 9~3803~ 12~1228~, 16~2221~ 17~5259~ 18~846~ 19~1519~ 20~1565~ 21~2307~.'),
  (20632, 26, 9, 1, 'He cried also in mine ears with a loud voice, saying, Cause them that have charge over the city to draw near, even every man with his destroying weapon in his hand.', '&para; 1~07121~ 5~0241~ 8~01419~ 9~06963~, 10~0559~, 15~06486~ 18~05892~ 21~07126~, 24~0376~ [25] 27~04892~ 28~03627~ 31~03027~.'),
  (11725, 14, 25, 12, 'And other ten thousand left alive did the children of Judah carry away captive, and brought them unto the top of the rock, and cast them down from the top of the rock, that they all were broken in pieces.', '[1] 2~06235~ 3~0505~ [4] 5~02416~ 8~01121~ 10~03063~ 13~07617~, 15~0935~ 19~07218~ 22~05553~, 26~07993~ 29~07218~ 32~05553~, 39~01234~.'),
  (25773, 42, 19, 28, 'And when he had thus spoken, he went before, ascending up to Jerusalem.', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~5023~ 5~2036~, 7~4198~ 8~1715~, 10~305~ 11~1519~ 12~2414~.'),
  (14830, 19, 61, 2, 'From the end of the earth will I cry unto thee, when my heart is overwhelmed: lead me to the rock that is higher than I.', '2~07097~ 5~0776~ 8~07121~ 13~03820~ 15~05848~: 16~05148~ 20~06697~ [21] 23~07311~'),
  (21869, 27, 4, 23, 'And whereas the king saw a watcher and an holy one coming down from heaven, and saying, Hew the tree down, and destroy it; yet leave the stump of the roots thereof in the earth, even with a band of iron and brass, in the tender grass of the field; and let it be wet with the dew of heaven, and let his portion be with the beasts of the field, till seven times pass over him;', '3~04430~ 4~02370~ 6~05894~ 10~06922~ 12~05182~ 13~04481~ 14~08065~, 16~0560~, 17~01414~ 19~0363~ 20~01414~, 22~02255~ 24~01297~ 25~07662~ 27~06136~ 30~08330~ 34~0772~, 38~0613~ 40~06523~ 42~05174~, 46~01883~ 49~01251~; 54~06647~ 57~02920~ 59~08065~, [61] 63~02508~ [64] 65~05974~ 67~02423~ 70~01251~, 71~05705~ 72~07655~ 73~05732~ 74~02499~ 75~05922~'),
  (15025, 19, 72, 16, 'There shall be an handful of corn in the earth upon the top of the mountains; the fruit thereof shall shake like Lebanon: and they of the city shall flourish like grass of the earth.', '4~06451~ 6~01250~ 9~0776~ 12~07218~ 15~02022~; 17~06529~ 20~07493~ 22~03844~: [24] 27~05892~ 29~06692~ 31~06212~ 34~0776~.'),
  (21144, 26, 27, 14, 'They of the house of Togarmah traded in thy fairs with horses and horsemen and mules.', '3~01004~ 5~08425~ 6~05414~ 9~05801~ 11~05483~ 13~06571~ 15~06505~.'),
  (6969, 7, 16, 13, 'And Delilah said unto Samson, Hitherto thou hast mocked me, and told me lies: tell me wherewith thou mightest be bound. And he said unto her, If thou weavest the seven locks of my head with the web.', '1~01807~ 2~0559~ 4~08123~, 5~02008~ 8~02048~ 11~01696~ 13~03577~: 14~05046~ 20~0631~. 23~0559~ 28~0707~ 30~07651~ 31~04253~ 34~07218~ 37~04545~.'),
  (9321, 11, 16, 30, 'And Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the LORD above all that were before him.', '1~0256~ 3~01121~ 5~06018~ 6~06213~ 7~07451~ 10~05869~ 13~03068~ [17] 18~06440~'),
  (15268, 19, 83, 18, 'That men may know that thou, whose name alone is JEHOVAH, art the most high over all the earth.', '[1] 3~03045~ 7~08034~ [9] 10~03068~, [11] 14~05945~ 18~0776~.'),
  (25232, 42, 7, 25, 'But what went ye out for to see? A man clothed in soft raiment? Behold, they which are gorgeously apparelled, and live delicately, are in kings'' courts.', '0~235~ 1~5101~ 4~1831~ 7~1492~? 9~444~ 10~294~ 11~1722~ 12~3120~ 13~2440~? 14~2400~, 17~1722~ 18~1741~ 19~2441~, 20~2532~ 21~5225~ 22~5172~, 23~1526~ 24~1722~ 26~933~.'),
  (1021, 1, 35, 5, 'And they journeyed: and the terror of God was upon the cities that were round about them, and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob.', '2~05265~: 5~02847~ 7~0430~ 11~05892~ [13] 15~05439~ 21~07291~ 22~0310~ 24~01121~ 26~03290~.'),
  (21327, 26, 34, 5, 'And they were scattered, because there is no shepherd: and they became meat to all the beasts of the field, when they were scattered.', '3~06327~, [5 6] 8~07462~: 12~0402~ 16~02416~ 19~07704~, 23~06327~.'),
  (15947, 19, 119, 40, 'Behold, I have longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousness.', '&para; 3~08373~ 6~06490~: 7~02421~ 11~06666~.');
