  (12831, 17, 8, 5, 'And said, If it please the king, and if I have found favour in his sight, and the thing seem right before the king, and I be pleasing in his eyes, let it be written to reverse the letters devised by Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, which he wrote to destroy the Jews which are in all the king''s provinces:', '1~0559~, 4~02896~ 6~04428~, 11~04672~ 12~02580~ 15~06440~, 18~01697~ [19] 20~03787~ 21~06440~ 23~04428~, [26] 27~02896~ 30~05869~, 34~03789~ 36~07725~ 38~05612~ 39~04284~ 41~02001~ 43~01121~ 45~04099~ 47~091~, 50~03789~ 52~06~ 54~03064~ [56] 60~04428~ 61~04082~:'),
  (7917, 9, 26, 5, 'And David arose, and came to the place where Saul had pitched: and David beheld the place where Saul lay, and Abner the son of Ner, the captain of his host: and Saul lay in the trench, and the people pitched round about him.', '1~01732~ 2~06965~, 4~0935~ 7~04725~ 9~07586~ 11~02583~: 13~01732~ 14~07200~ 16~04725~ 18~07586~ 19~07901~, 21~074~ 23~01121~ 25~05369~, 27~08269~ 30~06635~: 32~07586~ 33~07901~ 36~04570~, 39~05971~ 40~02583~ 42~05439~'),
  (5133, 5, 7, 16, 'And thou shalt consume all the people which the LORD thy God shall deliver thee; thine eye shall have no pity upon them: neither shalt thou serve their gods; for that will be a snare unto thee.', '3~0398~ 6~05971~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~ 13~05414~ 16~05869~ 20~02347~ 26~05647~ 28~0430~; [31 32] 34~04170~'),
  (20252, 24, 51, 31, 'One post shall run to meet another, and one messenger to meet another, to shew the king of Babylon that his city is taken at one end,', '1~07323~ 3~07323~ 5~07125~ 6~07323~, 9~05046~ 11~07125~ 12~05046~, 14~05046~ 16~04428~ 18~0894~ 21~05892~ 23~03920~ [25] 26~07097~,'),
  (23895, 40, 22, 13, 'Then said the king to the servants, Bind him hand and foot, and take him away, and cast him into outer darkness; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.', '0~5119~ 1~2036~ 3~935~ 6~1249~, 7~1210~ 8~846~ 9~5495~ 10~2532~ 11~4228~, 13~142~ 14~846~ 15~142~, 16~2532~ 17~1544~ [18] 19~1519~ 20~1857~ 21~4655~; 22~1563~ 24~2071~ 25~2805~ 26~2532~ 27~1030~ 29~3599~.'),
  (14565, 19, 42, 1, 'To the chief Musician, Maschil, for the sons of Korah. As the hart panteth after the water brooks, so panteth my soul after thee, O God.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 4~04905~, 7~01121~ 9] 9~07141~ 12~0354~ 13~06165~ 16~04325~ 17~0650~, 19~06165~ 21~05315~ 25~0430~.'),
  (17770, 23, 5, 22, 'Woe unto them that are mighty to drink wine, and men of strength to mingle strong drink:', '0~01945~ [2 4] 5~01368~ 7~08354~ 8~03196~, 10~0582~ 12~02428~ 14~04537~ 16~07941~:'),
  (7372, 9, 7, 13, 'So the Philistines were subdued, and they came no more into the coast of Israel: and the hand of the LORD was against the Philistines all the days of Samuel.', '&para; 2~06430~ 4~03665~, 7~0935~ 9~03254~ 12~01366~ 14~03478~: 17~03027~ 20~03068~ 24~06430~ 27~03117~ 29~08050~.'),
  (20313, 24, 52, 28, 'This is the people whom Nebuchadrezzar carried away captive: in the seventh year three thousand Jews and three and twenty:', '[1] 3~05971~ 5~05019~ 8~01540~: 11~07651~ 12~08141~ 13~07969~ 14~0505~ 15~03064~ 17~07969~ 19~06242~:'),
  (25514, 42, 12, 42, 'And the Lord said, Who then is that faithful and wise steward, whom his lord shall make ruler over his household, to give them their portion of meat in due season?', '0~1161~ 2~2962~ 3~2036~, 4~5101~ 5~686~ 6~2076~ 8~4103~ 9~2532~ 10~5429~ 11~3623~, 12~3739~ [13] 14~2962~ 17~2525~ 18~1909~ 19~846~ 20~2322~, 22~1325~ [23 24] 27~4620~ 28~1722~ 30~2540~?'),
  (22329, 29, 2, 9, 'They shall run to and fro in the city; they shall run upon the wall, they shall climb up upon the houses; they shall enter in at the windows like a thief.', '5~08264~ 8~05892~; 11~07323~ 14~02346~, 18~05927~ 21~01004~; 25~0935~ 28~02474~ 31~01590~.'),
  (7235, 9, 1, 16, 'Count not thine handmaid for a daughter of Belial: for out of the abundance of my complaint and grief have I spoken hitherto.', '0~05414~ 3~0519~ 4~06440~ 6~01323~ 8~01100~: 13~07230~ 16~07879~ 18~03708~ 21~01696~'),
  (3408, 3, 23, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (13598, 18, 31, 1, 'I made a covenant with mine eyes; why then should I think upon a maid?', '&para; 1~03772~ 3~01285~ 6~05869~; 11~0995~ 14~01330~?'),
