VALUES
  (19050, 24, 4, 14, 'O Jerusalem, wash thine heart from wickedness, that thou mayest be saved. How long shall thy vain thoughts lodge within thee?', '1~03389~, 2~03526~ 4~03820~ 6~07451~, 11~03467~. 16~0205~ 17~04284~ 18~03885~ 19~07130~'),
  (12441, 16, 7, 12, 'The children of Elam, a thousand two hundred fifty and four.', '1~01121~ 3~05867~, 5~0505~ 7~03967~ 8~02572~ 10~0702~.'),
  (2943, 3, 8, 21, 'And he washed the inwards and the legs in water; and Moses burnt the whole ram upon the altar: it was a burnt sacrifice for a sweet savour, and an offering made by fire unto the LORD; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '2~07364~ 4~07130~ 7~03767~ 9~04325~; 11~04872~ 12~06999~ 15~0352~ 18~04196~: [20] 23~05930~ 26~05207~ 27~07381~, [28] 33~0801~ 36~03068~; 39~03068~ 40~06680~ 41~04872~.'),
  (10592, 13, 8, 9, 'And he begat of Hodesh his wife, Jobab, and Zibia, and Mesha, and Malcham,', '2~03205~ 4~02321~ 6~0802~, 7~03103~, 9~06644~, 11~04331~, 13~04445~,'),
  (27240, 44, 9, 8, 'And Saul arose from the earth; and when his eyes were opened, he saw no man: but they led him by the hand, and brought him into Damascus.', '0~1161~ 1~4569~ 2~1453~ 3~575~ 5~1093~; 6~1161~ 8~846~ 9~3788~ 11~455~, 13~991~ 15~3762~: 16~1161~ 18~5496~ 19~846~ 22~5496~, 24~1521~ [25] 26~1519~ 27~1154~.'),
  (11441, 14, 11, 18, 'And Rehoboam took him Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of David to wife, and Abihail the daughter of Eliab the son of Jesse;', '1~07346~ 2~03947~ 4~04258~ 6~01323~ 7~01121~* 9~03406~ 11~01121~ 13~01732~ 15~0802~, [16] 17~032~ 19~01323~ 21~0446~ 23~01121~ 25~03448~;'),
  (1587, 2, 3, 3, 'And Moses said, I will now turn aside, and see this great sight, why the bush is not burnt.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~, 7~05493~, 9~07200~ 11~01419~ 12~04758~, 13~04069~ 15~05572~ 18~01197~.'),
  (721, 1, 26, 25, 'And he builded an altar there, and called upon the name of the LORD, and pitched his tent there: and there Isaac''s servants digged a well.', '2~01129~ 4~04196~ 7~07121~ 10~08034~ 13~03068~, 15~05186~ 17~0168~ 21~03327~ 22~05650~ 23~03738~ 25~0875~.'),
  (19937, 24, 39, 5, 'But the Chaldeans'' army pursued after them, and overtook Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho: and when they had taken him, they brought him up to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to Riblah in the land of Hamath, where he gave judgment upon him.', '2~03778~ 3~02428~ 4~07291~ 5~0310~ 8~05381~ 9~06667~ 12~06160~ 14~03405~: 19~03947~ 24~05927~ 26~05019~ 27~04428~ 29~0894~ 31~07247~ 34~0776~ 36~02574~, 39~01696~ 40~04941~'),
  (20805, 26, 16, 34, 'And the contrary is in thee from other women in thy whoredoms, whereas none followeth thee to commit whoredoms: and in that thou givest a reward, and no reward is given unto thee, therefore thou art contrary.', '2~02016~ [7] 8~0802~ 11~08457~, 14~0310~ 18~02181~: 23~05414~ 25~0868~, 28~0868~ 30~05414~ 35~01961~ 36~02016~.'),
  (4397, 4, 22, 17, 'For I will promote thee unto very great honour, and I will do whatsoever thou sayest unto me: come therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people.', '3~03513~ 6~03966~ 7~03513~ 8~03513~, 12~06213~ 15~0559~ 18~03212~ 23~06895~ 26~05971~.'),
  (9484, 11, 21, 25, 'But there was none like unto Ahab, which did sell himself to work wickedness in the sight of the LORD, whom Jezebel his wife stirred up.', '6~0256~, 9~04376~ 12~06213~ 13~07451~ 16~05869~ 19~03068~, 21~0348~ 23~0802~ 25~05496~.'),
  (29447, 50, 3, 10, 'That I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, being made conformable unto his death;', '3~1097~ 4~846~, 5~2532~ 7~1411~ 9~846~ 10~386~, 11~2532~ 13~2842~ 15~846~ 16~3804~, 19~4833~ 21~846~ 22~2288~;'),
  (2112, 2, 21, 30, 'If there be laid on him a sum of money, then he shall give for the ransom of his life whatsoever is laid upon him.', '3~07896~ 9~03724~, 13~05414~ 16~06306~ 19~05315~ 22~07896~'),
  (21802, 27, 2, 35, 'Then was the iron, the clay, the brass, the silver, and the gold, broken to pieces together, and became like the chaff of the summer threshingfloors; and the wind carried them away, that no place was found for them: and the stone that smote the image became a great mountain, and filled the whole earth.', '0~0116~ 3~06523~, 5~02635~, 7~05174~, 9~03702~, 12~01722~, 15~01855~ 16~02298~, 18~01934~ 21~05784~ 22~04481~ 24~07007~ 25~0147~; 28~07308~ 29~05376~ 30~01994~ 31~05376~, 32~03606~ 33~03809~ 34~0870~ 36~07912~ 41~069~ 43~04223~ 45~06755~ 46~01934~ 48~07229~ 49~02906~, 51~04391~ 53~03606~ 54~0772~.'),
  (9516, 11, 22, 28, 'And Micaiah said, If thou return at all in peace, the LORD hath not spoken by me. And he said, Hearken, O people, every one of you.', '1~04321~ 2~0559~, 5~07725~ 7~07725~ 9~07965~, 11~03068~ 14~01696~ 19~0559~, 20~08085~, 22~05971~,'),
  (6185, 6, 13, 24, 'And Moses gave inheritance unto the tribe of Gad, even unto the children of Gad according to their families.', '1~04872~ 2~05414~ [3] 6~04294~ 8~01410~, [9] 12~01121~ 14~01410~ 18~04940~.'),
  (21632, 26, 44, 24, 'And in controversy they shall stand in judgment; and they shall judge it according to my judgments: and they shall keep my laws and my statutes in all mine assemblies; and they shall hallow my sabbaths.', '2~07379~ 5~05975~ 7~08199~; [8] 11~08199~ 16~04941~: 20~08104~ 22~08451~ 25~02708~ 29~04150~; 33~06942~ 35~07676~.'),
  (18007, 23, 18, 1, 'Woe to the land shadowing with wings, which is beyond the rivers of Ethiopia:', '&para; 0~01945~ 3~0776~ 4~06767~ 6~03671~, [8] 9~05676~ 11~05104~ 13~03568~:'),
  (19614, 24, 27, 9, 'Therefore hearken not ye to your prophets, nor to your diviners, nor to your dreamers, nor to your enchanters, nor to your sorcerers, which speak unto you, saying, Ye shall not serve the king of Babylon:', '1~08085~ 6~05030~, 10~07080~, 14~02472~, 18~06049~, 22~03786~, 24~0559~ 27~0559~, 31~05647~ 33~04428~ 35~0894~:'),
  (28452, 46, 4, 3, 'But with me it is a very small thing that I should be judged of you, or of man''s judgment: yea, I judge not mine own self.', '0~1161~ 2~1698~ 4~2076~ 8~1646~ 9~1519~* 10~2443~ 14~350~ 15~5259~ 16~5216~, 17~2228~ 18~5259~ 19~442~ 20~2250~: 21~235~, 23~350~ 24~3761~ 27~1683~.'),
  (11534, 14, 17, 2, 'And he placed forces in all the fenced cities of Judah, and set garrisons in the land of Judah, and in the cities of Ephraim, which Asa his father had taken.', '2~05414~ 3~02428~ 7~01219~ 8~05892~ 10~03063~, 12~05414~ 13~05333~ 16~0776~ 18~03063~, 22~05892~ 24~0669~, 26~0609~ 28~01~ 30~03920~.'),
  (5564, 5, 25, 11, 'When men strive together one with another, and the wife of the one draweth near for to deliver her husband out of the hand of him that smiteth him, and putteth forth her hand, and taketh him by the secrets:', '1~0582~ 2~05327~ 3~03162~ 6~0376~ 7~0251~,* 10~0802~ 13~0259~ 15~07126~ 18~05337~ 20~0376~ 24~03027~ 28~05221~ 32~07971~ 34~03027~, 36~02388~ 40~04016~:'),
  (20961, 26, 21, 8, 'Again the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (26311, 43, 6, 39, 'And this is the Father''s will which hath sent me, that of all which he hath given me I should lose nothing, but should raise it up again at the last day.', '0~1161~ 1~5124~ 2~2076~ 4~3962~ 5~2307~ 6~3588~ 8~3992~ 9~3165~, 10~2443~ 12~3956~ 13~3739~ 16~1325~ 17~3427~ 20~622~ 21~846~ 22~3361~* 23~1537~,* 24~235~ 26~450~ 27~846~ 29~450~ 30~1722~ 32~2078~ 33~2250~.'),
  (7290, 9, 3, 7, 'Now Samuel did not yet know the LORD, neither was the word of the LORD yet revealed unto him.', '1~08050~ 4~02962~ 5~03045~ 7~03068~, 11~01697~ 14~03068~ 16~01540~'),
  (17233, 20, 28, 28, 'When the wicked rise, men hide themselves: but when they perish, the righteous increase.', '&para; 2~07563~ 3~06965~, 4~0120~ 5~05641~ 10~06~, 12~06662~ 13~07235~.'),
  (10428, 13, 4, 35, 'And Joel, and Jehu the son of Josibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,', '1~03100~, 3~03058~ 5~01121~ 7~03143~, 9~01121~ 11~08304~, 13~01121~ 15~06221~,'),
  (16644, 20, 8, 33, 'Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.', '0~08085~ 1~04148~, 4~02449~, 6~06544~'),
  (31003, 66, 17, 12, 'And the ten horns which thou sawest are ten kings, which have received no kingdom as yet; but receive power as kings one hour with the beast.', '0~2532~ 2~1176~ 3~2768~ 4~3739~ 6~1492~ 7~1526~ 8~1176~ 9~935~, 10~3748~ 12~2983~ 13~3768~ 14~932~ 16~3768~; 17~235~ 18~2983~ 19~1849~ 20~5613~ 21~935~ 22~3391~ 23~5610~ 24~3326~ 26~2342~.'),
  (3026, 3, 11, 24, 'And for these ye shall be unclean: whosoever toucheth the carcase of them shall be unclean until the even.', '6~02930~: 8~05060~ 10~05038~ 15~02930~ 18~06153~.'),
  (13020, 18, 7, 3, 'So am I made to possess months of vanity, and wearisome nights are appointed to me.', '5~05157~ 6~03391~ 8~07723~, 10~05999~ 11~03915~ 13~04487~'),
  (15836, 19, 114, 5, 'What ailed thee, O thou sea, that thou fleddest? thou Jordan, that thou wast driven back?', '[1] 5~03220~, 8~05127~? 10~03383~, [11] 14~05437~ 15~0268~?'),
  (10000, 12, 17, 9, 'And the children of Israel did secretly those things that were not right against the LORD their God, and they built them high places in all their cities, from the tower of the watchmen to the fenced city.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 6~02644~ [7] 8~01697~ [10] 15~03068~ 17~0430~, 20~01129~ 23~01116~ 27~05892~, 30~04026~ 33~05341~ 36~04013~ 37~05892~.'),
  (11483, 14, 13, 21, 'But Abijah waxed mighty, and married fourteen wives, and begat twenty and two sons, and sixteen daughters.', '1~029~ 3~02388~, 5~05375~ 6~06240~ 7~0702~* 8~0802~, 10~03205~ 11~06242~ 13~08147~ 14~01121~, 16~06240~ 17~08337~* 18~01323~.'),
  (25008, 42, 2, 23, '(As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that openeth the womb shall be called holy to the Lord;)', '0~(2531~ 3~1125~ 4~1722~ 6~3551~ 9~2962~ 10~3754~,* 11~3956~ 12~730~ 14~1272~ 16~3388~ 19~2564~ 20~40~ 23~2962~;)'),
  (7164, 8, 2, 8, 'Then said Boaz unto Ruth, Hearest thou not, my daughter? Go not to glean in another field, neither go from hence, but abide here fast by my maidens:', '1~0559~ 2~01162~ 4~07327~, 5~08085~ 9~01323~? 10~03212~ 13~03950~ 15~0312~ 16~07704~, 18~05674~ 22~01692~ 27~05291~:'),
  (27839, 44, 25, 27, 'For it seemeth to me unreasonable to send a prisoner, and not withal to signify the crimes laid against him.', '0~1063~ 2~1380~ 4~3427~ 5~249~ 7~3992~ 9~1198~, 10~2532~ 12~3361~ 14~4591~ 16~156~ [17] 18~2596~ 19~846~.'),
  (28914, 47, 5, 21, 'For he hath made him to be sin for us, who knew no sin; that we might be made the righteousness of God in him.', '0~1063~ 3~4160~ [5 6] 7~266~ 8~5228~ 9~2257~, 10~3588~ 11~1097~ 12~3361~ 13~266~; 14~2443~ 15~2249~ 18~1096~ 20~1343~ 22~2316~ 23~1722~ 24~846~.'),
  (28636, 46, 11, 20, 'When ye come together therefore into one place, this is not to eat the Lord''s supper.', '1~5216~ 3~4905~ 4~3767~ 5~1909~ 7~846~, [8] 9~2076~ 10~3756~ 12~5315~ 14~2960~ 15~1173~.'),
  (3252, 3, 17, 12, 'Therefore I said unto the children of Israel, No soul of you shall eat blood, neither shall any stranger that sojourneth among you eat blood.', '2~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~, 9~05315~ 13~0398~ 14~01818~, 18~01616~ 20~01481~ 21~08432~ 23~0398~ 24~01818~.'),
  (4972, 5, 2, 28, 'Thou shalt sell me meat for money, that I may eat; and give me water for money, that I may drink: only I will pass through on my feet;', '2~07666~ 4~0400~ 6~03701~, 10~0398~; 12~05414~ 14~04325~ 16~03701~, 20~08354~: 25~05674~ 28~07272~;'),
  (20111, 24, 48, 22, 'And upon Dibon, and upon Nebo, and upon Bethdiblathaim,', '2~01769~, 5~05015~, 8~01015~,'),
  (17334, 21, 1, 10, 'Is there any thing whereof it may be said, See, this is new? it hath been already of old time, which was before us.', '1~03426~ [2] 3~01697~ 8~0559~, 9~07200~, [11] 12~02319~? 16~03528~ 19~05769~, 22~06440~'),
  (29408, 50, 2, 1, 'If there be therefore any consolation in Christ, if any comfort of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any bowels and mercies,', '&para; [1 2] 3~3767~ 4~1536~ 5~3874~ 6~1722~ 7~5547~, 9~1536~ 10~3890~ 12~26~, 14~1536~ 15~2842~ 18~4151~, 20~1536~ 21~4698~ 22~2532~ 23~3628~,'),
  (10233, 12, 25, 3, 'And on the ninth day of the fourth month the famine prevailed in the city, and there was no bread for the people of the land.', '3~08672~ [4] [7] 8~02320~ 10~07458~ 11~02388~ 14~05892~, 19~03899~ 22~05971~ 25~0776~.'),
  (3870, 4, 7, 15, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (7500, 9, 13, 8, 'And he tarried seven days, according to the set time that Samuel had appointed: but Samuel came not to Gilgal; and the people were scattered from him.', '&para; 2~03176~ 3~07651~ 4~03117~, 9~04150~ 11~08050~ [12 13] 15~08050~ 16~0935~ 19~01537~; 22~05971~ 24~06327~'),
  (26787, 43, 17, 13, 'And now come I to thee; and these things I speak in the world, that they might have my joy fulfilled in themselves.', '0~1161~ 1~3568~ 3~2064~ 4~4314~ 5~4571~; 6~2532~ 8~5023~ 10~2980~ 11~1722~ 13~2889~, 14~2443~ 17~2192~ 18~1699~ 19~5479~ 20~4137~ 21~1722~ 22~846~.'),
  (28951, 47, 8, 3, 'For to their power, I bear record, yea, and beyond their power they were willing of themselves;', '0~3754~ 1~2596~ [2] 3~1411~, 6~3140~, 8~2532~ 9~5228~ [10] 11~1411~ [12 13] 16~830~;'),
  (17246, 20, 29, 13, 'The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the LORD lighteneth both their eyes.', '&para; 1~07326~ 4~08501~ 5~0376~ 7~06298~: 9~03068~ 10~0215~ 11~08147~ 13~05869~.'),
  (27318, 44, 10, 43, 'To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name whosoever believeth in him shall receive remission of sins.', '1~5129~ 2~3140~ 3~3956~ 5~4396~ 6~3140~, 8~1223~ 9~846~ 10~3686~ 11~3956~ 12~4100~ 13~1519~ 14~846~ 16~2983~ 17~859~ 19~266~.'),
  (6341, 6, 19, 13, 'And from thence passeth on along on the east to Gittahhepher, to Ittahkazin, and goeth out to Remmonmethoar to Neah;', '5~05674~ 8~06924~ 9~04217~ 10~01662~, 12~06278~, 15~03318~ 17~07417~ 19~05269~;'),
  (8086, 10, 2, 30, 'And Joab returned from following Abner: and when he had gathered all the people together, there lacked of David''s servants nineteen men and Asahel.', '1~03097~ 2~07725~ 4~0310~ 5~074~: 10~06908~ 13~05971~ 14~06908~, 16~06485~ 18~01732~ 19~05650~ 20~06240~ 21~08672~* 22~0376~ 24~06214~.'),
  (27015, 44, 3, 3, 'Who seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple asked an alms.', '0~3739~ 1~1492~ 2~4074~ 3~2532~ 4~2491~ 5~3195~ 7~1524~ 8~1519~ 10~2411~ 11~2065~ 13~1654~.'),
  (20678, 26, 11, 14, 'Again the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (26955, 44, 1, 16, 'Men and brethren, this scripture must needs have been fulfilled, which the Holy Ghost by the mouth of David spake before concerning Judas, which was guide to them that took Jesus.', '0~435~ [1] 2~80~, 3~5026~ 4~1124~ 5~1163~ 9~4137~, 10~3739~ 12~40~ 13~4151~ 14~1223~ 16~4750~ 18~1138~ 20~4277~ 21~4012~ 22~2455~, 23~3588~ 24~1096~ 25~3595~ 29~4815~ 30~2424~.'),
  (24911, 42, 1, 7, 'And they had no child, because that Elisabeth was barren, and they both were now well stricken in years.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~2258~ 3~3756~ 4~5043~, 5~2530~ 7~1665~ 8~2258~ 9~4723~, 10~2532~ 11~846~ 12~297~ 13~2258~ [14] 16~4260~ 17~1722~ 18~2250~.'),
  (9564, 12, 2, 5, 'And the sons of the prophets that were at Jericho came to Elisha, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the LORD will take away thy master from thy head to day? And he answered, Yea, I know it; hold ye your peace.', '2~01121~ 5~05030~ [7] 9~03405~ 10~05066~ 12~0477~, 14~0559~ 17~03045~ 21~03068~ 24~03947~ 26~0113~ 29~07218~ 31~03117~? 34~0559~, 37~03045~ [38] 42~02814~.'),
  (11921, 14, 33, 4, 'Also he built altars in the house of the LORD, whereof the LORD had said, In Jerusalem shall my name be for ever.', '2~01129~ 3~04196~ 6~01004~ 9~03068~, 12~03068~ 14~0559~, 16~03389~ 19~08034~ 22~05769~.'),
  (12174, 15, 6, 14, 'And the elders of the Jews builded, and they prospered through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah the son of Iddo. And they builded, and finished it, according to the commandment of the God of Israel, and according to the commandment of Cyrus, and Darius, and Artaxerxes king of Persia.', '2~07868~ 5~03062~ 6~01124~, 9~06744~ 12~05017~ 14~02292~ 16~05029~ 18~02148~ 20~01247~ 22~05714~. 25~01124~, 27~03635~ [28] 29~04481~ 32~02941~ 35~0426~ 37~03479~, 42~02942~ 44~03567~, 46~01868~, 48~0783~ 49~04430~ 51~06540~.'),
  (4982, 5, 3, 1, 'Then we turned, and went up the way to Bashan: and Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei.', '&para; 2~06437~, 5~05927~ 7~01870~ 9~01316~: 11~05747~ 13~04428~ 15~01316~ 17~03318~ 18~07125~ 24~05971~, 26~04421~ 28~0154~.'),
  (19080, 24, 5, 13, 'And the prophets shall become wind, and the word is not in them: thus shall it be done unto them.', '2~05030~ 5~07307~, 8~01696~ [9] 17~06213~'),
  (5014, 5, 4, 4, 'But ye that did cleave unto the LORD your God are alive every one of you this day.', '4~01695~ 7~03068~ 9~0430~ [10] 11~02416~ 17~03117~.'),
  (451, 1, 18, 23, 'And Abraham drew near, and said, Wilt thou also destroy the righteous with the wicked?', '&para; 1~085~ 3~05066~, 5~0559~, 9~05595~ 11~06662~ 12~05973~ 14~07563~?'),
  (24146, 40, 27, 7, 'And they took counsel, and bought with them the potter''s field, to bury strangers in.', '0~1161~ 2~2983~ 3~4824~, 5~59~ 6~1537~ 7~846~ 9~2763~ 10~68~, 11~1519~ 12~5027~ 13~3581~ 14~5027~.'),
  (12559, 16, 10, 1, 'Now those that sealed were, Nehemiah, the Tirshatha, the son of Hachaliah, and Zidkijah,', '&para; 3~02856~ [4] 5~05166~, 7~08660~, 9~01121~ 11~02446~, 13~06667~,'),
  (17799, 23, 7, 8, 'For the head of Syria is Damascus, and the head of Damascus is Rezin; and within threescore and five years shall Ephraim be broken, that it be not a people.', '2~07218~ 4~0758~ [5] 6~01834~, 9~07218~ 11~01834~ [12] 13~07526~; 16~08346~ 18~02568~ 19~08141~ 21~0669~ 23~02865~, 29~05971~.'),
  (17039, 20, 22, 15, 'Foolishness is bound in the heart of a child; but the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.', '&para; 0~0200~ [1] 2~07194~ 5~03820~ 8~05288~; [9] 11~07626~ 13~04148~ 17~07368~'),
  (973, 1, 33, 8, 'And he said, What meanest thou by all this drove which I met? And he said, These are to find grace in the sight of my lord.', '2~0559~, [4] 9~04264~ 12~06298~? 15~0559~, [16 17] 19~04672~ 20~02580~ 23~05869~ 26~0113~.'),
  (5160, 5, 8, 17, 'And thou say in thine heart, My power and the might of mine hand hath gotten me this wealth.', '2~0559~ 5~03824~, 7~03581~ 10~06108~ [12] 13~03027~ 15~06213~ 18~02428~.'),
  (18604, 23, 46, 9, 'Remember the former things of old: for I am God, and there is none else; I am God, and there is none like me,', '0~02142~ 3~07223~ 5~05769~: [8] 9~0410~, [11 12] [15 16] 17~0430~, [19 20] 21~0657~ 22~03644~'),
  (26386, 43, 7, 43, 'So there was a division among the people because of him.', '0~3767~ 2~1096~ 4~4978~ 5~1722~ 7~3793~ 8~1223~ 10~846~.'),
  (15017, 19, 72, 8, 'He shall have dominion also from sea to sea, and from the river unto the ends of the earth.', '3~07287~ 6~03220~ 8~03220~, 12~05104~ 15~0657~ 18~0776~.'),
  (17318, 20, 31, 25, 'Strength and honour are her clothing; and she shall rejoice in time to come.', '0~05797~ 2~01926~ [3] 5~03830~; 9~07832~ 11~03117~ 13~0314~.'),
  (24525, 41, 8, 14, 'Now the disciples had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.', '0~2532~ [1 2] 4~1950~ 6~2983~ 7~740~, 8~3756~ 9~2532~* 10~2192~ 12~1722~ 14~4143~ 15~3326~ 16~1438~ 18~1508~ 19~1520~ 20~740~.'),
  (22628, 33, 3, 11, 'The heads thereof judge for reward, and the priests thereof teach for hire, and the prophets thereof divine for money: yet will they lean upon the LORD, and say, Is not the LORD among us? none evil can come upon us.', '1~07218~ 3~08199~ 5~07810~, 8~03548~ 10~03384~ 12~04242~, 15~05030~ 17~07080~ 19~03701~: 23~08172~ 26~03068~, 28~0559~, [29] 32~03068~ 33~07130~ 36~07451~ 38~0935~'),
  (21892, 27, 5, 9, 'Then was king Belshazzar greatly troubled, and his countenance was changed in him, and his lords were astonied.', '0~0116~ 2~04430~ 3~01113~ 4~07690~ 5~0927~, 8~02122~ 10~08133~ 12~05922~, 15~07261~ 17~07672~.'),
  (5959, 6, 6, 4, 'And seven priests shall bear before the ark seven trumpets of rams'' horns: and the seventh day ye shall compass the city seven times, and the priests shall blow with the trumpets.', '1~07651~ 2~03548~ 4~05375~ 5~06440~ 7~0727~ 8~07651~ 9~07782~ 12~03104~: 15~07637~ 16~03117~ 19~05437~ 21~05892~ 22~07651~ 23~06471~, 26~03548~ 28~08628~ 31~07782~.'),
  (2405, 2, 30, 18, 'Thou shalt also make a laver of brass, and his foot also of brass, to wash withal: and thou shalt put it between the tabernacle of the congregation and the altar, and thou shalt put water therein.', '3~06213~ 5~03595~ [6] 7~05178~, 10~03653~ [11 12] 13~05178~, 15~07364~ [16] 20~05414~ 24~0168~ 27~04150~ 30~04196~, 34~05414~ 35~04325~'),
  (3682, 4, 2, 19, 'And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were forty thousand and five hundred.', '2~06635~, 7~06485~ [10] 11~0705~ 12~0505~ 14~02568~ 15~03967~.'),
  (13159, 18, 12, 22, 'He discovereth deep things out of darkness, and bringeth out to light the shadow of death.', '1~01540~ 3~06013~ 6~02822~, 9~03318~ 11~0216~ 15~06757~.'),
  (24210, 40, 28, 5, 'And the angel answered and said unto the women, Fear not ye: for I know that ye seek Jesus, which was crucified.', '0~1161~ 2~32~ 3~611~ 5~2036~ 8~1135~, 9~5399~ 10~3361~ 11~5210~: 12~1063~ 14~1492~ 15~3754~ 17~2212~ 18~2424~, 19~3588~ 21~4717~.'),
  (19731, 24, 31, 31, 'Behold, the days come, saith the LORD, that I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel, and with the house of Judah:', '2~03117~ 3~0935~, 4~05002~ 6~03068~, 10~03772~ 12~02319~ 13~01285~ 16~01004~ 18~03478~, 22~01004~ 24~03063~:'),
  (2987, 3, 10, 5, 'So they went near, and carried them in their coats out of the camp; as Moses had said.', '3~07126~, 5~05375~ 9~03801~ 10~02351~ 13~04264~; 15~04872~ 17~01696~.'),
  (8493, 10, 18, 7, 'Where the people of Israel were slain before the servants of David, and there was there a great slaughter that day of twenty thousand men.', '2~05971~ 4~03478~ 6~05062~ 7~06440~ 9~05650~ 11~01732~, 17~01419~ 18~04046~ 20~03117~ 22~06242~ 23~0505~ [24]'),
  (2372, 2, 29, 31, 'And thou shalt take the ram of the consecration, and seethe his flesh in the holy place.', '3~03947~ 5~0352~ 8~04394~, 10~01310~ 12~01320~ 15~06918~ 16~04725~.'),
  (28680, 46, 12, 30, 'Have all the gifts of healing? do all speak with tongues? do all interpret?', '0~2192~ 1~3361~* 2~3956~ 4~5486~ 6~2386~? 8~3956~ 9~2980~ 10~3361~* 12~1100~? 13~3361~ 14~3956~ 15~1329~?'),
  (23108, 39, 1, 10, 'Who is there even among you that would shut the doors for nought? neither do ye kindle fire on mine altar for nought. I have no pleasure in you, saith the LORD of hosts, neither will I accept an offering at your hand.', '[1 2] 8~05462~ 10~01817~ [11 12] 16~0215~ [17] 20~04196~ 22~02600~. 26~02656~ 29~0559~ 31~03068~ 33~06635~, 37~07521~ 39~04503~ 42~03027~.'),
  (17174, 20, 26, 24, 'He that hateth dissembleth with his lips, and layeth up deceit within him;', '&para; 2~08130~ 3~05234~ 6~08193~, 9~07896~ 10~04820~ 11~07130~'),
  (26368, 43, 7, 25, 'Then said some of them of Jerusalem, Is not this he, whom they seek to kill?', '0~3767~ 1~3004~ 2~5100~ 3~1537~ 6~2415~, 7~2076~ 8~3756~ 9~3778~ 11~3739~ 13~2212~ 15~615~?'),
  (29873, 55, 3, 4, 'Traitors, heady, highminded, lovers of pleasures more than lovers of God;', '0~4273~, 1~4312~, 2~5187~, 5~5369~ 6~3123~ 7~2228~ 10~5377~;'),
  (24225, 40, 28, 20, 'Teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you: and, lo, I am with you alway, even unto the end of the world. Amen.', '0~1321~ 1~846~ 3~5083~ 5~3956~ 6~3745~ 9~1781~ 10~5213~: 11~2532~, 12~2400~, 13~1473~ 14~1510~ 15~3326~ 16~5216~ 17~2250~ 18~3956~,* [19] 20~2193~ 22~4930~ 25~165~. 26~281~.'),
  (24842, 41, 15, 5, 'But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~3765~ 3~611~ 4~3762~; 5~5620~ 7~4091~ 8~2296~.'),
  (8527, 10, 19, 8, 'Then the king arose, and sat in the gate. And they told unto all the people, saying, Behold, the king doth sit in the gate. And all the people came before the king: for Israel had fled every man to his tent.', '2~04428~ 3~06965~, 5~03427~ 8~08179~. 11~05046~ 15~05971~, 16~0559~, 19~04428~ 21~03427~ 24~08179~. 28~05971~ 29~0935~ 30~06440~ 32~04428~: 34~03478~ 36~05127~ 38~0376~ 41~0168~.'),
  (20609, 26, 7, 23, 'Make a chain: for the land is full of bloody crimes, and the city is full of violence.', '&para; 0~06213~ 2~07569~: 5~0776~ 7~04390~ 9~01818~ 10~04941~, 13~05892~ 15~04390~ 17~02555~.'),
  (11456, 14, 12, 10, 'Instead of which king Rehoboam made shields of brass, and committed them to the hands of the chief of the guard, that kept the entrance of the king''s house.', '3~04428~ 4~07346~ 5~06213~ 6~04043~ 8~05178~, 10~06485~ [11] 14~03027~ 17~08269~ 20~07323~, 22~08104~ 24~06607~ 27~04428~ 28~01004~.'),
  (24982, 42, 1, 77, 'To give knowledge of salvation unto his people by the remission of their sins,', '1~1325~ 2~1108~ 4~4991~ 6~846~ 7~2992~ 8~1722~ 10~859~ 12~846~ 13~266~,'),
  (12696, 16, 13, 16, 'There dwelt men of Tyre also therein, which brought fish, and all manner of ware, and sold on the sabbath unto the children of Judah, and in Jerusalem.', '1~03427~ 4~06876~ 8~0935~ 9~01709~ 10~01709~,* 15~04377~, 17~04376~ 20~07676~ 23~01121~ 25~03063~, 28~03389~.'),
  (11100, 13, 26, 15, 'To Obededom southward; and to his sons the house of Asuppim.', '1~05654~ 2~05045~; 6~01121~ 8~01004~ 10~0624~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15704, 19, 106, 44, 'Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:', '2~07200~ 4~06862~, 7~08085~ 9~07440~:'),
  (17755, 23, 5, 7, 'For the vineyard of the LORD of hosts is the house of Israel, and the men of Judah his pleasant plant: and he looked for judgment, but behold oppression; for righteousness, but behold a cry.', '2~03754~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~ [8] 10~01004~ 12~03478~, 15~0376~ 17~03063~ 19~08191~ 20~05194~: 23~06960~ 25~04941~, 28~04939~; 30~06666~, 34~06818~.'),
  (3350, 3, 20, 27, 'A man also or woman that hath a familiar spirit, or that is a wizard, shall surely be put to death: they shall stone them with stones: their blood shall be upon them.', '1~0376~ 4~0802~ 6~03588~ 9~0178~, 14~03049~, 16~04191~ 20~04191~: 23~07275~ 26~068~: 28~01818~ [29 30]'),
  (21090, 26, 24, 25, 'Also, thou son of man, shall it not be in the day when I take from them their strength, the joy of their glory, the desire of their eyes, and that whereupon they set their minds, their sons and their daughters,', '2~01121~ 4~0120~, [5 6] [8] 11~03117~ 14~03947~ 18~04581~, 20~04885~ 23~08597~, 25~04261~ 28~05869~, 33~04853~ 35~05315~, 37~01121~ 40~01323~,'),
  (9557, 12, 1, 16, 'And he said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Forasmuch as thou hast sent messengers to inquire of Baalzebub the god of Ekron, is it not because there is no God in Israel to inquire of his word? therefore thou shalt not come down off that bed on which thou art gone up, but shalt surely die.', '2~01696~ 6~0559~ 8~03068~, 13~07971~ 14~04397~ 16~01875~ 18~01176~ 20~0430~ 22~06138~, [23 24] [27 28] 30~0430~ 32~03478~ 34~01875~ 37~01697~? 43~03381~ 46~04296~ 52~05927~, 55~04191~ 56~04191~.'),
  (23365, 40, 8, 10, 'When Jesus heard it, he marvelled, and said to them that followed, Verily I say unto you, I have not found so great faith, no, not in Israel.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~191~ [3] 5~2296~, 6~2532~ 7~2036~ 11~190~, 12~281~ 14~3004~ 16~5213~, 18~2147~ 19~3761~ 20~2147~ 22~5118~ 23~4102~, 25~3761~ 26~1722~ 27~2474~.'),
  (17938, 23, 14, 1, 'For the LORD will have mercy on Jacob, and will yet choose Israel, and set them in their own land: and the strangers shall be joined with them, and they shall cleave to the house of Jacob.', '&para; 2~03068~ 5~07355~ 7~03290~, 11~0977~ 12~03478~, 14~03240~ 19~0127~: 22~01616~ 25~03867~ 31~05596~ 34~01004~ 36~03290~.'),
  (21476, 26, 39, 19, 'And ye shall eat fat till ye be full, and drink blood till ye be drunken, of my sacrifice which I have sacrificed for you.', '3~0398~ 4~02459~ 8~07654~, 10~08354~ 11~01818~ 15~07943~, 18~02077~ 22~02076~'),
  (11408, 14, 10, 4, 'Thy father made our yoke grievous: now therefore ease thou somewhat the grievous servitude of thy father, and his heavy yoke that he put upon us, and we will serve thee.', '1~01~ 4~05923~ 5~07185~: 8~07043~ 12~07186~ 13~05656~ 16~01~, 19~03515~ 20~05923~ 23~05414~ 29~05647~'),
  (29596, 52, 2, 10, 'Ye are witnesses, and God also, how holily and justly and unblameably we behaved ourselves among you that believe:', '0~5210~ [1] 2~3144~, 3~2532~ 4~2316~ [5] 6~5613~ 7~3743~ 8~2532~ 9~1346~ 10~2532~ 11~274~ 14~1096~ 16~5213~ 18~4100~:'),
  (9561, 12, 2, 2, 'And Elijah said unto Elisha, Tarry here, I pray thee; for the LORD hath sent me to Bethel. And Elisha said unto him, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. So they went down to Bethel.', '1~0452~ 2~0559~ 4~0477~, 5~03427~ 12~03068~ 14~07971~ 17~01008~. 19~0477~ 20~0559~ [21 23] 25~03068~ 26~02416~, [28] 30~05315~ 31~02416~, 35~05800~ 40~03381~ 42~01008~.'),
  (24347, 41, 4, 14, 'The sower soweth the word.', '1~4687~ 2~4687~ 4~3056~.'),
  (21125, 26, 26, 16, 'Then all the princes of the sea shall come down from their thrones, and lay away their robes, and put off their broidered garments: they shall clothe themselves with trembling; they shall sit upon the ground, and shall tremble at every moment, and be astonished at thee.', '3~05387~ 6~03220~ 9~03381~ 12~03678~, 15~05493~ 17~04598~, 20~06584~ 22~07553~ 23~0899~: 26~03847~ 29~02731~; 32~03427~ 35~0776~, 38~02729~ [40] 41~07281~, 44~08074~'),
  (23063, 38, 12, 9, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that I will seek to destroy all the nations that come against Jerusalem.', '&para; 8~03117~, [9] 12~01245~ 14~08045~ 17~01471~ 19~0935~ 21~03389~.'),
  (3734, 4, 3, 37, 'And the pillars of the court round about, and their sockets, and their pins, and their cords.', '2~05982~ 5~02691~ 7~05439~, 10~0134~, 13~03489~, 16~04340~.'),
  (8419, 10, 15, 23, 'And all the country wept with a loud voice, and all the people passed over: the king also himself passed over the brook Kidron, and all the people passed over, toward the way of the wilderness.', '3~0776~ 4~01058~ 7~01419~ 8~06963~, 12~05971~ 14~05674~: 16~04428~ 20~05674~ 22~05158~ 23~06939~, 27~05971~ 29~05674~, 30~06440~ 32~01870~ 35~04057~.'),
  (28181, 45, 9, 10, 'And not only this; but when Rebecca also had conceived by one, even by our father Isaac;', '0~1161~ 1~3756~ 2~3440~ [3] 4~235~ 6~4479~ 7~2532~ 9~2845~ 10~1537~ 11~2192~ 12~1520~,* [13] 15~2257~ 16~3962~ 17~2464~;'),
  (2838, 3, 5, 3, 'Or if he touch the uncleanness of man, whatsoever uncleanness it be that a man shall be defiled withal, and it be hid from him; when he knoweth of it, then he shall be guilty.', '3~05060~ 5~02932~ 7~0120~, 9~02932~ [10 11] 17~02930~ 22~05956~ 27~03045~ [28 29] 34~0816~.'),
  (29192, 48, 5, 14, 'For all the law is fulfilled in one word, even in this; Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.', '0~1063~ 1~3956~ 3~3551~ 5~4137~ 6~1722~ 7~1520~ 8~3056~, [9] 10~1722~ 14~25~ 15~4675~ 16~4139~ 17~5613~ 18~1438~.'),
  (3774, 4, 4, 26, 'And the hangings of the court, and the hanging for the door of the gate of the court, which is by the tabernacle and by the altar round about, and their cords, and all the instruments of their service, and all that is made for them: so shall they serve.', '2~07050~ 5~02691~, 8~04539~ 11~06607~ 14~08179~ 17~02691~, [19] 22~04908~ 26~04196~ 28~05439~, 31~04340~, 35~03627~ 38~05656~, 43~06213~ 49~05647~.'),
  (3917, 4, 7, 62, 'One golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense:', '0~0259~ 1~02091~ 2~03709~ 4~06235~ [5] 6~04392~ 8~07004~:'),
  (5332, 5, 15, 7, 'If there be among you a poor man of one of thy brethren within any of thy gates in thy land which the LORD thy God giveth thee, thou shalt not harden thine heart, nor shut thine hand from thy poor brother:', '7~034~ 9~0259~ 12~0251~ 14~0259~ 17~08179~ 20~0776~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~ 26~05414~ 31~0553~ 33~03824~, 35~07092~ 37~03027~ 40~034~ 41~0251~:'),
  (26383, 43, 7, 40, 'Many of the people therefore, when they heard this saying, said, Of a truth this is the Prophet.', '0~4183~ 1~1537~ 3~3793~ 4~3767~, 7~191~ 9~3056~, 10~3004~, 13~230~ 14~3778~ 15~2076~ 17~4396~.'),
  (14729, 19, 53, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Mahalath, Maschil, A Psalm of David. The fool hath said in his heart, There is no God. Corrupt are they, and have done abominable iniquity: there is none that doeth good.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~04257~, 6~04905~, [7 8] 10] 10~01732~ 12~05036~ 14~0559~ 17~03820~, [18 19] 21~0430~. 22~07843~ 28~08581~ 29~05766~: [30 31] 34~06213~ 35~02896~.'),
  (20835, 26, 17, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (304, 1, 12, 3, 'And I will bless them that bless thee, and curse him that curseth thee: and in thee shall all families of the earth be blessed.', '3~01288~ 6~01288~ 9~0779~ 12~07043~ 19~04940~ 22~0127~ 24~01288~.'),
  (9514, 11, 22, 26, 'And the king of Israel said, Take Micaiah, and carry him back unto Amon the governor of the city, and to Joash the king''s son;', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~, 6~03947~ 7~04321~, 11~07725~ 13~0526~ 15~08269~ 18~05892~, 21~03101~ 23~04428~ 24~01121~;'),
  (27854, 44, 26, 15, 'And I said, Who art thou, Lord? And he said, I am Jesus whom thou persecutest.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~2036~, 3~5101~ 5~1488~, 6~2962~? 7~1161~ 9~2036~, 10~1473~ 11~1510~ 12~2424~ 13~3739~ 14~4771~ 15~1377~.'),
  (498, 1, 19, 37, 'And the firstborn bare a son, and called his name Moab: the same is the father of the Moabites unto this day.', '2~01067~ 3~03205~ 5~01121~, 7~07121~ 9~08034~ 10~04124~: 12~01931~ [13] 15~01~ 18~04124~ 21~03117~.'),
  (2884, 3, 6, 30, 'And no sin offering, whereof any of the blood is brought into the tabernacle of the congregation to reconcile withal in the holy place, shall be eaten: it shall be burnt in the fire.', '3~02403~, [5] 8~01818~ 10~0935~ 13~0168~ 16~04150~ 18~03722~ [19] 22~06944~ [23] 26~0398~: 30~08313~ 33~0784~.'),
  (7321, 9, 4, 17, 'And the messenger answered and said, Israel is fled before the Philistines, and there hath been also a great slaughter among the people, and thy two sons also, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead, and the ark of God is taken.', '2~01319~ 3~06030~ 5~0559~, 6~03478~ 8~05127~ 9~06440~ 11~06430~, 18~01419~ 19~04046~ 22~05971~, 25~08147~ 26~01121~ 28~02652~ 30~06372~, 32~04191~, 35~0727~ 37~0430~ 39~03947~.'),
  (4372, 4, 21, 27, 'Wherefore they that speak in proverbs say, Come into Heshbon, let the city of Sihon be built and prepared:', '5~04911~ 6~0559~, 7~0935~ 9~02809~, 12~05892~ 14~05511~ 16~01129~ 18~03559~:'),
  (18789, 23, 57, 15, 'For thus saith the high and lofty One that inhabiteth eternity, whose name is Holy; I dwell in the high and holy place, with him also that is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite ones.', '2~0559~ 4~07311~ 7~05375~ 9~07931~ 10~05703~, 12~08034~ [13] 14~06918~; 16~07931~ 19~04791~ 21~06918~ [22] [26 27] 30~01793~ 32~08217~ 33~07307~, 35~02421~ 37~07307~ 40~08217~, 43~02421~ 45~03820~ 49~01792~.'),
  (16289, 19, 141, 4, 'Incline not my heart to any evil thing, to practice wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.', '0~05186~ 3~03820~ [5] 6~07451~ 7~01697~, 9~05953~ 10~07562~ 11~05949~ 13~0376~ 15~06466~ 16~0205~: 21~03898~ 24~04516~.'),
  (17773, 23, 5, 25, 'Therefore is the anger of the LORD kindled against his people, and he hath stretched forth his hand against them, and hath smitten them: and the hills did tremble, and their carcases were torn in the midst of the streets. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.', '3~0639~ 6~03068~ 7~02734~ 10~05971~, 15~05186~ 17~03027~ 22~05221~ 26~02022~ 28~07264~, 31~05038~ [32] 33~05478~ 36~07130~ 39~02351~. 44~0639~ 48~07725~, 51~03027~ [52] 54~05186~'),
  (27386, 44, 13, 8, 'But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith.', '0~1161~ 1~1681~ 3~3097~ 4~1063~* 6~3779~ 8~846~ 9~3686~ 11~3177~) 12~436~ 13~846~, 14~2212~ 17~1294~ 19~446~ 20~575~ 22~4102~.'),
  (5392, 5, 18, 2, 'Therefore shall they have no inheritance among their brethren: the LORD is their inheritance, as he hath said unto them.', '5~05159~ 6~07130~ 8~0251~: 10~03068~ [11] 13~05159~, 17~01696~'),
  (3857, 4, 7, 2, 'That the princes of Israel, heads of the house of their fathers, who were the princes of the tribes, and were over them that were numbered, offered:', '2~05387~ 4~03478~, 5~07218~ 8~01004~ 11~01~, [13] 15~05387~ 18~04294~, 21~05975~ 25~06485~, 26~07126~:'),
  (21171, 26, 28, 5, 'By thy great wisdom and by thy traffic hast thou increased thy riches, and thine heart is lifted up because of thy riches:', '2~07230~ 3~02451~ [4] 7~07404~ 10~07235~ 12~02428~, 15~03824~ 18~01361~ 22~02428~:'),
  (14544, 19, 40, 10, 'I have not hid thy righteousness within my heart; I have declared thy faithfulness and thy salvation: I have not concealed thy lovingkindness and thy truth from the great congregation.', '3~03680~ 5~06666~ 6~08432~ 8~03820~; 11~0559~ 13~0530~ 16~08668~: 20~03582~ 22~02617~ 25~0571~ 28~07227~ 29~06951~.'),
  (5168, 5, 9, 5, 'Not for thy righteousness, or for the uprightness of thine heart, dost thou go to possess their land: but for the wickedness of these nations the LORD thy God doth drive them out from before thee, and that he may perform the word which the LORD sware unto thy fathers, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.', '3~06666~, 7~03476~ 10~03824~, 13~0935~ 15~03423~ 17~0776~: 21~07564~ 24~01471~ 26~03068~ 28~0430~ 32~03423~ 34~06440~ 40~06965~ 42~01697~ 45~03068~ 46~07650~ 49~01~, 50~085~, 51~03327~, 53~03290~.'),
  (30425, 60, 2, 10, 'Which in time past were not a people, but are now the people of God: which had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.', '0~3588~ 3~4218~ [4] 5~3756~ 7~2992~, 8~1161~ [9] 10~3568~ 12~2992~ 14~2316~: 15~3588~ 16~1653~ 17~3756~ 19~1653~, 20~1161~ 21~3568~ 24~1653~.'),
  (9024, 11, 8, 31, 'If any man trespass against his neighbour, and an oath be laid upon him to cause him to swear, and the oath come before thine altar in this house:', '2~0376~ 3~02398~ 6~07453~, 9~0423~ 11~05375~ 18~0422~, 21~0423~ 22~0935~ 23~06440~ 25~04196~ 28~01004~:'),
  (12753, 17, 2, 20, 'Esther had not yet shewed her kindred nor her people; as Mordecai had charged her: for Esther did the commandment of Mordecai, like as when she was brought up with him.', '0~0635~ [3] 4~05046~ 6~04138~ 9~05971~; 11~04782~ 13~06680~ 16~0635~ 17~06213~ 19~03982~ 21~04782~, 28~0545~'),
  (7355, 9, 6, 17, 'And these are the golden emerods which the Philistines returned for a trespass offering unto the LORD; for Ashdod one, for Gaza one, for Askelon one, for Gath one, for Ekron one;', '[2] 4~02091~ 5~02914~ 8~06430~ 9~07725~ [10] 13~0817~ 16~03068~; 18~0795~ 19~0259~, 21~05804~ 22~0259~, 24~0831~ 25~0259~, 27~01661~ 28~0259~, 30~06138~ 31~0259~;'),
  (7109, 7, 20, 48, 'And the men of Israel turned again upon the children of Benjamin, and smote them with the edge of the sword, as well the men of every city, as the beast, and all that came to hand: also they set on fire all the cities that they came to.', '2~0376~ 4~03478~ 6~07725~ 9~01121~ 11~01144~, 13~05221~ 17~06310~ 20~02719~, 24~04974~ [26] 27~05892~, 28~05704~ 30~0929~, 36~04672~: 39~07971~ 41~0784~ 44~05892~ 48~04672~.'),
  (20726, 26, 13, 9, 'And mine hand shall be upon the prophets that see vanity, and that divine lies: they shall not be in the assembly of my people, neither shall they be written in the writing of the house of Israel, neither shall they enter into the land of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the Lord GOD.', '2~03027~ 7~05030~ 9~02374~ 10~07723~, 13~07080~ 14~03577~: 21~05475~ 24~05971~, 29~03789~ 32~03791~ 35~01004~ 37~03478~, 41~0935~ 44~0127~ 46~03478~; 50~03045~ [53] 55~0136~ 56~03069~.'),
  (16270, 19, 139, 22, 'I hate them with perfect hatred: I count them mine enemies.', '1~08130~ 4~08503~ 5~08135~: 10~0341~.'),
  (2060, 2, 20, 4, 'Thou shalt not make unto thee any graven image, or any likeness of any thing that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth:', '3~06213~ 8~06459~, 11~08544~ [12 14] 15~0834~ [16] 18~08064~ 19~04605~, [22] 25~0776~ [29] 32~04325~ 35~0776~:'),
  (24815, 41, 14, 50, 'And they all forsook him, and fled.', '0~2532~ 2~3956~ 3~863~ 4~846~, 6~5343~.'),
  (7245, 9, 1, 26, 'And she said, Oh my lord, as thy soul liveth, my lord, I am the woman that stood by thee here, praying unto the LORD.', '2~0559~, 3~0994~ 5~0113~, [6] 8~05315~ 9~02416~, 11~0113~, [13] 15~0802~ 17~05324~ 21~06419~ 24~03068~.'),
  (25174, 42, 6, 16, 'And Judas the brother of James, and Judas Iscariot, which also was the traitor.', '1~2455~ [2 3] 5~2385~, 6~2532~ 7~2455~ 8~2469~, 9~3739~ 10~2532~ 11~1096~ 13~4273~.'),
  (29297, 49, 4, 9, '(Now that he ascended, what is it but that he also descended first into the lower parts of the earth?', '0~1161~* 4~305~, 5~5101~ 7~2076~ 8~1508~ 9~3754~ 10~2597~ 11~2532~ 12~2597~ 13~4412~ 14~1519~ 16~2737~ 17~3313~ 20~1093~?'),
  (25236, 42, 7, 29, 'And all the people that heard him, and the publicans, justified God, being baptized with the baptism of John.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 3~2992~ 5~191~ [6] 7~2532~ 9~5057~, 10~1344~ 11~2316~, 13~907~ 16~908~ 18~2491~.'),
  (30067, 58, 6, 7, 'For the earth which drinketh in the rain that cometh oft upon it, and bringeth forth herbs meet for them by whom it is dressed, receiveth blessing from God:', '0~1063~ 2~1093~ 3~3588~ 5~4095~ 7~5205~ 9~2064~ 10~4178~ 11~1909~ 12~846~, 13~2532~ 15~5088~ 16~1008~ 17~2111~ 19~2532~ 20~1565~* 21~1223~ 22~3739~ 25~1090~, 26~3335~ 27~2129~ 28~575~ 29~2316~:'),
  (14921, 19, 68, 12, 'Kings of armies did flee apace: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.', '0~04428~ 2~06635~ 4~05074~ 5~05074~: 9~05116~ 11~01004~ 12~02505~ 14~07998~.'),
  (3137, 3, 14, 21, 'And if he be poor, and cannot get so much; then he shall take one lamb for a trespass offering to be waved, to make an atonement for him, and one tenth deal of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering, and a log of oil;', '&para; [3] 4~01800~, 7~05381~ 8~03027~* 14~03947~ 15~0259~ 16~03532~ [17] 20~0817~ 23~08573~, 27~03722~ 31~0259~ 33~06241~ 36~05560~ 37~01101~ 39~08081~ 43~04503~, 46~03849~ 48~08081~;'),
  (22220, 28, 9, 3, 'They shall not dwell in the LORD''S land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things in Assyria.', '3~03427~ 6~03068~ 7~0776~; 9~0669~ 11~07725~ 13~04714~, 17~0398~ 18~02931~ [19] 21~0804~.'),
  (28610, 46, 10, 27, 'If any of them that believe not bid you to a feast, and ye be disposed to go; whatsoever is set before you, eat, asking no question for conscience sake.', '0~1161~ 1~1536~ 6~571~ 7~2564~ 8~5209~ [9 11] 12~2532~ 15~2309~ 17~4198~; 18~3956~ 21~3908~ 22~5213~, 23~2068~, 24~350~ 25~3367~ 26~350~ 27~1223~ 28~4893~ 29~1223~.'),
  (8533, 10, 19, 14, 'And he bowed the heart of all the men of Judah, even as the heart of one man; so that they sent this word unto the king, Return thou, and all thy servants.', '2~05186~ 4~03824~ 8~0376~ 10~03063~, [13 15] 16~0259~ 17~0376~; 21~07971~ [22 23] 26~04428~, 27~07725~ 32~05650~.'),
  (20913, 26, 20, 9, 'But I wrought for my name''s sake, that it should not be polluted before the heathen, among whom they were, in whose sight I made myself known unto them, in bringing them forth out of the land of Egypt.', '2~06213~ 5~08034~ 12~02490~ 13~05869~ 15~01471~, 16~08432~ [19] 22~05869~ 26~03045~ 32~03318~ 36~0776~ 38~04714~.'),
  (3561, 3, 26, 32, 'And I will bring the land into desolation: and your enemies which dwell therein shall be astonished at it.', '3~08074~ 5~0776~ 7~08074~: 10~0341~ 12~03427~ 16~08074~'),
  (22138, 28, 3, 1, 'Then said the LORD unto me, Go yet, love a woman beloved of her friend, yet an adulteress, according to the love of the LORD toward the children of Israel, who look to other gods, and love flagons of wine.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~ 6~03212~ 8~0157~ 10~0802~ 11~0157~ [13] 14~07453~, 17~05003~, 21~0160~ 24~03068~ 27~01121~ 29~03478~, 31~06437~ 33~0312~ 34~0430~, 36~0157~ 37~0809~ 39~06025~.'),
  (24085, 40, 26, 21, 'And as they did eat, he said, Verily I say unto you, that one of you shall betray me.', '0~2532~ 2~846~ 4~2068~, 6~2036~, 7~281~ 9~3004~ 11~5213~, 12~3754~ 13~1520~ 14~1537~ 15~5216~ 17~3860~ 18~3165~.'),
  (12942, 18, 4, 3, 'Behold, thou hast instructed many, and thou hast strengthened the weak hands.', '3~03256~ 4~07227~, 8~02388~ 10~07504~ 11~03027~.'),
  (22673, 33, 6, 16, 'For the statutes of Omri are kept, and all the works of the house of Ahab, and ye walk in their counsels; that I should make thee a desolation, and the inhabitants thereof an hissing: therefore ye shall bear the reproach of my people.', '2~02708~ 4~06018~ 6~08104~, 10~04639~ 13~01004~ 15~0256~, 18~03212~ 21~04156~; 25~05414~ 28~08047~, 31~03427~ 34~08322~: 38~05375~ 40~02781~ 43~05971~.'),
  (3177, 3, 15, 4, 'Every bed, whereon he lieth that hath the issue, is unclean: and every thing, whereon he sitteth, shall be unclean.', '1~04904~, 4~07901~ 8~02100~, 10~02930~: 13~03627~, 16~03427~, 19~02930~.'),
  (6485, 6, 24, 2, 'And Joshua said unto all the people, Thus saith the LORD God of Israel, Your fathers dwelt on the other side of the flood in old time, even Terah, the father of Abraham, and the father of Nachor: and they served other gods.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ 6~05971~, 8~0559~ 10~03068~ 11~0430~ 13~03478~, 15~01~ 16~03427~ 20~05676~ 23~05104~ 26~05769~, [27] 28~08646~, 30~01~ 32~085~, 35~01~ 37~05152~: 40~05647~ 41~0312~ 42~0430~.'),
  (22814, 36, 1, 18, 'Neither their silver nor their gold shall be able to deliver them in the day of the LORD''S wrath; but the whole land shall be devoured by the fire of his jealousy: for he shall make even a speedy riddance of all them that dwell in the land.', '2~03701~ 5~02091~ 8~03201~ 10~05337~ 14~03117~ 17~03068~ 18~05678~; 22~0776~ 25~0398~ 28~0784~ 31~07068~: 35~06213~ 38~0926~ 39~03617~ 44~03427~ 47~0776~.'),
  (19238, 24, 11, 3, 'And say thou unto them, Thus saith the LORD God of Israel; Cursed be the man that obeyeth not the words of this covenant,', '1~0559~ 6~0559~ 8~03068~ 9~0430~ 11~03478~; 12~0779~ [13] 15~0376~ 17~08085~ 20~01697~ 23~01285~,'),
  (22476, 30, 7, 3, 'The LORD repented for this: It shall not be, saith the LORD.', '1~03068~ 2~05162~ 9~0559~ 11~03068~.'),
  (13352, 18, 20, 17, 'He shall not see the rivers, the floods, the brooks of honey and butter.', '3~07200~ 5~06390~, 7~05104~, 9~05158~ 11~01706~ 13~02529~.'),
  (17794, 23, 7, 3, 'Then said the LORD unto Isaiah, Go forth now to meet Ahaz, thou, and Shearjashub thy son, at the end of the conduit of the upper pool in the highway of the fuller''s field;', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~03470~, 7~03318~ 10~07125~ 11~0271~, 14~07610~ 16~01121~, 19~07097~ 22~08585~ 25~05945~ 26~01295~ 29~04546~ 32~03526~ 33~07704~;'),
  (30903, 66, 11, 15, 'And the seventh angel sounded; and there were great voices in heaven, saying, The kingdoms of this world are become the kingdoms of our Lord, and of his Christ; and he shall reign for ever and ever.', '0~2532~ 2~1442~ 3~32~ 4~4537~; 5~2532~ 7~1096~ 8~3173~ 9~5456~ 10~1722~ 11~3772~, 12~3004~, 14~932~ 17~2889~ 19~1096~ [20 21] 23~2257~ 24~2962~, 25~2532~ 27~846~ 28~5547~; 29~2532~ 32~936~ 33~1519~ 34~165~ 36~165~.'),
  (17424, 21, 5, 18, 'Behold that which I have seen: it is good and comely for one to eat and to drink, and to enjoy the good of all his labour that he taketh under the sun all the days of his life, which God giveth him: for it is his portion.', '&para; [1] 5~07200~: [6 7] 8~02896~ 10~03303~ [11 12] 14~0398~ 17~08354~, 20~07200~ 22~02896~ 26~05999~ 29~05998~ 32~08121~ 33~04557~ 35~03117~ 38~02416~, 40~0430~ 41~05414~ [45] 47~02506~.'),
  (491, 1, 19, 30, 'And Lot went up out of Zoar, and dwelt in the mountain, and his two daughters with him; for he feared to dwell in Zoar: and he dwelt in a cave, he and his two daughters.', '&para; 1~03876~ 3~05927~ 6~06820~, 8~03427~ 11~02022~, 14~08147~ 15~01323~ 20~03372~ 22~03427~ 24~06820~: 27~03427~ 30~04631~, 34~08147~ 35~01323~.'),
  (19081, 24, 5, 14, 'Wherefore thus saith the LORD God of hosts, Because ye speak this word, behold, I will make my words in thy mouth fire, and this people wood, and it shall devour them.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~06635~, 10~01696~ 12~01697~, 16~05414~ 18~01697~ 21~06310~ 22~0784~, 25~05971~ 26~06086~, 30~0398~'),
  (14168, 19, 18, 41, 'They cried, but there was none to save them: even unto the LORD, but he answered them not.', '1~07768~, [3 4] 7~03467~ [8 9] 12~03068~, 15~06030~'),
  (29166, 48, 4, 19, 'My little children, of whom I travail in birth again until Christ be formed in you,', '&para; 0~3450~ 2~5040~, 4~3739~ 8~5605~ 9~3825~ 10~3757~ 11~891~* 12~5547~ 14~3445~ 15~1722~ 16~5213~,'),
  (5189, 5, 9, 26, 'I prayed therefore unto the LORD, and said, O Lord GOD, destroy not thy people and thine inheritance, which thou hast redeemed through thy greatness, which thou hast brought forth out of Egypt with a mighty hand.', '1~06419~ 5~03068~, 7~0559~, 9~0136~ 10~03069~, 11~07843~ 14~05971~ 17~05159~, 21~06299~ 24~01433~, 29~03318~ 32~04714~ 35~02389~ 36~03027~.'),
  (14675, 19, 49, 18, 'Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and men will praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself.', '3~02416~ 5~01288~ 7~05315~: [9] 11~03034~ 16~03190~'),
  (23072, 38, 13, 4, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the prophets shall be ashamed every one of his vision, when he hath prophesied; neither shall they wear a rough garment to deceive:', '8~03117~, [9] 11~05030~ 14~0954~ 16~0376~ 19~02384~, 23~05012~; 27~03847~ 29~08181~ 30~0155~ 32~03584~:'),
  (14798, 19, 58, 10, 'The righteous shall rejoice when he seeth the vengeance: he shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked.', '1~06662~ 3~08055~ 6~02372~ 8~05359~: 11~07364~ 13~06471~ 16~01818~ 19~07563~.'),
  (15828, 19, 113, 6, 'Who humbleth himself to behold the things that are in heaven, and in the earth!', '1~08213~ [2] 4~07200~ [5 8] 10~08064~, 14~0776~!'),
  (19057, 24, 4, 21, 'How long shall I see the standard, and hear the sound of the trumpet?', '4~07200~ 6~05251~, [7] 8~08085~ 10~06963~ 13~07782~?'),
  (3241, 3, 17, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (28994, 47, 10, 7, 'Do ye look on things after the outward appearance? If any man trust to himself that he is Christ''s, let him of himself think this again, that, as he is Christ''s, even so are we Christ''s.', '&para; 3~991~ 5~2596~ 8~4383~? 11~1536~ 12~3982~ 14~1438~ 17~1511~ 18~5547~, 20~3049~ 21~575~ 22~1438~ 23~3049~ 24~5124~ 25~3825~, 26~3754~, 27~2531~ 28~846~ [29] 30~5547~, 31~2532~ 32~3779~ [33] 34~2249~ 35~5547~.'),
  (1725, 2, 8, 10, 'And he said, To morrow. And he said, Be it according to thy word: that thou mayest know that there is none like unto the LORD our God.', '2~0559~, 4~04279~. 7~0559~, [8 9] 13~01697~: 17~03045~ [19 20] 25~03068~ 27~0430~.'),
  (19585, 24, 26, 4, 'And thou shalt say unto them, Thus saith the LORD; If ye will not hearken to me, to walk in my law, which I have set before you,', '3~0559~ 7~0559~ 9~03068~; 14~08085~ 18~03212~ 21~08451~, 25~05414~ 26~06440~'),
  (24389, 41, 5, 15, 'And they come to Jesus, and see him that was possessed with the devil, and had the legion, sitting, and clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~4314~ 4~2424~, 5~2532~ 6~2334~ 13~1139~, 15~2192~ 17~3003~, 18~2521~, 19~2532~ 20~2439~, 21~2532~ 25~4993~: 26~2532~ 29~5399~.'),
  (5051, 5, 4, 41, 'Then Moses severed three cities on this side Jordan toward the sun rising;', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~0914~ 3~07969~ 4~05892~ 7~05676~ 8~03383~ 11~04217~ 12~08121~;*'),
  (28514, 46, 7, 11, 'But and if she depart, let her remain unmarried, or be reconciled to her husband: and let not the husband put away his wife.', '0~1161~ 1~2532~ 2~1437~ 4~5563~, 7~3306~ 8~22~, 9~2228~ 11~2644~ [13] 14~435~: 15~2532~ 16~863~ 17~3361~ 19~435~ 21~863~ [22] 23~1135~.'),
  (24502, 41, 7, 28, 'And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children''s crumbs.', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 3~2532~ 4~3004~ 6~846~, 7~3483~, 8~2962~: 9~1063~ 10~2532~ 11~2952~ 12~5270~ 14~5132~ 15~2068~ 16~575~ 18~3813~ 19~5589~.'),
  (17466, 21, 7, 28, 'Which yet my soul seeketh, but I find not: one man among a thousand have I found; but a woman among all those have I not found.', '3~05315~ 4~01245~, 7~04672~ 9~0259~ 10~0120~ 13~0505~ 16~04672~; 19~0802~ 26~04672~.'),
  (21023, 26, 23, 7, 'Thus she committed her whoredoms with them, with all them that were the chosen men of Assyria, and with all on whom she doted: with all their idols she defiled herself.', '2~05414~ 4~08457~ [10 11] 13~04005~ 14~01121~ 16~0804~, 23~05689~: 27~01544~ 29~02930~'),
  (21326, 26, 34, 4, 'The diseased have ye not strengthened, neither have ye healed that which was sick, neither have ye bound up that which was broken, neither have ye brought again that which was driven away, neither have ye sought that which was lost; but with force and with cruelty have ye ruled them.', '1~02470~ 5~02388~, 9~07495~ 13~02470~, 18~02280~ [19 21] 22~07665~, 27~07725~ 32~05080~, 36~01245~ 40~06~; 43~02394~ 46~06531~ 49~07287~'),
  (19894, 24, 37, 11, 'And it came to pass, that when the army of the Chaldeans was broken up from Jerusalem for fear of Pharaoh''s army,', '&para; 8~02428~ 11~03778~ 14~05927~ 16~03389~ 18~06440~ 20~06547~ 21~02428~,'),
  (3249, 3, 17, 9, 'And bringeth it not unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, to offer it unto the LORD; even that man shall be cut off from among his people.', '1~0935~ 6~06607~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~, 14~06213~ 18~03068~; 21~0376~ 25~03772~ 29~05971~.'),
  (28973, 47, 9, 1, 'For as touching the ministering to the saints, it is superfluous for me to write to you:', '&para; 0~1063~ 1~3303~ 2~4012~ 4~1248~ 5~1519~ 7~40~, 9~2076~ 10~4053~ 12~3427~ 14~1125~ 16~5213~:'),
  (15591, 19, 104, 11, 'They give drink to every beast of the field: the wild asses quench their thirst.', '2~08248~ 5~02416~ 8~07704~: 11~06501~ 12~07665~ 14~06772~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (6647, 7, 5, 17, 'Gilead abode beyond Jordan: and why did Dan remain in ships? Asher continued on the sea shore, and abode in his breaches.', '0~01568~ 1~07931~ 2~05676~ 3~03383~: 7~01835~ 8~01481~ 10~0591~? 11~0836~ 12~03427~ 15~03220~ 16~02348~, 18~07931~ 21~04664~.'),
  (19229, 24, 10, 19, 'Woe is me for my hurt! my wound is grievous: but I said, Truly this is a grief, and I must bear it.', '0~0188~ 5~07667~! 7~04347~ 9~02470~: 12~0559~, 13~0389~ [15] 17~02483~, 21~05375~'),
  (23937, 40, 23, 9, 'And call no man your father upon the earth: for one is your Father, which is in heaven.', '0~2532~ 1~2564~ 2~3361~ [3] 4~5216~ 5~3962~ 6~1909~ 8~1093~: 9~1063~ 10~1520~ 11~2076~ 12~5216~ 13~3962~, 14~3588~ 16~1722~ 17~3772~.'),
  (10864, 13, 16, 36, 'Blessed be the LORD God of Israel for ever and ever. And all the people said, Amen, and praised the LORD.', '0~01288~ [1] 3~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~03478~ 8~05769~ 10~05769~. 14~05971~ 15~0559~, 16~0543~, 18~01984~ 20~03068~.'),
  (28463, 46, 4, 14, 'I write not these things to shame you, but as my beloved sons I warn you.', '&para; 1~1125~ 2~3756~ 4~5023~ 6~1788~ 7~5209~, 8~235~ 9~5613~ 10~3450~ 11~27~ 12~5043~ 14~3560~ [15]'),
  (16775, 20, 13, 19, 'The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul: but it is abomination to fools to depart from evil.', '&para; 1~08378~ 2~01961~ 4~06149~ 7~05315~: [9 10] 11~08441~ 13~03684~ 15~05493~ 17~07451~.'),
  (4720, 4, 31, 50, 'We have therefore brought an oblation for the LORD, what every man hath gotten, of jewels of gold, chains, and bracelets, rings, earrings, and tablets, to make an atonement for our souls before the LORD.', '3~07126~ 5~07133~ 8~03068~, 11~0376~ 13~04672~, 15~03627~ 17~02091~, 18~0685~, 20~06781~, 21~02885~, 22~05694~, 24~03558~, 28~03722~ 31~05315~ 32~06440~ 34~03068~.'),
  (10642, 13, 9, 19, 'And Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his brethren, of the house of his father, the Korahites, were over the work of the service, keepers of the gates of the tabernacle: and their fathers, being over the host of the LORD, were keepers of the entry.', '1~07967~ 3~01121~ 5~06981~, 7~01121~ 9~043~, 11~01121~ 13~07141~, 16~0251~, 19~01004~ 22~01~, 24~07145~, [25] 28~04399~ 31~05656~, 32~08104~ 35~05592~ 38~0168~: 41~01~, [42] 45~04264~ 48~03068~, [49] 50~08104~ 53~03996~.'),
  (20732, 26, 13, 15, 'Thus will I accomplish my wrath upon the wall, and upon them that have daubed it with untempered mortar, and will say unto you, The wall is no more, neither they that daubed it;', '3~03615~ 5~02534~ 8~07023~, 14~02902~ 17~08602~ [18] 21~0559~ 25~07023~ [26] [28] 32~02902~'),
  (2419, 2, 30, 32, 'Upon man''s flesh shall it not be poured, neither shall ye make any other like it, after the composition of it: it is holy, and it shall be holy unto you.', '1~0120~ 2~01320~ 7~03251~, 11~06213~ [12 13] 18~04971~ [22] 23~06944~, [24] 28~06944~'),
  (16687, 20, 10, 22, 'The blessing of the LORD, it maketh rich, and he addeth no sorrow with it.', '&para; 1~01293~ 4~03068~, 7~06238~, 10~03254~ 12~06089~'),
  (5093, 5, 6, 1, 'Now these are the commandments, the statutes, and the judgments, which the LORD your God commanded to teach you, that ye might do them in the land whither ye go to possess it:', '&para; [2] 4~04687~, 6~02706~, 9~04941~, 12~03068~ 14~0430~ 15~06680~ 17~03925~ 22~06213~ [23] 26~0776~ 29~05674~ 31~03423~'),
  (8265, 10, 10, 18, 'And the Syrians fled before Israel; and David slew the men of seven hundred chariots of the Syrians, and forty thousand horsemen, and smote Shobach the captain of their host, who died there.', '2~0758~ 3~05127~ 4~06440~ 5~03478~; 7~01732~ 8~02026~ [9 11] 12~07651~ 13~03967~ 14~07393~ 17~0758~, 19~0705~ 20~0505~ 21~06571~, 23~05221~ 24~07731~ 26~08269~ 29~06635~, 31~04191~'),
  (26735, 43, 15, 21, 'But all these things will they do unto you for my name''s sake, because they know not him that sent me.', '0~235~ 1~3956~ 3~5023~ 6~4160~ 8~5213~ 9~1223~ 10~3450~ 11~3686~ 12~3450~, 13~3754~ 15~1492~ 16~3756~ 19~3992~ 20~3165~.'),
  (5629, 5, 28, 12, 'The LORD shall open unto thee his good treasure, the heaven to give the rain unto thy land in his season, and to bless all the work of thine hand: and thou shalt lend unto many nations, and thou shalt not borrow.', '1~03068~ 3~06605~ 7~02896~ 8~0214~, 10~08064~ 12~05414~ 14~04306~ 17~0776~ 20~06256~, 23~01288~ 26~04639~ 29~03027~: 33~03867~ 35~07227~ 36~01471~, 41~03867~.'),
  (11039, 13, 24, 16, 'The nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezekel,', '1~06240~ 2~08672~ 3~06611~, 5~06242~ 7~03168~,'),
  (16498, 20, 3, 34, 'Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.', '2~03887~ 4~03887~: 7~05414~ 8~02580~ 11~06035~ 12~06041~.*'),
  (20534, 26, 3, 23, 'Then I arose, and went forth into the plain: and, behold, the glory of the LORD stood there, as the glory which I saw by the river of Chebar: and I fell on my face.', '2~06965~, 5~03318~ 8~01237~: 12~03519~ 15~03068~ 16~05975~ 20~03519~ 23~07200~ 26~05104~ 28~03529~: 31~05307~ 34~06440~.'),
  (4391, 4, 22, 11, 'Behold, there is a people come out of Egypt, which covereth the face of the earth: come now, curse me them; peradventure I shall be able to overcome them, and drive them out.', '[1 2] 4~05971~ 6~03318~ 8~04714~, 10~03680~ 12~05869~ 15~0776~: 16~03212~ 18~06895~ 25~03201~ 27~03898~ 32~01644~.'),
  (1644, 2, 5, 7, 'Ye shall no more give the people straw to make brick, as heretofore: let them go and gather straw for themselves.', '3~03254~ 4~05414~ 6~05971~ 7~08401~ 9~03835~ 10~03843~, 12~08543~ 13~08032~:* 16~03212~ 18~07197~ 19~08401~'),
  (4481, 4, 25, 5, 'And Moses said unto the judges of Israel, Slay ye every one his men that were joined unto Baalpeor.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 5~08199~ 7~03478~, 8~02026~ 10~0376~ 11~0376~ 13~0582~ 16~06775~ 18~01187~.'),
  (2351, 2, 29, 10, 'And thou shalt cause a bullock to be brought before the tabernacle of the congregation: and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands upon the head of the bullock.', '5~06499~ 8~07126~ 9~06440~ 11~0168~ 14~04150~: 16~0175~ 19~01121~ 21~05564~ 23~03027~ 26~07218~ 29~06499~.'),
  (8512, 10, 18, 26, 'And the watchman saw another man running: and the watchman called unto the porter, and said, Behold another man running alone. And the king said, He also bringeth tidings.', '2~06822~ 3~07200~ 4~0312~ 5~0376~ 6~07323~: 9~06822~ 10~07121~ 13~07778~, 15~0559~, [17] 18~0376~ 19~07323~ 23~04428~ 24~0559~, 28~01319~.'),
  (2645, 2, 38, 7, 'And he put the staves into the rings on the sides of the altar, to bear it withal; he made the altar hollow with boards.', '2~0935~ 4~0905~ 7~02885~ 10~06763~ 13~04196~, 15~05375~ 19~06213~ 22~05014~ 24~03871~.'),
  (22260, 28, 11, 11, 'They shall tremble as a bird out of Egypt, and as a dove out of the land of Assyria: and I will place them in their houses, saith the LORD.', '2~02729~ 5~06833~ 8~04714~, 12~03123~ 16~0776~ 18~0804~: 22~03427~ 26~01004~, 27~05002~ 29~03068~.'),
  (970, 1, 33, 5, 'And he lifted up his eyes, and saw the women and the children; and said, Who are those with thee? And he said, The children which God hath graciously given thy servant.', '&para; 3~05375~ 5~05869~, 7~07200~ 9~0802~ 12~03206~; 14~0559~, [16] 17~0428~ 22~0559~, 24~03206~ 26~0430~ 29~02603~ 31~05650~.'),
  (3047, 3, 11, 45, 'For I am the LORD that bringeth you up out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: ye shall therefore be holy, for I am holy.', '[2] 4~03068~ 6~05927~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~, 18~0430~: 23~06918~, [26] 27~06918~.'),
  (22623, 33, 3, 6, 'Therefore night shall be unto you, that ye shall not have a vision; and it shall be dark unto you, that ye shall not divine; and the sun shall go down over the prophets, and the day shall be dark over them.', '1~03915~ [2 3] 12~02377~; 17~02821~ 18~02821~* 25~07080~; 28~08121~ 31~0935~ 34~05030~, 37~03117~ 40~06937~'),
  (23010, 38, 9, 2, 'And Hamath also shall border thereby; Tyrus, and Zidon, though it be very wise.', '1~02574~ 4~01379~ 6~06865~, 8~06721~, 12~03966~ 13~02449~.'),
  (21401, 26, 36, 33, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; In the day that I shall have cleansed you from all your iniquities I will also cause you to dwell in the cities, and the wastes shall be builded.', '1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 7~03117~ 12~02891~ 17~05771~ [22] 24~03427~ 27~05892~, 30~02723~ 33~01129~.'),
  (25796, 42, 20, 3, 'And he answered and said unto them, I will also ask you one thing; and answer me:', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 7~2504~ 8~2065~ 9~2504~ 10~2065~ 11~5209~ 12~1520~ 13~3056~; 14~2532~ 15~2036~ 16~3427~:'),
  (5587, 5, 26, 15, 'Look down from thy holy habitation, from heaven, and bless thy people Israel, and the land which thou hast given us, as thou swarest unto our fathers, a land that floweth with milk and honey.', '1~08259~ 4~06944~ 5~04583~, 7~08064~, 9~01288~ 11~05971~ 12~03478~, 15~0127~ 19~05414~ 23~07650~ 26~01~, 28~0776~ 30~02100~ 32~02461~ 34~01706~.'),
  (21918, 27, 6, 4, 'Then the presidents and princes sought to find occasion against Daniel concerning the kingdom; but they could find none occasion nor fault; forasmuch as he was faithful, neither was there any error or fault found in him.', '0~0116~ 2~05632~ 4~0324~ 5~01934~ 6~01156~* 8~07912~ 9~05931~ 11~01841~ 12~06655~ 14~04437~; 15~03606~ 17~03202~ 18~07912~ 19~03809~ 20~05931~ 21~03809~ 22~07844~; 23~06903~ [26] 27~0540~, 28~03809~ 31~03606~ 32~07960~ 34~07844~ 35~07912~ 37~05922~.'),
  (29695, 53, 3, 1, 'Finally, brethren, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may have free course, and be glorified, even as it is with you:', '&para; 0~3063~, 1~80~, 2~4336~ 3~4012~ 4~2257~, 5~2443~ 7~3056~ 10~2962~ [13] 14~5143~, 15~2532~ 17~1392~, 18~2532~ 19~2531~ [20 21] 22~4314~ 23~5209~:'),
  (29421, 50, 2, 14, 'Do all things without murmurings and disputings:', '&para; 0~4160~ 2~3956~ 3~5565~ 4~1112~ 5~2532~ 6~1261~:'),
  (19963, 24, 40, 13, 'Moreover Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces that were in the fields, came to Gedaliah to Mizpah,', '1~03110~ 3~01121~ 5~07143~, 9~08269~ 12~02428~ [14] 17~07704~, 18~0935~ 20~01436~ 22~04708~,'),
  (53, 1, 2, 22, 'And the rib, which the LORD God had taken from man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man.', '2~06763~, 5~03068~ 6~0430~ 8~03947~ 10~0120~, 11~01129~ 14~0802~, 16~0935~ 20~0120~.'),
  (3545, 3, 26, 16, 'I also will do this unto you; I will even appoint over you terror, consumption, and the burning ague, that shall consume the eyes, and cause sorrow of heart: and ye shall sow your seed in vain, for your enemies shall eat it.', '3~06213~ 10~06485~ 13~0928~, 14~07829~, 18~06920~, 21~03615~ 23~05869~, 26~01727~ 28~05315~: 32~02232~ 34~02233~ 36~07385~, 39~0341~ 41~0398~'),
  (16125, 19, 126, 1, 'A Song of degrees. When the LORD turned again the captivity of Zion, we were like them that dream.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3] 3~04609~ 6~03068~ 8~07725~ 10~07870~ 12~06726~, 18~02492~.'),
  (12297, 15, 10, 36, 'Vaniah, Meremoth, Eliashib,', '0~02057~, 1~04822~, 2~0475~,'),
  (15210, 19, 80, 3, 'Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.', '2~07725~, 4~0430~, 8~06440~ 10~0215~; 15~03467~.'),
  (5673, 5, 28, 56, 'The tender and delicate woman among you, which would not adventure to set the sole of her foot upon the ground for delicateness and tenderness, her eye shall be evil toward the husband of her bosom, and toward her son, and toward her daughter,', '1~07390~ 3~06028~ 10~05254~ 12~03322~ 14~03709~ 17~07272~ 20~0776~ 22~06026~ 24~07391~, 26~05869~ 29~03415~ 32~0376~ 35~02436~, 39~01121~, 43~01323~,'),
  (3126, 3, 14, 10, 'And on the eighth day he shall take two he lambs without blemish, and one ewe lamb of the first year without blemish, and three tenth deals of fine flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and one log of oil.', '&para; 3~08066~ 4~03117~ 7~03947~ 8~08147~ 10~03532~ 12~08549~, 14~0259~ 16~03535~ 19~01323~ 20~08141~ 22~08549~, 24~07969~ 26~06241~ 29~05560~ [30] 33~04503~, 34~01101~ 36~08081~, 38~0259~ 39~03849~ 41~08081~.'),
  (28424, 46, 2, 14, 'But the natural man receiveth not the things of the Spirit of God: for they are foolishness unto him: neither can he know them, because they are spiritually discerned.', '0~1161~ 2~5591~ 3~444~ 4~1209~ 5~3756~ 7~3588~ 10~4151~ 12~2316~: 13~1063~ 15~2076~ 16~3472~ 18~846~: 19~3756~ 20~2532~* 21~1410~ 23~1097~ [24] 25~3754~ 28~4153~ 29~350~.'),
  (7512, 9, 13, 20, 'But all the Israelites went down to the Philistines, to sharpen every man his share, and his coulter, and his ax, and his mattock.', '3~03478~ 5~03381~ 8~06430~, 10~03913~ 12~0376~ 14~04282~, 17~0855~, 20~07134~, 23~04281~.'),
  (19251, 24, 11, 16, 'The LORD called thy name, A green olive tree, fair, and of goodly fruit: with the noise of a great tumult he hath kindled fire upon it, and the branches of it are broken.', '1~03068~ 2~07121~ 4~08034~, 6~07488~ 8~02132~, 9~03303~, [10] 12~08389~ 13~06529~: 16~06963~ 19~01419~ 20~01999~ 23~03341~ 24~0784~ 29~01808~ 33~07489~.'),
  (12271, 15, 10, 10, 'And Ezra the priest stood up, and said unto them, Ye have transgressed, and have taken strange wives, to increase the trespass of Israel.', '1~05830~ 3~03548~ 5~06965~, 7~0559~ 12~04603~, 15~03427~ 16~05237~ 17~0802~, 19~03254~ 21~0819~ 23~03478~.'),
  (5903, 6, 3, 4, 'Yet there shall be a space between you and it, about two thousand cubits by measure: come not near unto it, that ye may know the way by which ye must go: for ye have not passed this way heretofore.', '5~07350~ 12~0505~ 13~0520~ 15~04060~: 18~07126~ 24~03045~ 26~01870~ 31~03212~: 36~05674~ [37] 38~01870~ 39~08032~ 40~08543~.*'),
  (29369, 49, 6, 16, 'Above all, taking the shield of faith, wherewith ye shall be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked.', '0~1909~ 1~3956~, 2~353~ 4~2375~ 6~4102~, 7~3739~ 8~1722~ 11~1410~ 13~4570~ 14~3956~ 16~4448~ 17~956~ 20~4190~.'),
  (3585, 3, 27, 10, 'He shall not alter it, nor change it, a good for a bad, or a bad for a good: and if he shall at all change beast for beast, then it and the exchange thereof shall be holy.', '3~02498~ 6~04171~ 9~02896~ 12~07451~, 15~07451~ 18~02896~: 24~04171~ 25~04171~ 26~0929~ 28~0929~, 33~08545~ 37~06944~.'),
  (7988, 9, 30, 3, 'So David and his men came to the city, and, behold, it was burned with fire; and their wives, and their sons, and their daughters, were taken captives.', '1~01732~ 4~0582~ 5~0935~ 8~05892~, [11 12] 13~08313~ 15~0784~; 18~0802~, 21~01121~, 24~01323~, 27~07617~.'),
  (1797, 2, 10, 15, 'For they covered the face of the whole earth, so that the land was darkened; and they did eat every herb of the land, and all the fruit of the trees which the hail had left: and there remained not any green thing in the trees, or in the herbs of the field, through all the land of Egypt.', '2~03680~ 4~05869~ 8~0776~, 12~0776~ 14~02821~; 18~0398~ 20~06212~ 23~0776~, 27~06529~ 30~06086~ 33~01259~ 35~03498~: 38~03498~ 42~03418~ 45~06086~, 49~06212~ 52~07704~, 56~0776~ 58~04714~.'),
  (2557, 2, 35, 21, 'And they came, every one whose heart stirred him up, and every one whom his spirit made willing, and they brought the LORD''S offering to the work of the tabernacle of the congregation, and for all his service, and for the holy garments.', '2~0935~, 4~0376~ 5~0834~ 6~03820~ 9~05375~, 15~07307~ 17~05068~, [18] 20~0935~ 22~03068~ 23~08641~ 26~04399~ 29~0168~ 32~04150~, 37~05656~, 41~06944~ 42~0899~.'),
  (17872, 23, 10, 13, 'For he saith, By the strength of my hand I have done it, and by my wisdom; for I am prudent: and I have removed the bounds of the people, and have robbed their treasures, and I have put down the inhabitants like a valiant man:', '2~0559~, 5~03581~ 8~03027~ 11~06213~ [12] 16~02451~; 20~0995~: 24~05493~ 26~01367~ 29~05971~, 32~08154~ 34~06259~ 35~06264~,* 40~03381~ 42~03427~ 45~03524~ [46] 46~047~:'),
  (11822, 14, 29, 22, 'So they killed the bullocks, and the priests received the blood, and sprinkled it on the altar: likewise, when they had killed the rams, they sprinkled the blood upon the altar: they killed also the lambs, and they sprinkled the blood upon the altar.', '2~07819~ 4~01241~, 7~03548~ 8~06901~ 10~01818~, 12~02236~ [13] 16~04196~: 21~07819~ 23~0352~, 25~02236~ 27~01818~ 30~04196~: 32~07819~ 35~03532~, 38~02236~ 40~01818~ 43~04196~.'),
  (27172, 44, 7, 40, 'Saying unto Aaron, Make us gods to go before us: for as for this Moses, which brought us out of the land of Egypt, we wot not what is become of him.', '0~2036~ 2~2~, 3~4160~ 4~2254~ 5~2316~ 6~3739~ 8~4313~ 9~2257~: 10~1063~ [11 12] 13~3778~ 14~3475~, 15~3739~ 16~1806~ 17~2248~ 19~1537~ 21~1093~ 23~125~, 25~1492~ 26~3756~ 27~5101~ 29~1096~ 31~846~.'),
  (20265, 24, 51, 44, 'And I will punish Bel in Babylon, and I will bring forth out of his mouth that which he hath swallowed up: and the nations shall not flow together any more unto him: yea, the wall of Babylon shall fall.', '3~06485~ 4~01078~ 6~0894~, 11~03318~ 15~06310~ 21~01105~: 24~01471~ 28~05102~ 35~02346~ 37~0894~ 39~05307~.'),
  (5682, 5, 28, 65, 'And among these nations shalt thou find no ease, neither shall the sole of thy foot have rest: but the LORD shall give thee there a trembling heart, and failing of eyes, and sorrow of mind:', '2~01992~ 3~01471~ 8~07280~, 12~03709~ 15~07272~ 17~04494~: 20~03068~ 22~05414~ 26~07268~ 27~03820~, 29~03631~ 31~05869~, 33~01671~ 35~05315~:'),
  (15140, 19, 78, 18, 'And they tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.', '2~05254~ 3~0410~ 6~03824~ 8~07592~ 9~0400~ 12~05315~.'),
  (23533, 40, 12, 34, 'O generation of vipers, how can ye, being evil, speak good things? for out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh.', '1~1081~ 3~2191~, 4~4459~ 6~1410~, 7~5607~ 8~4190~, 9~2980~ 11~18~? 12~1063~ 14~1537~ 16~4051~ 19~2588~ 21~4750~ 22~2980~.'),
  (16618, 20, 8, 7, 'For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness is an abomination to my lips.', '2~02441~ 4~01897~ 5~0571~; 7~07562~ [8] 10~08441~ 13~08193~.'),
  (11765, 14, 27, 1, 'Jotham was twenty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also was Jerushah, the daughter of Zadok.', '&para; 0~03147~ [1] 2~06242~ 4~02568~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06240~ 16~08337~* 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 21~0517~ 22~08034~ [24] 25~03388~, 27~01323~ 29~06659~.'),
  (29183, 48, 5, 5, 'For we through the Spirit wait for the hope of righteousness by faith.', '0~1063~ 1~2249~ 4~4151~ 6~553~ 8~1680~ 10~1343~ 11~1537~ 12~4102~.'),
  (17965, 23, 14, 28, 'In the year that king Ahaz died was this burden.', '2~08141~ 4~04428~ 5~0271~ 6~04194~ 9~04853~.'),
  (23309, 40, 6, 17, 'But thou, when thou fastest, anoint thine head, and wash thy face;', '0~1161~ 1~4771~, 4~3522~, 5~218~ 6~4675~ 7~2776~, 8~2532~ 9~3538~ 10~4675~ 11~4383~;'),
  (27597, 44, 18, 24, 'And a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent man, and mighty in the scriptures, came to Ephesus.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~5100~ 3~2453~ 4~3686~ 5~625~, 6~1085~ 8~221~, 10~3052~ 11~435~, [12] 13~5607~ 14~1415~* 15~1722~ 17~1124~, 18~2658~ 19~1519~ 20~2181~.'),
  (23146, 39, 3, 16, 'Then they that feared the LORD spake often one to another: and the LORD hearkened, and heard it, and a book of remembrance was written before him for them that feared the LORD, and that thought upon his name.', '3~03373~ 5~03068~ 7~01696~ 8~0376~ 10~07453~: 13~03068~ 14~07181~, 16~08085~ [17] 20~05612~ 22~02146~ 24~03789~ 25~06440~ 30~03373~ 32~03068~, 35~02803~ 38~08034~.'),
  (20216, 24, 50, 41, 'Behold, a people shall come from the north, and a great nation, and many kings shall be raised up from the coasts of the earth.', '2~05971~ 4~0935~ 7~06828~, 10~01419~ 11~01471~, 13~07227~ 14~04428~ 18~05782~ 21~03411~ 24~0776~.'),
  (8950, 11, 7, 8, 'And his house where he dwelt had another court within the porch, which was of the like work. Solomon made also an house for Pharaoh''s daughter, whom he had taken to wife, like unto this porch.', '2~01004~ 5~03427~ [6] 7~0312~ 8~02691~ 9~01004~ 11~0197~, [12] 17~04639~. 18~08010~ 19~06213~ 22~01004~ 24~06547~ 25~01323~, 29~03947~ [30 31] 35~0197~.'),
  (18439, 23, 40, 10, 'Behold, the Lord GOD will come with strong hand, and his arm shall rule for him: behold, his reward is with him, and his work before him.', '2~0136~ 3~03069~ 5~0935~ 7~02389~ [8] 11~02220~ 13~04910~ 18~07939~ [19] 24~06468~ 25~06440~'),
  (23254, 40, 5, 10, 'Blessed are they which are persecuted for righteousness'' sake: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.', '0~3107~ [1] 5~1377~ 6~1752~ 8~1343~: 9~3754~ 10~846~ 11~2076~ 13~932~ 15~3772~.'),
  (3873, 4, 7, 18, 'On the second day Nethaneel the son of Zuar, prince of Issachar, did offer:', '2~08145~ 3~03117~ 4~05417~ 6~01121~ 8~06686~, 9~05387~ 11~03485~, 13~07126~:'),
  (17638, 22, 7, 2, 'Thy navel is like a round goblet, which wanteth not liquor: thy belly is like an heap of wheat set about with lilies.', '1~08326~ [2 3] 5~05469~ 6~0101~, [7] 8~02637~ 10~04197~: 12~0990~ [13 14] 16~06194~ 18~02406~ 20~05473~ 22~07799~.'),
  (14819, 19, 60, 3, 'Thou hast shewed thy people hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment.', '2~07200~ 4~05971~ 6~07186~: 12~08248~ 14~03196~ 16~08653~.'),
  (22506, 30, 9, 2, 'Though they dig into hell, thence shall mine hand take them; though they climb up to heaven, thence will I bring them down:', '2~02864~ 4~07585~, 8~03027~ 9~03947~ 14~05927~ 16~08064~, 22~03381~:'),
  (20621, 26, 8, 8, 'Then said he unto me, Son of man, dig now in the wall: and when I had digged in the wall, behold a door.', '1~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~, 8~02864~ 12~07023~: 17~02864~ 20~07023~, 22~0259~ 23~06607~.'),
  (6431, 6, 21, 43, 'And the LORD gave unto Israel all the land which he sware to give unto their fathers; and they possessed it, and dwelt therein.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~05414~ 5~03478~ 8~0776~ 11~07650~ 13~05414~ 16~01~; 19~03423~ 22~03427~'),
  (190, 1, 8, 6, 'And it came to pass at the end of forty days, that Noah opened the window of the ark which he had made:', '&para; 7~07093~ 9~0705~ 10~03117~, 12~05146~ 13~06605~ 15~02474~ 18~08392~ 22~06213~:'),
  (17674, 23, 1, 11, 'To what purpose is the multitude of your sacrifices unto me? saith the LORD: I am full of the burnt offerings of rams, and the fat of fed beasts; and I delight not in the blood of bullocks, or of lambs, or of he goats.', '1~04100~ [3] 5~07230~ 8~02077~ 11~0559~ 13~03068~: 16~07646~ 20~05930~ 22~0352~, 25~02459~ 28~04806~; 31~02654~ 35~01818~ 37~06499~, 40~03532~, 44~06260~.'),
  (8599, 10, 21, 11, 'And it was told David what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of Saul, had done.', '3~05046~ 4~01732~ 6~07532~ 8~01323~ 10~0345~, 12~06370~ 14~07586~, 16~06213~.'),
  (6659, 7, 5, 29, 'Her wise ladies answered her, yea, she returned answer to herself,', '1~02450~ 2~08282~ 3~06030~ 7~07725~ 8~0561~'),
  (5528, 5, 23, 22, 'But if thou shalt forbear to vow, it shall be no sin in thee.', '4~02308~ 6~05087~, 11~02399~'),
  (2946, 3, 8, 24, 'And he brought Aaron''s sons, and Moses put of the blood upon the tip of their right ear, and upon the thumbs of their right hands, and upon the great toes of their right feet: and Moses sprinkled the blood upon the altar round about.', '2~07126~ 3~0175~ 4~01121~, 6~04872~ 7~05414~ 10~01818~ 13~08571~ 16~03233~ 17~0241~, 21~0931~ 24~03233~ 25~03027~, 30~0931~ 33~03233~ 34~07272~: 36~04872~ 37~02236~ 39~01818~ 42~04196~ 44~05439~.'),
  (19186, 24, 9, 2, 'Oh that I had in the wilderness a lodging place of wayfaring men; that I might leave my people, and go from them! for they be all adulterers, an assembly of treacherous men.', '1~05414~ 6~04057~ 9~04411~ 12~0732~; 16~05800~ 18~05971~, 20~03212~ [25] 27~05003~, 29~06116~ 32~0898~.'),
  (3543, 3, 26, 14, 'But if ye will not hearken unto me, and will not do all these commandments;', '&para; 5~08085~ 11~06213~ 14~04687~;'),
  (12266, 15, 10, 5, 'Then arose Ezra, and made the chief priests, the Levites, and all Israel, to swear that they should do according to this word. And they sware.', '1~06965~ 2~05830~, 6~08269~ 7~03548~, 9~03881~, 12~03478~, 14~07650~ 18~06213~ 22~01697~. 25~07650~.'),
  (1555, 2, 1, 18, 'And the king of Egypt called for the midwives, and said unto them, Why have ye done this thing, and have saved the men children alive?', '2~04428~ 4~04714~ 5~07121~ 8~03205~, 10~0559~ 13~04069~ 16~06213~ 18~01697~, 21~02421~ 24~03206~ 25~02421~?'),
  (14032, 19, 9, 2, 'I will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most High.', '3~08055~ 5~05970~ 11~02167~ 14~08034~, 18~05945~.'),
  (18607, 23, 46, 12, 'Hearken unto me, ye stouthearted, that are far from righteousness:', '0~08085~ 4~03820~ 5~047~,* [7] 9~07350~ 10~06666~:'),
  (30605, 62, 3, 10, 'In this the children of God are manifest, and the children of the devil: whosoever doeth not righteousness is not of God, neither he that loveth not his brother.', '0~1722~ 1~5129~ 3~5043~ 5~2316~ 6~2076~ 7~5318~, 8~2532~ 10~5043~ 13~1228~: 14~3956~ 15~4160~ 16~3361~ 17~1343~ 18~2076~ 19~3756~ 20~1537~ 21~2316~, 22~2532~ 25~25~ 26~3361~ 27~846~ 28~80~.'),
  (25253, 42, 7, 46, 'My head with oil thou didst not anoint: but this woman hath anointed my feet with ointment.', '0~3450~ 1~2776~ 3~1637~ 5~218~ 6~3756~ 7~218~: 8~1161~ 10~3778~ 11~846~* 13~218~ 14~3450~ 15~4228~ 17~3464~.'),
  (18486, 23, 41, 26, 'Who hath declared from the beginning, that we may know? and beforetime, that we may say, He is righteous? yea, there is none that sheweth, yea, there is none that declareth, yea, there is none that heareth your words.', '2~05046~ 5~07218~, 9~03045~? 11~06440~, 15~0559~, [16 17] 18~06662~? [20 21] 24~05046~, [26 27] 30~08085~, [32 33] 36~08085~ 38~0561~.'),
  (15584, 19, 104, 4, 'Who maketh his angels spirits; his ministers a flaming fire:', '1~06213~ 3~04397~ 4~07307~; 6~08334~ 8~03857~ 9~0784~:'),
  (9576, 12, 2, 17, 'And when they urged him till he was ashamed, he said, Send. They sent therefore fifty men; and they sought three days, but found him not.', '3~06484~ 8~0954~, 10~0559~, 11~07971~. 13~07971~ 15~02572~ 16~0376~; 19~01245~ 20~07969~ 21~03117~, 23~04672~'),
  (20555, 26, 4, 17, 'That they may want bread and water, and be astonied one with another, and consume away for their iniquity.', '3~02637~ 4~03899~ 6~04325~, 9~08074~ 10~0376~ 12~0251~, 15~04743~ 18~05771~.'),
  (2187, 2, 24, 5, 'And he sent young men of the children of Israel, which offered burnt offerings, and sacrificed peace offerings of oxen unto the LORD.', '2~07971~ 4~05288~ 7~01121~ 9~03478~, 11~05927~ 13~05930~, 15~02076~ 16~08002~ 17~02077~ 19~06499~ 22~03068~.'),
  (25693, 42, 17, 28, 'Likewise also as it was in the days of Lot; they did eat, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they builded;', '0~3668~ 1~2532~ 2~5613~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 7~2250~ 9~3091~; 12~2068~, 14~4095~, 16~59~, 18~4453~, 20~5452~, 22~3618~;'),
  (18244, 23, 30, 18, 'And therefore will the LORD wait, that he may be gracious unto you, and therefore will he be exalted, that he may have mercy upon you: for the LORD is a God of judgment: blessed are all they that wait for him.', '&para; 4~03068~ 5~02442~, 10~02603~ 18~07311~, 23~07355~ 28~03068~ [29] 31~0430~ 33~04941~: 34~0835~ [35] 39~02442~'),
  (11366, 14, 8, 12, 'Then Solomon offered burnt offerings unto the LORD on the altar of the LORD, which he had built before the porch,', '&para; 1~08010~ 2~05927~ 4~05930~ 7~03068~ 10~04196~ 13~03068~, 17~01129~ 18~06440~ 20~0197~,'),
  (15970, 19, 119, 63, 'I am a companion of all them that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.', '&para; [1] 3~02270~ [6] 8~03372~ 14~08104~ 16~06490~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (19283, 24, 13, 8, 'Then the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (29843, 55, 1, 18, 'The Lord grant unto him that he may find mercy of the Lord in that day: and in how many things he ministered unto me at Ephesus, thou knowest very well.', '1~2962~ 2~1325~ 4~846~ 8~2147~ 9~1656~ 10~3844~ 12~2962~ 13~1722~ 14~1565~ 15~2250~: 16~2532~ 20~3745~ 24~1247~ 25~1722~ 26~2181~, 27~4771~ 28~1097~ 30~957~.'),
  (19650, 24, 29, 6, 'Take ye wives, and beget sons and daughters; and take wives for your sons, and give your daughters to husbands, that they may bear sons and daughters; that ye may be increased there, and not diminished.', '0~03947~ 2~0802~, 4~03205~ 5~01121~ 7~01323~; 9~03947~ 10~0802~ 13~01121~, 15~05414~ 17~01323~ 19~0582~, 23~03205~ 24~01121~ 26~01121~; 31~07235~ 35~04591~.'),
  (15372, 19, 89, 37, 'It shall be established for ever as the moon, and as a faithful witness in heaven. Selah.', '3~03559~ 5~05769~ 8~03394~, [10] 12~0539~ 13~05707~ 15~07834~. 16~05542~.'),
  (15110, 19, 77, 8, 'Is his mercy clean gone for ever? doth his promise fail for evermore?', '2~02617~ 4~0656~ 6~05331~? [8] 9~0562~ 10~01584~ 12~01755~ 13~01755?~*'),
  (586, 1, 23, 11, 'Nay, my lord, hear me: the field give I thee, and the cave that is therein, I give it thee; in the presence of the sons of my people give I it thee: bury thy dead.', '0~03808~, 2~0113~, 4~08085~: 6~07704~ 8~05414~ 12~04631~ [14] 18~05414~ 22~05869~ 25~01121~ 28~05971~ 29~05414~ 33~06912~ 35~04191~.'),
  (24338, 41, 4, 5, 'And some fell on stony ground, where it had not much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of earth:', '0~1161~ 1~243~ 2~4098~ 3~1909~ 5~4075~, 6~3699~ 8~2192~ 9~3756~ 10~4183~ 11~1093~; 12~2532~ 13~2112~ 16~1816~, 17~1223~ 19~2192~ 20~3361~ 21~899~ 23~1093~:'),
  (5621, 5, 28, 4, 'Blessed shall be the fruit of thy body, and the fruit of thy ground, and the fruit of thy cattle, the increase of thy kine, and the flocks of thy sheep.', '0~01288~ [1 2] 4~06529~ 7~0990~, 10~06529~ 13~0127~, 16~06529~ 19~0929~, 21~07698~ 24~0504~, 27~06251~ 30~06629~.'),
  (1965, 2, 16, 13, 'And it came to pass, that at even the quails came up, and covered the camp: and in the morning the dew lay round about the host.', '&para; 7~06153~ 9~07958~ 11~05927~, 13~03680~ 15~04264~: 19~01242~ 21~02919~ 22~07902~ 24~05439~ 26~04264~.'),
  (17538, 21, 12, 6, 'Or ever the silver cord be loosed, or the golden bowl be broken, or the pitcher be broken at the fountain, or the wheel broken at the cistern.', '1~03808~ 3~03701~ 4~02256~ 6~07576~ 9~02091~ 10~01543~ 12~07533~, 15~03537~ 17~07665~ 20~04002~, 23~01534~ 24~07533~ 27~0953~.'),
  (6507, 6, 24, 24, 'And the people said unto Joshua, The LORD our God will we serve, and his voice will we obey.', '2~05971~ 3~0559~ 5~03091~, 7~03068~ 9~0430~ 12~05647~, 15~06963~ 18~08085~.'),
  (28580, 46, 9, 24, 'Know ye not that they which run in a race run all, but one receiveth the prize? So run, that ye may obtain.', '&para; 1~1492~ 2~3756~ 3~3754~ 6~5143~ 7~1722~ 9~4712~ 10~5143~ 11~3303~ 12~3956~,* 13~1161~ 14~1520~ 15~2983~ 17~1017~? 18~3779~ 19~5143~, 20~2443~ 23~2638~.'),
  (3727, 4, 3, 30, 'And the chief of the house of the father of the families of the Kohathites shall be Elizaphan the son of Uzziel.', '2~05387~ 5~01004~ 8~01~ 11~04940~ 14~06956~ [15 16] 17~0469~ 19~01121~ 21~05816~.'),
  (24051, 40, 25, 33, 'And he shall set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.', '0~2532~ 3~2476~ 4~3303~* 6~4263~ 7~1537~ 8~846~ 10~1188~, 11~1161~ 13~2055~ 14~1537~ 16~2176~.'),
  (104, 1, 4, 24, 'If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly Lamech seventy and sevenfold.', '0~03588~ 1~07014~ 4~05358~ 5~07659~, 7~03929~ 8~07657~ 10~07651~.'),
  (6283, 6, 17, 1, 'There was also a lot for the tribe of Manasseh; for he was the firstborn of Joseph; to wit, for Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead: because he was a man of war, therefore he had Gilead and Bashan.', '&para; 4~01486~ 7~04294~ 9~04519~; [12] 14~01060~ 16~03130~; [17 18] 20~04353~ 22~01060~ 24~04519~, 26~01~ 28~01568~: 33~0376~ 35~04421~, 39~01568~ 41~01316~.'),
  (16139, 19, 128, 4, 'Behold, that thus shall the man be blessed that feareth the LORD.', '5~01397~ 7~01288~ 9~03373~ 11~03068~.'),
  (9874, 12, 12, 16, 'The trespass money and sin money was not brought into the house of the LORD: it was the priests''.', '1~0817~ 2~03701~ 4~02403~ 5~03701~ 8~0935~ 11~01004~ 14~03068~: 18~03548~.'),
  (4747, 4, 32, 23, 'But if ye will not do so, behold, ye have sinned against the LORD: and be sure your sin will find you out.', '6~06213~, 10~02398~ 13~03068~: 16~03045~ 18~02403~ 22~04672~.'),
  (18897, 23, 64, 3, 'When thou didst terrible things which we looked not for, thou camest down, the mountains flowed down at thy presence.', '2~06213~ 4~03372~ [5] 7~06960~ 12~03381~, 14~02022~ 16~02151~ 19~06440~.'),
  (290, 1, 11, 21, 'And Reu lived after he begat Serug two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.', '1~07466~ 2~02421~ 3~0310~ 5~03205~ 6~08286~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~ 10~07651~ 11~08141~, 13~03205~ 14~01121~ 16~01323~.'),
  (28806, 46, 16, 14, 'Let all your things be done with charity.', '0~1096~ 1~3956~ 2~5216~ 3~3956~ 5~1096~ 6~1722~ 7~26~.'),
  (5466, 5, 21, 13, 'And she shall put the raiment of her captivity from off her, and shall remain in thine house, and bewail her father and her mother a full month: and after that thou shalt go in unto her, and be her husband, and she shall be thy wife.', '3~05493~ 5~08071~ 8~07628~ 14~03427~ 17~01004~, 19~01058~ 21~01~ 24~0517~ 26~03117~ 27~03391~: 29~0310~ 33~0935~ 40~01166~, 46~0802~.'),
  (6766, 7, 9, 5, 'And he went unto his father''s house at Ophrah, and slew his brethren the sons of Jerubbaal, being threescore and ten persons, upon one stone: notwithstanding yet Jotham the youngest son of Jerubbaal was left; for he hid himself.', '2~0935~ 5~01~ 6~01004~ 8~06084~, 10~02026~ 12~0251~ 14~01121~ 16~03378~, [17] 20~07657~ 21~0376~, 23~0259~ 24~068~: 27~03147~ 29~06996~ 30~01121~ 32~03378~ 34~03498~; 37~02244~'),
  (28809, 46, 16, 17, 'I am glad of the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus: for that which was lacking on your part they have supplied.', '0~1161~ 2~5463~ 3~1909~ 5~3952~ 7~4734~ 8~2532~ 9~5415~ 10~2532~ 11~883~: 13~3754~ 16~5303~ 19~5216~ 20~3778~ 22~378~.'),
  (16664, 20, 9, 17, 'Stolen waters are sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.', '0~01589~ 1~04325~ 3~04985~, 5~03899~ [6] 8~05643~ 10~05276~.'),
  (29544, 51, 3, 11, 'Where there is neither Greek nor Jew, circumcision nor uncircumcision, Barbarian, Scythian, bond nor free: but Christ is all, and in all.', '0~3699~ 2~1762~ 3~3756~ 4~1672~ 5~2532~ 6~2453~, 7~4061~ 8~2532~ 9~203~, 10~915~, 11~4658~, 12~1401~ [13] 14~1658~: 15~235~ 16~5547~ [17] 18~3956~, 19~2532~ 20~1722~ 21~3956~.'),
  (24657, 41, 11, 6, 'And they said unto them even as Jesus had commanded: and they let them go.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~ 6~2531~ 7~2424~ 9~1781~: 10~2532~ 12~863~ 13~846~ 14~863~.'),
  (15879, 19, 118, 1, 'O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: because his mercy endureth for ever.', '&para; 2~03034~ 5~03068~; [7 8] 9~02896~: 12~02617~ [13] 15~05769~.'),
  (458, 1, 18, 30, 'And he said unto him, Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak: Peradventure there shall thirty be found there. And he said, I will not do it, if I find thirty there.', '2~0559~ [3 4] 5~04994~ 9~0136~ 11~02734~, 15~01696~: 19~07970~ 21~04672~ 25~0559~, 29~06213~ [30] 33~04672~ 34~07970~'),
  (8868, 11, 4, 16, 'Baanah the son of Hushai was in Asher and in Aloth:', '0~01195~ 2~01121~ 4~02365~ [5] 7~0836~ 10~01175~:'),
  (19580, 24, 25, 37, 'And the peaceable habitations are cut down because of the fierce anger of the LORD.', '2~07965~ 3~04999~ 6~01826~ 7~06440~ 10~02740~ 11~0639~ 14~03068~.'),
  (28419, 46, 2, 9, 'But as it is written, Eye hath not seen, nor ear heard, neither have entered into the heart of man, the things which God hath prepared for them that love him.', '0~235~ 1~2531~ 4~1125~ 5~3739~,* 6~3788~ 7~1492~ 8~3756~ 9~1492~, 10~3756~ 11~2532~* 12~3775~ 13~191~, 14~3756~ 15~2532~ 16~305~ 17~1909~ 19~2588~ 21~444~, 24~3739~ 25~2316~ 27~2090~ 31~25~ 32~846~.'),
  (17166, 20, 26, 16, 'The sluggard is wiser in his own conceit than seven men that can render a reason.', '&para; 1~06102~ [2] 3~02450~ 7~05869~ 10~07651~ 13~07725~ 15~02940~.'),
  (26467, 43, 9, 12, 'Then said they unto him, Where is he? He said, I know not.', '0~3767~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~4226~ 6~2076~ 7~1565~? 9~3004~, 11~1492~ 12~3756~.'),
  (1462, 1, 48, 6, 'And thy issue, which thou begettest after them, shall be thine, and shall be called after the name of their brethren in their inheritance.', '2~04138~, 5~03205~ 6~0310~ [11] 14~07121~ 15~05921~ 17~08034~ 20~0251~ 23~05159~.'),
  (13068, 18, 9, 8, 'Which alone spreadeth out the heavens, and treadeth upon the waves of the sea.', '3~05186~ 5~08064~, 7~01869~ 10~01116~ 13~03220~.'),
  (8309, 10, 12, 16, 'David therefore besought God for the child; and David fasted, and went in, and lay all night upon the earth.', '0~01732~ 2~01245~ 3~0430~ 6~05288~; 8~01732~ 9~06684~ 10~06685~,* 13~0935~, 15~07901~ 17~03885~ 20~0776~.'),
  (9458, 11, 20, 42, 'And he said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Because thou hast let go out of thy hand a man whom I appointed to utter destruction, therefore thy life shall go for his life, and thy people for his people.', '2~0559~ 6~0559~ 8~03068~, 13~07971~ [16] 17~03027~ 19~0376~ 25~02764~, 28~05315~ 33~05315~, 36~05971~ 39~05971~.'),
  (1334, 1, 44, 5, 'Is not this it in which my lord drinketh, and whereby indeed he divineth? ye have done evil in so doing.', '[0] [3] 7~0113~ 8~08354~, 11~05172~ 13~05172~? 17~07489~ 20~06213~.'),
  (27992, 45, 2, 14, 'For when the Gentiles, which have not the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, these, having not the law, are a law unto themselves:', '0~1063~ 1~3752~ 3~1484~, 4~3588~ 5~2192~ 6~3361~ 8~3551~, 9~4160~ 11~5449~ 13~3588~ 17~3551~, 18~3778~, 19~2192~ 20~3361~ 22~3551~, 23~1526~ 25~3551~ 27~1438~:'),
  (23580, 40, 13, 31, 'Another parable put he forth unto them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is like to a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field:', '0~243~ 1~3850~ 4~3908~ 6~846~, 7~3004~, 9~932~ 11~3772~ 12~2076~ 13~3664~ 16~2848~ 19~4615~, 20~3739~ 22~444~ 23~2983~, 25~4687~ 26~1722~ 27~846~ 28~68~:'),
  (1465, 1, 48, 9, 'And Joseph said unto his father, They are my sons, whom God hath given me in this place. And he said, Bring them, I pray thee, unto me, and I will bless them.', '1~03130~ 2~0559~ 5~01~, [7] 9~01121~, 11~0430~ 13~05414~ [17] 20~0559~, 22~03947~, 31~01288~'),
  (16891, 20, 17, 9, 'He that covereth a transgression seeketh love; but he that repeateth a matter separateth very friends.', '&para; 2~03680~ 4~06588~ 5~01245~ 6~0160~; 10~08138~ 12~01697~ 13~06504~ [14] 15~0441~.'),
  (9229, 11, 14, 3, 'And take with thee ten loaves, and cracknels, and a cruse of honey, and go to him: he shall tell thee what shall become of the child.', '1~03947~ 3~03027~ 4~06235~ 5~03899~, 7~05350~, 10~01228~ 12~01706~, 14~0935~ 19~05046~ 26~05288~.'),
  (30537, 61, 2, 21, 'For it had been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, after they have known it, to turn from the holy commandment delivered unto them.', '0~1063~ 3~2258~ 4~2909~ 6~846~ 7~3361~ 10~1921~ 12~3598~ 14~1343~, 15~2228~, 19~1921~ [20] 22~1994~ 23~1537~ 25~40~ 26~1785~ 27~3860~ 29~846~.'),
  (24043, 40, 25, 25, 'And I was afraid, and went and hid thy talent in the earth: lo, there thou hast that is thine.', '0~2532~ 3~5399~, 5~565~ 7~2928~ 8~4675~ 9~5007~ 10~1722~ 12~1093~: 13~2396~, [14] 16~2192~ [17 18] 19~4674~.'),
  (27940, 44, 28, 25, 'And when they agreed not among themselves, they departed, after that Paul had spoken one word, Well spake the Holy Ghost by Esaias the prophet unto our fathers,', '0~1161~ 4~5607~ 5~800~* 6~4314~ 7~240~, 9~630~, 12~3972~ 14~2036~ 15~1520~ 16~4487~ 17~3754~,* 18~2573~ 19~2980~ 21~40~ 22~4151~ 23~1223~ 24~2268~ 26~4396~ 27~4314~ 28~2257~ 29~3962~,'),
  (27454, 44, 14, 24, 'And after they had passed throughout Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia.', '0~2532~ 5~1330~ 6~4099~, 8~2064~ 9~1519~ 10~3828~.'),
  (469, 1, 19, 8, 'Behold now, I have two daughters which have not known man; let me, I pray you, bring them out unto you, and do ye to them as is good in your eyes: only unto these men do nothing; for therefore came they under the shadow of my roof.', '4~08147~ 5~01323~ 9~03045~ 10~0376~; 18~03318~ 22~06213~ [27] 28~02896~ 31~05869~: 34~0411~ 35~0582~ 36~06213~ 37~01697~ 38~0408~;* 41~0935~ 45~06738~ 48~06982~.'),
  (13546, 18, 29, 5, 'When the Almighty was yet with me, when my children were about me;', '2~07706~ [3] [7] 9~05288~ [10] 11~05439~'),
  (7465, 9, 11, 13, 'And Saul said, There shall not a man be put to death this day: for to day the LORD hath wrought salvation in Israel.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~, 7~0376~ 11~04191~ 13~03117~: 16~03117~ 18~03068~ 20~06213~ 21~08668~ 23~03478~.'),
  (20668, 26, 11, 4, 'Therefore prophesy against them, prophesy, O son of man.', '1~05012~ 4~05012~, 6~01121~ 8~0120~.'),
  (15084, 19, 75, 4, 'I said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn:', '1~0559~ 4~01984~, 7~01984~: 11~07563~, 14~07311~ 16~07161~:'),
  (22132, 28, 2, 18, 'And in that day will I make a covenant for them with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven, and with the creeping things of the ground: and I will break the bow and the sword and the battle out of the earth, and will make them to lie down safely.', '3~03117~ 6~03772~ 8~01285~ 13~02416~ 16~07704~, 20~05775~ 22~08064~, [24] 27~07431~ 30~0127~: 34~07665~ 36~07198~ 39~02719~ 42~04421~ 46~0776~, 53~07901~ 54~0983~.'),
  (7962, 9, 28, 13, 'And the king said unto her, Be not afraid: for what sawest thou? And the woman said unto Saul, I saw gods ascending out of the earth.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 8~03372~: 11~07200~ 15~0802~ 16~0559~ 18~07586~, 20~07200~ 21~0430~ 22~05927~ 26~0776~.'),
  (20110, 24, 48, 21, 'And judgment is come upon the plain country; upon Holon, and upon Jahazah, and upon Mephaath,', '1~04941~ 3~0935~ 6~04334~ 7~0776~; 9~02473~, 12~03096~, 15~04158~,'),
  (15649, 19, 105, 34, 'He spake, and the locusts came, and caterpillars, and that without number,', '1~0559~, 4~0697~ 5~0935~, 7~03218~, 11~04557~,'),
  (21616, 26, 44, 8, 'And ye have not kept the charge of mine holy things: but ye have set keepers of my charge in my sanctuary for yourselves.', '4~08104~ 6~04931~ 10~06944~: 14~07760~ 15~08104~ 18~04931~ 21~04720~'),
  (13639, 18, 32, 2, 'Then was kindled the wrath of Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the kindred of Ram: against Job was his wrath kindled, because he justified himself rather than God.', '2~02734~ 4~0639~ 6~0453~ 8~01121~ 10~01292~ 12~0940~, 15~04940~ 17~07410~: 19~0347~ 22~0639~ 23~02734~, 26~06663~ 27~05315~ 30~0430~.'),
  (18165, 23, 27, 5, 'Or let him take hold of my strength, that he may make peace with me; and he shall make peace with me.', '4~02388~ 7~04581~, [8] 11~06213~ 12~07965~ [15] 18~06213~ 19~07965~'),
  (30182, 58, 10, 33, 'Partly, whilst ye were made a gazingstock both by reproaches and afflictions; and partly, whilst ye became companions of them that were so used.', '0~3303~ 1~5124~,* 7~2301~ 8~5037~ 10~3680~ 11~2532~ 12~2347~; 13~1161~ 14~5124~, 17~1096~ 18~2844~ 22~390~ 23~3779~ 24~390~.'),
  (9240, 11, 14, 14, 'Moreover the LORD shall raise him up a king over Israel, who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam that day: but what? even now.', '2~03068~ 6~06965~ 8~04428~ 10~03478~, 14~03772~ 16~01004~ 18~03379~ 20~03117~:'),
  (22076, 27, 11, 31, 'And arms shall stand on his part, and they shall pollute the sanctuary of strength, and shall take away the daily sacrifice, and they shall place the abomination that maketh desolate.', '1~02220~ 3~05975~ 10~02490~ 12~04720~ 14~04581~, 18~05493~ 20~08548~ [21] 25~05414~ 27~08251~ 30~08074~.'),
  (20330, 25, 1, 11, 'All her people sigh, they seek bread; they have given their pleasant things for meat to relieve the soul: see, O LORD, and consider; for I am become vile.', '2~05971~ 3~0584~, 5~01245~ 6~03899~; 9~05414~ 12~04261~ 13~04262~* 15~0400~ 17~07725~ 19~05315~: 20~07200~, 22~03068~, 24~05027~; 29~02151~.'),
  (5578, 5, 26, 6, 'And the Egyptians evil entreated us, and afflicted us, and laid upon us hard bondage:', '2~04713~ 4~07489~ 7~06031~ 10~05414~ 13~07186~ 14~05656~:'),
  (15928, 19, 119, 21, 'Thou hast rebuked the proud that are cursed, which do err from thy commandments.', '&para; 2~01605~ 4~02086~ [5 6] 7~0779~, 10~07686~ 13~04687~.'),
  (2835, 3, 4, 35, 'And he shall take away all the fat thereof, as the fat of the lamb is taken away from the sacrifice of the peace offerings; and the priest shall burn them upon the altar, according to the offerings made by fire unto the LORD: and the priest shall make an atonement for his sin that he hath committed, and it shall be forgiven him.', '4~05493~ 7~02459~ 11~02459~ 14~03775~ 17~05493~ 20~02077~ 24~08002~; 27~03548~ 29~06999~ 33~04196~, 40~0801~ 43~03068~: 46~03548~ 50~03722~ 53~02403~ 57~02398~, 62~05545~'),
  (13789, 18, 37, 11, 'Also by watering he wearieth the thick cloud: he scattereth his bright cloud:', '2~07377~ 4~02959~ 7~05645~: 9~06327~ 11~0216~ 12~06051~:'),
  (12114, 15, 3, 8, 'Now in the second year of their coming unto the house of God at Jerusalem, in the second month, began Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and the remnant of their brethren the priests and the Levites, and all they that were come out of the captivity unto Jerusalem; and appointed the Levites, from twenty years old and upward, to set forward the work of the house of the LORD.', '&para; 3~08145~ 4~08141~ 7~0935~ 10~01004~ 12~0430~ 14~03389~, 17~08145~ 18~02320~, 19~02490~ 20~02216~ 22~01121~ 24~07597~, 26~03442~ 28~01121~ 30~03136~, 33~07605~ 36~0251~ 38~03548~ 41~03881~, 48~0935~ 51~07628~ 53~03389~; 55~05975~ 57~03881~, 59~06242~ 60~08141~ 61~01121~ 63~04605~, 66~05329~ 68~04399~ 71~01004~ 74~03068~.'),
  (19663, 24, 29, 19, 'Because they have not hearkened to my words, saith the LORD, which I sent unto them by my servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them; but ye would not hear, saith the LORD.', '4~08085~ 7~01697~, 8~05002~ 10~03068~, 13~07971~ 18~05650~ 20~05030~, 23~07925~ 25~07971~ [26] 31~08085~, 32~05002~ 34~03068~.'),
  (26956, 44, 1, 17, 'For he was numbered with us, and had obtained part of this ministry.', '0~3754~ 2~2258~ 3~2674~ 4~4862~ 5~2254~, 6~2532~ 8~2975~ 9~2819~ 11~5026~ 12~1248~.'),
  (23399, 40, 9, 10, 'And it came to pass, as Jesus sat at meat in the house, behold, many publicans and sinners came and sat down with him and his disciples.', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 6~2424~ 9~345~ 10~1722~ 12~3614~ 13~2532~,* 14~2400~, 15~4183~ 16~5057~ 17~2532~ 18~268~ 19~2064~ 22~4873~ 24~846~ 25~2532~ 26~846~ 27~3101~.'),
  (1846, 2, 12, 25, 'And it shall come to pass, when ye be come to the land which the LORD will give you, according as he hath promised, that ye shall keep this service.', '9~0935~ 12~0776~ 15~03068~ 17~05414~ 23~01696~, 27~08104~ 29~05656~.'),
  (20509, 26, 2, 8, 'But thou, son of man, hear what I say unto thee; Be not thou rebellious like that rebellious house: open thy mouth, and eat that I give thee.', '2~01121~ 4~0120~, 5~08085~ 8~01696~ 12~01961~ 14~04805~ 17~04805~ 18~01004~: 19~06475~ 21~06310~, 23~0398~ 26~05414~'),
  (1581, 2, 2, 22, 'And she bare him a son, and he called his name Gershom: for he said, I have been a stranger in a strange land.', '2~03205~ [3] 5~01121~, 8~07121~ 10~08034~ 11~01647~: 14~0559~, 19~01616~ 22~05237~ 23~0776~.'),
  (15985, 19, 119, 78, 'Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in thy precepts.', '&para; 2~02086~ 4~0954~; 8~05791~ 13~08267~: [14] 17~07878~ 20~06490~.'),
  (8629, 10, 22, 19, 'They prevented me in the day of my calamity: but the LORD was my stay.', '1~06923~ 5~03117~ 8~0343~: 11~03068~ 14~04937~.'),
  (4425, 4, 23, 4, 'And God met Balaam: and he said unto him, I have prepared seven altars, and I have offered upon every altar a bullock and a ram.', '1~0430~ 2~07136~ 3~01109~: 6~0559~ 11~06186~ 12~07651~ 13~04196~, 17~05927~ [19] 20~04196~ 22~06499~ 25~0352~.'),
  (30600, 62, 3, 5, 'And ye know that he was manifested to take away our sins; and in him is no sin.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~1565~ 6~5319~ 7~2443~ 9~142~ 10~2257~ 11~266~; 12~2532~ 13~1722~ 14~846~ 15~2076~ 16~3756~ 17~266~.'),
  (14769, 19, 56, 5, 'Every day they wrest my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.', '1~03117~ 3~06087~ 5~01697~: 8~04284~ [9] 13~07451~.'),
  (722, 1, 26, 26, 'Then Abimelech went to him from Gerar, and Ahuzzath one of his friends, and Phichol the chief captain of his army.', '&para; 1~040~ 2~01980~ 6~01642~, 8~0276~ 12~04828~, 14~06369~ 17~08269~ 20~06635~.'),
  (974, 1, 33, 9, 'And Esau said, I have enough, my brother; keep that thou hast unto thyself.', '1~06215~ 2~0559~, 4~03426~ 5~07227~, 7~0251~;'),
  (28623, 46, 11, 7, 'For a man indeed ought not to cover his head, forasmuch as he is the image and glory of God: but the woman is the glory of the man.', '0~1063~ 2~435~ 3~3303~ 4~3784~ 5~3756~ 7~2619~ [8] 9~2776~, 13~5225~ 15~1504~ 16~2532~ 17~1391~ 19~2316~: 20~1161~ 22~1135~ 23~2076~ 25~1391~ 28~435~.'),
  (10568, 13, 7, 25, 'And Rephah was his son, also Resheph, and Telah his son, and Tahan his son,', '1~07506~ [2] 4~01121~, 6~07566~, 8~08520~ 10~01121~, 12~08465~ 14~01121~,'),
  (16399, 19, 149, 5, 'Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.', '2~02623~ 4~05937~ 6~03519~: 10~07442~ 13~04904~.'),
  (28393, 46, 1, 14, 'I thank God that I baptized none of you, but Crispus and Gaius;', '&para; 1~2168~ 2~2316~ 3~3754~ 5~907~ 6~3762~ 8~5216~, 9~1508~ 10~2921~ 11~2532~ 12~1050~;'),
  (21921, 27, 6, 7, 'All the presidents of the kingdom, the governors, and the princes, the counsellors, and the captains, have consulted together to establish a royal statute, and to make a firm decree, that whosoever shall ask a petition of any God or man for thirty days, save of thee, O king, he shall be cast into the den of lions.', '0~03606~ 2~05632~ 5~04437~, 7~05460~, 10~0324~, 12~01907~, 15~06347~, 18~03272~ 20~06966~ 22~04430~ 23~07010~, 28~08631~ 29~0633~, 33~01156~ 35~01159~ 36~04481~ 37~03606~ 38~0426~ 40~0606~ 41~05705~ 42~08533~ 43~03118~, 44~03861~ 46~04481~, 48~04430~, 52~07412~ 55~01358~ 57~0744~.'),
  (23464, 40, 10, 37, 'He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me: and he that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.', '2~5368~ 3~3962~ 4~2228~ 5~3384~ 7~5228~ 8~1691~ 9~2076~ 10~3756~ 11~514~ 13~3450~: 14~2532~ 17~5368~ 18~5207~ 19~2228~ 20~2364~ 22~5228~ 23~1691~ 24~2076~ 25~3756~ 26~514~ 28~3450~.'),
  (14996, 19, 71, 11, 'Saying, God hath forsaken him: persecute and take him; for there is none to deliver him.', '0~0559~, 1~0430~ 3~05800~ 5~07291~ 7~08610~ [10 11] 14~05337~ [15]'),
  (9861, 12, 12, 3, 'But the high places were not taken away: the people still sacrificed and burnt incense in the high places.', '3~01116~ 7~05493~: 9~05971~ 11~02076~ 14~06999~ 18~01116~.'),
  (6528, 7, 1, 12, 'And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjathsepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.', '1~03612~ 2~0559~, 5~05221~ 6~07158~, 8~03920~ 14~05414~ 15~05915~ 17~01323~ 19~0802~.'),
  (15105, 19, 77, 3, 'I remembered God, and was troubled: I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed. Selah.', '1~02142~ 2~0430~, 5~01993~: 7~07878~, 10~07307~ 12~05848~. 13~05542~.'),
  (581, 1, 23, 6, 'Hear us, my lord: thou art a mighty prince among us: in the choice of our sepulchres bury thy dead; none of us shall withhold from thee his sepulchre, but that thou mayest bury thy dead.', '1~08085~, 3~0113~: [5] 7~0430~ 8~05387~ 10~08432~: 13~04005~ 16~06913~ 17~06912~ 19~04191~; 20~0376~ 21~03808~ 24~03607~ 28~06913~, 33~06912~ 35~04191~.'),
  (23240, 40, 4, 21, 'And going on from thence, he saw other two brethren, James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, in a ship with Zebedee their father, mending their nets; and he called them.', '0~2532~ 2~4260~ 4~1564~, 6~1492~ 7~243~ 8~1417~ 9~80~, 10~2385~ [11 12] 13~3588~ 14~2199~, 15~2532~ 16~2491~ 17~846~ 18~80~, 19~1722~ 21~4143~ 22~3326~ 23~2199~ 24~846~ 25~3962~, 26~2675~ 27~846~ 28~1350~; 29~2532~ 31~2564~ 32~846~.'),
  (10690, 13, 11, 9, 'So David waxed greater and greater: for the LORD of hosts was with him.', '1~01732~ 2~03212~ 3~01980~ 5~01419~: 8~03068~ 10~06635~ [11]'),
  (3724, 4, 3, 27, 'And of Kohath was the family of the Amramites, and the family of the Izeharites, and the family of the Hebronites, and the family of the Uzzielites: these are the families of the Kohathites.', '2~06955~ [3] 5~04940~ 8~06020~, 11~04940~ 14~03325~, 17~04940~ 20~02276~, 23~04940~ 26~05817~: [28] 30~04940~ 33~06956~.'),
  (27920, 44, 28, 5, 'And he shook off the beast into the fire, and felt no harm.', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 3~660~ 5~2342~ 6~1519~ 8~4442~, 10~3958~ 11~3762~ 12~2556~.'),
  (4624, 4, 29, 10, 'A several tenth deal for one lamb, throughout the seven lambs:', '3~06241~ 5~0259~ 6~03532~, 9~07651~ 10~03532~:'),
  (20380, 25, 3, 17, 'And thou hast removed my soul far off from peace: I forgat prosperity.', '3~02186~ 5~05315~ 7~02186~ 9~07965~: 11~05382~ 12~02896~.');
